WEBVTT

00:00:16.080 --> 00:00:21.260
A preface to the first edition of Jane Eyre being unnecessary, I gave none.

00:00:21.820 --> 00:00:26.600
This second edition demands a few words, both of acknowledgement and miscellaneous remark.

00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:32.780
My thanks are due in three quarters. To the public for the indulgent ear it has inclined

00:00:32.780 --> 00:00:38.680
to a plain tale with few pretensions. To the press for the fair field its honest suffrage

00:00:38.680 --> 00:00:45.580
has opened to an obscure aspirant. To my publishers for the aid their tact, their energy,

00:00:45.700 --> 00:00:51.380
their practical sense, and frank liberality have afforded to an unknown and un-recommended author.

00:00:52.200 --> 00:00:57.540
The press and the public are vague personifications for me and I must thank them in vague terms.

00:00:58.020 --> 00:01:02.140
But my publishers are definite so they are certain generous critics who have encouraged

00:01:02.140 --> 00:01:07.640
me as only large-hearted and high-minded men know how to encourage a struggling stranger.

00:01:08.200 --> 00:01:15.060
To them, i.e. to my publishers and select reviewers, I say cordially, gentlemen, I thank

00:01:15.060 --> 00:01:19.940
you from my heart. Having thus acknowledged what I owe to those who have aided and approved

00:01:19.940 --> 00:01:26.360
me, I turn to another class, a small one so far as I know, but not, therefore, to be overlooked.

00:01:26.860 --> 00:01:32.780
I mean the timorous or carpian few who doubt the tendency of such books as Jane Eyre, in

00:01:32.780 --> 00:01:39.380
whose eyes whatever is unusual is wrong, whose ears detect in each protest against bigotry,

00:01:39.760 --> 00:01:46.460
that parent of crime and insult to piety, that region of God on earth. I would suggest

00:01:46.460 --> 00:01:53.720
to such doubters certain obvious distinctions. I would remind them of simple truths. Conventionality

00:01:53.720 --> 00:02:00.260
is not morality. Self-righteousness is not religion. To attack the first is not to assail

00:02:00.260 --> 00:02:05.660
the last. To pluck the mask from the face of the Pharisee is not to lift an impious

00:02:05.660 --> 00:02:11.740
hand to the crown of thorns. These things and deeds are diametrically opposed. They

00:02:11.740 --> 00:02:18.520
are as distinct as advice from virtue. Men too often confound them. They should not be

00:02:18.520 --> 00:02:24.220
confounded. Appearance should not be mistaken for truth. Narrow human doctrines that only

00:02:24.220 --> 00:02:29.120
tend to elate and magnify a few should not be substituted for the world-redeeming creed

00:02:29.120 --> 00:02:36.200
of Christ. There is, I repeat it, a difference, and it is good, and not a bad action, to mark

00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:41.720
broadly and clearly the line of separation between them. The world may not like to see

00:02:41.720 --> 00:02:47.180
these ideas dissevered, for it has been accustomed to blend them, finding it convenient to make

00:02:47.180 --> 00:02:53.280
external show pass for sterling worth, to let whitewashed walls vouch for clean shrines.

00:02:53.500 --> 00:02:59.080
It may hate him who declares to scrutinize and expose, to raise the gilding and show

00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:05.440
base material under it, to penetrate the sepulcher and reveal carnal relics, but hate as it will,

00:03:05.440 --> 00:03:12.200
it is indebted to him. Ahab did not like Micaiah, because he never prophesied good concerning him,

00:03:12.340 --> 00:03:19.880
but evil. Probably he liked the sufferant son, Cheniah, better, yet Ahab have escaped a bloody

00:03:19.880 --> 00:03:26.340
death had he but stopped his ears to flattery, and opened them to faithful counsel. There is

00:03:26.340 --> 00:03:31.540
a man in our own days whose words are not framed to tickle delicate ears, who, to my thinking,

00:03:31.540 --> 00:03:37.500
comes before the great ones of society, much as the son of Imla came before the throned kings of

00:03:37.500 --> 00:03:43.660
Judah and Israel, and who speaks as deep, with a powerful, a prophet-like, a vital, as mean and

00:03:43.660 --> 00:03:50.320
dauntless and as daring. Is a satirist of vanity fair admired in high places? I cannot tell. But

00:03:50.320 --> 00:03:56.140
I think of some of those amongst whom he hurls the Greek fire of his sarcasm, and over whom he

00:03:56.140 --> 00:04:01.820
flashes the leavened brand of his denunciation, where to take his warnings in time, they or their

00:04:01.820 --> 00:04:09.160
seed might yet escape a fatal rimloth Gilead. Why have I alluded to this man? I have alluded to him,

00:04:09.160 --> 00:04:15.540
reader, because I think I see in him an intellect profounder and more unique than his contemporaries

00:04:15.540 --> 00:04:21.780
have yet recognized, because I regard him as the first social regenerator of the day, as the very

00:04:21.780 --> 00:04:27.680
master of that working core who would restore to rectitude the warped system of things, because I

00:04:27.680 --> 00:04:33.200
think no commentator on his writings has yet found the comparison that suits him, the terms which

00:04:33.200 --> 00:04:39.340
rightly characterize his talent. They say he is like Fielding, they talk of his wit, humor, comic

00:04:39.340 --> 00:04:45.660
powers. He resembles Fielding as an eagle does a vulture. Fielding could stoop on a carrion,

00:04:45.820 --> 00:04:51.760
but Thackerley never does. His wit is bright, his humor is attractive, but both bear the same

00:04:51.760 --> 00:04:56.780
relation to his serious genius that mere lambient sheet lightning playing under the edge of the

00:04:56.780 --> 00:05:03.840
summer cloud does to the electric death-spark hid in its womb. Finally, I have alluded to Mr. Thackerley,

00:05:03.920 --> 00:05:09.340
because to him, if he will accept the tribute of a total stranger, I have dedicated this second

00:05:09.340 --> 00:05:16.160
edition of Jane Eyre, Courier-Belle, Dec. 21, 1847.

00:05:17.440 --> 00:05:23.400
Note to the third edition. I avail myself of this opportunity, which a third edition of Jane Eyre

00:05:23.400 --> 00:05:29.420
affords me, of again addressing a word to the public, to exclaim that my claim to the title of

00:05:29.420 --> 00:05:35.660
novelist rests on this one work alone. If, therefore, the authorship of other works of

00:05:35.660 --> 00:05:41.180
fiction has been attributed to me, an honor is awarded where it is not merited, and consequently

00:05:41.180 --> 00:05:47.040
denied where it is justly due. This explanation will serve to rectify mistakes which have already

00:05:47.040 --> 00:05:54.140
been made and to prevent future errors. Courier-Belle, April 13, 1848.

00:06:18.220 --> 00:06:19.420
CHAPTER 1.

00:06:20.580 --> 00:06:23.360
There was no possibility of taking a walk that day.

00:06:23.360 --> 00:06:41.640
We had been wandering, indeed, in the leafless shrubbery an hour in the morning, but since dinner, Mrs. Reed, when there was no company dined early, the cold winter wind had brought with it clouds so somber and a rain so penetrating that further out-of-door exercise was now out of the question.

00:06:42.060 --> 00:06:47.540
I was glad of it. I never liked long walks, especially on chilly afternoons.

00:06:47.540 --> 00:07:01.900
Dreadful to me was the coming home in the raw twilight, with nipped fingers and toes and a heart saddened by the chitings of Bessie the nurse, and humbled by the consciousness of my physical infirmity to Eliza, John, and Georgina Reed.

00:07:02.680 --> 00:07:17.380
The said Eliza, John, and Georgina were now clustered round their mamma in the drawing-room. She lay reclined on a sofa by the fireside, and with her darlings about her, for the time neither quarreling nor crying, looked perfectly happy.

00:07:17.380 --> 00:07:46.980
Me, she had dispensed from joining the group, saying, she regretted to be under the necessity of keeping me at a distance, but that until she heard from Bessie, and could discover by her own observation, that I was endeavouring in good earnest to acquire a more sociable and childlike disposition, a more attractive and sprightly manner, something lighter, franker, more natural as it were, she must exclude me from the privileges intended for happy, contented little children.

00:07:47.380 --> 00:07:51.380
What does Bessie say I have done? I asked.

00:07:52.380 --> 00:08:06.840
Jane, I don't like cavalers or questioners. Besides, there is something truly forbidding in a child taking up her elders in that manner. Be seated somewhere, and until you can speak pleasantly, remain silent.

00:08:07.680 --> 00:08:31.020
A breakfast-room adjoined the drawing-room. I slipped in there. It contained a book-case. I soon possessed myself of a volume, taking care that should be one stored with pictures. I mounted into the window-seat, gathering up my feet, I sat cross-legged, like a Turk, and, having drawn the red-morning curtain nearly close, I was shrined in double retirement.

00:08:31.980 --> 00:08:49.400
Folds of scarlet drapery shed in my view to the right hand. To the left were the clear panes of glass, protecting, but not separating, from the dreary November day. At intervals, while turning over the leaves of my book, I studied the aspect of that winter afternoon.

00:08:50.040 --> 00:09:02.440
Afar, it offered a pale blank of mist and cloud. Near, a scene of wet lawn and storm-beat shrub, with ceaseless rain, sweeping away wildly before a long lamentable blast.

00:09:03.110 --> 00:09:19.200
I returned to my book, Bequick's History of Birds. The letter-press thereof I cared little for, speaking generally, and yet there were certain introductory pages that, child as I was, could not pass quite as blank.

00:09:19.200 --> 00:09:44.960
There were those which, treat of the haunts of sea-fowl, of solitary rocks and promontories, by them only inhabited, of the coast of Norway, studded with isles from its southern extremity, the Lindnes or Neys, to the North Cape, where the northern ocean, in vast whirls, boils around the naked, melancholy isles of farless Thurl, and the Atlantic surge, pours in among the stormy Hebrides.

00:09:49.200 --> 00:09:59.020
I studied the great shores of Lapland, Siberia, Spritzbergen, Novozembla, Iceland, Greenland, with the vast sweep of the Arctic zone and those forlorn regions of dreary space.

00:09:59.780 --> 00:10:12.100
That reservoir of frost and snow, where firm fields of ice, the accumulation of centuries of winter, glazed in alpine heights above, surround the pole and concenter the multiple rigors of extreme cold.

00:10:12.620 --> 00:10:23.000
Of these death-like realms, I formed an idea of my own, shadowy like all the half-comprehended notions that float dim through the children's brains, but strangely impressive.

00:10:23.960 --> 00:10:42.180
The words in these introductory pages connected themselves with succeeding vignettes and gave significance to the rock standing up alone in the sea of billow and spray, to the broken boat stranded on the desolate coast, to the cold and ghastly moon casting through bars of clouds at a wreck just sinking.

00:10:42.740 --> 00:10:57.480
I cannot tell what sentiment haunted the quite solitary churchyard, with its inscribed headstone, its gates, its two trees, its low horizon girdled by a broken wall, and its newly risen crescent attesting to the hour of evening-tude.

00:10:58.260 --> 00:11:09.000
The two ships becalmed on a torpid sea I believed to be marine phantoms. The fiend pining down the thief's back behind him I passed over quickly. It was an object of terror.

00:11:09.560 --> 00:11:16.220
So was the black-horned thing seated aloof on a rock, surveying the distant crowds of surrounding gallows.

00:11:17.120 --> 00:11:38.600
Each picture told a story, mysterious often to my underdeveloped understanding and imperfect feelings, yet ever profoundly interesting, as interesting as the tales Bessie sometimes narrated on winter evenings, when she chanced to be in a good humor, and when having brought her ironing table to the nursery hearth, she allowed us to sit about it.

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:56.440
And while she got up, Mrs. Reed's lace frills, and crimped her nightcap borders, fed our eager attentions with passages of love and adventure, taken from old fairy tales and other ballads, or, as at a later period I discovered, from the pages of Pamela and Henry, Earl of Moreland.

00:11:56.920 --> 00:12:07.160
With Bewick on my knee, I was then happy, happy at least in my way. I feared nothing but interruption, and that came too soon. The breakfast-room door was opened.

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:14.900
"'Bah! Madame Mope!' cried the voice of John Reed. Then he paused. He found the room apparently empty.

00:12:15.400 --> 00:12:22.260
"'Where the dickens is she?' he continued. "'Lizzie! Georgie!' calling to his sisters.

00:12:22.700 --> 00:12:27.740
"'Jone is not here. Tell Mama she has run out into the rain, bad animal.'

00:12:28.540 --> 00:12:45.240
"'It is well I drew the curtain,' thought I, and I wished fervently he might not discover my hiding place. Nor would John Reed have found it out himself. He was not quick, either of vision or conception, but Eliza just put her head in at the door and said it once.

00:12:45.500 --> 00:12:48.640
"'She's at the window seat, to be sure, Jack.'

00:12:48.930 --> 00:12:54.820
"'And out I came immediately, for I trembled at the idea of being dragged forth by the said Jack.

00:12:55.640 --> 00:12:58.880
"'What do you want?' I asked, with awkward diffidence.

00:12:59.420 --> 00:13:04.080
"'Say, what do you want, Master Reed?' was the answer.

00:13:04.260 --> 00:13:13.420
"'I want you to come here,' and seated himself in an armchair. He intimated by a gesture that I was to approach and stand before him.

00:13:14.100 --> 00:13:19.900
"'John Reed was a schoolboy of fourteen years old. Four years older than I, for I was but ten.

00:13:20.680 --> 00:13:28.440
"'Large and stout for his age with a dingy and unwholesome skin, thick liniments in a spacious visage, heavy limbs and large extremities.

00:13:28.660 --> 00:13:35.240
"'He gorged himself habitually at table, which made him bilious and gave him a dim, bleared eye and flabby cheeks.

00:13:35.680 --> 00:13:41.620
"'He ought now to have been at school, but his Mama had taken him home for a month or two on account of his delicate health.

00:13:42.180 --> 00:13:48.380
"'Mr. Miles, the Master, affirmed that he would do very well if he had fewer cakes and sweetmeats sent to him from home.

00:13:48.740 --> 00:14:00.900
"'But the Mother's heart turned from that opinion so harsh, and inclined rather to more the refined idea that John's sallowness was owing to over-application, and perhaps to pining after home.

00:14:01.600 --> 00:14:06.600
"'John had not much affection for his mother and sisters, and an antipathy to me.

00:14:06.620 --> 00:14:12.340
"'He bullied and punished me, not two or three times in a week, but once or twice a day.

00:14:12.540 --> 00:14:20.180
"'But continually every nerve I had feared him, and every morsel of flesh in my bones shrank when he came near.

00:14:20.740 --> 00:14:29.780
"'There were moments when I was bewildered by the terror he inspired, because I had no appeal whatever against either his menaces or his inflictions.

00:14:30.200 --> 00:14:37.940
"'The servants did not like to offend their young Master by taking my part against him, and Mrs. Reed was blind and deaf on the subject.

00:14:38.140 --> 00:14:46.940
"'She never saw him strike or heard him abuse me, though he did both now and then in her very presence, more frequently, however, behind her back.

00:14:47.760 --> 00:14:50.820
"'Habitually obedient to John, I came to his chair.

00:14:51.300 --> 00:14:57.000
"'He spent some three minutes in thrusting out his tongue at me as far as he could without damaging the roots.

00:14:57.520 --> 00:15:05.660
"'I knew he would soon strike, and while I dreaded the blow I mused on the disgusting and ugly appearance of him who would presently deal it.

00:15:06.240 --> 00:15:14.260
"'I wondered if he read that notion in my face, for, all at once without speaking, he struck, suddenly and strongly.

00:15:14.780 --> 00:15:20.020
"'I tottered, and on regaining my equilibrium, retired back a step or two from his chair.

00:15:20.840 --> 00:15:25.920
"'That was for your impudence in answering Mama a while since,' he said,

00:15:26.160 --> 00:15:33.900
"'and for your sneaking way of getting behind curtains, and for the look you had in your eyes two minutes since, you rat!'

00:15:35.260 --> 00:15:39.780
"'Accustomed to John Reed's abuse, I never had any idea of replying to it.

00:15:40.130 --> 00:15:44.140
"'My care was how to endure the blow, which was certainly follow the insult.

00:15:44.660 --> 00:15:48.220
"'What were you doing behind the curtain?' he asked.

00:15:48.900 --> 00:15:51.530
"'I was reading. Show the book.'

00:15:51.960 --> 00:15:54.550
"'I returned to the window and fetched it thence.

00:15:55.060 --> 00:16:00.380
"'You have no business to take our books. You are a dependent, Mama says.

00:16:00.520 --> 00:16:03.520
"'You have no money. Your father left you none.

00:16:03.820 --> 00:16:10.040
"'You ought to beg not to live here with gentlemen's children like us and eat the same meals we do,

00:16:10.040 --> 00:16:13.000
"'and wear the same clothes at our Mama's expense.

00:16:13.320 --> 00:16:18.060
"'Now I'll teach you to rummage my bookshelves, for they are mine.

00:16:18.220 --> 00:16:21.980
"'All the house belongs to me or will do in a few years.

00:16:22.160 --> 00:16:26.080
"'Go and stand by the door out of the way of the mirrors in the windows.'

00:16:27.120 --> 00:16:31.220
"'I did so, not at first aware of what was his intention.

00:16:31.520 --> 00:16:36.620
"'But when I saw him lift and poise the book and stand to enact to hurl it,

00:16:36.700 --> 00:16:40.400
"'I instinctively started aside with a cry of alarm.

00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:44.880
"'Not soon enough, however, the volume was flung, it hit me, and I fell,

00:16:45.220 --> 00:16:47.940
"'striking my head against the door and cutting it.

00:16:48.020 --> 00:16:50.140
"'The cut bled, the pain was sharp.

00:16:50.280 --> 00:16:53.980
"'My terror had passed its climax and other feelings succeeded.

00:16:54.660 --> 00:16:57.280
"'Wicked, cruel boy,' I said.

00:16:57.280 --> 00:16:58.860
"'You are like a murderer.

00:16:59.060 --> 00:17:00.680
"'You are like a slave driver.

00:17:00.740 --> 00:17:02.540
"'You are like the Roman emperors.'

00:17:03.400 --> 00:17:09.000
"'I had read Goldsmith's history of Rome and had formed my opinion of Nero and Calgula and etc.

00:17:09.460 --> 00:17:14.300
"'Also I had drawn parallels in silence which I never thought thus to have declared aloud.

00:17:14.880 --> 00:17:17.240
"'What? What?' he cried.

00:17:17.520 --> 00:17:19.320
"'Did she say that to me?

00:17:19.380 --> 00:17:21.780
"'Do you hear her, Eliza and Georgina?

00:17:22.160 --> 00:17:24.600
"'Won't I tell mama? But first!'

00:17:25.240 --> 00:17:27.220
"'He ran headlong at me.

00:17:27.420 --> 00:17:30.160
"'I felt him grasp my hair and my shoulder.

00:17:30.440 --> 00:17:32.600
"'He had closed with a desperate thing.

00:17:32.800 --> 00:17:35.240
"'I really saw him a tyrant, a murderer.

00:17:35.440 --> 00:17:39.220
"'I felt a drop or two of blood from my head trickle down my neck

00:17:39.220 --> 00:17:42.000
"'and was sensible of somewhat pungent suffering.

00:17:42.260 --> 00:17:45.740
"'These sensations for the time predominated over fear,

00:17:45.880 --> 00:17:48.280
"'and I received him in a frantic sort.

00:17:48.840 --> 00:17:51.520
"'I don't very well know what I did with my hands,

00:17:51.580 --> 00:17:55.960
"'but he called me, "'Rot! Rot!' and bellowed out loud.

00:17:56.400 --> 00:18:01.640
"'Aid was near him. Eliza and Georgina had run for Mrs. Reed, who had gone upstairs.

00:18:02.180 --> 00:18:06.140
"'She now came upon the scene, followed by Bessie and her maid Abbott.

00:18:06.460 --> 00:18:08.600
"'We were parted and I heard the words,

00:18:08.940 --> 00:18:13.280
"'Dear, dear, what a flurry to fly at Master John!'

00:18:13.280 --> 00:18:17.280
"'Did anyone ever see such a picture of passion?'

00:18:17.280 --> 00:18:19.280
"'Then Mrs. Reed subjoined,

00:18:19.500 --> 00:18:22.840
"'Take her away to the Red Room and lock her in there.'

00:18:23.720 --> 00:18:27.840
"'Four hands were immediately laid upon me and I was born upstairs.'

00:18:47.320 --> 00:18:52.460
CHAPTER II I resisted all the way, a new thing for me,

00:18:52.580 --> 00:18:56.980
and a circumstance which greatly strengthened the bad opinion Bessie and Miss Abbott were

00:18:56.980 --> 00:19:04.320
entertain of me. The fact is, I was a trifle beside myself, or rather out of myself, as

00:19:04.320 --> 00:19:09.640
the French would say. I was conscious that a moment's mutiny had already rendered me liable

00:19:09.640 --> 00:19:16.060
to strange penalties, and like any other rebel slave, I felt resolved in my desperation to go

00:19:16.060 --> 00:19:23.500
all lengths. Hold her at arms, Miss Abbott, she's like a mad cat. For shame, for shame,

00:19:23.500 --> 00:19:30.560
cried the lady's maid. What shocking conduct, Miss Eyre, to strike a young gentleman, your

00:19:30.560 --> 00:19:40.280
benefactress's son, your young master. Master, how is he my master? Am I a servant? No, you

00:19:40.280 --> 00:19:45.920
are less than a servant, for you do nothing for your keep. There, sit down and think over

00:19:45.920 --> 00:19:51.720
your wickedness. They had got me by this time into the apartment indicated by Mrs. Reed,

00:19:51.720 --> 00:19:58.340
and had thrust me upon a stool. My first impulse was to rise from it like a spring. Their two

00:19:58.340 --> 00:20:00.400
pair of hands arrested me instantly.

00:20:01.140 --> 00:20:06.920
"'If you don't sit still, you must be tied down,' said Bessie. Miss Abbott lend me your

00:20:06.920 --> 00:20:12.360
garters, for she will break mine directly.' Miss Abbott turned to divest a stout leg of

00:20:12.360 --> 00:20:18.200
the necessary ligature. This preparation for bonds, and the additional ignominy it inferred,

00:20:18.200 --> 00:20:24.620
took a little of the excitement out of me. Don't take them off, I cried. I will not stir.

00:20:25.220 --> 00:20:29.120
In guarantee whereof, I attached myself to the seat by my hands.

00:20:29.760 --> 00:20:35.500
"'Mind you don't,' said Bessie. When she had ascertained that I was really subsiding, she

00:20:35.500 --> 00:20:41.160
loosened her hold of me. Then she and Miss Abbott stood with folded arms, looking darkly

00:20:41.160 --> 00:20:48.120
and doubtfully on my face, as incredulous of my sanity. She never did so before. At

00:20:48.120 --> 00:20:54.380
last, said Bessie, turning to Abigail, "'But it was always in her,' was the reply. I've

00:20:54.380 --> 00:21:00.620
told Mrs. often my opinion about the child, and Mrs. agrees with me. She's an underhanded

00:21:00.620 --> 00:21:07.080
little thing. I never saw a girl of her age so much cover.' Bessie answered not, but air

00:21:07.080 --> 00:21:12.720
long addressing me, she said, "'You ought to be aware, Miss, that you are under obligation

00:21:12.720 --> 00:21:17.500
to Mrs. Reed. She keeps you. If she were to turn you out, you would have to go to the

00:21:17.500 --> 00:21:23.940
poorhouse.' I had nothing to say to these words. They were not new to me. My very first

00:21:23.940 --> 00:21:29.580
recollections of existence included hints of the same kind. This reproach of my dependence

00:21:29.580 --> 00:21:35.940
had become a vague sing-song in my ear, very painful and crushing, but only half intelligible.

00:21:36.520 --> 00:21:42.960
Miss Abbott joined in, "'And you ought to not think yourself an equal with the Mrs.

00:21:42.960 --> 00:21:48.320
Reed and Master Reed, because Mrs. kindly allows you to be brought up with them. They

00:21:48.320 --> 00:21:52.980
will have a great deal of money and you will have none. It is your place to be humble and

00:21:52.980 --> 00:21:59.120
to try to make yourself agreeable to them.' "'What we tell you is for your own good,'

00:21:59.120 --> 00:22:05.280
added Bessie in no harsh voice. "'You should try to be useful and pleasant. Then perhaps

00:22:05.280 --> 00:22:10.600
you would have a home here. But if you become passionate and rude, Mrs. will send you away,

00:22:10.600 --> 00:22:17.320
and I'm sure.' "'Besides,' said Miss Abbott, "'God will punish her. He might strike her

00:22:17.320 --> 00:22:21.920
dead in the midst of her tantrums, and then where would she go? Come, Bessie, we will

00:22:21.920 --> 00:22:27.940
leave her. I wouldn't have her heart for anything. Say your prayers, Miss Eyre, when you are

00:22:27.940 --> 00:22:33.020
by yourself, for if you don't repent, something bad might be permitted to come down the chimney

00:22:33.020 --> 00:22:38.080
and fetch you away.' They went, shutting the door and locking it behind them.

00:22:38.740 --> 00:22:45.260
The Red Room was a square chamber, very seldom slept in. I might say never indeed, unless

00:22:45.260 --> 00:22:50.860
when a chance influx of visitors at Gateshead Hall rendered it necessary to turn to account

00:22:50.860 --> 00:22:56.500
all the accommodation it contained. Yet it was one of the largest and stateliest chambers

00:22:56.500 --> 00:23:02.340
in the mansion. A bed supported on massive pillars of mahogany, hung with curtains of

00:23:02.340 --> 00:23:08.180
deep red damask, stood out like a tabernacle in the center. The two large windows with

00:23:08.180 --> 00:23:14.480
their blinds always drawn down were half shrouded in festoons and falls of similar drapery.

00:23:14.820 --> 00:23:19.640
The carpet was red. The table at the foot of the bed was covered with a crimson cloth.

00:23:20.180 --> 00:23:26.060
The walls were a soft fawn color with a blush of pink in it. The wardrobe, the toilet table,

00:23:26.060 --> 00:23:32.440
the chairs were of darkly polished old mahogany. Out of these surrounding shades rose high

00:23:32.440 --> 00:23:38.100
and glared white the piled up mattresses and pillows of the bed, spread with a snowy white

00:23:38.100 --> 00:23:43.600
Marcel's counterpane. Scarcely less prominent was an ample cushioned easy chair near the

00:23:43.600 --> 00:23:49.100
head of the bed, also white with a footstool before it, and looking, as I thought, like

00:23:49.100 --> 00:23:55.540
a pale throne. This room was chill because it seldom had a fire. It was silent because

00:23:55.540 --> 00:24:00.340
it was remote from the nursery and kitchen. Solemn because it was known to be so seldom

00:24:00.340 --> 00:24:05.920
entered. The housemaid alone came here on Saturdays to wipe from the mirrors and the

00:24:05.920 --> 00:24:12.720
furniture a week's quiet dust, and Mrs. Reed herself at far intervals visited it to review

00:24:12.720 --> 00:24:19.280
the contents of a certain secret drawer in the wardrobe, where were stored divers' parchments,

00:24:19.600 --> 00:24:24.720
her jeweled casket, and a miniature of her deceased husband, and in those last words

00:24:24.720 --> 00:24:30.600
lies the secret of the red room, the spell which kept it so lonely in spite of its grandeur.

00:24:31.320 --> 00:24:37.700
Mr. Reed had been dead nine years. It was in this chamber he breathed his last. Here

00:24:37.700 --> 00:24:43.300
he lay in state, hence his coffin was borne by the undertaker's men, and since that day,

00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:49.840
in a sense of dreary consecration, had guarded it from frequent intrusion. My seat, to which

00:24:49.840 --> 00:24:55.080
and the bitter Miss Abbott had left me riveted, was a low ottoman near the marble chimney

00:24:55.080 --> 00:25:01.240
piece. The bed rose before me. To my right hand there was a high dark wardrobe, with

00:25:01.240 --> 00:25:07.060
subdued broken reflections varying the gloss of its panels. To my left were the muffled

00:25:07.060 --> 00:25:12.220
windows. A great looking glass between them repeated the vacant majesty of the bed and

00:25:12.220 --> 00:25:17.920
room. I was not quite sure whether they had locked the door, and when I dared move I got

00:25:17.920 --> 00:25:25.420
up and went to see. Alas, yes, no jail was ever more secure. Returning, I had to cross

00:25:25.420 --> 00:25:31.300
before the looking glass. My fascinated glance involuntarily explored the depth it revealed.

00:25:32.060 --> 00:25:38.080
All looked colder and darker in that visionary hollow than in reality, and the strange little

00:25:38.080 --> 00:25:43.900
figure there gazing at me, with a white face and arms speckled the gloom, and the glittering

00:25:43.900 --> 00:25:49.780
eye of fear moving where all else was still, had the effect of a real spirit. I thought

00:25:49.780 --> 00:25:56.260
it like one of those tiny phantoms, half fairy, half imp, in Bessie's evening stories represented

00:25:56.260 --> 00:26:01.840
as coming out of a lone ferny dells in the moors, and appearing before the eyes of belated

00:26:01.840 --> 00:26:04.460
travellers. I returned to my stool.

00:26:05.540 --> 00:26:10.320
Superstition was with me at that moment, but it was not yet her hour for complete victory.

00:26:10.750 --> 00:26:16.400
My blood was still warm. The mood of the revolted slave was still bracing me with its bitter

00:26:16.400 --> 00:26:22.500
vigour. I had to stem a rapid rush of retrospective thought before I quailed the dismal present.

00:26:23.540 --> 00:26:29.300
All John Reed's violent tyrannies and all his sister's proud indifference, all his mother's

00:26:29.300 --> 00:26:35.180
aversion, all the servant's partiality, turned up in my disturbed mind like a dark deposit

00:26:35.180 --> 00:26:42.540
in a turpid well. Why was I always suffering, always brow-beaten, always accused, forever

00:26:42.540 --> 00:26:48.700
condemned? Why could I never please? Why is it useless to try and win anyone's favour?

00:26:49.400 --> 00:26:55.600
Eliza, who was headstrong and selfish, was respected. Georgiana, who had a spoiled temper,

00:26:55.880 --> 00:27:03.320
a very acrid spite, a capitious and insolent carriage, was universally indulged. Her beauty,

00:27:03.320 --> 00:27:08.780
her pink cheeks, and golden curls seemed to give delight to all who looked at her and

00:27:08.780 --> 00:27:14.940
to purchase indemnity for every fault. John, no one thwarted, much less punished. Though

00:27:14.940 --> 00:27:19.940
he twisted the necks of pigeons, killed the little pea-chicks, set the dogs at the sheep,

00:27:20.420 --> 00:27:24.680
stripped the hothouse vines of their fruit, and broke the buds of the choicest plants

00:27:24.680 --> 00:27:31.880
in the conservatory. He called his mother old girl, too. Sometimes reviled her for her

00:27:31.880 --> 00:27:38.580
dark skin similar to his own. Bluntly disregarded her wishes, not unfrequently tore and spoiled

00:27:38.580 --> 00:27:45.980
her silk attire, and he was still her own darling. I dared commit no fault. I strove

00:27:45.980 --> 00:27:52.360
to fulfil every duty and was turned naughty and tiresome, sullen and sneaking, from morning

00:27:52.360 --> 00:27:58.100
till noon and from noon to night. My head still ached and bled with the blow in the

00:27:58.100 --> 00:28:04.400
fall I had received. No one had reproved John for wantonly striking me, and because I had

00:28:04.400 --> 00:28:10.320
turned against him to avert farther irrational violence, I was loaded with general approbium.

00:28:11.200 --> 00:28:18.240
Unjust, unjust, said my reason, forced by the agonizing stimulus into precocious though

00:28:18.240 --> 00:28:25.360
transitory power, and resolve equally wrought up, instigated some strange expedient to achieve

00:28:25.360 --> 00:28:31.120
escape from the insupportable oppression, as running away, or if that could not be affected,

00:28:31.580 --> 00:28:37.080
never eating or drinking more and letting myself die. What a consternation of soul was

00:28:37.080 --> 00:28:43.540
mine that dreary afternoon! How all my brain was in a tumult, and all my heart in insurrection!

00:28:44.260 --> 00:28:49.700
Yet, in what darkness, what dense ignorance, was the mental battle fought? I could not

00:28:49.700 --> 00:28:56.180
answer the ceaseless inward question why. I thus suffered now. At the distance of how

00:28:56.180 --> 00:29:02.160
many years, I see it clearly. I was at discord at Gateshead Hall. I was like nobody there.

00:29:02.540 --> 00:29:08.540
I had nothing in harmony with Mrs. Reed or her children or her chosen vassalage. If they

00:29:08.540 --> 00:29:13.660
did not love me, in fact, as little as I did love them, they were not bound to regard with

00:29:13.660 --> 00:29:18.720
affection a thing that could not sympathize with one amongst them, a heterogeneous thing

00:29:18.720 --> 00:29:25.240
opposed to them in temperament and capacity in propensities, a useless thing, incapable

00:29:25.240 --> 00:29:31.360
of serving their interests or adding to their pleasure, a noxious thing, cherishing the

00:29:31.360 --> 00:29:37.020
germs of indignation at their treatment, of contempt of their judgment. I know that had

00:29:37.020 --> 00:29:42.980
I been a sanguine, brilliant, careless, exacting, handsome, romping child, though equally dependent

00:29:42.980 --> 00:29:48.800
and friendless, Mrs. Reed would have endured my presence much more complacently. Her children

00:29:48.800 --> 00:29:53.720
would have entertained me more of the cordiality of fellow feeling. The servants would have

00:29:53.720 --> 00:29:59.060
been less prone to make me the scapegoat of the nursery. Daylight began to forsake the

00:29:59.060 --> 00:30:04.340
red room. It was past four o'clock, and the beclouded afternoon was tending to a drear

00:30:04.340 --> 00:30:10.580
twilight. I heard the rain still beating continuously on the staircase window, and the wind howling

00:30:10.580 --> 00:30:18.080
in the grove behind the hall. I grew by degrees, cold as stone, and then my courage sank. My

00:30:18.080 --> 00:30:24.240
habitual mood of humiliation, self-doubt, forlorn depression, fell damp on the embers

00:30:24.240 --> 00:30:30.400
of my decaying ear. All said I was wicked, and perhaps I might be so. What thought I

00:30:30.400 --> 00:30:36.380
had been but just conceiving of starving myself to death! That certainly was a crime. And

00:30:36.380 --> 00:30:42.100
Was I fit to die, or was the vault under the chancel of Gateshead Church an inviting-born?

00:30:42.660 --> 00:30:48.180
In such vault I had been told did Mr. Reed lie buried, and led by this thought to recall

00:30:48.180 --> 00:30:53.620
his idea, I dwelt on it with gathering dread. I could not remember him, but I knew that

00:30:53.620 --> 00:30:58.740
he was my own uncle, my mother's brother, that he had taken me, when I was a parentless

00:30:58.740 --> 00:31:03.900
infant, to his house, and that in his last moments he had required a promise of Mrs.

00:31:03.900 --> 00:31:09.740
Reed, that she would rear and maintain me as one of her own children. Mrs. Reed probably

00:31:09.740 --> 00:31:14.800
considered that she had kept this promise, and so she had, I dare say, as well as her

00:31:14.800 --> 00:31:20.660
nature would permit her. But how could she really like an interloper not of her race,

00:31:21.080 --> 00:31:27.500
and unconnected with her, after her husband's death by any tie? It must have been most irksome

00:31:27.500 --> 00:31:33.000
to find herself bound by a hard-rung pledge to stand in the stead of a parent to a strange

00:31:33.000 --> 00:31:39.220
child she could not love, and to see an uncongenial alien permanently intruded on her own family

00:31:39.220 --> 00:31:39.660
group.

00:31:40.660 --> 00:31:47.060
A singular notion dawned upon me. I doubted not, never doubted, that if Mr. Reed had been

00:31:47.060 --> 00:31:53.620
alive he would have treated me kindly. And now I sat looking at the white bed, the overshadowed

00:31:53.620 --> 00:32:00.040
walls occasionally also turning a fascinated eye toward the gleaming mirror. I began to

00:32:00.040 --> 00:32:05.440
recall what I had heard of dead men troubled in their graves, by the violation of their

00:32:05.440 --> 00:32:11.020
last wishes revisited the earth to punish the perjured and avenged the oppressed, and

00:32:11.020 --> 00:32:16.340
I thought Mr. Reed's spirit, harassed by the wrongs of his sister's child, might quit

00:32:16.340 --> 00:32:22.060
its abode, whether in the church vault or in the unknown world of the departed, and rise

00:32:22.060 --> 00:32:28.900
before me in this chamber. I wiped my tears and hushed my sobs, fearful lest any sign

00:32:28.900 --> 00:32:35.060
of violent grief might waken a pre-natural voice to comfort me, or elicit from the gloom

00:32:35.060 --> 00:32:37.940
some hallowed face bending over me with strange pity.

00:32:38.840 --> 00:32:45.060
This idea, consolatory in theory, I felt would be terrible if realized. With all my might

00:32:45.060 --> 00:32:51.200
I endeavored to stifle it. I endeavored to be firm. Shaking my hair from my eyes I lifted

00:32:51.200 --> 00:32:56.060
my head and tried to look boldly around the dark room. At this moment a light gleamed

00:32:56.060 --> 00:33:02.460
on the wall. Was it, I asked myself, a ray from the moon penetrating some aperture in

00:33:02.460 --> 00:33:09.960
the blind? No, moonlight was still in this sturd. While I gazed it glided up to the ceiling

00:33:09.960 --> 00:33:15.800
and quivered over my head. I can now conjecture readily that this streak of light was in all

00:33:15.800 --> 00:33:21.940
likelihood a gleam from a lantern carried by someone across the lawn, but then, prepared

00:33:21.940 --> 00:33:28.600
as my mind was for horror, shaken as my nerves were by agitation, I thought the swift darting

00:33:28.600 --> 00:33:34.340
beam was a herald of some coming vision from another world. Oh, my heart beat thick. My

00:33:34.340 --> 00:33:40.440
head grew hot. A sound filled my ears which I deemed the rushing of wings. Something seemed

00:33:40.440 --> 00:33:47.540
near me. I was oppressed, suffocated. Endurance broke down. I rushed to the door and shook

00:33:48.300 --> 00:33:54.480
desperate effort. Steps came running from the outer passage. The key turned. Bessie and Abbott

00:33:54.480 --> 00:34:01.480
entered. Miss Eyre, are you ill? said Bessie. What a dreadful noise. It quite went through me,

00:34:01.780 --> 00:34:10.200
exclaimed Abbott. Take me out. Let me go to the nursery, was my cry. What for are you hurt? Have

00:34:10.200 --> 00:34:17.520
you seen something? Again demanded Bessie. Oh, I saw a light and I thought a ghost would come. I

00:34:17.520 --> 00:34:23.880
had now got hold of Bessie's hand and she did not snatch it from me. She has screamed on purpose,

00:34:24.200 --> 00:34:30.860
declared Abbott in some disgust. And what a scream! If she had been in great pain, one would have

00:34:30.860 --> 00:34:39.680
excused it. But she only wanted to bring us all here. I know her naughty tricks. What is all this?

00:34:40.100 --> 00:34:47.360
demanded another voice, prematurely. And Mrs. Reed came along the corridor, her cap flying wide,

00:34:47.360 --> 00:34:54.780
her gown rustling stormily. Abbott, Bessie, I believe I gave orders that Jane Eyre should

00:34:54.780 --> 00:35:02.040
be left in the Red Room till I came to her myself. Oh, Miss Jane screamed so loud, ma'am,

00:35:02.260 --> 00:35:10.040
pleaded Bessie. Let her go, was the only answer. Loose Bessie's hand, child. You cannot succeed

00:35:10.040 --> 00:35:16.680
in getting out by these means, be assured. I abhor artifice particularly in children.

00:35:16.680 --> 00:35:23.120
It is my duty to show you that tricks will not answer. You will now stay here an hour longer,

00:35:23.120 --> 00:35:29.300
and it is only on condition of perfect submission and stillness that I shall liberate you then.

00:35:29.800 --> 00:35:36.420
Oh, aunt, have pity. Forgive me, I cannot endure it. Let me be punished some other way. I shall

00:35:36.420 --> 00:35:44.040
be killed if silence. This violence is most repulsive. And so, no doubt, she felt it.

00:35:44.040 --> 00:35:50.260
I was a precocious actress in her eyes. She sincerely looked on me as a compound of virulent

00:35:50.260 --> 00:35:57.060
passions, mean spirit, and dangerous duplicity. Bessie and Abbott, having retreated, Mrs. Reed,

00:35:57.340 --> 00:36:04.060
impatient of my now frantic anguish and wild sobs, abruptly thrust me back and locked me in without

00:36:04.060 --> 00:36:10.720
farther parlay. I heard her sweeping away, and soon after she was gone, I suppose I had a species

00:36:10.720 --> 00:36:13.980
of fit. Unconsciousness closed the scene.

00:36:37.380 --> 00:36:38.420
CHAPTER III.

00:36:39.480 --> 00:36:44.140
The next thing I remember is waking up with a feeling as if I had had a frightful nightmare,

00:36:44.140 --> 00:36:49.320
and seeing before me a terrible red glare crossed with thick black bars.

00:36:50.040 --> 00:36:56.220
I heard voices, too, speaking with a hollow sound, and as if muffled by a rush of wind or water.

00:36:56.800 --> 00:37:03.000
Agitation, uncertainty, and an all-predominating sense of terror confused my faculties.

00:37:03.480 --> 00:37:09.500
Ere long, I became aware that someone was handling me, lifting me up and supporting me in a sitting

00:37:10.240 --> 00:37:14.700
and that more tenderly than I had ever been raised or upheld before.

00:37:15.860 --> 00:37:19.700
I rested my head against a pillow or an arm and felt easy.

00:37:21.620 --> 00:37:24.660
In five minutes more the cloud of bewilderment dissolved.

00:37:25.120 --> 00:37:29.980
I knew quite well that I was in my own bed and that the red glare was the nursery fire.

00:37:30.660 --> 00:37:33.420
It was night, a candle burnt on the table.

00:37:33.940 --> 00:37:36.600
Bessie stood at the bed foot with a basin in her hand,

00:37:36.600 --> 00:37:40.200
and a gentleman sat in a chair near my pillow leaning over me.

00:37:41.300 --> 00:37:46.620
I felt an inexpressible relief, a soothing conviction of protection and security when

00:37:46.620 --> 00:37:51.860
I knew that there was a stranger in the room, an individual not belonging to Gateshead and

00:37:51.860 --> 00:37:53.360
not related to Mrs. Reed.

00:37:54.140 --> 00:37:58.660
Turning from Bessie, though her presence was far less obnoxious to me than that of Abbott,

00:37:58.660 --> 00:38:02.280
for instance, would have been, I scrutinized the face of the gentleman.

00:38:02.820 --> 00:38:03.900
I knew him.

00:38:04.080 --> 00:38:06.220
It was Mr. Lloyd, an apothecary.

00:38:06.600 --> 00:38:10.040
Sometimes called in by Mrs. Reed when the servants were ailing.

00:38:10.600 --> 00:38:13.000
For herself and the children she employed a physician.

00:38:14.120 --> 00:38:16.920
Well, who am I, he asked.

00:38:17.600 --> 00:38:20.800
I pronounced his name, offering him at the same time my hand.

00:38:21.280 --> 00:38:25.520
He took it smiling and saying, we shall do very well by and by.

00:38:26.520 --> 00:38:28.780
Then he laid me down and addressing Bessie,

00:38:28.780 --> 00:38:32.540
charged her to be very careful that I was not disturbed during the night.

00:38:33.180 --> 00:38:38.020
Having given some further directions and intimates that he should call the next day,

00:38:38.640 --> 00:38:40.100
he departed to my grief.

00:38:40.940 --> 00:38:44.880
I felt so sheltered and befriended while he sat in the chair near my pillow,

00:38:45.240 --> 00:38:49.880
and as he closed the door after him, all the room darkened and my heart again sank.

00:38:50.780 --> 00:38:52.680
Inexpressible sadness weighed it down.

00:38:53.460 --> 00:38:55.480
Do you feel as if you should sleep, Miss?

00:38:55.880 --> 00:38:57.520
asked Bessie rather softly.

00:38:59.120 --> 00:39:00.840
Scarcely dared I answer her,

00:39:00.840 --> 00:39:03.100
for I feared the next sentence might be rough.

00:39:04.500 --> 00:39:05.300
I will try.

00:39:06.420 --> 00:39:08.660
Would you like to drink, or could you eat anything?

00:39:09.840 --> 00:39:11.260
No, thank you, Bessie.

00:39:12.600 --> 00:39:15.780
Then I think I shall go to bed, for it is past twelve o'clock.

00:39:16.320 --> 00:39:18.700
But you may call me if you want anything in the night.

00:39:20.240 --> 00:39:21.660
Wonderful civility, this.

00:39:22.180 --> 00:39:24.140
It emboldened me to ask a question.

00:39:25.620 --> 00:39:28.120
Bessie, what is the matter with me?

00:39:28.340 --> 00:39:29.160
Am I ill?

00:39:30.080 --> 00:39:33.400
You fell sick, I suppose, in the red room with crying.

00:39:33.900 --> 00:39:35.500
You'll be better soon, no doubt.

00:39:36.760 --> 00:39:39.320
Bessie went into the housemaid's apartment, which was near.

00:39:39.700 --> 00:39:40.780
I heard her say,

00:39:41.580 --> 00:39:44.140
Sarah, come and sleep with me in the nursery.

00:39:44.680 --> 00:39:48.020
I daren't for my life be alone with that poor child to-night.

00:39:48.400 --> 00:39:49.480
She might die.

00:39:50.100 --> 00:39:52.980
It's such a strange thing she should have that fit.

00:39:53.620 --> 00:39:55.100
I wonder if she saw anything.

00:39:55.860 --> 00:39:57.460
Mrs. was rather too hard.

00:39:58.320 --> 00:40:00.780
Sarah came back with her, they both went to bed.

00:40:01.180 --> 00:40:04.200
They were whispering together for half an hour before they fell asleep.

00:40:04.840 --> 00:40:07.780
I caught scraps of their conversation, from which I was able

00:40:07.780 --> 00:40:10.860
only too distinctly to infer the main subject discussed.

00:40:11.600 --> 00:40:14.540
Something passed her, all dressed in white and vanished.

00:40:15.280 --> 00:40:19.960
A great black dog behind him, three loud raps on the chamber door,

00:40:20.640 --> 00:40:24.620
a light in the churchyard just over his grave, etc.

00:40:27.460 --> 00:40:29.200
At last both slept.

00:40:29.880 --> 00:40:31.780
The fire and the candle went out.

00:40:32.220 --> 00:40:36.440
For me, the watches of that long night passed in ghastly wakefulness,

00:40:37.240 --> 00:40:41.300
strained by dread, such dread as children only can feel.

00:40:42.520 --> 00:40:46.540
No severe or prolonged bodily illness followed this incident of the red room.

00:40:47.160 --> 00:40:51.420
It only gave my nerves a shock, of which I feel the reverberation to this day.

00:40:52.160 --> 00:40:56.620
Yes, Mrs. Reed, to you I owe some fearful pangs of mental suffering.

00:40:56.620 --> 00:41:00.540
But I ought to forgive you, for you knew not what you did.

00:41:00.900 --> 00:41:05.840
While rending my heartstrings you thought you were only uprooting my bad propensities.

00:41:08.240 --> 00:41:13.060
Next day by noon I was up and dressed and sat wrapped in a shawl by the nursery hearth.

00:41:13.660 --> 00:41:15.780
I felt physically weak and broken down.

00:41:16.120 --> 00:41:19.720
But my worst ailment was an unutterable wretchedness of mind,

00:41:20.300 --> 00:41:23.500
a wretchedness which kept drawing from me silent tears.

00:41:23.500 --> 00:41:28.100
No sooner had I wiped one salt drop from my cheek than another followed.

00:41:29.020 --> 00:41:32.020
Yet, I thought, I ought to have been happy.

00:41:32.500 --> 00:41:34.060
For none of the Reeds were there.

00:41:34.360 --> 00:41:36.520
They were all gone out in the carriage with their mamma.

00:41:37.400 --> 00:41:40.280
Abbott, too, was sewing in another room, and Bessie,

00:41:40.440 --> 00:41:44.120
as she moved hither and thither putting away toys and arranging drawers,

00:41:44.740 --> 00:41:48.240
addressed to me every now and then a word of unwanted kindness.

00:41:50.060 --> 00:41:53.920
This state of things should have been to me a paradise of peace,

00:41:54.360 --> 00:41:58.420
accustomed, as I was, to a life of ceaseless reprimand and thankless fagging.

00:41:58.760 --> 00:42:03.800
But, in fact, my wracked nerves were now in such a state that no calm could soothe

00:42:03.800 --> 00:42:06.140
and no pleasure excite them agreeably.

00:42:08.560 --> 00:42:12.360
Bessie had been down to the kitchen, and she brought up with her a tart on a certain

00:42:12.360 --> 00:42:18.080
brightly painted china plate, whose bird of paradise nestling in a wreath of convivouli

00:42:18.080 --> 00:42:23.580
and rose buds had been wont to stir in me a most enthusiastic sense of admiration,

00:42:24.160 --> 00:42:27.960
and which plate I had often petitioned to be allowed to take in my hands

00:42:27.960 --> 00:42:33.140
in order to examine it more closely, but had always hitherto been deemed

00:42:33.140 --> 00:42:34.780
unworthy of such a privilege.

00:42:35.600 --> 00:42:38.560
This precious vessel was now placed on my knee,

00:42:38.940 --> 00:42:43.520
and I was cordially invited to eat the circlet of delicate pastry upon it.

00:42:44.200 --> 00:42:51.180
Vain favor, coming, like most other favors long deferred and often wished for, too late.

00:42:52.160 --> 00:42:55.680
I could not eat the tart, and the plumage of the bird,

00:42:55.960 --> 00:42:58.960
the tints of the flowers, seemed strangely faded.

00:43:00.500 --> 00:43:02.540
I put both plate and tart away.

00:43:04.700 --> 00:43:06.220
Bessie asked if I would have a book.

00:43:06.960 --> 00:43:10.160
The word book acted as a transient stimulus,

00:43:10.160 --> 00:43:13.400
and I begged her to fetch Gulliver's travels from the library.

00:43:13.520 --> 00:43:16.960
This book I had again and again perused with delight.

00:43:17.620 --> 00:43:22.060
I considered it a narrative of facts, and discovered in it a vein of interest

00:43:22.060 --> 00:43:24.200
deeper than what I found in fairy tales.

00:43:24.720 --> 00:43:29.240
For as to the elves, having sought them in vain among foxglove leaves and bells,

00:43:29.580 --> 00:43:33.460
under mushrooms, and beneath the ground ivy mantling old wall nooks,

00:43:33.960 --> 00:43:38.880
I had at length made up my mind to the sad truth that they were all gone out of England

00:43:38.880 --> 00:43:44.740
to some savage country where the woods were wilder and thicker, and the population more scant.

00:43:45.620 --> 00:43:51.520
Whereas Lilliput and Brobdignog being, in my creed, solid parts of the earth's surface,

00:43:51.860 --> 00:43:58.260
I doubted not that I might one day, by taking a long voyage, see with my own eyes the little

00:43:58.260 --> 00:44:04.800
fields, houses, and trees, the diminutive people, the tiny cows, sheep, and birds of the One Realm,

00:44:04.800 --> 00:44:10.580
and the cornfields forest high, the mighty mastiffs, the monster cats,

00:44:10.980 --> 00:44:13.080
the tower-like men and women of the other.

00:44:14.100 --> 00:44:18.180
Yet, when this cherished volume was now placed in my hand,

00:44:18.580 --> 00:44:23.460
when I turned over its leaves and sought in its marvelous pictures the charm I had,

00:44:23.740 --> 00:44:28.100
till now never failed to find, all was eerie and dreary.

00:44:28.540 --> 00:44:33.550
The giants were gaunt goblins, the pygmies malevolent and fearful imps.

00:44:34.170 --> 00:44:38.810
Gulliver, a most desolate wanderer in most dread and dangerous regions.

00:44:39.810 --> 00:44:46.430
I closed the book, which I dared no longer peruse and put it on the table beside the untasted tart.

00:44:48.150 --> 00:44:52.350
Bessie had now finished dusting and tidying the room, and having washed her hands,

00:44:52.390 --> 00:44:56.690
she opened a certain little drawer full of splendid shreds of silk and satin,

00:44:56.830 --> 00:44:59.430
and began making a new bonnet for Georgiana's doll.

00:45:00.870 --> 00:45:07.930
Meantime, she sang. Her song was, In the days when we went gypsying a long time ago.

00:45:08.970 --> 00:45:13.070
I had often heard the song before, and always with lively delight,

00:45:13.350 --> 00:45:16.570
for Bessie had a sweet voice, at least I thought so.

00:45:16.970 --> 00:45:22.610
But now, though her voice was still sweet, I found in its melody an indescribable sadness.

00:45:23.330 --> 00:45:29.970
Sometimes, preoccupied with her work, she sang the refrain very slowly, very lingeringly.

00:45:30.870 --> 00:45:38.230
A long time ago came out like the saddest cadence of a funeral hymn.

00:45:38.770 --> 00:45:43.350
She passed into another ballad, this time a really doleful one.

00:45:44.570 --> 00:45:51.650
My feet there soar and my limbs there weary. Long is the way and the mountains are wild.

00:45:52.210 --> 00:45:58.590
Soon will the twilight close moonless and dreary over the path of the poor orphan child.

00:45:59.570 --> 00:46:06.190
Why did they send me so far and so lonely, up where the moors spread and gray rocks are piled?

00:46:06.570 --> 00:46:12.490
Men are hard-hearted and kind angels only watch o'er the steps of a poor orphan child.

00:46:13.610 --> 00:46:16.950
Yet distant and soft the night breeze is blowing.

00:46:16.950 --> 00:46:24.330
Clouds there are none and clear stars be mild. God in his mercy protection is showing,

00:46:25.010 --> 00:46:31.990
comfort and hope to the poor orphan child. Even should I fall o'er the broken bridge passing

00:46:31.990 --> 00:46:39.150
or stray in the marshes by false lights beguiled, still will my father with promise and blessing

00:46:39.150 --> 00:46:46.510
take to his bosom the poor orphan child. There is a thought that for strength should avail me,

00:46:46.510 --> 00:46:53.890
though both shelter and kindred despoiled. Heaven is a home and rest will not fail me.

00:46:54.230 --> 00:46:56.730
God is a friend to the poor orphan child.

00:46:57.870 --> 00:47:01.730
Come, Miss Jane, don't cry, said Bessie as she finished.

00:47:02.850 --> 00:47:08.170
She might as well have said to the fire, don't burn. But how could she divine the

00:47:08.170 --> 00:47:14.010
morbid suffering to which I was a prey? In the course of the morning Mr. Lloyd came again.

00:47:14.010 --> 00:47:21.290
What? Already up? He said as he entered the nursery. Well, nurse, how is she?

00:47:21.990 --> 00:47:26.750
Bessie answered that I was doing very well. Then she ought to look more cheerful.

00:47:27.430 --> 00:47:33.570
Come here, Miss Jane. Your name is Jane, is it not? Yes, sir, Jane Eyre.

00:47:34.590 --> 00:47:40.490
Well, you have been crying, Miss Jane Eyre. Can you tell me what about? Have you any pain?

00:47:41.130 --> 00:47:46.190
No, sir. Oh, I dare say she is crying because she could not go out with the

00:47:46.190 --> 00:47:53.450
Misses in the carriage, interposed Bessie. Surely not. Why, she is too old for such pettishness.

00:47:54.290 --> 00:47:58.690
I thought so too, and my self-esteem being wounded by the false charge,

00:47:59.070 --> 00:48:05.050
I answered promptly. I never cried for such a thing in my life. I hate going out in the carriage.

00:48:05.050 --> 00:48:11.530
I cry because I am miserable. Oh, fie, Miss, said Bessie.

00:48:12.450 --> 00:48:16.750
The good apothecary appeared a little puzzled. I was standing before him.

00:48:16.970 --> 00:48:23.490
He fixed his eyes on me very steadily. His eyes were small and grey, not very bright,

00:48:23.870 --> 00:48:29.890
but I dare say I should think them shrewd now. He had a hard-featured yet good-natured looking face.

00:48:29.890 --> 00:48:32.650
Having considered me at leisure, he said,

00:48:33.290 --> 00:48:35.090
What made you ill yesterday?

00:48:35.910 --> 00:48:39.450
She had a fall, said Bessie, again putting in her word.

00:48:41.110 --> 00:48:47.030
Fall? Why, that is like a baby again. Can't she manage to walk at her age?

00:48:47.410 --> 00:48:49.310
She must be eight or nine years old.

00:48:50.310 --> 00:48:56.330
I was knocked down, was the blunt explanation, jerked out of me by another pang of mortified

00:48:56.330 --> 00:49:02.730
pride. But that did not make me ill, I added, while Mr. Lloyd helped himself to a pinch of snuff.

00:49:04.790 --> 00:49:07.430
As he was returning the box to his waistcoat pocket,

00:49:07.950 --> 00:49:10.990
a loud bell rang for the servant's dinner. He knew what it was.

00:49:11.790 --> 00:49:18.050
That's for you, nurse, he said. You can go down. I'll give Miss Jane a lecture till you come back.

00:49:19.350 --> 00:49:22.470
Bessie would rather have stayed, but she was obliged to go,

00:49:22.470 --> 00:49:26.530
because punctuality at meals was rigidly enforced at Gateshead Hall.

00:49:27.830 --> 00:49:32.950
The fall did not make you ill. What did, then? pursued Mr. Lloyd when Bessie was gone.

00:49:33.350 --> 00:49:37.370
I was shut up in a room where there is a ghost till after dark.

00:49:38.310 --> 00:49:41.790
I saw Mr. Lloyd smile and frown at the same time.

00:49:42.770 --> 00:49:46.870
Ghosts? What, are you a baby after all? You are afraid of ghosts?

00:49:47.830 --> 00:49:52.450
Of Mr. Reed's ghost I am. He died in that room and was laid out there.

00:49:52.470 --> 00:49:56.950
Neither Bessie nor anyone else will go into it at night, if they can help it.

00:49:57.230 --> 00:50:02.650
And it was cruel to shut me up alone without a candle, so cruel that I think I shall never forget it.

00:50:03.150 --> 00:50:08.350
Nonsense! And is it that makes you so miserable? Are you afraid now in daylight?

00:50:09.350 --> 00:50:12.770
No, but night will come again before long, and besides.

00:50:13.790 --> 00:50:17.950
I am unhappy, very unhappy, for other things.

00:50:19.050 --> 00:50:22.030
What other things? Can you tell me some of them?

00:50:23.110 --> 00:50:29.190
How much I wish to reply fully to this question, how difficult it was to frame any answer.

00:50:29.790 --> 00:50:33.230
Children can feel, but they cannot analyze their feelings.

00:50:33.730 --> 00:50:36.810
And if the analysis is partially affected in thought,

00:50:37.190 --> 00:50:40.650
they know not how to express the results of the process in words.

00:50:41.610 --> 00:50:46.950
Fearful, however, of losing this first and only opportunity of relieving my grief by imparting it,

00:50:46.950 --> 00:50:54.510
I, after a disturbed pause, contrived to frame a meager, though as far as it went, true response.

00:50:56.030 --> 00:51:00.510
For one thing, I have no father or mother, brothers or sisters.

00:51:01.270 --> 00:51:03.190
You have a kind aunt and cousins.

00:51:04.310 --> 00:51:06.650
Again I paused, then bunglingly announced.

00:51:07.630 --> 00:51:11.590
But John Reed knocked me down, and my aunt shut me up in the red room.

00:51:12.510 --> 00:51:15.050
Mr. Lloyd a second time produced his snuff-box.

00:51:16.430 --> 00:51:20.410
Don't you think Gateshead Hall a very beautiful house? he asked.

00:51:20.970 --> 00:51:24.570
Are you not very thankful to have such a fine place to live at?

00:51:25.350 --> 00:51:30.990
It is not my house, sir, and Abbott says I have less right to be here than a servant.

00:51:32.590 --> 00:51:36.510
You can't be silly enough to wish to leave such a splendid place.

00:51:37.530 --> 00:51:41.330
If I had anywhere else to go, I should be glad to leave it,

00:51:41.490 --> 00:51:44.650
but I can never get away from Gateshead till I am a woman.

00:51:46.150 --> 00:51:48.670
Perhaps you may, who knows?

00:51:49.910 --> 00:51:52.330
Have you any relations besides Mrs. Reed?

00:51:53.310 --> 00:51:57.230
I think not, sir. None belonging to your father?

00:51:58.950 --> 00:52:07.110
I don't know. I asked Aunt Reed once, and she said possibly I might have some poor, lowly relations called air,

00:52:07.430 --> 00:52:09.170
but she knew nothing about them.

00:52:09.990 --> 00:52:12.610
If you had such, would you like to go to them?

00:52:13.730 --> 00:52:19.230
I reflected. Poverty looks grim to grown people, still more so to children.

00:52:19.950 --> 00:52:24.050
They have not much idea of industrious, working, respectable poverty.

00:52:24.650 --> 00:52:28.970
They think of the word only as connected with ragged clothes, scanty food,

00:52:29.430 --> 00:52:36.330
fireless grates, rude manners, and debasing vices. Poverty, for me, was synonymous with degradation.

00:52:37.910 --> 00:52:42.510
No, I should not like to belong to poor people, was my reply.

00:52:43.230 --> 00:52:45.090
Not even if they were kind to you?

00:52:45.830 --> 00:52:50.950
I shook my head. I could not see how poor people had the means of being kind.

00:52:51.410 --> 00:52:57.210
And then, to learn to speak like them, to adopt their manners, to be uneducated,

00:52:57.310 --> 00:53:01.630
to grow up like one of the poor women I saw sometimes nursing their children

00:53:01.630 --> 00:53:05.050
or washing their clothes at the cottage doors of the village of Gateshead?

00:53:05.890 --> 00:53:10.870
No, I was not heroic enough to purchase liberty at the price of caste.

00:53:12.750 --> 00:53:15.950
But are your relatives so very poor? Are they working people?

00:53:18.030 --> 00:53:23.710
I cannot tell. Aunt Reed says if I have any, they must be a beggarly set.

00:53:24.250 --> 00:53:26.050
I should not like to go a-begging.

00:53:27.650 --> 00:53:29.410
Would you like to go to school?

00:53:30.690 --> 00:53:34.650
Again I reflected. I scarcely knew what school was.

00:53:35.850 --> 00:53:39.870
Bessie sometimes spoke of it as a place where young ladies sat in the stocks,

00:53:40.410 --> 00:53:44.830
wore backboards, and were expected to be exceedingly genteel and precise.

00:53:45.670 --> 00:53:48.370
John Reed hated his school and abused his master.

00:53:48.990 --> 00:53:51.750
But John Reed's tastes were no rule for mine.

00:53:52.430 --> 00:53:56.350
And if Bessie's accounts of school discipline, gathered from the young

00:53:56.350 --> 00:54:01.230
ladies of a family where she had lived before coming to Gateshead, were somewhat appalling,

00:54:01.230 --> 00:54:05.750
her details of certain accomplishments attained by these same young ladies were,

00:54:05.810 --> 00:54:07.890
I thought, equally attractive.

00:54:08.690 --> 00:54:13.530
She boasted of the beautiful paintings of landscapes and flowers by them executed,

00:54:14.190 --> 00:54:17.050
of songs they could sing and pieces they could play,

00:54:17.790 --> 00:54:21.530
of purses they could knit, of French books they could translate,

00:54:22.130 --> 00:54:25.250
till my spirit was moved to emulation as I listened.

00:54:25.950 --> 00:54:28.990
Besides, school would be a complete change.

00:54:28.990 --> 00:54:36.450
It implied a long journey, an entire separation from Gateshead, an entrance into a new life.

00:54:38.130 --> 00:54:43.830
I should indeed like to go to school, was the audible conclusion of my musings.

00:54:44.870 --> 00:54:50.430
Well, well, who knows what may happen, said Mr. Lloyd as he got up.

00:54:51.410 --> 00:54:56.450
The child ought to have a change of air and scene, he added, speaking to himself,

00:54:57.070 --> 00:54:58.490
nerves not in a good state.

00:55:00.050 --> 00:55:04.870
Bessie now returned. At the same moment the carriage was heard rolling up the gravel walk.

00:55:05.570 --> 00:55:10.930
Is that your mistress, nurse? asked Mr. Lloyd. I should like to speak to her before I go.

00:55:11.730 --> 00:55:15.390
Bessie invited him to walk into the breakfast room and led the way out.

00:55:15.870 --> 00:55:20.970
In the interview which followed between him and Mrs. Reed, I presume, from after occurrences,

00:55:21.270 --> 00:55:26.050
that the apothecary ventured to recommend my being sent to school, and the recommendation

00:55:26.050 --> 00:55:31.070
was no doubt readily enough adopted, for as Abbott said in discussing the subject with Bessie

00:55:31.070 --> 00:55:37.170
when both sat sewing in the nursery one night, after I was in bed, and, as they thought, asleep.

00:55:38.430 --> 00:55:43.470
Mrs. was, she dared say, glad enough to get rid of such a tiresome, ill-conditioned child,

00:55:43.810 --> 00:55:49.950
who always looked as if she were watching everybody and scheming plots underhand.

00:55:50.610 --> 00:55:55.710
Abbott, I think, gave me credit for being a sort of infantile Guy Fawkes.

00:55:56.550 --> 00:56:03.190
On that same occasion I learned for the first time from Miss Abbott's communications to Bessie

00:56:03.190 --> 00:56:08.570
that my father had been a poor clergyman, that my mother had married him against the wishes of her

00:56:08.570 --> 00:56:13.750
friends who considered the match beneath her, that my grandfather Reed was so irritated at

00:56:13.750 --> 00:56:19.510
her disobedience he cut her off without a shilling, that after my mother and father had been married

00:56:19.510 --> 00:56:25.230
a year, the latter caught the typhus fever while visiting among the poor of a large manufacturing

00:56:25.230 --> 00:56:31.430
town where his curacy was situated and where that disease was then prevalent, that my mother

00:56:31.430 --> 00:56:37.830
took the infection from him and both died within a month of each other. Bessie, when she heard

00:56:37.830 --> 00:56:44.910
this narrative, sighed and said, Poor Miss Jane is to be pitied too, Abbott. Yes, responded Abbott,

00:56:45.190 --> 00:56:49.670
if she were a nice pretty child, one might compassionate her forlornness,

00:56:49.890 --> 00:56:53.350
but one really cannot care for such a little toad as that.

00:56:54.450 --> 00:57:01.190
Not a great deal to be sure, agreed Bessie. At any rate, a beauty like Miss Georgiana would be more

00:57:01.190 --> 00:57:08.350
moving in the same condition. Yes, I dote on Miss Georgiana, cried the fervent Abbott, little darling,

00:57:08.630 --> 00:57:15.350
with her long curls and her blue eyes and such a sweet colour as she has, just as if she were painted.

00:57:16.610 --> 00:57:19.950
Bessie, I could fancy a Welsh rabbit for supper.

00:57:20.610 --> 00:57:26.510
So could I, with a roast onion. Come, we'll go down. They went.

00:57:46.490 --> 00:57:51.090
IV. From my discourse with Mr. Lloyd, and from

00:57:51.090 --> 00:57:56.070
the above-reported conference between Bessie and Abbott, I gathered enough hope to suffice

00:57:56.070 --> 00:58:02.210
as a motive for wishing to get well. A change seemed near. I desired and waited it in silence.

00:58:02.890 --> 00:58:07.810
It tarried, however. Days and weeks passed. I had regained my normal state of health,

00:58:07.830 --> 00:58:13.290
but no new illusion was made to the subject over which I brooded. Mrs. Reed surveyed me

00:58:13.290 --> 00:58:19.190
at times with a severe eye, but seldom addressed me. Since my illness she had drawn a more

00:58:19.190 --> 00:58:24.470
marked line of separation than ever between me and her own children, pointing me a small

00:58:24.470 --> 00:58:30.210
closet to sleep in by myself, condemning me to take my meals alone and pass all my time in the

00:58:30.210 --> 00:58:35.330
nursery while my cousins were constantly in the drawing-room. Not a hint, however, did she drop

00:58:35.330 --> 00:58:41.930
about sending me to school. Still I felt an instinctive certainty that she would not long

00:58:41.930 --> 00:58:47.590
endure me under the same roof with her, for her glance, now more than ever, when turned on me,

00:58:47.590 --> 00:58:54.950
expressed an insuperable and rooted aversion. Eliza and Georgiana, evidently acting according

00:58:54.950 --> 00:58:59.590
to others, spoke to me as little as possible. John thrust his tongue in his cheek whenever

00:58:59.590 --> 00:59:04.770
he saw me, and once attempted chastisement, but as I instantly turned against him, roused by the

00:59:04.770 --> 00:59:09.810
same sentiment of deep ire and desperate revolt which had stirred my corruption before, he thought

00:59:09.810 --> 00:59:16.790
it better to desist, and ran from me, tittering execrations, and bowing, I had burst his nose.

00:59:17.310 --> 00:59:21.910
I had indeed levelled at that prominent feature as hard a blow as my knuckles could inflict,

00:59:22.410 --> 00:59:26.850
and when I saw that either that or my look daunted him, I had the greatest inclination

00:59:26.850 --> 00:59:32.290
to follow up my advantage to purpose, but he was already with his mamma. I heard him in a

00:59:32.290 --> 00:59:38.230
blubbering tone commence the tale of how that nasty Jane Eyre had flown at him like a mad cat.

00:59:38.610 --> 00:59:43.710
He was stopped rather harshly. Don't talk to me about her, John. I told you not to go near her.

00:59:43.710 --> 00:59:49.350
She is not worthy of notice. I do not choose that either you or your sisters should associate with

00:59:49.350 --> 00:59:55.050
her. Here, leaning over the banister, I cried out suddenly, and without at all deliberating

00:59:55.050 --> 01:00:01.950
on my words, they are not fit to associate with me. Mrs. Reed was a rather stout woman,

01:00:01.950 --> 01:00:06.890
but on hearing this strange and audacious declaration, she ran nimbly up the stair,

01:00:07.310 --> 01:00:11.450
swept me like a whirlwind into the nursery, and crushing me down on the edge of my crib,

01:00:11.450 --> 01:00:16.850
dared me in an emphatic voice to rise from that place or utter one syllable during the

01:00:16.850 --> 01:00:22.550
remainder of the day. What would Uncle Reed say to you if he were alive was my scarcely voluntary

01:00:22.550 --> 01:00:27.410
demand. I say scarcely voluntary, for it seemed as if my tongue pronounced words without my will

01:00:27.410 --> 01:00:32.290
consenting to their utterance. Something spoke out of me over which I had no control.

01:00:33.270 --> 01:00:41.070
What? said Mrs. Reed under her breath. Her usually cold, composed grey eye became troubled with a

01:00:41.070 --> 01:00:47.130
hand from my arm, and gazed at me as if she really did not know whether I were child or fiend.

01:00:47.650 --> 01:00:54.510
I was now in for it. My Uncle Reed is in heaven, and can see all you do and think, and so can

01:00:54.510 --> 01:00:58.770
Papa and Mama. They know how you shut me up all day long, and how you wish me dead.

01:00:59.570 --> 01:01:03.990
Mrs. Reed soon rallied her spirits. She shook me most soundly. She boxed both my ears,

01:01:04.030 --> 01:01:10.670
and left me without a word. Bessie supplied the hiatus by a homily of an hour's length

01:01:10.670 --> 01:01:15.270
in which she proved beyond a doubt that I was the most wicked and abandoned child ever reared under

01:01:15.270 --> 01:01:20.310
a roof. I half believed her, for I felt indeed only bad feelings surging in my breast.

01:01:21.870 --> 01:01:25.930
November, December, and half of January passed away. Christmas and the New Year had been

01:01:25.930 --> 01:01:30.910
celebrating it at Gateshead with the usual festive cheer. Presents had been interchanged,

01:01:31.030 --> 01:01:35.290
dinners and evening parties given. From every enjoyment I was, of course, excluded.

01:01:35.290 --> 01:01:41.630
By a share of the gate, he consisted in witnessing the daily apparelling of Eliza and Georgiana,

01:01:41.950 --> 01:01:46.550
and seeing them descend to the drawing-room dressed out in the thin muslin frocks and scarlet

01:01:46.550 --> 01:01:51.930
sashes, with hair elaborately ring-lettered, and afterwards enlisting to the sound of the piano,

01:01:52.390 --> 01:01:57.050
or the harp played below, to the passing to and fro of the butler and footman,

01:01:57.450 --> 01:02:02.610
to the jingling of larsen china as refreshments were handed, to the broken hum of conversation

01:02:02.610 --> 01:02:07.910
as the drawing-room door opened and closed. When tired of this occupation, I would retire

01:02:07.910 --> 01:02:12.990
from the stair-head to the solitary and silent nursery. There, though somewhat sad, I was not

01:02:12.990 --> 01:02:17.970
miserable. To speak truth, I had not the least wish to go into company, for in company I was

01:02:17.970 --> 01:02:23.350
very rarely noticed, and if Bessie had been but kind and companionable, I should have deemed it

01:02:23.350 --> 01:02:27.430
a treat to spend the evenings quietly with her instead of passing them under the formidable eye

01:02:27.430 --> 01:02:32.150
of Mrs. Reid in a room full of ladies and gentlemen. But Bessie, as soon as she had dressed

01:02:32.150 --> 01:02:35.950
her young ladies, used to take herself off to the lively regions of the kitchen and

01:02:35.950 --> 01:02:41.650
housekeeper's room, generally bearing the candle along with her. I then sat with my doll on my knee

01:02:41.650 --> 01:02:46.390
till the fire got low, glancing around occasionally to make sure that nothing worse than myself haunted

01:02:46.390 --> 01:02:52.930
the shadowy room, and when the embers sank to a dull red, I undressed hastily, tugging at knots

01:02:52.930 --> 01:02:58.530
and strings as I best might, and sought shelter from cold and darkness in my crib. To this crib,

01:02:58.530 --> 01:03:05.270
I always took my doll. Human beings must love something, and in the dearth of worthier objects

01:03:05.270 --> 01:03:10.450
of affection, I contrived to find a pleasure in loving and cherishing a faded graven image,

01:03:11.050 --> 01:03:16.350
shabby as a miniature scarecrow. It puzzles me now to remember with what absurd sincerity I

01:03:16.350 --> 01:03:22.470
doted on this little toy, half fancying it alive and capable of sensation. I could not sleep unless

01:03:22.470 --> 01:03:28.930
it was folded in my nightgown, and when it lay there safe and warm, I was comparatively happy,

01:03:29.250 --> 01:03:34.930
believing it to be happy likewise. Long did the hours seem while I waited the departure of the

01:03:34.930 --> 01:03:40.030
company, and listened for the sound of Bessie's step on the stairs. Sometimes she would come up

01:03:40.030 --> 01:03:45.010
in the interval to seek her thimble or her scissors, or perhaps to bring me something by way of supper,

01:03:45.370 --> 01:03:50.950
a bun or a cheesecake. Then she would sit on the bed while I ate it, and when I had finished,

01:03:50.950 --> 01:03:56.650
she would tuck the clothes round me, and twice she kissed me and said good night, Miss Jane.

01:03:57.970 --> 01:04:02.650
When thus gentle, Bessie seemed to me the best, prettiest, kindest being in the world,

01:04:03.270 --> 01:04:08.390
and I wished most intensely that she would always be so pleasant and amiable, and never push me

01:04:08.390 --> 01:04:15.510
about or scold or task me unreasonably, as she was too often wont to do. Bessie Lee must, I think,

01:04:15.510 --> 01:04:21.470
have been a girl of great natural capacity, for she was smart in all she did, and had a remarkable

01:04:21.470 --> 01:04:26.990
knack of narrative, so at least I judge from the impression made on me by her nursery tales.

01:04:27.770 --> 01:04:31.190
She was pretty, too, if my recollections of her face and person are correct.

01:04:31.890 --> 01:04:37.910
I remember her as a slim young woman, with black hair, dark eyes, very nice features,

01:04:38.370 --> 01:04:43.210
and good clear complexion. But she had a capricious and hasty temper,

01:04:43.210 --> 01:04:48.270
and indifferent ideas of principle or justice. Still, such as she was,

01:04:48.550 --> 01:04:50.990
I preferred her to anyone else at Gateshead Hall.

01:04:52.470 --> 01:04:57.390
It was the 15th of January, about nine o'clock in the morning. Bessie was gone down to breakfast.

01:04:57.510 --> 01:05:03.310
My cousins had not yet been summoned to their mamma. Eliza was putting on her bonnet and warm

01:05:03.310 --> 01:05:09.150
garden coat to go and feed her poultry, an occupation of which she was fond, and not less

01:05:09.150 --> 01:05:13.490
of selling the eggs to the housekeeper and hoarding up the money she thus obtained.

01:05:14.290 --> 01:05:19.610
She had a turn for traffic and a marked propensity for saving, shown not only in the

01:05:19.610 --> 01:05:24.230
vending of eggs and chickens, but also in driving hard bargains with the gardener about flower roots,

01:05:24.570 --> 01:05:31.030
seeds and slips of plants, that functionary having orders from Mrs. Reed to buy of his young lady all

01:05:31.030 --> 01:05:36.470
the products of her parterre she wished to sell, and Eliza would have sewed the hair off her head

01:05:36.470 --> 01:05:41.730
if she could have made a handsome profit thereby. As to her money, she first secreted it in odd

01:05:41.730 --> 01:05:46.770
corners, wrapped in a rag or an old curl paper, but some of these hoards having been discovered

01:05:46.770 --> 01:05:52.750
by the housemaid, Eliza, fearful of one day losing her valued treasure, consented to entrust it to

01:05:52.750 --> 01:05:59.010
her mother at a usurious rate of interest, fifty or sixty per cent, which interest she exacted

01:05:59.010 --> 01:06:03.150
every quarter, keeping her accounts in a little book with anxious accuracy.

01:06:04.370 --> 01:06:09.210
Georgiana sat on a high stool, dressing her hair at the glass, and into weaving her curls

01:06:09.210 --> 01:06:14.550
with artificial flowers and faded feathers, of which she had found a store in a drawer in the

01:06:14.550 --> 01:06:19.070
attic. I was making my bed, having received strict orders from Bessie to get it arranged

01:06:19.070 --> 01:06:24.030
before she returned, for Bessie now frequently employed me as a sort of under-nursery maid

01:06:24.030 --> 01:06:29.930
to tidy the room, dust the chairs, etc. Having spread the quilt and folded my night-dress,

01:06:29.930 --> 01:06:34.690
I went to the window-seat to put in order some picture books of doll's-house furniture scattered

01:06:34.690 --> 01:06:40.770
there, and abrupt command from Georgiana to let her play things alone, for the tiny chairs and

01:06:40.770 --> 01:06:45.890
mirrors, the fairy plates and cups were her property, stop my proceedings. And then, for

01:06:45.890 --> 01:06:50.930
lack of other occupation, I fell to breathing on the frost-flowers with which the window was

01:06:50.930 --> 01:06:55.170
fretted, and thus clearing a space in the glass through which I might look out on the grounds,

01:06:55.170 --> 01:06:59.390
where all was still and petrified under the influence of a hard frost.

01:07:00.690 --> 01:07:05.650
From this window were visible the porter's lodge and the carriage road, and just as I dissolved so

01:07:05.650 --> 01:07:10.730
much of the silver-white foliage veiling the panes as left room to look out, I saw the gates thrown

01:07:10.730 --> 01:07:15.510
open, and a carriage roll through. I watched it ascending the drive with indifference.

01:07:15.910 --> 01:07:19.990
Carriages often came to Gateshead, but none ever brought visitors in whom I was interested.

01:07:19.990 --> 01:07:25.270
It stopped in front of the house. The doorbell rang loudly. The newcomer was admitted.

01:07:25.950 --> 01:07:29.730
All this being nothing to me, my vacant attention soon found lively retraction

01:07:29.730 --> 01:07:34.650
in the spectacle of a little hungry robin which came and chirruped on the twigs of the leafless

01:07:34.650 --> 01:07:39.610
cherry-tree nailed against the wall near the casement. The remnants of my breakfast of bread

01:07:39.610 --> 01:07:44.610
and milk stood on the table, and having crumbled a morsel of roll, I was tagging at the sash to put

01:07:44.610 --> 01:07:48.490
out the crumbs on the windowsill when Bessie came running upstairs into the nursery.

01:07:48.970 --> 01:07:52.530
Miss Jane, take off your pinafore. What are you doing there? Have you washed your hands

01:07:52.530 --> 01:07:57.110
and face this morning? I gave another tug before I answered, for I wanted the bird to be secure

01:07:57.110 --> 01:08:01.790
of its bread. The sash yielded. I scattered the crumbs, some on the stone sill, some on the

01:08:01.790 --> 01:08:06.870
cherry-tree bough. Then, closing the window, I replied, No, Bessie, I have only just finished

01:08:07.870 --> 01:08:12.550
dusting. Troublesome, careless child, what are you doing now? You look quite red as if you had been

01:08:12.550 --> 01:08:17.810
about some mischief. What were you opening the window for? I was spared the trouble of answering,

01:08:18.470 --> 01:08:23.430
Bessie seemed in too great a hurry to listen to explanations. She hauled me to the washstand,

01:08:24.210 --> 01:08:28.890
inflicted a merciless but happily brief scrub on my face and hands with soap, water and a coarse

01:08:28.890 --> 01:08:34.370
towel, disciplined my head with a bristly brush, denuded me of my pinafore, and then,

01:08:34.390 --> 01:08:38.370
hurrying me to the top of the stairs, bid me go down directly, as I was wanted in the breakfast

01:08:38.370 --> 01:08:43.790
room. I would have asked who wanted me. I would have demanded if Mrs. Reed was there, but Bessie

01:08:43.790 --> 01:08:49.570
was already gone, and had closed the nursery door upon me. I slowly descended. For nearly

01:08:49.570 --> 01:08:54.350
three months I had never been called to Mrs. Reed's presence. Restricted so long to the nursery,

01:08:54.830 --> 01:09:00.290
the breakfast dining and drawing-rooms were become, for me, awful regions on which it dismayed me to

01:09:00.290 --> 01:09:06.490
intrude. I now stood in the empty hall. Before me was the breakfast-room door, and I stopped,

01:09:06.810 --> 01:09:12.170
intimidated and trembling. What a miserable little paltrune had fear engendered of unjust

01:09:12.170 --> 01:09:16.550
punishment made of me in those days. I feared to return to the nursery, and feared to go forward

01:09:16.550 --> 01:09:21.930
to the parlour. Ten minutes I stood in agitated hesitation. The vehement ringing of the breakfast

01:09:21.930 --> 01:09:29.270
room bell decided me I must enter. Who could want me? I asked inwardly, as with both hands I turned

01:09:29.270 --> 01:09:34.770
the stiff door handle, which for a second or two resisted my efforts. What should I see besides

01:09:34.770 --> 01:09:40.830
Aunt Reed in the apartment, a man or woman? The handle turned, the door unclosed, and passing

01:09:40.830 --> 01:09:47.550
through and cutting low I looked up at a black pillar. Such at least appeared to me at first sight

01:09:47.550 --> 01:09:53.050
the straight, narrow, sable-clad shape standing erect on the rug. The grim face at the top was

01:09:53.050 --> 01:09:59.650
like a carved mask placed above the shaft by way of capital. Mrs. Reed occupied her usual seat by

01:09:59.650 --> 01:10:04.470
the fireside. She made a signal to me to approach. I did so, and she introduced me to the stony

01:10:04.470 --> 01:10:09.850
stranger with the words, This is the little girl respecting whom I applied to you.

01:10:10.430 --> 01:10:15.490
He, for it was a man, turned his head slowly towards where I stood, and having examined me

01:10:15.490 --> 01:10:19.730
with the two inquisitive-looking grey eyes which twinkled under a pair of bushy brows,

01:10:20.310 --> 01:10:27.510
said solemnly, and in a base voice, Her size is small. What is her age? Ten years. So much

01:10:27.510 --> 01:10:32.850
was the doubtful answer, and he prolonged his scrutiny for some minutes. Presently he addressed

01:10:32.850 --> 01:10:40.970
Your name, little girl? Jane Eyre, sir. In uttering these words I looked up. He seemed to me a tall

01:10:40.970 --> 01:10:46.850
gentleman, but then I was very little. His features were large, and they and all the lines of his frame

01:10:46.850 --> 01:10:54.030
were equally harsh and prim. Well, Jane Eyre, now are you a good child? Impossible to reply to this

01:10:54.030 --> 01:11:00.450
in the affirmative. My little world held a contrary opinion. I was silent. Mrs. Reed answered for me

01:11:00.450 --> 01:11:05.890
by an expressive shake of the head, adding soon, Perhaps the less said on that subject,

01:11:06.010 --> 01:11:11.390
the better, Mr. Brocklehurst. Sorry, indeed, to hear it. She and I must have some talk.

01:11:12.050 --> 01:11:15.730
And bending from the perpendicular, he installed his person in the armchair

01:11:15.730 --> 01:11:22.010
opposite Mrs. Reed's. Come here, he said. I stepped across the rug. He placed me

01:11:22.010 --> 01:11:27.330
square and straight before him. What a face he had, now that it was almost on a level with mine!

01:11:27.330 --> 01:11:32.270
What a great nose, and what a mouth, and what large, prominent teeth!

01:11:33.230 --> 01:11:39.150
No sight so sad as that of a naughty child, he began, especially a naughty little girl.

01:11:39.690 --> 01:11:45.270
Do you know where the wicked go after death? They go to hell, was my ready and orthodox answer.

01:11:45.870 --> 01:11:51.690
And what is hell, can you tell me that? A pit full of fire. And should you like to fall into

01:11:51.690 --> 01:11:57.350
that pit and to be burning there for ever? No, sir. What must you do to avoid it?

01:11:58.090 --> 01:12:01.710
I deliberated a moment. My answer, when it did come, was objectionable.

01:12:02.330 --> 01:12:07.830
I must keep in good health and not die. How could you keep in good health? Children younger

01:12:07.830 --> 01:12:12.130
than you die daily. I buried a little child of five years old only a day or two since.

01:12:12.490 --> 01:12:18.090
A good little child, whose soul is now in heaven. It is to be feared the same could not be said

01:12:18.090 --> 01:12:23.830
of you were you to be called hence. Not being in a condition to remove his doubt,

01:12:23.910 --> 01:12:29.210
I only cast my eyes down on the two large feet planted on the rug, and sighed,

01:12:29.270 --> 01:12:33.210
wishing myself far enough away. I hope that sigh is from the heart,

01:12:33.230 --> 01:12:37.990
and that you repent of ever having been the occasion of discomfort to your excellent benefactress.

01:12:39.970 --> 01:12:45.530
Benefactress, benefactress, said I inwardly. They all call Mrs. Reid my benefactress. If so,

01:12:45.530 --> 01:12:51.050
benefactress is a disagreeable thing. Do you say your prayers night and morning?

01:12:51.330 --> 01:12:55.090
continued my interrogator. Yes, sir. Do you read your Bible?

01:12:55.910 --> 01:13:01.970
Sometimes. With pleasure. Are you fond of it? I like revelations, and the Book of Daniel,

01:13:02.130 --> 01:13:06.990
and Genesis, and Samuel, and a little bit of Exodus, and some parts of Kings and Chronicles,

01:13:07.330 --> 01:13:11.350
and Job and Jonah. And the Psalms? I hope you like them.

01:13:11.910 --> 01:13:18.790
No, sir. No? Oh, shocking! I have a little boy younger than you, who knows six Psalms by heart.

01:13:19.190 --> 01:13:22.790
And when you ask him which he would rather have, a gingerbread nut to eat,

01:13:22.910 --> 01:13:29.670
or a verse of a Psalm to learn, he says, Oh, the verse of a Psalm! Angels sing Psalms, said he.

01:13:29.890 --> 01:13:35.690
I wish to be a little angel here below. He then gets two nuts in recompense for his infant piety.

01:13:36.650 --> 01:13:41.290
Psalms are not interesting, I remarked. That proves you have a wicked heart,

01:13:41.650 --> 01:13:45.150
and you must pray to God to change it, to give you a new and clean one,

01:13:45.430 --> 01:13:48.510
to take away your heart of stone and give you a heart of flesh.

01:13:49.470 --> 01:13:54.410
I was about to propound a question, touching the manner in which that operation of changing

01:13:54.410 --> 01:13:58.910
my heart was to be performed, when Mrs. Reid interposed, telling me to sit down.

01:13:59.150 --> 01:14:01.450
She then proceeded to carry on the conversation herself.

01:14:02.010 --> 01:14:06.910
Mr. Brocklehurst, I believe I intimated in the letter which I wrote to you three weeks ago

01:14:06.910 --> 01:14:11.150
that this little girl has not quite the character and disposition I could wish.

01:14:11.570 --> 01:14:16.650
Should you admit her into Lowood School, I should be glad if the superintendent and teachers were

01:14:16.650 --> 01:14:21.350
requested to keep a strict eye on her, and, above all, to guard against her worst fault,

01:14:21.830 --> 01:14:26.710
a tendency to deceit. I mention this in your hearing, Jane, that you may not attempt to

01:14:26.710 --> 01:14:28.350
pose on Mr. Brocklehurst.

01:14:29.650 --> 01:14:35.470
Well might I dread, well might I dislike Mrs. Reid, for it was her nature to wound me cruelly.

01:14:35.690 --> 01:14:41.150
Never was I happy in her presence. However carefully I obeyed, however strenuously I strove

01:14:41.150 --> 01:14:46.490
to please her, my efforts were still repulsed and repaid by such sentences as the above.

01:14:47.230 --> 01:14:53.010
Now uttered before a stranger, the accusation cut me to the heart. I dimly perceived that she was

01:14:53.010 --> 01:14:57.390
obliterating hope from the new place of existence which she destined me to enter.

01:14:58.050 --> 01:15:02.410
I felt, though I could not have expressed the feeling, that she was sowing aversion

01:15:02.410 --> 01:15:08.150
and unkindness along my future path. I saw myself transformed under Mr. Brocklehurst's

01:15:08.150 --> 01:15:13.350
eye into an artful, noxious child, and what could I do to remedy the injury?

01:15:14.570 --> 01:15:20.570
Nothing indeed, thought I, as I struggled to repress a sob and hastily wiped away some tears,

01:15:20.570 --> 01:15:23.650
the impotent evidences of my anguish.

01:15:24.690 --> 01:15:30.470
Deceit is indeed a sad fault in a child, said Mr. Brocklehurst. It is akin to falsehood,

01:15:30.950 --> 01:15:35.770
and all liars will have their portion in the lake burning with fire and brimstone.

01:15:36.730 --> 01:15:40.950
She shall, however, be watched, Mrs. Reid. I will speak to Miss Temple and the teachers.

01:15:41.210 --> 01:15:44.410
I should wish her to be brought up in a manner suiting her prospects,

01:15:44.410 --> 01:15:50.990
continued my benefactress, to be made useful, to be kept humble. As for the vacations,

01:15:50.990 --> 01:15:53.710
she will, with your permission, spend them always at Lowood.

01:15:54.490 --> 01:15:58.830
Your decisions are perfectly judicious, madam, returned Mr. Brocklehurst.

01:15:58.970 --> 01:16:03.390
Humility is a Christian grace, and one peculiarly appropriate to the pupils of Lowood.

01:16:03.830 --> 01:16:08.370
I, therefore, direct that special care shall be bestowed on its cultivation amongst them.

01:16:08.730 --> 01:16:12.770
I have studied how best to mortify in them the worldly sentiment of pride,

01:16:12.770 --> 01:16:16.070
and only the other day I had a pleasing proof of my success.

01:16:16.390 --> 01:16:19.690
My second daughter, Augusta, went with her mamma to visit the school,

01:16:19.710 --> 01:16:21.430
and on her return she exclaimed,

01:16:21.790 --> 01:16:25.090
O dear papa, how quiet and plain all the girls at Lowood look,

01:16:25.410 --> 01:16:27.390
with their hair combed behind their ears,

01:16:27.690 --> 01:16:31.230
and their long pinafores, those little holland pockets outside their frocks.

01:16:31.550 --> 01:16:33.730
They are almost like poor people's children.

01:16:34.110 --> 01:16:39.930
And, said she, they looked at my dress and mamma's as if they had never seen a silk gown before.

01:16:40.710 --> 01:16:44.290
This is the state of things I quite approve, returned Mrs. Reid.

01:16:44.830 --> 01:16:46.350
Had I sought all England over,

01:16:46.450 --> 01:16:50.610
I could scarcely have found a sister more exactly fitting a child like Jane Eyre.

01:16:51.110 --> 01:16:55.590
Consistency, my dear Mr. Brocklehurst, I advocate consistency in all things.

01:16:56.890 --> 01:16:59.450
Consistency, madam, is the first of Christian duties,

01:16:59.810 --> 01:17:03.790
and it has been observed in every arrangement connected with the establishment of Lowood.

01:17:04.130 --> 01:17:07.810
Plain fare, simple attire, unsophisticated accommodations,

01:17:08.290 --> 01:17:13.090
hardy and active habits such as the order of the day in the house and its inhabitants.

01:17:13.710 --> 01:17:14.910
Quite right, sir.

01:17:15.130 --> 01:17:18.450
I may then depend upon this child being received as a pupil at Lowood,

01:17:18.570 --> 01:17:21.950
and there being trained in conformity to her position and prospects.

01:17:22.550 --> 01:17:23.850
Madam, you may.

01:17:24.390 --> 01:17:27.130
She who shall be placed in that nursery of chosen plants,

01:17:27.370 --> 01:17:31.730
and I trust she will show herself grateful for the inestimable privilege of her election.

01:17:32.270 --> 01:17:35.150
I will send her then as soon as possible, Mr. Brocklehurst, for,

01:17:35.150 --> 01:17:40.130
I assure you, I feel anxious to be relieved of a responsibility that was becoming too irksome.

01:17:40.950 --> 01:17:42.290
No doubt, no doubt, madam.

01:17:42.490 --> 01:17:43.630
And now I wish you good morning.

01:17:43.770 --> 01:17:46.510
I shall return to Brocklehurst Hall in the course of a week or two.

01:17:46.930 --> 01:17:50.110
My good friend the archdeacon will not permit me to leave him sooner.

01:17:50.550 --> 01:17:53.450
I shall send Miss Temple notice that she is to expect a new girl,

01:17:53.470 --> 01:17:56.170
so that there will be no difficulty about receiving her.

01:17:56.410 --> 01:17:57.010
Good-bye.

01:17:57.630 --> 01:17:58.870
Good-bye, Mr. Brocklehurst.

01:17:59.170 --> 01:18:01.250
Remember me to Mrs. and Miss Brocklehurst,

01:18:01.370 --> 01:18:04.610
and to Augusta and Theodore and Master Brofton Brocklehurst.

01:18:05.150 --> 01:18:06.050
I will, madam.

01:18:06.370 --> 01:18:09.110
Little girl, here is a book entitled The Child's Guide.

01:18:09.270 --> 01:18:13.370
Read it with prayer, especially that part containing an account of the

01:18:13.370 --> 01:18:18.830
awfully sudden death of Martha Gee, a naughty child addicted to falsehood and deceit.

01:18:19.430 --> 01:18:23.170
With these words, Mr. Brocklehurst put into my hand a thin pamphlet,

01:18:23.270 --> 01:18:26.570
sewn in a cover, and having wrung for his carriage, he departed.

01:18:27.530 --> 01:18:29.090
Mrs. Reed and I were left alone.

01:18:29.510 --> 01:18:30.930
Some minutes passed in silence.

01:18:31.310 --> 01:18:32.010
She was sewing.

01:18:32.150 --> 01:18:33.270
I was watching her.

01:18:33.910 --> 01:18:38.170
Mrs. Reed might be at that time some six or seven and thirty.

01:18:38.630 --> 01:18:42.930
She was a woman of robust frame, square-shouldered and strong-limbed,

01:18:43.070 --> 01:18:46.070
not tall, and, though stout, not obese.

01:18:46.650 --> 01:18:51.130
She had a somewhat large face, the under-jaw being much developed and very solid.

01:18:51.570 --> 01:18:56.250
Her brow was low, her chin large and prominent, mouth and nose sufficiently regular.

01:18:56.750 --> 01:18:59.930
Under her light eyebrows glimmered an eye devoid of roof.

01:19:00.510 --> 01:19:02.010
Her skin was dark and opaque.

01:19:02.010 --> 01:19:03.630
Her hair nearly flaxen.

01:19:03.970 --> 01:19:05.890
Her constitution was sound as a bell.

01:19:06.190 --> 01:19:07.550
Illness never came near her.

01:19:07.930 --> 01:19:09.710
She was an exact, clever manager.

01:19:10.210 --> 01:19:12.990
Her household and tenentry were thoroughly under her control.

01:19:13.510 --> 01:19:16.930
Her children only at times defied her authority and laughed it to scorn.

01:19:17.390 --> 01:19:22.090
She dressed well, and had presents and port calculated to set off handsome attire.

01:19:22.930 --> 01:19:26.730
Sitting on a low stool a few yards from her armchair, I examined her figure.

01:19:27.330 --> 01:19:28.450
I perused her features.

01:19:28.450 --> 01:19:33.130
In my hand I held the tract containing the sudden death of the liar,

01:19:33.290 --> 01:19:38.390
to which narrative my attention had been pointed as to an appropriate warning.

01:19:39.230 --> 01:19:43.330
What had just passed, what Mrs. Reid had said concerning me to Mr. Brocklehurst,

01:19:43.410 --> 01:19:48.870
the whole tenor of their conversation was recent, raw and stinging in my mind.

01:19:49.290 --> 01:19:53.210
I had felt every word as acutely as I had heard it plainly,

01:19:53.210 --> 01:19:56.630
and a passion of resentment fermented now within me.

01:19:57.310 --> 01:20:00.290
Mrs. Reid looked up from her work, her eye settled on mine,

01:20:00.350 --> 01:20:03.430
her fingers at the same time suspended their nimble movements.

01:20:04.470 --> 01:20:07.590
Go out of the room, return to the nursery was her mandate.

01:20:08.370 --> 01:20:11.090
My look or something else must have struck her as offensive,

01:20:11.490 --> 01:20:14.550
for she spoke with extreme though suppressed irritation.

01:20:15.430 --> 01:20:18.210
I got up, I went to the door, I came back again,

01:20:18.590 --> 01:20:23.070
I walked to the window, across the room, and then close up to her.

01:20:24.210 --> 01:20:29.370
Speak I must, I had been trodden on severely, and must turn, but how?

01:20:30.210 --> 01:20:33.510
What strength had I to dart retaliation at my antagonist?

01:20:34.130 --> 01:20:37.310
I gathered my energies and launched them in this blunt sentence.

01:20:38.470 --> 01:20:42.750
I am not deceitful. If I were, I should say I loved you.

01:20:43.130 --> 01:20:45.590
But I declare I do not love you.

01:20:45.850 --> 01:20:48.710
I dislike you the worst of anybody in the world except John Reid.

01:20:49.270 --> 01:20:52.650
And this book about the liar you may give to your girl Georgiana,

01:20:52.650 --> 01:20:55.250
for it is she who tells lies and not I.

01:20:56.130 --> 01:20:58.710
Mrs. Reid's hands still lay on her work inactive,

01:20:59.070 --> 01:21:01.930
her eye of ice continued to dwell freezingly on mine.

01:21:02.470 --> 01:21:04.510
What more have you to say? she asked,

01:21:04.870 --> 01:21:08.450
rather in the tone in which a person might address an opponent of adult age,

01:21:08.830 --> 01:21:11.430
than such as is you ordinarily used to a child.

01:21:12.110 --> 01:21:16.170
That eye of hers, that voice, stirred every antipathy I had,

01:21:16.690 --> 01:21:20.610
shaking from head to foot, thrilled with ungovernable excitement,

01:21:20.610 --> 01:21:23.610
I continued, I am glad you are no relation of mine.

01:21:23.670 --> 01:21:26.090
I will never call you aunt again as long as I live.

01:21:26.310 --> 01:21:28.350
I will never come to see you when I am grown up.

01:21:28.550 --> 01:21:31.710
And if anyone asks me how I liked you and how you treated me,

01:21:31.890 --> 01:21:34.190
I will say the very thought of you makes me sick,

01:21:34.430 --> 01:21:36.470
and that you treated me with miserable cruelty.

01:21:37.090 --> 01:21:39.170
How dare you affirm that, Jane Eyre?

01:21:39.490 --> 01:21:43.110
How dare I, Mrs. Reid? How dare I? Because it is the truth.

01:21:43.470 --> 01:21:47.590
You think I have no feelings, and that I can do without one bit of love or kindness.

01:21:47.590 --> 01:21:50.350
But I cannot live so, and you have no pity.

01:21:50.730 --> 01:21:55.030
I shall remember how you thrust me back, roughly and violently thrust me back into the red room,

01:21:55.310 --> 01:21:58.530
and locked me up there to my dying day, though I was in agony,

01:21:58.690 --> 01:22:02.770
though I cried out while suffocating with distress, have mercy, have mercy, aunt Reid.

01:22:03.270 --> 01:22:06.070
And that punishment you made me suffer because your wicked boy

01:22:06.070 --> 01:22:08.410
struck me, knocked me down for nothing.

01:22:08.850 --> 01:22:12.550
I will tell anybody who asks me questions this exact tale.

01:22:12.870 --> 01:22:16.370
People think you are a good woman, but you are bad, hard-hearted.

01:22:16.370 --> 01:22:18.230
You are deceitful.

01:22:19.670 --> 01:22:23.430
Ere I had finished this reply, my soul began to expand, to exalt,

01:22:23.730 --> 01:22:27.210
with the strangest sense of freedom, of triumph I had ever felt.

01:22:27.910 --> 01:22:30.910
It seemed as if an invisible bond had burst,

01:22:31.210 --> 01:22:35.310
and that I had struggled out into unhoped for liberty.

01:22:36.330 --> 01:22:39.990
Not without cause was this sentiment. Mrs. Reid looked frightened.

01:22:40.430 --> 01:22:43.690
Her work had slipped from her knee. She was lifting up her hands,

01:22:43.690 --> 01:22:47.690
rocking herself to and fro, and even twisting her face as if she would cry.

01:22:48.170 --> 01:22:51.910
Jane, you are under a mistake. What is the matter with you? Why do you tremble so violently?

01:22:52.350 --> 01:22:55.170
Would you like to drink some water? No, Mrs. Reid.

01:22:56.030 --> 01:22:59.630
Is there anything else you wish for, Jane? I assure you I desire to be your friend.

01:23:00.210 --> 01:23:04.970
Not you. You told Mr. Brocklehurst I had a bad character, a deceitful disposition,

01:23:04.970 --> 01:23:09.370
and I'll let everybody at Lowood know what you are and what you have done.

01:23:10.050 --> 01:23:13.190
Jane, you don't understand these things. Children must be corrected for their faults.

01:23:13.990 --> 01:23:18.470
Deceit is not my fault, I cried out in a savage high voice.

01:23:18.750 --> 01:23:21.350
But you are passionate, Jane. That you must allow.

01:23:21.610 --> 01:23:24.690
Now return to the nursery. There's a deer. And lie down a little.

01:23:25.050 --> 01:23:27.530
I am not your dear. I cannot lie down.

01:23:27.690 --> 01:23:30.550
Send me to school soon, Mrs. Reid, for I hate to live here.

01:23:31.330 --> 01:23:36.550
I will indeed send her to school soon, murmured Mrs. Reid, sort of voce.

01:23:37.070 --> 01:23:39.910
And gathering up her work, she abruptly quitted the apartment.

01:23:40.590 --> 01:23:43.510
I was left there alone, winner of the field.

01:23:44.230 --> 01:23:47.350
It was the hardest battle I had fought, and the first victory I had gained.

01:23:47.950 --> 01:23:52.930
I stood a while on the rug, where Mr. Brocklehurst had stood, and I enjoyed my conqueror's solitude.

01:23:53.810 --> 01:24:00.150
First I smiled to myself and felt elated, but this fierce pleasure subsided in me as fast as

01:24:00.150 --> 01:24:05.730
did the accelerated throb of my pulses. A child cannot quarrel with its elders as I had done,

01:24:05.730 --> 01:24:10.210
cannot give its furious feelings uncontrolled play as I had given mine,

01:24:10.350 --> 01:24:14.470
without experiencing afterwards the pang of remorse and the chill of reaction.

01:24:14.970 --> 01:24:18.470
A ridge of lighted heath, alive, glancing, devouring,

01:24:19.110 --> 01:24:22.890
would have been a meat emblem of my mind when I accused and menaced Mrs. Reid.

01:24:23.430 --> 01:24:26.710
The same ridge, black and blasted after the flames are dead,

01:24:27.190 --> 01:24:30.130
would have represented as meatly my subsequent condition,

01:24:30.590 --> 01:24:34.910
when a half-hour's silence and reflection had shown me the madness of my conduct,

01:24:34.910 --> 01:24:38.450
and the dreariness of my hatred and hating position.

01:24:39.710 --> 01:24:42.850
Something of vengeance I had tasted for the first time,

01:24:43.370 --> 01:24:47.610
as aromatic wine it seemed on swallowing, warm and racy.

01:24:48.910 --> 01:24:54.590
Its after-flavour, metallic and corroding, gave me a sensation as if I had been poisoned.

01:24:55.410 --> 01:24:58.610
Willingly would I now have gone and asked Mrs. Reid's pardon,

01:24:59.010 --> 01:25:02.070
but I knew, partly from experience and partly from instinct,

01:25:02.710 --> 01:25:05.830
that was the way to make her repulse me with double scorn,

01:25:06.070 --> 01:25:09.870
thereby re-exciting every turbulent impulse of my nature.

01:25:11.270 --> 01:25:14.870
I would feign exercise some better faculty than that of fierce speaking,

01:25:15.590 --> 01:25:19.970
feign fine nourishment for some less fiendish feeling than that of sombre indignation.

01:25:20.230 --> 01:25:24.670
I took a book, some Arabian tales, I sat down in an endeavour to read.

01:25:25.250 --> 01:25:26.810
I could make no sense of the subject.

01:25:27.250 --> 01:25:32.050
My own thoughts swam always between me and the page I had usually found fascinating.

01:25:32.790 --> 01:25:35.090
I opened the glass door in the breakfast room.

01:25:35.370 --> 01:25:36.570
The shrubbery was quite still.

01:25:37.090 --> 01:25:40.990
The black frost rained, unbroken by sun or breeze through the grounds.

01:25:41.830 --> 01:25:44.690
I covered my head and arms with the skirt of my frock,

01:25:44.850 --> 01:25:48.630
and went out to walk in a part of the plantation which was quite sequestered.

01:25:49.330 --> 01:25:51.750
But I found no pleasure in the silent trees,

01:25:52.230 --> 01:25:56.030
the falling fur cones, the congealed relics of autumn,

01:25:56.310 --> 01:25:59.890
russet leaves swept by past winds and heaps and now stiffened together.

01:26:00.570 --> 01:26:05.150
I leaned against a gate and looked into an empty field where no sheep were feeding,

01:26:05.330 --> 01:26:07.090
where the short grass was nipped and blanched.

01:26:08.190 --> 01:26:11.070
It was a very grey day, a most opaque sky.

01:26:11.750 --> 01:26:14.710
Onding on snow, canopied all,

01:26:15.250 --> 01:26:22.130
thence flakes fell at intervals which settled on the hard plain and on the hoary lee without melting.

01:26:22.970 --> 01:26:25.130
I stood, a wretched child enough,

01:26:25.670 --> 01:26:27.390
whispering to myself over and over again,

01:26:27.390 --> 01:26:29.430
What shall I do? What shall I do?

01:26:30.510 --> 01:26:32.430
All at once I heard a clear voice call,

01:26:32.810 --> 01:26:35.070
Miss Jane, where are you? Come to lunch.

01:26:36.070 --> 01:26:38.550
It was Bessie I knew well enough, but I did not stir.

01:26:39.150 --> 01:26:41.230
Her light step came tripping down the path.

01:26:41.710 --> 01:26:45.090
You naughty little thing, she said, why don't you come when you're called?

01:26:46.330 --> 01:26:49.810
Bessie's presence, compared with the thoughts over which I had been brooding,

01:26:49.970 --> 01:26:52.910
seemed cheerful, even though as usual she was somewhat cross.

01:26:53.610 --> 01:26:57.310
The fact is, after my conflict with and victory over Mrs. Reid,

01:26:57.370 --> 01:27:01.090
I was not disposed to care much for the nursery maid's transitory anger,

01:27:01.210 --> 01:27:05.190
and I was disposed to bask in her youthful lightness of heart.

01:27:06.010 --> 01:27:09.330
I just put my two arms round her and said, Come Bessie, don't scold.

01:27:10.450 --> 01:27:15.710
The action was more frank and fearless than any I was habituated to indulge in.

01:27:15.830 --> 01:27:17.010
Somehow it pleased her.

01:27:17.530 --> 01:27:21.950
You're a strange little child, Miss Jane, she said, as she looked down at me,

01:27:21.950 --> 01:27:26.190
a little roving solitary thing, and you're going to school, I suppose.

01:27:27.470 --> 01:27:28.350
I nodded.

01:27:28.650 --> 01:27:30.590
And won't you be sorry to leave poor Bessie?

01:27:31.410 --> 01:27:34.150
What does Bessie care for me? She's always scolding me.

01:27:34.630 --> 01:27:37.990
Because you're such a queer, frightened, shy little thing, you should be bolder.

01:27:38.470 --> 01:27:39.690
What, to get more knocks?

01:27:40.550 --> 01:27:43.290
Nonsense. But you are rather put upon, that's certain.

01:27:43.850 --> 01:27:46.090
My mother said when she came down to see me last week,

01:27:46.330 --> 01:27:49.050
she would not like a little one of her own to be in your place.

01:27:49.790 --> 01:27:51.930
Now come in, I've got some good news for you.

01:27:52.730 --> 01:27:55.070
I don't think you have, Bessie.

01:27:55.550 --> 01:27:59.130
Child, what do you mean? What sorrowful eyes you fix on me.

01:27:59.710 --> 01:28:03.630
Well, but Misses and the young ladies and Master John are going out to tea this afternoon,

01:28:03.970 --> 01:28:05.290
and you shall have tea with me.

01:28:05.630 --> 01:28:07.650
I'll ask Cook to bake you a little cake,

01:28:07.890 --> 01:28:11.470
and then you shall help me to look over your drawers, for I am soon to pack your trunk.

01:28:11.970 --> 01:28:14.430
Misses intends you to leave Gateshead in a day or two,

01:28:14.590 --> 01:28:16.910
and you shall choose what toys you like to take with you.

01:28:18.090 --> 01:28:20.790
Bessie, you must promise not to scold me any more till I go.

01:28:21.550 --> 01:28:25.430
Well, I will. But mind you're a very good girl, and don't be afraid of me.

01:28:26.090 --> 01:28:30.090
Don't start when I chance to speak rather sharply, it's so provoking.

01:28:31.110 --> 01:28:35.370
I don't think I shall ever be afraid of you again, Bessie, because I've gotten used to you,

01:28:35.490 --> 01:28:37.610
and I shall soon have another set of people to dread.

01:28:38.430 --> 01:28:40.490
If you dread them, they'll dislike you.

01:28:41.030 --> 01:28:43.770
As you do, Bessie, I doubt dislike you, Miss.

01:28:43.990 --> 01:28:46.470
I believe I'm funner of you than of all the others.

01:28:47.250 --> 01:28:49.990
You don't show it, you sharp little thing.

01:28:49.990 --> 01:28:52.390
You've got quite a new way of talking.

01:28:52.870 --> 01:28:54.990
What makes you so venturesome and hardy?

01:28:55.750 --> 01:28:57.710
Well, I shall soon be away from you, and besides,

01:28:58.490 --> 01:29:01.250
I was going to say something about what had passed between me and Mrs. Reed,

01:29:01.270 --> 01:29:04.910
but on second thoughts I considered it better to remain silent on that head.

01:29:05.990 --> 01:29:07.830
And so you're glad to leave me?

01:29:08.010 --> 01:29:10.990
Not at all, Bessie, indeed. Just now I'm rather sorry.

01:29:11.790 --> 01:29:16.410
Just now? And rather? How coolly my little lady says it.

01:29:16.410 --> 01:29:20.270
And I say now, if I were to ask you for a kiss, you wouldn't give it me.

01:29:20.310 --> 01:29:21.930
You'd say you'd rather not.

01:29:22.570 --> 01:29:24.690
I'll kiss you and welcome. Bed your head down.

01:29:25.510 --> 01:29:30.370
Bessie stooped. We mutually embraced, and I followed her into the house quite comforted.

01:29:30.670 --> 01:29:35.090
That afternoon lapsed in peace and harmony, and in the evening Bessie told me some of her

01:29:35.090 --> 01:29:38.590
most enchanting stories, and sang me some of her sweetest songs.

01:29:39.150 --> 01:29:42.670
Even for me, life had its gleams of sunshine.

01:30:01.830 --> 01:30:02.370
V.

01:30:04.210 --> 01:30:08.690
Five o'clock had hardly struck on the morning of the nineteenth of January, when Bessie

01:30:08.690 --> 01:30:12.670
brought a candle into my closet and found me already up and nearly dressed.

01:30:13.210 --> 01:30:18.990
I had risen half an hour before her entrance and had washed my face and put on my clothes

01:30:18.990 --> 01:30:23.810
by the light of a half-moon just setting, whose rays streamed through the narrow window

01:30:23.810 --> 01:30:24.590
near my crib.

01:30:25.550 --> 01:30:30.650
I was to leave Gateshead that day by a coach which passed the lodge gates at six a.m.

01:30:31.730 --> 01:30:33.590
Bessie was the only person yet risen.

01:30:33.990 --> 01:30:38.150
She had lit a fire in the nursery, where she now proceeded to make my breakfast.

01:30:38.990 --> 01:30:44.230
Few children can eat when excited with the thoughts of a journey, nor could I.

01:30:45.010 --> 01:30:49.790
Bessie, having pressed me in vain to take a few spoonfuls of the boiled milk and bread

01:30:49.790 --> 01:30:54.590
she had prepared for me, wrapped up some biscuits in a paper and put them into my bag.

01:30:55.510 --> 01:31:00.390
Then she helped me own with my police and bonnet, and wrapping herself in a shawl, she

01:31:00.390 --> 01:31:01.790
and I left the nursery.

01:31:02.650 --> 01:31:05.150
As we passed Mrs. Reed's bedroom, she said,

01:31:05.730 --> 01:31:08.150
Will you go in and bid Mrs. good-bye?

01:31:09.210 --> 01:31:14.050
No, Bessie, she came to my crib last night when you were gone down to supper, and said

01:31:14.050 --> 01:31:19.030
I need not disturb her in the morning, or my cousins either, and she told me to remember

01:31:19.030 --> 01:31:23.790
that she had always been my best friend and to speak of her and be grateful to her accordingly.

01:31:24.950 --> 01:31:26.130
What did you say, Miss?

01:31:27.130 --> 01:31:31.350
Nothing, I covered my face with the bed-clothes and turned from her to the wall.

01:31:32.090 --> 01:31:33.930
That was wrong, Miss Jane.

01:31:35.150 --> 01:31:36.370
It was quite right, Bessie.

01:31:36.710 --> 01:31:38.450
Your missus has not been my friend.

01:31:38.790 --> 01:31:40.370
She has been my foe.

01:31:41.270 --> 01:31:43.130
Oh, Miss Jane, don't say so.

01:31:44.270 --> 01:31:48.810
Good-bye to Gateshead, cried I, as we passed through the hall and went out at the front

01:31:48.810 --> 01:31:49.150
door.

01:31:50.370 --> 01:31:52.510
The moon was set, and it was very dark.

01:31:53.010 --> 01:31:57.470
Bessie carried a lantern whose light glanced on wet steps and gravel roads soddened by

01:31:57.470 --> 01:31:58.430
a recent thaw.

01:31:59.110 --> 01:32:00.950
Raw and chill was the winter morning.

01:32:01.170 --> 01:32:03.690
My teeth chattered as I hastened down the drive.

01:32:04.510 --> 01:32:06.230
There was a light in the porter's lodge.

01:32:06.590 --> 01:32:10.230
When we reached it, we found the porter's wife just kindling her fire.

01:32:10.890 --> 01:32:14.970
My trunk, which had been carried down the evening before, stood corded at the door.

01:32:15.970 --> 01:32:21.090
It wanted but a few minutes of six, and shortly after that hour had struck, the distant roll

01:32:21.090 --> 01:32:22.970
of wheels announced the coming coach.

01:32:23.460 --> 01:32:27.770
I went to the door and watched its lamps approach rapidly through the gloom.

01:32:28.830 --> 01:32:31.770
Is she going by herself? asked the porter's wife.

01:32:32.830 --> 01:32:33.210
Yes.

01:32:34.070 --> 01:32:35.910
And how far is it?

01:32:36.290 --> 01:32:37.230
Fifty miles.

01:32:38.190 --> 01:32:39.170
What a long way!

01:32:39.690 --> 01:32:42.990
I wonder Mrs. Reed is not afraid to trust her so far alone.

01:32:44.290 --> 01:32:45.650
The coach drew up.

01:32:45.930 --> 01:32:50.170
There it was at the gates with its four horses and its top laden with passengers.

01:32:50.520 --> 01:32:53.470
The guard and coachman loudly urged haste.

01:32:53.590 --> 01:32:54.970
My trunk was hoisted up.

01:32:55.310 --> 01:32:58.470
I was taken from Bessie's neck, to which I clung with kisses.

01:32:59.670 --> 01:33:04.470
Be sure and take good care of her, cried she to the guard as he lifted me to the inside.

01:33:05.810 --> 01:33:07.490
Aye, aye, was the answer.

01:33:07.830 --> 01:33:09.290
The door was slapped too.

01:33:09.490 --> 01:33:12.570
A voice exclaimed, All right, and on we drove.

01:33:13.510 --> 01:33:19.330
Thus was I severed from Bessie and Gateshead, thus whirled away to unknown and, as I then

01:33:19.330 --> 01:33:21.490
deemed, remote and mysterious regions.

01:33:22.710 --> 01:33:24.570
I remember but little of the journey.

01:33:25.030 --> 01:33:29.610
I only know that the day seemed to me of a preternatural length, and that we appeared

01:33:29.610 --> 01:33:31.890
to travel over hundreds of miles of road.

01:33:32.730 --> 01:33:37.870
We passed through several towns, and in one, a very large one, the coach stopped.

01:33:38.590 --> 01:33:42.270
The horses were taken out, and the passengers alighted to dine.

01:33:42.950 --> 01:33:48.030
I was carried into an inn where the guard wanted me to have some dinner, but as I had

01:33:48.030 --> 01:33:53.670
no appetite, he left me in an immense room with a fireplace at each end, a chandelier

01:33:53.670 --> 01:33:58.190
pendant from the ceiling, and a little red gallery high up against the wall filled with

01:33:58.190 --> 01:33:59.170
musical instruments.

01:34:00.210 --> 01:34:05.670
Here I walked about for a long time, feeling very strange, and mortally apprehensive of

01:34:05.670 --> 01:34:11.010
someone coming in and kidnapping me, for I believed in kidnappers, their exploits having

01:34:11.010 --> 01:34:13.670
frequently figured in Bessie's fireside chronicles.

01:34:14.430 --> 01:34:15.950
At last the guard returned.

01:34:16.370 --> 01:34:18.530
Once more I was stowed away in the coach.

01:34:18.910 --> 01:34:24.450
My protector mounted his own seat, sounded his hollow horn, and away we rattled over

01:34:24.450 --> 01:34:25.970
the stony street of El.

01:34:27.090 --> 01:34:30.150
The afternoon came on wet and somewhat misty.

01:34:30.510 --> 01:34:35.570
As it waned into dusk, I began to feel that we were getting very far indeed from Gateshead.

01:34:36.230 --> 01:34:37.970
We ceased to pass through towns.

01:34:38.330 --> 01:34:39.310
The country changed.

01:34:39.950 --> 01:34:42.570
Great gray hills heaved up round the horizon.

01:34:43.110 --> 01:34:49.450
As twilight deepened, we descended a valley, dark with wood, and long after night had overclouded

01:34:49.450 --> 01:34:52.870
the prospect, I heard a wild wind rushing amongst trees.

01:34:54.310 --> 01:34:56.890
Lulled by the sound, I at last dropped asleep.

01:34:57.510 --> 01:35:01.650
I had not long slumbered when the sudden cessation of motion awoke me.

01:35:02.090 --> 01:35:05.970
The coach door was open, and a person like a servant was standing at it.

01:35:06.430 --> 01:35:09.070
I saw her face in dress by the light of the lamps.

01:35:10.310 --> 01:35:13.010
Is there a little girl called Jane Eyre here?

01:35:13.370 --> 01:35:14.010
She asked.

01:35:14.790 --> 01:35:17.370
I answered yes, and was then lifted out.

01:35:17.710 --> 01:35:20.910
My trunk was handed down, and the coach instantly drove away.

01:35:22.110 --> 01:35:26.470
I was stiff with long sitting, and bewildered with the noise and motion of the coach.

01:35:27.250 --> 01:35:29.550
Gathering my faculties, I looked about me.

01:35:29.990 --> 01:35:32.450
Rain, wind, and darkness fill the air.

01:35:32.930 --> 01:35:37.190
Nevertheless, I dimly discerned a wall before me, and a door open in it.

01:35:37.190 --> 01:35:40.010
Through this door I passed with my new guide.

01:35:40.750 --> 01:35:42.690
She shut and locked it behind her.

01:35:43.570 --> 01:35:48.850
There was now visible a house or houses, for the building spread far, with many windows,

01:35:49.330 --> 01:35:50.730
and lights burning in some.

01:35:51.490 --> 01:35:55.990
We went up a broad pebbly path, splashing wet, and were admitted at a door.

01:35:56.790 --> 01:36:00.930
Then the servant led me through a passage into a room with a fire, where she left me

01:36:00.930 --> 01:36:01.290
alone.

01:36:02.750 --> 01:36:05.850
I stood and warmed my numbed fingers over the blaze.

01:36:05.850 --> 01:36:07.250
Then I looked round.

01:36:07.790 --> 01:36:13.050
There was no candle, but the uncertain light from the hearth showed, by intervals, papered

01:36:13.050 --> 01:36:16.330
walls, carpet, curtains, shining mahogany furniture.

01:36:16.770 --> 01:36:22.250
It was a parlor, not so spacious or splendid as the drawing room at Gateshead, but comfortable

01:36:22.250 --> 01:36:22.730
enough.

01:36:23.630 --> 01:36:27.850
I was puzzling to make out the subject of a picture on the wall, when the door opened,

01:36:28.010 --> 01:36:30.070
and an individual carrying a light entered.

01:36:30.610 --> 01:36:32.170
Another followed close behind.

01:36:32.910 --> 01:36:38.450
The first was a tall lady with dark hair, dark eyes, and a pale and large forehead.

01:36:39.050 --> 01:36:44.090
Her figure was partly enveloped in a shawl, her countenance was grave, her bearing erect.

01:36:45.210 --> 01:36:50.030
The child is very young to be sent alone, said she, putting her candle down on the table.

01:36:51.070 --> 01:36:54.610
She considered me attentively for a minute or two, then further added,

01:36:55.550 --> 01:36:58.390
She had better be put to bed soon, she looks tired.

01:36:58.990 --> 01:37:02.650
Are you tired? she asked, placing her hand on my shoulder.

01:37:03.670 --> 01:37:04.890
A little, ma'am.

01:37:05.590 --> 01:37:07.050
And hungry too, no doubt.

01:37:07.590 --> 01:37:10.230
Let her have some supper before she goes to bed, Miss Miller.

01:37:10.990 --> 01:37:14.750
Is this the first time you have left your parents to come to school, my little girl?

01:37:15.910 --> 01:37:18.190
I explained to her that I had no parents.

01:37:18.890 --> 01:37:24.550
She inquired how long they had been dead, then how old I was, what was my name, whether

01:37:24.550 --> 01:37:26.470
I could read, write, and sew a little.

01:37:26.470 --> 01:37:31.350
Then she touched my cheek gently with her forefinger, and saying, she hoped I should

01:37:31.350 --> 01:37:34.510
be a good child, dismissed me along with Miss Miller.

01:37:36.050 --> 01:37:38.810
The lady I had left might be about twenty-nine.

01:37:39.270 --> 01:37:41.670
The one who went with me appeared some years younger.

01:37:42.470 --> 01:37:45.450
The first impressed me by her voice, look, and air.

01:37:46.210 --> 01:37:52.430
Miss Miller was more ordinary, ruddy in complexion, though of a careworn countenance, hurried

01:37:52.430 --> 01:37:56.990
in gait and action, like one who had always a multiplicity of tasks on hand.

01:37:57.510 --> 01:38:01.630
She looked, indeed, what I afterwards found she really was, an underteacher.

01:38:02.750 --> 01:38:09.030
Led by her, I passed from compartment to compartment, from passage to passage, of a large and irregular

01:38:09.030 --> 01:38:14.570
building, till, emerging from the total and somewhat dreary silence pervading that portion

01:38:14.570 --> 01:38:20.150
of the house we had traversed, we came upon the hum of many voices, and presently entered

01:38:20.150 --> 01:38:26.450
a wide, long room, with great deal-tables, two at each end, on each of which burnt a

01:38:26.450 --> 01:38:32.670
pair of candles, and seated all round on benches a congregation of girls of every age from

01:38:32.670 --> 01:38:34.070
nine or ten to twenty.

01:38:35.110 --> 01:38:40.690
Seen by the dim light of the dips, their number to me appeared countless, though not in reality

01:38:40.690 --> 01:38:41.630
exceeding eighty.

01:38:42.190 --> 01:38:47.230
They were uniformly dressed in brown-stuff frocks of quaint fashion, and long holland

01:38:47.910 --> 01:38:48.470
pinafores.

01:38:48.470 --> 01:38:50.110
It was the hour of study.

01:38:50.470 --> 01:38:55.950
They were engaged in conning over their to-morrow's task, and the hum I had heard was the combined

01:38:55.950 --> 01:38:57.930
result of their whispered repetitions.

01:38:59.250 --> 01:39:01.950
Miss Miller signed to me to sit on a bench near the door.

01:39:02.410 --> 01:39:05.610
Then, walking up to the top of the long room, she cried out,

01:39:06.250 --> 01:39:09.030
Monitors, collect the lesson books and put them away.

01:39:10.010 --> 01:39:15.150
Four tall girls arose from different tables, and going round, gathered the books and removed

01:39:15.150 --> 01:39:15.650
them.

01:39:16.390 --> 01:39:18.830
Miss Miller again gave the word of command.

01:39:19.970 --> 01:39:21.770
Monitors, fetch the supper-trays.

01:39:23.190 --> 01:39:28.830
The tall girls went out and returned presently, each bearing a tray, with portions of something

01:39:28.830 --> 01:39:34.590
I knew not what arranged thereon, and a pitcher of water and mug in the middle of each tray.

01:39:35.710 --> 01:39:37.310
The portions were handed round.

01:39:37.850 --> 01:39:41.930
Those who liked took a draught of the water, the mug being common to all.

01:39:42.570 --> 01:39:48.590
When it came to my turn, I drank, for I was thirsty, but did not touch the food, excitement

01:39:48.590 --> 01:39:51.130
and fatigue rendering me incapable of eating.

01:39:51.830 --> 01:39:56.050
I now saw, however, that it was a thin oaten cake shaved into fragments.

01:39:57.770 --> 01:40:03.450
The meal over prayers were read by Miss Miller, and the classes filed off, two and two, upstairs.

01:40:04.590 --> 01:40:09.110
Overpowered by this time with weariness, I scarcely noticed what sort of a place the

01:40:09.110 --> 01:40:13.510
bedroom was, except that, like the schoolroom, I saw it was very long.

01:40:14.690 --> 01:40:16.970
Tonight I was to be Miss Miller's bedfellow.

01:40:17.490 --> 01:40:19.090
She helped me to undress.

01:40:19.550 --> 01:40:24.330
When laid down, I glanced at the long rows of beds, each of which was quickly filled

01:40:24.330 --> 01:40:25.590
with two occupants.

01:40:26.150 --> 01:40:31.370
In ten minutes the single light was extinguished, and amidst silence and complete darkness,

01:40:31.750 --> 01:40:32.570
I fell asleep.

01:40:33.750 --> 01:40:35.150
The night passed rapidly.

01:40:35.550 --> 01:40:37.430
I was too tired even to dream.

01:40:37.830 --> 01:40:43.690
I only once awoke to hear the wind rave in furious gusts, and the rain fall in torrents,

01:40:43.790 --> 01:40:47.310
and to be sensible that Miss Miller had taken her place by my side.

01:40:47.950 --> 01:40:51.490
When I again unclosed my eyes, a loud bell was ringing.

01:40:52.150 --> 01:40:53.770
The girls were up and dressing.

01:40:54.370 --> 01:40:58.650
Day had not yet begun to dawn, and a rushlight or two burned in the room.

01:40:59.490 --> 01:41:01.170
I too rose reluctantly.

01:41:01.550 --> 01:41:06.370
It was bitter cold, and I dressed as well as I could for shivering, and washed when

01:41:06.370 --> 01:41:11.790
there was a basin at Liberty, which did not occur soon, as there was but one basin to

01:41:11.790 --> 01:41:14.870
six girls on the stands down the middle of the room.

01:41:15.910 --> 01:41:22.350
Again the bell rang, all formed in file, two and two, and in that order descended the stairs

01:41:22.350 --> 01:41:24.910
and entered the cold and dimly lit schoolroom.

01:41:25.670 --> 01:41:27.370
Here prayers were read by Miss Miller.

01:41:28.170 --> 01:41:30.930
Afterwards she called out, Form Classes.

01:41:31.570 --> 01:41:36.770
A great tumult succeeded for some minutes, during which Miss Miller repeatedly exclaimed,

01:41:37.010 --> 01:41:38.670
Silence! and Order!

01:41:39.810 --> 01:41:45.830
When it subsided, I saw them all drawn up in four semicircles before four chairs, placed

01:41:45.830 --> 01:41:46.870
at the four tables.

01:41:47.590 --> 01:41:52.830
All held books in their hands, and a great book, like a Bible, lay on each table before

01:41:52.830 --> 01:41:53.710
the vacant seat.

01:41:54.890 --> 01:41:59.890
A pause of some seconds succeeded, filled up by the low, vague hum of numbers.

01:42:00.370 --> 01:42:04.510
Miss Miller walked from class to class, hushing this indefinite sound.

01:42:05.970 --> 01:42:07.350
A distant bell tinkled.

01:42:08.070 --> 01:42:12.250
Immediately three ladies entered the room, each walked to a table and took her seat.

01:42:13.070 --> 01:42:18.070
Miss Miller assumed the fourth vacant chair, which was that nearest the door, and around

01:42:18.070 --> 01:42:20.190
which the smallest of the children were assembled.

01:42:20.830 --> 01:42:24.830
To this inferior class I was called, and placed at the bottom of it.

01:42:25.770 --> 01:42:27.190
Business now began.

01:42:27.570 --> 01:42:29.150
The day's collect was repeated.

01:42:29.730 --> 01:42:34.470
Then certain texts of scripture were said, and to these succeeded a protracted reading

01:42:34.470 --> 01:42:37.110
of chapters in the Bible, which lasted an hour.

01:42:37.770 --> 01:42:42.130
By the time that exercise was terminated, day had fully dawned.

01:42:42.330 --> 01:42:45.350
The indefatigable bell now sounded for the fourth time.

01:42:46.170 --> 01:42:49.410
The classes were marshalled and marched into another room to breakfast.

01:42:50.110 --> 01:42:53.690
How glad I was to behold a prospect of getting something to eat!

01:42:54.210 --> 01:42:58.730
I was now nearly sick from inanition, having taken so little the day before.

01:42:59.990 --> 01:43:05.990
The refectory was a great, low-sealed, gloomy room, on two long tables smoked basins of

01:43:05.990 --> 01:43:11.070
something hot, which, however, to my dismay, sent forth an odor far from inviting.

01:43:12.010 --> 01:43:17.230
I saw a universal manifestation of discontent when the fumes of the repast met the nostrils

01:43:17.230 --> 01:43:19.130
of those destined to swallow it.

01:43:19.450 --> 01:43:24.550
From the van of the procession, the tall girls of the first class rose the whispered words,

01:43:25.290 --> 01:43:25.810
Disgusting!

01:43:26.070 --> 01:43:27.650
The porridge is burnt again.

01:43:29.190 --> 01:43:31.690
Silence! ejaculated a voice.

01:43:32.210 --> 01:43:38.070
Not that of Miss Miller, but one of the upper teachers, a little and dark personage, smartly

01:43:38.070 --> 01:43:43.350
dressed, but of somewhat morose aspect, who installed herself at the top of one table,

01:43:43.790 --> 01:43:46.350
while a more buxom lady presided at the other.

01:43:46.970 --> 01:43:50.430
I looked in vain for her I had first seen the night before.

01:43:50.810 --> 01:43:51.890
She was not visible.

01:43:52.650 --> 01:43:57.530
Miss Miller occupied the foot of the table where I sat, and a strange, foreign-looking

01:43:57.530 --> 01:44:02.730
elderly lady, the French teacher, as I afterwards found, took the corresponding seat at the

01:44:02.730 --> 01:44:03.290
other board.

01:44:04.410 --> 01:44:06.790
A long grace was said, and a hymn sung.

01:44:07.370 --> 01:44:10.990
Then a servant brought in some tea for the teachers, and the meal began.

01:44:12.590 --> 01:44:17.690
Ravenous, and now very faint, I devoured a spoonful or two of my portion without thinking

01:44:17.690 --> 01:44:18.470
of its taste.

01:44:19.130 --> 01:44:20.770
But the first edge of hunger blunted.

01:44:21.150 --> 01:44:24.130
I perceived that I had got in hand a nauseous mess.

01:44:24.690 --> 01:44:27.470
Burnt porridge is almost as bad as rotten potatoes.

01:44:28.230 --> 01:44:30.470
Famine itself soon sickens over it.

01:44:31.350 --> 01:44:32.870
The spoons were moved slowly.

01:44:33.290 --> 01:44:38.490
I saw each girl taste her food and try to swallow it, but in most cases the effort was

01:44:38.490 --> 01:44:39.510
soon relinquished.

01:44:40.090 --> 01:44:42.930
Breakfast was over, and none had breakfasted.

01:44:43.710 --> 01:44:48.970
Thanks being returned for what we had not got, and a second hymn chanted, the refectory

01:44:48.970 --> 01:44:50.750
was evacuated for the schoolroom.

01:44:51.530 --> 01:44:56.690
I was one of the last to go out, and in passing the tables I saw one teacher take a basin

01:44:56.690 --> 01:44:58.250
of the porridge and taste it.

01:44:58.810 --> 01:45:04.090
She looked at the others, all their countenances expressed displeasure, and one of them, the

01:45:04.090 --> 01:45:05.310
stout one, whispered,

01:45:05.310 --> 01:45:06.690
Abominable stuff!

01:45:07.030 --> 01:45:07.790
How shameful!

01:45:09.270 --> 01:45:14.190
A quarter of an hour passed before lessons again began, during which the schoolroom was

01:45:14.190 --> 01:45:15.410
in a glorious tumult.

01:45:16.050 --> 01:45:21.010
For that space of time it seemed to be permitted to talk loud and more freely, and they used

01:45:21.010 --> 01:45:21.670
their privilege.

01:45:22.530 --> 01:45:27.150
The whole conversation ran on the breakfast, which one and all abused roundly.

01:45:27.930 --> 01:45:28.610
Poor things!

01:45:28.730 --> 01:45:30.790
It was the sole consolation they had.

01:45:31.410 --> 01:45:34.090
Miss Miller was now the only teacher in the room.

01:45:34.710 --> 01:45:38.990
A group of great girls standing about her spoke with serious and sullen gestures.

01:45:40.110 --> 01:45:45.330
I heard the name of Mr. Brocklehurst pronounced by some lips, at which Miss Miller shook her

01:45:45.330 --> 01:45:50.630
head disapprovingly, but she made no great effort to cheek the general wrath, doubtless

01:45:50.630 --> 01:45:51.690
she shared in it.

01:45:52.930 --> 01:45:54.990
A clock in the schoolroom struck nine.

01:45:55.530 --> 01:45:59.090
Miss Miller left her circle, and standing in the middle of the room cried,

01:45:59.090 --> 01:46:00.110
Silence!

01:46:00.430 --> 01:46:01.250
To your seats!

01:46:02.270 --> 01:46:03.370
Discipline prevailed.

01:46:03.710 --> 01:46:09.110
In five minutes the confused throng was resolved into order, and comparative silence quelled

01:46:09.110 --> 01:46:10.730
the babble clamor of tongues.

01:46:11.630 --> 01:46:16.870
The upper teachers now punctually resumed their posts, but still all seemed to wait.

01:46:17.870 --> 01:46:22.510
Ranged on benches down the sides of the room, the eighty girls sat motionless and erect.

01:46:23.310 --> 01:46:28.690
Acquaint assemblage, they appeared, all with plain locks combed from their faces, not a

01:46:28.690 --> 01:46:29.430
girl visible.

01:46:30.030 --> 01:46:35.230
In brown dresses, made high and surrounded by a narrow tucker about the throat, with

01:46:35.230 --> 01:46:39.910
little pockets of holland, shaped something like a highlander's purse, tied in front of

01:46:39.910 --> 01:46:45.710
their frocks, and destined to serve the purpose of a work bag, all too wearing woollen stockings

01:46:45.710 --> 01:46:48.770
and country-made shoes, fastened with brass buckles.

01:46:49.650 --> 01:46:54.490
Above twenty of those clad in this costume were full-grown girls, or rather young women.

01:46:54.910 --> 01:46:58.810
It suited them ill, and gave an air of oddity even to the prettiest.

01:46:59.990 --> 01:47:05.730
I was still looking at them, and also at intervals examining the teachers, none of whom precisely

01:47:05.730 --> 01:47:10.750
pleased me, for the stout one was a little coarse, the dark one not a little fierce,

01:47:11.290 --> 01:47:16.910
the foreigner harsh and grotesque, and Miss Miller, poor thing, looked purple, weather-beaten,

01:47:16.950 --> 01:47:23.510
and overworked, when, as my eye wandered from face to face, the whole school rose simultaneously,

01:47:23.810 --> 01:47:25.770
as if moved by a common spring.

01:47:26.830 --> 01:47:27.750
What was the matter?

01:47:28.130 --> 01:47:29.710
I had heard no order given.

01:47:30.010 --> 01:47:31.050
I was puzzled.

01:47:31.730 --> 01:47:37.190
Ere I had gathered my wits, the classes were again seated, but as all eyes now turned to

01:47:37.190 --> 01:47:42.250
one point, mine followed the general direction, and encountered the personage who had received

01:47:42.250 --> 01:47:43.190
me last night.

01:47:43.910 --> 01:47:48.410
She stood at the bottom of the long room, on the hearth, for there was a fire at each

01:47:48.410 --> 01:47:48.710
end.

01:47:49.030 --> 01:47:53.150
She surveyed the two rows of girls silently and gravely.

01:47:53.610 --> 01:47:57.930
Miss Miller approaching seemed to ask her a question, and having received her answer,

01:47:58.070 --> 01:48:00.070
went back to her place, and said aloud,

01:48:00.910 --> 01:48:03.770
Monitor of the first class, fetch the globes.

01:48:05.050 --> 01:48:09.790
While the direction was being executed, the lady consulted moved slowly up the room.

01:48:10.690 --> 01:48:17.030
I suppose I have a considerable organ of veneration, for I retain yet the sense of admiring awe

01:48:17.030 --> 01:48:19.010
with which my eyes traced her steps.

01:48:19.910 --> 01:48:25.950
Seen now in broad daylight, she looked tall, fair, and shapely, brown eyes with a benignant

01:48:25.950 --> 01:48:31.250
light in their iris, and a fine penciling of long lashes round, relieved the whiteness

01:48:31.250 --> 01:48:32.190
of her large front.

01:48:32.930 --> 01:48:37.710
On each of her temples her hair, of a very dark brown, was clustered in round curls,

01:48:38.070 --> 01:48:43.330
according to the fashion of those times, when neither smooth bands nor long ringlets were

01:48:43.330 --> 01:48:43.850
in vogue.

01:48:44.470 --> 01:48:49.930
Her dress, also in the mode of the day, was of purple cloth, relieved by a sort of Spanish

01:48:49.930 --> 01:48:51.230
trimming of black velvet.

01:48:52.050 --> 01:48:57.170
A gold watch, watches were not so common then as now, shone at her girdle.

01:48:58.170 --> 01:49:04.210
Let the reader add, to complete the picture, refined features, a complexion, if pale, clear,

01:49:04.850 --> 01:49:10.210
and a stately air and carriage, and he will have, at least, as clearly as words can give

01:49:10.210 --> 01:49:15.750
it, a correct idea of the exterior of Miss Temple, Maria Temple, as I afterwards saw

01:49:15.750 --> 01:49:19.270
the name written in a prayer book entrusted to me to carry to church.

01:49:20.430 --> 01:49:25.810
The superintendent of Lowood, for such was this lady, having taken her seat before a

01:49:25.810 --> 01:49:30.930
pair of globes placed on one of the tables, summoned the first class round her, and commenced

01:49:30.930 --> 01:49:32.510
giving a lesson on geography.

01:49:33.230 --> 01:49:35.290
The lower classes were called by the teachers.

01:49:35.990 --> 01:49:39.750
Repetitions in history, grammar, etc. went on for an hour.

01:49:40.330 --> 01:49:45.150
Writing and arithmetic succeeded, and music lessons were given by Miss Temple to some

01:49:45.150 --> 01:49:46.210
of the elder girls.

01:49:47.030 --> 01:49:51.310
The duration of each lesson was measured by the clock, which at last struck twelve.

01:49:52.050 --> 01:49:53.450
The superintendent rose.

01:49:54.290 --> 01:49:57.270
I have a word to address to the pupils, said she.

01:49:58.450 --> 01:50:03.430
The tumult of cessation from lessons was already breaking forth, but it sank at her voice.

01:50:04.070 --> 01:50:05.030
She went on.

01:50:05.910 --> 01:50:08.610
You had this morning a breakfast which you could not eat.

01:50:09.070 --> 01:50:09.990
You must be hungry.

01:50:10.610 --> 01:50:14.150
I have ordered that a lunch of bread and cheese shall be served to all.

01:50:15.090 --> 01:50:17.410
The teachers looked at her with a sort of surprise.

01:50:18.390 --> 01:50:24.450
It is to be done on my responsibility, she added, in an explanatory tone to them, and

01:50:24.450 --> 01:50:26.230
immediately afterwards left the room.

01:50:27.490 --> 01:50:31.870
The bread and cheese was presently brought in and distributed to the high delight and

01:50:31.870 --> 01:50:33.330
refreshment of the whole school.

01:50:34.230 --> 01:50:36.490
The order was now given to the garden.

01:50:37.310 --> 01:50:43.430
Each put on a coarse straw bonnet with strings of colored calico and a cloak of gray frieze.

01:50:44.050 --> 01:50:49.010
I was similarly equipped, and following the stream I made my way into the open air.

01:50:50.190 --> 01:50:55.390
The garden was a wide enclosure, surrounded with walls so high as to exclude every glimpse

01:50:55.390 --> 01:50:56.170
of prospect.

01:50:56.170 --> 01:51:02.630
A covered veranda ran down one side, and broad walks bordered a middle space divided in discourse

01:51:02.630 --> 01:51:03.490
of little beds.

01:51:04.410 --> 01:51:09.630
These beds were assigned as gardens for the pupils to cultivate, and each bed had an owner.

01:51:10.430 --> 01:51:14.730
When full of flowers they would doubtless look pretty, but now, at the latter end of

01:51:14.730 --> 01:51:17.990
January, all was wintry blight and brown decay.

01:51:18.870 --> 01:51:21.310
I shuddered as I stood and looked round me.

01:51:21.310 --> 01:51:27.810
It was an inclement day for outdoor exercise, not positively rainy, but darkened by a drizzling

01:51:27.810 --> 01:51:32.570
yellow fog, all underfoot was still soaking wet with the floods of yesterday.

01:51:33.870 --> 01:51:39.550
The stronger among the girls ran about and engaged in active games, but sundry pale and

01:51:39.550 --> 01:51:44.470
thin ones herded together for shelter and warmth in the veranda, and amongst these,

01:51:44.610 --> 01:51:49.550
as the dense mist penetrated to their shivering frames, I heard frequently the sound of a

01:51:49.550 --> 01:51:50.230
hollow cough.

01:51:51.250 --> 01:51:56.210
As yet I had spoken to no one, nor did anybody seem to take notice of me.

01:51:57.010 --> 01:52:01.790
I stood lonely enough, but to that feeling of isolation I was accustomed.

01:52:02.050 --> 01:52:03.550
It did not oppress me much.

01:52:04.390 --> 01:52:09.450
I leant against a pillar of the veranda, drew my gray mantle close about me, and, trying

01:52:09.450 --> 01:52:14.290
to forget the cold which nipped me without, and the unsatisfied hunger which gnawed me

01:52:14.290 --> 01:52:18.310
within, delivered myself up to the employment of watching and thinking.

01:52:19.050 --> 01:52:23.050
My reflections were too undefined and fragmentary to merit record.

01:52:23.730 --> 01:52:25.790
I hardly yet knew where I was.

01:52:26.270 --> 01:52:30.470
Gateshead and my past life seemed floated away to an immeasurable distance.

01:52:31.090 --> 01:52:35.650
The present was vague and strange, and of the future I could form no conjecture.

01:52:36.410 --> 01:52:39.990
I looked round the convent-like garden, and then up at the house.

01:52:40.390 --> 01:52:45.130
A large building, half of which seemed gray and old, the other half quite new.

01:52:45.950 --> 01:52:50.970
The new part, containing the schoolroom and dormitory, was lit by mullioned and lattice

01:52:50.970 --> 01:52:53.710
windows which gave it a church-like aspect.

01:52:54.390 --> 01:52:57.110
A stone tablet over the door bore this inscription.

01:52:58.590 --> 01:52:59.790
Lowood Institution.

01:53:00.390 --> 01:53:06.650
This portion was rebuilt A.D. blank by Naomi Brocklehurst of Brocklehurst Hall in this county.

01:53:07.790 --> 01:53:12.470
Let your light so shine before men that they may see your good works and glorify your Father

01:53:12.470 --> 01:53:13.430
which is in heaven.

01:53:13.950 --> 01:53:15.670
St. Matthew, verse 16.

01:53:16.750 --> 01:53:19.010
I read these words over and over again.

01:53:19.210 --> 01:53:24.350
I felt that an explanation belonged to them, and was unable fully to penetrate their import.

01:53:25.350 --> 01:53:30.470
I was still pondering the signification of Institution, and endeavoring to make out a

01:53:30.470 --> 01:53:34.730
connection between the first words and the verse of Scripture, when the sound of a cough

01:53:34.730 --> 01:53:37.010
close behind me made me turn my head.

01:53:37.710 --> 01:53:40.170
I saw a girl sitting on a stone bench near.

01:53:40.470 --> 01:53:44.630
She was bent over a book, on the perusal of which she seemed intent.

01:53:45.330 --> 01:53:47.270
From where I stood I could see the title.

01:53:48.130 --> 01:53:53.430
It was Rassilus, a name that struck me as strange and consequently attractive.

01:53:54.310 --> 01:53:57.950
In turning a leaf she happened to look up, and I said to her directly,

01:53:58.530 --> 01:53:59.710
Is your book interesting?

01:54:00.270 --> 01:54:04.230
I had already formed the intention of asking her to lend it to me some day.

01:54:04.990 --> 01:54:10.730
I like it, she answered, after a pause of a second or two, during which she examined me.

01:54:11.510 --> 01:54:12.530
What is it about?

01:54:12.790 --> 01:54:13.610
I continued.

01:54:14.430 --> 01:54:18.810
I hardly know where I found the hardyhood thus to open a conversation with a stranger.

01:54:19.430 --> 01:54:24.350
The step was contrary to my nature and habits, but I think her occupation touched a chord

01:54:24.350 --> 01:54:25.410
of sympathy somewhere.

01:54:25.910 --> 01:54:29.890
For I too liked reading, though of a frivolous and childish kind.

01:54:30.220 --> 01:54:34.090
I could not digest or comprehend the serious or substantial.

01:54:35.410 --> 01:54:38.710
You may look at it, replied the girl, offering me the book.

01:54:39.830 --> 01:54:40.730
I did so.

01:54:41.190 --> 01:54:45.390
A brief examination convinced me that the contents were less taking than the title.

01:54:46.090 --> 01:54:48.550
Rassilus looked dull to my trifling taste.

01:54:49.370 --> 01:54:52.390
I saw nothing about fairies, nothing about genii.

01:54:53.090 --> 01:54:56.790
No bright variety seemed spread over the closely printed pages.

01:54:57.370 --> 01:54:58.670
I returned it to her.

01:54:58.670 --> 01:55:04.050
She received it quietly, and without saying anything she was about to relapse into her

01:55:04.050 --> 01:55:05.210
former studious mood.

01:55:05.970 --> 01:55:08.090
Again I ventured to disturb her.

01:55:08.730 --> 01:55:11.750
Can you tell me what the writing on that stone over the door means?

01:55:12.230 --> 01:55:13.910
What is Lowood Institution?

01:55:15.150 --> 01:55:17.230
This house where you are come to live.

01:55:18.250 --> 01:55:19.910
And why do they call it Institution?

01:55:20.450 --> 01:55:22.770
Is it in any way different from other schools?

01:55:23.770 --> 01:55:25.770
It is partly a charity school.

01:55:25.770 --> 01:55:29.530
You and I, and all the rest of us, are charity children.

01:55:30.290 --> 01:55:31.790
I suppose you are an orphan.

01:55:32.110 --> 01:55:34.250
Are not either your father or your mother dead?

01:55:35.410 --> 01:55:37.170
Both died before I can remember.

01:55:38.330 --> 01:55:41.490
Well, all the girls here have lost either one or both parents.

01:55:41.830 --> 01:55:44.970
And this is called an Institution for educating orphans.

01:55:46.050 --> 01:55:47.190
Do we pay no money?

01:55:47.350 --> 01:55:48.450
Do they keep us for nothing?

01:55:49.610 --> 01:55:53.530
We pay, or our friends pay, fifteen pounds a year for each.

01:55:54.110 --> 01:55:56.630
Then why do they call us charity children?

01:55:57.770 --> 01:56:00.790
Because fifteen pounds is not enough for board and teaching,

01:56:01.010 --> 01:56:03.370
and the deficiency is supplied by subscription.

01:56:04.590 --> 01:56:05.730
Who subscribes?

01:56:06.550 --> 01:56:10.630
Different benevolent-minded ladies and gentlemen in this neighborhood and in London.

01:56:11.710 --> 01:56:13.250
Who is Naomi Brocklehurst?

01:56:14.270 --> 01:56:17.770
The lady who built the new part of this house, as that tablet records,

01:56:18.170 --> 01:56:21.070
and whose son overlooks and directs everything here.

01:56:21.850 --> 01:56:22.410
Why?

01:56:23.090 --> 01:56:26.350
Because he is treasurer and manager of the establishment.

01:56:27.590 --> 01:56:30.870
Then this house does not belong to that tall lady who wears a watch

01:56:30.870 --> 01:56:33.290
and who said we were to have some bread and cheese?

01:56:34.270 --> 01:56:34.950
To Miss Temple?

01:56:35.330 --> 01:56:36.890
Oh, no, I wish it did.

01:56:37.250 --> 01:56:40.190
She has to answer to Mr. Brocklehurst for all she does.

01:56:40.970 --> 01:56:44.150
Mr. Brocklehurst buys all our food and all our clothes.

01:56:45.310 --> 01:56:46.350
Does he live here?

01:56:47.270 --> 01:56:49.710
No, two miles off at a large hall.

01:56:50.670 --> 01:56:51.930
Is he a good man?

01:56:52.590 --> 01:56:56.050
He is a clergyman and is said to do a great deal of good.

01:56:57.110 --> 01:56:59.430
Did you say that tall lady was called Miss Temple?

01:57:00.710 --> 01:57:01.170
Yes.

01:57:01.750 --> 01:57:03.430
And what are the other teachers called?

01:57:04.690 --> 01:57:06.850
The one with red cheeks is called Miss Smith.

01:57:07.210 --> 01:57:09.490
She attends to the work and cuts out,

01:57:09.850 --> 01:57:13.350
for we make our own clothes, our frocks and polices, and everything.

01:57:14.170 --> 01:57:16.350
The little one with black hair is Miss Gatchard.

01:57:16.850 --> 01:57:20.970
She teaches history and grammar, and hears the second class repetitions.

01:57:20.970 --> 01:57:24.170
And the one who wears a shawl and has a pocket handkerchief

01:57:24.170 --> 01:57:27.510
tied to her side with a yellow ribbon is Madame Pierrot.

01:57:28.230 --> 01:57:31.150
She comes from Lille in France and teaches French.

01:57:32.210 --> 01:57:33.310
Do you like the teachers?

01:57:34.530 --> 01:57:35.170
Well, enough.

01:57:36.210 --> 01:57:38.750
Do you like the little black one and the madame?

01:57:38.990 --> 01:57:40.770
I cannot pronounce her name as you do.

01:57:42.190 --> 01:57:43.450
Miss Gatchard is hasty.

01:57:43.570 --> 01:57:45.730
You must take care not to offend her.

01:57:46.030 --> 01:57:48.190
Madame Pierrot is not a bad sort of person.

01:57:49.150 --> 01:57:51.610
But Miss Temple is the best, isn't she?

01:57:52.910 --> 01:57:55.170
Miss Temple is very good and very clever.

01:57:55.430 --> 01:57:58.810
She is above the rest because she knows far more than they do.

01:58:00.190 --> 01:58:01.310
Have you been long here?

01:58:02.050 --> 01:58:03.010
Two years.

01:58:04.210 --> 01:58:04.930
Are you an orphan?

01:58:06.050 --> 01:58:07.110
My mother is dead.

01:58:08.210 --> 01:58:09.290
Are you happy here?

01:58:10.430 --> 01:58:12.170
You ask rather too many questions.

01:58:12.410 --> 01:58:14.350
I have given you answers enough for the present.

01:58:14.810 --> 01:58:16.070
Now I want to read.

01:58:16.950 --> 01:58:19.650
But at that moment the summons sounded for dinner.

01:58:19.970 --> 01:58:21.270
All re-entered the house.

01:58:21.970 --> 01:58:25.470
The odor which now filled the refectory was scarcely more appetizing

01:58:25.470 --> 01:58:27.910
than that which had regaled our nostrils at breakfast.

01:58:28.570 --> 01:58:31.610
The dinner was served in two huge ten-plated vessels

01:58:31.610 --> 01:58:34.810
whence rose a strong steam redolent of rancid fat.

01:58:35.590 --> 01:58:38.470
I found the mess to consist of indifferent potatoes

01:58:38.470 --> 01:58:42.310
and strange shreds of rusty meat mixed and cooked together.

01:58:42.950 --> 01:58:47.390
Of this preparation a tolerably abundant plateful was apportioned to each pupil.

01:58:48.330 --> 01:58:50.850
I ate what I could and wondered within myself

01:58:50.850 --> 01:58:53.410
whether every day's fare would be like this.

01:58:54.530 --> 01:58:57.250
After dinner we immediately adjourned to the schoolroom.

01:58:57.750 --> 01:59:00.570
Lessons recommenced and were continued till five o'clock.

01:59:01.770 --> 01:59:04.010
The only marked event of the afternoon was

01:59:04.010 --> 01:59:07.070
that I saw the girl with whom I had conversed in the veranda

01:59:07.070 --> 01:59:10.470
dismissed in disgrace by Miss Gatchard from a history class

01:59:10.470 --> 01:59:13.690
and sent to stand in the middle of the large schoolroom.

01:59:14.410 --> 01:59:17.670
The punishment seemed to me in a high degree ignominious,

01:59:18.010 --> 01:59:19.630
especially for so great a girl.

01:59:20.190 --> 01:59:21.750
She looked thirteen or upwards.

01:59:22.570 --> 01:59:25.990
I expected she would show signs of great distress and shame,

01:59:26.470 --> 01:59:29.590
but to my surprise she neither wept nor blushed.

01:59:29.790 --> 01:59:34.170
Composed, though grave, she stood, the central mark of all eyes.

01:59:34.850 --> 01:59:39.350
But how can she bear it so quietly, so firmly, I asked of myself?

01:59:39.910 --> 01:59:45.030
Were I in her place, it seems to me I should wish the earth to open and swallow me up.

01:59:45.410 --> 01:59:48.430
She looks as if she were thinking of something beyond her punishment,

01:59:48.870 --> 01:59:52.990
beyond her situation, of something not round her nor before her.

01:59:53.390 --> 01:59:55.030
I have heard of daydreams.

01:59:55.030 --> 01:59:56.530
Is she in a daydream now?

01:59:57.230 --> 02:00:01.230
Her eyes are fixed on the floor, but I am sure they do not see it.

02:00:01.530 --> 02:00:04.710
Her sight seems turned in, gone down into her heart.

02:00:05.270 --> 02:00:07.690
She is looking at what she can remember, I believe,

02:00:07.690 --> 02:00:09.450
not at what is really present.

02:00:10.170 --> 02:00:13.510
I wonder what sort of a girl she is, whether good or naughty.

02:00:14.930 --> 02:00:17.670
Soon after five p.m., we had another meal,

02:00:18.010 --> 02:00:21.670
consisting of a small mug of coffee and half a slice of brown bread.

02:00:22.410 --> 02:00:25.410
I devoured my bread and drank my coffee with relish,

02:00:25.610 --> 02:00:27.970
but I should have been glad of as much more.

02:00:28.070 --> 02:00:29.370
I was still hungry.

02:00:30.070 --> 02:00:32.930
Half an hour's recreation succeeded, then study,

02:00:33.490 --> 02:00:36.990
then the glass of water and the piece of oat cake, prayers, and bed.

02:00:37.690 --> 02:00:39.790
Such was my first day at Lowood.

02:01:06.050 --> 02:01:08.850
CHAPTER VI

02:01:09.930 --> 02:01:21.290
The next day commenced as before, getting up and dressing by rush-light, but this morning we were obliged to dispense with the ceremony of washing, the water in the pitchers was frozen.

02:01:22.310 --> 02:01:36.930
A change had taken place in the weather the preceding evening, and a keen northeast wind, whistling through the crevices of our bedroom windows all night long, had made us shiver in our beds, and turned the contents of the ewers to ice.

02:01:36.930 --> 02:01:52.290
Before the long hour and a half of prayers and Bible reading was over, I felt ready to perish with the cold. Breakfast time came at last, and this morning the porridge was not burnt. The quality was eatable, the quantity small.

02:01:52.290 --> 02:01:57.370
How small my portion seemed! I wished it had been doubled.

02:01:58.850 --> 02:02:13.030
In the course of the day I was enrolled a member of the fourth class, and regular tasks and occupations were assigned me. Hitherto I had only been a spectator of the proceedings at Lowood. I was now to become an actor therein.

02:02:13.030 --> 02:02:40.850
At first, being little accustomed to learn by heart, the lessons appeared to me both long and difficult. The frequent change from task to task, too, bewildered me, and I was glad when about three o'clock in the afternoon Miss Smith put into my hands a border of muslin two yards long, together with needle, thimble, etc., and sent me to sit in a quiet corner of the schoolroom, with directions to hem the same.

02:02:40.850 --> 02:03:00.790
At that hour most of the others were sewing likewise, but one class still stood round Miss Scatchard's chair reading, and as all was quiet the subject of their lessons could be heard, together with the manner in which each girl acquitted herself, and the animate versions or commendations of Miss Scatchard on the performance.

02:03:00.790 --> 02:03:19.550
It was English history. Among the readers I observed my acquaintance of the veranda. At the commencement of the lesson her place had been at the top of the class, but for some error of pronunciation or some inattention to stops, she was suddenly sent to the very bottom.

02:03:19.550 --> 02:03:29.790
Even in that obscure position Miss Scatchard continued to make her an object of constant notice. She was continually addressing to her such phrases as the following.

02:03:31.070 --> 02:03:48.930
Burns, such it seems was her name. The girls here were all called by their surnames as boys are elsewhere. Burns, you are standing on the side of your shoe. Turn your shoes out immediately. Burns, you poke your chin most unpleasantly. Draw it in.

02:03:49.630 --> 02:03:57.390
Burns, I insist on your holding your head up. I will not have you before me in that attitude, etc., etc.

02:03:58.370 --> 02:04:14.470
A chapter having been read through twice, the books were closed and the girls examined. The lesson had comprised part of the reign of Charles I, and there were sundry questions about tonnage and poundage and ship money, which most of them appeared unable to answer.

02:04:14.470 --> 02:04:33.650
Still, every little difficulty was solved instantly when it reached Burns. Her memory seemed to have retained the substance of the whole lesson, and she was ready with answers on every point. I kept expecting that Miss Scatchard would praise her attention, but instead of that she suddenly cried out,

02:04:33.650 --> 02:04:53.970
You dirty disagreeable girl, you have never cleaned your nails this morning. Burns made no answer. I wondered at her silence. Why, thought I, does she not explain that she could neither clean her nails nor wash her face as the water was frozen?

02:04:54.870 --> 02:05:13.410
My attention was now called off by Miss Smith desiring me to hold a skein of thread. While she was winding it she talked to me from time to time, asking whether I had ever been at school before, whether I could mark, stitch, knit, etc. Till she dismissed me I could not pursue my observations on Miss Scatchard's movements.

02:05:13.410 --> 02:05:30.750
When I returned to my seat that lady was just delivering an order of which I did not catch the import. But Burns immediately left the class, and going into the small inner room where the books were kept, returned in half a minute, carrying in her hand a bundle of twigs tied together at one end.

02:05:30.750 --> 02:05:47.170
This ominous tool she presented to Miss Scatchard with a respectful curtsy. Then she quietly and without being told, unloosed her pinafore, and the teacher instantly and sharply inflicted on her neck a dozen strokes with a bunch of twigs.

02:05:47.170 --> 02:06:04.030
Not a tear rose to Burns' eye. And while I paused from my sewing, because my fingers quivered at this spectacle with a sentiment of unavailing and impotent anger, not a feature of her pensive face altered its ordinary expression.

02:06:05.070 --> 02:06:13.010
Hardened girl! exclaimed Miss Scatchard. Nothing can correct you of your slatternly habits. Carry the rod away.

02:06:14.770 --> 02:06:26.590
Burns obeyed. I looked at her narrowly as she emerged from the book closet. She was just putting back her handkerchief into her pocket, and the trace of a tear glistened on her thin cheek.

02:06:27.430 --> 02:06:40.490
The play hour in the evening I thought the pleasantest fraction of the day at Lowood. The bit of bread, the draught of coffee swallowed at five o'clock, had revived vitality, if it had not satisfied hunger.

02:06:41.570 --> 02:06:55.050
The long restraint of the day was slackened. The schoolroom felt warmer then in the morning, its fires being allowed to burn a little more brightly to supply in some measure the place of candles not yet introduced.

02:06:55.050 --> 02:07:02.510
The ruddy gloaming, the licensed uproar, the confusion of many voices gave one a welcome sense of liberty.

02:07:04.830 --> 02:07:17.310
On the evening of the day which I had seen Miss Scatchard flog her pupil, Burns, I wandered as usual among the forms and tables and laughing groups without a companion, yet not feeling lonely.

02:07:17.310 --> 02:07:36.850
When I passed the windows I now and then lifted a blind and looked out. It snowed fast, a drift was already forming against the lower panes. Putting my ear close to the window I could distinguish from the gleeful tumult within the disconsolate moan of the wind outside.

02:07:38.590 --> 02:07:49.610
Probably if I had lately left a good home and kind parents, this would have been the hour when I should most keenly have regretted the separation. That wind would then have saddened my heart.

02:07:49.610 --> 02:08:06.610
This obscure chaos would have disturbed my peace. As it was, I derived from both a strange excitement and reckless and feverish, I wished the wind to howl more wildly, the gloom to deepen to darkness and the confusion to rise to clamor.

02:08:07.850 --> 02:08:26.350
Jumping over forms and creeping under tables, I made my way to one of the fireplaces. There, kneeling by the high wire fender, I found Burns, absorbed, silent, abstracted from all around her by the companionship of a book, which she read by the dim glare of the embers.

02:08:28.930 --> 02:08:51.190
Is it still Ras Las? I asked, coming behind her. Yes, she said, and I have just finished it. And in five minutes more she shut it up. I was glad of this. Now, thought I, I can perhaps get her to talk. I sat down by her on the floor.

02:08:52.530 --> 02:09:11.890
What is your name besides Burns? Helen? Do you come a long way from here? I come from a place farther north, quite on the borders of Scotland. Will you ever go back? I hope so, but nobody can be sure of the future.

02:09:12.850 --> 02:09:28.810
You must wish to leave Lowood. No, why should I? I was sent to Lowood to get an education, and it would be of no use going away until I have attained that object. But that teacher, Miss Scatchard, is so cruel to you.

02:09:30.450 --> 02:09:46.910
Cruel? Not at all. She is severe. She dislikes my faults. And if I were in your place I should dislike her. I should resist her. If she struck me with that rod I should get it from her hand. I should break it under her nose.

02:09:49.110 --> 02:10:13.310
Probably you would do nothing of the sort, but if you did Mr. Brocklehurst would expel you from the school. That would be a great grief to your relations. It is far better to endure patiently a smart, which nobody feels but yourself, than to commit a hasty action whose evil consequences will extend to all connected with you. And besides, the Bible bids us return good for evil.

02:10:15.250 --> 02:10:38.650
But then it seems disgraceful to be flogged and to be sent to stand in the middle of a room full of people. And you are such a great girl. I am far younger than you and I could not bear it. Yet it would be your duty to bear it, if you could not avoid it. It is weak and silly to say you cannot bear what it is your fate to be required to bear.

02:10:39.550 --> 02:11:06.830
I heard her with wonder. I could not comprehend this doctrine of endurance. And still less I could understand or sympathize with the forbearance she expressed for her chastiser. Still I felt that Helen Burns considered things by a light invisible to my eyes. I suspected she might be right and I wrong. But I would not ponder the matter deeply. Like Felix I put it off to a more convenient season.

02:11:08.930 --> 02:11:14.410
You say you have faults, Helen. What are they? To me you seem very good.

02:11:15.890 --> 02:11:40.110
Then learn from me not to judge by appearances. I am, as Miss Gatchard said, slatternly. I seldom put and never keep things in order. I am careless. I forget rules. I read when I should learn my lessons. I have no method. And sometimes I say, like you, I cannot bear to be subjected to systematic arrangements.

02:11:40.110 --> 02:11:54.830
This is all very provoking to Miss Gatchard, who is naturally neat, punctual and particular. And cross and cruel, I added. But Helen Burns would not admit my addition. She kept silence.

02:11:56.150 --> 02:12:05.670
Is Miss Temple as severe to you as Miss Gatchard? At the utterance of Miss Temple's name, a soft smile flitted over her gray face.

02:12:06.810 --> 02:12:21.850
Miss Temple is full of goodness. It pains her to be severe to anyone, even the worst in the school. She sees my errors and tells me of them gently. And if I do anything worthy of praise, she gives me my mead liberally.

02:12:21.850 --> 02:12:41.030
One strong proof of my wretchedly defective nature is that even her expostulations, so mild, so rational, have not influenced to cure me of my faults. And even her praise, though I value it most highly, cannot stimulate me to continued care and foresight.

02:12:43.170 --> 02:12:48.770
That is curious, said I. It is so easy to be careful.

02:12:50.290 --> 02:13:03.170
For you I have no doubt it is. I observed you in your class this morning and saw you were closely attentive. Your thoughts never seemed to wander, while Miss Miller explained the lesson and questioned you.

02:13:03.770 --> 02:13:16.610
Now mine continually rove away when I should be listening to Miss Gatchard and collecting all she says with assiduity. Often I lose the very sound of her voice. I fall into a sort of dream.

02:13:17.410 --> 02:13:37.290
Sometimes I think I am in Northumberland and that the noises I hear around me are the bubbling of a little brook which runs through deep den near our house. Then, when it comes to my turn to reply, I have to be awakened. And having heard nothing of what was read for listening to the visionary brook, I have no answer ready.

02:13:39.310 --> 02:13:41.970
Yet how well you replied this afternoon.

02:13:41.970 --> 02:14:08.190
It was mere chance. The subject on which we had been reading had interested me. This afternoon, instead of dreaming of deep den, I was wondering how a man who wished to do right could act so unjustly and unwisely as Charles I sometimes did. And I thought, what a pity it was that, with his integrity and conscientiousness, he could see no farther than the prerogatives of the crown.

02:14:08.790 --> 02:14:30.350
If he had but been able to look at a distance and see how what they call the spirit of the age was tending. Still, I like Charles. I respect him. I pity him. Poor murdered king. Yet his enemies were the worst. They shed blood they had no right to shed. How dared they kill him.

02:14:31.670 --> 02:14:43.170
Helen was talking to herself now. She had forgotten I could not very well understand her, that I was ignorant, or nearly so, of the subject she discussed. I recalled her to my level.

02:14:43.170 --> 02:14:47.530
And when Miss Temple teaches you, do your thoughts wander then?

02:14:48.890 --> 02:15:03.470
No, certainly not often, because Miss Temple has generally something to say which is newer than my own reflections. Her language is singularly agreeable to me, and the information she communicates is often just what I wished to gain.

02:15:05.370 --> 02:15:07.670
Well then, with Miss Temple you are good?

02:15:08.650 --> 02:15:16.430
Yes, in a passive way. I make no effort. I follow as inclination guides me. There is no merit in such goodness.

02:15:17.930 --> 02:15:36.510
A great deal. You are good to those who are good to you. It is all I ever desire to be. If people were always kind and obedient to those who are cruel and unjust, the wicked people would have it all their own way. They would never feel afraid, and so they would never alter, but would grow worse and worse.

02:15:36.510 --> 02:15:47.750
When we are struck at without a reason, we should strike back again very hard. I am sure we should, so hard as to teach the person who struck us never to do it again.

02:15:49.690 --> 02:15:55.570
You will change your mind, I hope, when you grow older. As yet, you are but a little untaught girl.

02:15:55.570 --> 02:16:14.930
But I feel this, Helen. I must dislike those who, whatever I do to please them, persist in disliking me. I must resist those who punish me unjustly. It is as natural as that I should love those who show me affection, or submit to punishment when I feel it is deserved.

02:16:16.630 --> 02:16:36.030
Heathens and savage tribes hold that doctrine, but Christians and civilized nations disown it. How? I don't understand. It is not violence that best overcomes hate, nor vengeance that most certainly heals injury. What then?

02:16:36.710 --> 02:16:57.150
Read the New Testament and observe what Christ says and how he acts. Make his word your rule and his conduct your example. What does he say? Love your enemies. Bless them that curse you. Do good to them that hate you and despitefully use you.

02:16:57.150 --> 02:17:05.510
Then I should love Mrs. Read? Which I cannot do. I should bless her son John, which is impossible.

02:17:07.850 --> 02:17:22.450
In her turn, Helen Burns asked me to explain, and I proceeded forthwith to pour out, in my own way, the tale of my sufferings and resentments. Bitter and truculent when excited, I spoke as I felt, without reserve or softening.

02:17:23.610 --> 02:17:29.890
Helen heard me patiently to the end. I expected she would then make a remark, but she said nothing.

02:17:31.410 --> 02:17:36.950
Well, I asked impatiently, is not Mrs. Read a hard-hearted bad woman?

02:17:38.610 --> 02:17:55.470
She has been unkind to you, no doubt, because you see she dislikes your cast of character, as Miss Gatcher does mine. But how minutely you remember all she has done and said to you! What a singularly deep impression her injustice seems to have made on your heart!

02:17:55.470 --> 02:18:06.190
No illusage so brands its record on my feelings. Would you not be happier if you tried to forget her severity, together with the passionate emotions it excited?

02:18:06.190 --> 02:18:25.550
Life appears to me too short to be spent in nursing animosity or registering wrongs. We are and must be, one and all, burdened with faults in this world. But the time will soon come when, I trust, we shall put them off in putting off our corruptible bodies.

02:18:25.550 --> 02:18:41.170
When debasement and sin will fall from us with this cumbrous frame of flesh, and only the spark of the spirit will remain. The impalpable principle of light and thought, pure as when it left the Creator to inspire the Creator.

02:18:41.870 --> 02:19:00.390
Whence it came, it will return, perhaps again to be communicated to some being higher than man, perhaps to pass through gradations of glory from the pale human soul to brighten to the seraph. Surely it will never, on the contrary, be suffered to degenerate from man to fiend?

02:19:00.390 --> 02:19:19.210
No, I cannot believe that. I hold another creed, which no one ever taught me and which I seldom mention, but in which I delight and to which I cling, for it extends hope to all. It makes eternity a rest, a mighty home, not a terror and an abyss.

02:19:19.210 --> 02:19:43.570
Besides, with this creed I can so clearly distinguish between the criminal and his crime. I can so sincerely forgive the first while I abhor the last. With this creed revenge never worries my heart. The degradation never too deeply disgusts me. Injustice never crushes me too low. I live in calm, looking to the end.

02:19:44.910 --> 02:20:05.850
Helen's head, always drooping, sank a little lower as she finished this sentence. I saw by her look she wished no longer to talk to me, but rather to converse with her own thoughts. She was not allowed much time for meditation. A monitor, a great rough girl, presently came up, exclaiming in a strong Cumberland accent.

02:20:06.690 --> 02:20:14.650
Helen burns. If you don't go and put your drawer in order and fold up your work this minute, I'll tell Miss Getcher to come and look at it.

02:20:16.270 --> 02:20:23.130
Helen sighed as her reverie fled, and getting up, obeyed the monitor without reply, as without delay.

02:20:35.850 --> 02:20:36.470
.

02:20:57.070 --> 02:21:01.930
CHAPTER VII My first quarter at Lowood seemed an age,

02:21:02.250 --> 02:21:03.970
and not the Golden Age, either.

02:21:04.310 --> 02:21:07.290
It comprised an irksome struggle with difficulties

02:21:07.290 --> 02:21:10.410
in habituating myself to new rules and unwanted tasks.

02:21:11.430 --> 02:21:13.250
The fear of failure in these points

02:21:13.250 --> 02:21:16.250
harassed me worse than the physical hardships of my lot,

02:21:16.810 --> 02:21:18.270
though these were no trifles.

02:21:19.690 --> 02:21:24.370
During January, February, and part of March, the deep snows,

02:21:24.770 --> 02:21:27.630
and after the melting, the almost impassable roads

02:21:27.630 --> 02:21:30.370
prevented our stirring beyond the garden walls,

02:21:30.950 --> 02:21:32.210
except to go to church.

02:21:33.010 --> 02:21:36.310
But within these limits, we had to pass an hour every day

02:21:36.310 --> 02:21:37.370
in the open air.

02:21:37.950 --> 02:21:40.430
Our clothing was insufficient to protect us

02:21:40.430 --> 02:21:41.370
from the severe cold.

02:21:42.090 --> 02:21:43.150
We had no boots.

02:21:43.790 --> 02:21:46.250
The snow got into our shoes and melted there.

02:21:47.210 --> 02:21:50.490
Our ungloved hands became numbed and covered with chilglains,

02:21:51.350 --> 02:21:52.550
as were our feet.

02:21:53.630 --> 02:21:56.050
I remember well the distracting irritation

02:21:56.050 --> 02:21:58.190
I endured from this cause every evening,

02:21:58.710 --> 02:22:01.490
when my feet inflamed and the torture of thrusting

02:22:01.490 --> 02:22:05.270
the swelled, raw, and stiff toes into my shoes in the morning.

02:22:06.290 --> 02:22:09.070
Then the scanty supply of food was distressing.

02:22:09.970 --> 02:22:12.130
With a keen appetite of growing children,

02:22:12.610 --> 02:22:15.810
we had scarcely sufficient to keep alive a delicate invalid.

02:22:16.810 --> 02:22:18.630
From this deficiency of nourishment

02:22:18.630 --> 02:22:22.310
resulted in abuse, which pressed hardly on the younger pupils.

02:22:23.130 --> 02:22:25.950
Whenever the famished great girls had an opportunity,

02:22:26.350 --> 02:22:28.310
they would coax or menace the little ones out

02:22:28.310 --> 02:22:28.930
of their portion.

02:22:29.970 --> 02:22:33.290
Many a time I have shared between two claimants

02:22:33.290 --> 02:22:36.830
the precious morsel of brown bread distributed at teatime.

02:22:37.110 --> 02:22:40.610
And after relinquishing to a third half the contents

02:22:40.610 --> 02:22:43.330
of a mug of coffee, I have swallowed the remainder

02:22:43.330 --> 02:22:46.390
with an accompaniment of secret tears, forced for me

02:22:46.390 --> 02:22:48.050
by the exigency of hunger.

02:22:49.470 --> 02:22:51.770
Sundays were dreary days in that wintry season.

02:22:52.430 --> 02:22:55.230
We had to walk two miles to Brocklebridge Church,

02:22:55.790 --> 02:22:57.090
where our patron officiated.

02:22:57.890 --> 02:22:59.010
We set out cold.

02:22:59.350 --> 02:23:00.550
We arrived at Church colder.

02:23:01.430 --> 02:23:03.950
During the morning service, we became almost paralyzed.

02:23:04.730 --> 02:23:06.570
It was too far to return to dinner.

02:23:07.310 --> 02:23:09.190
And an allowance of cold meat and bread,

02:23:09.510 --> 02:23:11.950
in the same penorious proportion observed

02:23:11.950 --> 02:23:14.390
in our ordinary meals, was served round

02:23:14.390 --> 02:23:15.290
between the services.

02:23:16.790 --> 02:23:18.530
At the close of the afternoon service,

02:23:18.970 --> 02:23:21.230
we returned by an exposed and hilly road,

02:23:22.210 --> 02:23:24.170
where the bitter winter wind, blowing

02:23:24.170 --> 02:23:26.330
over a range of snowy summits to the north,

02:23:26.330 --> 02:23:28.770
almost flayed the skin from our faces.

02:23:29.990 --> 02:23:31.650
I can remember Miss Temple walking

02:23:31.650 --> 02:23:34.710
lightly and rapidly along our drooping line,

02:23:35.050 --> 02:23:38.410
her plaid cloak, which the frosty wind fluttered,

02:23:38.650 --> 02:23:41.630
gathered close about her, and encouraging us,

02:23:41.830 --> 02:23:44.850
by precept and example, to keep up our spirits

02:23:45.210 --> 02:23:49.050
and march forward, as she said, like stalwart soldiers.

02:23:50.070 --> 02:23:53.730
The other teachers, poor things, were generally themselves

02:23:53.730 --> 02:23:57.570
too much dejected to attempt the task of cheering others.

02:23:59.550 --> 02:24:02.330
How we longed for the light and heat of a blazing fire

02:24:02.330 --> 02:24:03.690
when we got back.

02:24:04.190 --> 02:24:06.930
But to the little ones, at least, this was denied.

02:24:07.550 --> 02:24:10.430
Each hearth in the schoolroom was immediately surrounded

02:24:10.430 --> 02:24:13.610
by a double row of great girls, and behind them,

02:24:13.870 --> 02:24:15.470
the younger children crouched in groups,

02:24:15.870 --> 02:24:18.370
wrapping their starved arms in their pinafores.

02:24:19.030 --> 02:24:20.730
A little solace came at tea time,

02:24:21.210 --> 02:24:23.190
in the shape of a double ration of bread,

02:24:23.190 --> 02:24:25.650
a whole instead of a half slice,

02:24:26.370 --> 02:24:29.190
with a delicious addition of a thin scrape of butter.

02:24:29.850 --> 02:24:32.490
It was the hebdominal treat to which we all looked forward

02:24:32.490 --> 02:24:33.750
from Sabbath to Sabbath.

02:24:34.570 --> 02:24:36.950
I generally contrived to reserve a moiety

02:24:36.950 --> 02:24:39.050
of this boundary past for myself,

02:24:39.890 --> 02:24:42.770
but the remainder I was invariably obliged to part with.

02:24:43.850 --> 02:24:46.790
The Sunday evening was spent in repeating, by heart,

02:24:47.190 --> 02:24:50.050
the church catechism and the fifth, sixth,

02:24:50.070 --> 02:24:51.810
and seventh chapters of St. Matthew,

02:24:52.330 --> 02:24:55.450
and in listening to a long sermon read by Miss Miller,

02:24:55.830 --> 02:24:58.190
whose irrepressible yawns attested her weariness.

02:24:59.190 --> 02:25:00.950
A frequent interlude of these performances

02:25:00.950 --> 02:25:03.410
was the enactment of the part of Eudicus

02:25:03.410 --> 02:25:05.570
by some half dozen of little girls,

02:25:06.130 --> 02:25:08.870
who, overpowered with sleep, would fall down,

02:25:09.290 --> 02:25:12.450
if not out of the third loft, yet off the fourth form,

02:25:13.230 --> 02:25:14.730
and be taken up half dead.

02:25:15.230 --> 02:25:17.610
The remedy was to thrust them forward

02:25:17.610 --> 02:25:19.130
into the center of the schoolroom

02:25:19.130 --> 02:25:22.110
and oblige them to stand there till the sermon was finished.

02:25:22.850 --> 02:25:24.570
Sometimes their feet failed them,

02:25:24.950 --> 02:25:26.510
and they sank together in a heap.

02:25:27.210 --> 02:25:30.290
They were then propped up with the monitor's high stools.

02:25:31.530 --> 02:25:34.610
I have not yet alluded to the visits of Mr. Brocklehurst,

02:25:35.050 --> 02:25:36.990
and indeed that gentleman was from home

02:25:36.990 --> 02:25:38.690
during the greater part of the first month

02:25:38.690 --> 02:25:39.630
after my arrival.

02:25:40.370 --> 02:25:43.130
Perhaps prolonging his stay with his friend, the archdeacon,

02:25:43.650 --> 02:25:45.330
his absence was a relief to me.

02:25:45.810 --> 02:25:47.890
I need not say that I have my own reasons

02:25:47.890 --> 02:25:50.870
for dreading his coming, but come he did at last.

02:25:51.590 --> 02:25:55.110
One afternoon, I had then been three weeks at Lowood,

02:25:55.550 --> 02:25:58.050
as I was sitting with a slate in my hand,

02:25:58.310 --> 02:26:00.170
puzzling over a sum and long division,

02:26:00.670 --> 02:26:03.430
my eyes, raised in abstraction to the window,

02:26:03.970 --> 02:26:05.950
caught sight of a figure just passing.

02:26:06.910 --> 02:26:10.430
I recognized almost instinctively that gaunt outline,

02:26:10.890 --> 02:26:13.690
and when, two minutes after, all the school,

02:26:14.010 --> 02:26:16.350
teachers included, rose en masse,

02:26:16.350 --> 02:26:18.530
it was not necessary for me to look up

02:26:18.530 --> 02:26:21.590
in order to ascertain whose entrance they thus greeted.

02:26:22.690 --> 02:26:24.730
A long stride measured the schoolroom,

02:26:25.150 --> 02:26:28.270
and presently beside Miss Temple, who herself had risen,

02:26:28.970 --> 02:26:31.670
stood the same black column which had frowned on me

02:26:31.670 --> 02:26:34.310
so ominously from the hearth rug of Gateshead.

02:26:35.390 --> 02:26:38.450
I now glance sideways at this piece of architecture.

02:26:38.810 --> 02:26:42.250
Yes, I was right, it was Mr. Brocklehurst,

02:26:42.770 --> 02:26:45.490
buttoned up in a certut, and looking longer,

02:26:45.970 --> 02:26:48.010
narrower, and more rigid than ever.

02:26:49.710 --> 02:26:53.030
I had my own reasons for being dismayed at this apparition.

02:26:53.650 --> 02:26:56.110
Too well I remembered the perfidious hints

02:26:56.110 --> 02:26:59.830
given by Mrs. Reed about my disposition, et cetera,

02:27:00.410 --> 02:27:02.590
the promise pledged by Mr. Brocklehurst

02:27:02.590 --> 02:27:06.070
to reprise Miss Temple and the teachers of a vicious nature.

02:27:06.910 --> 02:27:08.730
All along, I had been dreading

02:27:08.730 --> 02:27:10.130
the fulfillment of this promise.

02:27:10.470 --> 02:27:13.150
I had been looking out daily for the coming man,

02:27:13.510 --> 02:27:16.990
whose information respecting my past life and conversation

02:27:16.990 --> 02:27:19.290
was to brand me as a bad child forever.

02:27:19.830 --> 02:27:21.430
Now, there he was.

02:27:22.090 --> 02:27:24.330
He stood at Miss Temple's side.

02:27:24.690 --> 02:27:26.490
He was speaking low in her ear.

02:27:26.950 --> 02:27:30.390
I did not doubt he was making disclosures of my villainy,

02:27:30.570 --> 02:27:33.190
and I watched her eye with painful anxiety,

02:27:33.650 --> 02:27:37.250
expecting every moment to see its dark orb turn on me

02:27:37.250 --> 02:27:39.330
a glance of repugnance and contempt.

02:27:40.130 --> 02:27:43.090
I listened, too, and as I happened to be seated

02:27:43.090 --> 02:27:46.330
quite at the top of the room, I caught most of what he said.

02:27:46.730 --> 02:27:49.470
Its import relieved me from immediate apprehension.

02:27:50.390 --> 02:27:53.270
I suppose, Miss Temple, the thread I bought at Loughton

02:27:53.270 --> 02:27:53.830
will do.

02:27:54.170 --> 02:27:56.570
It struck me that it would be just of the quality

02:27:56.570 --> 02:27:59.930
for the calico chemises, and I sorted the needles to match.

02:28:00.450 --> 02:28:02.870
You may tell Miss Smith that I forgot to make

02:28:02.870 --> 02:28:04.590
a memorandum of the darning needles,

02:28:05.030 --> 02:28:07.590
but she shall have some papers sent in next week,

02:28:07.590 --> 02:28:10.550
and she is not on any account to give out more

02:28:10.550 --> 02:28:12.150
than one at a time to each pupil.

02:28:12.750 --> 02:28:15.050
If they have more, they are apt to be careless

02:28:15.050 --> 02:28:17.670
and lose them, and oh, ma'am.

02:28:17.850 --> 02:28:20.270
I wish the woolen stockings were better looked to.

02:28:20.750 --> 02:28:23.470
When I was here last, I went into the kitchen garden

02:28:23.470 --> 02:28:25.970
and examined the clothes drying on the line.

02:28:26.290 --> 02:28:28.010
There was a quantity of black hose

02:28:28.010 --> 02:28:29.910
in a very bad state of repair.

02:28:30.630 --> 02:28:32.090
From the size of the holes in them,

02:28:32.090 --> 02:28:35.150
I was sure they had not been well mended from time to time.

02:28:35.730 --> 02:28:36.470
He paused.

02:28:37.590 --> 02:28:40.810
Your direction shall be attended to, sir, said Miss Temple.

02:28:41.670 --> 02:28:44.310
And ma'am, he continued, the laundress tells me

02:28:44.310 --> 02:28:46.750
some of the girls have two clean tuckers in the week.

02:28:47.210 --> 02:28:48.030
It is too much.

02:28:48.430 --> 02:28:49.910
The rules limit them to one.

02:28:51.290 --> 02:28:53.450
I think I can explain that circumstance, sir.

02:28:54.050 --> 02:28:56.450
Agnes and Catherine Johnstone were invited to take tea

02:28:56.450 --> 02:28:58.290
with some friends at Loughton last Thursday,

02:28:58.650 --> 02:29:00.790
and I gave them leave to put on clean tuckers

02:29:00.790 --> 02:29:01.470
for the occasion.

02:29:02.470 --> 02:29:03.830
Mr. Brocklehurst nodded.

02:29:04.730 --> 02:29:06.610
Well, for once it may pass,

02:29:06.610 --> 02:29:09.710
but please not to let the circumstance occur too often.

02:29:10.290 --> 02:29:12.390
And there is another thing which surprised me.

02:29:12.590 --> 02:29:15.330
I find in settling accounts with the housekeeper

02:29:15.330 --> 02:29:18.170
that a lunch consisting of bread and cheese

02:29:18.170 --> 02:29:20.250
has twice been served out to the girls

02:29:20.250 --> 02:29:21.390
during the past fortnight.

02:29:22.090 --> 02:29:22.890
How is this?

02:29:23.330 --> 02:29:24.670
I looked over the regulations

02:29:24.670 --> 02:29:26.890
and I find no such meal as lunch mentioned.

02:29:27.570 --> 02:29:28.990
Who introduced this innovation?

02:29:29.370 --> 02:29:30.390
And by what authority?

02:29:31.730 --> 02:29:34.410
I must be responsible for the circumstance, sir,

02:29:34.890 --> 02:29:35.710
replied Miss Temple.

02:29:36.150 --> 02:29:37.930
The breakfast was so ill-prepared

02:29:37.930 --> 02:29:40.610
that the pupils could not possibly eat it,

02:29:40.690 --> 02:29:42.670
and I dared not allow them to remain fasting

02:29:42.670 --> 02:29:43.570
till dinner time.

02:29:44.690 --> 02:29:46.410
Madam, allow me an instant.

02:29:46.830 --> 02:29:49.230
You are aware that my plan in bringing up these girls

02:29:49.230 --> 02:29:52.730
is not to accustom them to habits of luxury and indulgence,

02:29:52.990 --> 02:29:56.170
but to render them hearty, patient, self-denying.

02:29:56.590 --> 02:29:58.830
Should any little accidental disappointment

02:29:58.830 --> 02:30:02.170
of the appetite occur, such as the spoiling of a meal,

02:30:02.550 --> 02:30:04.590
the under or the overdressing of a dish,

02:30:04.590 --> 02:30:07.330
the incident ought not to be neutralized

02:30:07.330 --> 02:30:09.210
by replacing with something more delicate

02:30:09.210 --> 02:30:10.490
the comfort lost,

02:30:10.870 --> 02:30:12.290
thus pampering the body

02:30:12.290 --> 02:30:14.590
and obviating the sum of this institution.

02:30:15.310 --> 02:30:16.490
It ought to be improved

02:30:16.490 --> 02:30:18.790
to the spiritual edification of the pupils

02:30:19.210 --> 02:30:21.170
by encouraging them to evince fortitude

02:30:21.170 --> 02:30:22.370
under temporary probation.

02:30:23.230 --> 02:30:26.650
A brief address on those occasions would not be mistimed,

02:30:26.790 --> 02:30:28.270
wherein a judicious instructor

02:30:28.270 --> 02:30:31.430
would take the opportunity of referring to the sufferings

02:30:31.430 --> 02:30:32.650
of the primitive Christians

02:30:32.650 --> 02:30:34.710
to the torments of martyrs,

02:30:34.910 --> 02:30:37.310
to the exhortations of our blessed Lord himself,

02:30:37.790 --> 02:30:39.110
calling upon his disciples

02:30:39.110 --> 02:30:40.930
to take up the cross and follow him,

02:30:41.350 --> 02:30:43.750
to his warnings that man should not live by bread alone,

02:30:43.930 --> 02:30:46.550
but by every word that proceedeth out of the mouth of God,

02:30:47.010 --> 02:30:48.750
to his divine consolations.

02:30:49.250 --> 02:30:52.350
If ye suffer hunger or thirst for my sake, happy are ye.

02:30:52.850 --> 02:30:55.150
Oh, madam, when you put bread and cheese

02:30:55.150 --> 02:30:57.610
instead of burnt porridge into these children's mouths,

02:30:57.950 --> 02:31:00.050
you may indeed feed their vile bodies,

02:31:00.050 --> 02:31:02.950
but you little think how you starve their immortal souls.

02:31:04.110 --> 02:31:05.850
Mr. Brocklehurst again paused,

02:31:06.430 --> 02:31:08.190
perhaps overcome by his feelings.

02:31:09.010 --> 02:31:10.170
Miss Temple had looked down

02:31:10.170 --> 02:31:11.790
when he first began to speak to her,

02:31:12.110 --> 02:31:14.110
but she now gazed straight before her,

02:31:14.250 --> 02:31:16.590
and her face, naturally pale as marble,

02:31:17.230 --> 02:31:19.730
appeared to be assuming also the coldness

02:31:19.730 --> 02:31:23.050
and fixity of that material, especially her mouth,

02:31:23.530 --> 02:31:24.950
closed as if it would have required

02:31:24.950 --> 02:31:27.070
a sculptor's chisel to open it,

02:31:27.130 --> 02:31:29.030
and her brow settled gradually

02:31:29.030 --> 02:31:30.570
into petrified severity.

02:31:32.190 --> 02:31:35.250
Meantime, Mr. Brocklehurst, standing on the hearth

02:31:35.250 --> 02:31:37.170
with his hands behind his back,

02:31:37.370 --> 02:31:39.190
majestically surveyed the whole school.

02:31:39.690 --> 02:31:41.790
Suddenly, his eyes gave a blink,

02:31:42.190 --> 02:31:43.350
as if it had meant something

02:31:43.350 --> 02:31:45.530
that either dazzled or shocked its pupil.

02:31:46.430 --> 02:31:48.710
Turning, he said in more rapid accents

02:31:48.710 --> 02:31:50.090
that he had hitherto used,

02:31:50.590 --> 02:31:52.650
Miss Temple, Miss Temple, what?

02:31:52.990 --> 02:31:54.790
What is that girl with curled hair?

02:31:55.250 --> 02:31:58.090
Red hair, ma'am, curled, curled all over.

02:31:59.030 --> 02:32:02.350
And extending his cane, he pointed to the awful object,

02:32:02.870 --> 02:32:04.730
his hand shaking as he did so.

02:32:05.430 --> 02:32:08.570
It is Julia Severn, replied Miss Temple very quietly.

02:32:09.550 --> 02:32:11.910
Julia Severn, ma'am, and why has she

02:32:11.910 --> 02:32:13.550
or any other curled hair?

02:32:14.210 --> 02:32:16.070
Why, in defiance of every precept

02:32:16.070 --> 02:32:17.510
and principle of this house,

02:32:17.830 --> 02:32:19.630
does she conform to the world so openly,

02:32:20.290 --> 02:32:23.310
here in an evangelical charitable establishment

02:32:23.310 --> 02:32:25.610
as to where her hair one mass of curls?

02:32:27.050 --> 02:32:28.770
Julia's hair curls naturally,

02:32:28.890 --> 02:32:30.970
returned Miss Temple, still more quietly.

02:32:31.910 --> 02:32:34.750
Naturally, yes, but we are not to conform to nature.

02:32:35.370 --> 02:32:37.590
I wish these girls to be the children of grace,

02:32:37.650 --> 02:32:39.010
and why that abundance?

02:32:39.670 --> 02:32:41.630
I have again and again intimated

02:32:41.630 --> 02:32:44.030
that I desire the hair to be arranged closely,

02:32:44.370 --> 02:32:45.830
modestly, plainly.

02:32:45.830 --> 02:32:48.710
Miss Temple, that girl's hair must be cut off entirely.

02:32:49.170 --> 02:32:50.790
I will send a borrower tomorrow,

02:32:50.790 --> 02:32:53.990
and I see others who are far too much of the excretions.

02:32:54.530 --> 02:32:56.630
That tall girl, tell her to turn round.

02:32:57.410 --> 02:32:59.010
Tell all the first form to rise up

02:32:59.010 --> 02:33:00.430
and direct their faces to the wall.

02:33:01.230 --> 02:33:03.450
Miss Temple passed her handkerchief over her lips,

02:33:03.810 --> 02:33:06.030
as if to smooth away the involuntary smile

02:33:06.030 --> 02:33:06.850
that curled them.

02:33:07.270 --> 02:33:08.530
She gave the order, however,

02:33:08.770 --> 02:33:10.310
and when the first class could take in

02:33:10.310 --> 02:33:12.670
what was required of them, they obeyed.

02:33:13.210 --> 02:33:14.770
Leaning a little back on my bench,

02:33:15.190 --> 02:33:16.670
I could see the looks and grimaces

02:33:16.670 --> 02:33:18.610
with which they commented on this maneuver.

02:33:19.070 --> 02:33:22.090
It was a pity Mr. Rocklehurst could not see them, too.

02:33:22.090 --> 02:33:23.930
He would perhaps have felt that.

02:33:24.290 --> 02:33:26.790
Whatever he might do with the outside of the cup and platter,

02:33:27.230 --> 02:33:29.270
the inside was farther beyond his interference

02:33:29.270 --> 02:33:30.110
than he imagined.

02:33:31.330 --> 02:33:33.610
He scrutinized the reverse of these living medals

02:33:33.610 --> 02:33:36.330
some five minutes, then pronounced sentence.

02:33:37.050 --> 02:33:39.250
These words fell like the knell of doom.

02:33:40.110 --> 02:33:42.310
All those top knots must be cut off.

02:33:43.310 --> 02:33:45.130
Miss Temple seemed to remonstrate.

02:33:46.030 --> 02:33:46.810
Madam, he would.

02:33:47.350 --> 02:33:48.850
I have a master to serve,

02:33:49.210 --> 02:33:50.730
whose kingdom is not of this world.

02:33:51.430 --> 02:33:54.050
My mission is to mortify in these girls

02:33:54.050 --> 02:33:55.390
the lust of the flesh,

02:33:55.750 --> 02:33:57.350
to teach them to clothe themselves

02:33:57.350 --> 02:33:59.330
with shame-facedness and sobriety,

02:33:59.690 --> 02:34:02.010
not with braided hair and costly apparel.

02:34:02.310 --> 02:34:03.990
And each of the young persons before us

02:34:03.990 --> 02:34:06.090
has a string of hair twisted in plates,

02:34:06.470 --> 02:34:08.110
which vanity itself might have woven.

02:34:08.470 --> 02:34:10.290
These, I repeat, must be cut off.

02:34:10.590 --> 02:34:13.470
Think of the time wasted of...

02:34:13.470 --> 02:34:15.470
Mr. Rocklehurst was here interrupted.

02:34:16.090 --> 02:34:19.630
Three other visitors, ladies, now entered the room.

02:34:20.170 --> 02:34:22.090
They ought to have come a little sooner

02:34:22.090 --> 02:34:24.130
to have heard his lecture on dress,

02:34:24.490 --> 02:34:26.250
for they were splendidly attired

02:34:26.250 --> 02:34:28.270
in velvet, silk, and furs.

02:34:29.050 --> 02:34:30.470
The two younger of the trio,

02:34:31.010 --> 02:34:32.910
fine girls of 16 and 17,

02:34:33.130 --> 02:34:36.010
had gray beaver hats, then in fashion,

02:34:36.830 --> 02:34:38.390
shaded with ostrich plumes,

02:34:38.850 --> 02:34:41.630
and from under the brim of this graceful headdress

02:34:41.630 --> 02:34:44.950
fell a profusion of light tresses elaborately curled.

02:34:45.610 --> 02:34:48.790
The elder lady was enveloped in a costly velvet shawl,

02:34:48.790 --> 02:34:50.650
trimmed with ermine,

02:34:51.310 --> 02:34:53.630
and she wore a false front of French girls.

02:34:55.070 --> 02:34:58.250
These ladies were deferentially received by Miss Temple

02:34:58.250 --> 02:35:01.150
as Mrs. and Mrs. Rocklehurst,

02:35:02.190 --> 02:35:04.770
and conducted to seats of honor at the top of the room.

02:35:05.390 --> 02:35:07.210
It seems they had come in the carriage

02:35:07.210 --> 02:35:08.690
with their reverend relative,

02:35:09.190 --> 02:35:11.290
and had been conducting a rummaging scrutiny

02:35:11.290 --> 02:35:12.550
of the room upstairs,

02:35:13.190 --> 02:35:15.610
while he transacted business with the housekeeper,

02:35:16.330 --> 02:35:17.270
questioned the laundress,

02:35:17.270 --> 02:35:18.970
and lectured the superintendent.

02:35:20.030 --> 02:35:22.570
They now proceeded to address diverse remarks

02:35:22.570 --> 02:35:24.030
and reproofs to Miss Smith,

02:35:24.510 --> 02:35:26.130
who was charged with the care of the linen

02:35:26.130 --> 02:35:28.050
in the inspection of the dormitories,

02:35:28.610 --> 02:35:30.810
but I had no time to listen to what they said.

02:35:31.910 --> 02:35:34.370
Other matters called off and enchanted my attention.

02:35:35.570 --> 02:35:37.750
Hitherto, while gathering up the discourse

02:35:37.750 --> 02:35:39.590
of Mrs. Rocklehurst and Miss Temple,

02:35:40.110 --> 02:35:41.790
I had not, at the same time,

02:35:42.170 --> 02:35:44.590
neglected precautions to secure my personal safety,

02:35:44.970 --> 02:35:46.690
which I thought would be effected

02:35:46.690 --> 02:35:48.390
if I could only elude observation.

02:35:49.090 --> 02:35:51.970
To this end, I had sat well back on the form,

02:35:52.610 --> 02:35:54.430
and while seeming to be busy with my sum,

02:35:54.730 --> 02:35:58.170
had held my slate in such a manner as to conceal my face.

02:35:58.710 --> 02:36:00.210
I might have escaped noticed,

02:36:01.050 --> 02:36:02.330
had not my treacherous slate

02:36:02.330 --> 02:36:04.730
somehow happened to slip from my hand

02:36:04.730 --> 02:36:07.330
and fallen with an obtrusive crash,

02:36:07.630 --> 02:36:09.630
directly drawn every eye upon me.

02:36:09.970 --> 02:36:11.670
I knew it was all over now,

02:36:12.030 --> 02:36:14.670
and as I stooped up to pick up the two fragments of slate,

02:36:14.670 --> 02:36:16.590
I rallied my forces for the worst.

02:36:17.130 --> 02:36:17.830
It came.

02:36:18.930 --> 02:36:21.870
A careless girl, said Mr. Rocklehurst,

02:36:22.390 --> 02:36:25.870
and immediately after, it is the new pupil I perceive.

02:36:26.570 --> 02:36:27.990
And before I could draw a breath,

02:36:28.310 --> 02:36:30.870
I must not forget I have a word to say respecting her.

02:36:31.610 --> 02:36:34.050
That aloud, how loud it seemed to me,

02:36:34.330 --> 02:36:36.170
let the child who broke her slate come forward.

02:36:37.590 --> 02:36:39.390
Of my own accord, I could not have stirred.

02:36:40.090 --> 02:36:43.010
I was paralyzed, but the two great girls

02:36:43.010 --> 02:36:45.110
who sat on each side of me,

02:36:45.690 --> 02:36:48.330
set me on my legs and pushed me towards the dread judge.

02:36:49.050 --> 02:36:52.450
And then Miss Temple gently assisted me to his very feet,

02:36:52.870 --> 02:36:54.290
and I caught her whispered counsel.

02:36:55.090 --> 02:36:56.250
Don't be afraid, Jane.

02:36:56.670 --> 02:36:57.890
I saw it was an accident.

02:36:58.750 --> 02:36:59.910
You shall not be punished.

02:37:00.950 --> 02:37:03.110
The kind whisper went to my heart like a dagger.

02:37:04.710 --> 02:37:07.270
Another minute, and she'll despise me for hypocrite,

02:37:07.310 --> 02:37:10.230
thought I, and an impulse of fury

02:37:10.230 --> 02:37:13.010
against Reed, Rocklehurst, and company

02:37:13.010 --> 02:37:15.670
bounded in my pulses at the conviction.

02:37:16.170 --> 02:37:17.510
I was no Helen Burns.

02:37:18.990 --> 02:37:21.410
Fetch that stool, said Mr. Rocklehurst,

02:37:21.970 --> 02:37:23.370
pointing to a very high one

02:37:23.370 --> 02:37:25.350
from which a monitor had just risen.

02:37:25.650 --> 02:37:26.450
It was brought.

02:37:27.210 --> 02:37:28.690
Place the child upon it.

02:37:29.630 --> 02:37:32.430
And I was placed there, by whom I don't know.

02:37:33.070 --> 02:37:35.210
I was in no condition to note particulars.

02:37:35.630 --> 02:37:38.130
I was only aware that they had hoisted me up

02:37:38.130 --> 02:37:40.410
to the height of Mr. Rocklehurst's nose,

02:37:41.330 --> 02:37:42.990
that he was within a yard of me,

02:37:43.050 --> 02:37:46.190
and that a spread of shot orange and purple silk polices

02:37:46.190 --> 02:37:50.110
and a cloud of silvery plumage extended and waved below me.

02:37:51.050 --> 02:37:52.410
Mr. Rocklehurst hemmed.

02:37:52.630 --> 02:37:55.310
Ladies, said he, turning to his family,

02:37:55.810 --> 02:37:57.710
Miss Temple, teachers, and children,

02:37:57.910 --> 02:37:59.070
you all see this girl?

02:37:59.670 --> 02:38:02.650
Of course they did, for I felt their eyes directed

02:38:02.650 --> 02:38:05.110
like burning glasses against my scorched skin.

02:38:05.970 --> 02:38:07.910
You see she is yet young.

02:38:08.550 --> 02:38:10.170
You observe that she possesses

02:38:10.170 --> 02:38:11.590
the ordinary form of childhood.

02:38:12.330 --> 02:38:14.190
God has graciously given her the shape

02:38:14.190 --> 02:38:15.670
that he has given to all of us.

02:38:16.010 --> 02:38:18.990
No signal deformity points her out as a marked character.

02:38:19.530 --> 02:38:21.330
Who would think that the evil one

02:38:21.330 --> 02:38:23.950
has already found a servant and agent in her?

02:38:24.290 --> 02:38:26.790
Yet such, I grieve to say, is the case.

02:38:28.110 --> 02:38:32.470
A pause, in which I began to steady the palsy of my nerves,

02:38:32.870 --> 02:38:34.790
and to feel that the Rubicon had passed.

02:38:35.290 --> 02:38:38.310
And that the trial, no longer to be shirked,

02:38:38.550 --> 02:38:39.750
must be firmly sustained.

02:38:41.210 --> 02:38:44.910
My dear children, pursued the black marble clergyman,

02:38:45.130 --> 02:38:48.770
with pathos, this is a sad, a melancholy occasion.

02:38:49.410 --> 02:38:52.130
For it becomes my duty to warn you that this girl,

02:38:52.250 --> 02:38:55.710
who might be one of God's own lambs, is a little cast away.

02:38:56.230 --> 02:38:57.850
Not a member of the true flock,

02:38:58.250 --> 02:39:00.610
but evidently an interloper and an alien.

02:39:01.090 --> 02:39:02.950
You must be on your guard against her.

02:39:02.950 --> 02:39:04.490
You must shun her example.

02:39:04.870 --> 02:39:06.930
If necessary, avoid her company.

02:39:07.530 --> 02:39:08.730
Exclude her from your sports,

02:39:09.170 --> 02:39:10.710
and shut her out from your converse.

02:39:11.390 --> 02:39:12.990
Teachers, you must watch her.

02:39:13.190 --> 02:39:14.530
Keep your eyes on her movements.

02:39:15.010 --> 02:39:15.970
Weigh well her words.

02:39:16.370 --> 02:39:17.450
Scrutinize her actions.

02:39:17.730 --> 02:39:19.350
Punish her body to save her soul.

02:39:20.110 --> 02:39:22.650
If, indeed, such salvation be possible.

02:39:23.230 --> 02:39:26.310
For, my tongue falters while I tell it,

02:39:26.590 --> 02:39:30.070
this girl, this child, the native of a Christian land,

02:39:30.550 --> 02:39:31.950
worse than many a little heathen

02:39:31.950 --> 02:39:34.990
who says its prayers to Brahma and kneels before Juggernaut,

02:39:35.390 --> 02:39:37.330
this girl is a liar.

02:39:39.010 --> 02:39:41.170
Now came a pause of 10 minutes,

02:39:41.570 --> 02:39:43.650
during which I, by this time,

02:39:44.010 --> 02:39:45.850
in perfect possession of my wits,

02:39:46.390 --> 02:39:48.510
observed all the female Brocklehursts

02:39:48.510 --> 02:39:50.310
produce their pocket handkerchiefs

02:39:50.310 --> 02:39:51.650
and apply them to their optics,

02:39:52.370 --> 02:39:54.950
while the elderly lady swayed herself to and fro,

02:39:55.350 --> 02:39:57.410
and the two younger ones whispered, how shocking.

02:39:58.310 --> 02:39:59.650
Mr. Brocklehurst resumed.

02:40:00.290 --> 02:40:02.590
This I learned from her benefactress,

02:40:03.210 --> 02:40:04.870
from the pious and charitable lady

02:40:04.870 --> 02:40:06.910
who adopted her in her orphaned state,

02:40:07.370 --> 02:40:08.790
reared her as her own daughter,

02:40:09.150 --> 02:40:10.930
and whose kindness, whose generosity,

02:40:11.250 --> 02:40:14.510
the unhappy girl repaid by an ingratitude so bad,

02:40:14.730 --> 02:40:17.570
so dreadful, that at last her excellent patroness

02:40:17.570 --> 02:40:20.530
was obliged to separate her from her own young ones,

02:40:21.090 --> 02:40:23.130
fearful lest her vicious examples

02:40:23.130 --> 02:40:24.550
should contaminate their purity.

02:40:25.210 --> 02:40:27.230
She has sent her here to be healed.

02:40:27.930 --> 02:40:30.170
Even as the Jews of old sent their disease

02:40:30.170 --> 02:40:31.910
to the troubled pool of Bethesda,

02:40:32.490 --> 02:40:34.190
and teachers, superintendent,

02:40:34.710 --> 02:40:36.850
I beg of you not to allow the waters

02:40:36.850 --> 02:40:38.190
to stagnate around her.

02:40:39.090 --> 02:40:40.650
With this sublime conclusion,

02:40:41.130 --> 02:40:44.150
Mr. Brocklehurst adjusted the top button of her Sertut,

02:40:44.750 --> 02:40:46.830
muttered something to his family, who rose,

02:40:47.210 --> 02:40:48.290
bowed to Miss Temple,

02:40:48.570 --> 02:40:51.930
and then all the great people sailed in state from the room.

02:40:52.990 --> 02:40:55.010
Turning at the door, my judge said,

02:40:55.810 --> 02:40:58.430
Let her stand half an hour longer on that stool,

02:40:58.770 --> 02:41:01.330
and let no one speak to her during the remainder of the day.

02:41:02.850 --> 02:41:05.530
There was I then, mounted aloft,

02:41:05.890 --> 02:41:08.530
I, who had said I could not bear the shame

02:41:08.530 --> 02:41:11.530
of standing on my natural feet in the middle of the room,

02:41:12.150 --> 02:41:15.330
was now exposed to general view on a pedestal of infamy.

02:41:16.210 --> 02:41:19.350
What my sensations were no language can describe,

02:41:20.030 --> 02:41:22.850
but just as they all rose, stifling my breath,

02:41:23.210 --> 02:41:24.330
and constricting my throat,

02:41:24.330 --> 02:41:26.350
a girl came up and passed me.

02:41:26.550 --> 02:41:28.690
In passing, she lifted her eyes.

02:41:29.290 --> 02:41:31.050
What a strange light inspired them!

02:41:31.530 --> 02:41:34.430
What an extraordinary sensation that rays sent through me!

02:41:34.970 --> 02:41:36.570
How the new feeling bore me up!

02:41:37.030 --> 02:41:40.870
It was as if a martyr, a hero, had passed a slave or victim,

02:41:41.390 --> 02:41:43.190
and imparted strength in the transit.

02:41:43.890 --> 02:41:47.010
I mastered the rising hysteria, lifted up my head,

02:41:47.390 --> 02:41:49.050
and took a firm stand on the stool.

02:41:49.730 --> 02:41:51.490
Helen Burns asked some slight question

02:41:51.490 --> 02:41:53.250
about her work of Miss Smith.

02:41:53.250 --> 02:41:56.170
Was chidden for the triviality of the inquiry,

02:41:56.930 --> 02:42:00.030
returned to her place, and smiled at me as she again went by.

02:42:00.510 --> 02:42:01.350
What a smile!

02:42:02.130 --> 02:42:04.910
I remember it now, and I know that it was the effluence

02:42:04.910 --> 02:42:06.990
of fine intellect, of true courage.

02:42:07.570 --> 02:42:10.150
It lit up her marked liniments, her thin face,

02:42:10.430 --> 02:42:12.810
her sunken gray eye, like a reflection

02:42:12.810 --> 02:42:14.290
from the aspect of an angel.

02:42:14.970 --> 02:42:18.190
Yet at that moment Helen Burns wore on her arm

02:42:18.810 --> 02:42:19.990
the untidy badge.

02:42:20.850 --> 02:42:22.970
Scarcely an hour ago I had heard her condemned

02:42:22.970 --> 02:42:25.590
by Miss Scatchard to a dinner of bread and water

02:42:25.590 --> 02:42:28.430
on the morrow, because she had blotted in exercise

02:42:28.430 --> 02:42:29.450
and copying it out.

02:42:30.690 --> 02:42:32.550
Such is the imperfect nature of man.

02:42:33.250 --> 02:42:36.130
Such spots are there on the disk of the clearest planet,

02:42:36.790 --> 02:42:38.550
and eyes like Miss Scatchard's can only

02:42:38.550 --> 02:42:42.210
see those minute defects and are blind to the full brightness

02:42:42.210 --> 02:42:42.970
of the orb.

02:43:05.890 --> 02:43:08.690
CHAPTER VIII.

02:43:08.690 --> 02:43:15.070
Ere the half-hour ended, five o'clock struck, school was dismissed, and all were gone into

02:43:15.070 --> 02:43:23.630
the refractory for tea. I now ventured to descend. It was deep dusk. I retired into a corner and sat

02:43:23.630 --> 02:43:30.670
down on the floor. The spell by which I had been so far supported began to dissolve. Reaction took

02:43:30.670 --> 02:43:37.970
place. And soon, so overwhelming was the grief that seized me, I sank prostrate with my face

02:43:37.970 --> 02:43:45.890
to the ground. Now I wept. Helen Burns was not here. Nothing sustained me. Left to myself,

02:43:46.090 --> 02:43:53.210
I abandoned myself. And my tears watered the boards. I had meant to be so good, and to do so

02:43:53.210 --> 02:44:00.070
much at Lowood, to make so many friends, to earn respect and win affection. Already I had made

02:44:00.070 --> 02:44:06.470
visible progress. That very morning I had reached the head of my class. Miss Miller had praised me

02:44:06.470 --> 02:44:14.330
informally. Miss Temple had smiled approbation. She had promised to teach me drawing. And to let

02:44:14.330 --> 02:44:20.290
me learn French, if I continued to make similar improvement two months longer. And then I was

02:44:20.290 --> 02:44:27.810
well received by my fellow pupils. Treated as an equal by those of my own age, and not molested by

02:44:27.810 --> 02:44:37.790
any. Now here I lay again, crushed and trodden on. And could I ever rise more? Never, I thought.

02:44:38.590 --> 02:44:46.290
Inartently I wished to die. While sobbing out this wish in broken accents, someone approached.

02:44:46.870 --> 02:44:54.790
I started up. Again, Helen Burns was near me. The fading fires just showed her coming up the long

02:44:54.790 --> 02:44:58.010
vacant room. She brought my coffee and bread.

02:44:59.570 --> 02:45:07.190
Come, eat something, she said. But I put both away from me, feeling as if a drop or a crumb

02:45:07.190 --> 02:45:13.890
would have choked me in my present condition. Helen regarded me, probably with surprise.

02:45:14.470 --> 02:45:21.090
I could not now abate my agitation, though I tried hard. I continued to weep aloud.

02:45:21.750 --> 02:45:27.150
She sat down on the ground near me, embraced her knees with her arms, and rested her head upon

02:45:27.150 --> 02:45:33.350
them. In that attitude she remained silent as an Indian. I was the first who spoke.

02:45:34.350 --> 02:45:39.030
Helen, why do you stay with a girl whom everyone believes to be a liar?

02:45:40.230 --> 02:45:45.250
Everybody Jane? Why, there are only eighty people who have heard you called so,

02:45:45.610 --> 02:45:49.910
and the world contains hundreds of millions. But what have I to do with millions?

02:45:49.910 --> 02:45:58.310
The eighty I know despise me. Jane, you are mistaken. Probably not one in the school

02:45:58.310 --> 02:46:03.450
either despises or dislikes you. Many, I am sure, pee you much.

02:46:05.130 --> 02:46:08.490
How can they pity me after what Mr. Brocklehurst has said?

02:46:10.170 --> 02:46:15.610
Mr. Brocklehurst is not a god, nor is he even a great and admired man.

02:46:16.250 --> 02:46:23.190
He is little liked here. He never took steps to make himself liked. Had he treated you as

02:46:23.190 --> 02:46:31.990
a special favorite you would have found enemies, declared or covert, all around you. As it is,

02:46:32.290 --> 02:46:38.450
the greater number would offer you sympathy if they dared. Teachers and pupils may look

02:46:38.450 --> 02:46:43.230
coldly on you for a day or two, but friendly feelings are concealed in their hearts,

02:46:43.230 --> 02:46:48.010
and if you persevere in doing well, these feelings will ere long appear

02:46:48.010 --> 02:46:54.770
so much the more evidently for their temporary suppression. Besides Jane, she paused.

02:46:56.410 --> 02:47:02.810
Well, Helen, said I, putting my hand into hers, she chafed my fingers gently to warm them,

02:47:03.110 --> 02:47:10.430
and went on. If all the world hated you and believed you wicked while your own conscience

02:47:10.430 --> 02:47:15.510
approved you and absolved you from guilt, you would not be without friends.

02:47:17.170 --> 02:47:23.550
No, I know I should think well of myself, but that is not enough. If others don't love me

02:47:23.550 --> 02:47:30.470
I would rather die than live. I cannot bear to be solitary and hated, Helen. Look here.

02:47:30.790 --> 02:47:37.230
To gain some real affection from you or Miss Temple or any other whom I truly love I would

02:47:37.810 --> 02:47:44.410
submit to have the bone of my arm broken, or to let a bull toss me, or to stand behind a kicking

02:47:44.410 --> 02:47:52.250
horse and let it dash its hoof at my chest. Hush, Jane, you think too much of the love of human

02:47:52.250 --> 02:47:59.010
beings. You are too impulsive, too venomous. The sovereign hand that created your frame

02:47:59.010 --> 02:48:04.770
and put life into it has provided you with other resources than your feeble self,

02:48:04.770 --> 02:48:12.450
or than creatures feeble as you. Besides this earth and besides the race of men, there isn't

02:48:12.450 --> 02:48:18.770
an invisible world and a kingdom of spirits. That world is round us, for it is everywhere,

02:48:19.430 --> 02:48:26.010
and those spirits watch us, for they are commissioned to guard us. And if we were dying

02:48:26.010 --> 02:48:34.050
in pain and shame, if scorns smote us on all sides and hatred crushed us, angels see our tortures,

02:48:34.050 --> 02:48:42.230
recognize our innocence. If innocent we be, as I know you are of this charge which Mr.

02:48:42.410 --> 02:48:48.210
Brocklehurst has weekly and pompously repeated at second hand from Mrs. Reed, for I read a

02:48:48.210 --> 02:48:55.130
sincere nature in your ardent eyes and on your clear front. And God waits only the separation

02:48:55.130 --> 02:49:02.370
of spirit from flesh to crown us with a full reward. Why, then, should we ever sink overwhelmed

02:49:02.370 --> 02:49:08.830
with distress, when life is so soon over and death is so certain an entrance to happiness,

02:49:09.210 --> 02:49:19.890
to glory? I was silent. Helen had calmed me, but in the tranquility she imparted there was an alloy

02:49:19.890 --> 02:49:27.410
of inexpressible sadness. I felt the impression of woe as she spoke, but I could not tell whence

02:49:27.410 --> 02:49:34.090
came, and when, having done speaking, she breathed a little fast and coughed short cough,

02:49:34.730 --> 02:49:39.590
I momentarily forgot my own sorrows to yield to a vague concern for her.

02:49:40.730 --> 02:49:46.810
Resting my head on Helen's shoulder, I put my arms round her waist. She drew me to her,

02:49:47.330 --> 02:49:54.290
and we reposed in silence. We had not sat long thus. When another person came in, some heavy

02:49:54.290 --> 02:50:02.030
clouds, swept from the sky by a rising wind, had left the moon bare, and her light streaming

02:50:02.030 --> 02:50:09.290
in through a window near, shone full both on us and on the approaching figure, which we at once

02:50:09.290 --> 02:50:17.550
recognized as Miss Temple. I came on purpose to find you, Jane Eyre, said she. I want you in my

02:50:17.550 --> 02:50:25.590
room, and as Helen Burns is with you, she may come too. We went, following the superintendent's

02:50:25.590 --> 02:50:32.210
guidance, we had to thread some intricate passages, and mount a staircase before we reached her

02:50:32.210 --> 02:50:39.890
apartment. It contained a good fire, and looked cheerful. Miss Temple told Helen Burns to be

02:50:39.890 --> 02:50:46.890
seated in a low armchair on one side of the hearth, and herself taking another, she called me to her

02:50:46.890 --> 02:50:55.050
side. Is it all over? she asked, looking down at my face. Have you cried your grief away?

02:50:56.190 --> 02:51:04.150
I am afraid I shall never do that. Why? Because I have been wrongly accused, and you, ma'am,

02:51:04.390 --> 02:51:10.870
and everybody else, will now think me wicked. We shall thank you what you prove yourself to be,

02:51:10.870 --> 02:51:18.350
my child. Continue to act as a good girl, and you will satisfy us. Shall I, Miss Temple?

02:51:19.090 --> 02:51:27.030
You will, said she, passing her arm round me. And now, tell me who is the lady who Mr.

02:51:27.210 --> 02:51:35.850
Brucklehurst called your benefactress? Mrs. Reed, my uncle's wife. My uncle is dead, and he left me

02:51:35.850 --> 02:51:44.970
to her care. Did she not then adopt you of her own accord? No, ma'am. She was sorry to have to do it.

02:51:45.830 --> 02:51:52.230
But my uncle, as I have often heard the servants say, got her to promise before he died that she

02:51:52.230 --> 02:51:58.950
would always keep me. Well now, Jane, you know, or at least I will tell you, that when a criminal

02:51:58.950 --> 02:52:05.770
is accused he is always allowed to speak in his own defense. You have been charged with falsehood.

02:52:05.850 --> 02:52:11.810
Defend yourself to me as well as you can. Say whatever your memory suggests is true,

02:52:12.210 --> 02:52:19.010
but add nothing, and exaggerate nothing. I resolved in the depth of my heart that I would

02:52:19.010 --> 02:52:25.550
be most moderate, most correct, and having reflected a few minutes in order to arrange

02:52:25.550 --> 02:52:33.110
coherently what I had to say, I told her all the story of my sad childhood. Exhausted by emotion,

02:52:33.110 --> 02:52:38.610
my language was more subdued than it generally was when it developed that sad theme.

02:52:39.730 --> 02:52:45.810
And mindful of Helen's warnings against the indulgence of resentment, I infused into the

02:52:45.810 --> 02:52:53.010
narrative far less of gall and warm wood than ordinary. Thus restrained and simplified,

02:52:53.550 --> 02:52:59.730
it sounded more credible. I felt as I went on that Miss Temple fully believed me.

02:53:01.230 --> 02:53:07.690
In the course of the tale I had mentioned Mr. Lloyd as having come to see me after the fit,

02:53:08.510 --> 02:53:16.810
for I never forgot the, to me, frightful episode of The Red Room, in detailing which my excitement

02:53:16.810 --> 02:53:23.350
was sure, in some degree, to break bounds, for nothing could soften in my recollection

02:53:23.350 --> 02:53:30.530
the spasm of agony which clutched my heart when Mrs. Reed spurned my wild supplication for pardon

02:53:31.350 --> 02:53:35.450
and locked me a second time in the dark and haunted chamber.

02:53:36.890 --> 02:53:42.850
I had finished. Miss Temple regarded me a few minutes in silence. She then said,

02:53:43.790 --> 02:53:50.390
I know something of Mr. Lloyd. I shall write to him if his reply agrees with your statement.

02:53:51.010 --> 02:53:57.510
You shall be publicly cleared from every imputation. To me, Jane, you are clear now.

02:53:58.690 --> 02:54:04.790
She kissed me and stuck keeping me at her side, where I was well contented to stand,

02:54:05.430 --> 02:54:11.870
for I derived a child's pleasure from the contemplation of her face, her dress, her one

02:54:11.870 --> 02:54:19.870
or two ornaments, her white forehead, her clustered and shining curls, and beaming dark eyes. She

02:54:19.870 --> 02:54:25.450
proceeded to address Helen Burns. How are you tonight, Helen? Have you coughed much today?

02:54:26.330 --> 02:54:31.330
Not quite so much, I think, ma'am. And the pain in your chest?

02:54:32.450 --> 02:54:39.090
It is a little better. Miss Temple got up, took her hand, and examined her pulse.

02:54:39.910 --> 02:54:46.890
Then she returned to her own seat. As she resumed it, I heard her sigh low. She was pensive a few

02:54:46.890 --> 02:54:53.730
minutes. Then, rousing herself, she said cheerfully, But you two are my visitors tonight.

02:54:53.870 --> 02:55:01.870
I must treat you as such. She rang a bell. Barbara? She said to the servant who answered it,

02:55:02.810 --> 02:55:08.330
I have not yet had tea. Bring the tray and place cups for these two young ladies.

02:55:09.870 --> 02:55:16.770
And a tray was soon brought. How pretty to my eyes did the china cups and bright teapot look.

02:55:16.890 --> 02:55:22.570
Placed on a little round table near the fire. How fragrant was the steam of the beverage

02:55:22.570 --> 02:55:30.250
and the scent of the toast? Of which, however, I, to my dismay, for I was beginning to be hungry,

02:55:31.110 --> 02:55:35.590
discerned only a very small portion. Miss Temple discerned it, too.

02:55:36.470 --> 02:55:40.970
Barbara, said she, Can you not bring a little more bread and butter?

02:55:41.510 --> 02:55:46.230
There is not enough for three. Barbara went out. She returned soon.

02:55:46.890 --> 02:55:51.630
Madam, Mrs. Hardin says she has sent up the usual quantity.

02:55:52.970 --> 02:56:00.210
Mrs. Hardin, be it observed, was the housekeeper, a woman after Mr. Brocklehurst's own heart,

02:56:00.970 --> 02:56:09.030
made up of equal parts of whalebone and iron. Oh, very well, returned Miss Temple. We must make

02:56:09.030 --> 02:56:16.250
do, Barbara, I suppose. And as the girl withdrew, she added smiling, Fortunately,

02:56:16.710 --> 02:56:20.930
I have it in my power to supply deficiencies for this once.

02:56:22.870 --> 02:56:29.010
Having invited Helen and me to approach the table and place before each of us a cup of tea

02:56:29.010 --> 02:56:36.610
with one delicious but thin morsel of toast, she got up, unlocked a drawer, and taking from it

02:56:36.610 --> 02:56:43.490
a parcel, wrapped in paper, disclosed presently to our eyes a good-sized seed cake.

02:56:44.450 --> 02:56:48.150
I meant to give each of you some of this to take with you,

02:56:48.630 --> 02:56:53.390
said she. But as there is so little toast, you must have it now.

02:56:54.410 --> 02:56:57.770
And she proceeded to cut slices with a generous hand.

02:57:00.330 --> 02:57:04.050
We feasted that evening as on nectar and ambrosia,

02:57:04.050 --> 02:57:10.610
and not the least delight of the entertainment was a smile of gratification with which our hostess

02:57:10.610 --> 02:57:17.670
regarded us, as we satisfied our famished appetites on the delicate fare she liberally supplied.

02:57:18.970 --> 02:57:26.630
Tea over and the tray removed, she again summoned us to the fire. We sat one on each side of her,

02:57:26.990 --> 02:57:33.550
and now a conversation followed between her and Helen, which it was indeed a privilege

02:57:33.550 --> 02:57:40.690
to be admitted to here. Miss Temple had always something of serenity in her air,

02:57:41.290 --> 02:57:49.230
of state in her mien, of refined propriety in her language, which precluded deviation into the

02:57:49.230 --> 02:57:56.010
ardent, the excited, the eager, something which chastened the pleasure of those who looked on her

02:57:56.010 --> 02:58:02.810
and listened to her by a controlling sense of awe. And such was my feeling now, but as to Helen

02:58:02.810 --> 02:58:12.230
I was struck with wonder. The refreshing meal, the brilliant fire, the presence and kindness of her

02:58:12.230 --> 02:58:19.170
beloved instructress, or, perhaps more than all these, something in her own unique mind had roused

02:58:19.170 --> 02:58:26.250
her powers within her. They woke, they kindled. First they glowed in the bright tint of her cheek,

02:58:26.890 --> 02:58:34.310
which till this hour I had never seen but pale and bloodless. Then they shone in the liquid luster

02:58:34.310 --> 02:58:42.010
of her eyes, which had suddenly acquired a beauty more singular than that of Miss Temple's, a beauty

02:58:42.010 --> 02:58:48.950
neither of fine colour, nor long eyelash, nor penciled brow, but of meaning, of movement,

02:58:48.950 --> 02:58:57.430
of radiance. Then her soul sat on her lips, and language flowed, from what source I cannot tell.

02:58:58.250 --> 02:59:04.870
Has a girl of fourteen a heart large enough, vigorous enough, to hold the swelling spring

02:59:04.870 --> 02:59:12.510
of pure, full, fervid eloquence? Such was a characteristic of Helen's discourse on that,

02:59:12.510 --> 02:59:19.570
to me, memorable evening. Her spirit seemed hastening to live within a very brief span,

02:59:20.170 --> 02:59:23.750
as much as many live during a protracted existence.

02:59:25.390 --> 02:59:32.330
They conversed of things I had never heard of, of nations and times past, of countries far away,

02:59:33.010 --> 02:59:39.610
of secrets of nature discovered or guessed at. They spoke of books, how many they had read,

02:59:40.330 --> 02:59:46.750
what stores of knowledge they possessed. Then they seemed so familiar with French names

02:59:46.750 --> 02:59:52.990
and French authors. But my amazement reached its climax when Miss Temple asked Helen

02:59:52.990 --> 02:59:58.010
if she sometimes snatched a moment to recall the Latin her father had taught her.

02:59:58.910 --> 03:00:05.050
And, taking a book from the shelf, bade her read and construe a page of Virgil.

03:00:05.590 --> 03:00:10.870
And Helen obeyed, my organ of veneration expanding at every sounding line.

03:00:11.670 --> 03:00:14.750
She had scarcely finished, ere the bell announced bedtime.

03:00:16.450 --> 03:00:23.330
No delay could be admitted. Miss Temple embraced us both, saying, as she drew us to her heart,

03:00:24.130 --> 03:00:30.010
God bless you, my children. Helen she held a little longer than me.

03:00:30.530 --> 03:00:36.970
She let her go more reluctantly. It was Helen her eye followed to the door. It was for her

03:00:36.970 --> 03:00:43.390
a second time, breathed a sad sigh. For her she wept a tear from her cheek.

03:00:45.330 --> 03:00:51.490
On reaching the bedroom we heard the voice of Miss Scatchard. She was examining drawers.

03:00:52.270 --> 03:00:59.290
She had just pulled out Helen Burns's. And when we entered Helen was greeted with a sharp reprimand,

03:00:59.290 --> 03:01:06.290
and told that tomorrow she should have half a dozen of untidily folded articles pinned to

03:01:06.290 --> 03:01:15.230
her shoulder. My things were indeed in shameful disorder, murmured Helen to me in a low voice.

03:01:16.110 --> 03:01:23.710
I intended to have arranged them, but I forgot. Next morning Miss Scatchard wrote

03:01:23.710 --> 03:01:32.110
inconspicuous characters on a piece of pasteboard, the word slattern, and bound it like a phylactery

03:01:32.670 --> 03:01:39.810
round Helen's large, mild, intelligent and benign-looking forehead. She wore it till evening,

03:01:40.210 --> 03:01:47.910
patient, unresentful, regarding it as a deserved punishment. The moment Miss Scatchard withdrew

03:01:47.910 --> 03:01:55.510
after afternoon school, I ran to Helen, tore it off, and thrust it into the fire, the fury of which

03:01:55.510 --> 03:02:03.050
she was incapable, had been burning in my soul all day, and tears, hot and large, had continually

03:02:03.050 --> 03:02:10.850
been scalding my cheek, for the spectacle of her sad resignation gave me an intolerable pain at the heart.

03:02:12.630 --> 03:02:19.830
About a week subsequently to the incidents above narrated, Miss Temple, who had written to Mr. Lloyd,

03:02:20.430 --> 03:02:28.210
received his answer. It appeared that what he said went to corroborate my account. Miss Temple,

03:02:28.470 --> 03:02:34.070
having assembled the whole school, announced the inquiry had been made into the charges alleged

03:02:34.070 --> 03:02:39.990
against Jane Eyre, and that she was most happy to be able to pronounce her completely cleared

03:02:39.990 --> 03:02:46.950
from every imputation. The teachers then shook hands with me and kissed me, and a murmur of pleasure

03:02:46.950 --> 03:02:54.830
ran through the ranks of my companions. Thus relieved of a grievous load, I, from that hour,

03:02:55.150 --> 03:03:01.590
set to work afresh, resolved to pioneer my way through every difficulty. I toiled hard,

03:03:01.850 --> 03:03:09.170
and my success was proportionate to my effort. My memory, not naturally tenacious, improved with

03:03:09.170 --> 03:03:17.110
practice. Exercise sharpened my wits. In a few weeks I was promoted to a higher class. In less

03:03:17.110 --> 03:03:23.010
than two months I was allowed to commence French and drawing. I learned the first two tenses of the

03:03:23.010 --> 03:03:31.190
verb etre, and sketched my first cottage, whose walls, by the by, outriled and sloped those of

03:03:31.190 --> 03:03:39.770
leaning tower of Pisa on the same day. That night, on going to bed, I forgot to prepare

03:03:40.530 --> 03:03:47.590
in imagination the barma-sized supper of hot roast potatoes, or white bread and new milk,

03:03:48.250 --> 03:03:55.310
with which I was wont to amuse my inward cravings. I feasted instead on the spectacle of ideal

03:03:55.310 --> 03:04:02.990
drawings, which I saw in the dark, all the work of my own hands, freely penciled houses and trees,

03:04:03.390 --> 03:04:09.830
picture-esque rocks and ruins, cup-like groups of cattle, sweet paintings of butterflies

03:04:09.830 --> 03:04:17.090
hovering over unblown roses, of birds picking at ripe cherries, of wren's nests

03:04:17.090 --> 03:04:25.150
and closing pearl-like eggs, wreathed about with young ivy sprays. I examined, too, in thought,

03:04:25.550 --> 03:04:32.390
the possibility of my ever being able to translate currently a certain little French story which Madame

03:04:32.390 --> 03:04:47.070
Perrault had that day shown me, nor was that problem solved to my satisfaction ere I fell

03:04:47.070 --> 03:04:53.230
than a stalled ox and hatred therewith. I would not now have exchanged Lowood

03:04:53.230 --> 03:04:57.910
with all its pervations for Gateshead and its daily luxuries.

03:05:18.950 --> 03:05:21.750
CHAPTER IX.

03:05:23.390 --> 03:05:32.830
But the pervations, or rather the hardships, of Lowood lessened. Spring drew on. She was indeed

03:05:32.830 --> 03:05:41.010
already come. The frost of winter had ceased. Its snows were melted. Its cutting winds ameliorated.

03:05:41.950 --> 03:05:50.090
My rigid feet, flayed and swollen to lameness by the sharp air of January, began to heal and

03:05:50.090 --> 03:05:56.570
subside under the gentler breathings of April. The nights and mornings, no longer by their

03:05:56.570 --> 03:06:02.750
Canadian temperature froze the very blood in our veins, we could now endure the play hour passed

03:06:02.750 --> 03:06:10.590
in the garden. Sometimes, on a sunny day, it began even to be pleasant and genial, and a

03:06:10.590 --> 03:06:17.210
greenness grew over those brown beds, which, freshening daily, suggested the thought that

03:06:17.810 --> 03:06:25.530
traversed them at night, and left each morning brighter traces of her steps. Flowers peeped out

03:06:25.530 --> 03:06:35.250
amongst the leaves, snowdrops, crocuses, purple arulaculas, and golden-eyed pansies. On Thursday

03:06:35.250 --> 03:06:43.050
afternoons, half holidays, we now took walks, and found still sweeter flowers opening by the

03:06:43.050 --> 03:06:51.290
side, under the hedges. I discovered, too, that a great pleasure, an enjoyment which the horizon

03:06:51.290 --> 03:06:58.090
only bounded, lay all outside the high and spiked guarded walls of our garden. This pleasure

03:06:58.090 --> 03:07:05.730
consisted in prospect of noble summits girdling a great hill hollow, rich in verdure and shadow,

03:07:05.730 --> 03:07:13.710
in a bright beck full of dark stones and sparkling eddies. How different had this scene looked when

03:07:13.710 --> 03:07:20.110
I viewed it laid out beneath the iron sky of winter, stiffened in frost, shrouded with snow.

03:07:20.950 --> 03:07:27.330
When mist as chill as death wandered to the impulse of east winds along those purple peaks,

03:07:27.910 --> 03:07:34.690
and rolled down Ing and Holm till they blended with the frozen fog of the beck. That beck itself

03:07:34.690 --> 03:07:41.990
was then a torrent, turbid and curbless. It tore asunder the wood, and sent a raving sound through

03:07:41.990 --> 03:07:51.030
the air, often thickened with wild rain or whirling sleet. And for the forest on its banks, that showed

03:07:51.030 --> 03:08:00.950
only ranks of skeletons. April advanced to May, a bright serene May it was. Days of blue sky,

03:08:00.950 --> 03:08:09.110
placid sunshine, and soft western or southern gales filled up its duration, and now vegetation

03:08:09.110 --> 03:08:18.310
matured with vigor. Lowood shook loose its tresses. It became all green, all flowery. Its great elm,

03:08:18.530 --> 03:08:26.630
ash and oak skeletons were restored to majestic life. Woodland plants sprang up profusely in its

03:08:27.990 --> 03:08:35.610
unnumbered varieties of moss filled its hollows, and it made a strange ground sunshine out of the

03:08:35.610 --> 03:08:43.030
wealth of its wild primrose plants. I have seen their pale gold gleam in overshadowed spots like

03:08:43.030 --> 03:08:50.630
scatterings of the sweetest luster. All this I enjoyed often and fully, free, unwatched,

03:08:50.630 --> 03:08:59.030
and almost alone. For this unwanted liberty and pleasure, there was a cause, to which it now

03:08:59.030 --> 03:09:07.550
becomes my task to advert. Have I not described a pleasant sight for a dwelling, when I speak of it

03:09:07.550 --> 03:09:14.090
as bosomed in del and wood, and rising from the verge of a stream? Assuredly pleasant enough,

03:09:14.090 --> 03:09:21.970
but whether healthy or not is another question. That forest del where Lowood lay was the cradle

03:09:21.970 --> 03:09:29.390
of fog and fog-bred pestilence, which quickening with a quickening spring crept into the orphan

03:09:29.390 --> 03:09:36.670
asylum, breathed typhus through its crowded schoolroom and dormitory, and air may arrived

03:09:36.670 --> 03:09:45.090
transformed the seminary into a hospital. Semi-starvation and neglected colds had

03:09:45.090 --> 03:09:51.370
predisposed most of the pupils to receive infection. Forty-five out of the eighty girls

03:09:51.370 --> 03:09:59.550
lay ill at one time. Classes were broken up, rules relaxed. The few who continued well were allowed

03:09:59.550 --> 03:10:05.790
almost unlimited license, because the medical attendant insisted on the necessity of frequent

03:10:05.790 --> 03:10:12.470
exercise to keep them in health, and had it been otherwise, no one had leisure to watch or restrain

03:10:12.470 --> 03:10:19.690
them. Miss Temple's whole attention was absorbed by the patients. She lived in the sickroom,

03:10:20.090 --> 03:10:26.190
never quitting it except to snatch a few hours' rest at night. The teachers were fully occupied

03:10:26.190 --> 03:10:32.690
with packing up and making other necessary preparations for the departure of those girls

03:10:32.690 --> 03:10:38.450
who were fortunate enough to have friends and relations able and willing to remove them from

03:10:38.450 --> 03:10:46.470
the seat of contagion. Many, already smitten, went home only to die. Some died at the school,

03:10:46.970 --> 03:10:52.670
and were buried quietly and quickly, the nature of the malady forbidding delay.

03:10:54.190 --> 03:10:59.870
While disease had thus become an inhabitant of Lowood and death its frequent visitor,

03:10:59.870 --> 03:11:07.790
while there was gloom and fear within its walls, while its rooms and passages steamed with hospital

03:11:07.790 --> 03:11:14.170
smells, the drug and the past still striving mainly to overcome the effluvia of mortality,

03:11:15.030 --> 03:11:29.810
that bright May shone unclouded over the bold hills and beautiful woodland out of doors. Its

03:11:29.810 --> 03:11:37.110
opened. Tulips and roses were in bloom. The borders of the little beds were gay with pink

03:11:37.110 --> 03:11:43.750
thrift and crimson double daisies. The sweetbriars gave out, morning and evening, their scent of

03:11:43.750 --> 03:11:50.750
spice and apples. For these fragrant treasures were all useless for most of the inmates of Lowood,

03:11:51.250 --> 03:11:56.270
except to furnish now and then a handful of herbs and blossoms to put in a coffin.

03:11:57.090 --> 03:12:04.310
But I, and the rest who continued well, enjoyed fully the beauties of the scene and season. They

03:12:04.310 --> 03:12:10.170
let us ramble in the wood like gypsies from morning till night. We did what we liked,

03:12:10.610 --> 03:12:17.490
went where we liked. We lived better, too. Mr. Brocklehurst and family never came near Lowood

03:12:17.490 --> 03:12:25.070
now. Household matters were not scrutinized into. The cross-housekeeper was gone, driven away by the

03:12:25.070 --> 03:12:32.950
fear of infection. Her successor, who had been matron at the Lowood dispensary, unused to the

03:12:32.950 --> 03:12:40.050
ways of her new abode, provided with comparative liberality. Besides, there were fewer to feed.

03:12:40.550 --> 03:12:47.630
The sick could eat little. Our breakfast basins were better filled. When there was no time to

03:12:47.630 --> 03:12:53.230
prepare a regular dinner, which often happened, she would give us a large piece of cold pie,

03:12:53.230 --> 03:12:58.770
or a thick slice of bread and cheese. And this we carried away with us to the wood,

03:12:59.350 --> 03:13:06.050
where we each chose the spot we liked best, and dined sumptuously. My favorite seat was a

03:13:06.050 --> 03:13:13.310
smooth and broad stone, rising white and dry from the very middle of the beck, and only to be got

03:13:13.310 --> 03:13:20.370
at by wading through the water, a feat I accomplished barefoot. The stone was just broad enough to

03:13:20.370 --> 03:13:28.350
accommodate, comfortably, another girl and me. At that time my chosen comrade, one Mary Anne Wilson,

03:13:29.150 --> 03:13:35.950
a shrewd, observant personage, whose society I took pleasure in, partly because she was witty

03:13:35.950 --> 03:13:43.510
and original, and partly because she had a manner which set me at my ease. Some years older than I,

03:13:43.890 --> 03:13:49.350
she knew more of the world, and could tell me many things I liked to hear. With her,

03:13:49.350 --> 03:13:56.850
my curiosity found gratification. To my faults also she gave ample indulgence, never imposing

03:13:56.850 --> 03:14:05.490
curb or rain on anything I said. She had a turn for narrative, I for analysis. She liked to inform,

03:14:05.850 --> 03:14:13.310
I to question. So we got on swimmingly together, deriving much entertainment, if not much

03:14:13.310 --> 03:14:21.270
improvement, from our mutual intercourse. And where, meantime, was Helen Burns? Why did I not

03:14:21.270 --> 03:14:27.890
spend these sweet days of liberty with her? Had I forgotten her? Or was I so worthless as to have

03:14:27.890 --> 03:14:34.770
grown tired of her pure society? Surely the Mary Anne Wilson I have mentioned was inferior to my

03:14:34.770 --> 03:14:41.450
first acquaintance. She could only tell me amusing stories, and reciprocate any racy and pungent

03:14:41.450 --> 03:14:48.050
gossip I chose to indulge in, while, if I had spoken truth of Helen, she was qualified to give

03:14:48.050 --> 03:14:54.910
those who enjoyed the privilege of her converse a taste of far higher things. True, reader,

03:14:55.450 --> 03:15:01.610
and I knew and felt this. And though I am a defective being, with many faults and few

03:15:01.610 --> 03:15:09.430
redeeming points, yet I never tired of Helen Burns, nor even ceased to cherish for her a sentiment

03:15:09.430 --> 03:15:18.370
of attachment, as strong, tender, and respectful as any that ever animated my heart. How could

03:15:18.370 --> 03:15:25.070
it be otherwise when Helen, at all times and under all circumstances, evinced for me a quiet

03:15:25.070 --> 03:15:33.250
and faithful friendship, which ill humor never soured, nor irritation never troubled? But Helen

03:15:33.250 --> 03:15:40.170
was ill at present. For some weeks she had been removed from my sight, till I knew not what room

03:15:40.170 --> 03:15:47.690
upstairs. She was not, I was told, in the hospital portion of the house with the fever patients.

03:15:49.050 --> 03:15:55.830
For her complaint was consumption, not typhus. And by consumption I, in my ignorance,

03:15:55.830 --> 03:16:02.130
understood something mild, which time and care would be sure to alleviate.

03:16:03.310 --> 03:16:09.670
I was confirmed in this idea by the fact of her once or twice coming downstairs on very warm,

03:16:09.930 --> 03:16:16.890
sunny afternoons, and being taken by Miss Temple into the garden. But on these occasions I was not

03:16:16.890 --> 03:16:24.610
allowed to go and speak to her. I only saw her from the schoolroom window, and then, not distinctly,

03:16:24.610 --> 03:16:29.950
for she was much wrapped up, and sat at a distance under the veranda.

03:16:31.550 --> 03:16:36.930
One evening, in the beginning of June, I had stayed out very late with Mary Anne in the wood.

03:16:37.590 --> 03:16:45.470
We had, as usual, separated ourselves from the others, and had wandered off far, so far that we

03:16:45.470 --> 03:16:53.950
lost our way, and had to ask it at a lonely cottage, where a man and woman lived, who looked after a

03:16:53.950 --> 03:17:02.230
of half-wild swine that fed on the mast in the wood. When we got back, it was after moonrise,

03:17:02.690 --> 03:17:10.350
a pony, which we knew to be the surgeon's, was standing at the garden door. Mary Anne remarked

03:17:10.350 --> 03:17:17.150
that she supposed someone must be very ill, as Mr. Bates had been sent for at that time of the

03:17:17.150 --> 03:17:23.150
evening. She went into the house. I stayed behind a few minutes to plant in my garden

03:17:23.150 --> 03:17:29.010
a handful of roots I had dug up in the forest, in which I feared would wither if I left them

03:17:29.010 --> 03:17:36.130
till the morning. This done, I lingered yet a little longer. The flowers smelt so sweet

03:17:36.130 --> 03:17:44.590
as the dew fell. It was such a pleasant evening, so serene, so warm. The still-glowing west promised

03:17:44.590 --> 03:17:51.950
so fairly another fine day on the morrow. The moon rose with such majesty in the grave east.

03:17:52.770 --> 03:17:59.250
I was noting these things and enjoying them as a child might, when it entered my mind as it had

03:17:59.250 --> 03:18:06.130
never done before. How sad to be lying now on a sickbed, and to be in danger of dying.

03:18:06.710 --> 03:18:12.390
This world is pleasant. It would be dreary to be called from it, and to have to go who knows where.

03:18:13.270 --> 03:18:19.870
And then my mind made its first earnest effort to comprehend what had been infused into it,

03:18:20.030 --> 03:18:26.550
concerning heaven and hell, and for the first time it recoiled, baffled, and for the first time

03:18:26.550 --> 03:18:34.290
glancing behind on each side, and before it, it saw all round an unfathomed gulf. It felt the one

03:18:34.290 --> 03:18:41.930
point where it stood, the present. All the rest was formless cloud and vacant depth, and it shuddered

03:18:41.930 --> 03:18:49.290
the thought of tottering and plunging amid the chaos. While pondering this new idea, I heard the

03:18:49.290 --> 03:18:57.130
front door open. Mr. Bates came out, and with him was a nurse. After she had seen him mount his horse

03:18:57.130 --> 03:19:03.830
and depart, she was about to close the door, but I ran up to her. How is Helen Burns?

03:19:04.870 --> 03:19:14.190
Very poorly was the answer. Is it her Mr. Bates has been to see? Yes. And what does he say about her?

03:19:15.090 --> 03:19:22.450
He says she'll not be here long. This phrase, uttered in my hearing yesterday, would have only

03:19:22.450 --> 03:19:27.950
conveyed the notion that she was about to be removed to Northumberland, to her own home.

03:19:28.590 --> 03:19:34.890
I should not have suspected that it meant she was dying, but I knew instantly now. It opened clear

03:19:34.890 --> 03:19:41.110
on my comprehension that Helen Burns was numbering her last days in this world, and that she was

03:19:41.110 --> 03:19:47.650
going to be taken to the region of spirits, if such region there were. I experienced a shock of

03:19:47.650 --> 03:19:55.490
horror, then a strong thrill of grief, then a desire, a necessity to see her, and I asked in

03:19:55.490 --> 03:20:02.350
what room she lay. She is in Miss Temple's room, said the nurse. May I go up and speak to her?

03:20:03.250 --> 03:20:08.430
Oh no, child, it is not likely, and now it is time for you to come in.

03:20:08.810 --> 03:20:11.610
You'll catch the fever if you stop out when the dew is falling.

03:20:13.510 --> 03:20:19.490
The nurse closed the front door. I went in by the side entrance, which led to the school room.

03:20:19.490 --> 03:20:26.530
I was just in time. It was nine o'clock, and Miss Miller was calling the pupils to go to bed.

03:20:27.790 --> 03:20:34.450
It might be two hours later, probably near eleven, when I, not having been able to fall asleep,

03:20:34.830 --> 03:20:40.030
and deeming from the perfect silence of the dormitory, that my companions were all wrapped

03:20:40.030 --> 03:20:47.490
in profound repose, rose softly, put on my frock over my nightdress, and without shoes,

03:20:47.490 --> 03:20:52.290
crept from the apartment, and set off in quest of Miss Temple's room.

03:20:53.130 --> 03:20:59.690
It was quite at the other end of the house, but I knew my way, and the light of the unclouded

03:20:59.690 --> 03:21:06.070
summer moon entering here and there at passage windows enabled me to find it without difficulty.

03:21:07.130 --> 03:21:12.970
An odor of camphor and burnt vinegar warned me when I came near the fever room,

03:21:12.970 --> 03:21:19.230
and I passed its door quickly, fearful lest the nurse who sat up all night should hear me.

03:21:20.030 --> 03:21:26.830
I dreaded being discouraged and sent back, for I must see Helen. I must embrace her before she died.

03:21:27.150 --> 03:21:31.990
I must give her one last kiss, exchange with her one last word.

03:21:33.390 --> 03:21:37.590
Having descended a staircase, traversed a portion of the house below,

03:21:38.110 --> 03:21:44.870
and succeeded in opening and shutting, without noise, two doors, I reached another flight of

03:21:44.870 --> 03:21:53.290
steps. These I mounted, and then, just opposite to me, was Miss Temple's room. A light shone

03:21:53.290 --> 03:21:57.990
through the keyhole, and from under the door, a profound stillness pervaded the vicinity.

03:21:58.410 --> 03:22:04.810
Coming near, I found the door slightly ajar, probably to admit some fresh air into the

03:22:04.810 --> 03:22:10.570
abode of sickness. Indisposed to hesitate, and full of impatient impulses,

03:22:11.630 --> 03:22:18.590
soul and senses quivering with keen throws, I put it back and looked in. My eye sought Helen,

03:22:19.010 --> 03:22:25.810
and feared to find death. Close by Miss Temple's bed, and half covered with its white curtains,

03:22:26.670 --> 03:22:32.210
there stood a little crib. I saw the outline of a form under the clothes,

03:22:32.790 --> 03:22:40.470
but the face was hid by the hangings. The nurse I had spoken to in the garden sat in an easy chair,

03:22:40.650 --> 03:22:48.470
asleep. An unsnuffed candle burnt dimly on the table. Miss Temple was not to be seen.

03:22:49.650 --> 03:22:54.790
I knew afterwards that she had been called to a delirious patient in the fever room.

03:22:55.370 --> 03:23:03.090
I advanced, then paused by the crib side. My hand was on the curtain, but I preferred speaking

03:23:03.090 --> 03:23:08.070
before I withdrew it. I still recoiled at the dread of seeing a corpse.

03:23:09.110 --> 03:23:16.030
Helen, I whispered softly, are you awake? She stirred herself, put back the curtain,

03:23:16.030 --> 03:23:20.910
and I saw her face, pale, wasted, but quite composed.

03:23:22.590 --> 03:23:27.050
She looked so little changed that my fear was instantly dissipated.

03:23:28.930 --> 03:23:37.270
Can it be you, Jane? She asked in her own gentle voice. Oh, I thought, she is not going to die.

03:23:37.550 --> 03:23:41.590
They are mistaken. She could not speak and look so calmly if she were.

03:23:42.230 --> 03:23:49.910
I got onto her crib and kissed her. Her forehead was cold and her cheek both cold and thin,

03:23:50.370 --> 03:23:55.150
and so were both her hand and wrist, but she smiled as of old.

03:23:56.010 --> 03:24:02.390
Why are you come here, Jane? It is past eleven o'clock. I heard it strike some minutes since.

03:24:03.150 --> 03:24:09.050
I came to see you, Helen. I heard you were very ill, and I could not sleep till I had spoken to

03:24:09.050 --> 03:24:14.210
you. You came to bid me good-bye, then. You were just in time, probably.

03:24:15.250 --> 03:24:23.010
Are you going somewhere, Helen? Are you going home? Yes, to my long home, my last home.

03:24:23.710 --> 03:24:31.370
No, no, Helen. I stopped, distressed. While I tried to devour my tears, a fit of coughing seized

03:24:31.370 --> 03:24:38.470
Helen. It did not, however, wake the nurse. When it was over, she lay some minutes exhausted.

03:24:39.050 --> 03:24:39.850
Then she whispered,

03:24:41.410 --> 03:24:46.330
Jane, your little feet are bare. Lie down and cover yourself with my quilt.

03:24:47.370 --> 03:24:51.710
I did so. She put her arm over me, and I nestled close to her.

03:24:52.330 --> 03:24:55.590
After a long silence, she resumed, still whispering,

03:24:56.290 --> 03:25:02.030
I am very happy, Jane, and when you hear that I am dead, you must be sure and not grieve.

03:25:02.550 --> 03:25:08.050
There is nothing to grieve about. We almost die one day, and the illness which is removing me

03:25:08.050 --> 03:25:16.070
is not painful. It is gentle and gradual. My mind is at rest. I leave no one to regret me much.

03:25:16.570 --> 03:25:23.310
I have only a father, and he is lately married, and will not miss me. By dying young,

03:25:23.450 --> 03:25:29.770
I shall escape great sufferings. I had not qualities or talents to make my way very well

03:25:29.770 --> 03:25:35.790
in the world. I should have been continually at fault. But where are you going to, Helen?

03:25:35.790 --> 03:25:41.990
Can you see? Do you know? I believe I have faith I am going to God.

03:25:43.030 --> 03:25:49.910
Where is God? What is God? My Maker and yours, who will never destroy what He created,

03:25:50.650 --> 03:25:56.950
I rely implicitly on His power and confide wholly in His goodness. I count the hours

03:25:56.950 --> 03:26:02.370
till that eventful One arrives, which shall restore me to Him, reveal Him to me.

03:26:03.090 --> 03:26:08.490
You are sure, then, Helen, that there is such a place as heaven, and that our souls can get

03:26:08.490 --> 03:26:16.250
to it when we die? I am sure there is a future state. I believe God is good. I can resign my

03:26:16.250 --> 03:26:23.030
immortal part to Him without any misgiving. God is my Father. God is my Friend. I love Him.

03:26:23.330 --> 03:26:29.290
I believe He loves me. And shall I see you again, Helen, when I die?

03:26:29.990 --> 03:26:36.890
You will come to the same region of happiness, be received by the same mighty universal parent.

03:26:37.370 --> 03:26:43.530
No doubt, dear Jane. Again I questioned, but this time only in thought.

03:26:44.610 --> 03:26:50.390
Where is that region? Does it exist? And I clasped my arms closer around heaven.

03:26:51.810 --> 03:26:59.210
She seemed dearer to me than ever. I felt as if I could not let her go. I lay with my face hidden

03:26:59.210 --> 03:27:06.750
on her neck. Presently, she said, in the sweetest tone, how comfortable I am. That last bit of

03:27:06.750 --> 03:27:13.990
coughing has tired me a little. I feel as if I could sleep. But don't leave me, Jane. I like

03:27:13.990 --> 03:27:22.790
to have you near me. I'll stay with you, dear Helen. No one shall take me away. Are you warm, darling?

03:27:23.790 --> 03:27:34.070
Yes. Good night, Jane. Good night, Helen. She kissed me and I her, and we both soon slumbered.

03:27:35.690 --> 03:27:44.250
When I awoke, it was day. An unusual movement roused me. I looked up. I was in somebody's arms.

03:27:45.130 --> 03:27:52.390
The nurse held me. She was carrying me back through the passage to the dormitory. I was not

03:27:52.390 --> 03:27:58.970
reprimanded for leaving my bed. People had something else to think about. No explanation

03:27:58.970 --> 03:28:05.550
was afforded then to my many questions. But a day or two afterwards, I learned that Miss Temple,

03:28:06.190 --> 03:28:13.050
on returning to her own room at dawn, had found me laid in the little crib, my face against Helen

03:28:13.050 --> 03:28:19.330
shoulders, my arm around her neck. I was asleep and Helen was dead.

03:28:21.670 --> 03:28:28.770
Her grave is in Brockle Bridge Churchyard. For fifteen years after her death, it was only

03:28:28.770 --> 03:28:36.290
covered by a grassy mound. But now a gray marble tablet marks the spot, inscribed with her name

03:28:36.290 --> 03:28:38.270
and the word RASARGAM.

03:28:52.610 --> 03:28:53.130
X.

03:28:57.150 --> 03:29:01.990
Hitherto I have recorded in detail the events of my insignificant existence.

03:29:02.290 --> 03:29:06.170
To the first ten years of my life I have given almost as many chapters.

03:29:06.910 --> 03:29:09.590
But this is not to be a regular autobiography.

03:29:09.590 --> 03:29:15.490
I am only bound to invoke memory where I know her responses will possess some degree of interest.

03:29:16.150 --> 03:29:20.650
Therefore, I now pass a space of eight years almost in silence.

03:29:21.490 --> 03:29:24.970
A few lines only are necessary to keep up the length of connection.

03:29:25.670 --> 03:29:32.190
When the typhus fever had fulfilled its mission of devastation at Lowood, it gradually disappeared from thence.

03:29:32.510 --> 03:29:38.130
But not till its virulence and the number of its victims had drawn public attention on the school.

03:29:39.750 --> 03:29:42.830
Inquiry was made into the origin of the scourge.

03:29:43.630 --> 03:29:48.710
And by degrees various facts came out which excited public indignation in a high degree.

03:29:49.770 --> 03:29:54.690
The unhealthy nature of the site, the quantity and quality of the children's food,

03:29:55.630 --> 03:30:03.030
the brackish, fetid water used in its preparation, the pupils' wretched clothing and accommodations.

03:30:03.630 --> 03:30:05.250
All these things were discovered.

03:30:06.070 --> 03:30:12.990
And the discovery produced a result more defined to Mr. Brocklehurst, but beneficial to the institution.

03:30:14.890 --> 03:30:17.950
Several wealthy and benevolent individuals in the county

03:30:17.950 --> 03:30:22.730
subscribed largely for the erection of a more convenient building and a better situation.

03:30:23.610 --> 03:30:27.890
New regulations were made. Improvements in diet and clothing introduced.

03:30:28.730 --> 03:30:32.010
The funds of the school were entrusted to the management of a committee.

03:30:32.480 --> 03:30:37.630
Mr. Brocklehurst, who, from his wealth and family connections, could not be overlooked,

03:30:38.330 --> 03:30:40.010
still retained the post of treasurer.

03:30:40.710 --> 03:30:46.870
But he was aided in the discharge of his duties by gentlemen of rather more enlarged and sympathizing minds.

03:30:47.790 --> 03:30:53.450
His office of inspector, too, was shared by those who knew how to combine reason with strictness,

03:30:53.850 --> 03:30:57.170
comfort with economy, compassion with uprightness.

03:30:57.910 --> 03:31:04.350
The school, thus improved, became in time a truly useful and noble institution.

03:31:05.590 --> 03:31:11.110
I remained an inmate of its walls, after its regeneration, for eight years.

03:31:11.630 --> 03:31:14.590
Six as pupil and two as teacher.

03:31:15.470 --> 03:31:19.910
And in both capacities I bear my testimony to its value and importance.

03:31:22.090 --> 03:31:26.450
During these eight years my life was uniform, but not unhappy.

03:31:27.190 --> 03:31:34.110
Because it was not inactive, I had the means of an excellent education placed within my reach.

03:31:35.110 --> 03:31:40.650
A fondness for some of my studies, and a desire to excel in all,

03:31:41.390 --> 03:31:48.990
together with a great delight in pleasing my teachers, especially such as I loved, urged me on.

03:31:49.930 --> 03:31:53.430
I availed myself fully of the advantages offered me.

03:31:54.150 --> 03:31:58.730
In time I rose to be the first girl of the first class.

03:31:59.690 --> 03:32:06.490
Then I was invested with the office of teacher, which I discharged with zeal for two years.

03:32:07.430 --> 03:32:09.830
But at the end of that time I altered.

03:32:11.390 --> 03:32:17.410
Miss Temple, through all changes, had thus far continued superintendent of the seminary.

03:32:17.870 --> 03:32:21.610
To her instruction I owed the best part of my acquirements.

03:32:22.350 --> 03:32:26.570
Her friendship and society had been my continual solace.

03:32:26.970 --> 03:32:32.370
She had stood me in the stead of mother, governess, and latterly companion.

03:32:33.690 --> 03:32:39.650
At this period she married, removed with her husband, a clergyman, an excellent man,

03:32:40.130 --> 03:32:45.910
almost worthy of such a wife, to a distant county, and consequently was lost to me.

03:32:46.290 --> 03:32:48.690
From the day she left I was no longer the same.

03:32:49.270 --> 03:32:56.170
With her was gone every settled feeling, every association that had made Lowood in some degree a home to me.

03:32:56.810 --> 03:33:01.010
I had imbibed from her something of her nature and much of her habits.

03:33:01.970 --> 03:33:03.330
More harmonious thoughts.

03:33:03.930 --> 03:33:07.830
What seemed better regulated feelings had become the inmates of my mind.

03:33:08.590 --> 03:33:11.030
I had given in allegiance to duty and order.

03:33:11.570 --> 03:33:12.450
I was quiet.

03:33:13.050 --> 03:33:14.570
I believed I was content.

03:33:15.310 --> 03:33:22.630
To the eyes of others, usually even to my own, I appeared a disciplined and subdued character.

03:33:23.770 --> 03:33:29.150
But destiny, in the shape of the Reverend Mr. Nazmuth, came between me and Miss Temple.

03:33:29.550 --> 03:33:35.570
I saw her in her travelling dress step into a post-chase shortly after the marriage ceremony.

03:33:35.910 --> 03:33:43.210
I watched the chase mount the hill and disappear beyond its brow, and then retired to my own room.

03:33:43.210 --> 03:33:49.730
And there spent in solitude the greatest part of the half-holiday granted in honour of the occasion.

03:33:52.190 --> 03:33:54.390
I walked about the chamber most of the time.

03:33:54.790 --> 03:34:00.370
I imagined myself only to be regretting my loss, and thinking how to repair it.

03:34:00.970 --> 03:34:08.330
But when my reflections were concluded, and I looked up and found that the afternoon was gone and evening far advanced,

03:34:09.010 --> 03:34:15.730
another discovery dawned on me, namely, that in the interval I had undergone a transforming process,

03:34:16.450 --> 03:34:19.590
that my mind had put off all that had borrowed from Miss Temple,

03:34:20.330 --> 03:34:26.850
or rather that she had taken with her the serene atmosphere I had been breathing in her vicinity,

03:34:27.650 --> 03:34:33.630
and that now I was left in my natural element and beginning to feel the stirring of old emotions.

03:34:34.290 --> 03:34:40.650
It did not seem as if a prop were withdrawn, but rather as if a motive were gone.

03:34:41.370 --> 03:34:45.070
It was not the power to be tranquil, which had failed me.

03:34:45.650 --> 03:34:48.450
But the reason for tranquillity was no more.

03:34:49.210 --> 03:34:51.910
My world had for some years been in Lowood.

03:34:52.630 --> 03:34:55.350
My experience had been of its rules and systems.

03:34:55.990 --> 03:35:02.150
Now I remembered that the real world was wide, and that a varied field of hopes and fears,

03:35:02.630 --> 03:35:08.810
of sensations and excitements, awaited those who had courage to go forth into its expanse,

03:35:09.270 --> 03:35:12.650
to seek real knowledge of life amidst its perils.

03:35:13.770 --> 03:35:17.030
I went to my window, opened it, and looked out.

03:35:17.890 --> 03:35:19.730
There were the two wings of the building.

03:35:20.570 --> 03:35:21.730
There was the garden.

03:35:22.690 --> 03:35:24.170
There were the skirts of Lowood.

03:35:24.910 --> 03:35:26.710
There was a hilly horizon.

03:35:27.750 --> 03:35:33.690
My eye passed all other objects to rest on those most remote, the blue peaks.

03:35:34.550 --> 03:35:36.550
It was those I longed to surmount.

03:35:37.550 --> 03:35:43.010
All within their boundary of rock and heath seemed prison ground, exile limits.

03:35:43.990 --> 03:35:51.310
I traced the white road winding round the base of one mountain, and vanishing in a gorge between two.

03:35:52.050 --> 03:35:54.310
How I longed to follow it farther.

03:35:55.250 --> 03:35:58.930
I recall the time when I had traveled that very road in a coach.

03:36:00.030 --> 03:36:02.350
I remembered descending that hill at twilight.

03:36:03.270 --> 03:36:07.890
An age seemed to have elapsed since the day which brought me first to Lowood.

03:36:08.730 --> 03:36:10.750
And I had never quitted it since.

03:36:11.970 --> 03:36:14.490
My vacations had all been spent at school.

03:36:15.470 --> 03:36:18.290
Mrs. Reed had never sent for me to Gateshead.

03:36:18.910 --> 03:36:23.150
Neither she nor any of her family had ever been to visit me.

03:36:23.690 --> 03:36:28.690
I had had no communication by letter or message with the outer world.

03:36:29.350 --> 03:36:41.710
School rules, school duties, school habits and notions and voices and faces and phrases and costumes and preferences and antipathies.

03:36:42.930 --> 03:36:47.750
Such was what I knew of existence, and now I felt that it was not enough.

03:36:48.290 --> 03:36:51.670
I tired of the routine of eight years in one afternoon.

03:36:52.570 --> 03:36:53.610
I desired liberty.

03:36:54.170 --> 03:36:55.730
For liberty I gasped.

03:36:56.130 --> 03:36:57.710
For liberty I uttered a prayer.

03:36:58.430 --> 03:37:01.210
It seemed scattered on the wind, then faintly blowing.

03:37:01.930 --> 03:37:05.910
I abandoned it and framed a humbler supplication.

03:37:06.210 --> 03:37:08.010
For change, stimulus.

03:37:08.970 --> 03:37:13.230
That petition, too, seemed swept off into vague space.

03:37:13.850 --> 03:37:16.990
Then I cried, half-desperate.

03:37:17.330 --> 03:37:19.570
Grant me at least a new servitude.

03:37:21.110 --> 03:37:25.710
Here a bell, ringing the hour of supper, called me downstairs.

03:37:27.050 --> 03:37:31.550
I was not free to resume the interrupted chain of my reflections till bedtime.

03:37:32.450 --> 03:37:39.370
Even then a teacher, who occupied the same room with me, kept me from the subject to which I longed to recur.

03:37:40.110 --> 03:37:42.810
By a prolonged effusion of small talk.

03:37:43.930 --> 03:37:46.050
How I wished sleep would silence her.

03:37:46.970 --> 03:37:58.030
It seemed as if, could I but go back to the idea which had last entered my mind as I stood at the window, some inventive suggestion would rise for my relief.

03:37:59.830 --> 03:38:02.050
Miss Grice snored at last.

03:38:02.470 --> 03:38:04.350
She was a heavy Welsh woman.

03:38:04.990 --> 03:38:12.190
Until now her habitual nasal strains had never been regarded by me in any other light than as a nuisance.

03:38:13.110 --> 03:38:16.210
Tonight I hailed the first deep notes with satisfaction.

03:38:17.010 --> 03:38:19.110
I was debarassed of interruption.

03:38:20.010 --> 03:38:22.670
My half-effaced thought instantly revived.

03:38:23.410 --> 03:38:25.050
A new servitude.

03:38:25.390 --> 03:38:31.810
There is something in that, I soliloquized, mentally, be it understood, I did not talk aloud.

03:38:32.830 --> 03:38:36.050
I know there is, because it does not sound too sweet.

03:38:36.730 --> 03:38:40.650
It is not like such words as liberty, excitement, enjoyment.

03:38:41.690 --> 03:38:45.390
Delightful sounds truly, but no more than sounds for me.

03:38:45.910 --> 03:38:50.750
And so hollow and fleeting that it is mere waste of time to listen to them.

03:38:51.250 --> 03:38:54.890
But servitude, that must be matter of fact.

03:38:55.650 --> 03:38:56.770
Anyone may serve.

03:38:57.450 --> 03:38:59.210
I have served here eight years.

03:38:59.750 --> 03:39:01.870
Now all I want is to serve elsewhere.

03:39:03.150 --> 03:39:05.050
Can I not get so much of my own will?

03:39:05.890 --> 03:39:07.190
Is not the thing feasible?

03:39:07.870 --> 03:39:16.650
Yes, yes, the end is not so difficult, if I had only a brain active enough to ferret out the means of attaining it.

03:39:17.390 --> 03:39:20.890
I sat up in bed, by way of arousing this said brain.

03:39:21.490 --> 03:39:22.730
It was a chilly night.

03:39:23.450 --> 03:39:29.870
I covered my shoulders with a shawl, and then I proceeded to think again with all my might.

03:39:31.390 --> 03:39:32.910
What do I want?

03:39:33.690 --> 03:39:39.910
A new place, in a new house, amongst new faces, under new circumstances.

03:39:40.330 --> 03:39:43.990
I want this because it is of no use wanting anything better.

03:39:44.530 --> 03:39:47.350
How do people do to get a new place?

03:39:48.190 --> 03:39:50.090
They apply to friends, I suppose.

03:39:50.830 --> 03:39:51.910
I have no friends.

03:39:52.790 --> 03:39:58.630
There are many others who have no friends, who must look about for themselves and be their own helpers.

03:39:58.790 --> 03:40:00.270
And what is their resource?

03:40:01.450 --> 03:40:02.790
I could not tell.

03:40:03.590 --> 03:40:04.790
Nothing answered me.

03:40:05.510 --> 03:40:08.910
I then ordered my brain to find a response, and quickly.

03:40:09.590 --> 03:40:11.250
It worked and worked faster.

03:40:11.910 --> 03:40:20.490
I felt the pulses throb in my head and temples, but for nearly an hour it worked in chaos, and no result came of its efforts.

03:40:21.710 --> 03:40:32.710
Feverish with vain labor, I got up and took a turn in the room, undrew the curtain, noted a star or two, shivered with cold, and again crept to bed.

03:40:33.630 --> 03:40:45.650
A kind fairy, in my absence, had surely dropped the required suggestion on my pillow, for as I lay down it came quietly and naturally to my mind.

03:40:46.510 --> 03:40:51.610
Those who want situations advertised, you must advertise in the blank share herald.

03:40:52.750 --> 03:40:53.230
How?

03:40:53.670 --> 03:40:55.490
I know nothing about advertising.

03:40:57.010 --> 03:40:59.330
Replies rose smooth and prompt now.

03:41:00.050 --> 03:41:06.890
You must enclose the advertisement and the money to pay for it under a cover directed to the editor of the herald.

03:41:07.330 --> 03:41:11.910
You must put it, the first opportunity you have, into the post at Loughton.

03:41:12.770 --> 03:41:16.710
Answers must be addressed to J. E. at the post office there.

03:41:17.470 --> 03:41:24.050
You can go and inquire in about a week after you send your letter, if any are come, and act accordingly.

03:41:24.910 --> 03:41:30.310
The scheme I went over twice, thrice, it was then digested in my mind.

03:41:31.070 --> 03:41:33.290
I had it in a clear, practical form.

03:41:33.850 --> 03:41:36.230
I felt satisfied and fell asleep.

03:41:36.650 --> 03:41:38.510
With earliest day I was up.

03:41:39.230 --> 03:41:45.410
I had my advertisement written, enclosed, and directed before the bell rang to rouse the school.

03:41:45.950 --> 03:41:46.930
It ran thus.

03:41:48.110 --> 03:41:53.290
A young lady accustomed to tuition, had I not been a teacher two years?

03:41:54.010 --> 03:41:59.690
Is desirous of meeting with a situation in a private family where the children are under fourteen.

03:42:00.770 --> 03:42:07.150
I thought that as I was barely eighteen, it would not do to undertake the guidance of pupils near my own age.

03:42:08.590 --> 03:42:15.990
She is qualified to teach the usual branches of a good English education, together with French, drawing, and music.

03:42:16.730 --> 03:42:24.710
In those days, reader, this now narrow catalogue of accomplishments would have been held tolerably comprehensive.

03:42:31.490 --> 03:42:35.130
This document remained locked in my drawer all day.

03:42:35.490 --> 03:42:40.290
After tea, I asked leave of the new superintendent to go to Loughton,

03:42:40.290 --> 03:42:46.910
in order to perform some small commissions for myself and one or two of my fellow teachers.

03:42:48.270 --> 03:42:49.730
Permission was readily granted.

03:42:49.990 --> 03:42:50.650
I went.

03:42:51.370 --> 03:42:57.470
It was a walk of two miles, and the evening was wet, but the days were still long.

03:42:58.090 --> 03:43:04.910
I visited a shop or two, slipped the letter into the post office, and came back, through heavy rain,

03:43:05.390 --> 03:43:08.550
with streaming garments, but with a relieved heart.

03:43:09.470 --> 03:43:11.990
The succeeding week seemed long.

03:43:12.810 --> 03:43:17.670
It came to an end at last, however, like all subluninary things,

03:43:18.070 --> 03:43:24.450
and once more, towards the end of a pleasant autumn day, I found myself afoot on the road to Loughton.

03:43:25.830 --> 03:43:34.010
A picturesque track it was, by the way, lying along the side of the beck, and through the sweetest curves of the dale.

03:43:34.630 --> 03:43:41.590
But that day I thought more of the letters, that might or might not be awaiting me at the little bur,

03:43:42.070 --> 03:43:46.210
whither I was bound, than of the charms of lee and water.

03:43:47.330 --> 03:43:52.330
My ostensible errand on this occasion was to get measured for a pair of shoes.

03:43:53.170 --> 03:43:57.910
So I discharged that business first, and when it was done,

03:43:57.910 --> 03:44:03.850
I stepped across the clean and quiet little street from the shoemaker's to the post office.

03:44:04.390 --> 03:44:11.090
It was kept by an old dame, who wore horned spectacles on her nose and black mittens on her hands.

03:44:11.910 --> 03:44:15.070
Are there any letters for J.E.? I asked.

03:44:15.910 --> 03:44:24.290
She peered at me over her spectacles, and then she opened a drawer and fumbled among its contents for a long time,

03:44:24.770 --> 03:44:27.190
so long that my hopes began to falter.

03:44:27.930 --> 03:44:32.590
At last, having held a document before her glasses for nearly five minutes,

03:44:33.190 --> 03:44:38.730
she presented it across the counter, accompanying the act by another inquisitive and mistrustful glance.

03:44:39.430 --> 03:44:40.810
It was for J.E.

03:44:41.410 --> 03:44:43.730
Is there only one? I demanded.

03:44:44.630 --> 03:44:50.550
There are no more, said she, and I put it back in my pocket and turned my face homeward.

03:44:51.070 --> 03:44:57.170
I could not open it then. Rules obliged me to be back by eight, and it was already half past seven.

03:44:58.110 --> 03:45:00.490
Various duties awaited me on my arrival.

03:45:00.670 --> 03:45:03.810
I had to sit with the girls during their hour of study.

03:45:04.550 --> 03:45:08.050
Then it was my turn to read prayers, to see them to bed.

03:45:09.050 --> 03:45:11.330
Afterwards, I supped with the other teachers.

03:45:12.210 --> 03:45:17.750
Even when we finally retired for the night, the inevitable Miss Grice was still my companion.

03:45:17.750 --> 03:45:25.510
We had only a short end of candle in our candlestick, and I dreaded lest she should talk till it was all burnt out.

03:45:26.230 --> 03:45:31.150
Fortunately, however, the heavy supper she had eaten produced a soporific effect.

03:45:32.150 --> 03:45:34.770
She was already snoring before I had finished undressing.

03:45:35.790 --> 03:45:37.730
There still remained an inch of candle.

03:45:38.510 --> 03:45:40.150
I now took out my letter.

03:45:40.530 --> 03:45:44.270
The seal was an initial F. I broke it.

03:45:44.470 --> 03:45:45.730
The contents were brief.

03:45:46.730 --> 03:45:53.950
If J. E., who advertised in the Blankshire Herald of last Thursday, possesses the requirements mentioned,

03:45:54.150 --> 03:45:59.850
and if she is in a position to give satisfactory references as to character and competency,

03:46:00.570 --> 03:46:07.090
a situation can be offered her where there is but one pupil, a little girl, under ten years of age,

03:46:07.330 --> 03:46:10.190
and where the salary is thirty pounds per annum.

03:46:10.190 --> 03:46:17.350
J. E. is requested to send references, name, address, and all particulars to the direction

03:46:17.350 --> 03:46:21.670
Mrs. Fairfax, Thornfield, near Millcote, Blankshire.

03:46:23.330 --> 03:46:25.490
I examined the document long.

03:46:26.070 --> 03:46:31.490
The writing was old-fashioned and rather uncertain, like that of an elderly lady.

03:46:32.270 --> 03:46:34.310
This circumstance was satisfactory.

03:46:34.850 --> 03:46:41.290
A private fear had haunted me, that in thus acting for myself, and by my own guidance,

03:46:41.730 --> 03:46:45.930
I ran the risk of getting into some scrape, and above all things,

03:46:46.390 --> 03:46:51.510
I wished the result of my endeavours to be respectable, proper, en rigale.

03:46:52.430 --> 03:46:58.150
I now felt that an elderly lady was no bad ingredient in the business I had on hand.

03:46:58.690 --> 03:47:03.010
Mrs. Fairfax. I saw her in a black gown and widow's cap.

03:47:03.610 --> 03:47:06.390
Frigid, perhaps, but not uncivil.

03:47:07.070 --> 03:47:11.190
A model of elderly English respectability. Thornfield.

03:47:11.850 --> 03:47:14.050
That, doubtless, was the name of her house.

03:47:14.450 --> 03:47:20.910
A neat, orderly spot, I was sure, though I failed in my efforts to conceive a correct plan of the premises.

03:47:22.010 --> 03:47:23.470
Millcote, Blankshire.

03:47:24.090 --> 03:47:30.230
I brushed up my recollection of the map of England. Yes, I saw it. Both the Shire and the town.

03:47:30.930 --> 03:47:36.090
Blankshire was seventy miles nearer London than the remote county where I now resided.

03:47:36.830 --> 03:47:38.710
That was a recommendation to me.

03:47:39.370 --> 03:47:41.630
I longed to go where there was life and movement.

03:47:42.570 --> 03:47:47.210
Millcote was a large manufacturing town on the blanks of the A-Blank.

03:47:48.670 --> 03:47:51.410
A busy place enough, doubtless.

03:47:51.410 --> 03:47:55.670
So much the better. It would be a complete change, at least.

03:47:56.450 --> 03:48:01.170
Not that my fancy was much captivated by the idea of long chimneys and clouds of smoke.

03:48:01.810 --> 03:48:06.970
But, I argued, Thornfield will, probably, be a good way from the town.

03:48:08.370 --> 03:48:11.770
Here the socket of the candle dropped, and the wick went out.

03:48:12.850 --> 03:48:18.290
Next day, new steps were to be taken. My plans could no longer be confined to my own breast.

03:48:18.850 --> 03:48:22.090
I must impart them in order to achieve their success.

03:48:22.990 --> 03:48:28.250
Having sought and obtained an audience of the superintendent during the noontide recreation,

03:48:29.090 --> 03:48:34.590
I told her I had a prospect of getting a new situation where the salary would be double what I now received.

03:48:35.410 --> 03:48:38.630
For at Lowood I got only fifteen pounds per annum.

03:48:39.250 --> 03:48:44.870
Anne requested she would break the matter for me to Mr. Brocklehurst, or some of the committee,

03:48:44.870 --> 03:48:50.010
and ascertain whether they would permit me to mention them as references.

03:48:51.410 --> 03:48:55.990
She obligantly consented to act as mediatrix in the matter.

03:48:56.830 --> 03:48:59.970
The next day she led the affair before Mr. Brocklehurst,

03:49:00.450 --> 03:49:04.790
who said that Mrs. Reed must be written to, as she was my natural guardian.

03:49:05.770 --> 03:49:09.990
A note was accordingly addressed to that lady, who returned for answer that,

03:49:09.990 --> 03:49:14.950
I might do as I pleased. She had long relinquished all interference in my affairs.

03:49:15.670 --> 03:49:17.730
This note went the round of the committee.

03:49:18.410 --> 03:49:21.950
And at last, after what appeared to me most tedious delay,

03:49:22.790 --> 03:49:25.690
formal leave was given me to better my condition if I could.

03:49:26.570 --> 03:49:30.310
Anne and assurance added that as I had always conducted myself well,

03:49:30.750 --> 03:49:36.190
both as teacher and pupil at Lowood, a testimonial of character and capacity,

03:49:36.650 --> 03:49:41.430
signed by the inspectors of that institution, should forthwith be furnished me.

03:49:42.210 --> 03:49:45.750
This testimonial I accordingly received in about a month,

03:49:46.650 --> 03:49:50.470
forwarded a copy of it to Mrs. Fairfax, and got that lady's reply,

03:49:51.110 --> 03:49:54.710
stating that she was satisfied, and fixing that day fortnight

03:49:54.710 --> 03:49:58.630
as a period for my assuming the post of governess in her house.

03:49:59.670 --> 03:50:01.930
I now busied myself in preparations.

03:50:02.650 --> 03:50:07.070
The fortnight passed rapidly. I had not a very large boardrobe,

03:50:07.590 --> 03:50:12.310
though it was adequate to my wants, and the last day sufficed to pack my trunk,

03:50:13.030 --> 03:50:16.250
the same I had brought with me eight years ago from Gateshead.

03:50:17.690 --> 03:50:20.750
The box was corded, the card nailed on.

03:50:21.410 --> 03:50:24.990
In half an hour the carrier was to call for it to take it to Lowton,

03:50:25.390 --> 03:50:29.950
whither I myself was to repair at an early hour the next morning to meet the coach.

03:50:30.510 --> 03:50:33.690
I had brushed my black, stuff travelling dress,

03:50:34.510 --> 03:50:36.850
prepared my bonnet, gloves, and muff,

03:50:37.610 --> 03:50:40.690
sought in all my drawers to see that no article was left behind,

03:50:41.350 --> 03:50:45.330
and now, having nothing more to do, I sat down and tried to rest.

03:50:45.890 --> 03:50:46.770
I could not.

03:50:47.410 --> 03:50:51.430
Though I had been on foot all day, I could not now repose an instant.

03:50:51.930 --> 03:50:53.190
I was too much excited.

03:50:53.770 --> 03:50:57.670
A phase of my life was closing tonight, a new one opening tomorrow.

03:50:58.690 --> 03:51:00.730
Impossible to slumber in the interval.

03:51:01.390 --> 03:51:05.210
I must watch feverishly while the change was being accomplished.

03:51:06.350 --> 03:51:09.010
Miss, said a servant who met me in the lobby,

03:51:09.410 --> 03:51:11.170
where I was wandering like a troubled spirit,

03:51:11.930 --> 03:51:13.930
a person below wishes to see you.

03:51:14.690 --> 03:51:19.330
The carrier, no doubt, I thought, and ran downstairs without inquiry.

03:51:20.010 --> 03:51:23.210
I was passing the back parlor or the teacher's sitting room,

03:51:23.970 --> 03:51:25.990
the door of which was half open,

03:51:25.990 --> 03:51:29.150
to go to the kitchen when someone ran out.

03:51:29.450 --> 03:51:30.930
It's her, I am sure.

03:51:31.090 --> 03:51:32.610
I could have told her anywhere,

03:51:33.570 --> 03:51:36.870
cried the individual who stopped my progress and took my hand.

03:51:37.830 --> 03:51:38.450
I looked.

03:51:39.350 --> 03:51:42.210
I saw a woman attired like a well-dressed servant,

03:51:42.530 --> 03:51:44.450
matronly, yet still young,

03:51:44.890 --> 03:51:47.470
very good-looking, with black hair and eyes,

03:51:47.970 --> 03:51:49.190
and lively complexion.

03:51:50.090 --> 03:51:52.010
Well, who is it? she asked,

03:51:52.390 --> 03:51:54.870
in a voice and with a smile I half recognized.

03:51:54.870 --> 03:51:57.950
You've not quite forgotten me, I think, Miss Jane.

03:51:59.350 --> 03:52:03.070
In another second I was embracing and kissing her rapturously.

03:52:03.810 --> 03:52:07.370
Bessie, Bessie, Bessie, was all I had said.

03:52:08.610 --> 03:52:10.630
Whereat she half laughed, half cried,

03:52:11.150 --> 03:52:12.710
and we both went into the parlor.

03:52:13.770 --> 03:52:16.950
By the fire stood a little fellow of three years old

03:52:16.950 --> 03:52:18.730
in plaid frock and trousers.

03:52:19.870 --> 03:52:22.690
That is my little boy, said Bessie directly.

03:52:23.330 --> 03:52:25.050
Then you are married, Bessie?

03:52:25.410 --> 03:52:28.450
Yes, nearly five years since to Robert Levin,

03:52:28.910 --> 03:52:32.090
a coachman, and I have a little girl besides Bobby there.

03:52:32.490 --> 03:52:33.530
That I've christened Jane.

03:52:33.950 --> 03:52:35.150
And you don't live at Gateshead?

03:52:35.910 --> 03:52:38.590
I live at the lodge the old porter has left.

03:52:39.430 --> 03:52:41.070
Well, and how do they all get on?

03:52:42.130 --> 03:52:43.970
Tell me everything about them, Bessie,

03:52:44.090 --> 03:52:45.770
but sit down first, and Bobby,

03:52:46.230 --> 03:52:47.810
come and sit on my knee, will you?

03:52:48.370 --> 03:52:50.730
But Bobby preferred sliding over to his mother.

03:52:51.930 --> 03:52:54.130
You're not grown so very tall, Miss Jane,

03:52:54.370 --> 03:52:56.930
nor so very stout, continued Mrs. Levin.

03:52:57.790 --> 03:53:00.350
I dare say they've not kept you too well at school.

03:53:01.050 --> 03:53:04.290
Miss Reed is the head and shoulders taller than you are,

03:53:04.670 --> 03:53:07.490
and Miss Georgiana would make two of you in breath.

03:53:08.650 --> 03:53:11.130
Georgiana is handsome, I suppose, Bessie?

03:53:11.350 --> 03:53:11.750
Very.

03:53:12.410 --> 03:53:15.030
She went up to London last winter with her mamma,

03:53:15.330 --> 03:53:17.270
and there everybody admired her,

03:53:17.670 --> 03:53:19.810
and a young lord fell in love with her,

03:53:19.810 --> 03:53:21.810
but his relations were against the match,

03:53:22.270 --> 03:53:23.310
and what do you think?

03:53:23.750 --> 03:53:26.450
He and Miss Georgiana made it up to run away,

03:53:26.770 --> 03:53:28.430
but they were found out and stopped.

03:53:29.210 --> 03:53:31.290
It was Miss Reed that found them out.

03:53:31.870 --> 03:53:34.950
I believe she was envious, and now she and her sister

03:53:34.950 --> 03:53:36.950
lead a cat and dog life together.

03:53:37.190 --> 03:53:38.390
They are always quarreling.

03:53:39.250 --> 03:53:41.430
Well, and what of John Reed?

03:53:42.550 --> 03:53:46.170
Oh, he is not doing so well as his mamma could wish.

03:53:46.650 --> 03:53:48.810
He went to college, and he got plucked.

03:53:48.810 --> 03:53:52.630
I think they call it, and then his uncles wanted him

03:53:52.630 --> 03:53:54.830
to be a barrister and study the law,

03:53:54.910 --> 03:53:57.550
but he is such a dissipated young man

03:53:57.550 --> 03:53:59.630
they will never make much of him, I think.

03:54:00.710 --> 03:54:02.070
What does he look like?

03:54:03.130 --> 03:54:04.350
He is very tall.

03:54:04.630 --> 03:54:07.030
Some people call him a fine-looking young man,

03:54:07.210 --> 03:54:09.070
but he has such thick lips.

03:54:10.370 --> 03:54:11.190
And Mrs. Reed?

03:54:12.190 --> 03:54:14.750
Mrs. looks stout and well enough in the face,

03:54:14.750 --> 03:54:17.390
but I think she's not quite easy in her mind.

03:54:17.390 --> 03:54:20.050
Mr. John's conduct does not please her.

03:54:20.210 --> 03:54:21.650
He spends a deal of money.

03:54:22.690 --> 03:54:24.390
Did she send you here, Bessie?

03:54:25.350 --> 03:54:28.850
No, indeed, but I have long waited to see you,

03:54:29.330 --> 03:54:31.890
and when I heard that there had been a letter from you

03:54:31.890 --> 03:54:33.830
and that you were going to another part of the country,

03:54:34.250 --> 03:54:36.570
I thought I'd just set off and get a look at you

03:54:36.570 --> 03:54:38.170
before you were quite out of my reach.

03:54:39.170 --> 03:54:41.610
I am afraid you were disappointed in me, Bessie,

03:54:41.610 --> 03:54:42.810
I said this laughing.

03:54:43.430 --> 03:54:45.110
I perceived that Bessie's glance,

03:54:45.110 --> 03:54:46.610
though it expressed regard,

03:54:47.030 --> 03:54:49.010
did in no shape denote admiration.

03:54:49.430 --> 03:54:50.930
No, Miss Jane, not exactly.

03:54:51.310 --> 03:54:52.390
You are genteel enough.

03:54:52.630 --> 03:54:53.710
You look like a lady,

03:54:54.170 --> 03:54:56.550
and it is as much as I ever expected of you.

03:54:56.770 --> 03:54:58.250
You were no beauty as a child.

03:54:59.050 --> 03:55:01.110
I smiled at Bessie's frank answer.

03:55:01.690 --> 03:55:03.150
I thought that it was correct,

03:55:03.450 --> 03:55:06.810
but I confess I was not quite indifferent to its import.

03:55:07.470 --> 03:55:10.030
At eighteen most people wish to please,

03:55:10.650 --> 03:55:13.790
and the conviction that they have not an exterior likely to second

03:55:13.790 --> 03:55:16.290
that desire brings anything but gratification.

03:55:17.310 --> 03:55:18.750
I daresay you were clever, though,

03:55:18.910 --> 03:55:20.850
continued Bessie by way of solace.

03:55:21.250 --> 03:55:22.090
What can you do?

03:55:22.470 --> 03:55:23.590
Can you play on the piano?

03:55:24.550 --> 03:55:25.110
A little.

03:55:25.970 --> 03:55:27.170
There was one in the room.

03:55:27.550 --> 03:55:29.230
Bessie went and opened it,

03:55:29.430 --> 03:55:31.750
and then asked me to sit down and give her a tune.

03:55:32.470 --> 03:55:33.930
I played a waltz or two,

03:55:34.050 --> 03:55:35.250
and she was charmed.

03:55:35.930 --> 03:55:38.090
The Miss Reeds could not play as well,

03:55:38.790 --> 03:55:39.930
said she exultingly.

03:55:40.530 --> 03:55:43.090
I always said you would surpass them in learning,

03:55:43.090 --> 03:55:44.710
and can you draw?

03:55:45.870 --> 03:55:48.410
That is one of my paintings over the chimney piece.

03:55:49.230 --> 03:55:51.290
It was a landscape in watercolours,

03:55:51.870 --> 03:55:54.270
of which I had made a present to the superintendent,

03:55:55.030 --> 03:55:59.110
in acknowledgement of her obliging mediation with the committee on my behalf,

03:55:59.610 --> 03:56:01.490
in which she had framed and glazed.

03:56:02.230 --> 03:56:04.550
Well, that is beautiful, Miss Jane.

03:56:05.070 --> 03:56:08.810
It is as fine a picture as any Miss Reeds' drawing master could paint,

03:56:09.170 --> 03:56:11.090
let alone the fine young ladies themselves,

03:56:11.090 --> 03:56:12.950
who could not come near it.

03:56:13.130 --> 03:56:14.310
And you have learnt French?

03:56:15.210 --> 03:56:15.990
Yes, Bessie.

03:56:16.490 --> 03:56:18.530
I can both read it and speak it.

03:56:19.290 --> 03:56:21.070
And you can work on muslin and canvas?

03:56:21.430 --> 03:56:22.070
I can.

03:56:22.910 --> 03:56:25.150
Oh, you were quite a lady, Miss Jane.

03:56:25.630 --> 03:56:26.810
I knew you would be.

03:56:27.130 --> 03:56:29.850
You will get on whether your relations noticed you or not.

03:56:30.610 --> 03:56:32.430
There was something I wanted to ask you.

03:56:32.870 --> 03:56:35.630
Have you ever heard anything from your father's kinsfolk?

03:56:36.250 --> 03:56:36.810
The heirs?

03:56:37.910 --> 03:56:39.030
Never in my life.

03:56:39.590 --> 03:56:43.270
Well, you know, Mrs. always said they were poor and quite despicable,

03:56:44.150 --> 03:56:45.290
and they may be poor,

03:56:45.590 --> 03:56:49.170
but I believe they are as much gentry as the Reeds are.

03:56:49.730 --> 03:56:52.090
For one day, nearly seven years ago,

03:56:52.510 --> 03:56:55.190
a Mr. Heir came to Gateshead and wanted to see you.

03:56:56.050 --> 03:56:59.470
Mrs. said you were at school, fifty miles off.

03:57:00.790 --> 03:57:04.090
He seemed so much disappointed, for he could not stay.

03:57:05.190 --> 03:57:07.850
He was going on a voyage to a foreign country,

03:57:07.850 --> 03:57:11.330
and the ship was to sail from London in a day or two.

03:57:11.790 --> 03:57:13.230
He looked quite a gentleman,

03:57:13.570 --> 03:57:15.450
and I believe he was your father's brother.

03:57:16.330 --> 03:57:18.710
What foreign country was he going to, Bessie?

03:57:19.510 --> 03:57:23.310
An island, thousands of miles off, where they make wine.

03:57:23.710 --> 03:57:24.910
The butler did tell me.

03:57:25.290 --> 03:57:26.890
Madeira, I suggested?

03:57:27.210 --> 03:57:27.730
Yes.

03:57:27.970 --> 03:57:28.810
That is it.

03:57:28.970 --> 03:57:30.010
That is the very word.

03:57:30.610 --> 03:57:31.470
So he went?

03:57:32.010 --> 03:57:32.530
Yes.

03:57:32.790 --> 03:57:35.150
He did not stay many minutes in the house.

03:57:35.670 --> 03:57:37.210
Mrs. was very high with him.

03:57:37.210 --> 03:57:40.670
She called him afterwards a sneaking tradesman.

03:57:41.210 --> 03:57:43.170
My Robert believes he was a wine merchant.

03:57:44.610 --> 03:57:45.850
Very likely, I returned,

03:57:46.170 --> 03:57:48.630
or perhaps clerk or agent to a wine merchant.

03:57:49.890 --> 03:57:52.770
Bessie and I conversed about old times an hour longer,

03:57:53.050 --> 03:57:55.670
and then she was obliged to leave me.

03:57:56.390 --> 03:58:00.190
I saw her again for a few minutes the next morning at Loughton,

03:58:00.470 --> 03:58:01.770
while I was waiting for my coach.

03:58:02.650 --> 03:58:06.090
We parted finally at the door of the Brocklehurst Arms there.

03:58:06.090 --> 03:58:08.210
Each went her separate way.

03:58:08.750 --> 03:58:10.790
She set off for the brow of Lowood Fell.

03:58:11.510 --> 03:58:14.590
To meet the conveyance which was to take her back to Gateshead,

03:58:15.330 --> 03:58:18.350
I mounted the vehicle which was to bear me to my new duties,

03:58:19.050 --> 03:58:22.030
and a new life in the unknown environs of Millcote.

03:58:45.230 --> 03:58:48.030
CHAPTER XI

03:58:48.030 --> 03:58:52.310
A new chapter in a novel is something like a new scene in a play,

03:58:52.910 --> 03:58:59.010
and when I draw up the curtain this time, reader, you must fancy you see a room in the Georgian

03:58:59.010 --> 03:59:06.070
at Milkoat, with such large figured papering on the walls as in rooms have, such a carpet,

03:59:06.490 --> 03:59:13.650
such furniture, such ornaments on the mantelpiece, such prints, including a portrait of George the

03:59:14.270 --> 03:59:18.550
and another of the Prince of Wales, and a representation of the death of Wolf.

03:59:19.550 --> 03:59:23.790
All this is visible to you by the light of an oil lamp hanging from the ceiling,

03:59:24.170 --> 03:59:28.850
and by that of an excellent fire, near which I sit in my cloak and bonnet,

03:59:29.150 --> 03:59:34.290
my muff and umbrella lie on the table, and I am warming away the numbness and chill

03:59:34.290 --> 03:59:39.370
contracted by sixteen hours exposure to the rawness of an October day.

03:59:40.090 --> 03:59:46.490
I left Lowton at four o'clock a.m., and the Milkoat town clock is now just striking eight.

03:59:47.570 --> 03:59:53.310
Reader, though I look comfortably accommodated, I am not very tranquil in my mind.

03:59:54.030 --> 03:59:57.330
I thought when the coach stopped here there would be someone to meet me.

03:59:57.710 --> 04:00:02.650
I looked anxiously around as I descended the wooden steps, the boots placed for my convenience,

04:00:03.490 --> 04:00:08.370
expecting to hear my name pronounced and to see some description of carriage waiting to convey

04:00:08.370 --> 04:00:14.910
to Thornfield. Nothing of the sort was visible, and when I asked a waiter if anyone had been to

04:00:14.910 --> 04:00:21.290
inquire after a mis-air I was answered in the negative, so I had no recourse but to request

04:00:21.290 --> 04:00:27.750
to be shown into a private room, and here I am waiting while all sorts of doubts and fears are

04:00:27.750 --> 04:00:35.170
troubling my thoughts. It is a very strange sensation to inexperienced youth to feel itself

04:00:35.170 --> 04:00:41.430
quite alone in the world, cut adrift from every connection, uncertain whether the port to which

04:00:41.430 --> 04:00:47.870
it is bound can be reached, and prevented by many impediments from returning to that it has quitted.

04:00:48.810 --> 04:00:56.310
The charm of adventure sweetens that sensation, the glow of pride warms it, but then the throb

04:00:56.310 --> 04:01:03.270
of fear disturbs it, and fear with me became predominant when half an hour elapsed and still

04:01:03.270 --> 04:01:06.990
I was alone. I bethought myself to ring the bell.

04:01:07.770 --> 04:01:12.670
Is there a place in this neighbourhood called Thornfield? I asked to the waiter who answered

04:01:12.670 --> 04:01:19.450
the summons. Thornfield? I don't know, ma'am, I'll inquire at the bar. He vanished but reappeared

04:01:19.450 --> 04:01:27.870
instantly. Is your name Air Miss? Yes. Person here waiting for you. I jumped up, took my muffened

04:01:27.870 --> 04:01:33.910
umbrella, and hastened into the inn passage. A man was standing by the open door, and in the

04:01:33.910 --> 04:01:41.070
lamplit street I dimly saw a one-horse conveyance. This will be your luggage, I suppose, said the

04:01:41.070 --> 04:01:47.810
man rather abruptly when he saw me, pointing to my trunk in the passage. Yes. He hoisted it

04:01:47.810 --> 04:01:54.270
on to the vehicle, which was a sort of car, and then I got in. Before he shot me up I asked him

04:01:54.270 --> 04:02:00.510
how far it was to Thornfield, a matter of six miles. How long shall we be before we get there?

04:02:01.070 --> 04:02:07.730
Happen an hour and a half? He fastened the car door, climbed to his own seat outside, and we set

04:02:07.730 --> 04:02:16.050
off. Our progress was leisurely and gave me ample time to reflect. I was content to be at length so

04:02:16.050 --> 04:02:21.850
near the end of my journey, and as I leaned back in the comfortable though not elegant conveyance

04:02:21.850 --> 04:02:29.190
I meditated much at my ease. I suppose, thought I, judging from the plainness of the servant

04:02:29.190 --> 04:02:35.810
and carriage, Mrs Fairfax is not a very dashing person. So much the better. I never lived amongst

04:02:35.810 --> 04:02:41.470
fine people but once, and I was very miserable with them. I wonder if she lives alone except

04:02:41.470 --> 04:02:47.910
for this little girl. If so, and if she is in any degree amiable, I shall surely be able to get on

04:02:47.910 --> 04:02:55.110
with her. I will do my best. It is a pity that doing one's best does not always answer. At

04:02:55.110 --> 04:03:01.010
Lowood, indeed, I took that resolution, kept it, and succeeded in pleasing. But with Mrs Read,

04:03:01.250 --> 04:03:08.510
I remember my best was always spurned with scorn. I pray God Mrs Fairfax may not turn out a second

04:03:08.510 --> 04:03:15.290
Mrs Read. But if she does, I'm not bound to stay with her. Let the worst come to the worst,

04:03:15.290 --> 04:03:19.930
I can advertise again. How far are we on our road now, I wonder?

04:03:21.270 --> 04:03:27.450
I let down the window and looked out. Millcote was behind us. Judging by the number of its lights,

04:03:27.510 --> 04:03:34.410
it seemed a place of considerable magnitude, much larger than Lowton. We were now, as far as I could

04:03:34.410 --> 04:03:40.390
see, on a sort of common, but there were houses scattered all over the district. I felt we were

04:03:40.390 --> 04:03:47.650
in a different region to Lowood, more populous, less picturesque, more stirring, less romantic.

04:03:48.750 --> 04:03:54.230
The roads were heavy, the night misty. My conductor let his horse walk all the way,

04:03:54.490 --> 04:04:00.890
and the hour and a half extended, I verily believe, to two hours. At last he turned in his seat and

04:04:00.890 --> 04:04:07.750
said, You're known so far for Thornfield now. Again I looked out. We were passing a church.

04:04:07.750 --> 04:04:15.290
I saw its low broad tower against the sky, and its bell was tolling a quarter. I saw a narrow

04:04:15.290 --> 04:04:21.570
galaxy of lights too on a hillside, marking a village or hamlet. About ten minutes after,

04:04:21.770 --> 04:04:27.930
the driver got down and opened a pair of gates. We passed through, and they clashed two behind us.

04:04:28.670 --> 04:04:33.370
We now slowly ascended a drive and came upon the long front of a house.

04:04:34.070 --> 04:04:40.510
Candlelight gleamed from one curtained bow window. All the rest were dark. The car stopped at the

04:04:40.510 --> 04:04:45.490
front door. It was opened by a maidservant. I alighted and went in.

04:04:46.410 --> 04:04:52.170
Will you walk this way, ma'am? said the girl, and I followed her across a square hall with high doors

04:04:52.170 --> 04:04:58.830
all round. She ushered me into a room whose double illumination of fire and candle at first dazzled

04:04:58.830 --> 04:05:04.010
me, contrasting as it did with the darkness to which my eyes had groaned for two hours inured.

04:05:04.930 --> 04:05:10.270
When I could see, however, a cosy and agreeable picture presented itself to my view.

04:05:11.070 --> 04:05:18.970
A snug small room, a round table by a cheerful fire, an armchair high-backed and old-fashioned,

04:05:19.330 --> 04:05:25.750
wherein sat the neatest imaginable little elderly lady in widow's cap, black silk gown,

04:05:25.750 --> 04:05:30.830
and snowy muslin apron, exactly like what I had fancied Mrs Fairfax,

04:05:31.210 --> 04:05:37.910
only less stately and milder looking. She was occupied in knitting. A large cat sat demurely

04:05:37.910 --> 04:05:43.550
at her feet. Nothing, in short, was wanting to complete the bow ideal of domestic comfort.

04:05:44.550 --> 04:05:49.170
A more reassuring introduction for a new governess could scarcely be conceived.

04:05:49.710 --> 04:05:56.290
There was no grandeur to overwhelm, no stateliness to embarrass, and then, as I entered,

04:05:56.690 --> 04:06:01.410
the old lady got up and promptly and kindly came forward to meet me.

04:06:01.710 --> 04:06:05.790
How do you do, my dear? I am afraid you have had a tedious ride.

04:06:06.490 --> 04:06:10.470
John drives so slowly. You must be cold. Come to the fire.

04:06:11.370 --> 04:06:15.870
Mrs Fairfax, I suppose, said I. Yes, you are right. Do sit down.

04:06:16.430 --> 04:06:22.770
She conducted me to her own chair, and then began to remove my shawl and untie my bonnet strings.

04:06:23.290 --> 04:06:25.770
I begged she would not give herself so much trouble.

04:06:26.730 --> 04:06:31.150
Oh, it is no trouble. I dare say your own hands are almost numbed with cold.

04:06:31.830 --> 04:06:36.710
Leah, make a little hot negus and cut a sandwich or two. Here are the keys of the storeroom.

04:06:37.330 --> 04:06:41.310
And she produced from her pocket a most housewifely bunch of keys,

04:06:41.310 --> 04:06:43.150
and delivered them to the servant.

04:06:43.870 --> 04:06:46.550
Now then, draw nearer to the fire, she continued.

04:06:46.910 --> 04:06:49.090
You have brought your luggage with you, haven't you, my dear?

04:06:49.790 --> 04:06:54.410
Yes, ma'am. I will see it carried into your room, she said, and bustled out.

04:06:55.250 --> 04:06:59.970
She treats me like a visitor, thought I. I little expected such a reception.

04:07:00.650 --> 04:07:03.130
I anticipated only coldness and stiffness.

04:07:03.730 --> 04:07:06.870
This is not like what I have heard of the treatment of governesses,

04:07:06.990 --> 04:07:09.290
but I must not exalt too soon.

04:07:10.390 --> 04:07:16.190
She returned, with her own hands, cleared her knitting apparatus and a book or two from the table,

04:07:16.490 --> 04:07:21.910
to make room for the tray which Leah now brought, and then herself handed me the refreshments.

04:07:22.550 --> 04:07:27.790
I felt rather confused at being the object of more attention than I had ever before received,

04:07:28.390 --> 04:07:31.950
and that too shown by my employer and superior.

04:07:32.750 --> 04:07:37.070
But as she did not herself seem to consider she was doing anything out of her place,

04:07:37.070 --> 04:07:40.430
I thought it better to take her civilities quietly.

04:07:41.030 --> 04:07:44.850
Shall I have the pleasure of seeing Miss Fairfax tonight? I asked,

04:07:45.230 --> 04:07:47.450
when I had partaken of what she offered me.

04:07:47.810 --> 04:07:51.770
What did you say, my dear? I am a little deaf, returned the good lady,

04:07:52.330 --> 04:07:53.810
approaching her ear to my mouth.

04:07:54.490 --> 04:07:56.710
I repeated the question more distinctly.

04:07:56.950 --> 04:08:02.290
Miss Fairfax? Oh, you mean Miss Varens. Varens is the name of your future pupil.

04:08:03.390 --> 04:08:05.690
Indeed, then she is not your daughter.

04:08:06.570 --> 04:08:08.650
No, I have no family.

04:08:09.850 --> 04:08:14.670
I should have followed up my first inquiry by asking in what way Miss Varens was connected

04:08:14.670 --> 04:08:19.230
with her, but I recollected it was not polite to ask too many questions.

04:08:19.830 --> 04:08:22.150
Besides, I was sure to hear in time.

04:08:22.930 --> 04:08:26.730
I am so glad, she continued as she sat down opposite to me

04:08:26.730 --> 04:08:30.430
and took the cat on her knee, I am so glad you are come.

04:08:30.970 --> 04:08:33.950
It will be quite pleasant living here now with a companion,

04:08:33.950 --> 04:08:39.250
to be sure it is pleasant at any time, for Thornfield is a fine old hall,

04:08:39.730 --> 04:08:44.170
rather neglected of late years perhaps, but still it is a respectable place.

04:08:44.770 --> 04:08:49.230
Yet, you know, in wintertime one feels dreary quite alone in the best quarters.

04:08:50.130 --> 04:08:56.450
I say alone, Leah is a nice girl to be sure, and John and his wife are very decent people,

04:08:56.810 --> 04:09:02.230
but then you see they are only servants, and one can't converse with them on terms of equality.

04:09:03.010 --> 04:09:07.230
One must keep them at a due distance for fear of losing one's authority.

04:09:07.970 --> 04:09:13.710
I am sure last winter, it was a very severe one if you recollect, and when it did not snow it

04:09:13.710 --> 04:09:19.750
rained and blew, not a creature but the butcher and postman came to the house from November till

04:09:19.750 --> 04:09:24.970
February, and I really got quite melancholy with sitting night after night alone.

04:09:25.630 --> 04:09:31.390
I had Leah in to read to me sometimes, but I don't think the poor girl liked the task much.

04:09:31.390 --> 04:09:38.870
She felt it confining. In spring and summer one got on better, sunshine and long days make such

04:09:38.870 --> 04:09:45.330
a difference, and then, just at the commencement of this autumn, little Adela Varens came and her

04:09:45.330 --> 04:09:51.730
nurse. A child makes a house alive all at once, and now you are here, I shall be quite gay.

04:09:52.710 --> 04:09:58.310
My heart really warmed to the worthy lady as I heard her talk, and I drew my chair a little

04:09:58.310 --> 04:10:04.030
nearer to her, and expressed my sincere wish that she might find my company as agreeable as she

04:10:04.030 --> 04:10:10.690
anticipated. But I'll not keep you sitting up late tonight, said she. It is on the stroke of

04:10:10.690 --> 04:10:15.890
twelve now, and you have been travelling all day. You must feel tired. If you've got your

04:10:15.890 --> 04:10:21.130
feet well warmed, I'll show you your bedroom. I've had the room next to mine prepared for you.

04:10:21.230 --> 04:10:25.750
It's only a small apartment, but I thought you would like it better than one of the large front

04:10:25.750 --> 04:10:32.010
chambers. To be sure they have finer furniture, but they are so dreary and solitary. I never

04:10:32.010 --> 04:10:39.210
sleep in them myself. I thanked her for her considerate choice, and as I really felt fatigued

04:10:39.210 --> 04:10:45.530
with my long journey, expressed my readiness to retire. She took my candle, and I followed her

04:10:45.530 --> 04:10:52.110
from the room. First she went to see if the hall door was fastened. Having taken the key from the

04:10:52.110 --> 04:10:58.290
lock, she led the way upstairs. The steps and banisters were evoke. The staircase window was

04:10:58.290 --> 04:11:04.290
high and latticed. Both it and the long gallery into which the bedroom doors opened looked as if

04:11:04.290 --> 04:11:10.970
they belonged to a church rather than a house. A very chill and vault-like air pervaded the

04:11:10.970 --> 04:11:18.490
stairs and gallery, suggesting cheerless ideas of space and solitude, and I was glad when finally

04:11:18.490 --> 04:11:24.570
ushered into my chamber to find it of small dimensions and furnished in ordinary modern style.

04:11:25.770 --> 04:11:32.550
When Mrs Fairfax had bid me a kind good night, and I had fastened my door, gazed leisurely around,

04:11:32.790 --> 04:11:38.930
and in some measure effaced the eerie impression made by that wide hall, that dark and spacious

04:11:38.930 --> 04:11:45.750
staircase, and that long cold gallery by the livelier aspect of my little room, I remembered

04:11:45.750 --> 04:11:52.230
that, after a day of bodily fatigue and mental anxiety, I was now at last in safe haven.

04:11:53.030 --> 04:11:59.350
The impulse of gratitude swelled my heart, and I knelt down at the bedside and offered up thanks

04:11:59.350 --> 04:12:05.750
where thanks were due, not forgetting, ere I rose, to implore aid on my further path,

04:12:06.190 --> 04:12:11.710
and the power of meriting the kindness which seemed so frankly offered me before it was earned.

04:12:12.510 --> 04:12:20.250
My couch had no thorns in it that night, my solitary room no fears. At once weary and

04:12:20.250 --> 04:12:29.870
content, I slept soon and soundly. When I awoke, it was broad day. The chamber looked such a bright

04:12:29.870 --> 04:12:35.730
little place to me as the sun shone in between the gay blue chintz window curtains, showing

04:12:35.730 --> 04:12:42.030
papered walls and a carpeted floor, so unlike the bare planks and stained plaster of low wood

04:12:42.030 --> 04:12:48.570
that my spirits rose at the view. Externals have a great effect on the young. I thought

04:12:48.570 --> 04:12:54.150
that a fairer era of life was beginning for me, one that was to have its flowers and pleasures

04:12:54.150 --> 04:13:01.150
as well as its thorns and toils. My faculties, roused by the change of scene, the new field

04:13:01.150 --> 04:13:08.170
offered to hope seemed all a stir. I cannot precisely define what they expected, but it was

04:13:08.170 --> 04:13:14.310
something pleasant, not perhaps that day or that month, but at an indefinite future period.

04:13:15.750 --> 04:13:23.510
I rose, I dressed myself with care, obliged to be plain, for I had no article of attire that was

04:13:23.510 --> 04:13:30.510
not made with extreme simplicity. I was still by nature solicitous to be neat. It was not my habit

04:13:30.510 --> 04:13:36.250
to be disregardful of appearance or careless of the impression I made. On the contrary,

04:13:36.730 --> 04:13:42.110
I ever wished to look as well as I could and to please as much as my want of beauty would permit.

04:13:43.250 --> 04:13:49.890
I sometimes regretted that I was not handsomer. I sometimes wished to have rosy cheeks, a straight

04:13:49.890 --> 04:13:57.070
nose, and small cherry mouth. I desired to be tall, stately, and finely developed in figure.

04:13:57.670 --> 04:14:04.090
I felt it a misfortune that I was so little, so pale, and had features so irregular and so marked.

04:14:04.790 --> 04:14:12.030
And why had I these aspirations and these regrets? It would be difficult to say. I could not then

04:14:12.030 --> 04:14:18.810
distinctly say it to myself, yet I had a reason, and a logical natural reason too. However,

04:14:19.310 --> 04:14:25.390
when I had brushed my hair very smooth and put on my black frock, which, quaker-like as it was,

04:14:25.390 --> 04:14:31.790
at least had the merit of fitting to a nicety, and adjusted my clean white tucker, I thought

04:14:31.790 --> 04:14:37.630
I should do respectably enough to appear before Mrs Fairfax, and that my new pupil would not at

04:14:37.630 --> 04:14:44.630
least recoil from me with antipathy. Having opened my chamber window and seen that I left all things

04:14:44.630 --> 04:14:52.190
straight and neat on the toilet table, I ventured forth. Traversing the long and matted gallery,

04:14:52.190 --> 04:14:58.390
I descended the slippery steps of oak. Then I gained the hall. I halted there a minute.

04:14:58.970 --> 04:15:04.810
I looked at some pictures on the walls. One, I remember, represented a grim man in a cuirass,

04:15:05.170 --> 04:15:11.010
and one a lady with powdered hair and a pearl necklace, and a bronze lamp pendant from the

04:15:11.010 --> 04:15:18.050
ceiling, at a great clock whose case was of oak, curiously carved, and ebon black with time and

04:15:18.050 --> 04:15:25.070
rubbing. Everything appeared very stately and imposing to me, and then I was so little accustomed

04:15:25.070 --> 04:15:32.150
to grandeur. The hall door, which was half of glass, stood open. I stepped over the threshold.

04:15:32.770 --> 04:15:39.570
It was a fine autumn morning. The early sun shone serenely on embrowned groves and still

04:15:39.570 --> 04:15:46.650
green fields. Advancing on to the lawn, I looked up and surveyed the front of the mansion. It was

04:15:46.650 --> 04:15:53.450
three storeys high, of proportions not vast, though considerable, a gentleman's manor house,

04:15:53.510 --> 04:16:00.190
not a nobleman's seat. Battlements round the top gave it a picturesque look. Its grey front

04:16:00.190 --> 04:16:05.590
stood out well from the background of a rookery, whose cawing tenants were now on the wing.

04:16:06.330 --> 04:16:11.890
They flew over the lawn and grounds to alight in a great meadow, from which these were separated

04:16:11.890 --> 04:16:19.290
by a sunk fence, and where an array of mighty old thorn-trees, strong, knotty, and broad as oaks,

04:16:19.510 --> 04:16:26.730
at once explained the etymology of the mansion's designation. Farther off were hills, not so lofty

04:16:26.730 --> 04:16:32.930
as those around Lowood, nor so craggy, nor so like barriers of separation from the living world,

04:16:33.430 --> 04:16:39.170
but yet quiet and lonely hills enough, and seeming to embrace Thornfield with a seclusion

04:16:39.170 --> 04:16:44.550
I had not expected to find existent so near the stirring locality of Millcote.

04:16:45.550 --> 04:16:51.130
A little hamlet, whose roofs were blent with trees, straggled up the side of one of these hills.

04:16:51.630 --> 04:16:58.410
The church of the district stood nearer Thornfield. Its old tower top looked over a knoll between the

04:16:58.410 --> 04:17:05.810
house and gates. I was yet enjoying the calm prospect and pleasant fresh air, yet listening

04:17:05.810 --> 04:17:11.550
with delight to the cawing of the rooks, yet surveying the wide, hoary front of the hall,

04:17:12.070 --> 04:17:16.890
and thinking what a great place it was for one lonely little dame like Mrs Fairfax to inhabit,

04:17:17.490 --> 04:17:19.470
when that lady appeared at the door.

04:17:19.970 --> 04:17:24.010
What, out already? said she. I see you are an early riser.

04:17:24.630 --> 04:17:29.310
I went up to her, and was received with an affable kiss and shake of the hand.

04:17:29.890 --> 04:17:34.450
How do you like Thornfield? she asked. I told her I liked it very much.

04:17:35.010 --> 04:17:41.130
Yes, she said, it is a pretty place, but I fear it will be getting out of order unless Mr Rochester

04:17:41.130 --> 04:17:46.710
should take it into his head to come and reside here permanently, or at least visit it rather

04:17:46.710 --> 04:17:51.770
oftener. Great houses and fine grounds require the presence of the proprietor.

04:17:52.670 --> 04:17:55.330
Mr Rochester? I exclaimed. Who is he?

04:17:55.970 --> 04:18:01.130
The owner of Thornfield, she responded quietly. Did you not know he was called Rochester?

04:18:01.850 --> 04:18:07.230
Of course I did not. I had never heard of him before, but the old lady seemed to regard his

04:18:07.230 --> 04:18:12.850
existence as a universally understood fact, with which everybody must be acquainted by instinct.

04:18:13.530 --> 04:18:16.990
I thought, I continued, Thornfield belonged to you.

04:18:17.450 --> 04:18:23.810
To me? Bless you, child, what an idea! To me, I am only the housekeeper, the manager.

04:18:24.330 --> 04:18:28.610
To be sure, I am distantly related to the Rochesters by the mother's side,

04:18:28.610 --> 04:18:34.770
or at least my husband was. He was a clergyman, incumbent of Hay, that little village yonder on

04:18:34.770 --> 04:18:41.490
the hill, and that church near the gates was his. The present Mr Rochester's mother was a Fairfax,

04:18:41.750 --> 04:18:47.810
and second cousin to my husband, but I never presume on the connection. In fact, it is nothing

04:18:47.810 --> 04:18:53.990
to me. I consider myself quite in the light of an ordinary housekeeper. My employer is always civil,

04:18:53.990 --> 04:19:01.650
and I expect nothing more. And the little girl, my pupil? She is Mr Rochester's ward.

04:19:02.130 --> 04:19:08.050
He commissioned me to find a governess for her. He intended to have her brought up in somethingshire,

04:19:08.090 --> 04:19:15.930
I believe. Here she comes, with her bon, as she calls her nurse. The enigma then was explained.

04:19:16.390 --> 04:19:23.890
This affable and kind little widow was no great dame, but a dependent like myself. I did not like

04:19:23.890 --> 04:19:30.290
her the worse for that. On the contrary, I felt better pleased than ever. The equality between her

04:19:30.290 --> 04:19:37.790
and me was real, not the mere result of condescension on her part. So much the better. My position was

04:19:37.790 --> 04:19:44.450
all the freer. As I was meditating on this discovery, a little girl, followed by her attendant,

04:19:44.850 --> 04:19:51.470
came running up the lawn. I looked at my pupil, who did not at first appear to notice me. She was

04:19:51.470 --> 04:19:58.230
quite a child, perhaps seven or eight years old, slightly built, with a pale, small featured face,

04:19:58.550 --> 04:20:01.930
and a redundancy of hair falling in curls to her waist.

04:20:03.210 --> 04:20:08.350
Good morning, Miss Adelia, said Mrs Fairfax. Come and speak to the lady who is to teach you,

04:20:08.490 --> 04:20:11.910
and to make you a clever woman one day. She approached.

04:20:13.130 --> 04:20:17.550
C'est le ma gouverneur, she said, pointing at me, and addressing her nurse, who answered.

04:20:17.550 --> 04:20:19.310
Mais oui, certainement.

04:20:19.850 --> 04:20:23.850
Are they foreigners, I inquired, amazed at hearing the French language?

04:20:24.550 --> 04:20:30.050
The nurse is a foreigner, and Adelia was born on the continent, and I believe never left it,

04:20:30.070 --> 04:20:34.970
till within six months ago. When she first came here she could speak no English,

04:20:35.210 --> 04:20:40.710
now she can make shift to talk it a little. I don't understand her, she mixes it so with French,

04:20:41.250 --> 04:20:43.830
but you will make out her meaning very well, I dare say.

04:20:44.990 --> 04:20:49.010
Fortunately, I had had the advantage of being taught French by a French lady,

04:20:49.010 --> 04:20:54.490
and as I had always made a point of conversing with Madame Pierrot as often as I could,

04:20:54.670 --> 04:20:59.610
and had besides during the last seven years learnt a portion of French by heart daily,

04:21:00.330 --> 04:21:04.970
applying myself to take pains with my accent, and imitating as closely as possible the

04:21:04.970 --> 04:21:10.090
pronunciation of my teacher, I had acquired a certain degree of readiness and correctness

04:21:10.090 --> 04:21:14.630
in the language, and was not likely to be much at a loss with Mademoiselle Adela.

04:21:15.450 --> 04:21:19.110
She came and shook hands with me when she heard that I was her governess,

04:21:19.670 --> 04:21:24.050
and as I led her into breakfast I addressed some phrases to her in her own tongue.

04:21:24.470 --> 04:21:30.010
She replied briefly at first, but after we were seated at the table, and she had examined me some

04:21:30.010 --> 04:21:35.030
ten minutes with her large hazel eyes, she suddenly commenced chattering fluently.

04:21:35.550 --> 04:21:39.890
Ah! cried she in French. You speak my language as well as Mr. Rochester does.

04:21:40.130 --> 04:21:44.870
I can talk to you as I can to him, and so can Sophie. She will be glad.

04:21:45.290 --> 04:21:51.810
Nobody here understands her. Madame Fairfax is all English. Sophie is my nurse. She came with me over

04:21:51.810 --> 04:21:57.270
the sea in a great ship with a chimney that smoked. How it did smoke! And I was sick,

04:21:57.350 --> 04:22:03.010
and so was Sophie, and so was Mr. Rochester. Mr. Rochester lay down on a sofa in a pretty room

04:22:03.010 --> 04:22:08.370
called the Salon, and Sophie and I had little beds in another place. I nearly fell out of mine.

04:22:08.550 --> 04:22:12.650
It was like a shelf. And, mademoiselle, what is your name?

04:22:13.450 --> 04:22:14.970
Air. Jane Air.

04:22:15.590 --> 04:22:21.930
Air? Bah! I cannot say it. Well, our ship stopped in the morning before it was quite daylight at a

04:22:21.930 --> 04:22:28.510
great city, a huge city with very dark houses and all smoky, not at all like the pretty clean town

04:22:28.510 --> 04:22:34.830
I came from. And Mr. Rochester carried me in his arms over a plank to the land, and Sophie came

04:22:34.830 --> 04:22:40.610
after, and we all got into a coach which took us to a beautiful large house, larger than this and

04:22:40.610 --> 04:22:47.210
finer, called an hotel. We stayed there nearly a week. I and Sophie used to walk every day in a

04:22:47.210 --> 04:22:53.150
great green place full of trees called the Park, and there were many children there besides me,

04:22:53.170 --> 04:22:57.010
and a pond with beautiful birds in it that I fed with crumbs.

04:22:57.830 --> 04:23:04.250
Can you understand her when she runs on so fast? asked Mrs. Fairfax. I understood her very well,

04:23:04.470 --> 04:23:07.430
for I had been accustomed to the fluent tongue of Madame Pierrot.

04:23:08.210 --> 04:23:13.230
I wish, continued the good lady, you could ask her a question or two about her parents.

04:23:13.870 --> 04:23:19.430
I wonder if she remembers them. Adèle, I inquired, with whom did you live when

04:23:19.430 --> 04:23:24.210
you were in that pretty clean town you spoke of? I lived long ago with Mama,

04:23:24.210 --> 04:23:30.710
but she is gone to the Holy Virgin. Mama used to teach me to dance and sing and to say verses.

04:23:31.770 --> 04:23:36.590
A great many gentlemen and ladies came to see Mama, and I used to dance before them,

04:23:36.730 --> 04:23:41.810
or to sit on their knees and sing to them. I liked it. Shall I let you hear me sing now?

04:23:42.570 --> 04:23:47.610
She had finished her breakfast, so I permitted her to give a specimen of her accomplishments.

04:23:48.670 --> 04:23:52.150
Descending from her chair, she came and placed herself on my knee.

04:23:52.150 --> 04:23:58.870
Then, folding her little hands demurely before her, shaking back her curls and lifting her eyes

04:23:58.870 --> 04:24:06.070
to the ceiling, she commenced singing a song from some opera. It was the strain of a forsaken lady

04:24:06.070 --> 04:24:12.710
who, after bewailing the perfidy of her lover, calls pride to her aid, desires her attendant

04:24:12.710 --> 04:24:18.450
to deck her in her brightest jewels and richest robes, and resolves to meet the false one that

04:24:18.450 --> 04:24:24.350
at a ball and prove to him by the gaiety of her demeanour how little his desertion has affected

04:24:24.350 --> 04:24:31.150
her. The subject seemed strangely chosen for an infant singer, but I suppose the point of the

04:24:31.150 --> 04:24:36.270
exhibition lay in hearing the notes of love and jealousy warbled with the lisp of childhood,

04:24:36.930 --> 04:24:41.130
and in very bad taste that point was, at least I thought so.

04:24:41.850 --> 04:24:46.970
Adelle sang the canzonette tunefully enough and with the naivety of her age.

04:24:47.750 --> 04:24:50.490
This achieved, she jumped from my knee and said,

04:24:51.030 --> 04:24:53.610
Now, mademoiselle, I will repeat you some poetry.

04:24:54.810 --> 04:24:56.910
Assuming an attitude, she began,

04:25:00.530 --> 04:25:05.310
and then, declaiming the little piece with an attention to punctuation and emphasis,

04:25:05.840 --> 04:25:12.250
a flexibility of voice and an appropriateness of gesture very unusual indeed at her age,

04:25:12.370 --> 04:25:14.990
and which proved she had been carefully trained.

04:25:15.690 --> 04:25:18.630
Was it your mamma who taught you that piece, I asked?

04:25:19.290 --> 04:25:22.410
Yes, and she just used to say it in this way,

04:25:22.830 --> 04:25:31.230
and she made me lift my hand so to remind me to raise my voice at the question.

04:25:31.770 --> 04:25:34.850
Now shall I dance for you? No, that will do.

04:25:35.310 --> 04:25:40.010
But after your mamma went to the Holy Virgin, as you say, with whom did you live then?

04:25:40.670 --> 04:25:46.450
With Madame Frederique and her husband. She took care of me, but she is nothing related to me.

04:25:46.730 --> 04:25:50.050
I think she is poor, for she had not so fine a house as mamma.

04:25:50.550 --> 04:25:55.270
I was not long there. Mr. Rochester asked me if I would like to go and live with him in England,

04:25:55.270 --> 04:25:59.870
and I said yes, for I knew Mr. Rochester before I knew Madame Frederique,

04:26:00.290 --> 04:26:03.970
and he was always kind to me and gave me pretty dresses and toys.

04:26:04.530 --> 04:26:08.610
But you see he has not kept his word, for he has brought me to England,

04:26:08.870 --> 04:26:12.030
and now he has gone back again himself, and I never see him.

04:26:13.450 --> 04:26:16.570
After breakfast, Adele and I withdrew to the library,

04:26:16.810 --> 04:26:21.390
which room, it appears, Mr. Rochester had directed should be used as the schoolroom.

04:26:22.370 --> 04:26:27.470
Most of the books were locked up behind glass doors, but there was one bookcase left open,

04:26:27.730 --> 04:26:30.990
containing everything that could be needed in the way of elementary works,

04:26:30.990 --> 04:26:37.910
and several volumes of light literature, poetry, biography, travels, a few romances, etc.

04:26:38.650 --> 04:26:43.370
I suppose he had considered that these were all the governess would require for her private

04:26:43.370 --> 04:26:50.150
perusal, and indeed they contented me amply for the present. Compared with the scanty pickings

04:26:50.150 --> 04:26:55.310
I had now and then been able to glean at Lowood, they seemed to offer an abundant harvest of

04:26:55.310 --> 04:27:01.790
entertainment and information. In this room too there was a cabinet piano, quite new and of

04:27:01.790 --> 04:27:09.970
superior tone, also an easel for painting and a pair of globes. I found my pupil sufficiently docile,

04:27:10.310 --> 04:27:16.870
though disinclined to apply. She had not been used to regular occupation of any kind. I felt

04:27:16.870 --> 04:27:22.490
it would be injudicious to confine her too much at first, so when I had talked to her a great deal

04:27:22.490 --> 04:27:28.010
and got her to learn a little, and when the morning had advanced to noon, I allowed her

04:27:28.010 --> 04:27:33.590
to return to her nurse. I then proposed to occupy myself till dinner time in drawing

04:27:33.590 --> 04:27:40.470
some little sketches for her use. As I was going upstairs to fetch my portfolio and pencils,

04:27:41.090 --> 04:27:42.590
Mrs Fairfax called to me.

04:27:42.890 --> 04:27:47.890
Your morning school hours are over now, I suppose, said she. She was in a room,

04:27:47.890 --> 04:27:53.370
the folding doors of which stood open. I went in when she addressed me. It was a large,

04:27:53.670 --> 04:27:59.630
stately apartment with purple chairs and curtains, a turkey carpet, walnut-panelled walls,

04:28:00.130 --> 04:28:07.770
one vast window rich in slanted glass, and a lofty ceiling nobly moulded. Mrs Fairfax was

04:28:07.770 --> 04:28:12.150
dusting some vases, a fine purple spar which stood on a sideboard.

04:28:12.870 --> 04:28:18.990
What a beautiful room, I exclaimed as I looked round, for I had never before seen any half so

04:28:18.990 --> 04:28:24.530
imposing. Yes, this is the dining room. I have just opened the window to let in a little air

04:28:24.530 --> 04:28:29.030
and sunshine, for everything gets so damp in apartments that are seldom inhabited.

04:28:29.750 --> 04:28:36.170
The drawing room yonder feels like a vault. She pointed to a wide arch corresponding to the window

04:28:36.170 --> 04:28:40.530
and hung like it with a Tyrian dyed curtain, now looped up.

04:28:40.990 --> 04:28:46.670
Mounting to it by two broad steps and looking through, I thought I caught a glimpse of a fairy

04:28:46.670 --> 04:28:53.150
place, so bright to my novice eyes appeared the view beyond. Yet it was merely a very pretty

04:28:53.150 --> 04:28:58.890
drawing room, and within it a boudoir, both spread with white carpets on which seemed laid

04:28:58.890 --> 04:29:05.910
brilliant garlands of flowers, both sealed with snowy mouldings of white grapes and vine leaves,

04:29:05.910 --> 04:29:12.530
beneath which glowed in rich contrast crimson couches and ottomans, while the ornaments on the

04:29:12.530 --> 04:29:19.010
pale Parisian mantelpiece were of sparkling bohemian glass, ruby red, and between the windows

04:29:19.010 --> 04:29:22.990
large mirrors repeated the general blending of snow and fire.

04:29:23.790 --> 04:29:30.290
In what order you keep these rooms, Mrs Fairfax, said I, no dust, no canvas coverings,

04:29:30.630 --> 04:29:34.210
except that the air feels chilly one would think they were inhabited daily.

04:29:34.890 --> 04:29:41.090
Why, Miss Eyre, though Mr Rochester's visits here are rare, they are always sudden and unexpected,

04:29:41.550 --> 04:29:45.530
and as I observed that it put him out to find everything swathed up,

04:29:45.930 --> 04:29:50.010
and to have a bustle of arrangement on his arrival, I thought it best to keep the rooms

04:29:50.010 --> 04:29:57.290
in readiness. Is Mr Rochester an exacting, fastidious sort of man? Not particularly so,

04:29:57.290 --> 04:30:03.110
but he has a gentleman's tastes and habits, and he expects to have things managed in conformity to

04:30:03.110 --> 04:30:09.570
them. Do you like him? Is he generally liked? Oh, yes, the family have always been respected

04:30:09.570 --> 04:30:14.750
here. Almost all the land in this neighbourhood, as far as you can see, has belonged to the

04:30:14.750 --> 04:30:21.670
Rochester's time out of mind. Well, but leaving his land out of the question, do you like him?

04:30:21.830 --> 04:30:28.010
Is he liked for himself? I have no course to do otherwise than like him, and I believe he

04:30:28.010 --> 04:30:33.810
is considered a just and liberal landlord by his tenants, but he has never lived much among them.

04:30:34.590 --> 04:30:41.990
But has he no peculiarities? What, in short, is his character? Oh, his character is unimpeachable,

04:30:41.990 --> 04:30:48.030
I suppose. He is rather peculiar, perhaps. He has travelled a great deal and seen a great deal of

04:30:48.030 --> 04:30:53.610
the world, I should think. I dare say he is clever, but I never had much conversation with him.

04:30:53.610 --> 04:30:59.090
In what way is he peculiar? I don't know. It is not easy to describe.

04:30:59.470 --> 04:31:04.930
Nothing striking, but you feel it when he speaks to you. You cannot be always sure whether he is

04:31:04.930 --> 04:31:10.970
ingest or earnest, whether he is pleased or the contrary. You don't thoroughly understand him,

04:31:10.990 --> 04:31:16.730
in short. At least I don't. But it is of no consequence. He is a very good master.

04:31:17.770 --> 04:31:21.690
This was all the account I got from Mrs Fairfax of her employer and mine.

04:31:22.270 --> 04:31:25.890
There are people who seem to have no notion of sketching a character,

04:31:26.370 --> 04:31:31.110
or observing and describing salient points, either in persons or things.

04:31:31.610 --> 04:31:38.210
The good lady evidently belonged to this class. My queries puzzled, but did not draw her out.

04:31:38.870 --> 04:31:45.350
Mr Rochester was Mr Rochester in her eyes. A gentleman, a landed proprietor, nothing more.

04:31:45.350 --> 04:31:51.510
She inquired and searched no further, and evidently wandered at my wish to gain a more

04:31:51.510 --> 04:31:57.910
definite notion of his identity. When we left the living room, she proposed to show me over

04:31:57.910 --> 04:32:03.330
the rest of the house, and I followed her upstairs and downstairs, admiring as I went,

04:32:03.830 --> 04:32:09.350
for all was well arranged and handsome. The large front chambers I thought especially grand,

04:32:09.350 --> 04:32:15.230
and some of the third story rooms, though dark and low, were interesting from their air of

04:32:15.230 --> 04:32:20.850
antiquity. The furniture once appropriated to the lower apartments had from time to time been

04:32:20.850 --> 04:32:27.590
removed here, as fashions changed, and the imperfect light entering by their narrow casement

04:32:27.590 --> 04:32:33.810
showed bedsteads of a hundred years old, chests in oak or walnut, looking with their strange

04:32:33.810 --> 04:32:41.670
of palm branches and cherub's heads, like types of the Hebrew ark, rows of venerable chairs,

04:32:41.990 --> 04:32:47.930
high-backed and narrow, stools still more antiquated, on whose cushioned tops were

04:32:47.930 --> 04:32:54.230
yet apparent traces of half-effaced embroideries wrought by fingers that for two generations had

04:32:54.230 --> 04:33:01.450
been coffin dust. All these relics gave to the third story of Thornfield Hall the aspect of a

04:33:01.450 --> 04:33:08.090
bloom of the past, a shrine of memory. I liked the hush, the gloom, the quaintness of these

04:33:08.090 --> 04:33:14.230
retreats in the day, but I by no means coveted a night's repose on one of those wide and heavy

04:33:14.230 --> 04:33:21.890
beds, shut in some of them with doors of oak, shaded others with wrought old English hangings

04:33:21.890 --> 04:33:28.330
crusted with thick work, portraying effigies of strange flowers and stranger birds and

04:33:28.330 --> 04:33:34.690
strangest human beings, all which would have looked strange indeed by the pallid gleam of moonlight.

04:33:35.690 --> 04:33:41.930
Do the servants sleep in these rooms? I asked. No, they occupy a range of smaller apartments

04:33:41.930 --> 04:33:48.310
to the back. No one ever sleeps here. One would almost say that if there were a ghost in Thornfield

04:33:48.310 --> 04:33:56.170
Hall this would be its haunt. So I think you have no ghosts then? None that I ever heard of,

04:33:56.170 --> 04:34:03.150
returned Mrs Fairfax, smiling. Nor any traditions of one? No legends or ghost stories?

04:34:03.970 --> 04:34:10.030
I believe not. And yet it is said the Rochester's have been rather a violent, rather than a quiet

04:34:10.030 --> 04:34:15.910
race in their time. Perhaps, though, that is the reason they rest tranquilly in their graves now.

04:34:16.690 --> 04:34:21.310
Yes, after life's fitful fever they sleep well, I muttered.

04:34:21.950 --> 04:34:25.850
Where are you going now, Mrs Fairfax? For she was moving away.

04:34:26.410 --> 04:34:29.510
On to the leads. Will you come and see the view from thence?

04:34:30.270 --> 04:34:36.150
I followed still, up a very narrow staircase to the attics, and thence by a ladder and through

04:34:36.150 --> 04:34:41.890
a trap door to the roof of the hall. I was now on a level with the crow colony and could see into

04:34:41.890 --> 04:34:48.270
their nests. Leaning over the battlements and looking far down, I surveyed the grounds laid

04:34:48.270 --> 04:34:54.190
out like a map. The bright and velvet lawn closely girdled the grey base of the mansion,

04:34:54.710 --> 04:35:02.350
the field wide as a park dotted with its ancient timber, the wood dun and seer divided by a path

04:35:02.350 --> 04:35:08.570
visibly overgrown, greener with moss than the trees were with foliage, the church at the gates,

04:35:08.690 --> 04:35:15.990
the road, the tranquil hills, all reposing in the autumn day's sun, the horizon bounded by a

04:35:15.990 --> 04:35:22.830
vicious sky, azure marbled with pearly white. No feature in the scene was extraordinary,

04:35:23.370 --> 04:35:29.290
but all was pleasing. When I turned from it and re-passed the trap door I could scarcely

04:35:29.290 --> 04:35:34.570
see my way down the ladder. The attic seemed black as a vault compared with that arch of

04:35:34.570 --> 04:35:41.290
blue air to which I had been looking up, and to that sunlit scene of grove, pasture, and green hill

04:35:41.290 --> 04:35:46.250
of which the hall was the centre and over which I had been gazing with delight.

04:35:47.550 --> 04:35:53.770
Mrs Fairfax stayed behind a moment to fasten the trap door. I, by drift of groping,

04:35:54.010 --> 04:36:00.150
found the outlet from the attic and proceeded to descend the narrow garret staircase. I lingered

04:36:00.150 --> 04:36:05.370
in the long passage to which this led, separating the front and back rooms of the third story,

04:36:05.930 --> 04:36:12.910
narrow, low, and dim, with only one little window at the far end, and looking, with its two rows of

04:36:12.910 --> 04:36:20.690
small black doors all shut, like a corridor in some bluebeard's castle. While I paced softly on,

04:36:21.070 --> 04:36:27.950
the last sound I expected to hear in so still a region, a laugh struck my ear. It was a curious

04:36:27.950 --> 04:36:36.090
laugh, distinct, formal, mirthless. I stopped. The sound ceased, only for an instant. It began

04:36:36.090 --> 04:36:43.390
again, louder, for at first, though distinct, it was very low. It passed off in a clamorous

04:36:43.390 --> 04:36:49.350
peel that seemed to wake an echo in every lonely chamber, though it originated but in one,

04:36:49.670 --> 04:36:52.690
and I could have pointed out the door whence the accents issued.

04:36:53.410 --> 04:36:57.770
Mrs Fairfax, I called out, for I now heard her descending the great stairs.

04:36:58.010 --> 04:37:00.250
Did you hear that loud laugh? Who is it?

04:37:00.970 --> 04:37:05.030
Some of the servants, very likely, she answered. Perhaps Grace Poole.

04:37:05.370 --> 04:37:12.690
Did you hear it? I again inquired. Yes, plainly. I often hear her. She sows in one of these rooms.

04:37:12.890 --> 04:37:19.270
Perhaps Leah is with her. They are frequently noisy together. The laugh was repeated in its low

04:37:19.270 --> 04:37:23.070
syllabic tone and terminated in an odd murmur.

04:37:23.670 --> 04:37:30.490
Grace! exclaimed Mrs Fairfax. I really did not expect any Grace to answer, for the laugh was

04:37:30.490 --> 04:37:37.110
as tragic as preternatural a laugh as any I have ever heard, and but that it was high noon,

04:37:37.510 --> 04:37:42.230
and that no circumstance of ghostliness accompanied the curious cationation,

04:37:42.650 --> 04:37:48.810
but that neither scene nor season favoured fear. I should have been superstitiously afraid.

04:37:49.270 --> 04:37:54.570
However, the event showed me I was a fool for entertaining a sense even of surprise.

04:37:55.350 --> 04:38:00.690
The door nearest me opened, and a servant came out, a woman of between thirty and forty,

04:38:01.210 --> 04:38:08.330
a set square-maid figure, red-haired, and with a hard plain face. Any apparition less romantic

04:38:08.330 --> 04:38:15.670
or less ghostly could scarcely be conceived. Too much noise, Grace, said Mrs Fairfax. Remember

04:38:15.670 --> 04:38:20.270
directions. Grace curtsied silently and went in.

04:38:21.210 --> 04:38:25.150
She is a person we have to sow and assist Leah in her housemaid's work,

04:38:25.370 --> 04:38:30.750
continued the widow, not altogether unobjectionable in some points, but she does well enough.

04:38:31.410 --> 04:38:34.770
By the by, how have you got on with your new pupil this morning?

04:38:35.530 --> 04:38:40.950
The conversation, thus turned on Adele, continued till we reached the light and

04:38:40.950 --> 04:38:45.910
cheerful region below. Adele came running to meet us in the hall, exclaiming,

04:38:50.250 --> 04:38:55.730
We found dinner ready and waiting for us in Mrs Fairfax's room.

04:39:17.830 --> 04:39:24.090
CHAPTER XII The promise of a smooth career, which my first

04:39:24.090 --> 04:39:30.350
introduction to Thornfield Hall seemed to pledge, was not belied on a longer acquaintance with

04:39:30.350 --> 04:39:37.330
the place and its inmates. Mrs. Fairfax turned out to be what she appeared, a placid-tempered,

04:39:37.810 --> 04:39:44.550
kind-natured woman of competent education and average intelligence. My pupil was a lively

04:39:44.550 --> 04:39:51.150
child, who had been spoilt and indulged, and therefore was sometimes wayward. But as she

04:39:51.550 --> 04:39:57.530
entirely to my care, and no injudicious interference from any quarter ever thwarted my plans for

04:39:57.530 --> 04:40:03.010
her improvement, she soon forgot her little freaks, and became obedient and teachable.

04:40:04.130 --> 04:40:10.410
She had no great talents, no marked traits of character, no peculiar development of feeling

04:40:10.410 --> 04:40:16.110
or taste which raised her one inch above the ordinary level of childhood. But neither had

04:40:16.110 --> 04:40:23.910
any deficiency or vice which sunk her below it. She made reasonable progress, entertained for me

04:40:23.910 --> 04:40:30.390
a vivacious, though perhaps not very profound, affection, and by her simplicity, gay prattle,

04:40:30.730 --> 04:40:37.170
and efforts to please, inspired me, in return, with a degree of attachment sufficient to make

04:40:37.170 --> 04:40:46.030
us both content in each other's society. This, par parenthese, will be thought cool language by

04:40:46.030 --> 04:40:51.430
persons who entertain solemn doctrines about the angelic nature of children, and the duty

04:40:51.430 --> 04:40:57.490
of those charged with their education to conceive for them an idolatrous devotion. But I am

04:40:57.490 --> 04:41:03.890
not writing to flatter parental egotism, to echo Kant, or to prop up Humbug. I am merely

04:41:03.890 --> 04:41:09.890
telling the truth. I felt a conscientious solicitude for Adele's welfare and progress,

04:41:10.270 --> 04:41:17.030
and a quiet liking for her little self, just as I cherished, towards Mrs. Fairfax, a thankfulness

04:41:17.030 --> 04:41:22.870
for her kindness, and a pleasure in her society proportionate to the tranquil regard she had

04:41:22.870 --> 04:41:29.810
for me, and the moderation of her mind and character. Anybody may blame me who likes,

04:41:30.350 --> 04:41:36.390
when I add further that, now and then, when I took a walk by myself in the grounds, when

04:41:36.390 --> 04:41:41.570
I went down to the gates, and looked through them along the road, or when, while Adele

04:41:41.570 --> 04:41:46.990
played with her nurse, and Mrs. Fairfax made jellies in the storeroom, I climbed the three

04:41:47.570 --> 04:41:53.590
staircases, raised the trap-door of the attic, and having reached the leads, looked out afar

04:41:53.590 --> 04:42:00.350
over sequestered field and hill, and a long dim skyline, that then I longed for a power

04:42:00.350 --> 04:42:07.250
which might overpass that limit, which might reach the busy world, towns, regions full

04:42:07.250 --> 04:42:13.910
of life I had heard of, but never seen, that then I desired more of practical experience

04:42:13.910 --> 04:42:19.710
than I possessed, more of intercourse with my kind, of acquaintance with a variety of

04:42:19.710 --> 04:42:27.150
character, than was here within my reach. I valued what was good in Mrs. Fairfax, and

04:42:27.150 --> 04:42:32.910
what was good in Adele, but I believed in the existence of other and more vivid kinds

04:42:32.910 --> 04:42:41.210
of goodness, and what I believed in I wished to behold. Who blames me? Many, no doubt,

04:42:41.530 --> 04:42:47.530
and I shall be called discontented. I could not help it. The restlessness was in my nature.

04:42:47.990 --> 04:42:53.730
It agitated me to pain sometimes. Then my sole relief was to walk along the corridor

04:42:53.730 --> 04:42:59.730
of the third story, backwards and forwards, safe in the silence and solitude of the spot,

04:43:00.190 --> 04:43:05.870
and allow my mind's eye to dwell on whatever bright visions rose before it, and certainly

04:43:05.870 --> 04:43:12.090
they were many and glowing, to let my heart be heaved by the exultant movement which,

04:43:12.250 --> 04:43:18.510
while it swelled it in trouble, expanded it with life, and best of all, to open my inward

04:43:18.510 --> 04:43:25.390
ear to a tale that was never ended, a tale my imagination created and narrated continuously,

04:43:26.010 --> 04:43:32.530
quickened with all of incident, life, fire, feeling, that I desired and had not in my

04:43:32.530 --> 04:43:33.630
actual existence.

04:43:35.830 --> 04:43:41.670
It is in vain to say human beings ought to be satisfied with tranquillity. They must

04:43:41.670 --> 04:43:48.110
have action, and they will make it if they cannot find it. Millions are condemned to

04:43:48.110 --> 04:43:54.710
be still a doom than mine, and millions are in silent revolt against their lot. Nobody

04:43:54.710 --> 04:44:00.350
knows how many rebellions, besides political rebellions, ferment in the masses of life

04:44:00.350 --> 04:44:07.130
which people earth. Women are supposed to be very calm generally, but women feel just

04:44:07.130 --> 04:44:12.490
as men feel. They need exercise for their faculties, and a field for their efforts,

04:44:12.490 --> 04:44:18.570
as much as their brothers do. They suffer from too rigid a restraint, too absolute a

04:44:18.570 --> 04:44:24.550
stagnation, precisely as men would suffer, and it is narrow-minded in their more privileged

04:44:24.550 --> 04:44:28.790
fellow-creatures to say that they ought to confine themselves to making puddings and

04:44:28.790 --> 04:44:34.530
knitting stockings, to playing on the piano and embroidering bags. It is thoughtless to

04:44:34.530 --> 04:44:40.330
condemn them, or laugh at them, if they seek to do more, or learn more, than custom has

04:44:40.330 --> 04:44:42.490
renounced necessary for their sex.

04:44:45.910 --> 04:44:53.130
When thus alone, I not unfrequently heard Grace Poole's laugh, the same peal, the same

04:44:53.130 --> 04:45:02.390
low, slow, ha-ha, which when first heard had thrilled me, I heard too her eccentric murmurs

04:45:02.390 --> 04:45:09.090
stranger than her laugh. There were days when she was quite silent, but there were others

04:45:09.090 --> 04:45:14.670
when I could not account for the sounds she made. Sometimes I saw her. She would come

04:45:14.670 --> 04:45:19.870
out of her room with a basin, or a plate, or a tray in her hand, go down to the kitchen,

04:45:19.970 --> 04:45:26.470
and shortly return, generally—oh, romantic reader, forgive me for telling the plain truth—bearing

04:45:26.470 --> 04:45:27.570
a pot of porter.

04:45:29.090 --> 04:45:34.150
Her appearance always acted as a damper to the curiosity raised by her oral oddities.

04:45:34.770 --> 04:45:40.890
Hard-featured and staid, she had no point to which interest could attach. I made some

04:45:40.890 --> 04:45:47.050
attempts to draw her into conversation, but she seemed a person of few words. A monosyllabic

04:45:47.050 --> 04:45:50.550
reply usually cut short every effort of that sort.

04:45:52.710 --> 04:45:58.170
The other members of the household—Viz John and his wife, Lair the housemaid, and Sophie

04:45:58.170 --> 04:46:04.830
the French nurse—were decent people, but in no respect remarkable. With Sophie I used

04:46:04.830 --> 04:46:10.250
to talk French, and sometimes I asked her questions about her native country, but she

04:46:10.250 --> 04:46:15.630
was not of a descriptive or narrative turn, and generally gave such rapid and confused

04:46:15.630 --> 04:46:20.090
answers as were calculated rather to check than encourage inquiry.

04:46:22.430 --> 04:46:26.310
October, November, December passed away.

04:46:27.170 --> 04:46:32.470
One afternoon in January Mrs. Fairfax had begged a holiday for Adèle because she had

04:46:32.470 --> 04:46:38.330
a cold, and as Adèle seconded the request with an ardour that reminded me how precious

04:46:38.330 --> 04:46:44.130
occasional holidays had been to me in my own childhood, I courted it, deeming that I did

04:46:44.130 --> 04:46:46.310
well in showing pliability on the point.

04:46:47.850 --> 04:46:54.470
It was a fine and calm day, though very cold. I was tired of sitting still in the library

04:46:54.470 --> 04:46:59.530
through a whole long morning. Mrs. Fairfax had just written a letter which was waiting

04:46:59.530 --> 04:47:06.430
to be posted, so I put on my bonnet and cloak, and volunteered to carry it to Hay. The distance,

04:47:06.630 --> 04:47:09.730
two miles, would be a pleasant winter afternoon walk.

04:47:10.950 --> 04:47:16.390
Having seen Adèle comfortably seated in her little chair by Mrs. Fairfax's parlour fireside,

04:47:16.770 --> 04:47:22.070
and given her her best wax doll, which I usually kept enveloped in silver paper in a drawer,

04:47:22.070 --> 04:47:27.790
to play with, and a storybook for change or amusement, and having replied to her,

04:47:28.270 --> 04:47:32.530
Revene bientot, ma bonne amie, ma chère mademoiselle Jeanette,

04:47:32.890 --> 04:47:34.830
with a kiss I set out.

04:47:35.950 --> 04:47:43.990
The ground was hard, the air was still, my road was lonely. I walked fast till I got

04:47:43.990 --> 04:47:50.870
warm, and then I walked slowly, to enjoy and analyse the species of pleasure brooding for

04:47:50.870 --> 04:47:57.390
me in the hour and situation. It was three o'clock, the church bell tolled as I passed

04:47:57.390 --> 04:48:03.830
under the belfry. The charm of the hour lay in its approaching dimness, in the low gliding

04:48:03.830 --> 04:48:05.470
and pale beaming sun.

04:48:06.590 --> 04:48:13.330
I was a mile from Thornfield, in a lane noted for wild roses in summer, for nuts and blackberries

04:48:13.330 --> 04:48:19.910
in autumn, and even now possessing a few coral treasures in hips and whores, but whose best

04:48:19.910 --> 04:48:26.670
winter delight lay in its utter solitude and leafless repose. If a breath of air stirred,

04:48:26.930 --> 04:48:32.730
it made no sound here, for there was not a holly, not an evergreen to rustle, and the

04:48:32.730 --> 04:48:39.150
stripped hawthorn and hazel bushes were as still as the white-worn stones which causewayed

04:48:39.150 --> 04:48:46.670
the middle of the path. Far and wide, on each side, there were only fields where no cattle

04:48:46.670 --> 04:48:52.290
now browsed, and the little brown birds which stirred occasionally in the hedge looked like

04:48:52.290 --> 04:48:54.850
single russet leaves that had forgotten to drop.

04:48:56.490 --> 04:49:02.990
This lane inclined uphill all the way to Hay. Having reached the middle, I sat down on the

04:49:02.990 --> 04:49:09.270
stile which led thence into a field. Gathering my mantle around me, and sheltering my hands

04:49:09.270 --> 04:49:14.710
in my muff, I did not feel the cold, though it froze keenly, as was attested by a sheet

04:49:14.710 --> 04:49:20.870
of ice covering the causeway, where a little brooklet, now congealed, had overflowed after

04:49:20.870 --> 04:49:22.890
a rapid thaw some days since.

04:49:24.110 --> 04:49:30.710
From my seat I could look down on Thornfield. The grey and battle-minted hall was the principal

04:49:30.710 --> 04:49:38.250
object in the vale below me. Its woods and dark rookery rose against the west. I lingered

04:49:38.250 --> 04:49:44.650
till the sun went down amongst the trees, and sank crimson and clear behind them. I

04:49:44.650 --> 04:49:45.910
then turned eastward.

04:49:47.290 --> 04:49:53.650
On the hilltop above me sat the rising moon, pale yet as a cloud, but brightening momentarily.

04:49:53.950 --> 04:50:00.690
She looked over Hay, which, half lost in trees, sent up a blue smoke from its few chimneys.

04:50:01.250 --> 04:50:07.230
It was yet a mile distant, but in the absolute hush I could hear plainly its thin murmurs

04:50:07.230 --> 04:50:14.950
of life. My ear, too, felt the flow of currents. In what dales and depths I could not tell,

04:50:15.490 --> 04:50:20.050
but there were many hills beyond Hay, and doubtless many becks threading their passes.

04:50:21.330 --> 04:50:27.530
That evening calm betrayed alike the tinkle of the nearest streams, the soft of the most

04:50:27.530 --> 04:50:28.030
remote.

04:50:29.670 --> 04:50:35.570
A rude noise broke on these fine ripplings and whisperings, at once so far away and so

04:50:35.570 --> 04:50:43.530
clear. A positive tramp-tramp, a metallic clatter which effaced the soft wave-wanderings

04:50:43.530 --> 04:50:50.650
as, in a picture, the solid mass of a crag, or the rough bowls of a great oak, drawn in

04:50:50.650 --> 04:50:57.490
dark and strong on the foreground, effaced the aerial distance of Asia Hill, sunny horizon,

04:50:57.790 --> 04:51:01.750
and blended clouds, where tint melts into tint.

04:51:02.530 --> 04:51:08.590
The din was on the causeway, a horse was coming, the windings of the lane yet hid it, but it

04:51:08.590 --> 04:51:15.630
approached. I was just leaving the stile, yet, as the path was narrow, I sat still to

04:51:15.630 --> 04:51:22.950
let it go by. In those days I was young, and all sorts of fancies bright and dark tenanted

04:51:22.950 --> 04:51:28.430
my mind. The memories of nursery stories were there amongst other rubbish, and when they

04:51:28.430 --> 04:51:33.670
occurred, maturing youth added to them a vigour and vividness beyond what childhood could

04:51:33.670 --> 04:51:40.210
give. As this horse approached, and as I watched for it to appear through the dusk, I remembered

04:51:40.210 --> 04:51:45.370
certain of Bessie's tales, wherein figured a North of England spirit called a guy-trash,

04:51:46.050 --> 04:51:52.630
which in the form of horse, mule, or large dog, haunted solitary ways, and sometimes

04:51:52.630 --> 04:51:56.690
came upon belated travellers, as this horse was now coming upon me.

04:51:58.590 --> 04:52:05.210
It was very near, but not yet in sight, when in addition to the tramp, tramp, I heard a

04:52:05.210 --> 04:52:11.270
rush under the hedge, and close down by the hazel stems glided a great dog, whose black

04:52:11.270 --> 04:52:16.910
and white colour made him a distinct object against the trees. It was exactly one form

04:52:16.910 --> 04:52:22.990
of Bessie's guy-trash, a lion-like creature with long hair and a huge head. It passed

04:52:22.990 --> 04:52:29.330
me, however, quietly enough, not staying to look up, with strange pretercanine eyes in

04:52:29.330 --> 04:52:36.710
my face, as I half expected it would. The horse followed, a tall steed, and on its back

04:52:36.710 --> 04:52:44.930
a rider. The man, the human being, broke the spell at once. Nothing ever rode the guy-trash.

04:52:44.930 --> 04:52:51.110
It was always alone, and goblins, to my notions, though they might tenet the dumb carcasses

04:52:51.110 --> 04:52:57.910
of beasts, could scarce covet shelter in the commonplace human form. No guy-trash was this,

04:52:58.270 --> 04:53:01.310
only a traveller, taking the short cut to Millcot.

04:53:02.950 --> 04:53:10.390
He passed, and I went on, a few steps, and I turned. A sliding sound, and an exclamation

04:53:10.390 --> 04:53:17.650
of, What the juice is to do now? And a clattering tumble arrested my attention. Man and horse

04:53:17.650 --> 04:53:23.230
were down. They had slipped on a sheet of ice which glazed the causeway. The dog came

04:53:23.230 --> 04:53:28.050
bounding back, and seeing his master in a predicament, and hearing the horse groan,

04:53:28.530 --> 04:53:33.390
barked until the evening hills echoed the sound, which was deep in proportion to his

04:53:33.390 --> 04:53:39.570
magnitude. He snuffed round the prostrate group, and then he ran up to me. It was all

04:53:39.570 --> 04:53:45.130
he could do. There was no other help at hand to summon. I obeyed him, and walked down to

04:53:45.130 --> 04:53:51.510
the traveller, by this time struggling himself free of his steed. His efforts were so vigorous,

04:53:51.630 --> 04:53:56.610
I thought he could not be much hurt, but I asked him the question, Are you injured, sir?

04:53:57.690 --> 04:54:03.590
I think he was swearing, but am not certain. However, he was pronouncing some formula,

04:54:03.590 --> 04:54:06.230
which prevented him from replying to me directly.

04:54:07.130 --> 04:54:09.830
Can I do anything? I asked again.

04:54:10.910 --> 04:54:17.210
You must just stand on one side, he answered as he rose, first to his knees, and then to

04:54:17.210 --> 04:54:17.790
his feet.

04:54:18.830 --> 04:54:26.290
I did. Whereupon began a heaving, stamping, clattering process, accompanied by a barking

04:54:26.290 --> 04:54:32.210
and baying, which removed me effectually some yards distance. But I would not be driven

04:54:32.210 --> 04:54:34.170
quite away till I saw the event.

04:54:35.790 --> 04:54:41.250
This was finally fortunate. The horse was re-established, and the dog was silenced with

04:54:41.250 --> 04:54:42.510
a down-pilot.

04:54:44.290 --> 04:54:49.930
The traveller now, stooping, felt his foot and leg as if trying whether they were sound.

04:54:50.730 --> 04:54:55.730
Apparently something ailed them, for he halted to the style whence I had just risen and sat

04:54:55.730 --> 04:54:56.190
down.

04:54:57.050 --> 04:55:02.690
I was in the mood for being useful, or at least officious, I think, for I now drew near

04:55:02.690 --> 04:55:03.650
him again.

04:55:04.590 --> 04:55:09.730
If you are hurt and want help, sir, I can fetch some one, either from Thornfield Hall

04:55:09.730 --> 04:55:10.630
or from Hay.

04:55:12.190 --> 04:55:16.490
Thank you, I shall do. I have no broken bones, only a sprain.

04:55:17.390 --> 04:55:22.790
And again he stood up and tried his foot, but the result extorted an involuntary, ugh!

04:55:24.690 --> 04:55:29.850
Something of daylight still lingered, and the moon was waxing bright, I could see him

04:55:29.850 --> 04:55:36.910
plainly. His figure was enveloped in a riding-cloak, fur-collared, and steel clasped. Its details

04:55:36.910 --> 04:55:41.790
were not apparent, but I traced the general points of middle height and considerable breadth

04:55:41.790 --> 04:55:49.790
of chest. He had a dark face, with stern features, and a heavy brow. His eyes and gathered eyebrows

04:55:49.790 --> 04:55:56.230
looked eyeful and thwarted just now. He was past youth, but had not reached middle age.

04:55:56.630 --> 04:55:58.430
Perhaps he might be thirty-five.

04:55:59.630 --> 04:56:06.750
I felt no fear of him, and but little shyness. Had he been a handsome, heroic-looking gentleman,

04:56:07.210 --> 04:56:12.330
I should not have dared to stand thus questioning him against his will, and offering my services

04:56:13.030 --> 04:56:19.770
unasked. I had hardly ever seen a handsome youth, never in my life spoken to one. I had

04:56:19.790 --> 04:56:27.350
a theoretical reverence and homage for beauty, elegance, gallantry, fascination. But had

04:56:27.350 --> 04:56:32.550
I met those qualities incarnate in masculine shape, I should have known instinctively that

04:56:32.550 --> 04:56:37.930
they neither had nor could have sympathy with anything in me, and should have shunned them

04:56:37.930 --> 04:56:42.890
as one would fire, lightning, or anything else that is bright but antipathetic.

04:56:44.130 --> 04:56:49.410
If even this stranger had smiled, and been good-humoured to me when I addressed him,

04:56:49.970 --> 04:56:54.970
if he had put off my offer of assistance gaily and with thanks, I should have gone on my

04:56:54.970 --> 04:57:01.290
way, and not felt any vocation to renew inquiries. But the frown, the roughness of the traveller

04:57:01.290 --> 04:57:06.810
set me at my ease. I retained my station when he waved to me to go, and announced,

04:57:07.330 --> 04:57:12.290
I cannot think of leaving you, sir, at so late an hour in this solitary lane, till I

04:57:12.290 --> 04:57:15.090
see you are fit to mount your horse.'

04:57:15.550 --> 04:57:20.370
He looked at me when I said this. He had hardly turned his eyes in my direction before.

04:57:21.850 --> 04:57:26.730
"'I should think you ought to be at home yourself,' said he, if you have a home in this neighbourhood.

04:57:26.990 --> 04:57:28.690
Where do you come from?'

04:57:29.870 --> 04:57:34.950
"'From just below, and I am not at all afraid of being out late when it is moonlight. I

04:57:34.950 --> 04:57:38.890
will run over to Hay for you with pleasure, if you wish it. Indeed, I am going there to

04:57:38.890 --> 04:57:40.930
post a letter.'

04:57:40.930 --> 04:57:46.490
"'You live just below? Do you mean at that house with the battlements?' Pointing to Thornfield

04:57:46.490 --> 04:57:52.210
Hall, on which the moon cast a hoary gleam, bringing it out distinct and pale from the

04:57:52.210 --> 04:57:57.710
woods, that by contrast with the western sky, now seemed one mass of shadow.

04:57:59.330 --> 04:58:00.330
"'Yes, sir.'

04:58:00.330 --> 04:58:02.310
"'Whose house is it?'

04:58:02.310 --> 04:58:04.450
"'Mr. Rochester's.'

04:58:04.450 --> 04:58:06.990
"'Do you know Mr. Rochester?'

04:58:06.990 --> 04:58:09.650
"'No, I have never seen him.'

04:58:09.650 --> 04:58:11.870
"'He is not resident, then?'

04:58:12.750 --> 04:58:13.230
"'No.'

04:58:13.230 --> 04:58:15.350
"'Can you tell me where he is?'

04:58:15.350 --> 04:58:16.490
"'I cannot.'

04:58:17.210 --> 04:58:21.130
"'You are not a servant at the Hall, of course. You are—'

04:58:21.390 --> 04:58:27.490
He stopped, ran his eye over my dress, which as usual was quite simple—a black merino

04:58:27.490 --> 04:58:33.330
cloak, a black beaver bonnet, neither of them half fine enough for a lady's maid. He seemed

04:58:33.330 --> 04:58:36.550
puzzled to decide what I was. I helped him.

04:58:36.810 --> 04:58:39.270
"'I am the governess.'

04:58:39.270 --> 04:58:41.970
"'Ah, the governess,' he repeated,

04:58:42.450 --> 04:58:46.190
"'due's taken me if I had not forgotten. The governess.'

04:58:46.190 --> 04:58:48.930
And again my raiment underwent scrutiny.

04:58:50.010 --> 04:58:55.330
In two minutes he rose from the stile. His face expressed pain when he tried to move.

04:58:56.510 --> 04:58:59.670
"'I cannot commission you to fetch help,' he said,

04:58:59.670 --> 04:59:02.710
"'but you may help me a little, if you will be so kind.'

04:59:04.450 --> 04:59:05.250
"'Yes, sir.'

04:59:05.250 --> 04:59:07.710
"'You have not an umbrella that I can use as a stick?'

04:59:10.050 --> 04:59:10.450
"'No.'

04:59:10.450 --> 04:59:14.710
"'Try to get hold of my horse's bridle, and lead him to me. You are not afraid?'

04:59:16.050 --> 04:59:21.090
"'I should have been afraid to touch a horse when alone, but when told to do it I was disposed

04:59:21.090 --> 04:59:26.810
to obey. I put down my muff on the stile, and went up to the tall steed. I endeavoured

04:59:26.810 --> 04:59:30.850
to catch the bridle, but it was a spirited thing, and would not let me come near its

04:59:30.850 --> 04:59:37.210
head. I made effort on effort, though in vain. Meantime I was mortally afraid of its trampling

04:59:38.690 --> 04:59:39.210
forefeet.'

04:59:39.210 --> 04:59:43.750
The traveller waited and watched for some time, and at last he laughed.

04:59:44.870 --> 04:59:46.730
"'I see,' he said,

04:59:47.070 --> 04:59:52.050
"'the mountain will never be brought to Mohammed. So all you can do is to aid Mohammed to go

04:59:52.050 --> 04:59:54.850
to the mountain. I must beg of you to come here.'

04:59:55.830 --> 04:59:59.610
"'I came. Excuse me,' he continued,

05:00:00.250 --> 05:00:03.010
"'necessity compels me to make you useful.'

05:00:03.790 --> 05:00:09.450
"'He laid a heavy hand on my shoulder, and leaning on me with some stress, limped to

05:00:09.450 --> 05:00:15.210
his horse. Having once caught the bridle, he mastered it directly, and sprang to his

05:00:15.210 --> 05:00:20.250
saddle, grimacing grimly as he made the effort, for it wrenched his sprain.'

05:00:21.670 --> 05:00:25.410
"'Now,' said he, releasing his underlip from a hard bite,

05:00:25.650 --> 05:00:29.570
"'just hand me my whip. It lies there under the hedge.'

05:00:29.570 --> 05:00:32.290
I sought it and found it.

05:00:33.450 --> 05:00:39.290
"'Thank you. Now make haste with a letter to Hay, and return as fast as you can.'

05:00:39.810 --> 05:00:46.450
A touch of a spurred heel made his horse first start and rear, and then bound away. The dog

05:00:46.450 --> 05:00:53.330
rushed in his traces. All three vanished, like heath that in the wilderness the wild wind

05:00:53.330 --> 05:00:54.370
whirls away.

05:00:56.390 --> 05:01:03.490
I took up my muff and walked on. The incident had occurred and was gone for me. It was an

05:01:03.490 --> 05:01:10.690
incident of no moment, no romance, no interest in a sense. Yet it marked with change one

05:01:10.690 --> 05:01:18.010
single hour of a monotonous life. My help had been needed and claimed. I had given it.

05:01:18.250 --> 05:01:23.910
I was pleased to have done something. Trivial, transitory though the deed was, it was yet

05:01:23.910 --> 05:01:27.890
an active thing, and I was weary of an existence all passive.

05:01:29.310 --> 05:01:34.450
The new face, too, was like a new picture introduced to the gallery of memory, and it

05:01:34.450 --> 05:01:40.030
was dissimilar to all the others hanging there, firstly because it was masculine, and secondly

05:01:40.030 --> 05:01:42.570
because it was dark, strong, and stern.

05:01:43.510 --> 05:01:48.010
I had it still before me when I entered Hay, and slipped the letter into the post office.

05:01:48.650 --> 05:01:54.490
I saw it as I walked fast downhill all the way home. When I came to the stile, I stopped

05:01:54.490 --> 05:01:59.570
a minute, looked round and listened, with an idea that a horse's hooves might ring on

05:01:59.570 --> 05:02:04.670
the causeway again, and that a rider in a cloak, and a guy-trash-like Newfoundland dog

05:02:04.670 --> 05:02:11.970
might again be apparent. I saw only the hedge, and a pollard willow before me, rising up

05:02:11.970 --> 05:02:18.330
still and straight to meet the moonbeams. I heard only the faintest waft of wind roaming

05:02:18.330 --> 05:02:24.710
fitful among the trees round Thornfield, a mile distant. And when I glanced down in the

05:02:24.710 --> 05:02:30.210
direction of the murmur, my eye, traversing the hall front, caught a light kindling in

05:02:30.210 --> 05:02:36.690
the window. It reminded me that I was late, and I hurried on. I did not like re-entering

05:02:36.690 --> 05:02:37.370
Thornfield.

05:02:38.910 --> 05:02:45.650
To pass its threshold was to return to stagnation, to cross the silent hall, to ascend the darksome

05:02:45.650 --> 05:02:52.070
staircase, to seek my own lonely little room, and then to meet, tranquil, Mrs. Fairfax,

05:02:52.550 --> 05:02:58.330
and spend the long winter evening with her, and her only, was to quell wholly the faint

05:02:58.330 --> 05:03:04.730
excitement wakened by my walk, to slip again over my faculties the viewless fetters of

05:03:04.730 --> 05:03:12.170
a uniform and too still existence, of an existence whose very privileges of security and ease

05:03:12.170 --> 05:03:18.690
I was becoming incapable of appreciating. What good it would have done me, at that time,

05:03:19.030 --> 05:03:24.710
to have been tossed in the storms of an uncertain, struggling life, and to have been taught by

05:03:24.710 --> 05:03:31.630
the rough and bitter experience to long for the calm amidst which I now repined. Yes,

05:03:32.090 --> 05:03:37.650
just as much good as it would do a man tired of sitting still in a too easy chair to take

05:03:37.650 --> 05:03:44.190
a long walk, and just as natural was the wish to stir, under my circumstances, as it would

05:03:44.190 --> 05:03:45.210
be under his.

05:03:46.450 --> 05:03:52.750
I lingered at the gates, I lingered on the lawn, I paced backwards and forwards on the

05:03:52.750 --> 05:03:57.830
pavement. The shutters of the glass door were closed, I could not see into the interior,

05:03:58.570 --> 05:04:04.750
and both my eyes and spirit seemed drawn from the gloomy house, from the grey hollow filled

05:04:04.750 --> 05:04:11.990
with rayless cells, as it appeared to me, to that sky expanded before me, a blue sea

05:04:11.990 --> 05:04:18.550
absolved from taint of cloud, the moon ascending it in solemn march, her orb seeming to look

05:04:18.550 --> 05:04:24.870
up as she left the hill-tops, from behind which she had come, far and farther below

05:04:24.870 --> 05:04:31.810
her, and aspired to the zenith, midnight dark in its fathomless depth and measureless distance,

05:04:32.610 --> 05:04:38.510
and for those trembling stars that followed her course, they made my heart tremble, my

05:04:38.510 --> 05:04:40.670
veins glow when I viewed them.

05:04:41.810 --> 05:04:47.990
Little things recall us to earth, the clock struck in the hall, that sufficed, I turned

05:04:47.990 --> 05:04:55.610
from moon and stars, opened a side door, and went in. The hall was not dark, nor yet

05:04:55.610 --> 05:05:01.830
was it lit, only by the high hung bronze lamp, a warm glow suffused both it and the lower

05:05:01.830 --> 05:05:08.550
steps of the oak staircase. This ruddy shine issued from the great dining-room, whose two-leafed

05:05:08.550 --> 05:05:14.490
door stood open and showed a genial fire in the grate, glancing on marble hearth and brass

05:05:14.490 --> 05:05:19.870
fire-irons, and revealing purple draperies and polished furniture in the most pleasant

05:05:19.870 --> 05:05:27.230
radiance. It revealed, too, a group near the mantelpiece. I had scarcely caught it, and

05:05:27.230 --> 05:05:32.270
scarcely become aware of a cheerful mingling of voices, amongst which I seemed to distinguish

05:05:32.270 --> 05:05:34.890
the tones of a dell when the door closed.

05:05:36.510 --> 05:05:42.830
I hastened to Mrs Fairfax's room. There was a fire there, too, but no candle and no Mrs

05:05:42.830 --> 05:05:50.750
Fairfax. Instead, all alone, sitting upright on the rug, and gazing with gravity at the

05:05:50.750 --> 05:05:57.410
blaze, I beheld a great black-and-white long-haired dog, just like the guy-trash of the lane.

05:05:58.370 --> 05:06:03.970
It was so like it that I went forward and said, Pilot, and the thing got up and came

05:06:03.970 --> 05:06:10.350
to me and stuffed me. I caressed him, and he wagged his great tail, but he looked an

05:06:10.350 --> 05:06:15.930
eerie creature to be alone with, and I could not tell whence he had come. I rang the bell,

05:06:16.010 --> 05:06:20.090
for I wanted a candle, and I wanted, too, to get an account of this visitant.

05:06:20.930 --> 05:06:21.910
Leia entered.

05:06:22.730 --> 05:06:24.110
What dog is this?

05:06:24.650 --> 05:06:25.830
He came with Master.

05:06:26.650 --> 05:06:27.390
With whom?

05:06:28.230 --> 05:06:31.070
With Master, Mr Rochester. He has just arrived.

05:06:32.390 --> 05:06:35.110
Indeed! And is Mrs Fairfax with him?

05:06:35.990 --> 05:06:40.970
Yes, and Miss Adele. They are in a dining-room, and John has gone for a surgeon, for Master

05:06:40.970 --> 05:06:44.390
has had an accident. His horse fell, and his ankle is sprained.

05:06:45.890 --> 05:06:47.610
Did the horse fall in Hay Lane?

05:06:48.690 --> 05:06:51.530
Yes. Coming down hill, it slipped on some ice.

05:06:53.110 --> 05:06:53.590
Ah!

05:06:54.530 --> 05:06:56.370
Bring me a candle, will you, Leia?

05:06:57.390 --> 05:07:03.070
Leia bought it. She entered, followed by Mrs Fairfax, who repeated the news, adding that

05:07:03.070 --> 05:07:08.570
for Mr Carter the surgeon was come, and was now with Mr Rochester. Then she hurried out

05:07:08.570 --> 05:07:13.130
to give orders about tea, and I went upstairs to take off my things.

05:07:35.770 --> 05:07:36.810
CHAPTER XIII.

05:07:38.030 --> 05:07:42.070
Mr. Rochester, it seems, by the surgeon's orders, went to bed early that night.

05:07:42.070 --> 05:07:44.450
Nor did he rise soon next morning.

05:07:44.990 --> 05:07:47.450
When he did come down, it was to attend to business.

05:07:48.050 --> 05:07:51.950
His agent and some of his tenants were arrived and waiting to speak with him.

05:07:52.870 --> 05:07:54.950
Adele and I had now to vacate the library.

05:07:55.390 --> 05:07:58.590
It would be in daily requisition as a reception room for callers.

05:07:59.330 --> 05:08:05.270
A fire was lit in an apartment upstairs, and there I carried our books and arranged it for the future schoolroom.

05:08:06.250 --> 05:08:10.410
I discerned in the course of the morning that Thornfield Hall was a changed place.

05:08:10.930 --> 05:08:16.910
No longer silent as a church, it echoed every hour or two to a knock at the door or a clang of the bell.

05:08:17.770 --> 05:08:22.690
Steps, too, often traversed the hall, and new voices spoke in different keys below.

05:08:23.610 --> 05:08:26.330
A rift from the outer world was flowing through it.

05:08:26.690 --> 05:08:30.230
It had a master. For my part, I liked it better.

05:08:32.290 --> 05:08:34.510
Adele was not easy to teach that day.

05:08:34.750 --> 05:08:35.850
She could not apply.

05:08:36.490 --> 05:08:41.170
She kept running to the door and looking over the banister to see if she could get a glimpse of Mr. Rochester.

05:08:41.930 --> 05:08:50.310
Then she coined pretexts to go downstairs in order, as I shrewdly suspected, to visit the library where I knew she was not wanted.

05:08:51.070 --> 05:08:57.230
Then, when I got a little angry and made her sit still, she continued to talk incessantly of her,

05:08:57.390 --> 05:09:02.270
a me, Mr. Edward Fairfax de Rochester, as she dubbed him.

05:09:02.870 --> 05:09:05.370
I had not before heard his praynomen.

05:09:06.330 --> 05:09:11.390
And to conjecture what presence he had brought her, for it appears that he had intimated the night before,

05:09:11.830 --> 05:09:18.330
that when his luggage came from Milket, there would be found amongst it a little box in whose contents she had an interest.

05:09:19.390 --> 05:09:27.470
Et celle-d'or signifiait, she said, qu'il y aura là-dedans un cadeau pour moi, et peut-être pour vous aussi, mademoiselle.

05:09:27.950 --> 05:09:32.270
Monsieur a parlé de vous. Il m'a demandé le nom de ma gouvernante.

05:09:32.710 --> 05:09:37.750
Et si elle n'était pas une petite personne, assez mince et un peu pâle?

05:09:38.310 --> 05:09:42.310
J'ai dit que oui, car c'est vrai, n'est-ce pas, mademoiselle?

05:09:43.930 --> 05:09:47.890
I and my pupil dined as usual in Mrs. Fairfax's parlour.

05:09:47.890 --> 05:09:52.190
The afternoon was wild and snowy, and we passed it in the schoolroom.

05:09:52.870 --> 05:09:57.230
At dark I allowed Adele to put away books and work, and to run downstairs.

05:09:57.730 --> 05:10:02.530
For from the comparative silence below, and from the cessation of appeals to the doorbell,

05:10:02.950 --> 05:10:05.790
I conjectured that Mr. Rochester was now at liberty.

05:10:06.770 --> 05:10:10.450
Left alone I walked to the window, but nothing was to be seen thence.

05:10:11.250 --> 05:10:15.810
Twilight and snowflakes together thickened the air, and hid the very shrubs on the lawn.

05:10:16.450 --> 05:10:19.530
I let down the curtain, and went back to the fireside.

05:10:20.590 --> 05:10:25.870
In the clear embers I was tracing a view, not unlike a picture I remembered to have seen of

05:10:25.870 --> 05:10:31.690
the Castle of Heidelberg on the Rhine, when Mrs. Fairfax came in, breaking up by her entrance the

05:10:31.690 --> 05:10:36.670
fiery mosaic I had been piecing together, and scattering, too, some heavy unwelcome thoughts

05:10:36.670 --> 05:10:42.870
that were beginning to throng on my solitude. Mr. Rochester would be glad if you and your

05:10:42.870 --> 05:10:46.570
couple would take tea with him in the drawing-room this evening, she said.

05:10:46.950 --> 05:10:50.910
He has been so much engaged all day that he could not ask to see you before.

05:10:52.070 --> 05:10:58.670
When is his tea-time? I inquired. Oh, at six o'clock. He keeps early hours in the country.

05:10:59.070 --> 05:11:03.670
You had better change your frock now. I will go with you and fasten it. Here is a candle.

05:11:04.510 --> 05:11:08.570
Is it necessary to change my frock? Yes, you had better.

05:11:08.930 --> 05:11:12.190
I always dress for the evening when Mr. Rochester is here.

05:11:12.890 --> 05:11:18.190
This additional ceremony seemed somewhat stately. However, I repaired to my room,

05:11:18.550 --> 05:11:24.970
and with Mrs. Fairfax's aid replaced my black stuffed dress by one of black silk. The best,

05:11:25.070 --> 05:11:30.810
and the only additional one I had, except for one of light grey, which, in my low-wood notion of

05:11:30.810 --> 05:11:35.190
the toilette, I thought too fine to be worn, except on first-rate occasions.

05:11:35.830 --> 05:11:38.990
You want a brooch, said Mrs. Fairfax.

05:11:40.310 --> 05:11:44.930
I had a single little pearl ornament which Miss Temple gave me as a parting keepsake.

05:11:45.490 --> 05:11:52.030
I put it on, and then we went downstairs. Unused as I was to strangers, it was rather a trial to

05:11:52.030 --> 05:11:57.930
appear thus formally summoned in Mr. Rochester's presence. I let Mrs. Fairfax proceed me into the

05:11:57.930 --> 05:12:03.690
dining-room, and kept in her shade as we crossed that apartment. And passing the arch, whose curtain

05:12:03.690 --> 05:12:10.810
was now dropped, entered the elegant recess beyond. Two wax candles stood lighted on the table,

05:12:10.950 --> 05:12:16.290
and two on the mantelpiece. Basking in the light and heat of a superb fire lay Pilate,

05:12:16.710 --> 05:12:23.170
Adele knelt near him. Half reclined on a couch appeared Mr. Rochester, his foot supported by

05:12:23.170 --> 05:12:28.550
the cushion. He was looking at Adele and the dog, the fire shone full on his face.

05:12:29.270 --> 05:12:35.410
I knew my traveller, with his broad and jetty eyebrows, his square forehead made square by

05:12:35.410 --> 05:12:41.770
the horizontal sweep of his black hair. I recognized his decisive nose, more remarkable

05:12:41.770 --> 05:12:48.330
for character than beauty, his full nostrils denoting, I thought, collar. His grim mouth,

05:12:48.470 --> 05:12:56.290
chin, and jaw. Yes, all three were very grim, and no mistake. His shape, now divested of cloak,

05:12:56.290 --> 05:13:02.030
I perceived harmonized in squareness with his physiognomy. I suppose it was a good figure in

05:13:02.030 --> 05:13:08.070
the athletic sense of the term, broad-chested and thin-flanked, though neither tall nor graceful.

05:13:09.950 --> 05:13:13.870
Mr. Rochester must have been aware of the entrance of Mrs. Fairfax and myself,

05:13:13.870 --> 05:13:19.330
but it appeared he was not in the mood to notice us, for he never lifted his head as we approached.

05:13:20.370 --> 05:13:26.170
"'Here is Miss Eyre, sir,' said Mrs. Fairfax in her quiet way. He bowed,

05:13:26.170 --> 05:13:29.090
still not taking his eyes from the group of the dog and child.

05:13:29.910 --> 05:13:36.030
"'Let Miss Eyre be seated,' he said, and there was something in the forced, stiff bow,

05:13:36.370 --> 05:13:40.610
in the impatient, yet formal tone, which seemed further to express,

05:13:40.990 --> 05:13:46.350
what the deuce is it to me whether Miss Eyre be there or not. At this moment I am not disposed

05:13:46.350 --> 05:13:53.630
to accost her.' I sat down quite disembarrassed. A reception of finished politeness would probably

05:13:53.630 --> 05:13:59.130
have confused me. I could not have returned or repaid it by answering grace and elegance on my

05:13:59.130 --> 05:14:06.730
part. But harsh caprice laid me under no obligation. On the contrary, a decent quiescence under the

05:14:06.730 --> 05:14:13.970
freak of manner gave me the advantage. Besides, the eccentricity of the proceeding was piquant.

05:14:13.970 --> 05:14:17.070
I felt interested to see how he would go on.

05:14:18.150 --> 05:14:24.970
He went on as a statue would. That is, he neither spoke nor moved. Mrs. Fairfax seemed to think

05:14:24.970 --> 05:14:32.370
it necessary that someone should be amiable, and she began to talk. Kindly as usual, and as usual,

05:14:32.670 --> 05:14:37.590
rather trite. She condoled with him on the pressure of business he had had all day,

05:14:37.990 --> 05:14:41.070
on the annoyance it must have been to him with that painful sprain.

05:14:41.070 --> 05:14:45.450
Then she commended his patience and perseverance in going through with it.

05:14:46.090 --> 05:14:53.250
"'Madam, I should like some tea,' was the sole rejoinder she got. She hastened to ring the bell,

05:14:53.530 --> 05:14:59.010
and when the tray came she proceeded to arrange the cups, spoons, etc., with assiduous celerity.

05:14:59.690 --> 05:15:03.710
I and Adèle went to the table, but the master did not leave his couch.

05:15:05.090 --> 05:15:09.630
"'Will you hand Mr. Rochester's cup?' said Mrs. Fairfax to me.

05:15:09.970 --> 05:15:16.450
Adèle might perhaps spill it. I did as requested. As he took the cup from my hand, Adèle,

05:15:16.690 --> 05:15:20.590
thinking the moment propitious for making a request in my favor, cried out,

05:15:21.230 --> 05:15:25.710
"'Is it not, sir, that there is a gift for Miss Airdrie in your little head?'

05:15:27.590 --> 05:15:31.010
"'Who talks of a gift?' he said gruffly.

05:15:31.110 --> 05:15:35.950
"'Did you expect a present, Miss Airdrie? Are you fond of presents?'

05:15:36.590 --> 05:15:41.070
And he searched my face with eyes that I saw were dark, irate, and piercing.

05:15:42.010 --> 05:15:47.670
"'I hardly know, sir. I have little experience of them. They are generally thought pleasant

05:15:47.670 --> 05:15:51.990
things. Generally thought? But what do you think?'

05:15:53.070 --> 05:15:57.050
"'I should be obliged to take time, sir, before I could give you an answer worthy

05:15:57.050 --> 05:16:01.370
of your acceptance. A present has many faces to it, has it not?

05:16:01.770 --> 05:16:05.650
And one should consider all before pronouncing an opinion as to its nature.'

05:16:06.790 --> 05:16:10.590
"'Miss Aire, you are not so unsophisticated as Adèle.

05:16:11.350 --> 05:16:16.910
She demands a cadeau clamorously the moment she sees me. You beat about the bush.'

05:16:18.510 --> 05:16:22.010
"'Because I have less confidence in my desserts than Adèle has.

05:16:22.150 --> 05:16:26.550
She can prefer the claim of old acquaintance and the right, too, of custom.

05:16:27.090 --> 05:16:30.430
For she says you have always been in the habit of giving her playthings.

05:16:30.750 --> 05:16:34.790
But if I had to make out a case, I should be puzzled, since I am a stranger

05:16:34.790 --> 05:16:37.590
and have done nothing to entitle me to an acknowledgment.'

05:16:38.410 --> 05:16:42.550
"'Oh, don't fall back on over modesty. I have examined Adèle,

05:16:42.850 --> 05:16:47.230
and find you have taken great pains with her. She is not bright.

05:16:47.230 --> 05:16:52.110
She has no talents. Yet in a short time she has made much improvement.'

05:16:53.890 --> 05:16:58.350
"'Sir, you have now given me my cadeau. I am obliged to you.

05:16:58.510 --> 05:17:02.910
It is the mead teacher's most covet, praise of their pupil's progress.'

05:17:05.130 --> 05:17:08.430
Said Mr. Rochester, and he took his tea in silence.

05:17:09.850 --> 05:17:13.930
"'Come to the fire,' said the master when the tray was taken away,

05:17:14.250 --> 05:17:17.010
and Mrs. Fairfax had settled into a corner with her knitting.

05:17:17.230 --> 05:17:20.150
While Adèle was leading me by the hand round the room,

05:17:20.470 --> 05:17:24.010
showing me the beautiful books and ornaments on the consoles and chiffonnières.

05:17:24.910 --> 05:17:29.070
We obeyed, as in duty bound. Adèle wanted to take a seat on my knee,

05:17:29.170 --> 05:17:31.550
but she was ordered to amuse herself with Pilate.

05:17:32.390 --> 05:17:34.910
"'You have been resident in my house three months?'

05:17:35.950 --> 05:17:36.990
"'Yes, sir.'

05:17:36.990 --> 05:17:37.950
"'And you came from?'

05:17:38.770 --> 05:17:40.930
"'From Lowood School in Blankshire.'

05:17:41.610 --> 05:17:43.310
"'Ah, a charitable concern.'

05:17:43.970 --> 05:17:45.330
"'How long were you there?'

05:17:46.890 --> 05:17:47.890
"'Eight years.'

05:17:47.890 --> 05:17:51.750
"'Eight years! You must be tenacious of life.

05:17:52.010 --> 05:17:55.470
I thought half the time in such a place would have done up any constitution.

05:17:56.370 --> 05:17:58.970
No wonder you have rather the look of another world.

05:17:59.570 --> 05:18:02.130
I marveled where you had got that sort of face.

05:18:02.750 --> 05:18:07.910
When you came on me in Hay Lane last night, I thought unaccountably of fairy tales,

05:18:08.310 --> 05:18:11.450
and had half a mind to demand whether you had bewitched my horse.

05:18:12.310 --> 05:18:14.070
I am not sure yet.'

05:18:15.630 --> 05:18:16.870
"'Who are your parents?'

05:18:18.050 --> 05:18:23.530
"'I have none. Nor ever had, I suppose. Do you remember them?'

05:18:25.530 --> 05:18:26.130
"'No.'

05:18:26.130 --> 05:18:30.950
"'I thought not. And so you were waiting for your people when you sat on that stile.'

05:18:31.610 --> 05:18:32.790
"'For whom, sir?'

05:18:33.870 --> 05:18:38.030
"'For the men in green. It was a proper moonlight evening for them.

05:18:38.310 --> 05:18:42.370
Did I break through one of your rings that you spread that damned ice on the causeway?'

05:18:43.030 --> 05:18:44.630
I shook my head.

05:18:45.590 --> 05:18:50.390
"'The men in green all forsook England a hundred years ago,' I said,

05:18:50.430 --> 05:18:52.230
speaking as seriously as he had done.

05:18:52.570 --> 05:18:57.150
"'And not even in Hay Lane or the fields about it could you find a trace of them.

05:18:57.410 --> 05:19:02.410
I don't think either summer or harvest or winter moon will ever shine on their revels more.'

05:19:03.650 --> 05:19:07.350
Mrs. Fairfax had dropped her knitting, and with raised eyebrows

05:19:07.350 --> 05:19:10.410
seemed wondering at what sort of talk this was.

05:19:12.930 --> 05:19:14.950
"'Well,' resumed Mr. Rochester,

05:19:14.990 --> 05:19:20.350
"'if you disown parents, you must have some sort of kinsfolk. Uncles and aunts?'

05:19:20.350 --> 05:19:23.050
"'No. None that I ever saw.'

05:19:23.050 --> 05:19:24.970
"'And your home?'

05:19:24.970 --> 05:19:26.290
"'I have none.'

05:19:26.290 --> 05:19:28.690
"'Where do your brothers and sisters live?'

05:19:28.690 --> 05:19:31.650
"'I have no brothers or sisters.'

05:19:31.650 --> 05:19:34.290
"'Who recommended you to come here?'

05:19:34.290 --> 05:19:38.090
I advertised, and Mrs. Fairfax answered my advertisement.

05:19:40.490 --> 05:19:44.290
"'Yes,' said the good lady, who now knew what ground we were upon,

05:19:44.670 --> 05:19:48.870
and I am daily thankful for the choice Providence led me to make.

05:19:49.270 --> 05:19:55.570
Miss Eyre has been an invaluable companion to me, and a kind and careful teacher to Adele.'

05:19:55.570 --> 05:20:00.050
"'Don't trouble yourself to give her character,' returned Mr. Rochester.

05:20:00.850 --> 05:20:06.590
Eulogiums will not bias me. I shall judge for myself.' She began by felling my horse.

05:20:07.950 --> 05:20:09.770
"'Sir,' said Mrs. Fairfax,

05:20:10.370 --> 05:20:14.870
"'I have to thank her for this sprain.' The widow looked bewildered.

05:20:15.590 --> 05:20:18.770
"'Miss Eyre, have you ever lived in a town?'

05:20:18.770 --> 05:20:19.850
"'No, sir.'

05:20:20.550 --> 05:20:25.670
"'Have you seen much society? None but the pupils and teachers of Lowood,

05:20:25.890 --> 05:20:29.610
and now the inmates of Thornfield. Have you read much?

05:20:30.370 --> 05:20:35.330
Only such books as came in my way, and they have not been numerous or very learned.'

05:20:37.630 --> 05:20:40.060
"'You have lived the life of a nun?'

05:20:40.710 --> 05:20:43.690
"'No doubt you are well drilled in religious forms.

05:20:44.250 --> 05:20:47.860
Brocklehurst, who I understand directs Lowood, is a parson, is he not?'

05:20:48.370 --> 05:20:49.140
"'Yes, sir.'

05:20:49.710 --> 05:20:51.970
"'And you girls probably worshiped him,

05:20:52.130 --> 05:20:55.150
as a convent full of religiores would worship their director.'

05:20:55.990 --> 05:20:57.310
"'Oh, no.'

05:20:57.870 --> 05:20:59.350
"'You are very cool.'

05:20:59.350 --> 05:21:04.430
"'No. What, a novice not worship her priest. That sounds blasphemous.'

05:21:05.790 --> 05:21:11.490
"'I disliked Mr. Brocklehurst, and I was not alone in the feeling. He is a harsh man,

05:21:11.710 --> 05:21:15.850
at once pompous and meddling. He cut off our hair and, for economy's sake,

05:21:16.330 --> 05:21:20.250
bought us bad needles and thread with which we could hardly sew.'

05:21:20.250 --> 05:21:26.670
"'That was very false economy,' remarked Mrs. Fairfax, who now again caught the drift of the dialogue.

05:21:27.610 --> 05:21:31.830
"'And was that the head in front of his offending?' demanded Mr. Rochester.

05:21:33.030 --> 05:21:37.110
"'He starved us when he had the sole superintendence of the provision department,

05:21:37.550 --> 05:21:42.090
before the committee was appointed. And he bored us with long lectures once a week,

05:21:42.270 --> 05:21:46.730
and with evening readings from books of his own indicting, about sudden deaths and judgments,

05:21:46.890 --> 05:21:49.290
which made us afraid to go to bed.'

05:21:49.290 --> 05:21:52.110
"'What age were you when you went to Lowood?'

05:21:53.150 --> 05:21:54.110
"'About ten.'

05:21:54.110 --> 05:21:58.070
"'And you stayed there eight years. You are now then eighteen?'

05:21:58.070 --> 05:22:04.290
"'I assented. Arithmetic, you see, is useful. Without its aid, I should hardly have been

05:22:04.290 --> 05:22:10.250
able to guess your age. It is a point difficult to fix, where the features and countenance are

05:22:10.250 --> 05:22:17.210
so much at variances in your case. And now, what did you learn at Lowood? Can you play?'

05:22:18.230 --> 05:22:18.870
"'A little.'

05:22:19.390 --> 05:22:26.870
"'Of course. That is the established answer. Go into the library. I mean, if you please.

05:22:26.870 --> 05:22:31.050
Excuse my tone of command. I am used to say, do this, and it is done.

05:22:31.450 --> 05:22:37.590
I cannot alter my customary habits for one new inmate. Go, then, into the library.

05:22:38.350 --> 05:22:43.350
Take a candle with you. Leave the door open, sit down to the piano, and play a tune.'

05:22:44.550 --> 05:22:46.770
I departed, obeying his directions.

05:22:49.030 --> 05:22:51.170
"'Enough,' he called out in a few minutes.

05:22:51.170 --> 05:22:55.110
"'You play a little, I see, like any other English schoolgirl.

05:22:55.610 --> 05:22:58.330
Perhaps rather better than some, but not well.'

05:22:59.370 --> 05:23:03.490
I closed the piano and returned. Mr. Rochester continued.

05:23:04.230 --> 05:23:09.490
"'Adèle showed me some sketches this morning, which she said were yours. I don't know whether

05:23:09.490 --> 05:23:13.090
they were entirely of your doing. Probably a master aided you?'

05:23:13.610 --> 05:23:16.390
"'No, indeed,' I interjected.

05:23:16.730 --> 05:23:21.150
"'Ah, that pricks pride. Well, fetch me your portfolio.'

05:23:21.170 --> 05:23:23.950
If you can vouch for its contents being original.

05:23:24.750 --> 05:23:28.630
But don't pass your word unless you are certain I can recognize patchwork.

05:23:29.630 --> 05:23:32.810
Then I will say nothing, and you shall judge for yourself, sir.'

05:23:34.310 --> 05:23:36.470
I brought the portfolio from the library.

05:23:37.590 --> 05:23:41.170
"'Approach the table,' he said, and I wheeled it to his couch.

05:23:43.050 --> 05:23:45.530
Adèle and Mrs. Fairfax drew near to see the pictures.

05:23:46.010 --> 05:23:48.470
"'No crowding,' said Mr. Rochester.

05:23:48.470 --> 05:23:53.190
"'Take the drawings from my hand as I finish with them, but don't push your faces up to mine.'

05:23:54.350 --> 05:23:57.410
He deliberately scrutinized each sketch and painting.

05:23:58.090 --> 05:24:02.510
Three he laid aside. The others, when he had examined them, he swept from him.

05:24:03.930 --> 05:24:07.850
"'Take them off to the other table, Mrs. Fairfax,' said he.

05:24:08.370 --> 05:24:12.030
"'And look at them with Adèle. You,' glancing at me.

05:24:12.590 --> 05:24:17.610
"'Resume your seat and answer my questions. I perceive those pictures were done by one hand.

05:24:17.610 --> 05:24:19.210
Was that hand yours?'

05:24:20.910 --> 05:24:21.410
"'Yes.'

05:24:21.410 --> 05:24:25.820
"'And when did you find time to do them? They have taken much time and some thought.'

05:24:26.970 --> 05:24:31.930
"'I did them in the last two vacations I spent at Lowood, when I had no other occupation.'

05:24:32.830 --> 05:24:34.410
"'Where did you get your copies?'

05:24:35.210 --> 05:24:36.380
"'Out of my head.'

05:24:37.210 --> 05:24:39.610
"'That head I see now on your shoulders?'

05:24:40.170 --> 05:24:41.010
"'Yes, sir.'

05:24:41.530 --> 05:24:44.010
"'Has it other furniture of the same kind within?'

05:24:44.910 --> 05:24:48.490
"'I should think it may have. I should hope better.'

05:24:50.250 --> 05:24:54.570
He spread the pictures before him and again surveyed them alternately.

05:24:55.690 --> 05:24:59.610
"'While he is so occupied, I will tell you, reader, what they are.

05:25:00.050 --> 05:25:03.710
And first, I must premise that they are nothing wonderful.

05:25:04.230 --> 05:25:07.430
The subjects had, indeed, risen vividly on my mind.

05:25:07.870 --> 05:25:13.990
As I saw them with the spiritual eye, before I attempted to embody them, they were striking.

05:25:14.010 --> 05:25:19.730
But my hand would not second my fancy, and in each case it had wrought out but a pale

05:25:19.730 --> 05:25:25.410
portrait of the thing I had conceived. These pictures were in watercolors.

05:25:25.910 --> 05:25:30.050
The first represented clouds, low and vivid, rolling over a swollen sea.

05:25:30.710 --> 05:25:34.830
All the distance was an eclipse. So too was the foreground, or rather,

05:25:35.210 --> 05:25:41.710
the nearest billows, for there was no land. One gleam of light lifted into relief a half-submerged

05:25:41.710 --> 05:25:47.050
mast, on which sat a cormorant, dark and large, with wings flecked with foam.

05:25:47.570 --> 05:25:52.910
Its beak held a gold bracelet set with gems, that I had touched with as brilliant tints as

05:25:52.910 --> 05:25:57.470
my palate could yield, and as glittering distinctness as my pencil could impart.

05:25:58.690 --> 05:26:03.330
Sinking below the burdened mast, a drowned corpse glanced through the green water.

05:26:03.910 --> 05:26:09.410
A fair arm was the only limb clearly visible, whence the bracelet had been washed or torn.

05:26:10.870 --> 05:26:18.070
The second picture contained for foreground only the dim peak of a hill, with grass and some leaves

05:26:18.070 --> 05:26:26.230
slanting as if by a breeze. Beyond and above spread an expanse of sky, dark blue as at twilight,

05:26:26.710 --> 05:26:32.790
rising into the sky was a woman's shape to the bust, portrayed in tints as dusk and soft as I

05:26:32.790 --> 05:26:39.390
could combine. The dim forehead was crowned with a star. The liniments below were seen as through

05:26:39.390 --> 05:26:46.830
a suffusion of vapor. The eyes shone dark and wild. The hair streamed shadowy, like a beamless

05:26:46.830 --> 05:26:53.670
cloud torn by storm or by electric travail. On the neck lay a pale reflection like moonlight.

05:26:54.330 --> 05:26:59.650
The same faint luster touched the train of thin clouds from which rose and bowed this vision of

05:26:59.650 --> 05:27:07.210
the evening star. The third showed the pinnacle of an iceberg piercing a polar winter sky.

05:27:07.730 --> 05:27:12.290
A muster of northern lights reared their dim lances close serried along the horizon.

05:27:13.170 --> 05:27:18.210
Throwing these into distance rose in the foreground a head, a colossal head inclined

05:27:18.210 --> 05:27:24.970
toward the iceberg and resting against it. Two thin hands joined under the forehead and supporting

05:27:24.970 --> 05:27:31.490
it drew up before the lower features a sable veil, a brow quite bloodless, white as bone,

05:27:31.490 --> 05:27:37.930
and an eye hollow and fixed, blank of meaning but for the glassiness of despair, alone were

05:27:37.930 --> 05:27:45.010
visible. Above the temples, amidst wreathe turban folds of black drapery, vague in its

05:27:45.010 --> 05:27:51.050
character and consistency as cloud, gleamed a ring of white flame, gemmed with sparkles of a more

05:27:51.050 --> 05:28:00.450
lurid tinge. This pale crescent was the likeness of a kingly crown. What it diademed was the shape

05:28:00.450 --> 05:28:08.350
which shape had none. Were you happy when you painted these pictures? asked Mr. Rochester

05:28:08.350 --> 05:28:16.310
presently. I was absorbed, sir, yes, and I was happy. To paint them in short was to enjoy one

05:28:16.310 --> 05:28:23.110
of the keenest pleasures I have ever known. That is not saying much. Your pleasures by your own

05:28:23.110 --> 05:28:29.590
account have been few. But I dare say you did exist in a kind of artist's dreamland while you

05:28:29.590 --> 05:28:37.210
arranged these strange tints. Did you sit at them long each day? I had nothing else to do

05:28:37.210 --> 05:28:43.170
because it was the vacation, and I sat at them from morning till noon and from noon till night.

05:28:43.670 --> 05:28:47.050
The length of the midsummer days favored my inclination to apply.

05:28:47.710 --> 05:28:54.750
And you felt self-satisfied with the result of your ardent labors. Far from it. I was tormented

05:28:54.750 --> 05:29:01.010
by the contrast between my idea and my handiwork. In each case, I had imagined something which I was

05:29:01.010 --> 05:29:08.710
quite powerless to realize. Not quite. You have secured the shadow of your thought,

05:29:09.150 --> 05:29:15.330
but no more, probably. You had not enough of the artist's skill and science to give it full being.

05:29:16.070 --> 05:29:23.370
Yet the drawings are, for a schoolgirl, peculiar. As to the thoughts, they are elfish.

05:29:24.290 --> 05:29:27.650
These eyes in the evening star you must have seen in a dream.

05:29:28.350 --> 05:29:33.970
How could you make them look so clear, and yet not at all brilliant? For the planet above

05:29:33.970 --> 05:29:40.470
quells their rays. And what meaning is that in their solemn depth? And who taught you to paint

05:29:40.470 --> 05:29:48.630
wind? There is a high gale in that sky and on this hilltop. Where did you see Latmos? For that is

05:29:48.630 --> 05:29:51.870
Latmos. There, put the drawings away.

05:29:53.910 --> 05:29:58.930
I had scarce tied the strings of the portfolio when looking at his watch he said abruptly,

05:29:59.490 --> 05:30:03.390
It is nine o'clock. What are you about, Miss Eyre, to let Adèle sit up so long?

05:30:03.650 --> 05:30:09.370
Take her to bed. Adèle went to kiss him before quitting the room. He endured the caress,

05:30:09.410 --> 05:30:13.710
but scarcely seemed to relish it more than Pilate would have done, nor so much.

05:30:15.710 --> 05:30:20.650
I wish you all good night now, said he, making a movement of the hand toward the door,

05:30:21.730 --> 05:30:27.730
in token that he was tired of our company, and wished to dismiss us. Mrs. Fairfax folded up her

05:30:27.730 --> 05:30:34.210
knitting. I took my portfolio, we curtsied to him, received a frigid bow in return, and so withdrew.

05:30:35.390 --> 05:30:41.750
You said Mr. Rochester was not strikingly peculiar, Mrs. Fairfax. I observed when I rejoined her in her

05:30:41.750 --> 05:30:50.030
room after putting Adèle to bed. Well, is he? I think so. He is very changeful and abrupt.

05:30:51.170 --> 05:30:58.370
True, no doubt he may appear so to a stranger, but I am so accustomed to his manner I never think of

05:30:58.370 --> 05:31:07.990
it, and then, if he has peculiarities of temper, allowance should be made. Why? Partly because it

05:31:07.990 --> 05:31:14.590
is his nature, and we can none of us help our nature, and partly because he has painful thoughts,

05:31:14.770 --> 05:31:24.410
no doubt, to harass him and make his spirits unequal. What about? Family troubles, for one thing,

05:31:24.750 --> 05:31:33.070
but he has no family. Not now, but he has had, or at least relatives. He lost his elder brother

05:31:33.070 --> 05:31:40.910
a few years since. His elder brother? Yes, the present Mr. Rochester has not been very long in

05:31:40.910 --> 05:31:48.850
possession of the property, only about nine years. Nine years is a tolerable time. Was he so very fond

05:31:48.850 --> 05:31:56.790
of his brother as to still be inconsolable for his loss? Why, no, perhaps not. I believe there were

05:31:56.790 --> 05:32:02.730
some misunderstandings between them. Mr. Roland Rochester was not quite just to Mr. Edward,

05:32:03.230 --> 05:32:09.510
and perhaps he prejudiced his father against him. The old gentleman was fond of money, and anxious

05:32:09.510 --> 05:32:14.250
to keep the family estate together. He did not like to diminish the property by division,

05:32:14.830 --> 05:32:19.490
and yet he was anxious that Mr. Edward should have wealth, too, to keep up the consequence of the

05:32:19.490 --> 05:32:25.930
name, and soon after he was of age some steps were taken that were not quite fair, and made a great

05:32:25.930 --> 05:32:32.070
seal of mischief. Old Mr. Rochester and Mr. Roland combined to bring Mr. Edward into what he

05:32:32.070 --> 05:32:38.250
considered a painful position, for the sake of making his fortune. What the precise nature of

05:32:38.250 --> 05:32:44.770
that position was, I never clearly knew, but his spirit could not brook what he had to suffer in it.

05:32:45.290 --> 05:32:51.170
He is not very forgiving. He broke with his family, and now for many years he has led an

05:32:51.170 --> 05:32:56.710
unsettled kind of life. I don't think he has ever been resident at Thornfield for a fortnight

05:32:56.710 --> 05:33:03.030
together, since the death of his brother without a will left him master of the estate, and indeed,

05:33:03.370 --> 05:33:10.910
no wonder he shuns the old place. Why should he shun it? Perhaps he thinks it gloomy.

05:33:12.050 --> 05:33:17.610
The answer was evasive. I should have liked something clearer, but Mrs. Fairfax either

05:33:17.610 --> 05:33:22.850
could not, or would not, give me more explicit information of the origin and nature of Mr.

05:33:23.110 --> 05:33:29.130
Rochester's trials. She averred they were a mystery to herself, and that what she knew was

05:33:29.130 --> 05:33:35.550
chiefly from conjecture. It was evident indeed that she wished me to drop the subject, which I

05:33:57.410 --> 05:33:58.070
XIV.

05:33:59.930 --> 05:34:02.950
For several subsequent days I saw little of Mr. Rochester.

05:34:03.480 --> 05:34:06.230
In the mornings he seemed much engaged with business,

05:34:06.610 --> 05:34:10.050
and in the afternoon gentleman from Milket or the neighborhood called,

05:34:10.430 --> 05:34:12.270
and sometimes stayed to dine with him.

05:34:13.090 --> 05:34:16.090
When his sprain was well enough to admit of horse exercise,

05:34:16.470 --> 05:34:19.590
he rode out a good deal, probably to return these visits,

05:34:19.970 --> 05:34:22.770
as he generally did not come back till late at night.

05:34:23.690 --> 05:34:27.610
During this interval even a dell was seldom sent forth to his presence,

05:34:28.350 --> 05:34:32.670
and all my acquaintance with him was confined to an occasional recontra in the hall,

05:34:32.670 --> 05:34:34.950
or on the stairs, or in the gallery,

05:34:35.490 --> 05:34:38.370
when he would sometimes pass me haughtily and coldly,

05:34:38.610 --> 05:34:42.090
just acknowledging my presence by a distant nod or a cool glance,

05:34:42.550 --> 05:34:45.730
and sometimes bow and smile with gentleman-like affability.

05:34:46.470 --> 05:34:48.690
His changes of mood did not offend me,

05:34:48.830 --> 05:34:51.630
because I saw that I had nothing to do with their alteration.

05:34:52.050 --> 05:34:55.610
The ebb and flow depended on causes quite disconnected with me.

05:34:57.010 --> 05:35:01.170
One day he had had company to dinner, and had sent for my portfolio,

05:35:01.170 --> 05:35:04.210
in order doubtless to exhibit its contents.

05:35:04.890 --> 05:35:08.110
The gentleman went away early to attend a public meeting in Milket,

05:35:08.510 --> 05:35:10.350
as Mrs. Fairfax informed me.

05:35:10.870 --> 05:35:15.310
But the night being wet and inclement, Mr. Rochester did not accompany them.

05:35:15.810 --> 05:35:17.910
Soon after they were gone he rang the bell.

05:35:18.430 --> 05:35:21.310
A message came that I and a dell were to go downstairs.

05:35:22.070 --> 05:35:24.150
I brushed a dell's hair and made her neat,

05:35:24.630 --> 05:35:28.090
and having ascertained that I was myself in my usual Quaker trim,

05:35:28.590 --> 05:35:30.190
where there was nothing to retouch,

05:35:30.190 --> 05:35:33.630
all being too close and plain, braided locks included,

05:35:34.030 --> 05:35:35.510
to admit of disarrangement.

05:35:35.970 --> 05:35:37.630
We descended, a dell,

05:35:38.110 --> 05:35:40.770
wondering whether the petite coffer was at length come,

05:35:41.170 --> 05:35:44.590
for owing to some mistake, its arrival had hitherto been delayed.

05:35:45.350 --> 05:35:46.430
She was gratified.

05:35:46.790 --> 05:35:49.950
There it stood, a little carton on the table when we entered the dining-room.

05:35:50.450 --> 05:35:52.150
She appeared to know it by instinct.

05:35:52.730 --> 05:35:54.230
Ma boite, ma boite!

05:35:54.470 --> 05:35:56.470
She exclaimed, running towards it.

05:35:56.810 --> 05:35:59.550
Yes, there is your boite at last.

05:35:59.550 --> 05:36:03.050
Take it into a corner, you genuine daughter of Paris,

05:36:03.490 --> 05:36:05.830
and amuse yourself with disemboweling it,

05:36:06.310 --> 05:36:09.290
said the deep and rather sarcastic voice of Mr. Rochester,

05:36:09.990 --> 05:36:13.290
proceeding from the depths of an immense easy chair at the fireside.

05:36:13.810 --> 05:36:15.770
And mind, he continued,

05:36:16.210 --> 05:36:19.750
don't bother me with any details of the anatomical process,

05:36:20.050 --> 05:36:22.430
or any notice of the condition of the entrails.

05:36:22.870 --> 05:36:25.290
Let your operation be conducted in silence.

05:36:26.950 --> 05:36:28.710
Tiens-toi tranquille, enfant.

05:36:28.710 --> 05:36:29.950
Comprends-tu?

05:36:32.010 --> 05:36:33.970
A dell seemed scarcely to need the warning.

05:36:34.410 --> 05:36:36.810
She had already retired to a sofa with her treasure,

05:36:37.090 --> 05:36:39.850
and was busy untying the cord which secured the lid.

05:36:40.690 --> 05:36:42.150
Having removed this impediment,

05:36:42.270 --> 05:36:44.930
and lifted certain silvery envelopes of tissue-paper,

05:36:45.330 --> 05:36:46.470
she merely exclaimed,

05:36:47.010 --> 05:36:49.590
Au ciel, que c'est beau!

05:36:50.430 --> 05:36:53.350
and then remained absorbed in ecstatic contemplation.

05:36:54.710 --> 05:36:56.030
Is monsieur there?

05:36:56.650 --> 05:36:58.430
Now demanded the master,

05:36:58.790 --> 05:37:01.210
half rising from his seat, to look round to the door,

05:37:01.430 --> 05:37:02.710
near which I still stood.

05:37:03.410 --> 05:37:05.870
Ah, well, come forward, be seated here.

05:37:06.370 --> 05:37:07.950
He drew a chair near his own.

05:37:08.350 --> 05:37:11.610
I am not fond of the prattle of children, he continued.

05:37:12.130 --> 05:37:13.750
For old bachelor as I am,

05:37:13.790 --> 05:37:16.890
I have no pleasant dissociations connected with their lisp.

05:37:17.590 --> 05:37:21.690
It would be intolerable to me to pass a whole evening tete-a-tete with a brat.

05:37:22.670 --> 05:37:25.210
Don't draw that chair farther off, Miss Ayres,

05:37:25.210 --> 05:37:27.230
sit down exactly where I placed it.

05:37:27.810 --> 05:37:29.750
If you please, that is.

05:37:30.630 --> 05:37:34.010
Confound these civilities, I continually forget them.

05:37:34.330 --> 05:37:37.550
Nor do I particularly affect simple-minded old ladies.

05:37:38.230 --> 05:37:40.270
By the by, I must have mine in mind.

05:37:40.650 --> 05:37:43.030
It won't do to neglect her, she is a Fairfax,

05:37:43.370 --> 05:37:44.330
or wed to one,

05:37:44.770 --> 05:37:46.990
and blood is said to be thicker than water.

05:37:47.870 --> 05:37:51.690
He rang, and dispatched an invitation to Mrs. Fairfax,

05:37:51.690 --> 05:37:53.970
who soon arrived, knitting-basket in hand.

05:37:54.670 --> 05:37:55.970
Good evening, madam.

05:37:56.710 --> 05:37:58.750
I sent to you for a charitable purpose.

05:37:59.170 --> 05:38:01.650
I have forbidden Adèle to talk to me about her presence,

05:38:01.690 --> 05:38:03.470
and she is bursting with repletion.

05:38:03.970 --> 05:38:07.150
Have the goodness to serve as her auditress and interlocutress.

05:38:07.650 --> 05:38:10.970
It will be one of the most benevolent acts you ever performed.

05:38:12.010 --> 05:38:14.570
Adèle, indeed, no sooner saw Mrs. Fairfax

05:38:14.570 --> 05:38:16.230
than she summoned her to her sofa,

05:38:16.230 --> 05:38:19.650
and there quickly filled her lap with the porcelain, the ivory,

05:38:20.010 --> 05:38:22.390
the wax and contents of her boite,

05:38:22.790 --> 05:38:25.310
pouring out meantime explanations and raptures

05:38:25.310 --> 05:38:27.710
in such broken English as she was mistress of.

05:38:28.650 --> 05:38:31.190
Now I have performed the part of a good host,

05:38:31.610 --> 05:38:32.850
pursued Mr. Rochester.

05:38:33.650 --> 05:38:36.150
Put my guests into the way of amusing each other.

05:38:36.490 --> 05:38:39.150
I ought to be at liberty to attend to my own pleasure.

05:38:39.690 --> 05:38:42.570
Miss Eyre, draw your chair still a little farther forward.

05:38:42.890 --> 05:38:44.310
You are yet too far back.

05:38:44.310 --> 05:38:48.390
I cannot see you without disturbing my position in this comfortable chair,

05:38:48.430 --> 05:38:50.290
which I have no mind to do.

05:38:51.390 --> 05:38:52.970
I did as I was bid,

05:38:53.250 --> 05:38:55.850
though I would much rather have remained somewhat in the shade.

05:38:56.370 --> 05:38:59.230
But Mr. Rochester had such a direct way of giving orders,

05:38:59.350 --> 05:39:01.790
it seemed a matter of course to obey him promptly.

05:39:02.730 --> 05:39:05.210
We were, as I have said, in the dining-room.

05:39:05.590 --> 05:39:07.550
The luster, which had been lit for dinner,

05:39:07.790 --> 05:39:09.830
filled the room with a festal breath of light.

05:39:10.390 --> 05:39:12.550
The large fire was all red and clear.

05:39:12.550 --> 05:39:14.970
The purple curtains hung rich and ample

05:39:14.970 --> 05:39:17.370
before the lofty window and loftier arch.

05:39:18.270 --> 05:39:21.630
Everything was still, save the subdued chat of Adele.

05:39:21.870 --> 05:39:23.330
She dared not speak loud.

05:39:24.030 --> 05:39:25.350
And filling up each pause,

05:39:25.730 --> 05:39:28.290
the beating of winter rain against the panes.

05:39:28.810 --> 05:39:31.790
Mr. Rochester, as he sat in his damask-covered chair,

05:39:32.570 --> 05:39:34.910
looked different to what I had seen him look before.

05:39:35.370 --> 05:39:37.950
Not quite so stern, much less gloomy.

05:39:38.510 --> 05:39:41.410
There was a smile on his lips and his eyes sparkled,

05:39:41.410 --> 05:39:43.950
whether with wine or not, I am not sure.

05:39:44.390 --> 05:39:46.050
But I think it very probable.

05:39:47.430 --> 05:39:49.950
He was, in short, in his after-dinner mood,

05:39:50.410 --> 05:39:53.730
more expanded in genial and also more self-indulgent

05:39:53.730 --> 05:39:56.030
than the frigid and rigid temperature of the morning.

05:39:56.810 --> 05:39:58.850
Still, he looked preciously grim,

05:39:59.510 --> 05:40:02.430
cushioning his massive head against the swelling back of his chair

05:40:02.430 --> 05:40:06.210
and receiving the light of the fire on his granite-hewn features,

05:40:06.210 --> 05:40:08.230
and in his great dark eyes.

05:40:08.230 --> 05:40:13.110
For he had great dark eyes, and very fine eyes, too,

05:40:13.450 --> 05:40:15.950
not without a certain change in their depth sometimes,

05:40:16.050 --> 05:40:20.710
which, if it was not softness, reminded you, at least, of that feeling.

05:40:21.970 --> 05:40:24.230
He had been looking two minutes at the fire,

05:40:24.950 --> 05:40:27.850
and I had been looking the same length of time at him.

05:40:28.370 --> 05:40:31.890
When turning suddenly, he caught my gaze fastened on his physiognomy.

05:40:32.470 --> 05:40:35.230
You examine me, Miss Eyre," he said.

05:40:35.230 --> 05:40:36.950
Do you think me handsome?

05:40:37.910 --> 05:40:41.110
I should, if I had deliberated, have replied to his question

05:40:41.110 --> 05:40:43.270
by something conventionally vague and polite,

05:40:43.490 --> 05:40:47.070
but the answer somehow slipped from my tongue before I was aware.

05:40:47.790 --> 05:40:48.510
No, sir.

05:40:49.410 --> 05:40:54.350
Ah, by my word, there is something singular about you," said he.

05:40:54.750 --> 05:40:59.690
You have the air of a little nonet, quaint, quiet, grave and simple,

05:40:59.950 --> 05:41:04.310
as you sit with your hands before you and your eyes generally bent on the carpet,

05:41:04.310 --> 05:41:08.470
except, by the by, when they are directed piercingly to my face,

05:41:08.770 --> 05:41:10.410
as just now, for instance.

05:41:11.090 --> 05:41:12.970
And when one asks you a question,

05:41:13.090 --> 05:41:15.590
or makes a remark to which you are obliged to reply,

05:41:16.070 --> 05:41:20.550
you wrap out a round rejoinder, which, if not blunt, is at least brusque.

05:41:20.870 --> 05:41:22.270
What do you mean by it?

05:41:23.190 --> 05:41:25.710
Sir, I was too plain, I beg your pardon.

05:41:26.090 --> 05:41:29.630
I ought to have replied that it was not easy to give an impromptu answer

05:41:29.630 --> 05:41:33.570
to a question about appearances, that tastes mostly differ,

05:41:33.570 --> 05:41:37.150
and that beauty is of little consequence or something of that sort.

05:41:37.790 --> 05:41:43.190
You ought to have replied no such thing, beauty of little consequence, indeed.

05:41:43.730 --> 05:41:47.590
And so, under pretense of softening the previous outrage,

05:41:47.990 --> 05:41:50.470
of stroking and soothing me into placidity,

05:41:51.090 --> 05:41:53.530
you stick a sly penknife under my ear.

05:41:53.850 --> 05:41:56.590
Go on, what fault do you find with me, pray?

05:41:57.150 --> 05:42:01.110
I suppose I have all my limbs and all my features like any other man.

05:42:01.810 --> 05:42:05.250
Mr. Rochester, allow me to disown my first answer.

05:42:05.690 --> 05:42:07.850
I intended no pointed repartee.

05:42:08.110 --> 05:42:09.390
It was only a blunder.

05:42:10.390 --> 05:42:11.410
Just so.

05:42:11.850 --> 05:42:12.950
I think so.

05:42:13.310 --> 05:42:15.270
And you shall be answerable for it.

05:42:15.730 --> 05:42:16.710
Criticize me.

05:42:17.150 --> 05:42:19.110
Does my forehead not please you?

05:42:19.630 --> 05:42:23.710
He lifted up the sable waves of hair which lay horizontally over his brow,

05:42:24.130 --> 05:42:26.790
and showed a solid enough mass of intellectual organs,

05:42:26.790 --> 05:42:31.590
but an abrupt deficiency where the suave sign of benevolence should have risen.

05:42:32.130 --> 05:42:34.150
Now, ma'am, am I a fool?

05:42:35.070 --> 05:42:36.410
Far from it, sir.

05:42:36.830 --> 05:42:41.530
You would perhaps think me rude if I inquired in return whether you are a philanthropist.

05:42:42.510 --> 05:42:47.090
There again, another stick of the penknife when she pretended to pat my head.

05:42:47.450 --> 05:42:51.790
And that is because I said I did not like the society of children and old women,

05:42:52.270 --> 05:42:53.230
low be it spoken.

05:42:54.330 --> 05:42:57.230
No, young lady, I am not a general philanthropist.

05:42:58.210 --> 05:42:59.630
But I bear a conscience.

05:43:00.310 --> 05:43:03.950
And he pointed to the prominences which are said to indicate that faculty,

05:43:04.430 --> 05:43:08.110
and which, fortunately for him, were sufficiently conspicuous,

05:43:08.550 --> 05:43:11.670
giving indeed a marked breadth to the upper part of his head.

05:43:12.290 --> 05:43:16.110
And besides, I once had a kind of rude tenderness of heart.

05:43:16.770 --> 05:43:20.110
When I was as old as you, I was a feeling enough fellow,

05:43:20.110 --> 05:43:23.470
partial to the unfledged, unfostered and unlucky,

05:43:24.250 --> 05:43:26.330
but fortune has knocked me about since.

05:43:27.030 --> 05:43:28.970
She has even kneaded me with her knuckles,

05:43:29.310 --> 05:43:34.150
and now I flatter myself that I am hard and tough as an India rubber ball.

05:43:35.850 --> 05:43:38.130
Pervious, though, through a chink or two still,

05:43:38.990 --> 05:43:41.750
and with one sentient point in the middle of the lump,

05:43:42.450 --> 05:43:45.270
yes, does that leave hope for me?

05:43:46.050 --> 05:43:47.450
Hope of what, sir?

05:43:47.450 --> 05:43:52.610
Of my final re-transformation from India rubber back to flesh.

05:43:54.190 --> 05:43:57.010
Decidedly he has had too much wine, I thought,

05:43:57.570 --> 05:44:00.490
and I did not know what answer to make his queer question.

05:44:01.230 --> 05:44:04.370
How could I tell whether he was capable of being re-transformed?

05:44:05.690 --> 05:44:08.090
You look very much puzzled, Miss Eyre.

05:44:08.770 --> 05:44:11.490
And though you are not pretty any more than I am handsome,

05:44:12.230 --> 05:44:14.390
yet a puzzled Eyre becomes you.

05:44:14.390 --> 05:44:16.650
Besides, it is convenient,

05:44:17.070 --> 05:44:20.290
for it keeps those searching eyes of yours away from my physiognomy

05:44:20.290 --> 05:44:23.070
and busies them with the worsted flowers of the rug.

05:44:23.510 --> 05:44:24.610
So puzzle on.

05:44:26.330 --> 05:44:30.310
Young lady, I am disposed to be gregarious and communicative tonight.

05:44:31.650 --> 05:44:33.850
With this announcement he rose from his chair

05:44:33.850 --> 05:44:36.310
and stood leaning his arm on the marble mantelpiece.

05:44:37.030 --> 05:44:40.530
In that attitude his shape was seen plainly as well as his face.

05:44:41.130 --> 05:44:43.290
His unusual breadth of chest,

05:44:43.850 --> 05:44:45.750
disproportionate almost to his length of limb,

05:44:46.590 --> 05:44:49.450
I am sure most people would have thought him an ugly man.

05:44:50.090 --> 05:44:52.970
Yet there was so much unconscious pride in his port,

05:44:53.530 --> 05:44:55.250
so much ease in his demeanor,

05:44:55.770 --> 05:44:59.170
such a look of complete indifference to his own external appearance.

05:45:00.550 --> 05:45:03.570
So haughty a reliance on the power of other qualities,

05:45:04.570 --> 05:45:06.490
intrinsic or adventitious,

05:45:06.490 --> 05:45:10.450
to atone for the lack of mere personal attractiveness,

05:45:11.290 --> 05:45:15.330
that in looking at him one inevitably shared the indifference

05:45:15.330 --> 05:45:19.650
and even in a blind imperfect sense put faith in the confidence.

05:45:20.510 --> 05:45:25.610
I am disposed to be gregarious and communicative tonight, he repeated.

05:45:26.150 --> 05:45:28.090
And that is why I sent for you.

05:45:28.370 --> 05:45:31.830
The fire and the chandelier were not sufficient company for me,

05:45:31.930 --> 05:45:35.130
nor would Pilate have been, for none of these can talk.

05:45:35.830 --> 05:45:40.470
Adele is a degree better, but still far below the mark, Mrs. Fairfax ditto.

05:45:41.510 --> 05:45:44.550
You, I am persuaded, can suit me if you will.

05:45:45.330 --> 05:45:48.370
You puzzled me the first evening I invited you down here.

05:45:48.830 --> 05:45:50.570
I have almost forgotten you since.

05:45:51.130 --> 05:45:53.370
Other ideas have driven yours from my head.

05:45:53.770 --> 05:45:56.070
But tonight I am resolved to be at ease,

05:45:56.410 --> 05:45:59.490
to dismiss what importunes and recall what pleases.

05:46:00.130 --> 05:46:03.550
It would please me now to draw you out, to learn more of you.

05:46:03.550 --> 05:46:04.770
Therefore speak.

05:46:08.230 --> 05:46:10.010
Instead of speaking I smiled,

05:46:10.590 --> 05:46:13.730
and not a very complacent or submissive smile either.

05:46:14.650 --> 05:46:16.550
Speak, he urged.

05:46:17.310 --> 05:46:18.450
What about, sir?

05:46:19.050 --> 05:46:19.950
Whatever you like.

05:46:20.450 --> 05:46:24.570
I leave both the choice of subject and the manner of treating it entirely to yourself.

05:46:25.970 --> 05:46:27.910
Accordingly I sat and said nothing.

05:46:28.650 --> 05:46:32.450
If he expects me to talk for the mere sake of talking and showing off,

05:46:32.450 --> 05:46:36.230
he will find he has addressed himself to the wrong person, I thought.

05:46:36.910 --> 05:46:38.470
You are dumb, Miss Eyre.

05:46:39.750 --> 05:46:41.170
I was dumb still.

05:46:41.950 --> 05:46:43.730
He bent his head a little toward me,

05:46:43.830 --> 05:46:47.170
and with a single hasty glance seemed to dive into my eyes.

05:46:50.010 --> 05:46:51.690
Stubborn, he said.

05:46:53.090 --> 05:46:56.230
And annoyed. Ah, it is consistent.

05:46:56.530 --> 05:46:59.950
I put my request in an absurd, almost insolent form.

05:46:59.950 --> 05:47:02.290
Miss Eyre, I beg your pardon.

05:47:02.830 --> 05:47:07.090
The fact is, once for all, I don't wish to treat you like an inferior.

05:47:07.810 --> 05:47:09.790
That is, correcting himself.

05:47:10.290 --> 05:47:14.910
I claim only such superiority as must result from twenty years' difference in age

05:47:14.910 --> 05:47:17.310
and a century's advance in experience.

05:47:17.910 --> 05:47:18.970
This is legitimate.

05:47:19.530 --> 05:47:21.470
Et je tiens, as Adèle would say.

05:47:21.850 --> 05:47:24.730
And it is by virtue of this superiority and this alone

05:47:24.730 --> 05:47:28.910
that I desire you to have the goodness to talk to me a little now and divert my thoughts,

05:47:28.910 --> 05:47:31.710
which are galled with dwelling on one point,

05:47:32.090 --> 05:47:33.770
cankering as a rusty nail.

05:47:35.070 --> 05:47:38.110
He had deigned an explanation, almost an apology,

05:47:38.650 --> 05:47:41.330
and I did not feel insensible to his condescension,

05:47:41.670 --> 05:47:43.190
and would not seem so.

05:47:44.550 --> 05:47:48.090
I am willing to amuse you if I can, sir, quite willing,

05:47:48.750 --> 05:47:52.830
but I cannot introduce a topic, because how do I know what will interest you?

05:47:53.310 --> 05:47:56.410
Ask me questions, and I will do my best to answer them.

05:47:57.950 --> 05:48:02.570
Then, in the first place, do you agree with me that I have a right to be a little masterful,

05:48:02.950 --> 05:48:05.770
abrupt, perhaps exacting, sometimes?

05:48:06.290 --> 05:48:10.390
On the grounds I stated, namely, that I am old enough to be your father,

05:48:10.570 --> 05:48:14.450
and that I have battled through a varied experience with many men of many nations,

05:48:14.910 --> 05:48:20.450
and roamed over half the globe, while you have lived quietly with one set of people in one house.

05:48:21.370 --> 05:48:22.970
Do as you please, sir.

05:48:24.090 --> 05:48:29.590
That is no answer, or rather, it is a very irritating, because a very evasive one.

05:48:30.050 --> 05:48:30.970
Reply clearly.

05:48:32.230 --> 05:48:36.530
I don't think, sir, you have a right to command me merely because you are older than I,

05:48:36.850 --> 05:48:39.250
or because you have seen more of the world than I have.

05:48:39.870 --> 05:48:44.790
Your claim to superiority depends on the use you have made of your time and experience.

05:48:45.490 --> 05:48:47.470
Hmm, promptly spoken.

05:48:48.070 --> 05:48:51.110
But I won't allow that, seeing as it would never suit my case,

05:48:51.110 --> 05:48:55.390
as I have made an indifferent, not to say bad, use of both advantages.

05:48:56.490 --> 05:49:01.990
Leaving superiority out of the question, then, you must still agree to receive my orders now and then,

05:49:02.170 --> 05:49:06.050
without being piqued or hurt by the tone of command, will you?

05:49:06.890 --> 05:49:11.570
I smiled. I thought to myself, Mr. Rochester is peculiar.

05:49:12.190 --> 05:49:16.610
He seems to forget that he pays me thirty pounds per annum for receiving his orders.

05:49:17.490 --> 05:49:22.930
The smile is very well, said he, catching instantly the passing expression.

05:49:23.610 --> 05:49:24.990
But speak, too.

05:49:27.510 --> 05:49:32.430
I was thinking, sir, that very few masters would trouble themselves to inquire

05:49:32.430 --> 05:49:36.530
whether or not their paid subordinates were piqued and hurt by their orders.

05:49:37.610 --> 05:49:42.170
Paid subordinate? What? You are my paid subordinate, are you?

05:49:43.090 --> 05:49:45.830
Oh, yes, I had forgotten the salary.

05:49:46.330 --> 05:49:50.590
Well, then, on that mercenary ground, will you agree to let me hector a little?

05:49:51.570 --> 05:49:57.030
No, sir, not on that ground, but on the ground that you did forget it,

05:49:57.030 --> 05:50:02.510
and that you care whether or not a dependent is comfortable in his dependency, I agree heartily.

05:50:03.890 --> 05:50:07.990
And will you consent to dispense with the great many conventional forms and phrases,

05:50:07.990 --> 05:50:11.410
without thinking that the omission arises from insolence?

05:50:12.710 --> 05:50:16.530
I am sure, sir, I would never mistake informality for insolence.

05:50:17.150 --> 05:50:22.570
One, I rather like. The other, nothing freeborn would submit to, even for a salary.

05:50:23.650 --> 05:50:28.010
Humbug! Most things freeborn will submit to anything for a salary.

05:50:28.390 --> 05:50:32.990
Therefore keep to yourself, and don't venture on generalities of which you are intensely ignorant.

05:50:34.630 --> 05:50:39.170
However, I mentally shake hands with you for your answer, despite its inaccuracy,

05:50:39.550 --> 05:50:43.750
and as much for the manner in which it was said, as for the substance of the speech.

05:50:44.330 --> 05:50:48.270
The manner was frank and sincere. One does not often see such a manner.

05:50:48.990 --> 05:50:55.730
No, on the contrary, affectation, or coldness, or stupid coarse-minded misapprehension of one's meaning,

05:50:56.170 --> 05:50:58.250
are the usual rewards of candor.

05:51:00.630 --> 05:51:06.930
Not three in three thousand raw schoolgirl governesses would have answered me as you have just done.

05:51:07.870 --> 05:51:13.730
But I don't mean to flatter you. If you are cast in a different mould to the majority, it is no merit of yours.

05:51:14.350 --> 05:51:19.930
Nature did it. And then, after all, I go too fast in my conclusions.

05:51:20.730 --> 05:51:24.190
For what I yet know, you may be no better than the rest.

05:51:24.190 --> 05:51:28.430
You may have intolerable defects to counterbalance your few good points.

05:51:29.790 --> 05:51:35.490
And so may you, I thought. My eyes met his as the idea crossed my mind.

05:51:36.050 --> 05:51:41.210
He seemed to read the glance, answering as if its import had been spoken as well as imagined.

05:51:42.490 --> 05:51:49.170
Yes, yes, you are right, said he. I have plenty of faults of my own, I know it,

05:51:49.170 --> 05:51:54.770
and I don't wish to palliate them, I assure you. God what, I need not be too severe about others.

05:51:55.250 --> 05:52:01.590
I have a past existence, a series of deeds, a colour of life to contemplate within my own breast,

05:52:02.190 --> 05:52:06.150
which might well call my sneers and censures from my neighbours to myself.

05:52:07.110 --> 05:52:13.490
I started, or rather, for like other defaulters I like to lay half the blame on ill-fortune and adverse circumstances,

05:52:14.330 --> 05:52:20.470
was thrust onto a wrong track at the age of one and twenty and have never recovered the right course since.

05:52:21.570 --> 05:52:28.750
But I might have been very different. I might have been as good as you, wiser, almost as stainless.

05:52:30.010 --> 05:52:35.270
I envy you, your peace of mind, your clean conscience, your unpolluted memory.

05:52:36.210 --> 05:52:41.730
Little girl, a memory without blot or contamination must be an exquisite treasure,

05:52:41.730 --> 05:52:46.510
an inexhaustible source of pure refreshment, is it not?

05:52:47.750 --> 05:52:50.670
How was your memory when you were eighteen, sir?

05:52:51.570 --> 05:52:58.990
All right then, limpid, salubrious. No gush of bilge-water had turned it to a fetid puddle.

05:52:59.670 --> 05:53:06.610
I was your equal at eighteen, quite your equal. Nature meant me to be on the whole a good man, Miss Eyre,

05:53:06.610 --> 05:53:10.470
one of the better kind. And you see I am not so.

05:53:11.310 --> 05:53:15.910
You would say you don't see it. At least I flatter myself I read as much in your eyes.

05:53:16.570 --> 05:53:21.150
Beware, by the way, what you express with that organ. I am quick at interpreting its language.

05:53:22.190 --> 05:53:30.210
Then take my word for it. I am not a villain. You are not to suppose that, not to attribute to me any such bad eminence.

05:53:30.210 --> 05:53:35.850
But, owing, I verily believe, rather to circumstances than to my natural bent,

05:53:36.450 --> 05:53:43.890
I am a trite commonplace sinner, hackneyed in all the poor petty dissipations with which the rich and worthless try to put on life.

05:53:45.130 --> 05:53:55.050
Do you wonder that I avow this to you? Know that in the course of your future life you will often find yourself elected the involuntary confidant of your acquaintance's secrets.

05:53:55.050 --> 05:54:04.130
People will instinctively find out, as I have done, that it is not your forte to tell of yourself, but to listen while others talk of themselves.

05:54:04.930 --> 05:54:12.110
They will feel, too, that you listen with no malevolent scorn of their indiscretion, but with a kind of innate sympathy,

05:54:13.010 --> 05:54:18.050
not the less comforting and encouraging because it is very unobtrusive in its manifestations.

05:54:20.030 --> 05:54:23.870
How do you know? How can you guess all this, sir?

05:54:24.610 --> 05:54:30.550
I know it well. Therefore I proceed almost as freely as if I were writing my thoughts in a diary.

05:54:31.530 --> 05:54:40.270
You would say I should have been superior to circumstances. So I should. So I should, but you see I was not.

05:54:41.310 --> 05:54:47.990
When fate wronged me, I had not the wisdom to remain cool. I turned desperate. Then I degenerated.

05:54:49.430 --> 05:54:57.230
Now, when any vicious simpleton excites my disgust by his paltry ribaldry, I cannot flatter myself that I am better than he.

05:54:57.730 --> 05:55:04.170
I am forced to confess that he and I are on a level. I wish I had stood firm. God knows I do.

05:55:05.110 --> 05:55:10.650
Dread remorse when you are tempted to err, Miss Eyre. Remorse is the poison of life.

05:55:12.110 --> 05:55:16.510
Repentance is said to be its cure, sir. It is not its cure.

05:55:17.910 --> 05:55:24.150
Reformation may be its cure, and I could reform. I have strength yet for that, if.

05:55:25.530 --> 05:55:30.170
But where is the use of thinking of it, hampered, burdened, cursed as I am?

05:55:30.610 --> 05:55:38.290
Besides, since happiness has irrevocably denied me, I have a right to get pleasure out of life, and I will get it, cost what it may.

05:55:38.970 --> 05:55:41.930
Then you will degenerate still more, sir.

05:55:42.690 --> 05:55:47.230
Possibly. Yet why should I, if I can get sweet, fresh pleasure?

05:55:47.890 --> 05:55:53.030
And I may get it as sweet and fresh as the wild honey the bee gathers on the moor.

05:55:54.190 --> 05:55:57.370
It will sting. It will taste bitter, sir.

05:55:58.570 --> 05:56:01.390
How do you know? You never tried it.

05:56:01.390 --> 05:56:09.150
How very serious, how very solemn you look, and you are as ignorant of the matter as this cameo head.

05:56:10.170 --> 05:56:11.830
Taking one from the mantelpiece.

05:56:12.390 --> 05:56:20.530
You have no right to preach to me, you neophyte, that have not passed the porch of life, and are absolutely unacquainted with its mysteries.

05:56:22.110 --> 05:56:30.610
I only remind you of your own words, sir. You said error brought remorse, and you pronounced remorse the poison of existence.

05:56:32.170 --> 05:56:37.870
And who talks of error now? I scarcely think the notion that flittered across my brain was an error.

05:56:38.470 --> 05:56:46.210
I believe it was an inspiration rather than a temptation. It was very genial, very soothing, I know that.

05:56:46.210 --> 05:56:55.310
Here it comes again. It is no devil, I assure you. Or if it be, it has put on the robes of an angel of light.

05:56:56.550 --> 05:57:00.730
I think I must admit so fair a guest when it asks entrance to my heart.

05:57:01.890 --> 05:57:04.830
Distrust it, sir. It is not a true angel.

05:57:05.930 --> 05:57:12.770
Once more, how do you know? By what instinct do you pretend to distinguish between a fallen seraph of the abyss,

05:57:12.770 --> 05:57:18.010
and a messenger from the internal throne, between a guide and a seducer?

05:57:19.850 --> 05:57:26.030
I judged by your countenance, sir, which was troubled when you said the suggestion had returned upon you.

05:57:27.210 --> 05:57:31.010
I feel sure it will work you more misery if you listen to it.

05:57:32.850 --> 05:57:37.390
Not at all. It bears the most gracious message in the world.

05:57:38.290 --> 05:57:43.190
For the rest, you are not my conscience-keeper, so don't make yourself uneasy.

05:57:45.310 --> 05:57:49.070
Here, come in, Bonnie Wanderer.

05:57:51.050 --> 05:57:56.390
He said this as if he spoke to a vision, viewless to any eye but his own.

05:57:56.950 --> 05:58:04.850
Then, folding his arms, which he had half extended, on his chest, he seemed to enclose in their embrace the invisible being.

05:58:06.310 --> 05:58:14.570
Now, he continued again addressing me, I have received the Pilgrim, a disguised deity, as I verily believe.

05:58:15.050 --> 05:58:21.390
Already it has done me good. My heart was a sort of charnel. It will now be a shrine.

05:58:22.630 --> 05:58:30.070
To speak truth, sir, I don't understand you at all. I cannot keep up the conversation, because it has got out of my depth.

05:58:31.090 --> 05:58:38.390
Only one thing I know. You said you were not as good as you should like to be, and that you regretted your own imperfection.

05:58:39.030 --> 05:58:45.550
One thing I can comprehend. You intimated that to have a sullied memory was a perpetual bane.

05:58:46.350 --> 05:58:52.970
It seems to me that if you tried hard, you would in time find it possible to become what you yourself would approve,

05:58:53.590 --> 05:58:58.450
and that if from this day you began with resolution to correct your thoughts and actions,

05:58:58.990 --> 05:59:05.470
you would in a few years have laid up a new and stainless store of recollections, to which you might revert with pleasure.

05:59:06.870 --> 05:59:12.370
Justly thought rightly said, Miss Eyre, and at this moment I am paving hell with energy.

05:59:13.310 --> 05:59:13.910
Sir?

05:59:14.910 --> 05:59:19.770
I am laying down good intentions, which I believe durable as flint.

05:59:20.470 --> 05:59:24.630
Certainly, my associates and pursuits shall be other than they have been.

05:59:25.430 --> 05:59:26.170
And better?

05:59:27.090 --> 05:59:31.910
And better. So much better as pure ore is than foul dross.

05:59:31.910 --> 05:59:39.170
You seem to doubt me. I don't doubt myself. I know what my aim is, what my motives are,

05:59:39.490 --> 05:59:46.310
and at this moment I pass a law unalterable as that of the Medes and Persians, that both are right.

05:59:48.550 --> 05:59:52.730
They cannot be, sir, if they require a new statute to legalize them.

05:59:53.190 --> 05:59:57.910
They are, Miss Eyre, though they absolutely require a new statute.

05:59:57.910 --> 06:00:02.550
Unheard of combinations of circumstances demand unheard of rules.

06:00:03.490 --> 06:00:09.750
That sounds dangerous, Maxim, sir, because one can see at once that it is liable to abuse.

06:00:11.730 --> 06:00:18.050
Sententious sage, so it is, but I swear by my household gods not to abuse it.

06:00:19.230 --> 06:00:20.770
You are human and fallible.

06:00:22.070 --> 06:00:24.770
I am, so are you. What then?

06:00:25.630 --> 06:00:32.190
The human and fallible should not irrigate a power with which the divine and perfect alone can be safely entrusted.

06:00:33.010 --> 06:00:33.710
What power?

06:00:34.250 --> 06:00:39.590
That of saying of any strange, unsanctioned line of action, Let it be right.

06:00:40.690 --> 06:00:43.850
Let it be right, the very words you have pronounced them.

06:00:44.830 --> 06:00:52.830
May it be right, then, I said, as I rose, deeming it useless to continue a discourse which was all darkness to me.

06:00:52.830 --> 06:01:01.210
And besides, sensible that the character of my interlocutor was beyond my penetration, at least beyond its present reach,

06:01:01.730 --> 06:01:07.330
and feeling the uncertainty, the vague sense of insecurity which accompanies a conviction of ignorance.

06:01:09.170 --> 06:01:10.470
Where are you going?

06:01:11.390 --> 06:01:14.030
To put Adele to bed. It is past her bedtime.

06:01:14.870 --> 06:01:17.850
You are afraid of me because I talk like a sphinx.

06:01:18.910 --> 06:01:24.950
Your language is enigmatical, sir, but though I am bewildered, I am certainly not afraid.

06:01:25.570 --> 06:01:29.670
You are afraid. Your self-love dreads a blunder.

06:01:31.570 --> 06:01:35.890
In that sense, I do feel apprehensive. I have no wish to talk nonsense.

06:01:37.010 --> 06:01:42.930
If you did, it would be in such a grave, quiet manner. I should mistake it for sense.

06:01:43.990 --> 06:01:45.730
Do you never laugh, Miss Eyre?

06:01:45.730 --> 06:01:52.890
Don't trouble yourself to answer. I see you laugh rarely, but you can laugh very merrily.

06:01:53.230 --> 06:01:57.730
Believe me, you are not naturally austere, any more than I am naturally vicious.

06:01:58.710 --> 06:02:06.870
The low-wood constraint still clings to you somewhat, controlling your features, muffling your voice, and restricting your limbs.

06:02:07.610 --> 06:02:13.290
And you fear in the presence of a man and a brother, or father, or master, or whatever you will.

06:02:13.290 --> 06:02:17.950
To smile too gaily, speak too freely, or move too quickly.

06:02:18.850 --> 06:02:26.190
But in time, I think you will learn to be natural with me, as I find it impossible to be conventional with you.

06:02:26.770 --> 06:02:32.190
And then your looks and movements will have more vivacity and variety than they dare offer now.

06:02:32.970 --> 06:02:38.370
I see at intervals the glance of a curious sort of bird through the close-set bars of a cage.

06:02:38.370 --> 06:02:46.950
A vivid, restless, resolute captive is there. Were it but free, it would soar cloud-high.

06:02:48.130 --> 06:02:49.830
You are still bent on going?

06:02:51.150 --> 06:02:53.210
It has struck nine, sir.

06:02:54.150 --> 06:02:58.790
Never mind. Wait a minute. Adele is not ready to go to bed yet.

06:03:00.470 --> 06:03:05.690
My position, Miss Eyre, with my back to the fire and my face to the room, favours observation.

06:03:05.690 --> 06:03:10.110
While talking to you, I have also occasionally watched Adele.

06:03:11.010 --> 06:03:19.250
I have my own reasons for thinking her a curious study, reasons that I may, nay, that I shall impart to you some day.

06:03:19.970 --> 06:03:24.770
She pulled out of her box about ten minutes ago a little pink silk frock.

06:03:25.270 --> 06:03:27.470
Rapture lit her face as she unfolded it.

06:03:27.850 --> 06:03:33.650
Coketry runs in her blood, blends with her brains, and seasons the marrow of her bones.

06:03:33.650 --> 06:03:39.030
Il faut que je le sais, she cried, et à l'instant même.

06:03:39.830 --> 06:03:41.070
And she rushed out of the room.

06:03:41.630 --> 06:03:44.250
She is now with Sophie, undergoing a robing process.

06:03:44.930 --> 06:03:49.330
In a few minutes she will re-enter, and I know what I shall see.

06:03:50.390 --> 06:03:56.830
A miniature of Céline Véran, as she used to appear on the boards at the rising of...

06:03:56.830 --> 06:03:58.250
But never mind that.

06:03:58.950 --> 06:04:03.070
However, my tenderest feelings are about to receive a shock.

06:04:03.670 --> 06:04:05.130
Such is my presentment.

06:04:07.930 --> 06:04:10.390
Stay now to see whether it will be realized.

06:04:13.250 --> 06:04:16.510
Ere long, Adele's little foot was heard tripping across the hall.

06:04:17.030 --> 06:04:20.050
She entered, transformed as her guardian had predicted.

06:04:20.670 --> 06:04:25.770
A dress of rose-coloured satin, very short, and as full in the skirt as it could be gathered,

06:04:25.770 --> 06:04:29.050
replaced the brown frock she had previously worn.

06:04:29.790 --> 06:04:31.650
A wreath of rose-buds circled her forehead.

06:04:32.270 --> 06:04:35.770
Her feet were dressed in silk stockings and small white satin sandals.

06:04:38.530 --> 06:04:42.470
Est-ce que ma robe va bien? she cried, bounding forward.

06:04:42.970 --> 06:04:46.770
Et mes souillets, et mes bras, tenez, je crois que je vais danser.

06:04:48.670 --> 06:04:53.770
And spreading out her dress, she chaussait across the room till having reached Mr. Rochester,

06:04:53.770 --> 06:04:57.250
she wheeled lightly round before him on tiptoe,

06:04:57.250 --> 06:04:59.750
then dropped on one knee at his feet, exclaiming,

06:05:00.090 --> 06:05:03.530
Monsieur, je vous remercie mille fois de votre bande.

06:05:04.490 --> 06:05:05.990
then rising, she added,

06:05:06.490 --> 06:05:10.050
C'est comme cela que m'a faissé, n'est-ce pas, Monsieur?

06:05:13.070 --> 06:05:14.810
Precisely was the answer.

06:05:15.410 --> 06:05:20.170
And comme cela, she charmed my English gold out of my British britch's pocket.

06:05:20.830 --> 06:05:22.990
I have been green too, Miss Ere.

06:05:22.990 --> 06:05:29.410
Aye, grass green, not a more vernal tint freshens you now than once freshened me.

06:05:30.090 --> 06:05:31.910
My spring is gone, however,

06:05:32.550 --> 06:05:35.810
but it has left me that French fleurette on my hands,

06:05:35.870 --> 06:05:38.470
which in some moods I would fain be rid of.

06:05:39.450 --> 06:05:42.310
Not valuing now the root whence it sprang,

06:05:42.590 --> 06:05:46.190
having found that it was of a sort which nothing but gold dust could manure,

06:05:46.970 --> 06:05:49.190
I have but half a liking to the blossom.

06:05:50.150 --> 06:05:53.350
Especially when it looks so artificial as just now.

06:05:54.550 --> 06:05:56.630
I keep it and rear it,

06:05:56.930 --> 06:06:00.430
rather on the Roman Catholic principle of expiating numerous sins,

06:06:00.710 --> 06:06:02.430
great or small, by one good work.

06:06:03.310 --> 06:06:05.310
I'll explain all this some day.

06:06:05.770 --> 06:06:06.570
Good night.

06:06:30.810 --> 06:06:32.370
CHAPTER XV.

06:06:33.410 --> 06:06:36.750
Mr. Rochester did, on a future occasion, explain it.

06:06:36.750 --> 06:06:40.610
It was one afternoon when he chanced to meet me and Adele in the grounds,

06:06:40.610 --> 06:06:43.610
and while she played with Pilate in her shuttlecock,

06:06:43.810 --> 06:06:47.510
he asked me to walk up and down a long beach avenue within sight of her.

06:06:48.430 --> 06:06:52.330
He then said that she was the daughter of a French opera dancer,

06:06:52.770 --> 06:06:57.990
Céline Véran, toward whom he had once cherished what he called a grande passion.

06:06:59.170 --> 06:07:03.390
This passion Céline had professed to return with even superior ardor.

06:07:03.390 --> 06:07:07.010
He thought himself her idol, ugly as he was.

06:07:07.290 --> 06:07:11.590
He believed, as he said, that she preferred his tail d'athlète

06:07:11.590 --> 06:07:14.350
to the elegance of the Apollo Belvedere.

06:07:16.270 --> 06:07:20.150
And, Miss Eyre, so much was I flattered by this preference

06:07:20.150 --> 06:07:25.390
of the Gaelic sylph for her British gnome that I installed her in an hotel,

06:07:25.950 --> 06:07:29.450
gave her a complete establishment of servants, a carriage,

06:07:29.450 --> 06:07:33.470
cashmere, diamonds, dentelles, etc.

06:07:34.730 --> 06:07:39.810
In short, I began the process of ruining myself in the received style,

06:07:40.110 --> 06:07:41.590
like any other spoonie.

06:07:42.290 --> 06:07:46.750
I had not, it seems, the originality to chalk out a new road to shame and destruction,

06:07:47.390 --> 06:07:52.790
but trod the old track with stupid exactness not to deviate an inch from the beaten center.

06:07:53.750 --> 06:07:58.570
I had, as I deserved to have, the fate of all other spoonies.

06:07:59.310 --> 06:08:03.410
Happening to call one evening when Céline did not expect me, I found her out.

06:08:04.050 --> 06:08:07.770
But it was a warm night, and I was tired of strolling through Paris,

06:08:08.350 --> 06:08:14.130
so I sat down in her boudoir, happy to breathe the air consecrated so lately by her presence.

06:08:15.030 --> 06:08:17.270
No, I exaggerate.

06:08:17.930 --> 06:08:21.190
I never thought there was any consecrating virtue about her.

06:08:21.610 --> 06:08:27.190
It was rather a sort of pastile perfume she had left, a scent of musk and amber,

06:08:27.190 --> 06:08:29.310
than an odor of sanctity.

06:08:30.270 --> 06:08:35.470
I was just beginning to stifle with the fumes of conservatory flowers and sprinkled essences

06:08:35.470 --> 06:08:39.110
when I bethought myself to open the window and step out onto the balcony.

06:08:40.250 --> 06:08:45.610
It was moonlight and gaslight besides, and very still and serene.

06:08:46.130 --> 06:08:48.510
The balcony was furnished with a chair or two.

06:08:48.810 --> 06:08:50.610
I sat down and took out a cigar.

06:08:51.270 --> 06:08:53.870
I will take one now, if you will excuse me.

06:08:54.710 --> 06:08:59.250
Here ensued a pause, filled up by the producing and lighting of a cigar.

06:09:00.210 --> 06:09:03.830
Having placed it to his lips and breathed a trail of Havana incense

06:09:03.830 --> 06:09:07.010
on the freezing and sunless air, he went on.

06:09:07.810 --> 06:09:12.370
I liked bonbons, too, in those days, Miss Eyre, and I was croquant,

06:09:12.850 --> 06:09:18.510
overlooked the barbarism, croquant chocolate comfits, and smoking alternately,

06:09:19.050 --> 06:09:22.790
watching meantime the équipages that rolled along the fashionable streets

06:09:22.790 --> 06:09:24.590
toward the neighboring opera house.

06:09:25.310 --> 06:09:29.990
When in an elegant closed carriage drawn by a beautiful pair of English horses

06:09:29.990 --> 06:09:36.310
and distinctly seen in the brilliant city night, I recognized the voiture I had given Céline.

06:09:37.350 --> 06:09:38.370
She was returning.

06:09:39.130 --> 06:09:43.350
Of course, my heart thumped with impatience against the iron rails I lent upon.

06:09:44.650 --> 06:09:47.850
The carriage stopped, as I had expected, at the hotel door.

06:09:48.390 --> 06:09:49.270
My flame.

06:09:49.830 --> 06:09:52.770
That is the very word for an opera in Emirata.

06:09:53.970 --> 06:09:54.470
Alighted.

06:09:55.350 --> 06:10:00.750
Though muffled in a cloak, an unnecessary encumbrance by the bayon so warm a June evening,

06:10:01.510 --> 06:10:05.570
I knew her instantly by her little foot seen peeping from the skirt of her dress

06:10:05.570 --> 06:10:07.830
as she skipped from the carriage step.

06:10:08.790 --> 06:10:13.710
Bending over the balcony, I was about to murmur mon ange, in a tone, of course,

06:10:14.070 --> 06:10:16.570
which should be audible to the ear of love alone,

06:10:17.310 --> 06:10:21.350
when a figure jumped from the carriage after her, cloaked also.

06:10:21.910 --> 06:10:25.310
But that was a spurred heel which had rung on the pavement,

06:10:25.790 --> 06:10:30.410
and that was a hatted head which now passed under the arched porte-cochet of the hotel.

06:10:32.790 --> 06:10:35.470
You never felt jealousy, did you, Miss Eyre?

06:10:36.150 --> 06:10:37.350
Of course not.

06:10:37.670 --> 06:10:39.090
I need not ask you.

06:10:39.470 --> 06:10:40.990
Because you never felt love.

06:10:41.890 --> 06:10:44.230
You have both sentiments yet to experience.

06:10:44.790 --> 06:10:45.990
Your soul sleeps.

06:10:46.610 --> 06:10:49.230
The shock is yet to be given which shall awaken it.

06:10:49.230 --> 06:10:52.930
You think all existence lapses in as quiet a flow

06:10:52.930 --> 06:10:55.750
as that in which your youth has hitherto slid away.

06:10:56.350 --> 06:10:58.910
Floating on with closed eyes and muffled ears,

06:10:59.370 --> 06:11:02.830
you neither see the rocks bristling not far off in the bed of the flood,

06:11:03.210 --> 06:11:05.370
nor hear the breakers boil at their base.

06:11:06.230 --> 06:11:09.050
But I tell you, and you may mark my words,

06:11:09.330 --> 06:11:12.430
you will come some day to a craggy pass in the channel,

06:11:13.030 --> 06:11:18.390
where the whole of life's stream will be broken up into whirl and tumult, foam and noise.

06:11:19.030 --> 06:11:21.870
Either you will be dashed to atoms on crag-points,

06:11:22.630 --> 06:11:29.110
or lifted up and borne on by some master wave into a calmer current, as I am now.

06:11:30.730 --> 06:11:32.270
I like this day.

06:11:32.970 --> 06:11:34.730
I like that sky of steel.

06:11:35.470 --> 06:11:39.050
I like the sternness and stillness of the world under this frost.

06:11:40.050 --> 06:11:43.790
I like Thornfield, its antiquity, its retirement,

06:11:44.410 --> 06:11:47.190
its old crow-trees and thorn-trees,

06:11:47.190 --> 06:11:52.470
its gray façade and lines of dark windows reflecting that metal welkin.

06:11:53.430 --> 06:11:56.650
And yet how long have I abhorred the very thought of it,

06:11:57.070 --> 06:12:01.470
shunned it like a great plague-house, how I do still abhor.

06:12:03.370 --> 06:12:05.690
He ground his teeth and was silent.

06:12:06.590 --> 06:12:09.790
He arrested his step and struck his boot against the hard ground.

06:12:10.710 --> 06:12:13.290
Some hated thought seemed to have him in its grip,

06:12:13.690 --> 06:12:16.470
and to hold him so tightly that he could not advance.

06:12:17.190 --> 06:12:20.090
We were ascending the avenue when he thus paused.

06:12:20.350 --> 06:12:21.680
The hall was before us.

06:12:22.370 --> 06:12:24.230
Lifting his eyes to its battlements,

06:12:24.650 --> 06:12:28.710
he cast over them such a glare as I never saw before or since.

06:12:29.390 --> 06:12:34.470
Pain, shame, ire, impatience, disgust, detestation,

06:12:34.930 --> 06:12:38.770
seemed momentarily to hold a quivering conflict in the large pupil

06:12:38.770 --> 06:12:41.030
dilating under his ebon eyebrow.

06:12:42.510 --> 06:12:45.010
Wild was the wrestle which should be paramount,

06:12:45.010 --> 06:12:49.730
but another feeling rose and triumphed, something hard and cynical,

06:12:50.390 --> 06:12:52.050
self-willed and resolute.

06:12:52.690 --> 06:12:55.570
It settled his passion and petrified his countenance.

06:12:56.070 --> 06:12:57.190
He went on.

06:12:58.830 --> 06:13:01.210
During the moment I was silent, Miss Eyre,

06:13:01.470 --> 06:13:03.870
I was arranging a point with my destiny.

06:13:05.030 --> 06:13:07.490
She stood there by that beach trunk,

06:13:08.350 --> 06:13:12.910
a hag like one of those who appeared to Macbeth on the heath of Foras.

06:13:14.230 --> 06:13:18.490
You like Thornfield? she said, lifting her finger.

06:13:19.170 --> 06:13:21.550
And then she wrote in the air a memento

06:13:21.550 --> 06:13:25.870
which ran in lurid hieroglyphics all along the house front

06:13:25.870 --> 06:13:28.810
between the upper and lower row of windows.

06:13:29.730 --> 06:13:33.270
Like it if you can, like it if you dare.

06:13:34.430 --> 06:13:38.390
I will like it, said I, I dare like it, and

06:13:38.390 --> 06:13:41.990
he subjoined moodily, I will keep my word.

06:13:41.990 --> 06:13:47.150
I will break obstacles to happiness, to goodness, yes, goodness.

06:13:47.970 --> 06:13:51.210
I wish to be a better man than I have been, than I am.

06:13:52.270 --> 06:13:56.210
As Job's Leviathan broke the spear, the dart, and the habergeon,

06:13:56.770 --> 06:13:59.770
hindrances which others count as iron and brass,

06:14:00.410 --> 06:14:03.330
I will esteem but straw and rotten wood.

06:14:05.250 --> 06:14:07.490
Adele here ran before him with her shuttlecock.

06:14:07.850 --> 06:14:10.290
Away! he cried harshly.

06:14:10.290 --> 06:14:13.090
Keep at a distance, child, or go into Sophie.

06:14:14.830 --> 06:14:17.450
Continuing then to pursue his walk in silence,

06:14:17.910 --> 06:14:21.830
I ventured to recall him to the point once he had abruptly diverged.

06:14:23.210 --> 06:14:26.230
Did you leave the balcony, sir? I asked.

06:14:27.090 --> 06:14:28.770
When mademoiselle Varon entered?

06:14:29.590 --> 06:14:33.390
I almost expected a rebuff for this hardly well-timed question,

06:14:33.750 --> 06:14:37.750
but on the contrary, waking out of his scowling abstraction,

06:14:37.750 --> 06:14:42.630
he turned his eyes towards me, and the shades seemed to clear off his brow.

06:14:43.490 --> 06:14:46.850
Oh, I had forgotten, Céline. Well, to resume.

06:14:47.190 --> 06:14:50.630
When I saw my charmer thus come in accompanied by a cavalier,

06:14:51.490 --> 06:14:55.570
I seemed to hear a hiss, and the green snake of jealousy,

06:14:55.770 --> 06:14:59.030
rising on undulating coils from the moonlit balcony,

06:14:59.550 --> 06:15:04.710
glided within my waistcoat, and ate its way in two minutes into my heart's core.

06:15:06.090 --> 06:15:06.690
Strange.

06:15:08.010 --> 06:15:11.550
He exclaimed, suddenly starting again from the point.

06:15:12.930 --> 06:15:16.970
Strange that I should choose you for the confidant of all this young lady.

06:15:18.450 --> 06:15:21.130
Passing strange that you should listen to me quietly,

06:15:21.790 --> 06:15:25.990
as if it were the most usual thing in the world for a man like me to tell stories of his

06:15:25.990 --> 06:15:30.310
opera mistresses to a quaint, inexperienced girl like you.

06:15:31.270 --> 06:15:34.570
But the last singularity explains the first.

06:15:34.570 --> 06:15:41.270
As I intimated once before, you, with your gravity, considerateness, and caution,

06:15:41.790 --> 06:15:47.830
were made to be the recipient of secrets. Besides, I know what sort of a mind I have

06:15:47.830 --> 06:15:53.130
placed in communication with my own. I know it is one not liable to take infection.

06:15:53.970 --> 06:15:57.370
It is a peculiar mind. It is a unique one.

06:15:58.670 --> 06:16:04.510
Happily, I do not mean to harm it, but if I did, it would not take harm from me.

06:16:05.210 --> 06:16:11.530
The more you and I converse, the better, for while I cannot blight you, you may refresh me.

06:16:12.810 --> 06:16:15.050
After this digression, he proceeded.

06:16:16.350 --> 06:16:21.530
I remained in the balcony. They will come to her boudoir, no doubt, I thought.

06:16:22.030 --> 06:16:26.530
Let me prepare an ambush. So, putting my hands through the open window,

06:16:26.870 --> 06:16:31.650
I drew the curtain over it, leaving only an opening through which I could take observations.

06:16:31.650 --> 06:16:37.570
Then I closed the casement, all but a chink just wide enough to furnish an outlet to lovers'

06:16:37.910 --> 06:16:43.810
whispered vows. Then I stole back to my chair, and as I resumed it, the pair came in.

06:16:44.470 --> 06:16:48.670
My eye was quickly at the aperture. Celine's chambermaid entered,

06:16:49.090 --> 06:16:55.470
little lamp, left it on the table, and withdrew. The couple were thus revealed to me clearly.

06:16:55.470 --> 06:17:02.330
Both removed their cloaks, and there was the Véran, shining in satin and jewels.

06:17:02.990 --> 06:17:08.190
My gifts, of course. And there was her companion, in an officer's uniform.

06:17:08.870 --> 06:17:15.370
And I knew him for a young rouet of a Vicomte, a brainless and vicious youth whom I had sometimes

06:17:15.370 --> 06:17:20.910
met in society, and had never thought of hating because I despised him so absolutely.

06:17:22.230 --> 06:17:27.050
Unrecognizing him, the fang of the snake of jealousy was instantly broken,

06:17:27.790 --> 06:17:32.110
because at the same moment my love for Celine sank under an extinguisher.

06:17:32.950 --> 06:17:39.550
A woman who could betray me for such a rival was not worth contending for. She deserved only scorn.

06:17:41.450 --> 06:17:44.350
Less, however, than I, who had been her dupe.

06:17:46.430 --> 06:17:50.730
They began to talk. Their conversation eased me completely.

06:17:51.650 --> 06:17:57.530
Frivolous, mercenary, heartless, and senseless. It was rather calculated to weary than enrage

06:17:57.530 --> 06:18:04.170
a listener. A card of mine lay on the table. This being perceived brought my name under discussion.

06:18:05.430 --> 06:18:08.830
Neither of them possessed energy or wit to belabor me soundly,

06:18:09.030 --> 06:18:13.830
but they insulted me as coarsely as they could in their little way, especially Celine,

06:18:14.250 --> 06:18:20.150
who even waxed rather brilliant on my personal defects. Deformities, as she termed them.

06:18:21.670 --> 06:18:26.660
Now it had been her custom to launch out into fervent admiration of what she called my

06:18:27.710 --> 06:18:34.530
beauté mal, wherein she differed diametrically from you, who told me point blank at the second

06:18:34.530 --> 06:18:41.270
interview that you did not think me handsome. The contrast struck me at the time, and

06:18:41.270 --> 06:18:42.940
Adele here came running up again.

06:18:44.680 --> 06:18:52.480
Monsieur, John has just been to say that your agent has called and wishes to see you.

06:18:53.920 --> 06:19:00.220
Ah, in that case I must bridge. Opening the window, I walked in upon them, liberated Celine

06:19:00.220 --> 06:19:05.900
for my protection, gave her notice to vacate her hotel, offered her purse for immediate

06:19:06.440 --> 06:19:12.820
exigencies. Disregarded screams, hysterics, prayers, protestations, convulsions,

06:19:13.360 --> 06:19:17.740
made an appointment with the Vicomte for a meeting at the Bois de Boulogne. Next morning

06:19:17.740 --> 06:19:23.220
I had the pleasure of encountering him, left a bullet in one of his poor etiolated arms,

06:19:23.780 --> 06:19:28.600
feeble as the wing of a chicken in the pip, and then thought I had done with the whole crew.

06:19:29.320 --> 06:19:35.680
But unluckily, the Véran, six months before, had given me this filette Adele,

06:19:35.800 --> 06:19:42.180
who she affirmed was my daughter. And perhaps she may be, though I see no proofs of such

06:19:42.180 --> 06:19:46.980
grim paternity written in her countenance. Pilot is more like me than she.

06:19:48.240 --> 06:19:51.940
Some years after I had broken with the mother, she abandoned her child,

06:19:52.360 --> 06:19:54.980
and ran away to Italy with a musician or singer.

06:19:56.140 --> 06:20:02.360
I acknowledge no natural claim on Adele's part to be supported by me, nor do I now acknowledge

06:20:02.360 --> 06:20:09.180
any, for I am not her father. But hearing that she was quite destitute, I took the poor thing

06:20:09.180 --> 06:20:15.660
out of the slime and mud of Paris and transplanted it here, to grow up clean in the wholesome soil

06:20:15.660 --> 06:20:22.520
of an English country garden. Mrs. Fairfax found you to train it, but now you know that it is the

06:20:22.520 --> 06:20:27.740
illegitimate offspring of a French opera girl, you will perhaps think differently of your post

06:20:27.740 --> 06:20:33.040
and protégé. You will be coming to me some day with notice that you have found another place,

06:20:33.440 --> 06:20:37.960
that you beg me to look out for a new governess, etc. Eh?

06:20:39.260 --> 06:20:46.120
No. Adele is not answerable for either her mother's faults or yours. I have a regard for her,

06:20:46.220 --> 06:20:52.460
and now that I know she is, in a sense, parentless, forsaken by her mother and disowned by you, sir.

06:20:52.520 --> 06:20:58.660
I shall cling closer to her than before. How could I possibly prefer the spoiled pet

06:20:58.660 --> 06:21:02.820
of a wealthy family, who would hate her governess as a nuisance,

06:21:03.160 --> 06:21:06.460
to a lonely little orphan who leans toward her as a friend?

06:21:07.200 --> 06:21:15.360
Oh, that is the light in which you view it. Well, I must go in now, and you too, it darkens.

06:21:16.460 --> 06:21:20.940
But I stayed out a few minutes longer with the Dellen pilot, ran a race with her,

06:21:20.940 --> 06:21:26.420
and played a game of battledore and shuttlecock. When we went in, and I had removed her bonnet and

06:21:26.420 --> 06:21:31.500
coat, I took her on my knee, kept her there an hour, allowing her to prattle as she liked,

06:21:31.920 --> 06:21:37.320
not rebuking even some little freedoms and trivialities into which she was apt to stray

06:21:37.320 --> 06:21:43.840
when much noticed, and which portrayed in her a superficiality of character, inherited probably

06:21:43.840 --> 06:21:51.180
from her mother, hardly congenial to an English mind. Still, she had her merits, and I was

06:21:51.180 --> 06:21:56.920
disposed to appreciate all that was good in her to the utmost. I sought in her countenance and

06:21:56.920 --> 06:22:03.720
features likeness to Mr. Rochester, but found none. No trait, no turn of expression announced

06:22:03.720 --> 06:22:10.400
relationship. It was a pity. If she could but have been proved to resemble him, he would have

06:22:10.400 --> 06:22:16.340
thought more of her. It was not till after I had withdrawn to my own chamber for the night

06:22:16.340 --> 06:22:23.040
that I steadily reviewed the tale Mr. Rochester had told me. As he had said, there was probably

06:22:23.040 --> 06:22:28.580
nothing at all extraordinary in the substance of the narrative itself. A wealthy Englishman's

06:22:28.580 --> 06:22:34.680
passion for a French dancer and her treachery to him were every day matters enough, no doubt,

06:22:34.680 --> 06:22:40.720
in society. But there was something decidedly strange in the paroxysm of emotion which had

06:22:40.720 --> 06:22:45.900
suddenly seized him when he was in the act of expressing the present contentment of his mood,

06:22:46.560 --> 06:22:53.100
and his newly revived pleasure in the old hall and its environs. I meditated wonderingly on this

06:22:53.100 --> 06:22:57.660
incident, but gradually quitting it as I found it for the present inexplicable.

06:22:58.220 --> 06:23:01.980
I turned to the consideration of my master's manner to myself.

06:23:02.740 --> 06:23:09.220
The confidence he thought fit to repose in me seemed a tribute to my discretion. I regarded

06:23:09.220 --> 06:23:16.400
and accepted it as such. His deportment had now for some weeks been more uniform toward me than

06:23:16.400 --> 06:23:23.600
at the first. I never seemed in his way. He did not take fits of chilling hauteur. When he

06:23:23.600 --> 06:23:29.060
met me unexpectedly, the encounter seemed more welcome. He had always a word and sometimes a

06:23:29.060 --> 06:23:35.480
smile for me. When summoned by formal invitation to his presence, I was honored by a cordiality of

06:23:35.480 --> 06:23:41.100
reception that made me feel I really possessed the power to amuse him, and that these evening

06:23:41.100 --> 06:23:47.940
conferences were sought as much for his pleasure as for my benefit. I indeed talked comparatively

06:23:47.940 --> 06:23:54.380
little, but I heard him talk with relish. It was his nature to be communicative. He liked to open

06:23:54.380 --> 06:24:00.840
to a mind unacquainted with the world glimpses of its scenes and ways. I do not mean its corrupt

06:24:00.840 --> 06:24:06.300
scenes in wicked ways, but such as derived their interest from the great scale on which they were

06:24:06.300 --> 06:24:12.420
acted, the strange novelty by which they were characterized. And I had a keen delight in

06:24:12.420 --> 06:24:18.680
receiving the new ideas he offered, in imagining the new pictures he portrayed, and following him

06:24:18.680 --> 06:24:25.300
in thought through the new regions he disclosed, never startled or troubled by one noxious illusion.

06:24:26.780 --> 06:24:32.420
The ease of his manner freed me from painful restraint. The friendly frankness, as correct

06:24:32.420 --> 06:24:38.600
as cordial, with which he treated me, drew me to him. I felt at times as if he were my relation

06:24:38.600 --> 06:24:44.620
rather than my master. Yet he was imperious sometimes still, but I did not mind that.

06:24:45.340 --> 06:24:52.940
I saw it was his way. So happy, so gratified did I become with this new interest added to life,

06:24:53.280 --> 06:24:58.800
that I ceased to pine after kindred. My thin crescent destiny seemed to enlarge.

06:24:59.240 --> 06:25:05.580
The blanks of existence were filled up. My bodily health improved. I gathered flesh and strength.

06:25:07.160 --> 06:25:14.420
And was Mr. Rochester now ugly in my eyes? No, reader. Gratitude, and many associations,

06:25:15.280 --> 06:25:22.340
all pleasurable and genial, made his face the object I best liked to see. His presence in a

06:25:22.340 --> 06:25:28.620
room was more cheering than the brightest fire. Yet I had not forgotten his faults. Indeed,

06:25:28.760 --> 06:25:35.560
I could not, for he brought them frequently before me. He was proud, sardonic, harsh to infuriating,

06:25:35.560 --> 06:25:42.220
of every description. In my secret soul I knew that his great kindness to me was balanced by

06:25:42.220 --> 06:25:50.160
unjust severity to many others. He was moody too, unaccountably so. I more than once, when sent for,

06:25:50.180 --> 06:25:55.900
to read to him, found him sitting in his library alone, with his head bent on his folded arms,

06:25:56.280 --> 06:26:01.620
and when he looked up, a morose, almost a malignant scowl blackened his features.

06:26:02.300 --> 06:26:09.280
But I believed that his moodiness, his harshness, and his former faults in morality—I say former,

06:26:09.280 --> 06:26:14.540
for now he seemed corrected of them—had their source in some cruel cross of fate.

06:26:15.320 --> 06:26:20.980
I believed he was naturally a man of better tendencies, higher principles, and purer tastes

06:26:20.980 --> 06:26:26.520
than such as circumstances had developed, education instilled, or destiny encouraged.

06:26:27.140 --> 06:26:32.160
I thought there were excellent materials in him, though for the present they hung together

06:26:32.160 --> 06:26:36.880
somewhat spoiled and tangled. I cannot deny that I grieved for his grief,

06:26:37.280 --> 06:26:40.920
whatever that was, and would have given much to assuage it.

06:26:43.040 --> 06:26:47.560
Though I had now extinguished my candle and was laid down in bed, I could not sleep for thinking

06:26:47.560 --> 06:26:53.220
of his look when he paused in the avenue, and told how his destiny had risen up before him,

06:26:53.220 --> 06:26:55.900
and dared him to be happy at Thornfield.

06:26:57.260 --> 06:27:04.620
Why not? I asked myself. What alienates him from the house? Will he leave it again soon?

06:27:05.360 --> 06:27:09.440
Mrs. Fairfax said he seldom stayed here longer than a fortnight at a time,

06:27:09.860 --> 06:27:16.560
and he has now been resident eight weeks. If he does go, the change will be doleful.

06:27:17.740 --> 06:27:20.540
Suppose he should be absent spring, summer, and autumn.

06:27:20.540 --> 06:27:23.880
How joyless sunshine and fine days will seem!

06:27:25.320 --> 06:27:31.040
I hardly know whether I had slept or not after this musing. At any rate, I started wide awake

06:27:31.040 --> 06:27:37.020
on hearing a vague murmur, peculiar and lugubrious, which sounded, I thought, just above me.

06:27:37.620 --> 06:27:43.020
I wished I had kept my candle burning. The night was drearily dark. My spirits were depressed.

06:27:44.120 --> 06:27:48.140
I rose and sat up in bed, listening. The sound was hushed.

06:27:48.840 --> 06:27:54.400
I tried again to sleep, but my heart beat anxiously. My inward tranquillity was broken.

06:27:54.860 --> 06:28:00.300
The clock, far down in the hall, struck two. Just then it seemed my chamber door was touched,

06:28:00.720 --> 06:28:05.300
as if fingers had swept the panels and groping away along the dark gallery outside.

06:28:06.000 --> 06:28:11.880
I said, Who is there? Nothing answered. I was chilled with fear.

06:28:12.580 --> 06:28:18.040
All at once I remembered that it might be Pilate, who, when the kitchen door chanced to be left

06:28:18.040 --> 06:28:22.600
open, not unfrequently found his way up to the threshold of Mr. Rochester's chamber.

06:28:23.200 --> 06:28:29.300
I had seen him lying there myself in the mornings. The idea calmed me somewhat. I lay down.

06:28:30.840 --> 06:28:36.580
Silence composes the nerves, and as an unbroken hush now reigned again through the whole house,

06:28:36.580 --> 06:28:42.660
I began to feel the return of slumber. But it was not fated that I should sleep that night.

06:28:43.440 --> 06:28:49.600
A dream had scarcely approached my ear when it fled a-frighted, scared by a marrow-freezing

06:28:49.600 --> 06:28:57.320
incident enough. This was a demonic laugh, low, suppressed, and deep, uttered, as it seemed,

06:28:57.400 --> 06:29:01.900
at the very keyhole of my chamber door. The head of my bed was near the door,

06:29:02.440 --> 06:29:07.820
and I thought at first the goblin laughter stood at my bedside, or rather crouched by my pillow,

06:29:08.460 --> 06:29:14.660
but I rose, looked around, and could see nothing, while as I still gazed the unnatural sound was

06:29:14.660 --> 06:29:21.320
reiterated, and I knew it came from behind the panels. My first impulse was to rise and

06:29:21.320 --> 06:29:27.580
fasten the bolt, my next, again to cry out, Who is there? Something gurgled and moaned.

06:29:28.320 --> 06:29:34.780
Ere long, steps retreated up the gallery toward the third-story staircase. A door had lately

06:29:34.780 --> 06:29:40.540
been made to shut in that staircase. I heard it open and close, and all was still.

06:29:41.520 --> 06:29:48.620
Was that Grace Poole? And is she possessed with a devil? thought I. Impossible now to

06:29:48.620 --> 06:29:54.200
remain longer by myself. I must go to Mrs. Fairfax. I hurried on my frock in a shawl.

06:29:54.200 --> 06:29:59.760
I withdrew the bolt and opened the door with a trembling hand. There was a candle burning

06:29:59.760 --> 06:30:07.440
just outside, and on the matting in the gallery. I was surprised at this circumstance, but still

06:30:07.440 --> 06:30:14.940
more was I amazed to perceive the air quite dim, as if filled with smoke. And while looking to

06:30:14.940 --> 06:30:21.560
the right hand and left, to find once these blue wreaths issued, I became further aware of a strong

06:30:21.560 --> 06:30:29.160
smell of burning. Something creaked. It was a door ajar, and that door was Mr. Rochester's,

06:30:29.340 --> 06:30:35.320
and the smoke rushed in a cloud from thence. I thought no more of Mrs. Fairfax. I thought no

06:30:35.320 --> 06:30:41.180
more of Grace Poole or the laugh. In an instant I was within the chamber. Tongues of flame darted

06:30:41.180 --> 06:30:46.980
round the bed. The curtains were on fire. In the midst of blazing vapor, Mr. Rochester lay

06:30:47.620 --> 06:30:49.200
motionless in deep sleep.

06:30:50.260 --> 06:30:57.980
Wake! Wake! I cried. I shook him, but he only murmured and turned. The smoke had stupefied him.

06:30:58.720 --> 06:31:03.840
Not a moment could be lost. The very sheets were kindling. I rushed to his base in an hour.

06:31:04.380 --> 06:31:08.500
Fortunately, one was wide and the other deep, and both were filled with water.

06:31:09.040 --> 06:31:13.900
I heaved them up, deluged the bed and its occupant, flew back to my own room,

06:31:13.900 --> 06:31:17.000
brought my own water jug, baptized the couch afresh,

06:31:17.300 --> 06:31:21.780
and by God's aid succeeded in extinguishing the flames which were devouring it.

06:31:23.880 --> 06:31:28.860
The hiss of the quenched element, the breakage of a pitcher which I had flung from my hand

06:31:28.860 --> 06:31:34.240
when I had emptied it, and, above all, the splash of the shower-bath I had liberally

06:31:34.240 --> 06:31:40.740
bestowed, roused Mr. Rochester at last. Though it was now dark, I knew he was awake,

06:31:40.740 --> 06:31:46.940
because I heard him fulminating strange anathemas at finding himself lying in a pool of water.

06:31:48.040 --> 06:31:54.980
Is there a flood? he cried. No, sir, I answered. But there has been a fire.

06:31:55.440 --> 06:31:58.960
Get up, do. You are quenched now. I will fetch you a candle.

06:32:00.260 --> 06:32:05.400
In the name of all the elves in Christendom, is that Jane Eyre? he demanded.

06:32:06.440 --> 06:32:11.140
What have you done with me, witch, sorceress? Who is in the room besides you?

06:32:11.380 --> 06:32:15.740
Have you plotted to drown me? I will fetch you a candle, sir.

06:32:15.920 --> 06:32:19.620
And in heaven's name, get up. Somebody has plotted something.

06:32:20.060 --> 06:32:23.000
You cannot too soon find out who and what it is.

06:32:24.260 --> 06:32:27.660
There, I am up now, but at your peril you fetch a candle yet.

06:32:28.140 --> 06:32:32.580
Wait two minutes till I get into some dry garments, if any dry there be.

06:32:33.220 --> 06:32:39.320
Yes, here is my dressing-gown. Now run. I did run. I brought the candle,

06:32:39.340 --> 06:32:43.560
which still remained in the gallery. He took it from my hand, held it up,

06:32:43.660 --> 06:32:46.680
and surveyed the bed. All blackened and scorched.

06:32:47.000 --> 06:32:50.000
The sheets drenched, the carpet round, swimming in water.

06:32:51.080 --> 06:32:57.700
What is it, and who did it? he asked. I briefly related to him what had transpired.

06:32:57.700 --> 06:33:02.800
The strange laugh I had heard in the gallery, the steps ascending to the third story,

06:33:03.200 --> 06:33:09.060
the smoke, the smell of fire which had conducted me to his room, in what state I had found matters

06:33:09.060 --> 06:33:13.480
there, and how I had deluged him with all the water I could lay hands on.

06:33:14.340 --> 06:33:17.980
He listened very gravely. His face, as I went on,

06:33:18.300 --> 06:33:23.640
expressed more concern than astonishment. He did not immediately speak when I had concluded.

06:33:25.840 --> 06:33:33.500
Shall I call Mrs. Fairfax? I asked. Mrs. Fairfax? No. What the deuce would you call her for?

06:33:33.800 --> 06:33:40.720
What can she do? Let her sleep unmolested. Then I will fetch Leah and wake John and his wife.

06:33:41.080 --> 06:33:46.700
Not at all. Just be still. You have a shawl on. If you are not warm enough,

06:33:46.800 --> 06:33:51.380
you may take my cloak yonder. Wrap it about yourself and sit down on the armchair.

06:33:51.960 --> 06:33:58.560
There, I will put it on. Now place your feet on the stool to keep them out of the wet. I am going

06:33:58.560 --> 06:34:04.640
to leave you a few minutes. I shall take the candle. Remain where you are until I return.

06:34:05.340 --> 06:34:12.880
Be as still as a mouse. I must pay a visit to the second story. Don't move, remember, or call anyone.

06:34:15.900 --> 06:34:21.640
He went. I watched the light withdraw. He passed up the gallery very softly,

06:34:22.360 --> 06:34:27.220
unclosed the staircase door with as little noise as possible, shut it after him,

06:34:27.560 --> 06:34:34.500
and the last ray vanished. I was left in total darkness. I listened for some noise but heard

06:34:34.500 --> 06:34:41.300
nothing. A very long time elapsed. I grew weary. It was cold, in spite of the cloak.

06:34:41.860 --> 06:34:46.220
And then I did not see the use of staying, as I was not to rouse the house.

06:34:47.140 --> 06:34:52.400
I was on the point of risking Mr. Rochester's displeasure by disobeying his orders when the

06:34:52.400 --> 06:34:58.060
light once more gleamed dimly on the gallery wall, and I heard his unshod feet tread the matting.

06:34:58.960 --> 06:35:06.420
I hope it is he, thought I, and not something worse. He re-entered, pale and very gloomy.

06:35:07.840 --> 06:35:14.540
I have found it all out, he said, setting his candle down on the washstand. It is as I thought.

06:35:15.980 --> 06:35:22.040
How, sir? He made no reply, but stood with his arms folded, looking on the ground.

06:35:23.280 --> 06:35:26.760
At the end of a few minutes he inquired in a rather peculiar tone.

06:35:27.320 --> 06:35:30.820
I forget whether you said you saw anything when you opened your chamber door.

06:35:31.760 --> 06:35:34.460
No, sir, only the candlestick on the ground.

06:35:35.100 --> 06:35:40.700
But you heard an odd laugh. You have heard that laugh before, I should think, or something like it.

06:35:41.700 --> 06:35:47.820
Yes, sir. There is a woman who sews here, called Grace Poole. She laughs in that way.

06:35:48.360 --> 06:35:49.940
She is a singular person.

06:35:51.200 --> 06:35:57.380
Just so. Grace Poole, you have guessed it. She is, as you say, singular. Very.

06:35:58.120 --> 06:36:03.520
Well, I shall reflect on the subject. Meantime, I am glad that you are the only person,

06:36:03.660 --> 06:36:07.920
beside myself, acquainted with the precise details of tonight's incident.

06:36:08.520 --> 06:36:14.420
You are no talking fool. Say nothing about it. I will account for this state of affairs.

06:36:15.000 --> 06:36:18.920
Pointing to the bed. And now, return to your own room.

06:36:19.360 --> 06:36:23.000
I shall do very well on the sofa in the library for the rest of the night.

06:36:23.280 --> 06:36:26.680
It is near four. In two hours the servants will be up.

06:36:28.280 --> 06:36:31.280
Good night, then, sir, said I, departing.

06:36:31.980 --> 06:36:37.260
He seemed surprised. Very inconsistently so, as he had just told me to go.

06:36:37.880 --> 06:36:42.680
What? he exclaimed. Are you quitting me already, and in that way?

06:36:44.400 --> 06:36:46.540
You said I might go, sir.

06:36:47.040 --> 06:36:52.260
But not without taking leave. Not without a word or two of acknowledgement and goodwill.

06:36:52.680 --> 06:36:55.360
Not, in short, in that brief, dry fashion.

06:36:56.380 --> 06:37:01.820
Why, you have saved my life, snatched me from a horrible and excruciating death,

06:37:02.160 --> 06:37:07.180
and you walk past me as if we were mutual strangers. At least shake hands.

06:37:08.700 --> 06:37:15.200
He held out his hand. I gave him mine. He took it first in one, then in both of his own.

06:37:15.820 --> 06:37:22.880
You have saved my life. I have a pleasure in owing you so immense a debt. I cannot say more.

06:37:24.280 --> 06:37:29.880
Nothing else that has being would have been tolerable to me in the character of creditor

06:37:29.880 --> 06:37:38.180
for such an obligation. But you, it is different. I feel your benefits no burden, Jane.

06:37:40.080 --> 06:37:46.760
He paused, gazed at me. Words almost visible trembled on his lips, but his voice was checked.

06:37:50.000 --> 06:37:55.800
Good night again, sir. There is no debt, benefit, burden, obligation in the case.

06:37:56.780 --> 06:38:04.620
I knew, he continued, you would do me good in some way, at some time. I saw it in your eyes when I

06:38:04.620 --> 06:38:13.940
first beheld you. Their expression and smile did not. Again he stopped. Did not. He proceeded

06:38:13.940 --> 06:38:20.480
hastily, strike delight into my very inmost heart, so for nothing. People talk of natural

06:38:20.480 --> 06:38:26.280
sympathies. I have heard of good, Jeannie. There are grains of truth in the wildest fables,

06:38:26.320 --> 06:38:35.000
my cherished preserver. Good night. Strange energy was in his voice, strange fire in his look.

06:38:36.540 --> 06:38:42.340
I am glad I happened to be awake, I said, and then I was going.

06:38:43.820 --> 06:38:46.060
What? You will go?

06:38:46.840 --> 06:38:48.680
I am cold, sir.

06:38:49.560 --> 06:38:54.620
Cold. Yes, and standing in a pool. Go then, Jane, go.

06:38:55.260 --> 06:39:02.140
But he still retained my hand, and I could not free it. I bethought myself of an expedient.

06:39:02.820 --> 06:39:06.660
I think I hear Mrs. Fairfax move, sir, said I.

06:39:07.980 --> 06:39:12.640
Well, leave me. He relaxed his fingers, and I was gone.

06:39:14.160 --> 06:39:20.140
I regained my couch, but never thought of sleep. Till morning dawned I was tossed on a buoyant but

06:39:20.140 --> 06:39:26.860
unquiet sea, where billows of trouble rolled under surges of joy. I thought sometimes I saw

06:39:26.860 --> 06:39:33.680
beyond its wild waters ashore, sweet as the hills of Beulah, and now and then a freshening gale,

06:39:34.020 --> 06:39:40.640
wakened by hope, bore my spirit triumphantly toward the born. But I could not reach it,

06:39:40.680 --> 06:39:48.220
even in fancy. A counteracting breeze blew off land and continually drove me back. Sense

06:39:48.220 --> 06:39:56.360
would resist delirium, judgment would warn passion. Too feverish to rest, I rose as soon as day dawned.

06:40:12.260 --> 06:40:12.780
XVI.

06:40:13.960 --> 06:40:18.340
I both wished and feared to see Mr. Rochester on the day which followed this sleepless night.

06:40:18.640 --> 06:40:21.940
I wanted to hear his voice again, yet feared to meet his eye.

06:40:22.520 --> 06:40:26.300
During the early part of the morning I momentarily expected his coming.

06:40:26.300 --> 06:40:35.000
He was not in the frequent habit of entering the school-room, but he did step in for a few minutes sometimes, and I had the impression that he was sure to visit it that day.

06:40:35.820 --> 06:40:40.980
But the morning passed just as usual. Nothing happened to interrupt the quiet course of Adèle's studies.

06:40:41.420 --> 06:40:53.220
Only, soon after breakfast, I heard some bustle in the neighbourhood of Mr. Rochester's chamber, Mrs. Fairfax's voice, and Leah's, and the cook's—that is, John's wife—and even John's own gruff tones.

06:40:53.220 --> 06:41:03.540
There were exclamations of what a mercy Master was not burnt in his bed. It is always dangerous to keep a candle lit at night. How providential that he had presence of mind to think of the water-junk!

06:41:03.700 --> 06:41:09.400
I hope he waked nobody. It is to be hoped that he will not take cold with sleeping on the library sofa, etc.

06:41:10.560 --> 06:41:23.980
Too much confabulation succeeded a sound of scrubbing and setting to rights, and when I passed the room, in going downstairs to dinner, I saw through the open door that all was again restored to complete order, only the bed was stripped of its hangings.

06:41:23.980 --> 06:41:42.380
Leah stood up in the window seat, rubbing the panes of glass dimmed with smoke. I was about to address her, for I wished to know what account had been given of the affair, but on advancing, I saw a second person in the chamber, a woman sitting on a chair by the bedside, and sewing rings to new curtains. That woman was no other than Grace Poole.

06:41:42.380 --> 06:42:09.680
There she sat, staid and taciturn, looking as usual, in her brown-stuffed gown, her check apron, white handkerchief, and cap. She was intent on her work, in which her whole thought seemed absorbed, on her hard forehead, and in her commonplace features, was nothing either of the paleness or desperation one would have expected to see marking the countenance of a woman who had attempted murder, and whose intended victim had followed her last night to her lair, and, as I believed, charged her with the crime she wished to perpetrate.

06:42:09.680 --> 06:42:28.180
I was amazed, confounded. She looked up, while I still gazed at her. No start, no increase or failure of colour betrayed emotion, consciousness of guilt, or fear of detection. She said, Good-morning, Miss, in her usual phlegmatic and brief manner, and taking up another ring and more tape, went on with her sewing.

06:42:29.120 --> 06:42:34.240
I will put it to the test, thought I, such absolute impenetrability as past comprehension.

06:42:35.260 --> 06:42:40.700
Good-morning, Grace, I said. Has anything happened here? I thought I heard the servants all talking together a while ago.

06:42:41.780 --> 06:42:53.160
Only Master had been reading in his bed last night. He fell asleep with his candle lit, and the curtains got on fire, but fortunately he awoke before the bed-clothes or the woodwork caught, and contrived to quench the flames with the water in the ewer.

06:42:53.800 --> 06:43:01.540
A strange affair, I said, in a low voice. Then, looking at her fixedly, did Mr. Rochester wake nobody? Did no one hear him move?

06:43:02.440 --> 06:43:14.420
She again raised her eyes to me, and this time there was something of consciousness in their expression. She seemed to examine me warily, then she answered, The servants sleep so far off, you know, Miss, they would not be likely to hear.

06:43:22.840 --> 06:43:30.180
Mrs. Fairfax's room and yours are the nearest to Master's, but Mrs. Fairfax said she heard nothing. When people get elderly, they often sleep heavy.

06:43:30.840 --> 06:43:40.840
She paused, then added, with a sort of assumed indifference, but still in a marked and significant tone. But you are young, Miss, and I should say a light sleeper. Perhaps you may have heard a noise.

06:43:40.840 --> 06:43:53.900
I did, said I, dropping my voice, so that Leah, who was still polishing the paints, could not hear me, and at first I thought it was Pilot. But Pilot cannot laugh, and I am certain I heard a laugh, and a strange one.

06:43:54.700 --> 06:44:07.520
She took a new needle full of thread, waxed it carefully, threaded her needle with a steady hand, and then observed with perfect composure. It is hardly likely Master would laugh, I should think, Miss, when he was in such danger. You must have been dreaming.

06:44:07.520 --> 06:44:17.420
I was not dreaming, I said, with some warmth, for her brazen coolness provoked me. Again she looked at me, and with the same scrutinising and conscious eye.

06:44:17.640 --> 06:44:24.160
Have you told Master that you heard a laugh? she inquired. I have not had the opportunity of speaking with him this morning.

06:44:25.020 --> 06:44:29.480
You did not think of opening your door and looking out into the gallery? she further asked.

06:44:30.100 --> 06:44:44.120
She appeared to be cross-questioning me, attempting to draw from me information unawares. The idea struck me, that if she discovered I knew or suspected her guilt, she would be playing of some of her malignant pranks on me. I thought it advisable to be on my guard.

06:44:44.900 --> 06:44:47.160
On the contrary, said I, I bolted my door.

06:44:47.940 --> 06:44:51.740
Then you are not in the habit of bolting your door every night before you get into bed?

06:44:52.540 --> 06:44:56.100
Fiend! she wants to know my habits, that she may lay her plans accordingly.

06:44:57.080 --> 06:45:14.720
Indignation again prevailed over prudence. I replied sharply. Hitherto I have often omitted to fasten the bolt. I did not think it necessary. I was not aware any danger or annoyance was to be dreaded at Thornfield Hall. But in future—and I laid marked stress on the words—I shall take good care to make all secure before I venture to lie down.

06:45:15.360 --> 06:45:37.200
It would be wise to do so, was her answer. This neighbourhood is as quiet as any I know, and I have never heard of the hall being attempted by robbers since it was a house, though there are hundreds of pounds worth of plate in the plate-closet, as is well known, and you see, for such a large house there are very few servants, because master has never lived here much, and when he does come, being a bachelor, he needs little waiting upon.

06:45:37.720 --> 06:46:01.540
But I always think it is best to err on the safe side. A door is soon fastened, and it is as well to have a drawn bolt between one and any mischief that may be about. A deal of people-miss are for trusting all to providence, but I say, providence will not dispense with the means, though he often blesses them when they are used discreetly. And here she closed her harangue, a long one for her, and uttered with the demureness of a quakeress.

06:46:02.180 --> 06:46:10.580
I still stood, absolutely dumbfounded at what appeared to me her miraculous self-possession, and the most inscrutable hypocrisy, when the cook entered.

06:46:11.160 --> 06:46:17.000
Mrs. Poole, said she, addressing Grace, the servant's dinner will soon be ready. Will you come down?

06:46:17.760 --> 06:46:21.720
No, just put my pint of porter and bitter pudding on a tray, and I'll carry it upstairs.

06:46:22.480 --> 06:46:23.660
You'll have some meat?

06:46:24.260 --> 06:46:26.920
Just a morsel, and a taste of cheese, that's all.

06:46:27.680 --> 06:46:28.380
And the sago?

06:46:29.140 --> 06:46:32.740
Never mind it at present. I shall be coming down before tea-time. I'll make it myself.

06:46:33.540 --> 06:46:38.400
The cook here turned to me, saying that Mrs. Fairfax was waiting for me, so I departed.

06:46:39.140 --> 06:46:57.660
I hardly heard Mrs. Fairfax's account of the curtain conflagration during dinner. So much was I occupied in puzzling my brains over the enigmatic character of Grace Poole, and still more in pondering the problem of her position at Thornfield, and questioning why she had not been given into custody that morning, or at the very least dismissed from her master's service.

06:46:58.240 --> 06:47:07.240
He had almost as much as declared his conviction of her criminality last night. What mysterious cause withheld him from accusing her? Why had he enjoined me, too, to secrecy?

06:47:11.900 --> 06:47:27.620
It was strange. A bold, vindictive, and haughty gentleman seemed somehow in the power of one of the meanest of his dependents, so much in her power, that even when she lifted her hand against his life he dared not openly charge her with the attempt, much less punish her for it.

06:47:28.100 --> 06:47:39.420
Had Grace been young and handsome, I should have been tempted to think that tenderer feelings than prudence or fear influenced Mr. Rochester in her behalf. But hard favoured and matronly as she was, the idea could not be admitted.

06:47:39.900 --> 06:47:56.720
Yet, I reflected, she has been young once. Her youth would be contemporary with her master's. Mrs. Fairfax told me once she had lived here for many years. I don't think she could ever have been pretty, but for aught I know she may possess originality and strength of character to compensate for want of personal advantages.

06:47:57.360 --> 06:48:02.380
Mr. Rochester is an amateur of the decided and eccentric. Grace is eccentric, at least.

06:48:03.120 --> 06:48:17.520
What if a former caprice, a freak very possible to a nature so sudden and headstrong as his, has delivered him into her power, and she now exercises over his actions a secret influence, the result of his own indiscretion, which he cannot shake off and dare not disregard?

06:48:18.120 --> 06:48:45.840
But having reached this point of conjecture, Mrs. Poole's square, flat figure, and uncomely, dry, even coarse face, recurred so distinctly to my mind's eye, that I thought, no, impossible, my supposition cannot be correct. Yet, suggested the secret voice which talks to us in our own hearts, you are not beautiful either, and perhaps Mr. Rochester approves you. At any rate, you have often felt as if he did, and last night, remember his words, remember his look, remember his voice.

06:48:46.380 --> 06:48:58.860
I well remembered all. Language, glance, and tone seemed at the moment vividly renewed. I was now in the schoolroom. Adele was drawing. I bent over her and directed her pencil. She looked up with a sort of start.

06:48:59.420 --> 06:49:01.700
Qu'avez-vous, mademoiselle? said she.

06:49:15.100 --> 06:49:31.020
I am hot, Adele was stooping. She went on sketching. I went on thinking. I hastened to drive from my mind the hateful notion I had been conceiving respecting Grace Poole. It disgusted me. I compared myself with her and found we were different.

06:49:31.620 --> 06:49:45.960
Bessie Leaven had said I was quite a lady, and she spoke truth. I was a lady. And now I looked much better than I did when Bessie saw me. I had more colour and more flesh, more life, more vivacity, because I had brighter hopes and keener enjoyments.

06:49:46.740 --> 06:50:02.520
Evening approaches, said I, as I looked toward the window. I have never heard Mr. Rochester's voice or step in the house to-day, but surely I shall see him before night. I feared the meeting in the morning. Now I desire it, because expectation has been so long baffled that it has grown impatient.

06:50:03.960 --> 06:50:22.740
When dusk actually closed, and when Adele left me to go and play in the nursery with Sophie, I did most keenly desire it. I listened for the bell to ring below. I listened for Leah coming up with a message. I fancied sometimes I heard Mr. Rochester's own tread, and I turned to the door, expecting it to open and envid him.

06:50:23.280 --> 06:50:37.820
The door remained shut. Darkness only came in through the window. Still it was not late. He often sent for me at seven and eight o'clock, and it was yet but six. Surely I should not be wholly disappointed to-night, when I had so many things to say to him.

06:50:38.280 --> 06:50:51.200
I wanted again to introduce the subject of Grace Poole, and to hear what he would answer. I wanted to ask him plainly if he really believed it was she who had made last night's hideous attempt, and if so why he kept her wickedness a secret.

06:50:51.200 --> 06:51:20.400
It little mattered whether my curiosity irritated him. I knew the pleasure of vexing and soothing him by turns. It was one I chiefly delighted in, and a sure instinct always prevented me from going too far. Beyond the verge of provocation, I never ventured. On the extreme brink, I liked well to try my skill. Retaining every minute form of respect, every propriety of my station, I could still meet him in argument without fear or uneasy restraint. This suited both him and me.

06:51:21.460 --> 06:51:37.020
A tread creaked on the stairs at last. Leah made her appearance, but it was only to intimate that tea was ready in Mrs. Fairfax's room. Thither I repaired, glad at least to go downstairs, for that brought me, I imagined, nearer to Mr. Rochester's presence.

06:51:37.640 --> 06:51:50.660
"'You must want your tea,' said the good lady, as I joined her. "'You ate so little at dinner.' I am afraid,' she continued, "'you are not well to-day. You look flushed and feverish.' Oh, quite well! I never felt better.'

06:51:53.300 --> 06:52:10.240
"'Then you must prove it by evincing a good appetite. Will you fill the teapot while I knit off this needle?' Having completed her task, she rose to draw down the blind, which she had hitherto kept up by way, I suppose, of making the most of daylight, though dusk was now fast deepening into total obscurity.

06:52:10.240 --> 06:52:19.180
"'It is fair to-night,' said she, as she looked through the panes, though not starlight, Mr. Rochester has on the whole had a favourable day for his journey.

06:52:20.180 --> 06:52:24.340
"'Journey? Is Mr. Rochester gone any where? I did not know he was out.'

06:52:25.280 --> 06:52:38.540
"'Oh, he set off the moment he had breakfasted. He has gone to Lees, Mr. Eshton's place, ten miles the other side Millcote. I believe there is quite a party assembled there—Lord Ingram, Sir George Lynn, Colonel Dent, and others.'

06:52:38.540 --> 06:52:40.980
"'Do you expect him back to-night?'

06:52:40.980 --> 06:52:55.020
"'No, nor to-morrow either. I should think he is very likely to stay a week or more. When these fine fashionable people get together, they are so surrounded by elegance and gaiety, so well provided with all that can please and entertain, they are in no hurry to separate.

06:52:55.680 --> 06:53:16.820
"'Gentlemen especially are often in request on such occasions, and Mr. Rochester is so talented and so lively in society that I believe he is a general favourite. The ladies are very fond of him, though you would not think his appearance calculated to recommend him particularly in their eyes, but I suppose his acquirements and abilities, perhaps his wealth and good blood, make amends for any little fault of look.

06:53:17.680 --> 06:53:19.900
"'Are there ladies at the Lees?'

06:53:19.900 --> 06:53:33.200
"'There are Mrs. Eshton and her three daughters. Very elegant young ladies indeed. And there are the Honourable Blanche and Mary Ingram, most beautiful women, I suppose. Indeed I have seen Blanche six or seven years since, when she was a girl of eighteen.

06:53:33.200 --> 06:53:49.900
"'She came here to a Christmas ball and party Mr. Rochester gave. You should have seen the dining-room that day, how richly it was decorated, how brilliantly lit up. I should think there were fifty ladies and gentlemen present, all of the First County families, and Miss Ingram was considered the belle of the evening.

06:53:50.560 --> 06:53:54.080
"'You saw her,' you say, Mrs. Fairfax. What was she like?'

06:53:54.080 --> 06:54:17.940
"'Yes, I saw her. The dining-room doors were thrown open, and as it was Christmas time, the servants were allowed to assemble in the hall, to hear some of the ladies sing and play. Mr. Rochester would have me to come in, and I sat down in a quiet corner and watched them. I never saw a more splendid scene. The ladies were magnificently dressed, most of them, at least most of the younger ones, looked handsome, but Miss Ingram was certainly the queen.'

06:54:18.580 --> 06:54:20.480
"'And what was she like?'

06:54:20.480 --> 06:54:46.600
"'Tall, fine bust, sloping shoulders, long graceful neck, olive complexion, dark and clear, noble features, eyes rather like Mr. Rochester's, large and black and as brilliant as her jewels. And then she had such a fine head of hair, raven black and so becomingly arranged, a crown of thick plates behind and in front the longest, glossiest curls I ever saw.

06:54:46.600 --> 06:55:02.600
"'She was dressed in pure white. An amber-coloured scarf was passed over her shoulder and across her breast, tied at the side and descending in long fringed ends below her knee. She wore an amber-coloured flower, too, in her hair. It contrasted well with the jetty mass of her curls.

06:55:03.500 --> 06:55:17.640
"'She was greatly admired, of course. Yes, indeed, and not only for her beauty, but for her accomplishments. She was one of the ladies who sang, a gentleman accompanied her on the piano. She and Mr. Rochester sang a duet.'

06:55:18.280 --> 06:55:25.600
"'Mr. Rochester? I was not aware he could sing. Oh, he has a fine bass voice, and an excellent taste for music.

06:55:26.180 --> 06:55:28.700
"'And Miss Ingram, what sort of a voice had she?'

06:55:29.460 --> 06:55:41.860
"'A very rich and powerful one. She sang delightfully. It was a treat to listen to her, and she played afterwards. I am no judge of music, but Mr. Rochester is, and I heard him say her execution was remarkably good.

06:55:41.860 --> 06:55:46.260
"'And this beautiful and accomplished lady, she is not yet married?'

06:55:46.260 --> 06:55:56.520
"'It appears not. I fancy neither she nor her sister have very large fortunes. Old Lord Ingram's estates were chiefly entailed, and the eldest son came for everything almost.

06:55:56.520 --> 06:56:05.460
"'But I wonder no wealthy nobleman or gentleman has taken a fancy to her. Mr. Rochester, for instance. He is rich. Is he not?'

06:56:05.460 --> 06:56:13.500
"'Oh, yes. But you see there is a considerable difference in age. Mr. Rochester is nearly forty. She is but twenty-five.'

06:56:13.500 --> 06:56:17.380
"'What of that? More unequal matches are made every day.'

06:56:17.940 --> 06:56:26.520
"'True. Yet I should scarcely fancy Mr. Rochester would entertain any idea of the sort. But you eat nothing. You have scarcely tasted since you began tea.'

06:56:26.520 --> 06:56:30.180
"'No, I am too thirsty to eat. Will you let me have another cup?'

06:56:30.180 --> 06:56:40.080
"'I was about to revert again to the probability of a union between Mr. Rochester and the beautiful Blanche, but Adele came in, and the conversation was turned into another channel.

06:56:40.860 --> 06:56:55.340
"'When once more alone, I reviewed the information I had got, looked into my heart, examined its thoughts and feelings, and endeavoured to bring back with a strict hand such as had been straying through imagination's boundless and trackless waste into the safefold of common sense.

06:56:55.960 --> 06:57:11.600
"'Arraigned at my own bar, memory having given her evidence of the hopes, wishes, sentiments I had been cherishing since last night, of the general state of mind in which I had indulged for nearly a fortnight past, reason having come forward and told, in her own quiet way, a plain unvarnished tale,

06:57:11.600 --> 06:57:27.840
"'showing how I had rejected the real and rabidly devoured the ideal, I pronounced judgment to this effect, that a greater fool than Jane Eyre had never breathed the breath of life, that a more fantastic idiot had never surfeited herself on sweet lies and swallowed poison as if it were nectar.

06:57:28.700 --> 06:57:36.220
"'You,' I said, a favourite with Mr. Rochester, you gifted with the power of pleasing him, you of importance to him in any way.

06:57:36.580 --> 06:57:46.920
"'Go, your folly sickens me, and you have derived pleasure from occasional tokens of preference, equivocal tokens, shown by a gentleman of family and a man of the world to a dependent and a novice.

06:57:46.920 --> 06:57:59.760
"'How dared you, poor stupid dupe! Could not even self-interest make you wiser? You repeated to yourself this morning the brief scene of last night. Cover your face and be ashamed. He said something in praise of your eyes, did he?

06:58:06.080 --> 06:58:29.740
"'Blind puppy, open their bleared lids and look on your own accursed senselessness. It does good to no woman to be flattered by her superior who cannot possibly intend to marry her, and it is madness in all women to let a secret love kindle within them which, if unreturned and unknown, must devour the life that feeds it, and if discovered and responded to, must lead, ignis facius-like, into miry wilds whence there is no end to it.

06:58:30.820 --> 06:58:48.740
"'Listen, then, Jane Eyre, to your sentence. Tomorrow, place the glass before you and draw in chalk your own picture, faithfully, without softening one defect. Amid no harsh line, smooth away no displeasing irregularity. Right under it, portrait of a governess, disconnected, poor, and plain.

06:58:49.900 --> 06:59:10.060
"'Afterwards, take a piece of smooth ivory. You have one prepared in your drawing-box. Take your palette, mix your freshest, finest, clearest tints, choose your most delicate camel-hair pencils, delineate carefully the loveliest face you can imagine, paint it in your softest shades and sweetest lines, according to the description given by Mrs Fairfax of Blanchingram.

06:59:10.060 --> 06:59:25.580
"'Remember the raven ringlets, the oriental eye. What, you revert to Mr Rochester as a model. Order, no snivel, no sentiment, no regret. I will endure only sense and resolution. Recall the august yet harmonious lineaments, the Grecian neck and bust.

06:59:25.580 --> 06:59:41.140
"'Let the round and dazzling arm be visible, and the delicate hand. Amid neither diamond ring nor gold bracelet. Portray faithfully the attire, aerial lace and glistening satin, graceful scarf and golden rose. Call it Blanche, unaccomplished lady of rank.

06:59:42.100 --> 06:59:59.360
"'Whenever in future you should chance to fancy Mr Rochester thinks well of you, take out these two pictures and compare them. Say, Mr Rochester might probably win that noble lady's love, if he chose to strive for it. Is it likely he would waste a serious thought on this indigent and insignificant plebeian?

06:59:59.360 --> 07:00:06.460
"'I'll do it,' I resolved. And having framed this determination, I grew calm and fell asleep.

07:00:07.180 --> 07:00:25.800
"'I kept my word. An hour or two sufficed to sketch my own portrait in crayons, and in less than a fortnight I had completed an ivory miniature of an imaginary Blanche Ingram. It looked like a lovely face enough, and when compared with the real head in chalk, the contrast was as great as self-control could desire.

07:00:25.800 --> 07:00:35.340
"'I derived benefit from the task. It had kept my head and hands employed, and had given force and fixedness to the new impressions I wished to stamp indelibly on my heart.

07:00:36.080 --> 07:00:53.380
"'Ere long, I had reason to congratulate myself on the course of wholesome discipline to which I had thus forced my feelings to submit. Thanks to it, I was able to meet subsequent occurrences with a decent calm, which had they found me unprepared, I should probably have been unequal to maintain, even externally.'

07:01:12.340 --> 07:01:12.840
XVII.

07:01:13.160 --> 07:01:18.900
A week passed, and no news arrived of Mr. Rochester. Ten days, and still he did not

07:01:18.900 --> 07:01:24.280
come. Mrs. Fairfax said she should not be surprised if he were to go straight from the

07:01:24.280 --> 07:01:29.200
East to London, and thence to the Continent, and not show his face again at Thornfield

07:01:29.200 --> 07:01:34.260
for a year to come. He had not infrequently quitted it in a manner quite as abrupt and

07:01:34.260 --> 07:01:40.000
unexpected. When I heard this, I was beginning to feel a strange chill and failing at the

07:01:40.000 --> 07:01:45.320
heart. I was actually permitting myself to experience a sickening sense of disappointment,

07:01:45.820 --> 07:01:50.960
but rallying my wits, and recollecting my principles, I at once called my sensations

07:01:50.960 --> 07:01:55.820
to order. And it was wonderful how I got over the temporary blunder, how I cleared

07:01:55.820 --> 07:02:00.820
up the mistake of supposing Mr. Rochester's movements, a matter in which I had any cause

07:02:00.820 --> 07:02:06.100
to take a vital interest. Not that I humbled myself by a slavish notion of inferiority.

07:02:06.440 --> 07:02:12.200
On the contrary, I just said, You have nothing to do with the master of Thornfield, further

07:02:12.200 --> 07:02:16.620
than to receive the salary he gives you for teaching his protégé, and to be grateful

07:02:16.620 --> 07:02:23.580
and kind treatment, as, if you do your duty, you have a right to expect at his hands. Be

07:02:23.580 --> 07:02:29.080
sure that is the only tie he seriously acknowledges between you and him, so don't make him the

07:02:29.080 --> 07:02:34.240
object of your fine feelings, your raptures, agonies, and so forth. He is not of your order.

07:02:34.620 --> 07:02:39.860
Keep to your caste, and be too self-respecting to lavish the love of the whole heart, soul,

07:02:39.900 --> 07:02:44.120
and strength where such a gift is not wanted, and would be despised.

07:02:44.880 --> 07:02:50.800
I went on with my day's business tranquilly, but ever and anon vague suggestions kept wandering

07:02:50.800 --> 07:02:57.080
across my brain of reasons why I should quit Thornfield, and I kept involuntarily framing

07:02:57.080 --> 07:03:02.380
advertisements and pondering conjectures about new situations. These thoughts I did not think

07:03:02.380 --> 07:03:05.320
to check. They might germinate and bear fruit if they could.

07:03:06.500 --> 07:03:10.980
Mr. Rochester had been absent upwards of a fortnight when the Post brought Mrs. Fairfax

07:03:10.980 --> 07:03:11.360
a letter.

07:03:12.000 --> 07:03:16.780
"'It is from the Master,' said she, as she looked at the direction. Now I suppose we

07:03:16.780 --> 07:03:21.660
shall know whether we are to expect his return or not.' And while she broke the seal and

07:03:21.660 --> 07:03:27.060
perused the document, I went on taking my coffee. We were at breakfast. It was hot,

07:03:27.360 --> 07:03:33.120
and I attributed to that circumstance a fiery glow which suddenly rose to my face. Why my

07:03:33.120 --> 07:03:38.520
hand shook, and why I involuntarily spilt half the contents of my cup into my saucer,

07:03:38.520 --> 07:03:40.160
I did not choose to consider.'

07:03:40.860 --> 07:03:45.760
"'Well, I sometimes think we are too quiet. But we run a chance of being busy enough now,

07:03:46.000 --> 07:03:51.100
for a little while at least,' said Mrs. Fairfax, still holding the note before her spectacles.

07:03:51.820 --> 07:03:57.360
"'Ere I permitted myself to request an explanation, I tied the string of Adele's pinafore, which

07:03:57.360 --> 07:04:02.100
happened to be loose. Having helped her also to another bun, and refilled her mug with

07:04:02.480 --> 07:04:03.960
I said nonchalantly,

07:04:04.460 --> 07:04:08.360
"'Mr. Rochester is not likely to return soon, I suppose.'

07:04:08.360 --> 07:04:14.000
"'Indeed he is. In three days, he says. That will be next Thursday, and not alone either.

07:04:14.260 --> 07:04:19.140
I don't know how many of the fine people at the Lees are coming with him. He sends directions

07:04:19.140 --> 07:04:23.800
for all the best bedrooms to be prepared, and the library and drawing-rooms are to be

07:04:23.800 --> 07:04:28.720
cleaned out. I am to get more kitchen-hands from the George Inn at Milkoat, and from wherever

07:04:28.720 --> 07:04:33.060
else I can. And the ladies will bring their maids, and the gentlemen their valets. So

07:04:33.060 --> 07:04:34.840
we shall have a full house of it.'

07:04:34.840 --> 07:04:39.180
And Mrs. Fairfax swallowed her breakfast, and hastened away to commence operations.

07:04:39.800 --> 07:04:44.920
The three days were, as she had foretold, busy enough. I had thought all the rooms at

07:04:44.920 --> 07:04:50.360
Thornfield beautifully clean and well arranged, but it appears I was mistaken. Three women

07:04:50.360 --> 07:04:55.680
were got to help, and such scrubbing, such brushing, such washing of paint and beating

07:04:55.680 --> 07:05:00.560
of carpets, such taking down and putting up of pictures, such polishing of mirrors

07:05:00.560 --> 07:05:05.920
and lusters, such lighting of fires in bedrooms, such airing of sheets and feather beds on

07:05:05.920 --> 07:05:11.540
hearths, I never beheld either before or since. Adèle ran quite wild in the midst of it.

07:05:11.840 --> 07:05:16.280
The preparations for company and the prospect of their arrival seemed to throw her into

07:05:16.280 --> 07:05:21.900
ecstasies. She would have Sophie to look over all her toilettes, as she called frocks, to

07:05:21.900 --> 07:05:28.380
any that were passé, and to air and arrange the new. For herself, she did nothing but

07:05:28.380 --> 07:05:33.840
caper about in the front chambers, jump on and off of the bedsteads, and lie on the mattresses

07:05:33.840 --> 07:05:38.940
and piled up bolsters and pillows before the enormous fires roaring in the chimneys. From

07:05:38.940 --> 07:05:44.580
school duties she was exonerated. Mrs. Fairfax had pressed me into her service, and I was

07:05:44.580 --> 07:05:49.720
all day in the storeroom, helping or hindering her and the cook, learning to make custards

07:05:49.720 --> 07:05:54.060
and cheesecakes and French pastry, to truss game and garnish dessert dishes.

07:05:54.640 --> 07:06:00.200
The party were expected to arrive on Thursday afternoon, in time for dinner at six. During

07:06:00.200 --> 07:06:05.780
the intervening period I had no time to nurse chimeras, and I believe I was as active and

07:06:05.780 --> 07:06:11.660
gay as anybody Adèle accepted. Still, now and then I received a damping check to my

07:06:11.660 --> 07:06:16.640
cheerfulness, and was in spite of myself thrown back on the region of doubts and portents

07:06:16.640 --> 07:06:22.520
and dark conjectures. This was when I chanced to see the third-storey staircase door, which

07:06:22.520 --> 07:06:28.240
of late had always been kept locked, open slowly and give passage to the form of Grace

07:06:28.240 --> 07:06:34.000
Poole in prim cap, white apron, and handkerchief, when I watched her glide along the gallery,

07:06:34.260 --> 07:06:39.680
her quiet tread muffled in a list slipper, when I saw her look into the bustling, topsy-turvy

07:06:39.680 --> 07:06:44.360
bedrooms, just to say a word, perhaps, to the charwoman about the proper way to polish

07:06:44.360 --> 07:06:49.920
a grate, or clean a marble mantelpiece, or take stains from papered walls, and then pass

07:06:49.920 --> 07:06:55.340
on. She would thus descend to the kitchen once a day, eat her dinner, smoke a moderate

07:06:55.340 --> 07:07:00.200
pipe on the hearth, and go back, carrying her pot of porter with her, for her private

07:07:00.200 --> 07:07:05.940
solace in her own gloomy upper haunt. Only one hour in all the twenty-four did she pass

07:07:05.940 --> 07:07:10.960
with her fellow servants below. All the rest of her time was spent in some low-sealed oaken

07:07:10.960 --> 07:07:17.380
of the second storey. There she sat, and sewed, and probably laughed drearily to herself,

07:07:17.840 --> 07:07:23.680
as companionless as a prisoner in his dungeon. The strangest thing of all was that not a

07:07:23.680 --> 07:07:29.060
soul in the house except me noticed her habits, or seemed to marvel at them. No one discussed

07:07:29.060 --> 07:07:34.440
her position or her employment. No one pitied her solitude or isolation. I once, indeed,

07:07:34.600 --> 07:07:38.960
overheard part of a dialogue between Leah and one of the charwomen of which Grace formed

07:07:38.960 --> 07:07:44.060
the subject. Leah had been saying something I had not caught, and the charwomen remarked,

07:07:44.260 --> 07:07:46.260
"'She gets good wages, I guess.'

07:07:46.260 --> 07:07:50.780
"'Yes,' said Leah. "'I wish I had as good. Not that mine are to complain of. There's

07:07:50.780 --> 07:07:55.240
no stinginess at Thornfield, but they are not one fifth of the sum Mrs. Poole receives.

07:07:55.600 --> 07:08:00.460
And she is laying by. She goes every quarter to the bank at Millcote. I should not wonder,

07:08:00.580 --> 07:08:05.060
but she has saved enough to keep her independent if she liked to leave. But I suppose she's

07:08:05.060 --> 07:08:09.940
got used to the place, and then she's not forty yet, and strong and able for anything.

07:08:10.380 --> 07:08:12.840
It is too soon for her to give up business.'

07:08:12.840 --> 07:08:15.840
"'She is a good hand, I dare say,' said the charwoman.

07:08:16.460 --> 07:08:21.620
"'Ah, she understands what she has to do. Nobody better,' rejoined Leah significantly.

07:08:22.360 --> 07:08:27.220
"'And it is not every one could fill her shoes. Not for all the money she gets.'

07:08:27.220 --> 07:08:31.380
"'That it is not,' was the reply. I wonder whether the master—'

07:08:31.380 --> 07:08:36.100
The charwoman was going on, but here Leah turned and perceived me, and she instantly

07:08:36.100 --> 07:08:37.580
gave her companion a nudge.

07:08:38.320 --> 07:08:43.560
"'Doesn't she know?' I heard the woman whisper. Leah shook her head, and the conversation

07:08:43.560 --> 07:08:48.460
was of course dropped. All I had gathered from it amounted to this—that there was

07:08:48.460 --> 07:08:53.480
a mystery at Thornfield, and that from participation in that mystery I was purposely excluded.

07:08:54.640 --> 07:08:59.720
Thursday came. All work had been completed the previous evening. Carpets were laid down,

07:08:59.720 --> 07:09:05.440
bed-hangings festooned, radiant white counter-panes spread, toilet-tables arranged, furniture

07:09:05.440 --> 07:09:10.920
rubbed, flowers piled in vases. Both chambers and saloons looked as fresh and bright as

07:09:10.920 --> 07:09:15.480
hands could make them. The hall, too, was scoured, and the great carved clock, as well

07:09:15.480 --> 07:09:19.900
as the steps and banisters of the staircase, were polished to the brightness of glass.

07:09:20.260 --> 07:09:25.540
In the dining-room the sideboard flashed resplendent with plate. In the drawing-room and boudoir

07:09:25.540 --> 07:09:28.360
vases of exotics bloomed on all sides.

07:09:29.440 --> 07:09:35.160
Afternoon arrived. Mrs. Fairfax assumed her best black satin gown, her gloves, and her

07:09:35.160 --> 07:09:39.600
gold watch, for it was her part to receive the company, to conduct the ladies to their

07:09:39.600 --> 07:09:44.540
rooms, etc. Adèle, too, would be dressed, though I thought she had little chance of

07:09:44.540 --> 07:09:49.400
being introduced to the party, that day at least. However, to please her, I allowed Sophie

07:09:49.400 --> 07:09:54.940
to apparel her in one of her short full muslin frocks. For myself I had no need to make any

07:09:54.940 --> 07:10:00.200
I should not be called upon to quit my sanctum of the school-rooms, for a sanctum it was

07:10:00.200 --> 07:10:03.500
now become to me, a very pleasant refuge in time of trouble.

07:10:04.300 --> 07:10:09.360
It had been a mild, serene spring day, one of those days which, toward the end of March

07:10:09.360 --> 07:10:14.320
or the beginning of April, rise shining over the earth as heralds of summer. It was drawing

07:10:14.320 --> 07:10:19.020
to an end now, but the evening was even warm, and I sat at work in the school-room with

07:10:19.020 --> 07:10:19.840
the window open.

07:10:19.840 --> 07:10:25.920
It gets late, said Mrs. Fairfax, entering in rustling state. I am glad I ordered dinner

07:10:25.920 --> 07:10:31.860
an hour after the time Mr. Rochester mentioned, for it is past six now. I have sent John down

07:10:31.860 --> 07:10:36.340
to the gates to see if there is anything on the road. One can see a long way from thence

07:10:36.340 --> 07:10:37.520
in the direction of Millcote.

07:10:38.200 --> 07:10:39.240
She went to the window.

07:10:39.580 --> 07:10:43.280
Here he is, said she. Well, John, leaning out, any news?

07:10:43.800 --> 07:10:47.080
Their coming man was the answer. They'll be here in ten minutes.

07:10:47.760 --> 07:10:53.620
Adèle flew to the window. I followed, taking care to stand on one side, so that, screened

07:10:53.620 --> 07:10:56.460
by the curtain, I could see without being seen.

07:10:57.400 --> 07:11:02.440
The ten minutes John had given seemed very long, but at last wheels were heard. Four

07:11:02.440 --> 07:11:08.240
equestrians galloped up the drive, and after them came two open carriages. Fluttering veils

07:11:08.240 --> 07:11:13.380
and waving plumes filled the vehicles. Two of the cavaliers were young, dashing-looking

07:11:13.380 --> 07:11:19.800
The third was Mr. Rochester, on his black horse, Miss Ruhr, pilot bounding before him.

07:11:20.060 --> 07:11:25.080
At his side rode a lady, and he and she were the first of the party. Her purple riding

07:11:25.080 --> 07:11:30.140
habit almost swept the ground, her veil streamed long on the breeze, mingling with its transparent

07:11:30.140 --> 07:11:33.620
folds and gleaming through them, shone rich raven ringlets.

07:11:34.340 --> 07:11:39.620
Miss Ingram, exclaimed Mrs. Fairfax, and away she hurried to her post below.

07:11:40.520 --> 07:11:45.140
The cavalcade, following the sweep of the drive, quickly turned the angle of the house,

07:11:45.280 --> 07:11:50.180
and I lost sight of it. Adèle now petitioned to go down, but I took her on my knee and

07:11:50.180 --> 07:11:54.580
gave her to understand that she must not on any account think of venturing in sight of

07:11:54.580 --> 07:12:00.340
the ladies, either now or at any other time, unless expressly sent for, that Mr. Rochester

07:12:00.340 --> 07:12:06.540
would be very angry, etc. Some natural tears she shed on being told this, but as I began

07:12:06.540 --> 07:12:09.260
to look very grave, she consented at last to wipe them.

07:12:10.120 --> 07:12:15.380
A joyous stir was now audible in the hall. Gentleman's deep tones and ladies' silvery

07:12:15.380 --> 07:12:21.760
accents blend harmoniously together, and distinguishable above all, though not loud, was the sonorous

07:12:21.760 --> 07:12:27.000
voice of the master of Thornfield Hall, welcoming his fair and gallant guests under its roof.

07:12:27.600 --> 07:12:32.140
Then light steps ascended the stairs, and there was a tripping through the gallery,

07:12:32.140 --> 07:12:37.180
and soft cheerful laughs, and opening and closing doors, and for a time a hush.

07:12:38.260 --> 07:12:43.100
Elle est changeante de toilettes, said Adèle, who listening attentively had followed every

07:12:43.100 --> 07:12:45.180
movement, and she sighed.

07:12:45.400 --> 07:12:50.900
Chez maman, said she, quand il y avait du monde, je l'a sauvée partout, au salon et

07:12:50.900 --> 07:12:57.020
de la loose chambreuse. Souvent je regardais les femmes de chambre coffrées et habillées

07:12:57.020 --> 07:13:02.000
les dames, et c'était si amusant, comme celle-là on apprende.

07:13:02.000 --> 07:13:06.960
Don't you feel hungry, Adèle? Mais oui, mademoiselle, voire cinq ou six

07:13:06.960 --> 07:13:10.200
yeux, qu'en nous n'avons pas mange.

07:13:11.160 --> 07:13:15.460
Well now, while the ladies are in their rooms, I will venture down and get you something

07:13:15.460 --> 07:13:21.760
to eat. And issuing from my asylum, with precaution, I sought a back-stairs which conducted directly

07:13:21.760 --> 07:13:27.100
to the kitchen. All in that region was fire and commotion. The soup and fish were in

07:13:27.100 --> 07:13:31.960
the last stage of projection, and the cook hung over her crucibles in a frame of mind

07:13:31.960 --> 07:13:37.060
and body threatening spontaneous combustion. In the servants' hall, two coachmen and

07:13:37.060 --> 07:13:41.800
three gentleman's gentlemen stood or sat around the fire. The Abigail's, I suppose,

07:13:41.860 --> 07:13:46.280
were upstairs with their mistresses. The new servants, that had been hired from Milcote,

07:13:46.560 --> 07:13:47.920
were bustling about everywhere.

07:13:48.880 --> 07:13:53.980
Threading this chaos, I at last reached the larder. There I took possession of a cold

07:13:53.980 --> 07:13:59.480
chicken, a roll of bread, some tarts, a plate or two, and a knife and fork. With this booty

07:13:59.480 --> 07:14:04.580
I made a hasty retreat. I had regained the gallery, and was just shutting the back door

07:14:04.580 --> 07:14:09.020
behind me, when an accelerated hum warned me that the ladies were about to issue from

07:14:09.020 --> 07:14:13.740
their chambers. I could not proceed to the schoolroom without passing some of their doors,

07:14:13.740 --> 07:14:18.820
and running the risk of being surprised with my cargo of victualage, so I stood still at

07:14:18.820 --> 07:14:24.340
the end, which, being windowless, was dark, quite dark now, for the sun was set and twilight

07:14:24.340 --> 07:14:29.540
gathering. Presently the chambers gave up their fair tenants one after another. Each

07:14:29.540 --> 07:14:34.940
came out gaily and airily, with dress that gleamed lustrous through the dark. For a moment

07:14:34.940 --> 07:14:40.000
they stood grouped together at the other extremity of the gallery, conversing in a key of sweet

07:14:40.000 --> 07:14:45.280
subdued vivacity. They then descended down the staircase almost as noiselessly as a bright

07:14:45.280 --> 07:14:50.260
mist rolls down a hill. Their collective appearance had left on me an impression of high-born

07:14:50.260 --> 07:14:55.920
elegance, such as I had never before received. I found Adele peeping through the schoolroom

07:14:55.920 --> 07:14:57.360
door, which she held ajar.

07:14:57.740 --> 07:15:02.860
"'What beautiful ladies!' cried she in English. "'Oh, I wish I might go to them. Do you think

07:15:02.860 --> 07:15:06.160
Mr. Rochester will send for us by-and-by, after dinner?'

07:15:06.160 --> 07:15:10.980
"'No, indeed I don't. Mr. Rochester has something else to think about. Never mind

07:15:10.980 --> 07:15:15.240
the ladies to-night. Perhaps you will see them to-morrow. Here is your dinner.' She

07:15:15.240 --> 07:15:19.680
was really hungry, so the chicken and tarts served to divert her attention for a time.

07:15:20.080 --> 07:15:25.280
It was well I secured this forage, or both she, I, and Sophie, to whom I conveyed a share

07:15:25.280 --> 07:15:29.960
of our past, would have run a chance of getting no dinner at all. Every one downstairs was

07:15:29.960 --> 07:15:31.820
too much engaged to think of us.

07:15:32.540 --> 07:15:37.640
The dessert was not carried out until after nine, and at ten footmen were still running

07:15:37.640 --> 07:15:43.340
to-and-fro with trays and coffee-cups. I allowed Adele to sit up much later than usual, for

07:15:43.340 --> 07:15:47.720
she declared she could not possibly go to sleep while the doors kept opening and shutting

07:15:47.720 --> 07:15:53.600
below, and people bustling about. Besides, she added, a message might possibly come from

07:15:53.600 --> 07:15:57.840
Mr. Rochester when she was undressed. Et alors quel dommage!

07:15:58.460 --> 07:16:03.660
I told her stories as long as she would listen to them, and then for a change I took her

07:16:03.660 --> 07:16:09.300
out into the gallery. The hall lamp was now lit, and it amused her to look over the balustrade

07:16:09.300 --> 07:16:14.200
and watch the servants passing backwards and forwards. When the evening was far advanced,

07:16:14.560 --> 07:16:19.460
a sound of music issued from the drawing-room, whither the piano had been removed, Adele

07:16:19.460 --> 07:16:25.120
and I sat down on the top step of the stairs to listen. Presently a voice blent with the

07:16:25.120 --> 07:16:30.900
rich tones of the instrument. It was a lady who sang, and sweet her notes were. The solo

07:16:30.900 --> 07:16:36.340
over, a duet followed, and then a glee, a joyous conversational murmur filled up the

07:16:36.340 --> 07:16:42.940
intervals. I listened long. Suddenly I discovered that my ear was wholly intent on analyzing

07:16:42.940 --> 07:16:48.060
the mingled sounds, and trying to discriminate amidst the confusion of accents those of

07:16:48.060 --> 07:16:54.040
Mr. Rochester. And when it caught them, which it soon did, it found a further task in framing

07:16:54.040 --> 07:16:57.600
the tones rendered by distance inarticulate into words.

07:16:58.460 --> 07:17:03.600
The clock struck eleven. I looked at Adele, whose head leant against my shoulder. Her

07:17:03.600 --> 07:17:09.120
eyes were waxing heavy, so I took her up in my arms and carried her off to bed. It was

07:17:09.120 --> 07:17:11.860
near one before the gentlemen and ladies sought their chambers.

07:17:13.060 --> 07:17:18.020
The next day was as fine as its predecessor. It was devoted by the party to an excursion

07:17:18.020 --> 07:17:22.740
to some site in the neighborhood. They set out early in the forenoon, some on horseback,

07:17:22.740 --> 07:17:28.060
the rest in carriages. I witnessed both the departure and the return. Miss Ingram, as

07:17:28.060 --> 07:17:33.500
before, was the only lady equestrian, and as before, Mr. Rochester galloped at her side.

07:17:33.920 --> 07:17:39.460
The two rode a little apart from the rest. I pointed out this circumstance to Mrs. Fairfax,

07:17:39.620 --> 07:17:41.560
who was standing at the window with me.

07:17:41.980 --> 07:17:45.880
"'You said it was not likely they should think of being married,' said I. But you

07:17:45.880 --> 07:17:50.240
see Mr. Rochester evidently prefers her to any of the other ladies.'

07:17:50.240 --> 07:17:52.740
"'Yes,' I dare say. No doubt he admires her.'

07:17:53.520 --> 07:17:58.420
"'And she him?' I added. Look how she leans her head towards him, as if she were conversing

07:17:58.420 --> 07:18:03.920
confidentially. I wish I could see her face. I have never had a glimpse of it yet.'

07:18:03.920 --> 07:18:08.500
"'You will see her this evening,' answered Mrs. Fairfax. I happened to remark to Mr.

07:18:08.720 --> 07:18:13.540
Rochester how much Adele wished to be introduced to the ladies, and he said, "'Oh, let her

07:18:13.540 --> 07:18:17.380
come into the drawing-room after dinner, and request Miss Eyre to accompany her.'

07:18:18.420 --> 07:18:22.940
"'Yes, he said that from mere politeness. I need not go, I am sure,' I answered.

07:18:23.740 --> 07:18:28.180
"'Well, I observed to him that as you were unused to company, I did not think you would

07:18:28.180 --> 07:18:33.100
like appearing before so gay a party, all strangers, and he replied in his quick way,

07:18:33.280 --> 07:18:38.380
"'Nonsense! If she objects, tell her it is my particular wish, and if she resists, say

07:18:38.380 --> 07:18:41.040
I shall come and fetch her in case of contumency.'

07:18:41.040 --> 07:18:46.380
"'I will not give him that trouble,' I answered. I will go, if no better may be. But I don't

07:18:46.380 --> 07:18:49.080
like it. Shall you be there, Mrs. Fairfax?'

07:18:49.080 --> 07:18:54.140
"'No, I played it off, and he admitted my plea. I'll tell you how to manage, so as

07:18:54.140 --> 07:18:58.740
to avoid the embarrassment of making a formal entrance, which is the most disagreeable part

07:18:58.740 --> 07:19:03.780
of the business. You must go into the drawing-room while it is empty, before the ladies leave

07:19:03.780 --> 07:19:08.480
the dinner-table. Choose your seat in any quiet nook you like. You need not stay long

07:19:08.480 --> 07:19:13.640
after the gentlemen come in, unless you please. Just let Mr. Rochester see you are there,

07:19:13.640 --> 07:19:19.060
and then slip away. No one will notice you. Will these people remain long, do you think?

07:19:19.780 --> 07:19:25.200
Perhaps two or three weeks. Certainly not more. After the Easter recess, Sir George

07:19:25.200 --> 07:19:29.900
Lynn, who was lately elected Member for Millcote, will have to go up to town and take his seat.

07:19:30.440 --> 07:19:35.880
I dare say Mr. Rochester will accompany him. It surprises me that he has already made so

07:19:35.880 --> 07:19:41.660
protracted a stay at Thornfield. It was with some trepidation that I perceived the hour

07:19:41.660 --> 07:19:47.000
when I was to repair with my charge to the drawing-room. Adèle had been in a state of

07:19:47.000 --> 07:19:51.640
ecstasy all day, after hearing she was to be presented to the ladies in the evening,

07:19:51.900 --> 07:19:57.200
and it was not till Sophie commenced the operation of dressing her that she sobered down. Then

07:19:57.200 --> 07:20:01.760
the importance of the process quickly steadied her, and by the time she had her curls arranged

07:20:01.760 --> 07:20:07.460
in well-smoothed drooping clusters, her pink satin frock put on, her long sash tied, and

07:20:07.460 --> 07:20:13.580
her lace mittens adjusted, she looked as grave as any judge. No need to warn her not to disarrange

07:20:13.580 --> 07:20:18.440
her attire. When she was dressed, she sat demurely down in her little chair, taking

07:20:18.440 --> 07:20:23.240
care previously to lift up the satin skirt, for fear she should crease it, and assured

07:20:23.240 --> 07:20:30.060
me she would not stir thence till I was ready. This I quickly was. My best dress, the silver-grey

07:20:30.060 --> 07:20:34.540
one, purchased for Miss Temple's wedding and never worn since, was soon put on, my

07:20:34.540 --> 07:20:39.760
hair was soon smoothed, my sole ornament, the pearl brooch, soon assumed. We descended.

07:20:41.040 --> 07:20:44.980
Fortunately there was another entrance to the drawing-room than that through the saloon

07:20:44.980 --> 07:20:50.120
where they were all seated at dinner. We found the apartment vacant, a large fire burning

07:20:50.120 --> 07:20:55.460
silently on the marble hearth, and wax candles shining in bright solitude, amid the exquisite

07:20:55.460 --> 07:20:59.880
flowers with which the tables were adorned. The crimson curtain hung before the arch,

07:20:59.880 --> 07:21:04.840
Slight as was the separation, this drapery formed from the party in the adjoining saloon.

07:21:05.080 --> 07:21:09.100
They spoke in so low a key that nothing of their conversation could be distinguished

07:21:09.100 --> 07:21:15.360
beyond a soothing murmur. Adele, who appeared still to be under the influence of a most

07:21:15.360 --> 07:21:19.940
solemnizing impression, sat down, without a word, on the footstool I pointed out for

07:21:19.940 --> 07:21:25.540
her. I retired to a window-seat, and taking a book from a table near, endeavoured to read.

07:21:26.280 --> 07:21:29.900
Adele brought her stool to my feet. Ere long she touched my knee.

07:21:30.440 --> 07:21:32.000
What is it, Adele?

07:21:32.660 --> 07:21:38.220
——Ece que je ne puis pas prendre une seule de ces fleurs magnifiques, mademoiselle,

07:21:38.720 --> 07:21:40.520
seulement pour compléter ma toilette.

07:21:41.640 --> 07:21:47.180
You think too much of your toilette, Adele, but you may have a flower. And I took a rose

07:21:47.180 --> 07:21:52.280
from a vase, and fastened it in her sash. She sighed a sigh of ineffable satisfaction,

07:21:52.280 --> 07:21:58.020
as if her cup of happiness were now full. I turned my face away. To conceal a smile

07:21:58.020 --> 07:22:02.320
I could not suppress, there was something ludicrous as well as painful in the little

07:22:02.320 --> 07:22:05.620
Parisian's earnest and innate devotion to matters of dress.

07:22:06.640 --> 07:22:11.640
A soft sound of rising now became audible. The curtain was swept back from the arch.

07:22:12.000 --> 07:22:16.180
Through it appeared the dining-room, with its lit luster pouring down light on the silver

07:22:16.180 --> 07:22:21.540
and glass of a magnificent dinner-service, covering a long table. A band of ladies stood

07:22:21.540 --> 07:22:27.200
in the opening. They entered, and the curtain fell behind them. There were but eight. Yet

07:22:27.200 --> 07:22:32.200
somehow as they flocked in, they gave the impression of a much larger number. Some of

07:22:32.200 --> 07:22:37.240
them were very tall, many of them were dressed in white, and all had a sweeping amplitude

07:22:37.240 --> 07:22:43.580
of a ray that seemed to magnify their persons as a mist magnifies the moon. I rose and curtsied

07:22:43.580 --> 07:22:48.540
to them. One or two bent their heads in return. The others only stared at me.

07:22:49.200 --> 07:22:54.120
They dispersed around the room, reminding me by the lightness and buoyancy of their

07:22:54.120 --> 07:22:59.840
movements of a flock of white plumey birds. Some of them threw themselves in half-reclining

07:22:59.840 --> 07:23:05.120
positions on the sofas and ottomans. Some bent over the tables, and examined the flowers

07:23:05.120 --> 07:23:10.720
and books. The rest gathered in a group around the fire. All talked in a low but clear tone

07:23:10.720 --> 07:23:15.420
which seemed habitual to them. I knew their names afterwards, and may as well mention

07:23:15.420 --> 07:23:16.020
them now.

07:23:16.960 --> 07:23:22.180
First, there was Mrs. Eshton, and two of her daughters. She had evidently been a handsome

07:23:22.180 --> 07:23:27.640
woman, and was well preserved still. Of her daughters, the eldest, Amy, was rather little,

07:23:28.160 --> 07:23:33.260
naïve and childlike in face and manner, and piquant in form. Her white muslin dress and

07:23:33.260 --> 07:23:39.760
blue sash became her well. The second, Louisa, was taller and more elegant in figure, with

07:23:39.760 --> 07:23:45.440
a very pretty face, of that order the French term me-noir chiffon. Both sisters were as

07:23:45.440 --> 07:23:51.500
fair as lilies. Lady Lynn was a large and stout personage of about forty, very erect,

07:23:51.820 --> 07:23:57.300
very haughty-looking, richly dressed in a satin robe of changeful sheen, her dark hair

07:23:57.300 --> 07:24:01.920
shewn glossily under the shade of an azure plume, and within the circlet of a band of

07:24:01.920 --> 07:24:02.320
gems.

07:24:03.420 --> 07:24:09.660
Mrs. Colonel Dent was less showy, but, I thought, more ladylike. She had a slight figure, a pale

07:24:10.010 --> 07:24:15.900
face, and fair hair. Her black satin dress, her scarf of rich foreign lace, and her pearl

07:24:15.900 --> 07:24:21.100
ornaments pleased me better than the rainbow radiance of the title Dame. But the three

07:24:21.100 --> 07:24:25.980
most distinguished, partly perhaps because the tallest figures of the band, were the

07:24:25.980 --> 07:24:32.060
dowager Lady Ingram, and her daughters, Blanche and Mary. They were all three of the loftiest

07:24:32.060 --> 07:24:37.580
stature of women. The dowager might be between forty and fifty, her shape was still fine,

07:24:37.580 --> 07:24:43.240
her hair, by candlelight at least, still black. Her teeth, too, were still apparently perfect.

07:24:43.760 --> 07:24:48.340
Most people would have termed her a splendid woman of her age, and so she was, no doubt,

07:24:48.520 --> 07:24:53.660
physically speaking. But then there was an expression of almost insupportable haughtiness

07:24:53.660 --> 07:24:58.800
in her bearing and countenance. She had Roman features, and a double chin, disappearing

07:24:58.800 --> 07:25:04.240
into a throat like a pillar. These features appeared to me not only inflated and darkened,

07:25:04.240 --> 07:25:10.180
but even furrowed with pride, and the chin was sustained by the same principle, in a

07:25:10.180 --> 07:25:16.900
position of almost preternatural erectness. She had likewise a fierce and hard eye. It

07:25:16.900 --> 07:25:21.660
reminded me of Mrs. Reade's. She mouthed her words in speaking. Her voice was deep,

07:25:21.960 --> 07:25:28.700
its inflections very pompous, very dogmatical, very intolerable in short. A crimson velvet

07:25:28.700 --> 07:25:35.100
and a shawl turban of some gold-rot Indian fabric invested her, I suppose she thought,

07:25:35.440 --> 07:25:37.420
with a truly imperial dignity.

07:25:39.100 --> 07:25:45.020
Blanche and Mary were of equal stature, straight and tall as poplars. Mary was too slim for

07:25:45.020 --> 07:25:50.460
her height, but Blanche was moulded like a dion. I regarded her, of course, with special

07:25:50.460 --> 07:25:55.580
interest. First, I wished to see whether her appearance accorded with Mrs. Fairfax's description.

07:25:55.580 --> 07:26:01.020
Secondly, whether it at all resembled the fancy miniature I had painted of her. And

07:26:01.020 --> 07:26:06.680
thirdly, it will out, whether it were such as I should fancy, likely to suit Mr. Rochester's

07:26:06.680 --> 07:26:13.460
tastes. As far as person went, she added point for point, both to my picture and to Mrs.

07:26:13.660 --> 07:26:18.620
Fairfax's description. The noble bust, the sloping shoulders, the graceful neck, the

07:26:18.620 --> 07:26:24.140
dark eyes and black ringlets, were all there. But her face—her face was like her mother's,

07:26:24.140 --> 07:26:29.800
a youthful, unfurrowed likeness, the same low brow, the same high features, the same

07:26:29.800 --> 07:26:35.740
pride. It was not, however, so Saturnine a pride. She laughed continually. Her laugh

07:26:35.740 --> 07:26:40.500
was satirical, and so was the habitual expression of her arched and haughty lip.

07:26:41.700 --> 07:26:46.800
Genius is said to be self-conscious. I cannot tell whether Miss Ingram was a genius, but

07:26:46.800 --> 07:26:52.980
she was self-conscious, remarkably self-conscious indeed. She entered into a discourse on botany

07:26:52.980 --> 07:26:57.920
with the gentle Mrs. Dent. It seemed Mrs. Dent had not studied that science, though,

07:26:57.960 --> 07:27:03.740
as she said, she liked flowers, especially wild ones. Miss Ingram had, and she ran over

07:27:03.740 --> 07:27:10.100
its vocabulary with an air. I presently perceived she was what is vernacularly termed trailing

07:27:10.100 --> 07:27:15.600
Mrs. Dent, that is, playing on her ignorance. Her trail might be clever, but it was decidedly

07:27:15.600 --> 07:27:21.580
not good-natured. She played, her execution was brilliant. She sang, her voice was fine.

07:27:21.920 --> 07:27:26.920
She talked French apart to her mamma, and she talked it well, with fluency and with

07:27:26.920 --> 07:27:31.400
a good accent. Mary had a milder and more open countenance

07:27:31.400 --> 07:27:36.980
than Blanche, softer features, too, and a skin some shades fairer. Miss Ingram was dark

07:27:36.980 --> 07:27:42.660
as a Spaniard. But Mary was deficient in life. Her face lacked expression, her eye luster.

07:27:43.060 --> 07:27:48.360
She had nothing to say, and having once taken her seat, remained fixed like a statue in

07:27:48.360 --> 07:27:51.800
its niche. The sisters were both attired in spotless white.

07:27:52.660 --> 07:27:57.520
And did I now think Miss Ingram such a choice as Mr. Rochester would be likely to make?

07:27:58.200 --> 07:28:03.540
I could not tell. I did not know his taste in female beauty. If he liked the majestic,

07:28:03.860 --> 07:28:09.140
she was the very type of majesty. Then she was accomplished, sprightly. Most gentlemen

07:28:09.140 --> 07:28:13.820
would admire her, I thought, and that he did admire her, I seem already to have obtained

07:28:13.820 --> 07:28:18.720
proof. To remove the last shade of doubt, it remained but to see them together.

07:28:20.240 --> 07:28:25.300
You are not to suppose, reader, that Adèle has all this time been sitting motionless

07:28:25.300 --> 07:28:31.120
on the stool at my feet. No, when the ladies entered, she rose, advanced to meet them,

07:28:31.420 --> 07:28:33.640
made a stately reverence, and said with gravity,

07:28:34.400 --> 07:28:35.440
Bonjour, mesdames.

07:28:36.320 --> 07:28:39.940
And Miss Ingram had looked down at her with a mocking air, and exclaimed,

07:28:39.940 --> 07:28:41.660
Oh, what a little puppet!

07:28:42.960 --> 07:28:44.440
Lady Lynne had remarked,

07:28:44.640 --> 07:28:49.280
It is Mr. Rochester's ward, I suppose, the little French girl he was speaking of.

07:28:50.200 --> 07:28:56.120
Mrs. Dent had kindly taken her hand, and given her a kiss. Amy and Louisa Eshton had cried

07:28:56.120 --> 07:28:58.980
out simultaneously, What a love of a child!

07:28:59.860 --> 07:29:05.200
And then they had called her to a sofa, where she now sat ensconced between them, chattering

07:29:05.740 --> 07:29:11.120
in French and broken English, absorbing not only the young lady's attention, but that

07:29:11.120 --> 07:29:15.240
of Mrs. Eshton and Lady Lynne, and getting spoiled to her heart's content.

07:29:16.120 --> 07:29:22.180
At last coffee is brought in, and the gentlemen are summoned. I sit in the shade, if any shade

07:29:22.180 --> 07:29:27.420
there be in this brilliantly lit apartment. The window-curtain half hides me. Again the

07:29:27.420 --> 07:29:32.500
arch yawns. They come. The collective appearance of the gentlemen, like that of the ladies,

07:29:32.500 --> 07:29:38.140
is very imposing. They are all costumed in black. Most of them are tall, some young.

07:29:38.760 --> 07:29:44.100
Henry and Frederick Lynne are very dashing sparks indeed, and Colonel Dent is a fine

07:29:44.100 --> 07:29:50.000
soldierly man. Mr. Eshton, the magistrate of the district, is gentleman-like. His hair

07:29:50.000 --> 07:29:54.800
is quite white, his eyebrows and whiskers still dark, which gives him something of the

07:29:54.800 --> 07:29:56.760
appearance of a noble father of the theatre.

07:29:57.700 --> 07:30:03.260
Lord Ingram, like his sisters, is very tall. Like them also he is handsome. But he shares

07:30:03.260 --> 07:30:08.340
Mary's apathetic and listless look. He seems to have more length of limb than vivacity

07:30:08.340 --> 07:30:10.240
of blood or vigour of brain.

07:30:10.920 --> 07:30:12.560
And where is Mr. Rochester?

07:30:13.460 --> 07:30:20.180
He comes in last. I am not looking at the arch, yet I see him enter. I try to concentrate

07:30:20.180 --> 07:30:25.380
my attention on the netting-needles, on the meshes of the purse I am forming. I wish only

07:30:25.380 --> 07:30:30.100
to think of the work I have in my hands, to see only the silver beads and silk threads

07:30:30.100 --> 07:30:35.880
that lie in my lap, whereas I distinctly behold his figure, and I inevitably recall the moment

07:30:35.880 --> 07:30:41.280
when I last saw it, just after I had rendered him what he deemed an essential service, and

07:30:41.280 --> 07:30:46.440
he, holding my hand and looking down in my face, surveyed me with eyes that revealed

07:30:46.440 --> 07:30:53.320
a heart full and eager to overflow, in whose emotions I had a part. How near had I approached

07:30:53.320 --> 07:30:59.240
him at that moment! What had occurred since, calculated to change his and my relative positions,

07:30:59.880 --> 07:31:05.880
yet now how distant, how far estranged we were! So far estranged that I did not expect

07:31:05.880 --> 07:31:11.180
him to come and speak to me. I did not wonder when, without looking at me, he took a seat

07:31:11.180 --> 07:31:15.100
at the other side of the room, and began conversing with some of the ladies.

07:31:17.720 --> 07:31:22.860
No sooner did I see that his attention was riveted on them, and that I might gaze without

07:31:22.860 --> 07:31:29.200
being observed, than my eyes were drawn involuntarily to his face. I could not keep their lids under

07:31:29.200 --> 07:31:33.020
control. They would rise, and the irises would fix on him.

07:31:33.700 --> 07:31:39.720
I looked, and had an acute pleasure in looking, a precious yet poignant pleasure, pure gold

07:31:39.720 --> 07:31:44.760
with a steely point of agony, a pleasure like what the thirst-perishing man might feel,

07:31:45.120 --> 07:31:49.820
who knows the well to which he has crept his poison, yet stoops and drinks divine draughts

07:31:49.820 --> 07:31:55.720
nevertheless. Most true is it that beauty is in the eye of the gazer. My master's colourless

07:31:55.720 --> 07:32:01.520
olive face, square massive brow, broad and jetty eyebrows, deep eyes, strong features,

07:32:01.720 --> 07:32:07.920
firm grim mouth, all energy, decision, will, were not beautiful, according to rule. Oh,

07:32:07.920 --> 07:32:12.620
but they were beautiful to me. They were full of an interest, an influence, that quite mastered

07:32:12.620 --> 07:32:16.840
me, that took my feelings from my own power, and fettered them in his.

07:32:17.780 --> 07:32:22.800
I had not intended to love him. The reader knows I had wrought hard to extirpate from

07:32:22.800 --> 07:32:27.540
my soul the germs of love there detected, and now, at the first renewed view of him,

07:32:27.780 --> 07:32:32.840
they spontaneously arrived, green and strong. He made me love him without looking at me.

07:32:33.540 --> 07:32:38.980
I compared him with his guests. What was the gallant grace of the lins, the languid elegance

07:32:38.980 --> 07:32:43.620
of Lord Ingram, even the military distinction of Colonel Dent, contrasted with his look

07:32:43.620 --> 07:32:49.520
of native pith and genuine power? I had no sympathy in their appearance, their expression,

07:32:50.000 --> 07:32:54.460
yet I could imagine that most observers would call them attractive, handsome, imposing,

07:32:54.920 --> 07:32:59.180
while they would pronounce Mr. Rochester at once harsh-featured and melancholy-looking.

07:32:59.820 --> 07:33:05.080
I saw them smile, laugh. It was nothing. The light of the candles had as much soul in it

07:33:05.080 --> 07:33:09.960
as their smile. The tinkle of the bell as much significance as their laugh. I saw Mr.

07:33:09.960 --> 07:33:15.540
Rochester smile. His stern features softened. His eye grew both brilliant and gentle, its

07:33:15.540 --> 07:33:21.480
ray both searching and sweet. He was talking, at the moment, to Louisa and Amy Eshton. I

07:33:21.480 --> 07:33:26.500
wondered to see them receive with calm that look which seemed to me so penetrating. I

07:33:26.500 --> 07:33:31.540
expected their eyes to fall, their colour to rise under it. Yet I was glad when I found

07:33:31.540 --> 07:33:36.780
that they were in no sense moved. He is not to them what he is to me, I thought. He is

07:33:36.780 --> 07:33:43.140
not of their kind. I believe he is of mine. I am sure he is. I feel akin to him. I understand

07:33:43.140 --> 07:33:48.140
the language of his countenance and movements. Though rank and wealth sever us widely, I

07:33:48.140 --> 07:33:52.720
have something in my brain and heart, in my blood and nerves, that assimilates me mentally

07:33:52.720 --> 07:33:58.040
to him. Did I say, a few days since, that I had nothing to do with him but to receive

07:33:58.040 --> 07:34:03.040
my salary at his hands? Did I forbid myself to think of him in any other light than as

07:34:03.040 --> 07:34:09.280
a paymaster? Blasphemy against nature! Every good, true, vigorous feeling I have gathers

07:34:09.280 --> 07:34:15.220
impulsively around him. I know I must conceal my sentiments. I must smother hope. I must

07:34:15.220 --> 07:34:20.720
remember that he cannot care much for me. For when I say that I am of his kind, I do

07:34:20.720 --> 07:34:25.980
not mean that I have his force to influence, and his spell to attract. I mean only that

07:34:25.980 --> 07:34:31.560
I have certain tastes and feelings in common with him. I must then repeat continually that

07:34:31.560 --> 07:34:36.520
we are forever sundered. And yet, while I breathe and think, I must love him.

07:34:37.900 --> 07:34:44.820
Coffee is handed. The ladies, since the gentlemen entered, have become lively as larks. Conversation

07:34:44.820 --> 07:34:50.960
waxes brisk and merry. Colonel Dent and Mrs. Eshton argue on politics. Their wives listen.

07:34:51.540 --> 07:34:56.760
The two proud dowagers, Lady Lynn and Lady Ingram, confabulate together. Sir George,

07:34:56.760 --> 07:35:01.880
whom by the by I have forgotten to describe, a very big and very fresh-looking country

07:35:01.880 --> 07:35:07.320
gentleman, stands before their sofa, coffee-cup in hand, and occasionally puts in a word.

07:35:08.000 --> 07:35:12.900
Mr. Frederick Lynn has taken a seat beside Mary Ingram, and is showing her the engravings

07:35:12.900 --> 07:35:19.060
of a splendid volume. She looks, smiles now and then, but apparently says little. The

07:35:19.060 --> 07:35:23.760
tall and phlegmatic Lord Ingram leans with folded arms on the chair-back of the little

07:35:23.760 --> 07:35:29.720
and lively Amy Eshton. She glances up at him, and chatters like a wren. She likes him better

07:35:29.720 --> 07:35:35.020
than she does Mr. Rochester. Henry Lynn has taken possession of an Ottoman at the feet

07:35:35.020 --> 07:35:40.260
of Louisa. Adele shares it with him. He is trying to talk French with her, and Louisa

07:35:40.260 --> 07:35:46.100
laughs at his blunders. With whom will blanching grim pair? She is standing alone at the table,

07:35:46.500 --> 07:35:51.840
bending gracefully over an album. She seems waiting to be sought. But she will not wait

07:35:51.840 --> 07:35:59.780
too long. She herself selects a mate. Mr. Rochester, having quitted the Eshton's, stands

07:35:59.780 --> 07:36:05.620
on the hearth as solitary as she stands by the table. She confronts him, taking her station

07:36:05.620 --> 07:36:07.700
on the opposite side of the mantelpiece.

07:36:08.340 --> 07:36:11.520
—Mr. Rochester, I thought you were not fond of children?

07:36:12.240 --> 07:36:13.260
—Nor am I.

07:36:13.780 --> 07:36:19.060
—Then what induced you to take charge of such a little doll as that?—pointing to

07:36:19.060 --> 07:36:20.960
Adele. Where did you pick her up?

07:36:21.700 --> 07:36:24.300
—I did not pick her up. She was left on my hands.

07:36:24.840 --> 07:36:26.540
—You should have sent her to school.

07:36:27.100 --> 07:36:30.060
—I could not afford it. Schools are so dear.

07:36:30.620 --> 07:36:35.440
—Why, I suppose you have a governess for her. I saw a person with her just now. Is

07:36:35.440 --> 07:36:40.680
she gone? Oh, no, there she is still, behind the window-curtain. You pay her, of course.

07:36:40.800 --> 07:36:45.820
I should think it quite as expensive. More so, for you have them both to keep in addition.

07:36:46.700 --> 07:36:52.640
I feared, or should I say I hoped, the illusion to me would make Mr. Rochester glance in my

07:36:52.640 --> 07:36:58.100
way, and I involuntarily shrank further into the shade. But he never turned his eyes.

07:36:58.640 --> 07:37:03.060
—I have not considered the subject, he said he indifferently, looking straight before

07:37:03.060 --> 07:37:08.800
him. No, you men never do consider economy and good sense. You should hear Mama on the

07:37:08.800 --> 07:37:14.240
chapter of governesses. Mary and I have had, I should think, a dozen at least in our day,

07:37:14.240 --> 07:37:21.220
half of them detestable and the rest ridiculous and all incubi. Were they not, Mama? Did you

07:37:21.220 --> 07:37:27.220
speak my own? The young lady, thus claimed as the dowager's special property, reiterated

07:37:27.220 --> 07:37:33.080
her question with an explanation. Oh, my dearest, don't mention governesses. The word makes

07:37:33.080 --> 07:37:38.720
me nervous. I have suffered a martyrdom from their incompetency and caprice. I thank Heaven

07:37:39.260 --> 07:37:47.120
Mrs. Dent here bent over to the pious lady and whispered something in her ear. I suppose

07:37:47.120 --> 07:37:51.900
from the answer elicited, it was a reminder that one of the anathematized race was present.

07:37:52.540 --> 07:37:55.960
—Tante P., said her ladyship, I hope it may do her good.

07:37:56.680 --> 07:38:02.640
Then, in a lower tone, but still loud enough for me to hear, I noticed her. I am a judge

07:38:02.640 --> 07:38:06.580
of physiognomy, and in hers I see all the faults of her class.

07:38:07.320 --> 07:38:10.740
—What are they, madam? inquired Mr. Rochester aloud.

07:38:11.100 --> 07:38:17.280
—I will tell you in your private ear, replied she, wagging her turban three times with portentous

07:38:17.280 --> 07:38:25.000
significancy. But my curiosity will be past its appetite. It craves food now. Ask Blanche.

07:38:25.080 --> 07:38:26.680
She is nearer you than I.

07:38:27.620 --> 07:38:33.480
—Oh, don't refer him to me, Mama. I have just one word to say of the whole tribe. They

07:38:33.480 --> 07:38:38.700
are a nuisance. Not that I ever suffered much from them. I took care to turn the tables.

07:38:39.140 --> 07:38:44.040
What tricks Theodore and I used to play on our Miss Wilsons and Miss Grays and Madame

07:38:44.040 --> 07:38:49.840
Joubert's! Mary was always too sleepy to join in a plot with spirit. The best fun was

07:38:49.840 --> 07:38:55.260
with Madame Joubert. Miss Wilson was a poor, sickly thing, lacrimose and low-spirited,

07:38:55.560 --> 07:39:03.460
not worth the trouble of vanquishing in short, and Mrs. Gray was coarse and insensible. No

07:39:03.460 --> 07:39:09.040
Madame Joubert. I see her yet in her raging passions, when we had driven her to extremities,

07:39:09.460 --> 07:39:14.400
spilt our tea, crumpled our bread and butter, tossed our books up to the ceiling, and played

07:39:14.400 --> 07:39:19.940
a cherry-vary with the ruler and desk, the fender and fire-irons. Theodore, do you remember

07:39:19.940 --> 07:39:20.980
those merry days?

07:39:22.160 --> 07:39:28.360
—Yes, to be sure I do, drawled Lord Ingram. And the poor old stick used to cry out, Oh,

07:39:28.360 --> 07:39:33.500
you villainous childs! And then we sermonised her on the presumption of attempting to teach

07:39:33.500 --> 07:39:37.440
such clever blades as we were, when she herself was so ignorant.

07:39:38.320 --> 07:39:45.060
We did. And Tito, you know I helped you in prosecuting, or persecuting, your tutor, way-faced

07:39:45.060 --> 07:39:50.540
Mr. Vining, the parson in the PIP, as we used to call him. He and Miss Wilson took the liberty

07:39:50.540 --> 07:39:55.780
of falling in love with each other, at least Tito and I thought so. We surprised sundry

07:39:56.400 --> 07:40:01.540
glances and sighs, which we interpreted as tokens of la belle passion. And I promised

07:40:01.540 --> 07:40:06.560
you the public soon had the benefit of our discovery. We employed it as a sort of lever

07:40:06.560 --> 07:40:11.120
to hoist our dead-weights from the house. Dear mamma there, as soon as she got an inkling

07:40:11.120 --> 07:40:16.100
of the business, found out that it was of an immoral tendency. Did you not, my lady

07:40:16.100 --> 07:40:16.560
mother?

07:40:17.340 --> 07:40:22.480
—Certainly my best. And I was quite right. Depend on that. There are a thousand reasons

07:40:22.480 --> 07:40:28.140
liaisons between governesses and tutors should never be tolerated a moment in any well-regulated

07:40:28.140 --> 07:40:35.220
houses. Firstly—Oh, gracious mammas, spare us the enumeration! All rest we all know them.

07:40:35.500 --> 07:40:40.220
Danger of bad example to the innocence of childhood, distractions and consequent neglect

07:40:40.220 --> 07:40:45.420
of duty on the part of the attached, mutual reliance and reliance, confidence thence resulting,

07:40:45.720 --> 07:40:50.660
insolence accompanying, mutiny and general blow-up. Am I right, Baroness Ingram of Ingram

07:40:50.660 --> 07:40:51.060
Park?

07:40:51.840 --> 07:40:54.640
—My lily-flower, you are right now as always.

07:40:55.480 --> 07:40:58.020
Then no more need be said. Change the subject.

07:40:59.200 --> 07:41:04.720
Amy Eshton, not hearing or not heeding this dictum, joined in with her soft infantine

07:41:04.720 --> 07:41:10.680
tone. Luisa and I used to quiz our governess too. But she was such a good creature. She

07:41:10.680 --> 07:41:15.440
would bear anything. Nothing put her out. She was never cross with us, was she, Luisa?

07:41:15.440 --> 07:41:21.660
No, never. We might do what we pleased, ransack her desk and her work-box, and turn her drawers

07:41:21.660 --> 07:41:26.420
inside out. And she was so good-natured, she would give us anything we asked for.

07:41:27.200 --> 07:41:32.440
I suppose now, said Miss Ingram, curling her lips sarcastically, we shall have an abstract

07:41:32.440 --> 07:41:37.880
of the memoirs of all the governesses extant. In order to avert such a visitation, I again

07:41:37.880 --> 07:41:42.400
move the introduction of a new topic. Mr. Rochester, do you second my motion?

07:41:43.260 --> 07:41:46.160
—Madam, I support you on this point, as on every other.

07:41:46.800 --> 07:41:51.920
Then on me be the onus of bringing it forward. Signor Eduardo, are you in voice to-night?

07:41:52.740 --> 07:41:59.460
Dona Bianca, if you command it, I will be. Then, Signor, I lay on you my sovereign behest,

07:41:59.660 --> 07:42:04.680
to furbish up your lungs and other vocal organs, as they will be wanted on my royal service.

07:42:05.700 --> 07:42:08.440
Who would not be the Rizio of so divine a Mary?

07:42:09.160 --> 07:42:14.380
—A fig for Rizio! cried she, tossing her head with all its curls, as she moved to the

07:42:14.380 --> 07:42:21.360
piano. It is my opinion the fiddler David must have been an insipid sort of fellow.

07:42:21.740 --> 07:42:26.760
I like Black Bothwell better. To my mind a man is nothing without a spice of the devil

07:42:26.760 --> 07:42:31.980
in him. And history may say what it will of James Hepburn. But I have a notion he was

07:42:31.980 --> 07:42:36.740
just the sort of wild, fierce bandit hero to whom I could have consented to gift my

07:42:36.740 --> 07:42:37.120
hand.

07:42:38.420 --> 07:42:43.480
—Gentlemen, you hear? Now which of you most resembles Bothwell? cried Mr. Rochester.

07:42:44.160 --> 07:42:47.400
—I should say the preference lies with you, responded Colonel Dent.

07:42:48.120 --> 07:42:51.460
—On my honour, I am much obliged to you, was the reply.

07:42:52.900 --> 07:42:57.880
Miss Ingram, who had now seated herself with a proud grace at the piano, spreading out

07:42:57.880 --> 07:43:04.560
her snowy robes in queenly amplitude, commenced a brilliant prelude, talking mean-time. She

07:43:04.560 --> 07:43:09.260
appeared to be on her high horse to-night. Both her words and her air seemed intended

07:43:09.260 --> 07:43:14.500
to excite not only the admiration, but the amazement of her auditors. She was evidently

07:43:14.500 --> 07:43:18.000
bent on striking them as something very dashing and daring indeed.

07:43:18.520 --> 07:43:23.540
"'Oh, I am so sick of the young men of the present day!' exclaimed she, rattling away

07:43:23.540 --> 07:43:29.760
at the instrument. Poor puny things! not fit to stir a step beyond papa's park gates,

07:43:29.760 --> 07:43:35.640
nor to go even so far without mamma's permission and guardianship. Creatures so absorbed in

07:43:35.640 --> 07:43:40.820
care about their pretty faces, and their white hands, and their small feet, as if a man had

07:43:40.820 --> 07:43:45.720
anything to do with beauty, as if loveliness were not the special prerogative of woman,

07:43:46.080 --> 07:43:51.500
her legitimate appanage and heritage. I grant an ugly woman is a blot on the fair face of

07:43:51.500 --> 07:43:57.020
creation. But as to gentlemen, let them be solicitous to possess only strength and valour.

07:43:57.020 --> 07:44:02.720
Let their motto be, Hunt, shoot, and fight, the rest is not worth a Philip. Such should

07:44:02.720 --> 07:44:04.460
be my device, were I a man.

07:44:05.320 --> 07:44:09.120
"'Whenever I marry,' she continued, after a pause which none interrupted,

07:44:09.500 --> 07:44:14.960
"'I am resolved my husband shall be not a rival, but a foil to me. I will suffer no

07:44:14.960 --> 07:44:20.420
competitor near the throne. I shall exact an undivided homage. His devotions shall not

07:44:20.420 --> 07:44:26.260
be shared between me and the shape he sees in his mirror. Mr. Rochester, now sing, and

07:44:26.260 --> 07:44:27.540
I will play for you.'

07:44:28.120 --> 07:44:30.540
"'I am all obedience,' was the response.

07:44:31.400 --> 07:44:36.900
"'Here, then, is a corsaire song. Know that I dote on corsaires, and for that reason sing

07:44:36.900 --> 07:44:42.780
it conspirito. Commands from Miss Ingram's lips would put spirit into a mug of milk and

07:44:42.780 --> 07:44:48.480
water. Take care, then. If you don't please me, I will shame you by showing you how things

07:44:48.480 --> 07:44:54.840
should be done. That is offering a premium on incapacity. I shall now endeavour to fail.

07:44:55.560 --> 07:45:01.220
"'Garde vous en bien. If you err willfully, I shall devise a proportionate punishment.'

07:45:01.220 --> 07:45:05.760
Miss Ingram ought to be clement, for she has it in her power to inflict a chastisement

07:45:05.760 --> 07:45:07.000
beyond mortal endurance.

07:45:07.640 --> 07:45:10.320
"'Ha! explain,' commanded the lady.

07:45:10.900 --> 07:45:16.140
"'Pardon me, madame. No need of explodation. Your own fine sense must inform you that one

07:45:16.140 --> 07:45:19.320
of your frowns would be a sufficient substitute for capital punishment.'

07:45:20.460 --> 07:45:26.140
"'Sing!' said she. And again touching the piano, she commenced an accompaniment in spirited

07:45:26.140 --> 07:45:26.660
style.

07:45:27.620 --> 07:45:32.900
"'Now is my time to slip away,' thought I. But the tones that then severed the air arrested

07:45:32.900 --> 07:45:39.800
me. Mrs. Fairfax had said Mr. Rochester possessed a fine voice. He did—a mellow, powerful

07:45:39.800 --> 07:45:45.240
bass into which he threw his own feeling, his own force, finding a way through the ear

07:45:45.240 --> 07:45:51.640
to the heart, and there waking sensation strangely. I waited till the last deep and full vibration

07:45:51.640 --> 07:45:57.240
had expired, till the tide of talk, checked an instant, had resumed its flow. I then quitted

07:45:57.240 --> 07:46:01.720
my sheltered corner, and made my exit by the side door, which was fortunately near.

07:46:02.520 --> 07:46:07.400
"'Thence a narrow passage led into the hall. In crossing it, I perceived my sandal was

07:46:07.400 --> 07:46:11.960
loose. I stepped to tie it, kneeling down for that purpose on the mat at the floor of

07:46:11.960 --> 07:46:18.160
the staircase. I heard the dining-room door unclose, a gentleman come out. Rising hastily,

07:46:18.240 --> 07:46:21.640
I stood face to face with him. It was Mr. Rochester.

07:46:23.040 --> 07:46:24.700
"'How do you do?' he asked.

07:46:25.240 --> 07:46:26.880
"'I am very well, sir.'

07:46:26.880 --> 07:46:30.000
"'Why did you not come and speak to me in the room?'

07:46:30.000 --> 07:46:34.840
"'I thought I might have retorted the question on him who put it, but I would not take that

07:46:34.840 --> 07:46:40.100
freedom. I answered, I did not wish to disturb you, as you seemed engaged, sir.'

07:46:40.720 --> 07:46:42.580
"'What have you been doing in my absence?'

07:46:43.500 --> 07:46:45.940
"'Nothing particular, teaching a dell as usual.'

07:46:46.820 --> 07:46:51.670
"'And getting a good deal paler than you were, as I saw at first sight. What is the matter?'

07:46:52.680 --> 07:46:53.770
"'Nothing at all, sir.'

07:46:54.380 --> 07:46:57.250
"'Did you take any cold that night you half-drowned me?'

07:46:57.960 --> 07:46:58.980
"'Not in the least.'

07:47:00.020 --> 07:47:02.760
"'Return to the drawing-room. You are deserting too early.'

07:47:03.300 --> 07:47:04.420
"'I am tired, sir.'

07:47:05.000 --> 07:47:06.700
He looked at me for a minute.

07:47:07.280 --> 07:47:10.240
"'And a little depressed, he said. What about? Tell me.'

07:47:11.100 --> 07:47:13.060
"'Nothing, nothing, sir. I am not depressed.'

07:47:13.760 --> 07:47:18.880
"'But I affirm that you are. So much depressed that a few more words would bring tears to your eyes.

07:47:19.220 --> 07:47:23.960
Indeed, they are there now, shining and swimming, and a bead has slipped from the lash and fallen

07:47:23.960 --> 07:47:30.180
on to the flag. If I had time, and was not in mortal dread of some prating prig of a servant

07:47:30.180 --> 07:47:35.560
passing, I would know what all this means. Well, to-night I excuse you. But understand that,

07:47:35.700 --> 07:47:40.420
so long as my visitors stay, I expect you to appear in the drawing-room every evening.

07:47:40.820 --> 07:47:46.180
It is my wish. Don't neglect it. Now go and send Sophie for a dell. Good night, my—'

07:47:46.740 --> 07:47:50.320
He stopped, bit his lip, and abruptly left me.

07:48:13.340 --> 07:48:13.980
18.

07:48:15.500 --> 07:48:18.960
Merry days were these at Thornfield Hall, and busy days too.

07:48:18.960 --> 07:48:23.620
How different from the first three months of stillness, monotony, and solitude I had

07:48:23.620 --> 07:48:24.800
passed beneath its roof!

07:48:25.440 --> 07:48:30.460
All sad feelings seemed now driven from the house, all gloomy associations forgotten.

07:48:31.060 --> 07:48:33.500
There was life everywhere, movement all day long.

07:48:33.940 --> 07:48:38.820
You could not now traverse the gallery, once so hushed, nor enter the front chambers, once

07:48:38.820 --> 07:48:43.360
so tenantless, without encountering a smart lady's maid or a dandy valet.

07:48:44.000 --> 07:48:48.600
The kitchen, the butler's pantry, the servant's hall, the entrance hall were equally alive,

07:48:48.600 --> 07:48:53.820
and the saloons were only left void and still when the blue sky and halcyon sunshine of

07:48:53.820 --> 07:48:57.160
the genial spring weather called their occupants out into the grounds.

07:48:57.800 --> 07:49:03.000
Even when that weather was broken, and continuous rain set in for some days, no damp seemed

07:49:03.000 --> 07:49:04.300
cast over enjoyment.

07:49:04.980 --> 07:49:09.720
Indoor amusements only became more lively and varied, in consequence of the stop put

07:49:09.720 --> 07:49:10.740
to outdoor gaiety.

07:49:11.520 --> 07:49:15.500
I wondered what they were going to do the first evening a change of entertainment was

07:49:15.500 --> 07:49:15.960
proposed.

07:49:15.960 --> 07:49:20.480
They spoke of playing charades, but in my ignorance I did not understand the term.

07:49:21.000 --> 07:49:25.700
The servants were called in, the dining-room tables wheeled away, the lights otherwise

07:49:25.700 --> 07:49:29.220
disposed, the chairs placed in a semi-circle opposite the arch.

07:49:29.780 --> 07:49:34.320
While Mr. Rochester and the other gentlemen directed these alterations, the ladies were

07:49:34.320 --> 07:49:36.900
running up and down stairs, ringing for their maids.

07:49:37.320 --> 07:49:42.380
Mrs. Fairfax was summoned to give information respecting the resources of the house in shawls,

07:49:42.960 --> 07:49:48.140
draperies of any kind, and certain wardrobes of the third story were ransacked, and their

07:49:48.140 --> 07:49:54.000
contents, in the shape of brocaded and hooped petticoats, satin sacks, black modes, lace

07:49:54.000 --> 07:49:57.880
lapettes, etc., were brought down in the armfuls by the Abigail's.

07:49:58.200 --> 07:50:02.780
Then a selection was made, and such things as were chosen were carried to the boudoir

07:50:02.780 --> 07:50:03.920
within the drawing-room.

07:50:05.060 --> 07:50:10.220
Meantime Mr. Rochester had again summoned the ladies around him, and was selecting certain

07:50:10.220 --> 07:50:12.000
of their number to be of his party.

07:50:12.640 --> 07:50:14.740
"'Miss Ingram is mine, of course,' said he.

07:50:15.200 --> 07:50:18.260
Afterwards he named the two Mrs. Eshton and Mrs. Dent.

07:50:18.920 --> 07:50:23.380
He looked at me, I happened to be near him, as I had been fastening the clasp of Mrs.

07:50:23.440 --> 07:50:25.380
Dent's bracelet, which had gotten loose.

07:50:26.080 --> 07:50:27.500
"'Will you play?' he asked.

07:50:28.020 --> 07:50:28.880
I shook my head.

07:50:29.180 --> 07:50:31.960
He did not insist, which I rather feared he would have done.

07:50:32.240 --> 07:50:35.020
He allowed me to return quietly to my usual seat.

07:50:35.020 --> 07:50:38.540
He and his aides now withdrew behind the curtain.

07:50:39.000 --> 07:50:43.320
The other party, which was headed by Colonel Dent, sat down on the crescent of chairs.

07:50:44.000 --> 07:50:48.740
One of the gentlemen, Mr. Eshton, observing me, seemed to propose that I should be asked

07:50:48.740 --> 07:50:52.180
to join them, but Lady Ingram instantly negatived the notion.

07:50:52.980 --> 07:50:54.280
"'No,' I heard her say.

07:50:54.460 --> 07:50:58.540
She looks too stupid for any game of the sort.'

07:50:58.540 --> 07:51:01.860
Ere long a bell tinkled, and the curtain drew up.

07:51:02.360 --> 07:51:07.840
Within the arch, the bulky figure of Sir George Lynn, whom Mr. Rochester had likewise chosen,

07:51:08.160 --> 07:51:10.120
was seen enveloped in a white sheet.

07:51:10.660 --> 07:51:17.160
Before him, on a table, lay open a large book, and at his side stood Amy Eshton, draped in

07:51:17.160 --> 07:51:20.220
Mr. Rochester's cloak and holding a book in her hand.

07:51:20.820 --> 07:51:26.160
Somebody unseen rang a bell merrily, then Adèle, who had insisted on being one of her

07:51:26.160 --> 07:51:31.180
guardians' party, bounded forward, scattering round her the contents of a basket of flowers

07:51:31.180 --> 07:51:32.480
she carried on her arm.

07:51:33.200 --> 07:51:39.140
Then appeared the magnificent figure of Miss Ingram, clad in white, a long veil on her

07:51:39.140 --> 07:51:41.540
head, and a wreath of roses round her brow.

07:51:42.100 --> 07:51:46.280
By her side walked Mr. Rochester, and together they drew near the table.

07:51:46.920 --> 07:51:52.300
They knelt, while Mrs. Dent and Louisa Eshton, dressed also in white, took up their stations

07:51:52.300 --> 07:51:53.080
behind them.

07:51:53.500 --> 07:51:58.360
A ceremony followed, in dumb show, in which it was easy to recognize the pantomime of

07:51:58.360 --> 07:51:58.880
a marriage.

07:51:59.380 --> 07:52:04.940
At its termination, Colonel Dent and his party consulted in whispers for two minutes, then

07:52:04.940 --> 07:52:06.000
the Colonel called out,

07:52:06.740 --> 07:52:07.380
"'Bride!'

07:52:07.380 --> 07:52:10.440
Mr. Rochester bowed, and the curtain fell.

07:52:11.660 --> 07:52:15.040
A considerable interval elapsed before it rose again.

07:52:15.680 --> 07:52:19.980
Its second rising displayed a more elaborately prepared scene than the last.

07:52:20.480 --> 07:52:25.400
The drawing-room, as I have before observed, was raised two steps above the dining-room,

07:52:25.400 --> 07:52:30.300
and on the top of the upper step, placed a yard or two back within the room, appeared

07:52:30.300 --> 07:52:35.620
a large marble basin, which I recognized as an ornament of the Conservatory, where it

07:52:35.620 --> 07:52:41.000
usually stood, surrounded by exotics and tenanted by goldfish, and whence it must have been

07:52:41.000 --> 07:52:44.120
transported with some trouble, on account of its size and weight.

07:52:45.320 --> 07:52:50.680
Seated on the table, by the side of this basin, was seen Mr. Rochester, costumed in shawls,

07:52:50.680 --> 07:52:51.960
with a turban on his head.

07:52:52.420 --> 07:52:56.800
His dark eyes and swarthy skin and panum features suited the costume exactly.

07:52:57.280 --> 07:53:01.820
He looked the very model of an Eastern emir, an agent or a victim of the bow-string.

07:53:02.700 --> 07:53:04.800
Presently advanced into view Miss Ingram.

07:53:05.280 --> 07:53:10.820
She too was attired in Oriental fashion, a crimson scarf tied sash-like round the waist,

07:53:11.280 --> 07:53:15.940
an embroidered handkerchief knotted about her temples, her beautifully molded arms bare,

07:53:15.940 --> 07:53:21.320
one of them upraised in the act of supporting a pitcher, poised gracefully on her head.

07:53:22.020 --> 07:53:27.780
Both her cast of form and feature, her complexion and her general air, suggested the idea of

07:53:27.780 --> 07:53:32.780
some Israeliteish princess of the patriarchal days, and such was doubtless the character

07:53:32.780 --> 07:53:34.160
she intended to represent.

07:53:35.220 --> 07:53:39.060
She approached the basin, and bent over it as if to fill her pitcher.

07:53:39.660 --> 07:53:41.320
She again lifted it to her head.

07:53:41.800 --> 07:53:46.140
The personage on the well-brink now seemed to accost her to make some request.

07:53:46.880 --> 07:53:50.940
She hasted, let down her pitcher on her hand, and gave him to drink.

07:53:51.480 --> 07:53:56.540
From the bosom of his robe, then produced a casket, opened it, and showed magnificent

07:53:56.540 --> 07:54:00.220
bracelets and earrings, she acted astonishment and admiration.

07:54:00.760 --> 07:54:02.780
Kneeling he laid the treasure at her feet.

07:54:03.260 --> 07:54:06.460
In credulity and delight were expressed by her looks and gestures.

07:54:06.780 --> 07:54:10.900
The stranger fastened the bracelets on her arms and the rings in her ears.

07:54:11.480 --> 07:54:13.020
It was Eliezer and Rebecca.

07:54:13.580 --> 07:54:15.120
The camels only were wanting.

07:54:16.140 --> 07:54:18.900
The divining party again laid their heads together.

07:54:19.360 --> 07:54:23.340
Apparently it could not agree about the word or syllable the scene illustrated.

07:54:24.160 --> 07:54:28.960
Colonel Dent, their spokesman, demanded the tableau of the whole, whereupon the curtain

07:54:28.960 --> 07:54:29.800
again descended.

07:54:30.720 --> 07:54:35.800
On its third rising, only a portion of the drawing-room was disclosed, the rest being

07:54:35.800 --> 07:54:39.920
concealed by a screen, hung with some sort of dark and coarse drapery.

07:54:40.360 --> 07:54:41.860
The marble basin was removed.

07:54:42.180 --> 07:54:45.080
In its place stood a deal table and a kitchen chair.

07:54:45.640 --> 07:54:51.240
These objects were visible by a very dim light proceeding from a horn lantern, the wax candles

07:54:51.240 --> 07:54:52.580
being all extinguished.

07:54:53.360 --> 07:54:58.400
Amidst this sordid scene sat a man with his clenched hands resting on his knees, and

07:54:58.400 --> 07:54:59.740
his eyes bent on the ground.

07:55:00.280 --> 07:55:05.420
I knew Mr. Rochester, though the begrimed face, the disordered dress, his coat hanging

07:55:05.420 --> 07:55:09.440
loose from one arm, as if it had been almost torn from his back in a scuffle.

07:55:09.920 --> 07:55:14.540
The desperate and scowling countenance, the rough bristling hair, might well have disguised

07:55:14.540 --> 07:55:15.120
him.

07:55:15.360 --> 07:55:17.740
As he moved, a chain clanked.

07:55:17.900 --> 07:55:19.880
To his wrists were attached fetters.

07:55:20.900 --> 07:55:24.980
Bridewell, exclaimed Colonel Dent, and the charade was solved.

07:55:26.640 --> 07:55:31.400
A sufficient interval having elapsed for the performers to resume their ordinary costume,

07:55:32.000 --> 07:55:33.600
they re-entered the dining-room.

07:55:33.600 --> 07:55:36.040
Mr. Rochester led in Miss Ingram.

07:55:36.320 --> 07:55:38.420
She was complimenting him on his acting.

07:55:38.960 --> 07:55:43.540
"'Do you know,' said she, "'that of the three characters I liked you in the last best?

07:55:43.900 --> 07:55:48.220
Oh, had you but lived a few years earlier, what a gallant gentleman-high-woman you would

07:55:48.220 --> 07:55:49.320
have made!'

07:55:49.320 --> 07:55:53.460
"'Is all the soot washed from my face?' he asked, turning it toward her.

07:55:53.880 --> 07:55:55.540
"'Alas, yes, the more's the pity.

07:55:55.900 --> 07:55:59.360
Nothing could be more becoming to your complexion than Ruffian's rouge.

07:56:00.240 --> 07:56:02.580
You would like a hero of the road, then?'

07:56:03.060 --> 07:56:08.040
An English hero of the road would be the next best thing to an Italian bandit, and that

07:56:08.040 --> 07:56:10.340
could only be surpassed by a Levantine pirate.

07:56:11.320 --> 07:56:13.900
Well, whatever I am, remember you are my wife.

07:56:14.140 --> 07:56:18.280
We were married an hour since, in the presence of all these witnesses.'

07:56:18.280 --> 07:56:20.640
She giggled, and her colour rose.

07:56:21.940 --> 07:56:26.080
"'Now, Dent,' continued Mr. Rochester, "'it is your turn.'

07:56:26.080 --> 07:56:29.880
And as the other party withdrew, he and his band took the vacated seats.

07:56:30.430 --> 07:56:33.140
Miss Ingram placed herself at her leader's right hand.

07:56:33.560 --> 07:56:36.940
The other diviners filled the chairs on either side of him and her.

07:56:37.600 --> 07:56:39.300
I did not now watch the actors.

07:56:39.720 --> 07:56:42.340
I no longer waited with interest for the curtain to rise.

07:56:42.820 --> 07:56:45.140
My attention was absorbed by the spectators.

07:56:45.640 --> 07:56:50.740
My eyes, air while fixed on the arch, were now irresistibly attracted to the semicircle

07:56:50.740 --> 07:56:51.260
of chairs.

07:56:52.040 --> 07:56:57.780
What charade Colonel Dent and his party played, what word they chose, how they acquitted themselves,

07:56:57.800 --> 07:56:58.920
I no longer remember.

07:56:59.240 --> 07:57:02.200
But I still see the consultation which followed each scene.

07:57:02.760 --> 07:57:06.520
I see Mr. Rochester turn to Miss Ingram, and Miss Ingram to him.

07:57:07.120 --> 07:57:11.600
I see her incline her head towards him till the jetty curls almost touch his shoulder

07:57:11.600 --> 07:57:13.120
and wave against his cheek.

07:57:13.680 --> 07:57:15.500
I hear their mutual whisperings.

07:57:15.800 --> 07:57:20.660
I recall their interchanged glances, and something even of the feeling roused by the spectacle

07:57:20.660 --> 07:57:22.360
returns in memory at this moment.

07:57:23.140 --> 07:57:26.480
I have told you, reader, that I had learned to love Mr. Rochester.

07:57:26.900 --> 07:57:32.280
I could not unlove him now, merely because I found that he had ceased to notice me, because

07:57:32.280 --> 07:57:36.620
I might pass hours in his presence, and he would never once turn his eyes in my direction,

07:57:37.160 --> 07:57:42.040
because I saw all his attentions appropriated by a great lady who scorned to touch me with

07:57:42.040 --> 07:57:46.600
the hem of her robes as she passed, who, if ever her dark and imperious eye fell on

07:57:46.600 --> 07:57:51.920
me by chance, would withdraw it instantly, as from an object too mean to merit observation.

07:57:53.000 --> 07:57:58.660
I could not unlove him, because I felt sure he would soon marry this very lady, because

07:57:58.660 --> 07:58:04.000
I read daily in her a proud security in his intentions respecting her, because I witnessed

07:58:04.000 --> 07:58:09.360
hourly in him a style of courtship which, if careless and choosing rather to be sought

07:58:09.360 --> 07:58:15.560
than to seek, was yet in its very carelessness captivating, and in its very pride irresistible.

07:58:16.720 --> 07:58:21.420
There was nothing to cool or banish love in these circumstances, though much to create

07:58:21.420 --> 07:58:27.140
despair. Much too, you will think, reader, to engender jealousy, if a woman in my position

07:58:27.140 --> 07:58:32.300
could presume to be jealous of a woman in Miss Ingram's. But I was not jealous, or

07:58:32.300 --> 07:58:37.680
very rarely. The nature of the pain I suffered could not be explained by that word. Miss

07:58:37.680 --> 07:58:43.180
Ingram was a mark beneath jealousy. She was too inferior to excite the feeling. Pardon

07:58:43.180 --> 07:58:49.460
the seeming paradox, I mean what I say. She was very showy, but she was not genuine. She

07:58:49.460 --> 07:58:54.840
had a fine person, many brilliant attainments, but her mind was poor, her heart barren by

07:58:54.840 --> 07:59:00.960
nature. Nothing bloomed spontaneously on that soil, no unforced natural fruit delighted

07:59:00.960 --> 07:59:06.940
by its freshness. She was not good. She was not original. She used to repeat sounding

07:59:06.940 --> 07:59:13.300
phrases from books. She never offered or had an opinion of her own. She advocated a high

07:59:13.300 --> 07:59:18.380
tone of sentiment, but she did not know the sensations of sympathy and pity. Tenderness

07:59:18.380 --> 07:59:24.680
and truth were not in her. Too often she betrayed this. By the undue vent she gave to a spiteful

07:59:24.680 --> 07:59:29.960
antipathy she had conceived against little Adèle, pushing her away with some contumilius

07:59:29.960 --> 07:59:35.140
epithet if she happened to approach her, sometimes ordering her from the room, and always treating

07:59:35.140 --> 07:59:40.400
her with coldness and acrimony. Other eyes besides mine watched these manifestations

07:59:40.400 --> 07:59:46.640
of character, watched them closely, keenly, shrewdly. Yes, the future bridegroom, Mr.

07:59:46.640 --> 07:59:52.340
Rochester himself, exercised over his intended a ceaseless surveillance, and it was from

07:59:52.340 --> 07:59:58.100
this sagacity, this guardedness of his, this perfect clear consciousness of his fair one's

07:59:58.100 --> 08:00:03.500
defects, this obvious absence of passion in his sentiments towards her, that my ever-torturing

08:00:03.500 --> 08:00:09.400
pain arose. I saw that he was going to marry her for family, perhaps political reasons,

08:00:09.800 --> 08:00:15.320
because her rank and connections suited him. I felt he had not given her his love, and

08:00:15.320 --> 08:00:20.600
that her qualifications were ill-adapted to win from him that treasure. This was the point.

08:00:21.140 --> 08:00:25.740
This was where the nerve was touched and teased. This was where the fever was sustained and

08:00:25.740 --> 08:00:32.060
fed. She could not charm him. If she had managed the victory at once, and

08:00:32.060 --> 08:00:36.840
he had yielded, and sincerely laid his heart at her feet, I should have covered my face,

08:00:37.220 --> 08:00:42.240
turned to the wall, and figuratively have died to them. If Miss Ingram had been a good

08:00:42.240 --> 08:00:47.980
and noble woman, endowed with force, fervour, kindness, sense, I should have had one vital

08:00:47.980 --> 08:00:53.760
struggle with two tigers, jealousy and despair. Then my heart torn out and devoured, I should

08:00:53.760 --> 08:00:59.280
have admired her, acknowledged her excellence, and been quiet for the rest of my days. And

08:00:59.280 --> 08:01:04.740
the more absolute her superiority, the deeper would have been my admiration, the more truly

08:01:04.740 --> 08:01:10.460
tranquil my quiescence. But as matters really stood, to watch Miss Ingram's efforts at

08:01:10.460 --> 08:01:15.700
fascinating Mr. Rochester, to witness their repeated failure, herself unconscious that

08:01:15.700 --> 08:01:21.640
they did fail, vainly fancying that each shaft hit the mark, and infatuatedly pluming herself

08:01:21.640 --> 08:01:27.200
on success, when her pride and self-complacency repelled further and further what she wished

08:01:27.200 --> 08:01:34.160
to allure, to witness this was to be at once under ceaseless excitation and ruthless restraint.

08:01:34.160 --> 08:01:40.560
Because when she failed, I saw how she might have succeeded. Arrows that continually glanced

08:01:40.560 --> 08:01:45.440
off from Mr. Rochester's breast, and fell harmless at his feet, might, I knew, if shot

08:01:45.440 --> 08:01:50.740
by a surer hand, have quivered keen in his proud heart, have called love into his stern

08:01:50.740 --> 08:01:57.360
eye and softness into his sardonic face, or better still, without weapons, a silent conquest

08:01:57.360 --> 08:02:03.480
might have been won. Why can she not influence him more when she is privileged to draw so

08:02:03.480 --> 08:02:09.480
near to him? I asked myself. Surely she cannot truly like him, or not like him with true

08:02:09.480 --> 08:02:16.040
affection. If she did, she need not coin her smile so lavishly, flash her glances so unremittingly,

08:02:16.340 --> 08:02:22.740
manufacture airs so elaborate, graces so multitudinous. It seems to me that she might, by merely

08:02:22.740 --> 08:02:27.620
sitting quietly at his side, saying little and looking less, get nigher his heart.

08:02:28.320 --> 08:02:33.280
I have seen in his face a far different expression from that which hardens it now, while she

08:02:33.280 --> 08:02:38.940
is so vivaciously accosting him. But then it came of itself. It was not elicited by

08:02:38.940 --> 08:02:45.100
meretricious arts and calculated manoeuvres, and one had but to accept it, to answer what

08:02:45.100 --> 08:02:50.300
he asked without pretension, to address him when needful, without grimace, and it increased,

08:02:50.660 --> 08:02:56.480
and grew kindlier and more genial, and warmed one like a fostering sunbeam. How will she

08:02:56.480 --> 08:03:01.520
manage to please him when they are married? I do not think she will manage it, and yet

08:03:01.520 --> 08:03:06.300
it might be managed, and his wife might, I verily believe, be the very happiest woman

08:03:06.300 --> 08:03:07.420
the sun shines on.

08:03:08.660 --> 08:03:13.920
I have not yet said anything condemnatory of Mr. Rochester's project of marrying for

08:03:13.920 --> 08:03:18.700
interest and connections. It surprised me when I first discovered that such was his

08:03:18.700 --> 08:03:23.800
intention. I had thought him a man unlikely to be influenced by motives so commonplace

08:03:23.800 --> 08:03:29.000
in his choice of a wife. But the longer I considered the position, education, etc. of

08:03:29.000 --> 08:03:34.060
the parties, the less I felt justified in judging and blaming either him or Miss Ingram

08:03:34.060 --> 08:03:39.200
for acting in conformity to ideas and principles instilled into them, doubtless from their

08:03:39.200 --> 08:03:44.640
childhood. All their class held these principles. I supposed, then, that they had reasons for

08:03:44.640 --> 08:03:50.020
holding them such as I could not fathom. It seemed to me that, were I a gentleman like

08:03:50.020 --> 08:03:55.140
him, I would take to my bosom only such a wife as I could love. But the very obviousness

08:03:55.680 --> 08:04:00.260
to the husband's own happiness offered by this plan convinced me that there must be

08:04:00.260 --> 08:04:04.880
arguments against its general adoption of which I was quite ignorant. Otherwise I felt

08:04:04.880 --> 08:04:07.520
sure all the world would act as I wished to act.

08:04:08.440 --> 08:04:13.440
But in other points, as well as this, I was growing very lenient to my master. I was forgetting

08:04:13.440 --> 08:04:18.720
all his faults, for which I had once kept a sharp look-out. It had formerly been my

08:04:18.720 --> 08:04:24.040
endeavour to study all sides of his character, to take the bad with the good, and from the

08:04:24.040 --> 08:04:30.540
trust weighing of both, to form an equitable judgment. Now I saw no bad. The sarcasm that

08:04:30.540 --> 08:04:35.540
had repelled, the harshness that had startled me once, were only like keen condiments in

08:04:35.540 --> 08:04:40.920
a choice dish. Their presence was pungent, but their absence would be felt as comparatively

08:04:40.920 --> 08:04:46.760
insipid. And as for the vague something, was it a sinister or a sorrowful, a designing

08:04:46.760 --> 08:04:51.800
or a desponding expression, that opened upon a careful observer now and then in his eye,

08:04:51.800 --> 08:04:57.380
and closed again before one could fathom the strange depth partially disclosed? That something

08:04:57.380 --> 08:05:02.320
which used to make me fear and shrink, as if I had been wandering amongst volcanic-looking

08:05:02.320 --> 08:05:08.560
hills, and had suddenly felt the ground quiver and seen it gape, that something I, at intervals,

08:05:08.780 --> 08:05:14.640
beheld still, and with throbbing heart, but not with palsied nerves. Instead of wishing

08:05:14.640 --> 08:05:20.140
to shun, I longed only to dare, to divine it, and I thought Miss Ingram happy because

08:05:20.140 --> 08:05:24.940
one day she might look into the abyss at her leisure, explore its secrets, and analyse

08:05:24.940 --> 08:05:31.240
their nature. Meantime, while I thought only of my master and his future bride, saw only

08:05:31.240 --> 08:05:36.560
them, heard only their discourse, and considered only their movements of importance, the rest

08:05:36.560 --> 08:05:41.160
of the party were occupied with their own separate interests and pleasures. The ladies

08:05:41.160 --> 08:05:46.300
Lin and Ingram continued to consort in solemn conferences when they nodded their two turbans

08:05:46.300 --> 08:05:52.320
and held up their forehands in confronting gestures of surprise or mystery or horror,

08:05:52.660 --> 08:05:58.300
according to the theme on which their gossip ran, like a pair of magnified puppets. Mild

08:05:58.300 --> 08:06:03.620
Mrs. Dent talked with good-natured Mrs. Eshton, and the two sometimes bestowed a courteous

08:06:03.620 --> 08:06:09.840
word or smile on me. Sir George Lin, Colonel Dent, and Mr. Eshton discussed politics or

08:06:09.840 --> 08:06:15.960
county affairs or justice business. Lord Ingram flirted with Amy Eshton. Louisa played and

08:06:15.960 --> 08:06:21.120
sang to and with one of the messers Lin, and Mary Ingram listened languidly to the gallant

08:06:21.120 --> 08:06:27.300
speeches of the other. Sometimes all, as with one consent, suspended their by-play to observe

08:06:27.300 --> 08:06:33.540
and listen to the principal actors, for, after all, Mr. Rochester and, because closely connected

08:06:33.540 --> 08:06:38.700
with him, Miss Ingram, were the life and soul of the party. If he was absent from the room

08:06:38.700 --> 08:06:43.520
an hour, a perceptible dullness seemed to steal over the spirits of his guests, and

08:06:43.520 --> 08:06:47.720
his re-entrance was sure to give a fresh impulse to the vivacity of conversation.

08:06:49.400 --> 08:06:54.800
The want of his animating influence appeared to be peculiarly felt on one day that he had

08:06:54.800 --> 08:07:00.300
been summoned to Millcote on business, and was not likely to return until late. The afternoon

08:07:00.300 --> 08:07:05.480
was wet. A walk the party had proposed to take to see a gypsy camp, lately pitched on

08:07:05.480 --> 08:07:11.120
a common beyond Hay, was consequently deferred. Some of the gentlemen were gone to the stables.

08:07:11.120 --> 08:07:15.880
The younger ones, together with the younger ladies, were playing billiards in the billiard-room.

08:07:16.460 --> 08:07:21.400
The dowagers Ingram and Lin sought solace in a quiet game at cards. Blanche Ingram,

08:07:21.620 --> 08:07:27.180
after having repelled by supercilious taciturnity some efforts of Mrs. Dent and Mrs. Eshton

08:07:27.180 --> 08:07:32.440
to draw her into conversation, had first murmured over some sentimental tunes and eras on the

08:07:32.440 --> 08:07:37.550
piano, and then, having fetched a novel from the library, had flung herself in haughty

08:07:37.550 --> 08:07:43.670
on a sofa, and prepared to beguile, by the spell of fiction, the tedious hours of absence.

08:07:44.510 --> 08:07:49.110
The room and house were silent. Only now and then the merriment of the billiard-players

08:07:49.110 --> 08:07:54.830
was heard from above. It was verging on dusk, and the clock had already given warning of

08:07:54.830 --> 08:07:59.230
the hour to dress for dinner, when little Adèle, who knelt by me in the drawing-room

08:07:59.230 --> 08:08:00.910
window-seat, suddenly exclaimed,

08:08:04.270 --> 08:08:09.670
I turned, and Miss Ingram darted forward from her sofa. The others, too, looked up from

08:08:09.670 --> 08:08:14.630
their several occupations, for at the same time a crunching of wheels and a splashing

08:08:14.630 --> 08:08:19.470
tramp of horse-hooves became audible on the wet gravel. A post-chase was approaching.

08:08:20.510 --> 08:08:25.650
"'What can possess him to come home in that style?' said Miss Ingram. He rode Monsieur

08:08:25.650 --> 08:08:30.210
the black horse, did he not, when he went out, and Pilot was with him. What has he done

08:08:30.210 --> 08:08:35.330
with the animals?' As she said this, she approached her tall person and ample garments

08:08:35.330 --> 08:08:40.630
so near the window that I was obliged to bend back almost to the breaking of my spine. In

08:08:40.630 --> 08:08:45.750
her eagerness she did not observe me at first, but when she did, she curled her lip and moved

08:08:45.750 --> 08:08:51.270
to another casement. The post-chase stopped. The driver rang the door-bell, and a gentleman

08:08:51.270 --> 08:08:57.110
alighted in travelling garb. But it was not Mr. Rochester. It was a tall, fashionable-looking

08:08:57.110 --> 08:08:58.530
man, a stranger.

08:08:59.390 --> 08:09:04.410
"'How provoking!' exclaimed Miss Ingram. "'You tiresome monkey!' apostrophising

08:09:04.410 --> 08:09:09.590
Adele, who perched you up in the window to give false intelligence. And she cast on me

08:09:09.590 --> 08:09:15.710
an angry glance, as if I were in fault. Some parlaying was audible in the hall, and soon

08:09:15.710 --> 08:09:20.870
the newcomer entered. He bowed to Lady Ingram, as deeming her the eldest lady present.

08:09:21.610 --> 08:09:26.970
"'It appears I come at an inopportune time, madam,' said he, when my friend Mr. Rochester

08:09:26.970 --> 08:09:32.310
is from home. But I arrive from a very long journey, and I think I may presume so far

08:09:32.310 --> 08:09:38.050
on old and intimate acquaintance as to install myself here till he returns. His manner was

08:09:38.050 --> 08:09:44.030
polite. His accent, in speaking, struck me as being somewhat unusual, not precisely foreign,

08:09:44.350 --> 08:09:50.250
but still not altogether English. His age might be about Mr. Rochester's, between thirty

08:09:50.250 --> 08:09:56.550
and forty. His complexion was singularly sallow. Otherwise he was a fine-looking man, at first

08:09:56.550 --> 08:10:01.870
quite especially. On closer examination you detected something in his face that displeased,

08:10:02.230 --> 08:10:07.890
or rather that failed to please. His features were regular, but too relaxed. His eye was

08:10:07.890 --> 08:10:13.090
large and well cut, but the life looking out of it was a tame vacant life. At least so

08:10:13.090 --> 08:10:16.850
I thought. The sound of the dressing-bell dispersed the

08:10:16.850 --> 08:10:22.470
party. It was not quite till after dinner that I saw him again. He seemed quite a disease.

08:10:22.470 --> 08:10:27.850
But I liked his physiognomy even less than before. It struck me as being at the same

08:10:27.850 --> 08:10:33.530
time unsettled and inanimate. His eye wandered, and had no meaning in its wandering. This

08:10:33.530 --> 08:10:39.710
gave him an odd look, such as I never remembered to have seen. For a handsome and not an unamiable

08:10:39.710 --> 08:10:44.950
looking man, he repelled me exceedingly. There was no power in that smooth-skinned face of

08:10:44.950 --> 08:10:50.770
a full oval shape, no firmness in that aquiline nose and small cherry mouth. There was no thought

08:10:50.770 --> 08:10:56.870
on the low even forehead, no command in the blank brown eye. As I sat in my usual nook,

08:10:57.150 --> 08:11:01.470
and looked at him with the light of the gerundoles on the pantalpiece beaming full over him,

08:11:01.770 --> 08:11:06.630
for he occupied an armchair drawn close to the fire, and kept shrinking still nearer

08:11:06.630 --> 08:11:12.470
as if he were cold, I compared him with Mr. Rochester. I think, with deference be it spoken,

08:11:12.830 --> 08:11:17.690
the contrast could not be much greater between a sleek gander and a fierce falcon, between

08:11:17.690 --> 08:11:23.610
a meek sheep and the rough-coated keen-eyed dog, its guardian. He had spoken of Mr. Rochester

08:11:23.610 --> 08:11:29.170
as an old friend. A curious friendship theirs must have been, a pointed illustration indeed

08:11:29.170 --> 08:11:35.050
of the old adage that extremes meet. Two or three of the gentlemen sat near him, and I

08:11:35.050 --> 08:11:39.770
caught at times scraps of their conversation across the room. At first I could not make

08:11:39.770 --> 08:11:44.670
much sense of what I had heard, for the discourse of Louisa Eshton and Mary Ingram, who sat

08:11:44.670 --> 08:11:50.970
confused the fragmentary sentences that reached me at intervals. These last were discussing

08:11:50.970 --> 08:11:56.350
the stranger. They both called him a beautiful man. Louisa said he was a love of a creature,

08:11:56.430 --> 08:12:01.970
and she adored him, and Mary instanced his pretty little mouth and nice nose as her ideal

08:12:01.970 --> 08:12:02.630
of the charming.

08:12:03.210 --> 08:12:12.150
"'And what sweet-tempered forehead he has!' cried Louisa. "'So smooth! None of those

08:12:12.150 --> 08:12:15.130
acid eye and smile!'

08:12:15.850 --> 08:12:20.710
And then, to my great relief, Mr. Henry Lyne summoned them to the other side of the room,

08:12:20.950 --> 08:12:24.290
to settle some point about the deferred excursion to Haycommon.

08:12:24.690 --> 08:12:29.890
I was now able to concentrate my attention on the group by the fire, and I presently

08:12:29.890 --> 08:12:34.490
gathered that the new-comer was called Mr. Mason. Then I learned that he was but just

08:12:34.490 --> 08:12:39.330
arrived in England, and that he came from some hot country, which was the reason doubtless

08:12:39.330 --> 08:12:44.210
his face was so sallow, and he sat so near the hearth, and wore a shirt-out in the house.

08:12:45.130 --> 08:12:50.790
Presently the words Jamaica, Kingston, Spanish Town, indicated the West Indies as his residence,

08:12:51.150 --> 08:12:55.610
and it was with no little surprise that I gathered ere long that he had first seen and

08:12:55.610 --> 08:13:00.650
become acquainted with Mr. Rochester. He spoke of his friend's dislike of the burning heats,

08:13:00.950 --> 08:13:05.590
the hurricanes, and the rainy seasons of that region. I knew Mr. Rochester had been

08:13:05.590 --> 08:13:11.690
Mrs. Fairfax had said so, but I thought the continent of Europe had bounded his wanderings.

08:13:11.990 --> 08:13:17.390
Till now I had never heard a hint given of visits to more distant shores. I was pondering

08:13:17.390 --> 08:13:22.870
these things when an incident, and a somewhat unexpected one, broke the thread of my musings.

08:13:23.430 --> 08:13:28.310
Mr. Mason, shivering as some one chanced to open the door, asked for more coal to be put

08:13:28.310 --> 08:13:32.970
on the fire, which had burnt out its flame, though its mass of cinder still shone hot

08:13:32.970 --> 08:13:38.630
and red. The footman who had brought the coal in going out stopped near Mr. Eshton's chair,

08:13:38.970 --> 08:13:43.950
and said something to him in a low voice, of which I heard only the words, Old Woman,

08:13:44.310 --> 08:13:45.190
quite troublesome.

08:13:46.150 --> 08:13:50.230
"'Tell her she shall be put in the stocks if she does not take herself off,' replied

08:13:50.230 --> 08:13:50.850
the magistrate.

08:13:51.530 --> 08:13:56.250
"'No stop,' interrupted Colonel Dent. "'Don't send her away, Eshton. We might turn the

08:13:56.250 --> 08:14:01.710
thing to account. Better consult the ladies.' And speaking aloud, he continued, "'Ladies,

08:14:01.710 --> 08:14:06.470
you talked of going to Hay Common to visit the gypsy camp. Sam here says that one of

08:14:06.470 --> 08:14:10.870
the old mother-bunches is in the servants' hall at this moment, and insists upon being

08:14:10.870 --> 08:14:15.790
brought in before the quality to tell them their fortunes. Would you like to see her?'

08:14:15.790 --> 08:14:20.590
"'Surely, Colonel,' cried Lady Ingram, "'you would not encourage such a low imposter.

08:14:21.190 --> 08:14:23.790
Dismiss her by all means at once.'

08:14:23.790 --> 08:14:29.290
"'I cannot persuade her to go away, my lady,' said the footman, "'nor can any of the servants.

08:14:29.770 --> 08:14:35.170
Mrs. Fairfax is with her just now, entreating her to be gone. But she has taken a chair

08:14:35.170 --> 08:14:39.630
in the chimney-corner, and says nothing shall stir her from it till she gets leave to come

08:14:39.630 --> 08:14:40.930
in here.'

08:14:40.930 --> 08:14:43.730
"'What does she want?' asked Mrs. Eshton.

08:14:44.470 --> 08:14:49.130
"'To tell the gentry their fortunes,' she says, ma'am. She swears she must and will

08:14:49.130 --> 08:14:50.050
do it.'

08:14:50.050 --> 08:14:53.390
"'What does she like?' inquired the Mrs. Eshton, in a breath.

08:14:54.090 --> 08:14:58.190
"'A shockingly ugly old creature, Miss, almost as black as a croc.'

08:14:58.790 --> 08:15:02.010
"'Why, she's a real sorceress,' cried Frederick Lynn.

08:15:02.050 --> 08:15:04.490
"'Let us have her in, of course.'

08:15:04.490 --> 08:15:06.210
"'To be sure,' rejoined his brother,

08:15:06.230 --> 08:15:09.830
"'it would be a thousand pities to throw away such a chance of fun.'

08:15:10.890 --> 08:15:14.650
"'My dear boys, what are you thinking about?' exclaimed Mrs. Lynn.

08:15:15.130 --> 08:15:20.770
"'I cannot possibly countenance any such inconsistent proceeding,' chimed in the dowager Ingram.

08:15:21.470 --> 08:15:25.830
"'Indeed, ma'am, but you can, and will,' pronounced the haughty voice of Blanche,

08:15:25.830 --> 08:15:32.110
as she turned round on the piano-stool, where till now she had sat silent, apparently examining

08:15:32.110 --> 08:15:33.470
sundry sheets of music.

08:15:34.010 --> 08:15:39.270
"'I have a curiosity to hear my fortune told. Therefore, Sam, order the beldame forward.'

08:15:40.070 --> 08:15:42.470
"'My darling Blanche, recollect.'

08:15:42.990 --> 08:15:48.430
"'I do. I recollect all you can suggest, and I must have my will. Quick, Sam.'

08:15:48.430 --> 08:15:52.370
"'Yes, yes, yes,' cried all the juveniles, both ladies and gentlemen.

08:15:52.630 --> 08:15:54.790
"'Let her come. It will be excellent sport.'

08:15:55.630 --> 08:15:57.210
The footman still lingered.

08:15:57.430 --> 08:15:59.690
"'She looks such a rough one,' said he.

08:16:00.410 --> 08:16:03.490
"'Go!' ejaculated Miss Ingram. And the man went.

08:16:04.550 --> 08:16:07.050
Excitement instantly seized the whole party.

08:16:07.430 --> 08:16:11.310
A running fire of raillery and jests was proceeding when Sam returned.

08:16:12.250 --> 08:16:14.070
"'She won't come now,' said he.

08:16:14.390 --> 08:16:17.530
"'She says it's not her mission to appear before the vulgar herd.

08:16:17.930 --> 08:16:21.830
"'Them's her words. I must show her into a room by herself,

08:16:21.830 --> 08:16:25.270
and then those who wish to consult her must go to her one by one.'

08:16:26.250 --> 08:16:29.150
"'You see now, my queenly Blanche,' began Lady Ingram.

08:16:29.530 --> 08:16:32.950
"'She encroaches. Be advised, my angel girl, and—'

08:16:33.270 --> 08:16:36.350
"'Show her into the library, of course,' cut in the angel girl.

08:16:36.430 --> 08:16:40.090
"'It is not my mission to listen to her before the vulgar herd, either.

08:16:40.370 --> 08:16:44.310
I mean to have her all to myself. Is there a fire in the library?'

08:16:45.270 --> 08:16:47.790
"'Yes, ma'am. But she looks such a tinkler.'

08:16:48.410 --> 08:16:50.990
"'Cease that chatter, blockhead, and do my bidding.'

08:16:51.950 --> 08:16:56.770
Again Sam vanished, and mystery, animation, expectation rose to full

08:16:56.770 --> 08:17:01.510
flow once more. "'She's ready now,' said the footman, as he reappeared.

08:17:01.810 --> 08:17:04.250
"'She wishes to know who will be her first visitor.'

08:17:05.250 --> 08:17:09.350
"'I think I had better just look in upon her before any of the ladies go,'

08:17:09.350 --> 08:17:12.850
said Colonel Dent. "'Tell her Sam a gentleman is coming.'

08:17:13.830 --> 08:17:18.730
Sam went, and returned. "'She says, sir, that she'll have no gentleman.

08:17:18.730 --> 08:17:21.470
They need not trouble themselves to come near her.'

08:17:21.910 --> 08:17:24.830
Nor,' he added with difficulty, suppressing a titter,

08:17:25.110 --> 08:17:28.630
"'any ladies either, except the young and the single.'

08:17:29.730 --> 08:17:35.130
"'By Jove, she has taste!' exclaimed Henry Lynn. Miss Ingram rose solemnly.

08:17:35.530 --> 08:17:39.690
"'I go first,' she said, in a tone which might have befitted the leader

08:17:39.690 --> 08:17:43.730
of A Forlorn Hope, mounting a breach in the van of his men.

08:17:44.450 --> 08:17:49.630
"'Oh, my best, oh, my dearest, pause, reflect!' was her mamma's cry.

08:17:50.010 --> 08:17:53.910
But she swept past her in stately silence, passed through the door,

08:17:54.050 --> 08:17:57.450
which Colonel Dent held open, and we heard her enter the library.

08:17:58.250 --> 08:18:02.890
A comparative silence ensued. Lady Ingram thought it lecar to ring her

08:18:02.890 --> 08:18:07.510
hands, which she did accordingly. Miss Mary declared she felt for her

08:18:07.510 --> 08:18:12.050
part she never dared venture. Amy and Louisa Ashton tittered under their

08:18:12.050 --> 08:18:16.470
breath, and looked a little frightened. The minutes passed very slowly.

08:18:16.810 --> 08:18:20.970
Fifteen were counted before the library door again opened. Miss Ingram

08:18:20.970 --> 08:18:25.190
returned to us through the arch. Would she laugh? Would she take it as a

08:18:25.190 --> 08:18:30.390
joke? All eyes met her with a glance of eager curiosity, and she met all

08:18:30.390 --> 08:18:34.530
eyes with one of rebuff and coldness. She looked neither flurried nor merry.

08:18:34.890 --> 08:18:38.130
She walked stiffly to her seat, and took it in silence.

08:18:38.870 --> 08:18:40.990
"'Well, Blanche?' said Lord Ingram.

08:18:41.550 --> 08:18:43.930
"'What did she say, sister?' asked Mary.

08:18:44.490 --> 08:18:48.510
"'What do you think? How do you feel? Is she a real fortune-teller?'

08:18:48.510 --> 08:18:50.050
demanded the Mrs. Ashton.

08:18:50.650 --> 08:18:53.730
"'Now, now, good people,' returned Miss Ingram.

08:18:53.930 --> 08:18:57.970
"'Don't press upon me. Really, your organs of wonder and credulity are

08:18:57.970 --> 08:19:02.690
easily excited. You seem, by the importance of you all—my good mamma

08:19:03.270 --> 08:19:07.130
included—to ascribe to this matter, absolutely to believe that we have

08:19:07.130 --> 08:19:10.450
a genuine witch in the house who is in close alliance with the old

08:19:10.450 --> 08:19:15.230
gentleman. I have seen a gypsy vagabond, she has practised in hackneyed

08:19:15.230 --> 08:19:19.590
fashion the science of palmistry, and told me what such people usually

08:19:19.590 --> 08:19:24.470
tell. My whim is gratified, and now I think Mr. Ashton will do well to

08:19:24.470 --> 08:19:27.130
put the hag in the stocks to-morrow morning, as he threatened.'

08:19:28.210 --> 08:19:32.650
Miss Ingram took a book, lent back in her chair, and so declined further

08:19:32.650 --> 08:19:37.550
conversation. I watched her for nearly half an hour. During all that time

08:19:37.550 --> 08:19:41.410
she never turned a page, and her face grew momentarily darker, more

08:19:41.410 --> 08:19:46.450
dissatisfied, and more sourly expressive of disappointment. She had

08:19:46.450 --> 08:19:50.390
obviously not heard anything to her advantage, and it seemed to me from

08:19:50.390 --> 08:19:54.630
her prolonged fit of gloom and taciturnity that she herself, notwithstanding

08:19:55.150 --> 08:19:58.570
her professed indifference, attached undue importance to

08:19:59.290 --> 08:20:04.750
had been made her. Meantime Mary Ingram, Amy, and Louisa Ashton declared

08:20:04.750 --> 08:20:09.250
they dared not go alone, and yet they all wished to go. A negotiation

08:20:09.250 --> 08:20:13.070
was opened through the medium of the Ambassador, Sam, and after much

08:20:13.070 --> 08:20:17.190
pacing to and fro, till I think the said Sam's calves must have ached

08:20:17.190 --> 08:20:20.830
with the exercise, permission was at last, with great difficulty,

08:20:21.330 --> 08:20:24.830
extorted from the rigorous Sybil, for the three to wait upon her in a

08:20:24.830 --> 08:20:29.710
Their visit was not so still as Miss Ingram's had been. We heard

08:20:29.710 --> 08:20:33.430
hysterical giggling, and little shrieks proceeding from the library,

08:20:33.710 --> 08:20:36.910
and at the end of about twenty minutes they burst the door open and

08:20:36.910 --> 08:20:40.470
came running across the hall, as if they were half scared out of their

08:20:40.470 --> 08:20:40.910
wits.

08:20:41.450 --> 08:20:45.090
"'I am sure she is something not right,' they cried, one and all.

08:20:45.270 --> 08:20:49.590
"'She told us such things. She knows all about us.' And they sank

08:20:49.590 --> 08:20:52.690
breathless into the various seats the gentlemen hastened to bring

08:20:52.690 --> 08:20:57.610
them. Pressed for further explanation, they declared she had told

08:20:57.610 --> 08:21:00.650
them of things they had said and done when they were mere children,

08:21:01.290 --> 08:21:04.430
described books and ornaments they had in their bidoires at home,

08:21:04.850 --> 08:21:08.550
keepsakes that different relations had presented to them. They had

08:21:08.550 --> 08:21:12.510
affirmed that she had even divined their thoughts, and had whispered

08:21:12.510 --> 08:21:16.210
in the ear of each the name of the person she liked best in the world,

08:21:16.550 --> 08:21:20.610
and informed them of what they wished for most. Here the gentlemen

08:21:20.610 --> 08:21:24.130
interposed with earnest petitions to be further enlightened on these

08:21:24.130 --> 08:21:28.830
two last-named points, but they got only blushes, ejaculations, tremors

08:21:28.830 --> 08:21:33.190
and titters in return for their importunity. The matrons, meantime,

08:21:33.490 --> 08:21:37.610
offered vinaigrettes and wielded fans, and again and again reiterated

08:21:37.610 --> 08:21:41.330
the expression of their concern that their warning had not been taken

08:21:41.330 --> 08:21:45.410
in time. And the elder gentlemen laughed, and the younger urged their

08:21:45.410 --> 08:21:50.010
services on the agitated fair ones. In the midst of the tumult, and

08:21:50.010 --> 08:21:53.810
while my eyes and ears were fully engaged in the scene before me, I

08:21:53.810 --> 08:21:57.890
heard a hem close at my elbow. I turned, and saw Sam.

08:21:58.850 --> 08:22:02.450
If you please, Miss, the gypsy declares that there is another young

08:22:02.450 --> 08:22:06.290
single lady in the room who has not been to her yet, and she swears she

08:22:06.290 --> 08:22:10.410
will not go till she has seen all. I thought it must be you. There is

08:22:10.410 --> 08:22:12.850
no one else for it. What shall I tell her?

08:22:13.650 --> 08:22:17.490
Oh, I will go by all means, I answered, and I was glad of the

08:22:17.490 --> 08:22:22.370
unexpected opportunity to gratify my much excited curiosity. I slipped

08:22:22.370 --> 08:22:26.410
out of the room, unobserved by any eye, for the company were gathered in

08:22:26.410 --> 08:22:30.330
one mass about the trembling trio just returned, and I closed the door

08:22:30.330 --> 08:22:31.530
quietly behind me.

08:22:32.050 --> 08:22:35.950
If you like, Miss, said Sam, I'll wait in the hall for you, and if she

08:22:35.950 --> 08:22:39.950
frightens you, just call and I'll come in. No, Sam, return to the

08:22:39.950 --> 08:22:42.090
kitchen. I am not in the least afraid.

08:22:42.730 --> 08:22:46.270
Nor was I, but I was a good deal interested and excited.

08:23:09.650 --> 08:23:12.450
CHAPTER XIX.

08:23:13.770 --> 08:23:19.330
The library looked tranquil enough as I entered it, and the Sibyl, if Sibyl she

08:23:19.330 --> 08:23:24.950
were, was seated snugly enough in an easy chair at the chimney corner. She had on a

08:23:24.950 --> 08:23:30.370
red cloak and a black bonnet, or rather a broad brim gypsy hat tied down with a

08:23:30.370 --> 08:23:35.130
striped handkerchief under her chin. An extinguished candle stood on the table.

08:23:35.650 --> 08:23:40.270
She was bending over the fire and seemed reading in a little black book, like a

08:23:40.270 --> 08:23:45.970
book by the light of the blaze. She muttered the words to herself as most old

08:23:45.970 --> 08:23:51.090
women do while she read. She did not desist immediately on my entrance. It

08:23:51.090 --> 08:23:55.350
appeared she wished to finish a paragraph. I stood on the rug and warmed

08:23:55.350 --> 08:23:59.230
my hands, which were rather cold with sitting at a distance from the drawing

08:23:59.230 --> 08:24:05.030
room fire. I felt now as composed as ever I did in my life. There was nothing

08:24:05.030 --> 08:24:10.070
indeed in the gypsy's appearance to trouble one's calm. She shut her book and

08:24:10.070 --> 08:24:15.690
slowly looked up. Her hat brim partially shaded her face, yet I could see as she

08:24:15.690 --> 08:24:21.830
raised it that it was a strange one. It looked all brown and black. Elf-locks

08:24:21.830 --> 08:24:25.870
bristled out from beneath a white band which passed under her chin and came

08:24:25.870 --> 08:24:31.610
half over her cheeks, or rather jaws. Her eyes confronted me at once with a bold

08:24:31.610 --> 08:24:32.650
and direct gaze.

08:24:33.270 --> 08:24:39.850
Well, and you want your fortune told? She said in a voice as decided as her glance,

08:24:40.090 --> 08:24:45.210
as harsh as her features. I don't care about it, mother. You may please

08:24:45.210 --> 08:24:51.470
yourself, but I ought to warn you. I have no faith. It's like your impotence to say

08:24:51.470 --> 08:24:57.210
so. I expect it of you. I heard it in your step as you crossed the threshold.

08:24:57.970 --> 08:25:05.130
Did you? You have a quick ear. I have, and a quick eye, and a quick brain. You need

08:25:05.130 --> 08:25:10.970
them all in your trade. I do, especially when I've customers like you to deal

08:25:10.970 --> 08:25:20.090
with. Why don't you tremble? I'm not cold. Why don't you turn pale? I am not sick.

08:25:20.090 --> 08:25:28.910
Why don't you consult my art? I'm not silly. The old crone knickered a laugh

08:25:28.910 --> 08:25:33.770
under her bonnet and bandage. She then drew out a short black pipe, and lighting

08:25:33.770 --> 08:25:39.030
it began to smoke. Having indulged a while in this sedative, she raised her

08:25:39.030 --> 08:25:43.730
bent body, took the pipe from her lips, and while gazing steadily at the fire,

08:25:43.730 --> 08:25:53.750
said very deliberately, You are cold, you are sick, and you are silly. Prove it, I

08:25:53.750 --> 08:26:02.530
rejoined. I will, in a few words. You are cold because you are alone. No contact

08:26:02.530 --> 08:26:07.920
strikes the fire from you that is in you. You are sick because the best of

08:26:07.920 --> 08:26:14.360
things, the highest and sweetest given to man, keeps far away from you. You are

08:26:14.360 --> 08:26:20.040
silly because you suffer as you may. You will not beckon it to approach, nor will

08:26:20.040 --> 08:26:26.540
you stir one step to meet it where it waits you. She again put her short black

08:26:26.540 --> 08:26:32.560
pipe to her lips, and renewed her smoking with vigor. You might say all that to

08:26:32.560 --> 08:26:37.900
almost anyone who you knew lived as a solitary dependent in a great house. I

08:26:37.900 --> 08:26:44.340
might say it to almost anyone, but would it be true of almost anyone? In my

08:26:44.340 --> 08:26:51.280
circumstances? Yes, just so, in your circumstances, but find me another

08:26:51.280 --> 08:26:58.260
precisely placed as you are. It would be easy to find you thousands. You could

08:26:58.260 --> 08:27:04.760
scarcely find me one. If you knew it, you are peculiarly situated. Very near

08:27:04.760 --> 08:27:12.680
happiness, yes, within reach of it. The materials are all prepared. There only

08:27:12.680 --> 08:27:19.660
wants a movement to combine them. Chance laid them somewhat apart. Let them be

08:27:19.660 --> 08:27:27.020
once approached, and bliss results. I don't understand enigmas. I never could

08:27:27.020 --> 08:27:33.580
guess a riddle in my life. If you wish me to speak more plainly, show me your palm.

08:27:34.560 --> 08:27:41.480
And I must cross it with silver, I suppose? To be sure. I gave her a shilling.

08:27:42.320 --> 08:27:46.840
She put it into an old stocking-foot, which she took out of her pocket, and

08:27:46.840 --> 08:27:52.680
having tied it round and returned it, she told me to hold out my hand. I did. She

08:27:52.680 --> 08:27:58.400
arched her face to the palm, and poured over it without touching it. It is too

08:27:58.960 --> 08:28:06.700
said she. I can make nothing of such a hand as that, almost without lines. Besides,

08:28:07.140 --> 08:28:16.260
what is in a palm? Destiny is not written there. I believe you, said I. No, she

08:28:16.260 --> 08:28:23.080
continued. It is in the face, on the forehead, about the eyes, in the lines of

08:28:23.080 --> 08:28:30.440
the mouth. Kneel and lift up your head. Ah, now you are coming to reality, I said

08:28:30.440 --> 08:28:35.900
as I obeyed her. I shall begin to put some faith in you presently. I knelt

08:28:35.900 --> 08:28:40.080
within half a yard of her. She stirred the fire so that a ripple of light broke

08:28:40.080 --> 08:28:45.060
from the disturbed coal. The glare, however, as she sat, only threw her face

08:28:45.060 --> 08:28:53.060
into deeper shadow. Mine, it illumined. I wonder with what feelings you came to me

08:28:53.060 --> 08:28:59.240
tonight, she said when she had examined me a while. I wonder what thoughts are

08:28:59.240 --> 08:29:03.900
busy in your heart during all the hours you sit in yonder room with the fine

08:29:03.900 --> 08:29:09.500
people flitting before you like shapes in a magic lantern, just as little

08:29:09.500 --> 08:29:14.280
sympathetic communion passing between you and them as if they were really mere

08:29:14.280 --> 08:29:22.980
shadows of human forms and not the actual substance. I feel tired

08:29:22.980 --> 08:29:30.960
often, sleepy sometimes, but seldom sad. Then you have some secret hope to boy

08:29:30.960 --> 08:29:37.740
you up and please you with whispers of the future? Not I. The utmost I hope is

08:29:37.740 --> 08:29:42.320
to save enough money out of my earnings to set up a school some day in a little

08:29:42.320 --> 08:29:48.980
house rented by myself. A mean nutriment for the spirit to exist on, and sitting

08:29:48.980 --> 08:29:55.640
in that window seat. You see, I know your habits. You have learned them from the

08:29:55.640 --> 08:30:03.360
servants. Ah, you think yourself sharp. Well, perhaps I have. To speak truth, I

08:30:03.360 --> 08:30:09.080
have an acquaintance with one of them, Mrs. Poole. I started to my feet when I

08:30:09.080 --> 08:30:14.260
heard the name. You have, have you? thought I. There is diablerie in the

08:30:16.660 --> 08:30:23.700
Don't be alarmed, continued the strange being. She is a safe hand, is Mrs. Poole.

08:30:24.000 --> 08:30:29.860
Close and quiet. Anyone may repose confidence in her. But as I was saying,

08:30:30.260 --> 08:30:35.200
sitting in that window seat, do you think of nothing but your future school? Have

08:30:35.200 --> 08:30:39.420
you no present interest in any of the company who occupy the sofas and chairs

08:30:39.420 --> 08:30:45.920
before you? Is there not one face you study, one figure whose movements you

08:30:45.920 --> 08:30:52.280
follow with at least curiosity? I like to observe all the faces and all the

08:30:52.280 --> 08:31:00.060
figures. But you never single one from the rest? Or it may be two? I do

08:31:00.060 --> 08:31:05.240
frequently, when the gestures or looks of a pair seem telling a tale. It amuses me

08:31:05.240 --> 08:31:14.220
watch them. What tale do you like best to hear? Oh, I have not much choice. They

08:31:14.220 --> 08:31:18.700
generally run on the same theme, courtship, and promise to end in the same

08:31:18.700 --> 08:31:26.840
catastrophe, marriage. And do you like that monotonous theme? Positively I don't

08:31:26.840 --> 08:31:33.480
care about it. It is nothing to me. Nothing to you? When lady, young and full

08:31:33.480 --> 08:31:39.480
of life and health, charming with beauty and endowed with the gifts of rank and

08:31:39.480 --> 08:31:50.080
fortune, sits and smiles in the eyes of a gentleman you... I what? You know. And

08:31:50.080 --> 08:31:56.040
perhaps think well of. I don't know the gentleman here. I have scarcely

08:31:56.040 --> 08:32:00.820
interchanged a syllable with one of them. And as to thinking well of them, I

08:32:00.820 --> 08:32:07.080
respectable and stately and middle-aged, and others young, dashing, handsome and

08:32:07.080 --> 08:32:11.360
lively. But certainly they are all at liberty to be the recipients of whose

08:32:11.360 --> 08:32:16.540
smiles they please, without my feeling disposed to consider the transaction of

08:32:16.540 --> 08:32:23.080
any moment to me. You don't know the gentleman here. You have not exchanged a

08:32:23.080 --> 08:32:29.500
syllable with one of them. Will you say that of the master of the house? He is

08:32:29.500 --> 08:32:36.460
not at home. A profound remark. A most ingenious quibble. He went to Millcote

08:32:36.460 --> 08:32:41.140
this morning, and will be back here tonight or tomorrow. Does that

08:32:41.140 --> 08:32:46.380
circumstance exclude him from the list of your acquaintance? Blot him, as it were,

08:32:46.480 --> 08:32:52.760
out of existence? No, but I can scarcely see what Mr. Rochester has to do with

08:32:52.760 --> 08:32:57.980
the theme you had introduced. I was talking of ladies smiling in the eyes of

08:32:57.980 --> 08:33:03.000
the gentleman, and of late so many smiles have been shed into Mr. Rochester's

08:33:03.000 --> 08:33:08.460
eyes that they overflow like two cups filled above the brim. Have you never

08:33:08.460 --> 08:33:14.580
remarked that? Mr. Rochester has a right to enjoy the society of his guests.

08:33:16.040 --> 08:33:21.300
No question about his right, but have you never observed that, of all the tales

08:33:21.300 --> 08:33:26.820
told here about matrimony, Mr. Rochester has been favoured with the most lively

08:33:26.820 --> 08:33:31.940
and the most continuous? The eagerness of a listener quickens the tongue of a

08:33:31.940 --> 08:33:36.860
narrator. I said this rather to myself than to the gypsy, whose strange talk,

08:33:37.020 --> 08:33:42.440
voice, manner, had by this time wrapped me in a kind of dream. One unexpected

08:33:42.440 --> 08:33:46.680
sentence came from her lips after another, till I got involved in a web of

08:33:46.680 --> 08:33:51.640
mystification, and wondered what unseen spirit had been sitting for weeks by my

08:33:52.320 --> 08:33:58.840
watching its workings, and taking record of every pulse. Eagerness of a listener,

08:33:59.740 --> 08:34:07.380
repeated she. Yes, Mr. Rochester has sat by the hour, his ear inclined to the

08:34:07.380 --> 08:34:12.920
fascinating lips that took such delight in their task of communicating, and Mr.

08:34:13.060 --> 08:34:18.220
Rochester was so willing to receive and looked so grateful for the pastime

08:34:18.220 --> 08:34:25.160
given him. You have noticed this? Grateful? I cannot remember detecting gratitude in

08:34:25.160 --> 08:34:32.440
his face. Detecting? You have analyzed then, and what did you detect if not gratitude?

08:34:33.460 --> 08:34:40.300
I said nothing. You have seen love, have you not, and looking forward you have

08:34:41.200 --> 08:34:49.560
and beheld his bride happy? Not exactly. Your witch's skill is rather at fault

08:34:49.560 --> 08:34:57.720
sometimes. What the devil have you seen then? Never mind. I came here to inquire,

08:34:57.780 --> 08:35:04.120
not to confess. Is it known that Mr. Rochester is to be married? Yes, and to

08:35:04.120 --> 08:35:10.980
beautiful Miss Ingram. Shortly? Appearances would warrant that conclusion,

08:35:11.520 --> 08:35:16.980
and no doubt, though with an audacity that once chastising out of you, you seem

08:35:16.980 --> 08:35:22.540
to question it, they will be a superlatively happy pair. He must love such

08:35:22.540 --> 08:35:29.060
a handsome, noble, witty, accomplished lady, and probably she loves him, or if

08:35:29.060 --> 08:35:34.800
not his purse, at least his purse. I know she considers the Rochester estate

08:35:34.800 --> 08:35:41.620
eligible to the last degree, though, God pardon me, I told her something on that

08:35:41.620 --> 08:35:46.700
point about an hour ago which made her look wondrous grave. The corners of her

08:35:46.700 --> 08:35:53.500
mouth fell half an inch. I would advise her black avest suitor to look out. If

08:35:53.500 --> 08:36:01.260
another comes with a longer or clearer rent roll, he's dished. But mother, I did

08:36:01.260 --> 08:36:06.820
not come to hear Mr. Rochester's fortune. I came to hear my own, and you have told

08:36:06.820 --> 08:36:15.020
me nothing of it. Your fortune is yet doubtful. When I examined your face, one

08:36:15.020 --> 08:36:21.420
trait contradicted another. Chance has meted you a measure of happiness, that I

08:36:21.420 --> 08:36:28.280
knew it before I came here this evening. She has laid it carefully on one side

08:36:28.280 --> 08:36:34.280
for you. I saw her do it. It depends on yourself to stretch out your hand and

08:36:34.280 --> 08:36:40.580
take it up, but whether you will do so is the problem I study. Kneel again on the

08:36:40.580 --> 08:36:48.220
rug. Don't keep me long. The fire scorches me. I knelt. She did not stoop

08:36:48.220 --> 08:36:54.720
towards me, but only gazed leaning back in her chair. She began muttering. The

08:36:54.720 --> 08:37:01.320
flame flickers in the eye. The eye shines like dew. It looks soft and full of

08:37:01.320 --> 08:37:08.400
feeling. It smiles at my jargon. It is susceptible. Impression follows

08:37:08.400 --> 08:37:15.680
impression through its clear sphere. Where it ceases to smile, it is sad. An

08:37:15.680 --> 08:37:22.360
unconscious lassitude weighs on the lid. That signifies melancholy resulting from

08:37:22.360 --> 08:37:29.700
loneliness. It turns from me. It will not suffer further scrutiny. It seems to deny

08:37:29.700 --> 08:37:35.120
by a mocking glance the truth of the discoveries I have already made. To

08:37:35.120 --> 08:37:40.680
disown the charge of both sensibility and chagrin, its pride and reserve only

08:37:40.680 --> 08:37:50.280
opinion. The eye is favorable. As to the mouth, it delights at times in laughter.

08:37:50.880 --> 08:37:56.720
It is disposed to impart all that the brain conceives. Though I dare say it would

08:37:56.720 --> 08:38:03.220
be silent on much the heart experiences. Mobile and flexible, it was never

08:38:03.220 --> 08:38:08.780
intended to be compressed in the eternal silence of solitude. It is a mouth which

08:38:08.780 --> 08:38:14.800
should speak much and smile often and have human affection for its interlocutor.

08:38:16.220 --> 08:38:23.420
That feature is too propitious. I see no enemy to a fortunate issue but in the

08:38:23.420 --> 08:38:29.660
brow. And that brow professes to say I can live alone if self-respect and

08:38:29.660 --> 08:38:37.080
circumstance require me so to do. I need not sell my soul to buy bliss. I have an

08:38:37.080 --> 08:38:42.320
inward treasure born with me which can keep me alive if all extraneous delights

08:38:42.320 --> 08:38:48.060
should be withheld or offered only at a price I cannot afford to give. The

08:38:48.060 --> 08:38:54.240
forehead declares reason sits firm and holds the reins and she will not let the

08:38:54.240 --> 08:39:00.100
feelings burst away and hurry her into wild chasms. The passions may rage

08:39:00.100 --> 08:39:06.820
furiously like true heathens as they are and the desires may imagine all sorts of

08:39:07.720 --> 08:39:14.460
but judgment shall still have the last word in every argument and the casting

08:39:14.460 --> 08:39:21.490
vote in every decision. Strong wind, earthquake, shock and fire may pass by

08:39:21.700 --> 08:39:28.210
but I shall follow the guiding of that still small voice which interprets the

08:39:28.210 --> 08:39:29.730
of conscience.

08:39:33.250 --> 08:39:42.050
Well said, forehead. Your declaration shall be respected. I have formed my plans,

08:39:42.910 --> 08:39:48.330
right plans I deem them, and in them I have attended to the claims of conscience,

08:39:48.790 --> 08:39:54.350
the counsels of reason. I know how soon youth would fade in the bloom parish,

08:39:54.350 --> 08:40:01.330
if in the cup of bliss offered but one drag of shame or one flavor of remorse

08:40:01.330 --> 08:40:08.290
were detected and I do not want sacrifice, sorrow, disillusion, such as not

08:40:08.290 --> 08:40:15.330
my taste. I wish to foster not to blight, to earn gratitude not to ring tears of

08:40:15.330 --> 08:40:22.890
blood, no nor of brine. My harvest must be in smiles, in endearments, in sweet.

08:40:22.890 --> 08:40:29.910
That will do. I think I rave in a kind of exquisite delirium. I should wish now to

08:40:29.910 --> 08:40:36.690
protract this moment ad infinitum but I dare not. So far I have governed myself

08:40:36.690 --> 08:40:42.390
thoroughly. I have acted as I inwardly swore I would act but further might try

08:40:42.390 --> 08:40:47.010
me beyond my strength. Rise, Miss Eyre, leave me, the play is played out.

08:40:49.410 --> 08:40:57.250
Where was I? Did I wake or sleep? Had I been dreaming? Did I dream still? The old

08:40:57.250 --> 08:41:03.270
woman's voice had changed, her accent, her gesture, and all were familiar to me

08:41:03.270 --> 08:41:09.170
as my own face in a glass, as the speech of my own tongue. I got up but did not

08:41:09.170 --> 08:41:16.670
go. I looked, I stirred the fire, and I looked again. But she drew her bonnet and

08:41:16.670 --> 08:41:23.090
bandage closer about her face, and again beckoned me to depart. The flame

08:41:23.090 --> 08:41:27.330
illuminated, her hand stretched out. Roused now and on the alert for

08:41:27.330 --> 08:41:32.830
discoveries, I at once noticed that hand. It was no more the withered limb of an

08:41:32.830 --> 08:41:37.970
eld than my own. It was a rounded supple member with smooth fingers

08:41:37.970 --> 08:41:43.310
symmetrically turned, a broad ring flashed on the little finger, and stooping

08:41:43.310 --> 08:41:49.330
forward, I looked at it and saw a gem I had seen a hundred times before. Again I

08:41:49.330 --> 08:41:54.910
looked at the face, which was no longer turned from me. On the contrary, the

08:41:54.910 --> 08:42:01.310
bonnet was doffed, the bandage displaced, the head advanced. Well, Jane, do you know

08:42:01.310 --> 08:42:13.290
me? asked the familiar voice. Only take off the red cloak, sir, and then, but the

08:42:13.290 --> 08:42:22.370
There then, off ye lendings. And Mr. Rochester stepped out of his disguise. Now, sir, what a strange idea.

08:42:23.030 --> 08:42:29.030
But well carried out, eh? Don't you think so? With the ladies you must have managed well.

08:42:29.410 --> 08:42:43.270
But not with you? You did not act the character of a gypsy with me. What

08:42:43.270 --> 08:42:49.570
you have been trying to draw me out. Or in. You have been talking nonsense to make me

08:42:49.570 --> 08:42:52.730
talk nonsense. It is scarcely fair, sir.

08:42:53.550 --> 08:42:55.210
Do you forgive me, Jane?

08:42:56.090 --> 08:43:02.250
I cannot tell till I have thought it all over. If, on reflection, I find I have fallen into

08:43:02.250 --> 08:43:07.150
no great absurdity, I shall try to forgive you. But it was not right.

08:43:08.230 --> 08:43:14.330
Oh, you have been very correct, very careful, very sensible.

08:43:15.230 --> 08:43:21.470
I reflected, and thought on the whole I had. It was a comfort, but indeed, I had been on

08:43:21.470 --> 08:43:26.410
my guard almost from the beginning of the interview. Something of masquerade I suspected.

08:43:27.130 --> 08:43:31.870
I knew gypsies and fortune-tellers did not express themselves as this seeming old woman

08:43:31.870 --> 08:43:38.570
had expressed herself. Besides, I had noted her feigned voice, her anxiety to conceal

08:43:38.570 --> 08:43:45.350
her features. But my mind had been running on Grace Poole, that living enigma, that mystery

08:43:45.350 --> 08:43:49.570
of mysteries as I considered her. I had never thought of Mr. Rochester.

08:43:50.790 --> 08:43:57.830
Well, he said, what are you musing about? What does that grave smile signify?

08:43:58.850 --> 08:44:04.570
Wonder and self-congratulations, sir. I have your permission to retire now, I suppose?

08:44:05.370 --> 08:44:10.070
No, stay a moment, and tell me what the people in the drawing-room yonder are doing.

08:44:11.310 --> 08:44:13.070
Discussing the gypsy, I dare say.

08:44:13.970 --> 08:44:16.870
Sit down. Let me hear what they said about me.

08:44:17.430 --> 08:44:22.830
I had better not stay long, sir. It must be near eleven o'clock. Oh, are you aware, Mr.

08:44:23.070 --> 08:44:26.570
Rochester, that a stranger has arrived here since you left this morning?

08:44:27.170 --> 08:44:32.710
A stranger? No. Who can it be? I expected no one. Is he gone?

08:44:33.670 --> 08:44:38.290
No. He said he had known you long, and that he could take the liberty of installing himself

08:44:38.290 --> 08:44:39.290
here till you returned.

08:44:39.890 --> 08:44:42.490
The devil he did! Did he give his name?

08:44:43.230 --> 08:44:49.050
His name is Mason, sir, and he comes from the West Indies. From Spanish town in Jamaica,

08:44:49.050 --> 08:44:55.650
I think. Mr. Rochester was standing near me. He had taken my hand, as if to lead me to

08:44:55.650 --> 08:45:02.890
a chair. As I spoke, he gave my wrist a convulsive grip. The smile on his lips froze. Apparently

08:45:02.890 --> 08:45:04.430
a spasm caught his breath.

08:45:06.130 --> 08:45:13.670
Mason, the West Indies, he said, in the tone one might fancy a speaking automaton to announce

08:45:13.670 --> 08:45:14.710
its single words.

08:45:15.210 --> 08:45:22.930
Mason, the West Indies, he reiterated, and he went over the syllables three times, growing

08:45:22.930 --> 08:45:27.970
in the interval of speaking whiter than ashes. He hardly seemed to know what he was doing.

08:45:28.530 --> 08:45:31.490
Do you feel ill, sir? I inquired.

08:45:32.270 --> 08:45:39.010
Jane, I've got a blow. I've got a blow, Jane, he staggered. Oh, lean on me, sir.

08:45:39.930 --> 08:45:43.350
Jane, you offered me your shoulder once before. Let me have it now.

08:45:44.270 --> 08:45:50.090
Yes, sir, yes, and my arm. He sat down and made me sit beside him.

08:45:50.790 --> 08:45:55.710
Holding my hand in both his own, he chafed it, gazing on me at the same time with the

08:45:55.710 --> 08:45:57.450
most troubled and dreary look.

08:45:58.490 --> 08:46:05.670
My little friend, said he, I wish I were in a quiet island with only you, and trouble

08:46:05.670 --> 08:46:09.250
and danger and hideous recollections removed from me.

08:46:09.910 --> 08:46:13.350
Can I help you, sir? I'd give my life to serve you.

08:46:14.630 --> 08:46:18.550
Jane, if aid is wanted, I'll seek it at your hands. I promise you that.

08:46:19.390 --> 08:46:24.170
Thank you, sir. Tell me what to do. I'll try at least to do it.

08:46:25.750 --> 08:46:30.290
Fetch me now, Jane, a glass of wine from the dining-room. They will be at supper there,

08:46:30.450 --> 08:46:32.910
and tell me if Mason is with them and what he is doing.

08:46:33.950 --> 08:46:39.590
I went. I found all the party in the dining-room at supper, as Mr. Rochester had said. They

08:46:39.590 --> 08:46:44.890
were not seated at table. The supper was arranged on the sideboard. Each had taken what he chose,

08:46:44.890 --> 08:46:49.390
and then stood about here and there in groups, their plates and glasses in their hands.

08:46:50.830 --> 08:46:56.870
Everyone seemed in high glee. Laughter and conversation were general and animated. Mr.

08:46:57.050 --> 08:47:01.810
Mason stood near the fire, talking to Colonel and Mrs. Dent, and appeared as merry as any

08:47:01.810 --> 08:47:02.370
of them.

08:47:02.930 --> 08:47:09.050
I filled a wine-glass. I saw Miss Ingram watch me frowningly as I did so. She thought I was

08:47:09.050 --> 08:47:15.290
taking a liberty, I dare say, and I returned to the library. Mr. Rochester's extreme pallor

08:47:15.290 --> 08:47:20.830
had disappeared, and he looked once more firm and stern. He took the glass from my hand.

08:47:21.730 --> 08:47:28.450
Here is to your health, minister and spirit, he said. He swallowed the contents and returned

08:47:28.450 --> 08:47:29.390
it to me.

08:47:29.950 --> 08:47:31.210
What are they doing, Jane?

08:47:32.170 --> 08:47:33.630
Laughing and talking, sir.

08:47:34.150 --> 08:47:38.850
They don't look grave and mysterious, as if they had heard something strange.

08:47:39.890 --> 08:47:42.930
Not at all. They are full of jests and gaiety.

08:47:43.570 --> 08:47:44.370
And Mason?

08:47:45.130 --> 08:47:46.710
He was laughing, too.

08:47:47.750 --> 08:47:51.790
If all these people came in a body and spat at me, what would you do, Jane?

08:47:53.070 --> 08:47:57.490
Turn them out of the room, sir, if I could. He half-smiled.

08:47:58.090 --> 08:48:03.870
But if I were to go to them, and they only looked at me coldly and whispered sneeringly

08:48:03.870 --> 08:48:08.730
amongst each other, and then dropped off and left me one by one, what then, would you go

08:48:08.730 --> 08:48:09.330
with them?

08:48:09.970 --> 08:48:14.310
I rather think not, sir. I should have more pleasure in staying with you.

08:48:14.750 --> 08:48:15.930
To comfort me?

08:48:17.150 --> 08:48:20.830
Yes, sir, to comfort you, as well as I could.

08:48:21.430 --> 08:48:24.750
And if they laid you under a ban for adhering to me?

08:48:24.750 --> 08:48:31.570
I probably should know nothing about their ban, and if I did, I should care nothing about it.

08:48:32.190 --> 08:48:34.470
Then you could dare censure for my sake.

08:48:35.130 --> 08:48:40.850
I could dare it for the sake of any friend who deserved my adherence, as you I am sure do.

08:48:42.170 --> 08:48:47.010
Go back now into the room, step quietly up to Mason, and whisper in his ear that Mr.

08:48:47.250 --> 08:48:52.010
Rochester has come and wishes to see him. Show him in here, and then leave me.

08:48:52.990 --> 08:48:54.110
Yes, sir.

08:48:55.050 --> 08:49:00.430
I did his behest. The company all stared at me as I passed straight among them. I sought

08:49:00.430 --> 08:49:06.230
Mr. Mason, delivered the message, and proceeded him from the room. I ushered him into the

08:49:06.230 --> 08:49:08.350
library, and then I went upstairs.

08:49:10.410 --> 08:49:15.510
At a late hour, after I had been in bed some time, I heard the visitors prepare to their

08:49:15.510 --> 08:49:19.730
chambers. I distinguished Mr. Rochester's voice, and heard him say,

08:49:19.730 --> 08:49:22.430
This way, Mason. This is your room.

08:49:23.690 --> 08:49:29.370
He spoke cheerfully. The gay tones set my heart at ease. I was soon asleep.

08:49:48.270 --> 08:49:48.750
XX.

08:49:52.850 --> 08:49:57.730
I had forgotten to draw my curtain, which I usually did, and also to let down my window

08:49:57.730 --> 08:49:58.170
blind.

08:49:58.690 --> 08:50:03.470
The consequence was that when the moon, which was full and bright, for the night was fine,

08:50:04.190 --> 08:50:08.930
came in her course to that space in the sky opposite my casement, and looked in at me

08:50:08.930 --> 08:50:13.270
through the unveiled panes, her glorious gaze roused me.

08:50:13.670 --> 08:50:18.710
Awakening in the dead of night, I opened my eyes on her disc, silver-white and crystal

08:50:18.710 --> 08:50:19.170
clear.

08:50:20.030 --> 08:50:22.310
It was beautiful, but too solemn.

08:50:23.330 --> 08:50:26.310
I half rose and stretched my arm to draw the curtain.

08:50:27.130 --> 08:50:28.970
Good God, what a cry!

08:50:29.750 --> 08:50:35.910
The night, its silence, its rest, was rent entwined by a savage, a sharp, a shrilly sound

08:50:35.910 --> 08:50:38.730
that ran from end to end of Thornfield Hall.

08:50:39.910 --> 08:50:45.290
My pulse stopped, my heart stood still, my stretched arm was paralyzed.

08:50:46.350 --> 08:50:48.270
The cry died and was not renewed.

08:50:49.210 --> 08:50:54.430
Indeed, whatever being uttered that fearful shriek could not soon repeat it.

08:50:54.930 --> 08:51:00.610
Not the widest-winged condor on the Andes could, twice in succession, send out such

08:51:00.610 --> 08:51:02.810
a yell from the cloud shrouding his airy.

08:51:03.410 --> 08:51:07.290
The thing delivering such utterance must rest ere it could repeat the effort.

08:51:08.430 --> 08:51:14.630
It came out of the third story, for it passed overhead, and overhead, yes, in the room just

08:51:14.630 --> 08:51:20.770
above my chamber ceiling, I now heard a struggle, a deadly one, it seemed, from the noise, and

08:51:20.770 --> 08:51:29.290
a half-smothered voice shouted, help, help, help, three times, rapidly, will no one come,

08:51:29.690 --> 08:51:35.710
it cried, and then, while the staggering and stamping went on wildly, I distinguished through

08:51:35.710 --> 08:51:40.250
plank and plaster, Rochester, Rochester, for God's sake, come.

08:51:41.670 --> 08:51:47.510
A chamber door opened, someone ran or rushed along the gallery, another step stamped on

08:51:47.510 --> 08:51:50.550
above, and something fell, and there was silence.

08:51:51.670 --> 08:51:56.850
I had put on some clothes, the horror shook all my limbs, I issued for my apartment.

08:51:58.270 --> 08:52:04.670
The sleepers were all aroused, ejaculations, terrified murmurs sounded in every room, door

08:52:04.670 --> 08:52:09.630
after door unclosed, one looked out and another looked out, the gallery filled.

08:52:10.450 --> 08:52:15.030
Gentlemen and ladies alike had quitted their beds, and, oh, what is it?

08:52:15.230 --> 08:52:15.930
Who is hurt?

08:52:15.930 --> 08:52:17.390
What has happened?

08:52:17.690 --> 08:52:18.330
Fetch a light.

08:52:18.890 --> 08:52:19.630
Is it fire?

08:52:20.270 --> 08:52:21.090
Are there robbers?

08:52:21.410 --> 08:52:22.550
Where shall we run?

08:52:23.310 --> 08:52:28.130
Was demanded confusedly on all hands, but for the moonlight, they would have been in

08:52:28.130 --> 08:52:33.930
complete darkness, they ran to and fro, they crowded together, some sobbed, some stumbled,

08:52:34.390 --> 08:52:36.410
the confusion was inextricable.

08:52:37.350 --> 08:52:43.010
Where the devil is Rochester, cried Colonel Dent, I cannot find him in his bed.

08:52:44.270 --> 08:52:51.890
Here, here, was shouted in return, be composed all of you, I'm coming, and the door at the

08:52:51.890 --> 08:52:57.130
end of the gallery opened, and Mr. Rochester advanced with a candle, he had just descended

08:52:57.130 --> 08:53:03.110
from the upper storey, one of the ladies ran to him directly, she seized his arm, it was

08:53:03.110 --> 08:53:03.870
Miss Ingram.

08:53:05.330 --> 08:53:12.230
What awful event has taken place, said she, speak, let us know the worst at once.

08:53:13.350 --> 08:53:19.710
Don't pull me down or strangle me, he replied, for the Mrs. Eshton were clinging about him

08:53:19.710 --> 08:53:25.730
now, and the two dowagers in vast white wrappers were bearing down on him like ships in full

08:53:25.730 --> 08:53:26.090
sail.

08:53:27.370 --> 08:53:33.650
All's right, all's right, he cried, it's a mere rehearsal of much ado about nothing,

08:53:34.290 --> 08:53:36.650
ladies keep off, for I shall wax dangerous.

08:53:37.970 --> 08:53:44.550
And dangerous he looked, his black eyes darted sparks, calming himself by an effort, he added,

08:53:45.210 --> 08:53:51.490
a servant has had the nightmare, that is all, she is an excitable nervous person, she construed

08:53:51.490 --> 08:53:56.030
her dream into an apparition or something of that sort, no doubt, and has taken a fit

08:53:56.030 --> 08:53:56.690
with fright.

08:53:57.470 --> 08:54:02.530
Now then, I must see you all back into your rooms, for till the house is settled she cannot

08:54:02.530 --> 08:54:08.330
be looked after, gentlemen have the goodness to set the ladies the example, Miss Ingram,

08:54:08.490 --> 08:54:15.150
I am sure you will not fail in evincing superiority to idle terrors, Amy and Louisa, return to

08:54:15.150 --> 08:54:22.110
your nests like a pair of doves as you are, Madame, to the dowagers, you will take cold

08:54:22.110 --> 08:54:25.550
to a dead certainty if you stay in this chill gallery any longer.

08:54:25.970 --> 08:54:32.330
And so, by dint of alternate coaxing and commanding, he contrived to get them all once more enclosed

08:54:32.330 --> 08:54:37.150
in their separate dormitories, I did not wait to be ordered back to mine, but retreated

08:54:37.150 --> 08:54:40.010
unnoticed, as unnoticed I had left it.

08:54:40.530 --> 08:54:46.610
Not however to go to bed, on the contrary, I began and dressed myself carefully, the

08:54:46.610 --> 08:54:51.390
sounds I had heard after the scream, and the words that had been uttered, had probably

08:54:51.390 --> 08:54:56.890
been heard only by me, for they had proceeded from the room above mine, but they assured

08:54:56.890 --> 08:55:00.830
me that it was not a servant's dream which had thus struck horror through the house,

08:55:01.160 --> 08:55:06.590
and that the explanation Mr. Rochester had given was merely an invention framed to pacify

08:55:06.590 --> 08:55:07.270
his guests.

08:55:08.630 --> 08:55:10.970
I dressed, then, to be ready for emergencies.

08:55:12.050 --> 08:55:16.990
When dressed, I sat a long time by the window, looking out over the silent grounds and silvered

08:55:16.990 --> 08:55:19.430
fields, and waiting for I knew not what.

08:55:20.350 --> 08:55:24.610
It seemed to me that some event must follow the strange cry, struggle, and call.

08:55:25.870 --> 08:55:28.330
No, stillness returned.

08:55:28.990 --> 08:55:34.570
Each murmur and movement ceased gradually, and in about an hour Thornfield Hall was again

08:55:34.570 --> 08:55:35.790
as hushed as a desert.

08:55:36.750 --> 08:55:40.070
It seemed that sleep and night had resumed their empire.

08:55:41.130 --> 08:55:42.790
Meantime, the moon declined.

08:55:43.350 --> 08:55:44.610
She was about to set.

08:55:45.190 --> 08:55:49.950
Not liking to sit in the cold and darkness, I thought I would lie down on my bed, dressed

08:55:49.950 --> 08:55:50.710
as I was.

08:55:51.370 --> 08:55:54.470
I left the window and moved with little noise across the carpet.

08:55:54.910 --> 08:55:59.410
As I stooped to take off my shoes, a cautious hand tapped low at the door.

08:56:00.310 --> 08:56:01.190
Am I wanted?

08:56:01.790 --> 08:56:02.530
I asked.

08:56:03.810 --> 08:56:04.650
Are you up?

08:56:04.970 --> 08:56:07.490
Asked the voice I expected to hear.

08:56:08.090 --> 08:56:10.110
Namely, my master's.

08:56:10.810 --> 08:56:11.430
Yes, sir.

08:56:12.170 --> 08:56:12.870
And dressed?

08:56:14.170 --> 08:56:14.690
Yes.

08:56:15.590 --> 08:56:17.070
Come out, then, quietly.

08:56:18.090 --> 08:56:19.350
I obeyed.

08:56:19.630 --> 08:56:22.090
Mr. Rochester stood in the gallery holding a light.

08:56:22.890 --> 08:56:24.090
I want you.

08:56:24.090 --> 08:56:24.870
He said.

08:56:25.690 --> 08:56:28.070
Come this way, take your time, and make no noise.

08:56:28.950 --> 08:56:30.010
My slippers were thin.

08:56:30.530 --> 08:56:32.970
I could walk the matted floor as softly as a cat.

08:56:33.830 --> 08:56:38.530
He glided up the gallery and up the stairs and stopped in the dark, low corridor of the

08:56:38.530 --> 08:56:39.630
fateful third story.

08:56:40.450 --> 08:56:42.330
I had followed and stood at his side.

08:56:43.250 --> 08:56:44.870
Have you a sponge in your room?

08:56:45.630 --> 08:56:46.950
He asked in a whisper.

08:56:48.070 --> 08:56:48.710
Yes, sir.

08:56:49.430 --> 08:56:51.670
And have you any salts, volatile salts?

08:56:52.510 --> 08:56:52.990
Yes.

08:56:53.620 --> 08:56:55.450
Go back and fetch both.

08:56:56.250 --> 08:57:02.050
I returned, sought the sponge on the washstand, the salts in my drawer, and once more retraced

08:57:02.050 --> 08:57:02.710
my steps.

08:57:03.450 --> 08:57:04.370
He still waited.

08:57:05.350 --> 08:57:06.970
He held a key in his hand.

08:57:07.490 --> 08:57:10.330
Approaching one of the small black doors, he put it in the lock.

08:57:10.810 --> 08:57:12.910
He paused and addressed me again.

08:57:14.170 --> 08:57:16.190
You don't turn sick at the sight of blood?

08:57:17.830 --> 08:57:19.250
I think I shall not.

08:57:19.610 --> 08:57:21.110
I have never been tried yet.

08:57:21.790 --> 08:57:26.570
I felt a thrill while I answered him, but no coldness and no faintness.

08:57:27.430 --> 08:57:30.030
Just give me your hand, he said.

08:57:30.570 --> 08:57:32.770
It will not do to risk a fainting fit.

08:57:34.050 --> 08:57:35.590
I put my fingers into his.

08:57:36.170 --> 08:57:38.710
Warm and steady was his remark.

08:57:39.410 --> 08:57:41.050
He turned the key and opened the door.

08:57:42.310 --> 08:57:47.550
I saw a room I remembered to have seen before, the day Mrs. Fairfax showed me over the house.

08:57:48.370 --> 08:57:54.090
It was hung with tapestry, but the tapestry was now looped up in one part, and there was

08:57:54.090 --> 08:57:56.670
a door apparent, which had then been concealed.

08:57:57.550 --> 08:58:00.510
This door was open, a light shone out of the room within.

08:58:00.910 --> 08:58:06.130
I heard thence a snarling, snatching sound, almost like a dog quarreling.

08:58:06.810 --> 08:58:12.330
Mr. Rochester, putting down his candle, said to me, Wait a minute, and he went forward

08:58:12.330 --> 08:58:13.410
to the inner apartment.

08:58:13.410 --> 08:58:19.610
A shout of laughter greeted his entrance, noisy at first, and terminating in Grace

08:58:19.610 --> 08:58:21.550
Poole's own goblin ha-ha.

08:58:22.570 --> 08:58:24.050
She then was there.

08:58:24.950 --> 08:58:30.050
He made some sort of arrangement without speaking, though I heard a low voice address him.

08:58:30.370 --> 08:58:32.610
He came out and closed the door behind him.

08:58:33.330 --> 08:58:39.030
Here, Jane, he said, and I walked around to the other side of a large bed, which with

08:58:39.030 --> 08:58:42.510
its drawn curtains concealed a considerable portion of the chamber.

08:58:42.970 --> 08:58:44.890
An easy chair was near the bedhead.

08:58:45.290 --> 08:58:48.770
A man sat in it, dressed with the exception of his coat.

08:58:49.410 --> 08:58:50.230
He was still.

08:58:50.730 --> 08:58:53.070
His head leant back, his eyes were closed.

08:58:53.990 --> 08:58:56.230
Mr. Rochester held a candle over him.

08:58:57.250 --> 08:59:02.650
I recognized in his pale and seemingly lifeless face the stranger Mason.

08:59:03.410 --> 08:59:08.510
I saw, too, that his linen on one side and one arm was almost soaked in blood.

08:59:09.330 --> 08:59:13.590
Hold the candle, said Mr. Rochester, and I took it.

08:59:14.010 --> 08:59:16.310
He fetched a basin of water from the washstand.

08:59:17.070 --> 08:59:19.110
Hold that, said he.

08:59:19.650 --> 08:59:20.530
I obeyed.

08:59:21.190 --> 08:59:25.530
He took the sponge, dipped it in, and moistened the corpse-like face.

08:59:26.230 --> 08:59:29.670
He asked for my smelling-bottle and applied it to the nostrils.

08:59:30.850 --> 08:59:33.110
Mr. Mason shortly unclosed his eyes.

08:59:33.550 --> 08:59:34.570
He groaned.

08:59:34.570 --> 08:59:39.610
Mr. Rochester opened the shirt of the wounded man, whose arm and shoulder were bandaged.

08:59:40.250 --> 08:59:42.770
He sponged away blood, trickling fast down.

08:59:44.550 --> 08:59:48.870
Is there immediate danger, murmured Mr. Mason.

08:59:50.750 --> 08:59:52.510
No, a mere scratch.

08:59:52.990 --> 08:59:54.390
Don't be so overcome, man.

08:59:54.490 --> 08:59:55.050
Bear up.

08:59:55.410 --> 08:59:57.350
I'll fetch a surgeon for you now myself.

08:59:57.730 --> 09:00:00.410
You'll be able to be removed by morning, I hope.

09:00:01.170 --> 09:00:02.670
Jane, he continued.

09:00:02.670 --> 09:00:03.550
Sir?

09:00:04.650 --> 09:00:10.350
I shall have to leave you in this room with this gentleman for an hour, or perhaps two hours.

09:00:11.390 --> 09:00:13.930
You will sponge the blood as I do when it returns.

09:00:14.610 --> 09:00:19.910
If he feels faint, you will put the glass of water on that stand to his lips and your salts to his

09:00:19.910 --> 09:00:23.150
nose. You will not speak to him on any pretext.

09:00:24.190 --> 09:00:29.450
And Richard, it will be at the peril of your life if you speak to her.

09:00:29.450 --> 09:00:34.910
Open your lips, agitate yourself, and I'll not answer for the consequences.

09:00:36.610 --> 09:00:40.790
Again the poor man groaned. He looked as if he dared not move.

09:00:41.170 --> 09:00:46.030
Fear, either of death or of something else, appeared almost to paralyze him.

09:00:46.770 --> 09:00:52.210
Mr. Rochester put the now bloody sponge into my hand, and I proceeded to use it as he had done.

09:00:53.050 --> 09:00:55.070
He watched me a second, then saying,

09:00:55.610 --> 09:00:57.390
Remember, no conversation.

09:00:58.150 --> 09:00:59.250
He left the room.

09:01:00.210 --> 09:01:04.070
I experienced a strange feeling as the key graded in the lock,

09:01:04.470 --> 09:01:07.110
and the sound of his retreating steps ceased to be heard.

09:01:07.990 --> 09:01:10.410
Here, then, I was, in the third story,

09:01:11.250 --> 09:01:13.530
fastened into one of its mystic cells.

09:01:14.670 --> 09:01:19.310
Night around me, a pale and bloody spectacle under my eyes and hands,

09:01:19.970 --> 09:01:23.070
a murderous hardly separated from me by a single door.

09:01:23.630 --> 09:01:25.450
Yes, that was appalling.

09:01:25.990 --> 09:01:31.350
The rest I could bear, but I shuddered at the thought of Grace Poole bursting out upon me.

09:01:32.490 --> 09:01:34.530
I must keep to my post, however.

09:01:34.790 --> 09:01:40.390
I must watch this ghastly countenance, these blue still lips forbidden to unclose,

09:01:40.950 --> 09:01:45.050
these eyes now shut, now opening, now wandering through the room,

09:01:45.430 --> 09:01:49.210
now fixing on me, and ever glazed with the dullness of horror.

09:01:49.830 --> 09:01:53.890
I must dip my hand again and again in the basin of blood and water,

09:01:53.890 --> 09:01:56.130
and wipe away the trickling gore.

09:01:57.030 --> 09:02:00.810
I must see the light of the unsnuffed candle wane on my employment.

09:02:01.490 --> 09:02:04.910
The shadows darken on the wrought antique tapestry round me,

09:02:05.310 --> 09:02:08.150
and grow black under the hangings of the vast old bed,

09:02:08.830 --> 09:02:12.370
and quiver strangely over the door of a great cabinet opposite,

09:02:13.250 --> 09:02:19.650
whose front, divided into twelve panels, bore in grim design the heads of the twelve apostles,

09:02:20.250 --> 09:02:23.770
each enclosed in its separate panel as in a frame.

09:02:23.890 --> 09:02:28.410
While above them at the top rose an ebon crucifix and a dying Christ.

09:02:29.790 --> 09:02:34.390
According, as the shifting obscurity and flickering gleam hovered here or glanced there,

09:02:34.810 --> 09:02:37.970
it was now the bearded physician Luke that bent over his brow,

09:02:38.470 --> 09:02:44.910
now St. John's long hair that waved, and anon the devilish face of Judas that grew out of the pain,

09:02:45.270 --> 09:02:49.170
and seemed gathering life and threatening a revelation of the arch-traitor,

09:02:49.570 --> 09:02:52.390
of Satan himself, in his subordinate's form.

09:02:53.730 --> 09:02:56.690
Amidst all this, I had to listen as well as watch,

09:02:57.210 --> 09:03:01.890
to listen for the movements of the wild beast, or the fiend in yonder side den.

09:03:02.670 --> 09:03:06.010
But since Mr. Rochester's visit, it seemed spellbound.

09:03:06.810 --> 09:03:10.350
All the night I heard but three sounds at three long intervals,

09:03:11.050 --> 09:03:18.550
a step-creek, a momentary renewal of the snarling canine voice, and a deep human groan.

09:03:20.610 --> 09:03:26.890
Then my own thoughts worried me. What crime was this that lived incarnate in this sequestered

09:03:26.890 --> 09:03:33.910
mansion, and could neither be expelled nor subdued by the owner? What mystery that broke out now in

09:03:33.910 --> 09:03:40.470
fire and now in blood at the deadliest hour of the night? What creature was it that masked in an

09:03:40.470 --> 09:03:47.450
ordinary woman's face and shape uttered the voice now of a mocking demon and anon of a carrion-seeking

09:03:47.450 --> 09:03:55.650
bird of prey? And this man I bent over, this commonplace, quiet stranger, how had he become

09:03:55.650 --> 09:04:02.230
involved in the web of horror? And why had the fury flown at him? What made him seek this quarter

09:04:02.230 --> 09:04:09.430
of the house at an untimely season, when he should have been asleep in bed? I had heard Mr. Rochester

09:04:09.430 --> 09:04:16.650
assign him an apartment below. What brought him here? And why now was he so tame under the violence

09:04:16.650 --> 09:04:22.850
or treachery done him? Why did he so quietly submit to the concealment Mr. Rochester enforced?

09:04:23.590 --> 09:04:30.970
Why did Mr. Rochester enforce this concealment? His guest had been outraged. His own life,

09:04:31.110 --> 09:04:36.350
on a former occasion, had been hideously plotted against, and both attempts he smothered in secrecy

09:04:36.350 --> 09:04:46.630
and sank in oblivion. Lastly, I saw Mr. Mason was submissive to Mr. Rochester, and that the

09:04:46.630 --> 09:04:52.390
over the inertness of the former. The few words which had passed between them assured me of this.

09:04:52.870 --> 09:04:58.250
It was evident that in their former intercourse the passive disposition of the one had been

09:04:58.250 --> 09:05:04.510
habitually influenced by the active energy of the other. Whence then had arisen Mr. Rochester's

09:05:04.510 --> 09:05:10.450
dismay when he heard of Mr. Mason's arrival? Why had the mere name of this unresisting individual,

09:05:10.450 --> 09:05:16.690
whom his word now suffice to control like a child, fallen on him a few hours since as a

09:05:16.690 --> 09:05:23.890
thunderbolt might fall on an oak? Oh, I could not forget his look and his paleness when he whispered,

09:05:23.910 --> 09:05:30.370
Jane, I have got a blow. I have got a blow, Jane. I could not forget how the arm had trembled which

09:05:30.370 --> 09:05:36.110
he rested on my shoulder, and it was no light matter which could thus bow the resolute spirit

09:05:36.110 --> 09:05:39.630
and thrill the vigorous frame of Fairfax Rochester.

09:05:41.530 --> 09:05:48.570
When will he come? When will he come? I cried inwardly as the night lingered and lingered,

09:05:48.950 --> 09:05:57.050
as my bleeding patient drooped, moaned, sickened, and neither day nor aid arrived. I had again and

09:05:57.050 --> 09:06:03.210
again held the water to Mason's white lips, again and again offered him the stimulating salts.

09:06:03.730 --> 09:06:09.130
My efforts seemed ineffectual. Either bodily or mental suffering, or loss of blood,

09:06:09.210 --> 09:06:17.150
or all three combined were fast prostrating his strength. He moaned so and looked so weak,

09:06:17.370 --> 09:06:22.930
wild, and lost. I feared he was dying, and I might not even speak to him.

09:06:25.470 --> 09:06:32.050
The candle, wasted at last, went out. As it expired, I perceived streaks of gray

09:06:32.050 --> 09:06:38.230
edging the window curtains. Dawn was then approaching. Presently, I heard pilot bark

09:06:38.230 --> 09:06:45.350
far below, out of his distant kennel in the courtyard. Hope revived, nor was it unwarranted.

09:06:45.790 --> 09:06:50.690
In five minutes more, the grating key, the yielding lock, warned me my watch was relieved.

09:06:51.230 --> 09:06:56.310
It could not have lasted more than two hours. Many a week has seemed shorter.

09:06:58.030 --> 09:07:01.590
Mr. Rochester entered, and with him the surgeon he had been to fetch.

09:07:02.750 --> 09:07:09.110
Now, Carter, be on the alert, he said to this last. I give you but half an hour for dressing

09:07:09.110 --> 09:07:15.730
the wound, fastening the bandages, getting the patient downstairs and all. But is he fit to move,

09:07:16.430 --> 09:07:22.650
sir? No doubt of it. It is nothing serious. He is nervous. His spirits must be kept up.

09:07:22.650 --> 09:07:28.010
Come, set to work. Mr. Rochester drew back the thick curtain,

09:07:28.370 --> 09:07:33.110
drew up the holland blind, let in all the daylight he could, and I was surprised and

09:07:33.110 --> 09:07:38.450
cheered to see how far dawn was advanced, what rosy streaks were beginning to brighten the east.

09:07:40.430 --> 09:07:43.450
Then he approached Mason, whom the surgeon was already handling.

09:07:45.470 --> 09:07:48.850
Now, my good fellow, how are you? He asked.

09:07:50.330 --> 09:07:58.350
She's done for me, I fear, was the faint reply. Not a whit. Courage. This day,

09:07:58.450 --> 09:08:03.050
fortnight, you'll hardly be a pin the worse of it. You've lost a little blood, that's all.

09:08:03.870 --> 09:08:10.490
Carter, assure him there's no danger. I can do that conscientiously, said Carter,

09:08:10.490 --> 09:08:15.050
who had now undone the bandages. Only I wish I could have got here sooner.

09:08:15.710 --> 09:08:21.310
He would not have bled so much. But how is this? The flesh on the shoulder is torn as well as cut.

09:08:21.730 --> 09:08:25.030
This wound was not done with a knife. There have been teeth here.

09:08:26.050 --> 09:08:34.890
She bit me, he murmured. She worried me like a tigress when Rochester got the knife from her.

09:08:35.810 --> 09:08:41.330
You should not have yielded. You should have grappled with her at once, said Mr. Rochester.

09:08:42.730 --> 09:08:49.730
But under such circumstances, what could one do, returned Mason. Oh, it was frightful,

09:08:49.910 --> 09:08:56.790
he added, shuddering. And I did not expect it. She looked so quiet at first.

09:08:58.350 --> 09:09:06.970
I warned you, was his friend's answer. I said, be on your guard when you go near her. Besides,

09:09:07.050 --> 09:09:12.090
you might have waited till tomorrow, and had me with you. It was mere folly to attempt the

09:09:12.090 --> 09:09:19.950
interview tonight and alone. I thought I could have done some good. You thought, you thought.

09:09:20.310 --> 09:09:24.370
Yes, it makes me impatient to hear you. But however, you have suffered,

09:09:24.910 --> 09:09:31.270
and are likely to suffer enough for not taking my advice. So I'll say no more. Carter, hurry,

09:09:31.770 --> 09:09:34.390
hurry. The sun will soon rise, and I must have him off.

09:09:35.530 --> 09:09:40.410
Directly, sir. The shoulder is just bandaged. I must look to this other wound in the arm.

09:09:40.850 --> 09:09:48.670
She has had her teeth here too, I think. She sucked the blood. She said she'd drain my heart,

09:09:49.390 --> 09:09:57.250
said Mason. I saw Mr. Rochester shudder. A singularly marked expression of disgust,

09:09:57.610 --> 09:10:02.610
horror, hatred warped his countenance almost to distortion. But he only said,

09:10:03.150 --> 09:10:09.390
Come, be silent, Richard, and never mind her gibberish. Don't repeat it. I wish I could forget

09:10:09.390 --> 09:10:16.690
it, was the answer. You will when you are out of the country, when you get back to Spanish Town.

09:10:16.690 --> 09:10:21.930
You may think of her as dead and buried, or rather, you need not think of her at all.

09:10:23.310 --> 09:10:25.350
Impossible to forget this night.

09:10:26.990 --> 09:10:32.170
It is not impossible. Have some energy, man. You thought you were as dead as a herring two

09:10:32.170 --> 09:10:38.590
hours since, and you are all alive and talking now. There. Carter has done with you, or nearly so.

09:10:39.110 --> 09:10:45.030
I'll make you decent in a trice. Jane. He turned to me for the first time since his re-entrance.

09:10:45.670 --> 09:10:51.210
Take this key. Go down to my bedroom and walk straight forward into my dressing room. Open

09:10:51.210 --> 09:10:56.270
the top drawer of the wardrobe and take out a clean shirt and a neck handkerchief. Bring them

09:10:56.270 --> 09:11:03.130
here and be nimble. I went, sought the repository he had mentioned, found the articles named,

09:11:03.210 --> 09:11:10.370
and returned with them. Now, said he, go to the other side of the bed while I order his toilet.

09:11:10.370 --> 09:11:16.070
But don't leave the room. You may be wanted again. I retired as directed.

09:11:17.770 --> 09:11:20.550
Was anybody below stirring when you went down, Jane?

09:11:21.170 --> 09:11:26.250
inquired Mr. Rochester presently. No, sir. All was very still.

09:11:28.050 --> 09:11:33.250
We shall get you off cannily, Dick, and it will be better, both for your sake and for that of the

09:11:33.250 --> 09:11:39.110
poor creature in Yonder. I have striven long to avoid exposure, and I should not like it to come

09:11:39.110 --> 09:11:46.650
last. Here, Carter, help him on with his waistcoat. Where did you leave your furred cloak? You can't

09:11:46.650 --> 09:11:52.930
travel a mile without that, I know, in this damned cold climate. In your room? Jane, run down to Mr.

09:11:53.150 --> 09:11:59.430
Mason's room, the one next mine, and fetch a cloak you will see there. Again I ran, and again

09:11:59.430 --> 09:12:05.510
returned, bearing an immense mantle lined and edged with fur. Now I have another errand for you,

09:12:06.310 --> 09:12:14.190
said my untiring master. You must away to my room again. What a mercy you are shod with velvet,

09:12:14.570 --> 09:12:21.310
Jane. A clod-hopping messenger would never do at this juncture. You must open the middle drawer of

09:12:21.310 --> 09:12:25.650
my toilet table and take out a little file and a little glass you will find there. Quick.

09:12:26.530 --> 09:12:32.810
I flew thither and back, bringing the desired vessels. That's well. Now, doctor, I shall take

09:12:32.810 --> 09:12:39.170
liberty of administering a dose myself, on my own responsibility. I got this cordial at Rome

09:12:39.170 --> 09:12:44.590
of an Italian charlatan, a fellow you would have kicked, Carter. It's not a thing to be used

09:12:45.110 --> 09:12:51.270
indiscriminately, but it is good upon occasion. As now, for instance, Jane a little water.

09:12:52.370 --> 09:12:56.890
He held out the tiny glass. I half filled it from the water bottle on the washstand.

09:12:56.890 --> 09:13:05.590
That will do. Now wet the lip of the file. I did so. He measured twelve drops of the crimson liquid

09:13:05.590 --> 09:13:11.170
and presented it to Mason. Drink, Richard. It will give you the heart you lack for an hour or so.

09:13:11.650 --> 09:13:20.170
But will it hurt me? Is it inflammatory? Drink, drink, drink. Mr. Mason obeyed because it was

09:13:20.170 --> 09:13:26.710
evidently useless to resist. He was dressed now. He still looked pale, but he was no longer gory

09:13:26.710 --> 09:13:31.210
and sullied. Mr. Rochester let him sit three minutes after he had swallowed the liquid.

09:13:31.810 --> 09:13:40.510
He then took his arm. Now, I am sure you can get on your feet, he said. Try. The patient rose.

09:13:41.370 --> 09:13:46.410
Carter, take him under the other shoulder. Be of good cheer, Richard. Step out. That's it.

09:13:47.370 --> 09:13:54.790
I do feel better, remarked Mr. Mason. I'm sure you do. Now, Jane,

09:13:54.790 --> 09:13:59.790
trip on before us away to the back stairs. Unbolt the side passage door and tell the

09:13:59.790 --> 09:14:04.810
driver of the post-chase you will see in the yard, or just outside, for I told him not to drive his

09:14:04.810 --> 09:14:10.270
rattling wheels over the pavement, to be ready, we are coming, and, Jane, if anyone is about,

09:14:10.490 --> 09:14:16.330
come to the foot of the stairs and hem. It was by this time half past five,

09:14:16.550 --> 09:14:21.330
and the sun was on the point of rising, but I found the kitchen still dark and silent.

09:14:21.910 --> 09:14:27.990
The side passage door was fastened. I opened it with as little noise as possible. All the yard

09:14:27.990 --> 09:14:33.870
was quiet, but the gates stood wide open, and there was a post-chase with horses ready harnessed

09:14:33.870 --> 09:14:39.950
and drivers seated on the box stationed outside. I approached him and said the gentlemen were coming.

09:14:40.350 --> 09:14:46.290
He nodded. Then I looked carefully round and listened. The stillness of early morning slumbered

09:14:46.290 --> 09:14:51.950
everywhere. The curtains were yet drawn over the servants' chamber windows. Little birds were

09:14:51.950 --> 09:14:56.950
just twittering in the blossom-blanched orchard trees, whose boughs drooped like white garland

09:14:56.950 --> 09:15:02.010
over the wall enclosing one side of the yard. The carriage horses stamped from time to time

09:15:02.010 --> 09:15:09.630
in their closed stables. All else was still. The gentlemen now appeared. Mason, supported by

09:15:09.630 --> 09:15:16.050
Mr. Rochester and the surgeon, seemed to walk with tolerable ease. They assisted him into the chase.

09:15:16.290 --> 09:15:17.350
Carter followed.

09:15:18.790 --> 09:15:25.290
Take care of him, said Mr. Rochester to the latter, and keep him at your house till he is quite well.

09:15:25.610 --> 09:15:30.490
I shall ride over in a day or two to see how he gets on. Richard, how is it with you?

09:15:31.430 --> 09:15:33.450
The fresh air revives me, Fairfax.

09:15:34.970 --> 09:15:39.530
Leave the window open on his side, Carter. There is no wind. Goodbye, Dick.

09:15:40.610 --> 09:15:41.090
Fairfax.

09:15:42.250 --> 09:15:43.490
Well, what is it?

09:15:44.270 --> 09:15:50.610
Let her be taken care of. Let her be treated as tenderly as may be. Let her...

09:15:51.690 --> 09:15:53.950
He stopped and burst into tears.

09:15:54.990 --> 09:16:02.890
I do my best, and have done it and will do it, was the answer. He shut up the chase door

09:16:02.890 --> 09:16:04.510
and the vehicle drove away.

09:16:05.930 --> 09:16:12.310
Yet would to God there was an end of all this, added Mr. Rochester as he closed and barred the

09:16:12.310 --> 09:16:18.950
yard gates. This done, he moved with slow step and abstracted air towards a door in the wall

09:16:18.950 --> 09:16:24.530
bordering the orchard. I, supposing he had done with me, prepared to return to the house.

09:16:25.290 --> 09:16:31.650
Again, however, I heard him call Jane. He had opened the portal and stood at it, waiting for me.

09:16:33.450 --> 09:16:37.810
Come where there is some freshness for a few moments, he said.

09:16:38.590 --> 09:16:42.210
That house is a mere dungeon. Don't you feel it so?

09:16:43.190 --> 09:16:45.930
It seems to me a splendid mansion, sir.

09:16:46.510 --> 09:16:51.030
The glamour of inexperience is over your eyes, he answered.

09:16:52.030 --> 09:16:56.510
And you see it through a charmed medium. You cannot discern that the gilding is

09:16:56.510 --> 09:17:02.330
slime and the silk drapery's cobwebs, that the marble is sordid slate and the polished wood

09:17:02.330 --> 09:17:09.670
merely refuse chips and scaly bark. Now here, he pointed to the leafy enclosure we had entered,

09:17:09.670 --> 09:17:17.170
is all real, sweet and pure. He strayed down a walk, edged with box, with apple trees,

09:17:17.350 --> 09:17:22.150
pear trees and cherry trees on one side, and a border on the other full of all sorts of

09:17:22.150 --> 09:17:28.490
old-fashioned flowers, stalks, sweet Williams, primroses, pansies, mingled with southern wood,

09:17:28.790 --> 09:17:35.410
sweet briar, and fragrant herbs. They were fresh now, as a succession of April showers and gleams

09:17:35.410 --> 09:17:40.950
followed by a lovely spring morning could make them. The sun was just entering the dappled east,

09:17:41.490 --> 09:17:45.950
and his light illumined the wreathed and dewy orchard trees that shone down the quiet walks

09:17:45.950 --> 09:17:54.290
under them. Jane, will you have a flower? He gathered a half-blown rose, the first on the

09:17:54.290 --> 09:18:02.510
bush, and offered it to me. Thank you, sir. And do you like this sunrise, Jane, that sky with

09:18:02.510 --> 09:18:09.150
high and light clouds which are sure to melt away as the day waxes warm, this placid and balmy

09:18:09.150 --> 09:18:19.050
atmosphere? I do very much. You have passed a strange night, Jane. Yes, sir. And it has made

09:18:19.050 --> 09:18:25.950
you look pale. Were you afraid when I left you alone with Mason? I was afraid of someone coming

09:18:25.950 --> 09:18:32.710
out of the inner room. But I had fastened the door. I had the key in my pocket. I should have

09:18:32.710 --> 09:18:39.870
been a careless shepherd if I had left a lamb, my pet lamb, so near a wolf's den, unguarded.

09:18:40.890 --> 09:18:46.370
You were safe. Will Grace Poole live here still, sir?

09:18:47.310 --> 09:18:51.510
Oh, yes. Don't trouble your head about her. Put the thing out of your thoughts.

09:18:52.850 --> 09:18:59.670
Yet it seems to me your life is hardly secure while she stays. Never fear. I will take care

09:18:59.670 --> 09:19:08.170
of myself. Is the danger you apprehended last night gone by now, sir? I cannot vouch for that

09:19:08.170 --> 09:19:15.030
till Mason is out of England, nor even then. To live for me, Jane, is to stand on a crater crust

09:19:15.030 --> 09:19:23.190
which may crack and spew fire any day. But Mr. Mason seems a man easily led. Your influence,

09:19:23.390 --> 09:19:29.090
sir, is evidently potent with him. He will never set you at defiance or willfully injure you.

09:19:30.590 --> 09:19:37.070
Oh, no. Mason will not defy me, nor, knowing it, will he hurt me. But unintentionally,

09:19:37.470 --> 09:19:44.650
he might in a moment by one careless word deprive me, if not of life, yet forever of happiness.

09:19:45.690 --> 09:19:51.970
Tell him to be cautious, sir. Let him know what you fear, and show him how to avert the danger.

09:19:53.330 --> 09:19:58.710
He laughed sardonically, hastily took my hand, and as hastily threw it from him.

09:19:59.950 --> 09:20:05.430
If I could do that, simpleton, where would the danger be? Annihilate it in a moment.

09:20:05.990 --> 09:20:11.190
Ever since I have known Mason, I have only to say to him, do that, and the thing has been done.

09:20:11.190 --> 09:20:17.090
But I cannot give him orders in this case. I cannot say beware of harming me, Richard,

09:20:17.710 --> 09:20:22.010
for it is imperative that I should keep him ignorant that harm to me is possible.

09:20:23.070 --> 09:20:29.670
Now you look puzzled, and I will puzzle you further. You are my little friend, are you not?

09:20:31.050 --> 09:20:34.850
I like to serve you, sir, and to obey you in all that is right.

09:20:36.390 --> 09:20:42.390
Precisely. I see you do. I see genuine contentment in your gait and mean,

09:20:42.870 --> 09:20:49.030
your eye and face. When you are helping me and pleasing me, working for me, and with me,

09:20:49.210 --> 09:20:54.870
in, as you characteristically say, all that is right. For if I bid you do what you thought

09:20:54.870 --> 09:21:01.090
wrong, there would be no light-footed running, no neat-handed alacrity, no lively glance and

09:21:01.830 --> 09:21:06.810
complexion. My friend would then turn to me, quiet and pale, and would say,

09:21:07.310 --> 09:21:12.130
No, sir, that is impossible. I cannot do it, because it is wrong.

09:21:12.870 --> 09:21:20.590
And would become immutable as a fixed star. Will you too have power over me, and may injure me?

09:21:21.290 --> 09:21:23.810
Yet I dare not show you where I am vulnerable.

09:21:24.270 --> 09:21:27.850
Less faithful and friendly as you are, you should transfix me at once.

09:21:29.530 --> 09:21:35.030
If you have no more to fear from Mr. Mason than you have from me, sir, you are very safe.

09:21:36.250 --> 09:21:40.610
God grant it may be so. Here, Jane, is an arbor. Sit down.

09:21:41.630 --> 09:21:46.210
The arbor was an arch in the wall, lined with ivy. It contained a rustic seat.

09:21:47.270 --> 09:21:51.930
Mr. Rochester took it, leaving room, however, for me, but I stood before him.

09:21:52.430 --> 09:21:56.490
Sit, he said. The bench is long enough for two.

09:21:57.110 --> 09:22:01.970
You don't hesitate to take a place at my side, do you? Is that wrong, Jane?

09:22:03.330 --> 09:22:08.270
I answered him by assuming it. To refuse would, I felt, have been unwise.

09:22:09.250 --> 09:22:15.190
Now, my little friend, while the sun drinks the dew, while all the flowers in this old garden

09:22:15.190 --> 09:22:20.270
awake and expand, and the birds fetch their young ones breakfast out of the thorn field,

09:22:20.650 --> 09:22:25.230
and the early bees do their first spell of work, I'll put a case to you,

09:22:25.230 --> 09:22:34.010
which you must endeavor to suppose your own. But first, look at me, and tell me, are you at ease,

09:22:34.350 --> 09:22:38.310
and not fearing that I err in detaining you, or that you err in staying?

09:22:39.930 --> 09:22:41.710
No, sir, I am content.

09:22:44.090 --> 09:22:54.930
Well then, Jane, call to aid your fancy. Suppose you were no longer a girl well reared and

09:22:55.670 --> 09:23:02.590
imagine yourself in a remote foreign land. Conceive that you there committed a capital error,

09:23:02.950 --> 09:23:08.210
no matter of what nature or from what motives, but one whose consequences must follow you

09:23:08.210 --> 09:23:14.650
through life and taint all your existence. Mind, I don't say a crime. I am not speaking

09:23:14.650 --> 09:23:19.270
of shedding of blood or any other guilty act which might make the perpetrator amenable to the law.

09:23:19.830 --> 09:23:26.030
My word is error. The results of what you have done become in time to you utterly insupportable.

09:23:26.610 --> 09:23:32.810
You take measures to obtain relief, unusual measures, but neither unlawful nor culpable.

09:23:34.370 --> 09:23:39.910
Still, you are miserable, for hope has quitted you on the very confines of life.

09:23:40.550 --> 09:23:46.390
Your sun at noon darkens in an eclipse, which you feel will not leave it till the time of setting.

09:23:47.030 --> 09:23:51.230
Bitter and base associations have become the sole food of your memory.

09:23:51.910 --> 09:23:58.650
You wander here and there, seeking rest in exile, happiness in pleasure. I mean in heartless,

09:23:58.870 --> 09:24:06.090
sensual pleasure, such as dulls intellect and blights feeling. Heart weary and soul withered,

09:24:06.390 --> 09:24:11.130
you come home after years of voluntary banishment. You make a new acquaintance,

09:24:11.130 --> 09:24:17.070
how or where, no matter. You find in this stranger much of the good and bright qualities

09:24:17.070 --> 09:24:21.650
which you have sought for twenty years and never before encountered.

09:24:22.890 --> 09:24:27.930
And they are all fresh, healthy, without soil and without taint.

09:24:29.070 --> 09:24:36.070
Such society revives, regenerates. You feel better days come back, higher wishes,

09:24:36.070 --> 09:24:42.870
purer feelings. You desire to recommence your life, and spend what remains to you of days in

09:24:42.870 --> 09:24:48.910
a way more worthy of an immortal being. To attain this end, are you justified in overleaping an

09:24:48.910 --> 09:24:55.170
obstacle of custom, a mere conventional impediment which neither your conscience sanctifies nor your

09:24:55.170 --> 09:25:03.690
judgment approves? He paused for an answer, and what was I to say? Oh, for some good spirit to

09:25:03.690 --> 09:25:12.030
suggest a judicious and satisfactory response, vain aspiration. The west wind whispered in the

09:25:12.030 --> 09:25:18.770
ivy round me, but no gentle aerial borrowed its breath as a medium of speech. The birds

09:25:18.770 --> 09:25:26.170
sang in the treetops, but their song, however sweet, was inarticulate. Again Mr. Rochester

09:25:26.170 --> 09:25:35.230
propounded his query. Is the wandering and sinful, but now rest-seeking and repentant man,

09:25:35.890 --> 09:25:41.930
justified in daring the world's opinion in order to attach himself forever this gentle, gracious,

09:25:42.330 --> 09:25:47.530
genial stranger, thereby securing his own peace of mind and regeneration of life?

09:25:48.630 --> 09:25:56.730
Sir, I answered, a wanderer's repose or a sinner's reformation should never depend on a fellow

09:25:56.730 --> 09:26:03.670
creature. Men and women die, philosophers falter in wisdom, and Christians in goodness.

09:26:05.350 --> 09:26:10.390
If anyone you know has suffered and erred, let him look higher than his equals for strength

09:26:10.390 --> 09:26:18.710
to amend and solace to heal. But the instrument, the instrument, God who does the work,

09:26:19.030 --> 09:26:27.110
ordains the instrument. I have myself, I tell it you without parable, been a worldly, dissipated,

09:26:27.470 --> 09:26:32.150
restless man, and I believe I have found the instrument for my cure and...

09:26:33.270 --> 09:26:40.510
He paused. The birds went on caroling, the leaves lightly rustling. I almost wondered

09:26:40.510 --> 09:26:45.590
they did not check their song and whispers to catch the suspended revelation, but they

09:26:45.590 --> 09:26:51.850
would have had to wait many minutes, so long was the silence protracted. At last I looked

09:26:51.850 --> 09:26:55.550
up at the tardy speaker. He was looking eagerly at me.

09:26:56.850 --> 09:27:04.210
Little friend, said he in a quite changed tone, while his face changed too, losing all its

09:27:04.210 --> 09:27:11.210
softness and gravity, and becoming harsh and sarcastic. You have noticed my tender penchant

09:27:11.210 --> 09:27:16.190
for Miss Ingram. Don't you think if I married her she would regenerate me with a vengeance?

09:27:17.650 --> 09:27:22.850
He got up instantly and went to the other end of the walk, and when he came back he was humming

09:27:22.850 --> 09:27:31.630
a tune. Jane, said he stopping before me. You are quite pale with your vigils. Don't you

09:27:31.630 --> 09:27:39.770
curse me for disturbing your rest? Curse you? No, sir. Shake hands in confirmation of the word.

09:27:40.730 --> 09:27:46.170
What cold fingers! They were warmer last night when I touched them at the door of the mysterious

09:27:46.170 --> 09:27:54.010
chamber. Jane, when will you watch with me again? Whenever I can be useful, sir.

09:27:55.570 --> 09:28:02.290
For instance, the night before I am married? I am sure I shall not be able to sleep. Will you

09:28:02.290 --> 09:28:08.690
promise to sit up with me, to bear me company? To you I can talk of my lovely one, for now you

09:28:08.690 --> 09:28:19.090
have seen her and know her. Yes, sir. She is a rare one, is she not, Jane? Yes, sir. A strapper,

09:28:19.170 --> 09:28:26.130
a real strapper, Jane, big brown and buxom with hair just as the ladies of Carthage must have had.

09:28:26.830 --> 09:28:32.230
Bless me, there's dent and linen in the stables. Go, in by the shrubbery, through that wicket.

09:28:33.850 --> 09:28:39.230
As I went one way, he went another, and I heard him in the yard, saying cheerfully,

09:28:40.610 --> 09:28:44.530
Mason got the start of you all this morning. He was gone before sunrise.

09:28:45.310 --> 09:28:53.150
I rose at four to see him off.

09:29:22.710 --> 09:29:24.110
XXI.

09:29:24.110 --> 09:29:33.610
Presentiments are strange things, and so are sympathies, and so are signs, and the three combined make one mystery to which humanity has not yet found the key.

09:29:34.370 --> 09:29:38.770
I never laughed at presentiments in my life, because I have had strange ones of my own.

09:29:39.290 --> 09:29:51.390
Sympathies, I believe, exist, for instance, between far-distant, long-absent, wholly estranged relatives asserting, notwithstanding their alienation, the unity of the source to which each traces his origin.

09:29:51.390 --> 09:29:59.750
Whose workings baffle mortal comprehension, and signs, for aught we know, may be but the sympathies of nature with man.

09:30:01.350 --> 09:30:15.910
When I was a little girl, only six years old, I one night heard Bessie Levin say to Martha Abbott that she had been dreaming about a little child, and that to dream of children was a sure sign of trouble, either to oneself or one's kin.

09:30:16.470 --> 09:30:22.950
The saying might have worn out of my memory, had not a circumstance immediately followed which served indelibly to fix it there.

09:30:23.410 --> 09:30:27.990
The next day Bessie was sent for home to the death-bed of her little sister.

09:30:29.970 --> 09:30:49.710
Of late I had often recalled this saying and this incident, for during the past weeks scarcely a night had gone over my couch that had not brought with it a dream of an infant, which I sometimes hushed in my arms, sometimes dandled on my knee, sometimes watched playing with daisies on a lawn, or again dabbling its hands in running water.

09:30:50.230 --> 09:30:53.970
It was a wailing child this night, and a laughing one the next.

09:30:54.410 --> 09:30:57.490
Now it nestled close to me, and now it ran from me.

09:30:57.950 --> 09:31:07.050
But whatever mood the apparition evinced, whatever aspect it wore, it failed not for seven successive nights to meet me the moment I entered the land of slumber.

09:31:08.990 --> 09:31:18.530
I did not like this iteration of one idea, this strange recurrence of one image, and I grew nervous as bedtime approached and the hour of the vision drew near.

09:31:19.230 --> 09:31:21.630
It was from companionship with this baby.

09:31:22.130 --> 09:31:33.850
Phantom, I had been roused on that moonlight night when I heard the cry, and it was on the afternoon of the day following I was summoned downstairs by a message that someone wanted me in Mrs. Fairfax's room.

09:31:34.450 --> 09:31:39.670
On repairing thither I found a man waiting for me, having the appearance of a gentleman servant.

09:31:40.070 --> 09:31:45.550
He was dressed in deep mourning, and the hat he held in his hand was surrounded with a crepe band.

09:31:49.570 --> 09:32:01.830
"'I dare say you hardly remember me, Miss,' he said, rising as I entered, "'but my name is Levin. I lived Coachman with Mrs. Reed when you were at Gateshead. Eight or nine years since, and I live there still.'

09:32:01.830 --> 09:32:12.230
"'Oh, Robert, how do you do? I remember you very well. You used to give me a ride sometimes on Miss Georgiana's Bay Pony. And how is Bessie? You are married to Bessie?'

09:32:12.850 --> 09:32:22.250
"'Yes, Miss. My wife is very hardy, thank you. She brought me another little one about two months since. We have three now, and both mother and child are thriving.'

09:32:22.850 --> 09:32:25.450
"'And are the family well at the house, Robert?'

09:32:25.450 --> 09:32:32.090
"'I am sorry I can't give you better news of them, Miss. They are very badly at present, in great trouble.'

09:32:32.690 --> 09:32:39.990
"'I hope no one is dead,' I said, glancing at his black dress. He too looked down at the crepe round his hat and replied.'

09:32:41.230 --> 09:32:45.830
"'Mr. John died yesterday, was a week, at his chambers in London.'

09:32:45.830 --> 09:32:47.350
"'Mr. John?'

09:32:48.370 --> 09:32:48.850
"'Yes.'

09:32:48.850 --> 09:32:51.050
"'And how does his mother bear it?'

09:32:51.530 --> 09:33:01.890
"'Why, you see, Miss Eyre, it is not a common mishap. His life has been very wild. These last three years he gave himself up to strange ways, and his death was shocking.'

09:33:02.450 --> 09:33:04.750
"'I heard from Bessie he was not doing well.'

09:33:06.210 --> 09:33:20.250
"'Doing well? He could not do worse. He ruined his health and his estate amongst the worst men and the worst women. He got into debt and into jail. His mother helped him out twice, but as soon as he was free he returned to his old companions and habits.

09:33:20.950 --> 09:33:44.010
"'His head was not strong. The knaves he lived amongst fooled him beyond anything I ever heard. He came down to Gateshead about three weeks ago and wanted Misses to give up all to him. Misses refused. Her means have long been much reduced by his extravagance, so he went back again. And the next news was that he was dead. How he died God knows. They say he killed himself.'

09:33:44.690 --> 09:33:49.490
"'I was silent. The things were frightful.' Robert Levin resumed.

09:33:50.310 --> 09:34:00.210
"'Misses had been out of health herself for some time. She had got very stout, but was not strong with it, and the loss of money and fear of poverty were quite breaking her down.

09:34:00.870 --> 09:34:16.070
"'The information about Mr. John's death and the manner of it came too suddenly. It brought on a stroke. She was three days without speaking. But last Tuesday she seemed rather better. She appeared as if she wanted to say something and kept making signs to my wife and mumbling.

09:34:16.750 --> 09:34:23.450
"'It was only yesterday morning, however, that Bessie understood she was pronouncing your name. And at last she made out the words,

09:34:24.130 --> 09:34:27.830
"'Bring Jane. Fetch Jane Eyre. I want to speak to her.'

09:34:28.350 --> 09:34:38.110
"'Bessie is not sure whether she is in her right mind or means anything by the words. But she told Miss Reed and Miss Georgiana and advised them to send for you.'

09:34:38.110 --> 09:34:52.770
"'The young ladies put it off at first. But their mother grew so restless and said, Jane, Jane, so many times that at last they consented. I left Gates' head yesterday. And if you can get ready, Miss, I should like to take you back with me early tomorrow morning.'

09:34:53.710 --> 09:34:57.890
"'Yes, Robert. I shall be ready. It seems to me that I ought to go.'

09:34:58.650 --> 09:35:06.890
"'I think so too, Miss. Bessie said she was sure you would not refuse. But I suppose you will have to ask leave before you can get off?'

09:35:07.850 --> 09:35:09.930
"'Yes, and I will do it now.'

09:35:09.930 --> 09:35:18.570
"'And having directed him to the servant's hall and recommended him to the care of John's wife and the attentions of John himself, I went in search of Mr. Rochester.

09:35:20.010 --> 09:35:29.010
"'He was not in any of the lower rooms. He was not seen in the yard, the stables, or the grounds. I asked Mrs. Fairfax if she had seen him.

09:35:29.600 --> 09:35:38.850
"'Yes, she believed he was playing billiards with Miss Ingram. To the billiard room I hastened. The click of balls and the hum of voices resounded thence.

09:35:38.850 --> 09:35:48.030
"'Mr. Rochester, Miss Ingram, and two Mrs. Eshton and their admirers were all busied in the game. It required some courage to deserve so interesting a party.

09:35:48.710 --> 09:35:54.350
"'My errand, however, was one I could not defer. So I approached the master, where he stood at Miss Ingram's side.

09:35:54.350 --> 09:35:59.510
"'She turned as I drew near and looked at me haughtily. Her eyes seemed to demand,

09:35:59.890 --> 09:36:02.350
"'What can this creeping creature want now?'

09:36:02.350 --> 09:36:04.770
"'When I said in a low voice,

09:36:05.110 --> 09:36:06.550
"'Mr. Rochester,'

09:36:06.850 --> 09:36:14.570
"'she made a movement as if tempted to order me away. I remember her appearance at that moment. It was very graceful and very striking.

09:36:15.210 --> 09:36:20.450
"'She wore a morning robe of sky-blue crepe. A gauzy azure scarf was twisted in her hair.

09:36:20.790 --> 09:36:26.350
"'She had been all animation with the game, and irritated pride did not lower the expression of her haughty lineaments.

09:36:28.710 --> 09:36:30.830
"'Does that person want you?'

09:36:30.830 --> 09:36:36.910
"'She inquired of Mr. Rochester, and Mr. Rochester turned to see who the person was.

09:36:36.910 --> 09:36:44.470
"'He made a curious grimace, one of his strange and equivocal demonstrations, threw down his cue, and followed me from the room.

09:36:46.010 --> 09:36:51.250
"'Well, Jane,' he said, as he rested his back against the schoolroom door, which he had shut.

09:36:51.970 --> 09:36:56.050
"'If you please, sir, I want leave of absence for a week or two.'

09:36:56.050 --> 09:36:58.770
"'What to do? Where to go?'

09:36:59.670 --> 09:37:02.130
"'To see a sick lady who was sent for me.'

09:37:02.130 --> 09:37:05.070
"'What sick lady? Where does she live?'

09:37:07.170 --> 09:37:09.210
"'At Gateshead, in Blankshire.'

09:37:10.130 --> 09:37:15.830
"'Blankshire? That is a hundred miles off. Who may she be that sends for people to see her at that distance?'

09:37:17.050 --> 09:37:19.750
"'Her name is Reed, sir, Mrs. Reed.'

09:37:20.930 --> 09:37:26.030
"'Reed of Gateshead? There was a Reed of Gateshead, a magistrate.'

09:37:26.770 --> 09:37:28.830
"'It is his widow, sir.'

09:37:30.630 --> 09:37:34.070
"'And what have you to do with her? How do you know her?'

09:37:34.670 --> 09:37:38.310
"'Mr. Reed was my uncle, my mother's brother.'

09:37:39.070 --> 09:37:43.830
"'The deuce he was! You never told me that before. You always said you had no relations.'

09:37:45.330 --> 09:37:51.090
"'None that would own me, sir. Mr. Reed is dead, and his wife cast me off.'

09:37:51.730 --> 09:37:52.250
"'Why?'

09:37:52.830 --> 09:37:56.710
"'Because I was poor and burdensome, and she disliked me.'

09:37:56.710 --> 09:38:04.050
"'But Reed left children. You must have cousins. Sir George Lynn was talking of a Reed of Gateshead yesterday. Who?' he said.

09:38:04.070 --> 09:38:14.290
"'Was one of the various rascals on town. And Ingram was mentioning a Georgiana Reed of the same place, who was much admired for her beauty a season or two ago in London.'

09:38:14.800 --> 09:38:25.810
"'John Reed is dead too, sir. He ruined himself and half ruined his family, and is supposed to have committed suicide. The news so shocked his mother that it brought on an apoplectic attack.'

09:38:27.730 --> 09:38:39.250
"'And what good can you do her? Nonsense, Jane. I would never think of running a hundred miles to see an old lady who will, perhaps, be dead before you reach her. Besides, you say she cast you off.'

09:38:40.090 --> 09:38:47.510
"'Yes, sir, but that is long ago, and when her circumstances were very different. I could not be easy to neglect her wishes now.'

09:38:48.490 --> 09:38:49.710
"'How long will you stay?'

09:38:50.750 --> 09:38:52.770
"'As short a time as possible, sir.'

09:38:54.050 --> 09:38:56.530
"'Promise me only to stay a week.'

09:38:56.530 --> 09:39:01.570
"'I had better not pass my word. I might be obliged to break it.'

09:39:01.570 --> 09:39:08.470
"'At all events, you will come back. You will not be induced under any pretext to take up a permanent residence with her.'

09:39:08.470 --> 09:39:11.930
"'Oh no! I shall certainly return if all be well.'

09:39:13.230 --> 09:39:16.530
"'And who goes with you? You don't travel a hundred miles alone.'

09:39:17.870 --> 09:39:20.830
"'No, sir. She has sent her coachman.'

09:39:20.830 --> 09:39:22.590
"'A person to be trusted?'

09:39:23.430 --> 09:39:26.970
"'Yes, sir. He has lived ten years in the family.'

09:39:26.970 --> 09:39:28.590
"'Mr. Rochester meditated.'

09:39:29.950 --> 09:39:31.590
"'When do you wish to go?'

09:39:32.630 --> 09:39:34.590
"'Early tomorrow morning, sir.'

09:39:35.330 --> 09:39:42.330
"'Well, you must have some money. You can't travel without money, and I dare say you have not much. I have given you no salary yet.'

09:39:42.330 --> 09:39:46.090
"'How much have you in the world, Jane?' he asked, smiling.

09:39:46.670 --> 09:39:49.850
"'I drew out my purse. A meager thing it was.'

09:39:50.430 --> 09:39:52.150
"'Five shillings, sir.'

09:39:52.150 --> 09:40:00.070
"'He took the purse, poured the hoard into his palm, and chuckled over it, as if its scantiness amused him. Soon he produced his pocket-book.'

09:40:00.990 --> 09:40:08.970
"'Here,' said he, offering me a note. It was fifty pounds, and he owed me but fifteen. I told him I had no change.'

09:40:08.970 --> 09:40:13.810
"'I don't want change. You know that. Take your wages.'

09:40:14.350 --> 09:40:16.650
"'I declined, accepting more than was my due.'

09:40:17.230 --> 09:40:21.530
"'He scowled at first. Then, as if recollecting something, he said,

09:40:22.090 --> 09:40:29.570
"'Right, right. Better not give you all now. You would perhaps stay away three months if you had fifty pounds. There are ten. Is it not plenty?'

09:40:31.030 --> 09:40:33.510
"'Yes, sir. But now you owe me five.'

09:40:33.510 --> 09:40:36.570
"'Come back for it, then. I am your banker for forty pounds.'

09:40:37.990 --> 09:40:43.070
"'Mr. Rochester, I may as well mention another matter of business to you while I have the opportunity.'

09:40:44.410 --> 09:40:46.990
"'Matter of business? I am curious to hear it.'

09:40:47.990 --> 09:40:51.870
"'You have as good as informed me, sir, that you are going shortly to be married.'

09:40:52.490 --> 09:40:53.830
"'Yes, what then?'

09:40:54.610 --> 09:40:59.890
"'In that case, sir, Adele ought to go to school. I am sure you will perceive the necessity of it.'

09:41:00.930 --> 09:41:05.310
"'To get her out of my bride's way? Who might otherwise walk over her rather too emphatically?

09:41:05.890 --> 09:41:14.310
"'There is sense in the suggestion. Not a doubt of it. Adele, as you say, must go to school. And you, of course, must march straight to the devil.'

09:41:15.630 --> 09:41:20.210
"'I hope not, sir. But I must seek another situation somewhere.'

09:41:20.810 --> 09:41:29.070
"'In course,' he exclaimed, with a twang of voice and a distortion of features equally fantastic and ludicrous. He looked at me some minutes.'

09:41:30.830 --> 09:41:36.010
"'And old Madame Reed, or the missus, her daughters, will be solicited by you to seek a place, I suppose?'

09:41:37.610 --> 09:41:43.890
"'No, sir. I am not on such terms with my relatives as would justify me in asking favors of them. But I shall advertise.'

09:41:45.390 --> 09:41:48.330
"'You shall walk up the pyramids of Egypt,' he growled.

09:41:48.550 --> 09:41:56.890
"'At your peril you advertise. I wish I had only offered you a sovereign instead of ten pounds. Give me back nine pounds, Jane. I have a use for it.'

09:41:57.390 --> 09:42:03.650
"'And so have I, sir,' I returned, putting my hands in my purse behind me. I could not spare the money on any account.'

09:42:05.330 --> 09:42:12.110
"'Little niggered,' said he, refusing me a pecuniary request. Give me five pounds, Jane.'

09:42:12.590 --> 09:42:14.850
"'Not five shilling, sir, nor five pence.'

09:42:15.890 --> 09:42:17.950
"'Just let me look at the cash.'

09:42:18.590 --> 09:42:21.070
"'No, sir. You are not to be trusted.'

09:42:22.110 --> 09:42:22.670
"'Jane.'

09:42:23.490 --> 09:42:24.050
"'Sir.'

09:42:24.050 --> 09:42:25.590
"'Promise me one thing.'

09:42:26.250 --> 09:42:29.370
"'I'll promise you anything, sir, that I think I am likely to perform.'

09:42:30.230 --> 09:42:36.730
"'Not to advertise, and to trust this quest of a situation to me. I'll find you one in time.'

09:42:37.310 --> 09:42:45.410
"'I shall be glad so to do, sir, if you, in your turn, will promise that I and Adèle shall be both safe out of the house before your bride enters it.'

09:42:46.490 --> 09:42:50.390
"'Very well, very well. I'll pledge my word on it. You go tomorrow, then.'

09:42:51.310 --> 09:42:53.610
"'Yes, sir. Early.'

09:42:53.610 --> 09:42:56.370
"'Shall you come down to the drawing-room after dinner?'

09:42:57.230 --> 09:42:59.430
"'No, sir. I must prepare for the journey.'

09:43:00.610 --> 09:43:03.430
"'Then you and I must bid goodbye for a little while.'

09:43:03.430 --> 09:43:05.850
"'I suppose so, sir.'

09:43:06.950 --> 09:43:13.570
"'And how do people perform that ceremony of parting, Jane? Teach me. I'm not quite up to it.'

09:43:13.570 --> 09:43:19.490
"'They say, farewell, or any other form they prefer. Then say it.'

09:43:20.850 --> 09:43:23.290
"'Farewell, Mr. Rochester, for the present.'

09:43:24.250 --> 09:43:26.050
"'What must I say?'

09:43:27.530 --> 09:43:30.570
"'The same, if you like, sir.'

09:43:31.610 --> 09:43:34.770
"'Farewell, Miss Eyre, for the present.'

09:43:34.770 --> 09:43:36.050
"'Is that all?'

09:43:38.730 --> 09:43:39.290
"'Yes.'

09:43:39.810 --> 09:43:50.590
"'It seems stingy to my notions, and dry, and unfriendly. I should like something else, a little addition to the right.'

09:43:50.590 --> 09:43:55.370
"'But no, that would not content me either. So you'll do no more than say farewell, Jane.'

09:43:56.310 --> 09:44:01.530
"'It is enough, sir. As much goodwill may be conveyed in one hearty word as in many.'

09:44:02.750 --> 09:44:08.030
"'Very likely. But it is blank and cool. Farewell.'

09:44:08.810 --> 09:44:15.350
"'How long is he going to stand with his back against that door?' I asked myself. I went to commence my packing.'

09:44:15.350 --> 09:44:24.270
"'The dinner bell rang, and suddenly away he bolted without another syllable. I saw him no more during the day, and was off before he had risen in the morning.

09:44:25.630 --> 09:44:33.150
"'I reached the lodge at Gateshead about five o'clock in the afternoon of the first of May. I stepped in there before going up to the hall.

09:44:33.150 --> 09:44:44.950
"'It was very clean and neat. The ornamental windows were hung with little white curtains. The floor was spotless. The grate and fire irons were burnished bright, and the fire burnt clear.'

09:44:46.070 --> 09:44:51.890
"'Bessie sat on the hearth, nursing her last-born, and Robert and his sister played quietly in a corner.

09:44:53.170 --> 09:44:57.710
"'Bless you! I knew you would come!' exclaimed Mrs. Levin as I entered.

09:44:59.210 --> 09:45:07.630
"'Yes, Bessie,' said I, after I had kissed her, and I trust I am not too late. How is Mrs. Reed? Alive still, I hope?'

09:45:08.470 --> 09:45:17.910
"'Yes, she is alive, and more sensible and collected than she was. The doctor says she may linger a week or two yet, but he hardly thinks she will finally recover.'

09:45:18.470 --> 09:45:20.170
"'Has she mentioned me lately?'

09:45:20.990 --> 09:45:28.410
"'She was talking of you only this morning and wishing you would come. But she is sleeping now, or was ten minutes ago when I was up at the house.

09:45:28.890 --> 09:45:38.050
"'She generally lies in a kind of lethargy all the afternoon and wakes up about six or seven. Will you rest yourself here an hour, Miss, and then I will go up with you?'

09:45:39.650 --> 09:45:44.750
"'Robert had entered, and Bessie laid her sleeping child in the cradle and went to welcome him.

09:45:45.650 --> 09:45:51.690
"'Afterwards she insisted on my taking off my bonnet and having some tea, for she said I looked pale and tired.

09:45:51.950 --> 09:46:00.810
"'I was glad to accept her hospitality, and I submitted to be relieved of my travelling garb just as passively as I used to let her undress me when a child.'

09:46:02.410 --> 09:46:18.890
"'Old times crowded fast back on me as I watched her bustling about, setting out the tea tray with her best china, cutting bread and butter, toasting a tea cake, and, between wiles, giving little Robert or Jane an occasional tap or push, just as she used to give me in former days.

09:46:19.530 --> 09:46:23.370
"'Bessie had retained her quick temper as well as her light foot and good looks.

09:46:24.290 --> 09:46:31.430
"'Tea ready I was going to approach the table, but she desired me to sit still, quite in her old peremptory tones.

09:46:32.950 --> 09:46:47.710
"'I must be served at the fireside,' she said, and she placed before me a little round stand with my cup and a plate of toast, absolutely as she used to accommodate me with some privately purloined dainty on a nursery chair, and I smiled and obeyed her as in bygone days.'

09:46:50.050 --> 09:47:00.630
"'She wanted to know if I was happy at Thornfield Hall and what sort of a person the mistress was, and when I told her there was only a master, whether he was a nice gentleman and if I liked him.

09:47:01.170 --> 09:47:07.050
"'I told her he was rather an ugly man, but quite a gentleman, and that he treated me kindly and I was content.

09:47:07.690 --> 09:47:15.210
"'Then I went on to describe to her the gay company that had lately been staying at the house, and to these details Bessie listened with interest.

09:47:15.470 --> 09:47:17.910
"'They were precisely of the kind she relished.

09:47:18.730 --> 09:47:21.910
"'In such conversation an hour was soon gone.

09:47:22.830 --> 09:47:28.390
"'Bessie restored to me my bonnet, etc., and, accompanied by her, I quitted the lodge for the hall.

09:47:28.390 --> 09:47:35.030
"'It was also accompanied by her that I had, nearly nine years ago, walked down the path I was now ascending.

09:47:35.470 --> 09:47:51.550
"'On a dark, misty, raw morning in January I had left a hostile roof with a desperate and embittered heart, a sense of outlawry and almost of reprobation, to seek the chilly harbourage of Lowood, that borne so far away and unexplored.

09:47:52.770 --> 09:47:55.950
"'The same hostile roof now again rose before me.

09:47:56.070 --> 09:48:00.110
"'My prospects were doubtful yet, and I had yet an aching heart.

09:48:00.610 --> 09:48:10.430
"'I still felt as a wanderer on the face of the earth, but I experienced firmer trust in myself and my own powers, and lest withering dread of oppression.

09:48:11.210 --> 09:48:17.310
"'The gaping wound of my wrongs, too, was now quite healed, and the flame of resentment extinguished.

09:48:19.270 --> 09:48:24.310
"'You shall go into the breakfast room first,' said Bessie, as she proceeded me through the hall.

09:48:24.830 --> 09:48:27.570
"'The young ladies will be there.'

09:48:28.330 --> 09:48:30.770
"'In another moment I was within that apartment.

09:48:31.110 --> 09:48:37.770
"'There was every article of furniture, looking just as it did on the morning I was first introduced to Mr. Brocklehurst.

09:48:38.570 --> 09:48:42.050
"'The very rug he had stood upon still covered the hearth.

09:48:42.810 --> 09:48:54.830
"'Glancing at the bookcases, I thought I could distinguish the two volumes of Buick's British Birds, occupying their old place on the third shelf, and Gulliver's Travels, and the Aramean Nights ranged just above.

09:48:57.870 --> 09:49:03.050
"'The inanimate objects were not changed, but the living things had altered past recognition.

09:49:05.470 --> 09:49:14.870
"'Two young ladies appeared before me, one very tall, almost as tall as Miss Ingram, very thin, too, with a sallow face and severe mien.

09:49:15.230 --> 09:49:30.170
"'There was something acidic in her look, which was augmented by the extreme plainness of a straight skirted, black, stuffed dress, a starched linen collar, hair combed away from the temples, and the nun-like ornament of a string of ebony beads and a crucifix.

09:49:30.750 --> 09:49:37.950
"'This, I felt sure, was Eliza, though I could trace little resemblance to her former self in that elongated and colorless visage.

09:49:39.890 --> 09:49:47.130
"'The other was as certainly Georgiana, but not the Georgiana I remembered, the slim and fairy-like girl of eleven.

09:49:47.810 --> 09:49:57.910
"'This was a full-blown, very plump damsel, fair as waxwork, with handsome and regular features, languishing blue eyes and ring-lidded yellow hair.

09:49:58.250 --> 09:50:08.830
"'The hue of her dress was black, too, but its fashion was so different from her sister's, so much more flowing and becoming, it looked as stylish as the others looked puritanical.

09:50:10.590 --> 09:50:20.390
"'In each of the sisters there was one trait of the mother, and only one. The thin and pallid elder daughter had her parents' cairn-gorm eye.

09:50:20.570 --> 09:50:32.950
"'The blooming and luxuriant younger girl had the contour of chin and jaw, perhaps a little softened, but still imparting an indescribable hardness to the countenance otherwise so voluptuous in buxom.

09:50:34.590 --> 09:50:40.390
"'Both ladies, as I advanced, rose to welcome me, and both addressed me by the name of Miss Eyre.

09:50:41.250 --> 09:50:49.350
"'Eliza's greeting was delivered in a short, abrupt voice, without a smile, and then she sat down again, fixed her eyes on the fire, and seemed to forget me.

09:50:50.090 --> 09:50:52.350
"'Georgiana added to her, How do you do?

09:50:52.870 --> 09:51:08.870
"'Several common places about my journey, the weather, and so on, uttered in rather a drawling tone, and accompanied by sundry sign glances that measured me from head to foot, now traversing the folds of my drab merino police, and now lingering on the plain trimming of my cottage bonnet.

09:51:08.870 --> 09:51:15.330
"'Young ladies have a remarkable way of letting you know that they think you a quiz, without actually saying the words.

09:51:15.810 --> 09:51:27.110
"'A certain superciliousness of look, coolness of manner, nonchalance of tone, express fully their sentiments on the point, without committing them by any positive rudeness in word or deed.

09:51:28.650 --> 09:51:35.370
"'A sneer, however, whether covert or open, had now no longer that power over me it once possessed.

09:51:35.790 --> 09:51:44.690
"'As I sat between my cousins, I was surprised to find how easy I felt under the total neglect of the one and the semi-sarcastic attentions of the other.

09:51:45.410 --> 09:51:49.010
"'Eliza did not mortify, nor Georgiana ruffle me.

09:51:49.530 --> 09:51:52.190
"'The fact was I had other things to think about.

09:51:52.650 --> 09:51:58.310
"'Within the last few months feelings had been stirred in me so much more potent than any they could raise.

09:51:58.950 --> 09:52:06.010
"'Pains and pleasures so much more acute and exquisite had been excited than any it was in their power to inflict or bestow.

09:52:06.190 --> 09:52:10.170
"'That their errors gave me no concern, either for good or bad.'

09:52:11.190 --> 09:52:20.270
"'How is Mrs. Reed?' I asked soon, looking calmly at Georgiana, who thought it fit to bridle at the direct dress, as if it were an unexpected liberty.

09:52:21.770 --> 09:52:29.290
"'Mrs. Reed? Ah, Mama, you mean? She is extremely poorly. I doubt if you can see her to-night.'

09:52:29.290 --> 09:52:35.070
"'If,' said I, you would just step upstairs and tell her I am come. I should be much obliged to you.'

09:52:37.250 --> 09:52:41.210
"'Georgiana almost started, and she opened her blue eyes wild and wide.

09:52:41.650 --> 09:52:49.020
"'I know she had a particular wish to see me,' I added, and I would not defer attending to her desire longer than is absolutely necessary.

09:52:50.930 --> 09:52:54.870
"'Mama dislikes being disturbed in an evening,' remarked Eliza.

09:52:55.590 --> 09:53:04.650
"'I soon rose, quietly took off my bonnet and gloves uninvited, and said I would just step out to Bessie, who was, I dared say, in the kitchen,

09:53:04.650 --> 09:53:09.530
"'and ask her to ascertain whether Mrs. Reed was disposed to receive me or not to-night.'

09:53:09.530 --> 09:53:15.750
"'I went, and having found Bessie and dispatched her on my errand, I proceeded to take further measures.

09:53:16.450 --> 09:53:26.430
"'It had heretofore been my habit always to shrink from arrogance. Received as I have been to-day, I should, a year ago, have resolved to quit Gateshead the very next morning.

09:53:27.030 --> 09:53:31.010
"'Now it was disclosed to me all at once that that would be a foolish plan.

09:53:31.490 --> 09:53:37.850
"'I had taken a journey of a hundred miles to see my aunt, and I must stay with her till she was better, or dead.

09:53:38.270 --> 09:53:44.730
"'As to her daughter's pride or folly, I must put it on one side, make myself independent of it.

09:53:45.110 --> 09:53:52.350
"'So I addressed the housekeeper, asked her to show me a room, told her I should probably be a visitor here for a week or two,

09:53:52.350 --> 09:53:58.830
"'had my trunk conveyed to my chamber, and followed it thither myself. I met Bessie on the landing.

09:54:00.870 --> 09:54:07.410
"'Mrs. is awake,' said she. I have told her you are here. Come and let us see if she will know you.'

09:54:07.890 --> 09:54:14.950
"'I did not need to be guided to the well-known room to which I had so often been summoned for chastisement or reprimand in former days.

09:54:14.950 --> 09:54:22.930
"'I hastened before Bessie. I softly opened the door. A shaded light stood on the table, for it was now getting dark.

09:54:23.430 --> 09:54:27.170
"'There was the great four-post bed, with amber hangings as of old.

09:54:27.970 --> 09:54:36.810
"'There the toilet table, the armchair, and the footstool, at which I had a hundred times been sentenced to kneel, to ask pardon for offences by me uncommitted.

09:54:37.410 --> 09:54:45.010
"'I looked into a certain corner near, half expecting to see the slim outline of a once-dreaded switch which used to lurk there,

09:54:45.290 --> 09:54:49.390
"'waiting to leap out imp-like and lace my quivering palm or shrinking neck.

09:54:49.790 --> 09:54:54.930
"'I approached the bed. I opened the curtains and leant over the high-piled pillows.

09:54:56.910 --> 09:55:01.690
"'Well did I remember Mrs. Reed's face, and I eagerly sought the familiar image.

09:55:02.330 --> 09:55:07.870
"'It is a happy thing that time quells the longings of vengeance and hushes the promptings of rage and aversion.

09:55:08.530 --> 09:55:16.610
"'I had left this woman in bitterness and hate, and I came back to her now with no other emotion than a sort of ruth for her great sufferings,

09:55:17.150 --> 09:55:23.350
"'and a strong yearning to forget and forgive all injuries, to be reconciled and clasp hands in amity.

09:55:25.650 --> 09:55:30.090
"'The well-known face was there, stern, relentless as ever.

09:55:30.430 --> 09:55:37.410
"'There was that peculiar eye which nothing could melt, and the somewhat raised, imperious, despotic eyebrow.

09:55:37.730 --> 09:55:40.690
"'How often had it lowered on me menace and hate?

09:55:40.890 --> 09:55:46.650
"'And how the recollection of childhood's terrors and sorrows revived as I traced its harsh line now?

09:55:46.850 --> 09:55:51.030
"'And yet I stooped down and kissed her. She looked at me.

09:55:51.970 --> 09:55:54.570
"'Is this Jane Eyre?' she said.

09:55:55.290 --> 09:55:57.830
"'Yes, Aunt Reed. How are you, dear aunt?'

09:55:59.730 --> 09:56:03.010
"'I had once vowed that I would never call her aunt again.

09:56:03.190 --> 09:56:06.250
"'I thought it no sin to forget and break that vow now.

09:56:06.810 --> 09:56:10.130
"'My fingers had fastened on her hand which lay outside the sheet.

09:56:10.510 --> 09:56:15.370
"'Had she pressed mine kindly, I should at that moment have experienced true pleasure.

09:56:15.850 --> 09:56:22.570
"'But unimpressionable natures are not soon softened, nor are natural antipathies so readily eradicated.

09:56:23.130 --> 09:56:30.050
"'Mrs. Reed took her hand away, and turning her face rather from me, she remarked that the night was warm.

09:56:30.910 --> 09:56:39.850
"'Again she regarded me so idly, I felt at once that her opinion of me, her feeling towards me, was unchanged and unchangeable.

09:56:40.370 --> 09:56:49.530
"'I knew by her stony eye, opaque to tenderness, indissoluble to tears, that she was resolved to consider me bad to the last,

09:56:50.190 --> 09:56:56.130
"'because to believe me good would give her no generous pleasure, only a sense of mortification.

09:56:57.370 --> 09:57:04.330
"'I felt pain, and then I felt Eyre, and then I felt a determination to subdue her,

09:57:04.330 --> 09:57:08.450
"'to be her mistress in spite both of her nature and her will.

09:57:08.870 --> 09:57:11.610
"'My tears had risen just as in childhood.

09:57:12.070 --> 09:57:13.910
"'I ordered them back to their source.

09:57:14.350 --> 09:57:18.450
"'I brought a chair to the bedhead, and sat down and leaned over the pillow.

09:57:19.590 --> 09:57:26.190
"'You sent for me, I said, and I am here, and it is my intention to stay till I see how you get on.'

09:57:27.810 --> 09:57:30.190
"'Oh, of course, you have seen my daughters.'

09:57:32.770 --> 09:57:33.290
"'Yes.'

09:57:33.290 --> 09:57:38.210
"'Well, you may tell them I wish you to stay till I can talk some things over with you I have in my mind.

09:57:38.730 --> 09:57:42.110
"'Tonight it is too late, and I have a difficulty in recalling them.

09:57:42.410 --> 09:57:44.770
"'But there was something I wished to say.

09:57:45.150 --> 09:57:47.050
"'Let me see.'

09:57:48.930 --> 09:57:54.830
"'The wandering look and changed utterance told what wreck had taken place in her once vigorous frame.

09:57:55.630 --> 09:57:58.770
"'Turning restlessly, she drew the bedclothes round her.

09:57:59.300 --> 09:58:02.570
"'My elbow, resting on a corner of the quilt, fixed it down.

09:58:02.710 --> 09:58:04.310
"'She was at once irritated.

09:58:05.530 --> 09:58:06.990
"'Sit up,' said she.

09:58:07.050 --> 09:58:09.150
"'Don't annoy me with holding the clothes fast.

09:58:09.190 --> 09:58:10.530
"'Are you Jane Eyre?'

09:58:11.150 --> 09:58:12.950
"'I am Jane Eyre.'

09:58:13.510 --> 09:58:16.750
"'I have had more trouble with that child than anyone would believe.

09:58:17.090 --> 09:58:22.890
"'Such a burden to be left on my hands, and so much annoyance as she caused me daily and hourly

09:58:22.890 --> 09:58:30.210
"'with her incomprehensible disposition and her sudden starts of temper and her continual, unnatural watchings of one's movements.

09:58:30.630 --> 09:58:34.870
"'I declare she talked to me once like something mad, or like a fiend.

09:58:35.030 --> 09:58:38.130
"'No child ever spoke or looked as she did.

09:58:38.130 --> 09:58:40.430
"'I was glad to get her away from the house.

09:58:40.610 --> 09:58:42.670
"'What did they do with her at Lowood?

09:58:42.990 --> 09:58:45.630
"'The fever broke out there and many of the pupils died.

09:58:45.930 --> 09:58:47.730
"'She, however, did not die.

09:58:47.730 --> 09:58:49.310
"'But I said she did.

09:58:49.310 --> 09:58:51.270
"'I wish she had died.'

09:58:52.190 --> 09:58:54.030
"'A strange wish, Mrs. Reed.

09:58:54.270 --> 09:58:56.370
"'Why do you hate her so?'

09:58:57.030 --> 09:59:03.390
"'I had a dislike to her mother always, for she was my husband's only sister and a great favorite with him.

09:59:03.630 --> 09:59:07.390
"'He opposed the family's disowning her when she made her low marriage,

09:59:07.860 --> 09:59:11.330
"'and when news came of her death he wept like a simpleton.

09:59:11.790 --> 09:59:16.290
"'He would send for the baby, though I entreated him rather to put it out to nurse,

09:59:17.010 --> 09:59:18.270
"'and pay for its maintenance.

09:59:18.430 --> 09:59:21.130
"'I hated it the first time I set my eyes on it.

09:59:21.290 --> 09:59:23.650
"'A sickly whining, pining thing.

09:59:23.890 --> 09:59:26.170
"'It would wail in its cradle all night long,

09:59:26.210 --> 09:59:30.650
"'not screaming heartily like any other child, but whimpering and moaning.

09:59:31.510 --> 09:59:36.330
"'Reed pitied it, and he used to nurse it and notice it as if it had been his own,

09:59:36.490 --> 09:59:39.290
"'more indeed than he ever noticed his own at that age.

09:59:39.810 --> 09:59:43.010
"'He would try to make my children friendly to the little beggar.

09:59:43.010 --> 09:59:47.530
"'The darlings could not bear it, and he was angry with them when they showed their dislike.

09:59:47.950 --> 09:59:51.890
"'In his last illness he had it brought continually to his bedside,

09:59:52.730 --> 09:59:57.170
"'and but an hour before he died he bound me by vow to keep the creature.

09:59:57.630 --> 10:00:00.870
"'I would as soon have been charged with a pauper brat out of a workhouse,

10:00:01.390 --> 10:00:04.070
"'but he was weak, naturally weak.

10:00:04.810 --> 10:00:08.550
"'John does not at all resemble his father, and I am glad of it.

10:00:08.610 --> 10:00:10.990
"'John is like me and like my brothers.

10:00:10.990 --> 10:00:12.510
"'He is quite a Gibson.

10:00:13.150 --> 10:00:16.390
"'Oh, I wish he would cease tormenting me with letters for money.

10:00:16.550 --> 10:00:19.610
"'I have no more money to give him. We are getting poor.

10:00:20.630 --> 10:00:24.750
"'I must send away half the servants and shut up part of the house, or let it off.

10:00:24.990 --> 10:00:29.030
"'I can never submit to do that. Yet how are we to get on?

10:00:29.450 --> 10:00:32.970
"'Two thirds of my income goes in paying the interest of mortgages.

10:00:33.370 --> 10:00:36.710
"'John gambles dreadfully and always loses, poor boy.

10:00:36.910 --> 10:00:38.850
"'He is beset by sharpers.

10:00:38.850 --> 10:00:42.190
"'John is sunk and degraded. His look is frightful.

10:00:42.190 --> 10:00:44.610
"'I feel ashamed for him when I see him.'

10:00:46.990 --> 10:00:48.750
"'She was getting much excited.

10:00:49.170 --> 10:00:54.070
"'I think I had better leave her now,' said I to Bessie, who stood on the other side of the bed.

10:00:55.970 --> 10:00:59.870
"'Perhaps you had, Miss, but she often talks in this way towards night.

10:00:59.990 --> 10:01:02.390
"'In the morning she is calmer.'

10:01:02.390 --> 10:01:05.930
"'I rose. Stop!' exclaimed Mrs. Reed.

10:01:05.930 --> 10:01:08.250
"'There is another thing I wish to say.

10:01:08.550 --> 10:01:12.670
"'He threatens me. He continually threatens me with his own death or mine.

10:01:12.750 --> 10:01:17.130
"'And I dream sometimes that I see him laid out with a great wound in his throat,

10:01:17.250 --> 10:01:19.370
"'or with a swollen and blackened face.

10:01:19.410 --> 10:01:22.890
"'I am come to a strange pass. I have heavy troubles.

10:01:23.230 --> 10:01:26.710
"'What is to be done? How is the money to be had?'

10:01:27.410 --> 10:01:30.590
"'Bessie now endeavoured to persuade her to take a sedative draught.

10:01:30.730 --> 10:01:32.570
"'She succeeded with difficulty.

10:01:33.230 --> 10:01:37.490
"'Soon after Mrs. Reed grew more composed and sank into a dozing state.

10:01:37.730 --> 10:01:39.090
"'I then left her.

10:01:40.070 --> 10:01:44.430
"'More than ten days elapsed before I had again any conversation with her.

10:01:44.750 --> 10:01:47.610
"'She continued either delirious or lethargic,

10:01:47.650 --> 10:01:51.450
"'and the doctor forbade everything which could painfully excite her.

10:01:51.670 --> 10:01:55.310
"'Mean time I got on as well as I could with Georgiana and Eliza.

10:01:55.610 --> 10:01:58.570
"'They were very cold, indeed, at first.

10:01:59.230 --> 10:02:02.150
"'Eliza would sit half the day sewing, reading, or writing,

10:02:02.150 --> 10:02:05.310
"'and scarcely utter a word either to me or her sister.

10:02:06.110 --> 10:02:09.650
"'Georgiana would chatter nonsense to her canary-bird by the hour

10:02:09.650 --> 10:02:11.330
"'and take no notice of me.

10:02:11.450 --> 10:02:15.350
"'But I was determined not to seem at a loss for occupation or amusement.

10:02:15.710 --> 10:02:19.390
"'I had brought my drawing materials with me, and they served me for both.

10:02:21.270 --> 10:02:23.970
"'Provided with a case of pencils and some sheets of paper,

10:02:24.090 --> 10:02:26.590
"'I used to take a seat apart from them near the window

10:02:26.590 --> 10:02:29.390
"'and busy myself in sketching fancy vignettes,

10:02:29.710 --> 10:02:32.130
"'representing any scene that happened momentarily

10:02:32.130 --> 10:02:35.390
"'to shape itself in the ever-shifting kaleidoscope of imagination.

10:02:35.770 --> 10:02:38.210
"'A glimpse of sea between two rocks,

10:02:38.310 --> 10:02:41.190
"'the rising moon, and a ship crossing its disk,

10:02:41.210 --> 10:02:43.390
"'a group of reeds and water flags,

10:02:43.630 --> 10:02:47.210
"'and an iad's head, crowned with lotus flowers rising out of them,

10:02:47.630 --> 10:02:50.070
"'an elf sitting in a hedge sparrow's nest,

10:02:50.330 --> 10:02:51.990
"'under a wreath of hawthorn bloom.

10:02:53.410 --> 10:02:55.650
"'One morning I fell into sketching a face.

10:02:55.870 --> 10:02:59.470
"'What sort of a face it was to be, I did not care or know.

10:03:00.010 --> 10:03:04.230
"'I took a soft black pencil, gave it a broad point, and worked away.

10:03:04.910 --> 10:03:08.470
"'Soon I had traced on the paper a broad and prominent forehead

10:03:08.470 --> 10:03:10.950
"'and a square lower outline of visage.

10:03:11.190 --> 10:03:12.930
"'That contour gave me pleasure.

10:03:13.470 --> 10:03:16.370
"'My fingers proceeded actively to fill it with features.

10:03:17.130 --> 10:03:20.490
"'Strongly marked horizontal eyebrows must be traced under that brow.

10:03:20.890 --> 10:03:21.970
"'Then followed, to the left of the face,

10:03:21.990 --> 10:03:26.850
"'naturally a well-defined nose with a straight ridge and full nostrils,

10:03:26.850 --> 10:03:30.990
"'then a flexible-looking mouth, by no means narrow,

10:03:30.990 --> 10:03:35.350
"'then a firm chin with a decided cleft down the middle of it.

10:03:35.350 --> 10:03:38.230
"'Of course, some black whiskers were wanted

10:03:38.230 --> 10:03:41.010
"'and some jetty hair tufted on the temples

10:03:41.010 --> 10:03:43.110
"'and waved above the forehead.

10:03:43.810 --> 10:03:45.270
"'Now for the eyes.

10:03:45.750 --> 10:03:47.390
"'I had left them to the last

10:03:47.390 --> 10:03:49.510
"'because they required the most careful working.

10:03:50.050 --> 10:03:51.550
"'I drew them large.

10:03:51.990 --> 10:03:53.070
"'I shaped them well.

10:03:53.210 --> 10:03:55.690
"'The eyelashes I traced long and somber.

10:03:55.890 --> 10:03:58.750
"'The irises, lustrous and large.

10:03:59.930 --> 10:04:04.750
"'Good, but not quite the thing, I thought, as I surveyed the effect.

10:04:05.290 --> 10:04:07.790
"'They want more force and spirit.

10:04:08.010 --> 10:04:10.230
"'And I wrought the shades blacker

10:04:10.230 --> 10:04:12.630
"'that the lights might flash more brilliantly.

10:04:13.150 --> 10:04:15.690
"'A happy touch or two secured success.

10:04:16.530 --> 10:04:19.330
"'There, I had a friend's face under my gaze.

10:04:19.890 --> 10:04:23.730
"'And what did it signify that those young ladies turned their backs on me?

10:04:24.110 --> 10:04:25.550
"'I looked at it.

10:04:25.550 --> 10:04:27.530
"'I smiled at the speaking likeness.

10:04:27.730 --> 10:04:30.250
"'I was absorbed and content.'

10:04:32.410 --> 10:04:34.770
"'Is that a portrait of someone you know?'

10:04:34.770 --> 10:04:37.590
"'asked Eliza, who had approached me unnoticed.

10:04:38.130 --> 10:04:40.710
"'I responded that it was merely a fancy head

10:04:40.710 --> 10:04:42.550
"'and hurried it beneath the other sheets.

10:04:42.990 --> 10:04:44.310
"'Of course I lied.

10:04:44.470 --> 10:04:48.350
"'It was, in fact, a very faithful representation of Mr. Rochester.

10:04:49.330 --> 10:04:52.090
"'What was that to her, or to anyone but myself?'

10:04:52.630 --> 10:04:54.370
"'Georgiana also advanced to look.

10:04:54.950 --> 10:04:56.890
"'The other drawings pleased her much,

10:04:56.950 --> 10:04:58.970
"'but she called that an ugly man.

10:04:59.550 --> 10:05:01.710
"'They both seemed surprised at my skill.

10:05:02.270 --> 10:05:04.250
"'I offered to sketch their portraits,

10:05:04.510 --> 10:05:07.330
"'and each, in turn, sat for a pencil outline.

10:05:08.170 --> 10:05:10.410
"'Then Georgiana produced her album.

10:05:10.930 --> 10:05:13.850
"'I promised to contribute a watercolor drawing.

10:05:14.330 --> 10:05:16.530
"'This put her at once into good humor.

10:05:19.530 --> 10:05:21.470
"'Before we had been out two hours,

10:05:21.530 --> 10:05:23.930
"'we were deep in confidential conversation.

10:05:24.850 --> 10:05:27.550
"'She had favored me with a description of the brilliant winter

10:05:27.550 --> 10:05:29.710
"'she had spent in London two seasons ago,

10:05:29.950 --> 10:05:32.190
"'of the admiration she had there excited,

10:05:32.310 --> 10:05:34.010
"'the attention she had received,

10:05:34.190 --> 10:05:37.290
"'and I even got hints of the titled conquest she had made.

10:05:37.650 --> 10:05:39.730
"'In the course of the afternoon and evening

10:05:39.730 --> 10:05:41.330
"'these hints were enlarged on.

10:05:41.890 --> 10:05:44.070
"'Various soft conversations were reported

10:05:49.330 --> 10:05:52.290
"'and the style of fashionable life was that day improvised by her

10:05:52.290 --> 10:05:53.090
"'for my benefit.

10:05:53.590 --> 10:05:56.530
"'The communications were renewed from day to day.

10:05:56.750 --> 10:06:01.590
"'They always ran on the same theme, herself, her loves and woes.

10:06:01.690 --> 10:06:04.030
"'It was strange she never once inverted

10:06:04.030 --> 10:06:07.190
"'either to her mother's illness or her brother's death

10:06:07.190 --> 10:06:10.050
"'or the present gloomy state of the family's prospects.

10:06:10.470 --> 10:06:14.230
"'Her mind seemed wholly taken up with reminiscences of past gaiety

10:06:14.230 --> 10:06:16.910
"'and aspirations after dissipations to come.

10:06:17.570 --> 10:06:19.670
"'She passed about five minutes each day

10:06:19.670 --> 10:06:21.710
"'in her mother's sick room and no more.

10:06:23.030 --> 10:06:24.730
"'Eliza still spoke little.

10:06:24.850 --> 10:06:26.990
"'She had evidently no time to talk.

10:06:27.170 --> 10:06:30.110
"'I never saw a busier person than she seemed to be.

10:06:30.170 --> 10:06:32.470
"'Yet it was difficult to say what she did,

10:06:32.470 --> 10:06:35.210
"'or rather to discover any results of her diligence.

10:06:35.650 --> 10:06:37.830
"'She had an alarm to call her up early.

10:06:37.950 --> 10:06:40.790
"'I know not how she occupied herself before breakfast,

10:06:40.950 --> 10:06:44.410
"'but after that meal she divided her time into regular portions

10:06:47.030 --> 10:06:49.370
"'three times a day she studied a little book,

10:06:49.590 --> 10:06:52.790
"'which I found, on inspection, was a common prayer book.

10:06:53.130 --> 10:06:56.470
"'I asked her once what was the great attraction of that volume

10:06:56.470 --> 10:06:58.630
"'and she said, the rubric.

10:06:59.210 --> 10:07:01.910
"'Three hours she gave to stitching, with gold thread,

10:07:02.190 --> 10:07:04.230
"'the border of a square crimson cloth,

10:07:04.530 --> 10:07:05.990
"'almost large enough for a carpet.

10:07:06.770 --> 10:07:09.530
"'In answer to my inquiries after the use of this article

10:07:09.530 --> 10:07:12.790
"'she informed me it was a covering for the altar of a new church

10:07:12.790 --> 10:07:14.390
"'lately erected near Gates Head.

10:07:14.950 --> 10:07:17.130
"'Two hours she devoted to her diary,

10:07:17.450 --> 10:07:19.830
"'two to working by herself in the kitchen garden,

10:07:19.990 --> 10:07:22.390
"'and one to the regulation of her accounts.

10:07:22.830 --> 10:07:25.670
"'She seemed to want no company, no conversation.

10:07:26.050 --> 10:07:28.010
"'I believed she was happy in her way.

10:07:28.270 --> 10:07:30.070
"'This routine sufficed for her,

10:07:30.070 --> 10:07:33.030
"'and nothing annoyed her so much as the occurrence of any incident

10:07:33.030 --> 10:07:35.830
"'which forced her to vary its clockwork regularity.

10:07:37.630 --> 10:07:39.250
"'She told me one evening,

10:07:39.270 --> 10:07:42.190
"'when more disposed to be communicative than usual,

10:07:44.390 --> 10:07:48.010
"'the ruin of the family had been a source of profound affliction to her.

10:07:48.370 --> 10:07:49.950
"'But she had now, she said,

10:07:50.110 --> 10:07:52.190
"'settled her mind and formed her resolution.

10:07:52.650 --> 10:07:55.170
"'Her own fortune she had taken care to secure,

10:07:55.170 --> 10:07:58.250
"'and when her mother died, and it was wholly improbable,

10:07:58.350 --> 10:08:01.590
"'she tranquilly remarked that she should either recover or linger long,

10:08:01.710 --> 10:08:04.290
"'she would execute a long, cherished project,

10:08:04.570 --> 10:08:07.990
"'seek retirement where punctual habits would be permanently secured

10:08:07.990 --> 10:08:11.150
"'from disturbance and place safe barriers between herself

10:08:11.150 --> 10:08:12.210
"'and a frivolous world.

10:08:15.710 --> 10:08:19.430
"'Of course not. Georgiana and she had nothing in common.

10:08:19.690 --> 10:08:20.870
"'They never had had.

10:08:21.170 --> 10:08:24.490
"'She would not be burdened with her society for any consideration.

10:08:25.170 --> 10:08:27.090
"'Georgiana should take her own course,

10:08:27.090 --> 10:08:29.590
"'and she, Eliza, would take hers.

10:08:31.270 --> 10:08:33.890
"'Georgiana, when not unburdening her heart to me,

10:08:34.030 --> 10:08:36.070
"'spent most of her time in lying on the sofa,

10:08:36.290 --> 10:08:38.130
"'freading about the dullness of the house,

10:08:38.150 --> 10:08:41.250
"'and wishing over and over again that her Aunt Gibson

10:08:41.250 --> 10:08:43.570
"'would send her an invitation up to town.

10:08:44.390 --> 10:08:46.590
"'It would be so much better,' said she,

10:08:46.650 --> 10:08:49.190
"'if she could only get out of the way for a month or two

10:08:49.190 --> 10:08:50.150
"'till all was over.

10:08:50.970 --> 10:08:53.530
"'I did not ask what she meant by all being over,

10:08:53.530 --> 10:08:56.650
"'but I suppose she referred to the expected decease of her mother

10:08:56.650 --> 10:08:58.770
"'and the gloomy sequel of funeral rites.

10:08:59.450 --> 10:09:02.390
"'Eliza generally took no more notice of her sister's indolence

10:09:02.390 --> 10:09:05.690
"'and complaints than if no such murmuring, lounging object

10:09:05.690 --> 10:09:07.090
"'had been before her.

10:09:07.270 --> 10:09:10.050
"'One day, however, as she put away her account book

10:09:15.470 --> 10:09:18.470
"'Georgiana, a more vain and absurd animal than you

10:09:18.470 --> 10:09:20.430
"'was certainly never allowed to cummer the earth.

10:09:20.650 --> 10:09:24.050
"'You had no right to be born, for you make no use of life.

10:09:24.630 --> 10:09:27.530
"'Instead of living for, in, and with yourself

10:09:27.530 --> 10:09:29.170
"'as a reasonable being ought,

10:09:29.430 --> 10:09:31.790
"'you seek only to fasten your feebleness

10:09:31.790 --> 10:09:33.370
"'on some other person's strength.

10:09:33.490 --> 10:09:36.490
"'If no one can be found willing to unburden her or himself

10:09:36.490 --> 10:09:38.870
"'with such a fat, weak, puffy, useless thing,

10:09:39.010 --> 10:09:42.630
"'you cry out that you are ill-treated, neglected, miserable.

10:09:44.390 --> 10:09:47.490
"'You must be a scene of continual change and excitement,

10:09:47.490 --> 10:09:49.690
"'or else the world is a dungeon.

10:09:50.030 --> 10:09:52.810
"'You must be admired, you must be courted,

10:09:52.850 --> 10:09:53.990
"'you must be flattered.

10:09:54.330 --> 10:09:57.110
"'You must have music, dancing, and society,

10:09:57.170 --> 10:09:59.070
"'or you languish, you die away.

10:09:59.290 --> 10:10:02.010
"'Have you no sense to devise a system which will make you

10:10:02.010 --> 10:10:04.810
"'independent of all efforts and all wills but your own?

10:10:05.010 --> 10:10:07.730
"'Take one day, share it into sections,

10:10:07.970 --> 10:10:10.070
"'to each section apportion its task.

10:10:14.610 --> 10:10:15.650
"'Include all.

10:10:16.410 --> 10:10:19.050
"'Do each piece of business in its turn with method,

10:10:19.370 --> 10:10:20.850
"'with rigid regularity.

10:10:21.710 --> 10:10:25.130
"'The day will close almost before you are aware it has begun,

10:10:25.210 --> 10:10:27.770
"'and you are indebted to no one for helping you

10:10:27.770 --> 10:10:29.570
"'to get rid of one vacant moment.

10:10:29.790 --> 10:10:32.830
"'You have had to seek no one's company, conversation,

10:10:33.090 --> 10:10:34.390
"'sympathy, forbearance.

10:10:34.490 --> 10:10:38.250
"'You have lived, in short, as an independent being ought to do.

10:10:38.650 --> 10:10:39.950
"'Take this advice.

10:10:44.390 --> 10:10:45.790
"'What else happen what may?

10:10:46.430 --> 10:10:50.490
"'Neglect it, go on as heretofore craving, whining, and idling,

10:10:50.810 --> 10:10:52.710
"'and suffer the results of your idiocy,

10:10:52.850 --> 10:10:55.170
"'however bad and insuperable they may be.

10:10:55.410 --> 10:10:57.730
"'I tell you this plainly, and listen.

10:10:58.090 --> 10:11:01.630
"'For though I shall no more repeat what I am now about to say,

10:11:01.850 --> 10:11:03.550
"'I shall steadily act on it.

10:11:04.210 --> 10:11:07.030
"'After my mother's death I wash my hands of you.

10:11:07.270 --> 10:11:10.770
"'From the day her coffin is carried to the vault in Gateshead Church

10:11:10.770 --> 10:11:14.310
"'you and I will be as separate as if we had never known each other.

10:11:14.390 --> 10:11:17.570
"'You need not think that because we chanced to be born

10:11:17.570 --> 10:11:19.590
"'of the same parents I shall suffer you

10:11:19.590 --> 10:11:21.770
"'to fasten me down by even the feeblest claim.

10:11:22.110 --> 10:11:23.610
"'I can tell you this.

10:11:23.770 --> 10:11:27.890
"'If the whole human race, ourselves accepted, were swept away

10:11:27.890 --> 10:11:30.370
"'and we too stood alone on the earth,

10:11:30.470 --> 10:11:34.650
"'I would leave you in the old world and betake myself to the new.'"

10:11:34.650 --> 10:11:36.850
She closed her lips.

10:11:37.910 --> 10:11:41.510
"'You might have spared yourself the trouble of delivering that tirade,'

10:11:41.950 --> 10:11:42.690
"'answered Georgiana.

10:11:44.390 --> 10:11:47.110
"'Because you are the most selfish, heartless creature in existence,

10:11:47.390 --> 10:11:49.730
"'and I know your spiteful hatred towards me.

10:11:49.890 --> 10:11:52.710
"'I have had a specimen of it before in the trick you played me

10:11:52.710 --> 10:11:54.350
"'about Lord Edwin Veer.

10:11:54.710 --> 10:11:58.050
"'You could not bear me to be raised above you, to have a title,

10:11:58.390 --> 10:12:01.690
"'to be received into circles where you dare not show your face,

10:12:01.710 --> 10:12:04.470
"'and so you acted the spy and informer

10:12:04.470 --> 10:12:07.030
"'and ruined my prospects for ever.'

10:12:07.030 --> 10:12:10.970
Georgiana took out her handkerchief and blew her nose for an hour afterwards.

10:12:11.730 --> 10:12:15.930
Eliza sat cold, impassable, and assiduously industrious.

10:12:17.250 --> 10:12:20.470
True, generous feeling is made small account of by some,

10:12:20.870 --> 10:12:22.530
but here were two natures rendered,

10:12:22.930 --> 10:12:24.770
the one intolerably acrid,

10:12:25.150 --> 10:12:27.790
the other despicably savourless for the want of it.

10:12:28.430 --> 10:12:30.970
Feeling without judgment is a washy-draught indeed,

10:12:31.430 --> 10:12:34.010
but judgment untempered by feeling is too bitter

10:12:34.010 --> 10:12:36.390
and husky a morsel for human deglutition.

10:12:37.890 --> 10:12:39.930
It was a wet and windy afternoon.

10:12:41.050 --> 10:12:43.090
Georgiana had fallen asleep on the sofa,

10:12:43.390 --> 10:12:44.810
overprousal of a novel.

10:12:45.490 --> 10:12:48.630
Eliza was gone to attend a saint's day service at the new church.

10:12:49.250 --> 10:12:52.110
For, in matters of religion, she was a rigid formalist.

10:12:52.690 --> 10:12:54.910
No weather ever prevented the punctual discharge

10:12:54.910 --> 10:12:57.030
of what she considered her devotional duties.

10:12:57.530 --> 10:13:00.550
Fair or foul, she went to church thrice every Sunday

10:13:00.550 --> 10:13:03.390
and as often on weekdays as there were prayers.

10:13:05.930 --> 10:13:07.670
I bethought myself to go upstairs

10:13:07.670 --> 10:13:11.310
and see how the dying woman sped, who lay there almost unheated.

10:13:11.550 --> 10:13:14.270
The very servants paid her but a remittent attention.

10:13:14.730 --> 10:13:17.090
The hired nurse, being little looked after,

10:13:17.410 --> 10:13:19.470
would slip out of the room whenever she could.

10:13:20.270 --> 10:13:23.430
Bessie was faithful, but she had her own family to mind

10:13:23.430 --> 10:13:25.510
and could only come occasionally to the hall.

10:13:26.390 --> 10:13:28.290
I found the sick room unwatched.

10:13:28.390 --> 10:13:30.710
As I had expected, no nurse was there.

10:13:31.130 --> 10:13:33.870
The patient lay still and seemingly lethargic.

10:13:34.330 --> 10:13:36.190
Her livid face sunk in the pillows.

10:13:37.670 --> 10:13:38.410
She was lying in the grate.

10:13:38.970 --> 10:13:41.670
I renewed the fuel, rearranged the bedclothes,

10:13:42.050 --> 10:13:44.830
gazed awhile on her who could not now gaze on me,

10:13:44.950 --> 10:13:46.430
and then I moved away to the window.

10:13:48.930 --> 10:13:51.570
The rain beat strongly against the panes.

10:13:51.790 --> 10:13:53.570
The wind blew tempestuously.

10:13:54.750 --> 10:13:56.610
One lies there, I thought,

10:13:56.910 --> 10:13:59.490
who will soon be beyond the war of earthly elements.

10:14:00.150 --> 10:14:03.750
Whither will that spirit, now struggling to quit its material tenement,

10:14:04.370 --> 10:14:06.010
flit when at length released?

10:14:07.670 --> 10:14:11.010
In pondering the great mystery, I thought of Helen Burns,

10:14:11.710 --> 10:14:13.090
recalled her dying words,

10:14:13.530 --> 10:14:17.170
her faith, her doctrine of the equality of disembodied souls.

10:14:17.870 --> 10:14:20.770
I was still listening and thought to her well-remembered tones,

10:14:21.330 --> 10:14:23.630
still picturing her pale and spiritual aspect,

10:14:24.010 --> 10:14:26.170
her wasted face and sublime gaze

10:14:26.170 --> 10:14:28.270
as she lay on her placid deathbed

10:14:28.270 --> 10:14:32.390
and whispered her longing to be restored to her divine father's bosom

10:14:32.390 --> 10:14:35.070
when a feeble voice murmured from the couch behind.

10:14:35.910 --> 10:14:37.250
Who is that?

10:14:38.970 --> 10:14:41.830
I knew Mrs. Reed had not spoken for days.

10:14:42.410 --> 10:14:43.270
Was she reviving?

10:14:43.750 --> 10:14:44.930
I went up to her.

10:14:46.070 --> 10:14:47.230
It is I, Aunt Reed.

10:14:48.710 --> 10:14:51.430
Who, I? was her answer.

10:14:51.930 --> 10:14:52.910
Who are you?

10:14:54.470 --> 10:14:58.290
Looking at me was surprised and a sort of alarm, but still not wildly.

10:14:59.330 --> 10:15:01.430
You are quite a stranger to me.

10:15:01.590 --> 10:15:02.410
Where is Bessie?

10:15:03.590 --> 10:15:05.250
She is at the lodge, Aunt.

10:15:07.670 --> 10:15:09.870
She repeated, Who calls me Aunt?

10:15:10.410 --> 10:15:13.090
You are not one of the Gipsons, and yet I know you.

10:15:13.750 --> 10:15:16.310
That face, and the eyes and forehead

10:15:16.310 --> 10:15:18.670
are quite familiar to me.

10:15:19.010 --> 10:15:22.210
You are like, Why, you are like Jane Eyre.

10:15:22.910 --> 10:15:23.990
I said nothing.

10:15:24.530 --> 10:15:27.730
I was afraid of occasioning some shock by declaring my identity.

10:15:29.050 --> 10:15:30.370
Yet, said she,

10:15:31.010 --> 10:15:34.150
I am afraid it is a mistake. My thoughts deceive me.

10:15:34.450 --> 10:15:36.270
I wished to see Jane Eyre,

10:15:37.670 --> 10:15:42.030
where none exists. Besides, in eight years she must be so changed.

10:15:42.930 --> 10:15:44.390
I now gently assured her

10:15:44.390 --> 10:15:47.610
that I was the person she had supposed and desired me to be.

10:15:47.910 --> 10:15:49.510
And seeing that I was understood,

10:15:49.730 --> 10:15:51.490
and that her senses were quite collected,

10:15:51.890 --> 10:15:55.590
I explained how Bessie had sent her husband to fetch me from Thornfield.

10:15:57.330 --> 10:15:59.210
I am very ill, I know,

10:15:59.410 --> 10:16:00.430
she said ere long.

10:16:00.950 --> 10:16:03.430
I was trying to turn myself a few minutes since,

10:16:03.730 --> 10:16:05.630
and I find I cannot move a limb.

10:16:07.670 --> 10:16:09.110
It is my mind before I die.

10:16:09.690 --> 10:16:12.350
What we think little of in health burdens us

10:16:12.350 --> 10:16:14.810
at such an hour as the present is to me.

10:16:15.110 --> 10:16:18.250
Is the nurse here, or is there no one in the room but you?

10:16:19.290 --> 10:16:21.050
I assured her we were alone.

10:16:21.910 --> 10:16:25.070
Well, I have twice done you a wrong which I regret now.

10:16:25.590 --> 10:16:27.990
One was in breaking the promise which I gave my husband

10:16:27.990 --> 10:16:29.710
to bring you up as my own child.

10:16:30.210 --> 10:16:32.190
The other, she stopped.

10:16:33.150 --> 10:16:35.790
After all, it is of no great importance perhaps,

10:16:37.670 --> 10:16:38.930
and then I might get better,

10:16:39.150 --> 10:16:41.370
and to humble myself so to her is painful.

10:16:42.430 --> 10:16:45.630
She made an effort to alter her position, but failed.

10:16:46.210 --> 10:16:47.390
Her face changed.

10:16:47.830 --> 10:16:50.510
She seemed to experience some inward sensation,

10:16:51.210 --> 10:16:54.250
the precursor perhaps of the last pang.

10:16:55.850 --> 10:16:57.790
Well, I must get it over.

10:16:58.450 --> 10:16:59.810
Eternity is before me.

10:17:00.210 --> 10:17:01.610
I had better tell her.

10:17:02.470 --> 10:17:04.650
Go to my dressing case, open it,

10:17:07.670 --> 10:17:08.310
and take her directions.

10:17:09.270 --> 10:17:11.070
Read the letter, she said.

10:17:11.970 --> 10:17:14.050
It was short and thus conceived.

10:17:15.710 --> 10:17:18.410
Madame, will you have the goodness to send me the address

10:17:18.410 --> 10:17:21.350
of my niece Jane Eyre and to tell me how she is?

10:17:21.650 --> 10:17:24.090
It is my intention to write shortly and desire her

10:17:24.090 --> 10:17:25.090
to come to me at Madera.

10:17:25.950 --> 10:17:28.850
Providence has blessed my endeavours to secure a competency,

10:17:29.310 --> 10:17:33.130
and as I am unmarried and childless I wish to adopt her

10:17:33.130 --> 10:17:35.410
during my life and bequeath her at my death

10:17:37.670 --> 10:17:40.470
I am Madame, etc., etc.

10:17:40.750 --> 10:17:42.090
John Eyre, Madera

10:17:43.030 --> 10:17:45.290
It was dated three years back.

10:17:46.190 --> 10:17:48.710
Why did I never hear of this? I asked.

10:17:49.950 --> 10:17:52.410
Because I disliked you too fixedly and thoroughly

10:17:52.410 --> 10:17:55.110
ever to lend a hand in lifting you to prosperity.

10:17:55.590 --> 10:17:57.670
I could not forget your conduct to me, Jane,

10:17:58.030 --> 10:18:00.490
the fury with which you once turned on me,

10:18:00.730 --> 10:18:02.750
the tone in which you declared you abhorred me

10:18:02.750 --> 10:18:04.390
the worst of anybody in the world,

10:18:07.670 --> 10:18:09.930
and the very thought of me made you sick

10:18:09.930 --> 10:18:12.890
and asserted that I had treated you with miserable cruelty.

10:18:13.570 --> 10:18:15.470
I could not forget my own sensations

10:18:15.470 --> 10:18:18.390
when you thus started up and poured out the venom of your mind.

10:18:18.970 --> 10:18:22.010
I felt fear as if an animal that I had struck or pushed

10:18:22.010 --> 10:18:25.410
had looked up at me with human eyes and cursed me in a man's voice.

10:18:26.370 --> 10:18:28.430
Bring me some water. Oh, make haste.

10:18:29.610 --> 10:18:31.550
Dear Mrs. Reed, said I,

10:18:31.630 --> 10:18:33.350
as I offered her the draught she required.

10:18:34.030 --> 10:18:36.930
Think no more of this. Let it pass away from your mind.

10:18:37.670 --> 10:18:39.370
Forgive me for my passionate language.

10:18:39.550 --> 10:18:43.490
I was a child then. Eight, nine years have passed since that day.

10:18:44.570 --> 10:18:46.370
She heeded nothing of what I said,

10:18:46.770 --> 10:18:48.950
but when she had tasted the water in drawn breath,

10:18:49.090 --> 10:18:50.090
she went on thus.

10:18:51.330 --> 10:18:53.510
I tell you I could not forget it,

10:18:53.610 --> 10:18:57.010
and I took my revenge. For you to be adopted by your uncle

10:18:57.010 --> 10:19:00.650
and placed in a state of ease and comfort was what I could not endure.

10:19:01.150 --> 10:19:04.490
I wrote to him. I said I was sorry for his disappointment,

10:19:04.850 --> 10:19:06.430
but Jane Eyre was dead.

10:19:07.670 --> 10:19:09.110
I had a typhus fever at Lowood.

10:19:10.070 --> 10:19:11.370
Now act as you please.

10:19:11.650 --> 10:19:13.270
Write and contradict my assertion.

10:19:13.490 --> 10:19:15.850
Expose my falsehood as soon as you like.

10:19:16.590 --> 10:19:18.710
You were born, I think, to be my torment.

10:19:19.270 --> 10:19:22.270
My last hour is wracked by the recollection of a deed

10:19:22.270 --> 10:19:25.550
which, but for you, I should never have been tempted to commit.

10:19:27.790 --> 10:19:30.810
If you could but be persuaded to think no more of an ant

10:19:30.810 --> 10:19:33.450
and to regard me with kindness and forgiveness.

10:19:35.690 --> 10:19:37.650
You have a very bad disposition

10:19:37.670 --> 10:19:38.910
said she.

10:19:39.630 --> 10:19:42.390
And one to this day I feel it impossible to understand

10:19:42.390 --> 10:19:46.790
how for nine years you could be patient and quiescent under any treatment

10:19:47.210 --> 10:19:49.930
and in the tenth break out all fire and violence

10:19:49.930 --> 10:19:51.230
I could never comprehend.

10:19:53.190 --> 10:19:55.530
My disposition is not so bad as you think.

10:19:55.690 --> 10:19:58.590
I am passionate, but not vindictive.

10:19:59.170 --> 10:20:00.910
Many a time as a little child

10:20:00.910 --> 10:20:04.490
I should have been glad to love you if you would have let me

10:20:04.490 --> 10:20:07.450
and I long earnestly to be reconciled to you now.

10:20:07.670 --> 10:20:08.670
Kiss me, aunt.

10:20:10.630 --> 10:20:12.550
I approached my cheek to her lips.

10:20:12.930 --> 10:20:14.350
She would not touch it.

10:20:14.690 --> 10:20:17.070
She said I oppressed her by leaning over the bed

10:20:17.070 --> 10:20:18.710
and again demanded water.

10:20:19.330 --> 10:20:22.990
As I laid her down, for I raised her and supported her on my arm

10:20:22.990 --> 10:20:23.710
while she drank.

10:20:24.390 --> 10:20:27.350
I covered her ice cold and clammy hand with mine.

10:20:28.110 --> 10:20:30.450
The feeble fingers shrank for my touch.

10:20:31.050 --> 10:20:32.910
The glazing eyes shunned my gaze.

10:20:38.050 --> 10:20:39.510
I said at last,

10:20:40.150 --> 10:20:42.110
You have my full and free forgiveness.

10:20:42.930 --> 10:20:45.630
Ask now for God's and be at peace.

10:20:47.390 --> 10:20:48.890
Poor suffering woman.

10:20:49.330 --> 10:20:53.610
It was too late for her to make now the effort to change her habitual frame of mind.

10:20:54.110 --> 10:20:55.930
Living she had ever hated me.

10:20:56.130 --> 10:20:57.970
Dying she must hate me still.

10:20:58.930 --> 10:21:01.190
The nurse now entered and Bessie followed.

10:21:02.410 --> 10:21:04.290
I yet lingered half an hour longer

10:21:04.290 --> 10:21:07.550
hoping to see some sign of amity but she gave none.

10:21:07.670 --> 10:21:10.590
She was fast relapsing into stupor.

10:21:11.230 --> 10:21:12.970
Nor did her mind again rally.

10:21:13.530 --> 10:21:15.610
At twelve o'clock that night she died.

10:21:16.390 --> 10:21:18.710
I was not present to close her eyes.

10:21:18.950 --> 10:21:20.390
Nor were either of her daughters.

10:21:21.010 --> 10:21:23.890
They came to tell us the next morning that all was over.

10:21:24.550 --> 10:21:26.430
She was by that time laid out.

10:21:27.050 --> 10:21:28.990
Eliza and I went to look at her.

10:21:29.430 --> 10:21:33.530
Georgiana who had burst out into loud weeping said she dared not go.

10:21:34.510 --> 10:21:35.510
There was stretched.

10:21:37.670 --> 10:21:38.550
She was in an active frame.

10:21:38.770 --> 10:21:40.050
Rigid and still.

10:21:40.850 --> 10:21:43.350
Her eye of flint was covered with its cold lid.

10:21:43.910 --> 10:21:48.750
Her brow and strong traits wore yet the impress of her inexorable soul.

10:21:49.610 --> 10:21:52.830
A strange and solemn object was that corpse to me.

10:21:53.070 --> 10:21:55.110
I gazed on it with gloom and pain.

10:21:55.810 --> 10:21:56.830
Nothing soft.

10:21:57.070 --> 10:21:57.830
Nothing sweet.

10:21:58.350 --> 10:22:02.570
Nothing pitying or hopeful or subduing did it inspire.

10:22:03.390 --> 10:22:06.250
Only a grating anguish for her woes.

10:22:07.730 --> 10:22:12.830
And a somber, tearless dismay at the fearfulness of death in such a form.

10:22:14.390 --> 10:22:16.230
Eliza surveyed her parent calmly.

10:22:17.010 --> 10:22:19.750
After a silence of some minutes she observed.

10:22:21.450 --> 10:22:24.970
With her constitution she should have lived to a good old age.

10:22:25.690 --> 10:22:27.410
Her life was shortened by trouble.

10:22:28.430 --> 10:22:30.990
And then a spasm constricted her mouth for an instant.

10:22:31.770 --> 10:22:34.270
As it passed away she turned and left the room.

10:22:34.470 --> 10:22:35.730
And so did I.

10:22:36.290 --> 10:22:38.870
Neither of us had dropped a tear.

10:23:02.610 --> 10:23:09.210
Jane Eyre by Charlotte Bronte, Chapter 22

10:23:16.270 --> 10:23:25.730
Mr. Rochester had given me but one week's leave of absence, yet a month elapsed before I quitted Gateshead.

10:23:26.330 --> 10:23:35.750
I wished to leave immediately after the funeral, but Georgiana entreated me to stay till she could get off to London.

10:23:37.010 --> 10:23:49.710
With her, she was now at last invited by her uncle, Mr. Gibson, who had come down to direct his sister's interment and settle family affairs.

10:23:50.790 --> 10:23:56.110
Georgiana said she dreaded being left alone with Eliza.

10:23:56.510 --> 10:24:04.970
From her, she got neither sympathy in her dejection, support in her fears, nor aid in her preparations.

10:24:05.890 --> 10:24:19.970
So I bore with her feeble-minded wailings and selfish lamentations as well as I could, and did my best in sewing for her and packing her dresses.

10:24:20.540 --> 10:24:36.650
It is true that while I worked, she would idle, and I thought to myself, if you and I were destined to live always together, cousin, we would commence matters on a different footing.

10:24:37.360 --> 10:24:42.310
I should not settle tamely down into being the forbearing party.

10:24:42.730 --> 10:24:51.410
I should assign you your share of labour and compel you to accomplish it, or else it should be left undone.

10:24:52.330 --> 10:25:01.850
I should insist also on your keeping some of those drawling half-insincere complaints hushed in your own breast.

10:25:02.510 --> 10:25:18.010
It is only because our connection happens to be very transitory and comes at a peculiarly mournful season that I consent thus to render it so patient and compliant on my part.

10:25:18.710 --> 10:25:28.890
At last I saw Georgiana off, but now it was Eliza's turn to request me to stay another week.

10:25:29.650 --> 10:25:35.050
Her plans required all her time and attention, she said.

10:25:35.790 --> 10:25:54.170
She was about to depart for some unknown bourn, and all day long she stayed in her own room, her door bolted within, filling trunks, emptying drawers, burning papers, and holding no communication with anyone.

10:25:54.970 --> 10:26:02.990
She wished me to look after the house, to see callers, and answer notes of condolence.

10:26:03.910 --> 10:26:09.430
One morning she told me I was liberty, and she added,

10:26:09.970 --> 10:26:15.190
I am obliged to you for your valuable services and discreet conduct.

10:26:15.650 --> 10:26:22.090
There is some difference between living with such and one as you and with Georgiana.

10:26:22.950 --> 10:26:28.310
You perform your own part in life and burden no one.

10:26:29.210 --> 10:26:32.570
Tomorrow, she continued, I set out for the continent.

10:26:33.190 --> 10:26:40.410
I shall take up my abode in a religious house near Lille, a nunnery, you would call it.

10:26:40.710 --> 10:26:43.850
There I shall be quiet and unmolested.

10:26:44.310 --> 10:26:55.850
I shall devote myself for a time to the examination of the Roman Catholic dogmas and to a careful study of the workings of their system.

10:26:56.490 --> 10:27:14.650
If I find it to be, as I half suspect it is, the one best calculated to ensure the doing of all things, decently and in order, I shall embrace the tenets of Rome and probably take the veil.

10:27:15.430 --> 10:27:22.010
I neither expressed surprise at this resolution nor attempted to dissuade her from it.

10:27:22.010 --> 10:27:26.210
The vocation will fit you to a hair, I thought.

10:27:26.830 --> 10:27:28.530
Much good may it do you.

10:27:30.210 --> 10:27:31.810
When we parted she said,

10:27:31.970 --> 10:27:33.690
Good-bye, cousin, Jane Eyre.

10:27:33.930 --> 10:27:34.990
I wish you well.

10:27:35.250 --> 10:27:36.850
You have some sense.

10:27:37.530 --> 10:27:38.670
I then returned.

10:27:39.090 --> 10:27:42.130
You are not without sense, cousin Eliza.

10:27:42.450 --> 10:27:49.830
But what you have, I suppose, in another year will be walled up alive in a French convent.

10:27:49.830 --> 10:27:54.210
However, it is not my business and so it suits you.

10:27:54.410 --> 10:27:55.770
I don't much care.

10:27:56.770 --> 10:28:04.010
You are in the right, said she, and with these words we each went our separate way.

10:28:04.730 --> 10:28:19.630
As I shall not have occasion to refer either to her or her sister again, I may as well mention here that Georgiana made an advantageous match with a wealthy worn-out man of fashion.

10:28:19.630 --> 10:28:33.690
And that Eliza actually took the veil and is at this day superior of the convent where she passed the period of her novitiate and which she endowed with her fortune.

10:28:34.650 --> 10:28:42.370
How people feel when they are returning home from an absence, long or short, I did not know.

10:28:42.810 --> 10:28:45.790
I had never experienced the sensation.

10:28:45.790 --> 10:29:04.790
I had known what it was to come back to Gateshead when a child after a long walk, to be scolded for looking cold or gloomy, and later what it was to come back from church to Lowood to long for a plenteous meal and a good fire.

10:29:05.790 --> 10:29:08.370
And to be unable to get either.

10:29:09.170 --> 10:29:13.070
Neither of these returnings was very pleasant or desirable.

10:29:13.850 --> 10:29:23.870
No magnet drew me to a given point, increasing in its strength, of attraction the nearer I came.

10:29:24.350 --> 10:29:27.890
The return to Thornfield was yet to be tried.

10:29:29.970 --> 10:29:34.310
My journey seemed tedious, very tedious.

10:29:35.110 --> 10:29:41.730
Fifty miles one day, a night spent at an inn, fifty miles the next day.

10:29:41.730 --> 10:29:48.350
During the first twelve hours I thought of Mrs. Reed in her last moments.

10:29:49.110 --> 10:29:57.630
I saw her disfigured and discoloured face and heard her strangely altered voice.

10:29:58.350 --> 10:30:06.070
I mused on the funeral day the coffin, the hearse, the black train of tenants and servants.

10:30:06.790 --> 10:30:08.890
Few was the number of relatives.

10:30:09.650 --> 10:30:14.930
The gaping vault, the silent church, the solemn service.

10:30:15.850 --> 10:30:18.770
Then I thought of Elisa and Georgiana.

10:30:19.630 --> 10:30:27.170
I beheld one the sign-assure of a ballroom, the other the inmate of a convent cell.

10:30:27.590 --> 10:30:35.050
And I dwelt on and analysed their separate peculiarities of person and character.

10:30:37.410 --> 10:30:43.590
The evening arrival at the great town of scattered these thoughts.

10:30:44.410 --> 10:30:46.810
Night gave them quite another turn.

10:30:47.550 --> 10:30:50.610
I lay down on my traveller's bed.

10:30:51.190 --> 10:30:54.290
I left reminiscence for anticipation.

10:30:55.970 --> 10:31:01.590
I was going back to Thornfield, but how long was I to stay there?

10:31:02.210 --> 10:31:04.510
Not long of that I was sure.

10:31:05.210 --> 10:31:09.930
I had heard from Mrs. Fairfax in the interim of my absence.

10:31:10.590 --> 10:31:13.530
The party at the hall was dispersed.

10:31:14.310 --> 10:31:21.850
Mr. Rochester had left for London three weeks ago, but he was then expected to return in a fortnight.

10:31:22.710 --> 10:31:28.750
Mrs. Fairfax surmised that he was gone to make arrangements for his wedding,

10:31:29.370 --> 10:31:32.270
as he had talked of purchasing a new carriage.

10:31:32.810 --> 10:31:39.430
She said the idea of his marrying Miss Ingram still seemed strange to her,

10:31:39.710 --> 10:31:45.530
but from what everybody said and from what she had herself seen

10:31:45.530 --> 10:31:51.070
she could no longer doubt that the event would shortly take place.

10:31:51.830 --> 10:31:58.130
You would be strangely incredulous if you did doubt it, was my mental comment.

10:31:58.470 --> 10:32:00.210
I don't doubt it.

10:32:01.870 --> 10:32:03.470
The question followed.

10:32:03.970 --> 10:32:05.350
Where was I to go?

10:32:05.850 --> 10:32:08.670
I dreamt of Miss Ingram all the night.

10:32:08.910 --> 10:32:14.710
In a vivid morning dream I saw her closing the gates of Thornfield against me

10:32:14.710 --> 10:32:17.510
and pointing me out another road,

10:32:18.010 --> 10:32:21.510
and Mr. Rochester looked on with his arms folded,

10:32:22.310 --> 10:32:27.590
smiling sardonically, as it seemed at both her and me.

10:32:28.190 --> 10:32:34.230
I had not notified to Mrs. Fairfax the exact date of my return,

10:32:34.830 --> 10:32:39.850
for I did not wish either car or carriage to meet me at Millcote.

10:32:40.530 --> 10:32:44.830
I proposed to walk the distance quietly by myself,

10:32:45.170 --> 10:32:49.570
and very quietly, after leaving my box in the Osler's care,

10:32:50.070 --> 10:32:54.870
did I slip away from the George Inn about six o'clock of a June evening

10:32:54.870 --> 10:32:57.870
and take the old road to Thornfield,

10:32:58.510 --> 10:33:04.330
a road which lay chiefly through fields and was now a little frequented.

10:33:05.410 --> 10:33:12.510
It was not a bright or splendid summer evening, though fair and soft.

10:33:13.030 --> 10:33:16.350
The haymakers were at work all along the road,

10:33:16.530 --> 10:33:22.850
and the sky, though far from cloudless, was such as promised well for the future.

10:33:22.850 --> 10:33:29.070
Its blue, where blue was visible, was mild and settled,

10:33:29.530 --> 10:33:33.010
and its cloud strata high and thin.

10:33:33.870 --> 10:33:38.910
The west too was warm, no watery gleam chilled it.

10:33:39.070 --> 10:33:47.270
It seemed as if there was a fire lit, an altar burning behind its screen of marbled vapour,

10:33:47.590 --> 10:33:52.090
and out of the apertures shone a golden redness.

10:33:52.090 --> 10:33:57.490
I felt glad as the road shortened before me,

10:33:57.730 --> 10:34:04.230
so glad that I stopped once to ask myself what joy meant,

10:34:04.610 --> 10:34:10.790
and to remind reason that it was not to my home I was going,

10:34:11.110 --> 10:34:14.190
or to a permanent resting place,

10:34:14.450 --> 10:34:20.110
or to a place where fond friends looked out for me and waited my arrival.

10:34:20.110 --> 10:34:27.510
Mrs Fairfax will smile you a calm welcome, to be sure, said I,

10:34:27.990 --> 10:34:32.930
and little Adele will clap her hands and jump to see you,

10:34:33.110 --> 10:34:38.270
but you know very well you are thinking of another than they,

10:34:40.510 --> 10:34:45.230
and that he is not thinking of you.

10:34:47.330 --> 10:34:51.490
But what is so headstrong as youth?

10:34:52.230 --> 10:34:55.230
What so blind as inexperience?

10:34:56.410 --> 10:35:01.410
These affirmed that it was pleasure enough to have the privilege

10:35:01.410 --> 10:35:07.660
of again looking on Mr Rochester, whether he looked on me or not.

10:35:08.690 --> 10:35:10.030
And they added,

10:35:10.030 --> 10:35:15.150
Heyson, Heyson, be with him while you may,

10:35:15.690 --> 10:35:22.130
but a few more days or weeks at most, and you are parted from him for ever.

10:35:22.630 --> 10:35:28.350
And then I strangled a new-born agony, a deformed thing,

10:35:28.730 --> 10:35:34.250
which I could not persuade myself to own and rear, and ran on.

10:35:36.230 --> 10:35:40.510
They are making hay too in thorn-field meadows,

10:35:40.630 --> 10:35:44.470
or rather the labourers are just quitting their work

10:35:44.470 --> 10:35:48.430
and returning home with their rakes on their shoulders.

10:35:49.150 --> 10:35:52.110
Now at the hour I arrive.

10:35:52.670 --> 10:35:57.310
I have but a field or two to traverse,

10:35:57.670 --> 10:36:01.630
and then I shall cross the road and reach the gates.

10:36:01.630 --> 10:36:05.150
How full the hedges are of roses!

10:36:05.830 --> 10:36:08.430
But I have no time to gather any.

10:36:08.830 --> 10:36:10.810
I want to be at the house.

10:36:11.350 --> 10:36:17.330
I passed a tall briar shooting leafy and flowery branches across the path.

10:36:17.950 --> 10:36:21.610
I see the narrow stile with stone steps,

10:36:21.950 --> 10:36:25.770
and I see Mr Rochester sitting there,

10:36:25.970 --> 10:36:28.850
a book and a pencil in his hand.

10:36:28.850 --> 10:36:30.230
He is writing.

10:36:33.050 --> 10:36:39.050
Well, he is not a ghost, yet every nerve I have is unstrung.

10:36:39.290 --> 10:36:42.830
For a moment I am beyond my own mastery.

10:36:43.310 --> 10:36:44.530
What does it mean?

10:36:44.930 --> 10:36:49.410
I did not think I should tremble in this way when I saw him,

10:36:49.810 --> 10:36:53.910
or lose my voice or the power of motion in his presence.

10:36:54.390 --> 10:36:57.630
I will go back as soon as I can stir.

10:36:57.630 --> 10:37:01.550
I need not make an absolute fool of myself.

10:37:02.310 --> 10:37:04.210
I know another way to the house.

10:37:04.810 --> 10:37:08.090
It does not signify if I knew twenty ways,

10:37:08.450 --> 10:37:09.870
for he has seen me.

10:37:13.430 --> 10:37:17.290
Hello, he cries, and he puts up his book and his pencil.

10:37:17.690 --> 10:37:20.770
There you are. Come on, if you please.

10:37:21.690 --> 10:37:23.950
I suppose I do come on.

10:37:24.370 --> 10:37:26.670
Though in what fashion, I know not.

10:37:26.670 --> 10:37:29.930
Being scarcely cognizant of my movements,

10:37:30.550 --> 10:37:33.710
and solicitous only to appear calm,

10:37:34.070 --> 10:37:38.810
and above all to control the working muscles of my face,

10:37:39.330 --> 10:37:43.230
which I feel rebel insolently against my will,

10:37:43.710 --> 10:37:48.190
and struggle to express what I have resolved to conceal.

10:37:49.110 --> 10:37:52.230
But I have a veil. It is down.

10:37:52.230 --> 10:37:57.530
I am a makeshift yet to behave with decent composure.

10:37:58.510 --> 10:38:00.550
And this is Jane Eyre.

10:38:01.110 --> 10:38:04.270
Are you coming from Millcote, and on foot?

10:38:05.130 --> 10:38:08.010
Yes, just one of your tricks.

10:38:08.390 --> 10:38:10.250
Not to send for a carriage,

10:38:11.250 --> 10:38:15.990
and come clattering over street and road like a common mortal,

10:38:16.650 --> 10:38:21.470
but to steal into the vicinage of your home along with twilight,

10:38:21.470 --> 10:38:26.310
just as if you were a dream or a shade.

10:38:26.910 --> 10:38:31.850
What deduce have you done with yourself this last month?

10:38:34.870 --> 10:38:38.750
I have been with my answer, who is dead.

10:38:39.930 --> 10:38:42.610
A true Janean reply.

10:38:43.490 --> 10:38:45.710
Good angels be my guard.

10:38:46.150 --> 10:38:48.570
She comes from the other world,

10:38:48.570 --> 10:38:51.970
from the abode of people who are dead,

10:38:52.230 --> 10:38:56.970
and tells me so when she meets me alone here in the gloaming.

10:38:57.450 --> 10:39:00.030
If I dared, I'd touch you,

10:39:00.190 --> 10:39:04.050
to see if you are substance or shadow, you elf.

10:39:04.710 --> 10:39:08.510
But I'd as soon offer to take hold of a blue,

10:39:08.710 --> 10:39:12.490
ignis fatuous light in a marsh.

10:39:13.390 --> 10:39:16.590
Truant, Truant, he added,

10:39:16.590 --> 10:39:18.970
when he had paused an instant.

10:39:19.510 --> 10:39:21.770
Absent from me a whole month,

10:39:22.310 --> 10:39:25.030
and forgetting me quite, I'll be sworn.

10:39:27.910 --> 10:39:32.310
I knew there would be pleasure in meeting my master again,

10:39:32.930 --> 10:39:35.310
even though I'd broken by the fear

10:39:35.310 --> 10:39:39.250
that he was so soon to cease to be my master,

10:39:39.550 --> 10:39:43.770
and by the knowledge that I was nothing to him.

10:39:43.770 --> 10:39:47.010
But there was ever in Mr. Rochester,

10:39:47.390 --> 10:39:48.930
so at least I thought,

10:39:49.410 --> 10:39:53.430
such a wealth of the power of communicating happiness,

10:39:54.190 --> 10:39:58.930
that taste but of the crumbs he scattered to stray,

10:39:59.510 --> 10:40:04.550
and stranger birds like me was to feast genially.

10:40:05.090 --> 10:40:07.710
His last words were balm.

10:40:08.190 --> 10:40:12.350
They seemed to imply that he's imported something to him.

10:40:12.350 --> 10:40:15.690
Whether I forgot him or not,

10:40:16.310 --> 10:40:20.130
and he had spoken of Thornfield as my home,

10:40:20.690 --> 10:40:23.250
would that it were my home.

10:40:24.450 --> 10:40:26.370
He did not leave the stile,

10:40:26.570 --> 10:40:29.550
and I hardly liked to ask to go by.

10:40:30.170 --> 10:40:33.890
I inquired soon if he had not been to London.

10:40:35.790 --> 10:40:40.150
Yes, I suppose you found that out by second sight.

10:40:41.210 --> 10:40:44.150
Mrs. Fairfax told me in a letter.

10:40:45.670 --> 10:40:49.250
And did she inform you what I went to do?

10:40:50.210 --> 10:40:53.530
Oh, yes, sir. Everybody knew your errand.

10:40:54.890 --> 10:40:57.010
You must see the carriage, Jane,

10:40:57.270 --> 10:41:02.150
and tell me if you don't think it will suit Mrs. Rochester exactly,

10:41:03.570 --> 10:41:07.210
and whether she won't look like Queen Bodicea

10:41:07.210 --> 10:41:11.330
leaning back against those purple cushions.

10:41:11.630 --> 10:41:15.150
I wish, Jane, I were a trifle better adapted

10:41:15.150 --> 10:41:17.890
to match with her externally.

10:41:18.670 --> 10:41:21.330
Tell me now, fairy as you are,

10:41:21.650 --> 10:41:25.310
can't you give me a charm or a filter

10:41:25.310 --> 10:41:30.630
or something of that sort to make me a handsome man?

10:41:32.350 --> 10:41:36.390
It would be past the power of magic, sir,

10:41:36.390 --> 10:41:38.910
and in thought I added,

10:41:39.390 --> 10:41:42.430
a loving eye is all the charm needed

10:41:42.430 --> 10:41:45.590
to such you are handsome enough.

10:41:47.030 --> 10:41:52.850
Or rather, your sternness has a power beyond beauty.

10:41:54.870 --> 10:41:58.910
Mr. Rochester had sometimes read my unspoken thoughts

10:41:58.910 --> 10:42:02.410
with an acumen to me incomprehensible.

10:42:02.410 --> 10:42:06.230
In the present instance he took no notice

10:42:06.230 --> 10:42:08.450
of my abrupt focal response,

10:42:09.530 --> 10:42:15.030
but he smiled at me with a certain smile he had of his own,

10:42:15.350 --> 10:42:18.550
and which he used but on rare occasions.

10:42:19.110 --> 10:42:22.370
He seemed to think it too good for common purposes.

10:42:22.830 --> 10:42:25.570
It was the real sunshine of feeling.

10:42:25.990 --> 10:42:28.150
He shed it over me now.

10:42:29.030 --> 10:42:31.530
Pass, Janet, said he,

10:42:31.690 --> 10:42:34.330
making room for me to cross the stile.

10:42:34.810 --> 10:42:40.270
Go up home and stay your weary little wandering feet

10:42:40.270 --> 10:42:42.970
at a friend's threshold.

10:42:44.130 --> 10:42:48.990
All I had now to do was to obey him in silence.

10:42:49.690 --> 10:42:53.430
No need for me to colloquise further.

10:42:54.250 --> 10:42:56.990
I got over the stile without a word

10:42:56.990 --> 10:42:59.690
and meant to leave him calmly.

10:43:00.450 --> 10:43:02.670
An impulse held me fast.

10:43:03.590 --> 10:43:08.030
A force turned me round, I said,

10:43:08.590 --> 10:43:11.130
or something in me said for me,

10:43:11.590 --> 10:43:13.250
and in spite of me.

10:43:14.510 --> 10:43:18.190
Thank you, Mr. Rochester, for your great kindness.

10:43:18.430 --> 10:43:22.970
I am strangely glad to get back again to you,

10:43:22.970 --> 10:43:28.010
and wherever you are is my home, my only home.

10:43:29.190 --> 10:43:33.690
I walked on so fast that even he could hardly have overtaken me

10:43:33.690 --> 10:43:34.850
had he tried.

10:43:36.110 --> 10:43:40.370
Little Adele was half wild with delight when she saw me.

10:43:40.810 --> 10:43:45.870
Mrs. Fairfax received me with her usual plain friendliness.

10:43:46.810 --> 10:43:52.130
Leah smiled, and even Sophie bid me bonsoir

10:43:52.130 --> 10:43:53.750
with glee.

10:43:54.430 --> 10:43:56.070
This was very pleasant.

10:43:56.410 --> 10:44:01.610
There is no happiness like that of being loved by your fellow creatures

10:44:01.610 --> 10:44:06.730
and feeling that your presence is an addition to their comfort.

10:44:07.890 --> 10:44:12.390
I that evening shut my eyes resolutely against the future.

10:44:13.150 --> 10:44:17.970
I stopped my cars against the voice that kept warning me

10:44:17.970 --> 10:44:20.950
of near separation and coming grief.

10:44:20.950 --> 10:44:25.890
When tea was over, and Mrs. Fairfax had taken her knitting,

10:44:26.330 --> 10:44:29.610
and I had assumed a low seat near her,

10:44:29.870 --> 10:44:35.050
and Adele kneeling on the carpet had nestled close up to me,

10:44:35.330 --> 10:44:39.750
and a sense of mutual affection seemed to surround us

10:44:39.750 --> 10:44:42.250
with a ring of golden peace,

10:44:42.830 --> 10:44:49.310
I uttered a silent prayer that we might not be parted far or soon.

10:44:49.310 --> 10:44:55.650
But when, as we thus sat, Mr. Rochester entered unannounced,

10:44:56.050 --> 10:45:02.430
and looking at us, seemed to take pleasure in the spectacle of a group so amicable,

10:45:03.090 --> 10:45:06.990
when he said he supposed the old lady was all right,

10:45:07.450 --> 10:45:11.430
now that she had got her adopt daughter back again,

10:45:11.430 --> 10:45:15.010
and added that he saw Adele was

10:45:15.010 --> 10:45:19.190
prêt et croquer sa petite maman anglaise.

10:45:19.710 --> 10:45:24.510
I half ventured to hope that he would even after his marriage

10:45:24.510 --> 10:45:29.250
keep us together somewhere under the shelter of his protection,

10:45:29.650 --> 10:45:34.570
and not quite exiled from the sunshine of his presence.

10:45:35.910 --> 10:45:42.230
A fortnight of dubious calm succeeded my return to Thornfield Hall.

10:45:42.930 --> 10:45:45.370
Nothing was said of the master's marriage,

10:45:45.370 --> 10:45:49.750
and I saw no preparation going on for such an event.

10:45:50.550 --> 10:45:56.810
Almost every day I asked Mrs. Fairfax if she had yet heard anything decided.

10:45:57.370 --> 10:46:00.350
Her answer was always in the negative.

10:46:01.230 --> 10:46:06.450
Once, she said, she had actually put the question to Mr. Rochester

10:46:06.450 --> 10:46:10.490
as to when he was going to bring his bride home.

10:46:11.150 --> 10:46:16.590
But he had answered her only by a joke and one of his queer looks,

10:46:17.470 --> 10:46:20.730
and she could not tell what to make of him.

10:46:21.910 --> 10:46:26.230
One thing specially surprised me, and that was

10:46:26.230 --> 10:46:29.830
There were no journeyings backward and forward,

10:46:30.430 --> 10:46:32.990
no visits to Ingram Park.

10:46:33.290 --> 10:46:37.910
To be sure, it was twenty miles off on the borders of another county,

10:46:38.330 --> 10:46:41.630
but what was that distance to an ardent lover?

10:46:42.490 --> 10:46:47.390
To so practised and indefatigable a horseman as Mr. Rochester,

10:46:48.030 --> 10:46:50.390
it would be but a morning's ride.

10:46:50.390 --> 10:46:55.470
I began to cherish hopes I had no right to conceive,

10:46:56.290 --> 10:46:58.470
that the match was broken off,

10:46:59.090 --> 10:47:01.090
that rumour had been mistaken,

10:47:01.810 --> 10:47:05.090
that one or both parties had changed their minds.

10:47:05.710 --> 10:47:11.410
I used to look at my master's face to see if it was sad or fierce,

10:47:11.530 --> 10:47:19.830
but I could not remember the time when it had been so uniformly clear of clouds or evil feelings.

10:47:19.830 --> 10:47:24.610
If, in the moments I and my pupil spent with him,

10:47:24.730 --> 10:47:29.010
I lacked spirits and sank into inevitable dejection,

10:47:29.990 --> 10:47:32.130
he became even gay.

10:47:32.870 --> 10:47:36.510
Neither had he called me more frequently to his presence,

10:47:36.990 --> 10:47:39.530
never been kinder to me when there,

10:47:39.850 --> 10:47:44.610
and alas, never had I loved him so well.

10:47:52.850 --> 10:47:54.250
Thank you.

10:48:19.090 --> 10:48:25.430
CHAPTER XXIII A

10:48:25.430 --> 10:48:35.230
Splendid midsummer shone over England, skies so pure, suns so radiant, as were then seen

10:48:35.230 --> 10:48:43.890
in long succession, seldom favour, even singly, our wave-girt land.

10:48:44.890 --> 10:48:51.670
It was as if a band of Italian days had come from the south like a flock of glorious passenger

10:48:52.390 --> 10:49:00.070
and lighted to rest them on the cliffs of Albion. The hay was all got in, the fields

10:49:00.070 --> 10:49:08.690
round Thornfield were green and shorn, the roads white and baked, the trees were in their dark

10:49:08.690 --> 10:49:17.990
prime, hedge and wood, full-leaved and deeply tinted, contrasted well with the sunny hue

10:49:17.990 --> 10:49:26.210
of the cleared meadows between. On Midsummer Eve Adele, weary with gathering wild strawberries

10:49:26.210 --> 10:49:32.330
in Hay Lane half the day, had gone to bed with the sun. I watched her drop asleep,

10:49:32.330 --> 10:49:41.030
and when I left her I sought the garden. It was now the sweetest hour of the 24,

10:49:41.750 --> 10:49:50.690
day its fervid fires had wasted, and dew fell cool on Panting Plain and Scorched Summit.

10:49:52.170 --> 10:50:00.170
Where the sun had gone down in simple state, pure of the pomp of clouds spread a solemn

10:50:00.170 --> 10:50:08.690
purple burning with the light of red jewel and furnace flame at one point. On one hill peak,

10:50:08.690 --> 10:50:15.450
and extending high and wide, soft and still, softer over half heaven,

10:50:16.030 --> 10:50:24.410
East had its own charm or fine deep blue, and its own modest gem a casino and solitary star.

10:50:24.770 --> 10:50:29.470
Soon it would boast the moon, but she was yet beneath the horizon.

10:50:30.810 --> 10:50:37.890
I walked a while on the pavement, but a subtle, well-known scent, that of a cigar,

10:50:37.890 --> 10:50:45.970
stole from some window. I saw the library casement open at hand breadth. I knew I might be watched

10:50:45.970 --> 10:50:55.470
thence, so I went part into the orchard. No nook in the grounds more sheltered and more Eden-like.

10:50:55.990 --> 10:51:03.330
It was full of trees, it bloomed with flowers. A very high wall shut it out from the court

10:51:03.330 --> 10:51:08.990
on one side. On the other a beach avenue screamed it from the lawn.

10:51:09.890 --> 10:51:17.890
At the bottom was a sunk fence. Its sole separation from lonely fields a winding walk

10:51:17.890 --> 10:51:24.450
bordered with laurels and terminating in a giant horse chestnut, circled at the base by a seat,

10:51:24.850 --> 10:51:31.410
led down to the fence. Here one could wander unseen. While such honeydew fell,

10:51:31.410 --> 10:51:39.330
such silence rained, such gloaming gathered, I felt as if I could haunt such shade for ever.

10:51:39.610 --> 10:51:46.350
But in threading the flower and fruit parterres at the upper part of the enclosure,

10:51:46.770 --> 10:51:53.190
enticed there by the light, the now rising moon cast on this more open quarter,

10:51:53.190 --> 10:52:03.190
my step is stayed, not by sound, not by sight, but once more by a warning fragrance.

10:52:04.390 --> 10:52:12.570
Sweet brier and southern wood, jasmine, pink and rose have long been yielding their evening

10:52:13.040 --> 10:52:24.190
of incense. This new scent is neither of shrub nor flower. It is, I know it well. It is Mr.

10:52:24.430 --> 10:52:34.420
Rochester's cigar. I look round and I listen. I see trees laden with ripening fruit. I hear a

10:52:34.420 --> 10:52:44.940
gale warbling in a wood half a mile off. No moving form is visible. No coming step audible,

10:52:45.540 --> 10:52:53.860
but that perfume increases. I must flee. I make for the wicket leading to the shrubbery,

10:52:54.060 --> 10:53:02.700
and I see Mr. Rochester entering. I step aside into the ivy recess. He will not stay long.

10:53:02.700 --> 10:53:09.120
He will soon return whence he came, and if I sit still he will never see me.

10:53:09.800 --> 10:53:18.300
But no, even tide is as pleasant to him as to me, and this antique garden as attractive.

10:53:18.460 --> 10:53:26.120
And he strolls on, now lifting the gooseberry tree branches to look at the fruit, large as plums,

10:53:26.120 --> 10:53:30.980
with which they are laden, now taking a ripe cherry from the wall,

10:53:31.340 --> 10:53:39.100
now stooping towards a knot of flowers either to inhale their fragrance or to admire the dew

10:53:39.100 --> 10:53:56.100
beads on their petals. A great moth goes humming by me. It alights on a plant at Mr. Rochester's

10:53:56.100 --> 10:54:05.780
thought I, and he is occupied too. Perhaps if I walk softly I can slip away unnoticed.

10:54:06.900 --> 10:54:15.220
I trod on an edging of turf that the crackle of the pebbly gravel might not betray me.

10:54:15.960 --> 10:54:21.900
He was standing among the beds at a yard or two distance from where I had to pass.

10:54:22.460 --> 10:54:25.500
The moth apparently engaged him.

10:54:25.960 --> 10:54:32.820
I shall get by very well, I meditated, as I crossed his shadow thrown long over the garden

10:54:32.820 --> 10:54:38.840
by the moon, not yet risen high. He said quietly, without turning,

10:54:40.400 --> 10:54:43.500
Jane, come and look at this fellow.

10:54:44.460 --> 10:54:51.880
I had made no noise. He had not eyes behind. Could his shadow feel?

10:54:51.900 --> 10:54:55.940
I started at first, and then I approached him.

10:54:57.240 --> 10:55:03.800
Look at his wings, said he. He reminds me rather of a West Indian insect.

10:55:04.460 --> 10:55:10.120
One does not often see so large and gay a night-rover in England.

10:55:11.100 --> 10:55:13.040
There he has flown.

10:55:13.940 --> 10:55:21.380
The moth roamed away. I was sheepishly retreating also, but Mr. Rochester followed me,

10:55:21.380 --> 10:55:24.220
and when we reached the wicket, he said,

10:55:25.160 --> 10:55:30.560
Turn back. On so lovely a night it is ashamed to sit in the house,

10:55:30.780 --> 10:55:37.480
and surely no one can wish to go to bed while sunset is thus at meeting with moonrise.

10:55:38.880 --> 10:55:45.660
It is one of my faults that though my tongue is sometimes prompt enough as an answer,

10:55:46.220 --> 10:55:50.820
there are times when it sadly fails me in framing an excuse.

10:55:50.820 --> 10:55:59.880
And always the lapse occurs at some crisis, when a facile word or plausible pretext is

10:55:59.880 --> 10:56:04.360
specially wanting to get me out of painful embarrassment.

10:56:05.340 --> 10:56:11.720
I did not like to walk at this hour alone with Mr. Rochester in the shadowy orchard,

10:56:11.720 --> 10:56:15.620
but I could not find a reason to allege for leaving him.

10:56:16.320 --> 10:56:24.240
I followed with lagging step, and thoughts busily bent on discovering a means of extrication.

10:56:24.820 --> 10:56:33.200
But he himself looked so composed and so grave also, I became ashamed of feeling any confusion.

10:56:33.960 --> 10:56:40.900
The evil, if evil existent or prospective there was, seemed to lie with me only.

10:56:41.420 --> 10:56:44.740
His mind was unconscious and quiet.

10:56:46.440 --> 10:56:53.340
Jane, he recommenced as we entered the laurel walk, and slowly strayed down in the direction

10:56:53.340 --> 10:56:59.820
of the sunk fence and the horse chestnut. Thornfield is a pleasant place in summer,

10:57:00.000 --> 10:57:07.380
is it not? Yes, sir. You must have become in some degree attached to the house,

10:57:07.560 --> 10:57:14.140
you who have an eye for natural beauties and a good deal of the organ of attesiveness.

10:57:15.620 --> 10:57:24.220
I am attached to it indeed. And though I don't comprehend how it is, I perceive you have acquired

10:57:24.220 --> 10:57:32.340
a degree of regard for that foolish little child, Adele, too, and even for simple Dame Fairfax.

10:57:33.500 --> 10:57:37.340
Yes, sir, in a different way I have an affection for both.

10:57:38.120 --> 10:57:41.720
And would be sorry to part with them? Yes.

10:57:42.680 --> 10:57:50.320
Pity, he said, and sighed and paused. It is always the way of events in this life,

10:57:50.380 --> 10:57:57.620
he continued presently. No sooner have you got settled in a pleasant resting place than a voice

10:57:57.620 --> 10:58:04.400
calls out to you to rise and move on, for the hour of repose is expired.

10:58:05.780 --> 10:58:11.040
Must I move on, sir? I asked. Must I leave Thornfield?

10:58:12.040 --> 10:58:18.880
I believe you must, Jane. I am sorry, Janet, but I believe indeed you must.

10:58:20.340 --> 10:58:24.400
This was a blow, but I did not let it prostrate me.

10:58:25.380 --> 10:58:29.540
Well, sir, I shall be ready when the order to march comes.

10:58:30.660 --> 10:58:35.540
It is come now. I must give it tonight.

10:58:37.260 --> 10:58:44.860
Then you are going to be married, sir. Exactly. Precisely. With your usual

10:58:44.860 --> 10:58:51.640
acuteness you have hit the nail straight on the head. Soon, sir?

10:58:52.540 --> 10:58:54.100
Very soon.

10:58:55.360 --> 10:59:06.160
My, that is Miss Eyre, and you'll remember, Jane, the first time I, or Rumour, plainly intimated to

10:59:06.160 --> 10:59:15.200
you that it was my intention to put my old bachelor's neck into the sacred noose, to enter into

10:59:15.200 --> 10:59:24.600
the holier state of matrimony, to take Miss Ingram to my bosom. In short, she is an extensive

10:59:24.600 --> 10:59:34.420
armful, but that's not to the point. One can't have too much of such a very excellent thing

10:59:34.420 --> 10:59:43.240
as my beautiful blanche. Well, as I was saying, listen to me, Jane. You're not turning your head

10:59:43.240 --> 10:59:51.320
to look after more moths, are you? That was only a lady-clop, child, flying away home.

10:59:51.660 --> 10:59:59.240
I wish to remind you that it was you who first said to me, with that discretion I respect in you,

10:59:59.300 --> 11:00:07.600
with that foresight, prudence and humility which befit your responsible and dependent position,

11:00:07.600 --> 11:00:15.760
that in case I married Miss Ingram, both you and little Adèle had better trot forthwith.

11:00:16.420 --> 11:00:23.220
I pass over the sort of slur conveyed in this suggestion on the character of my beloved.

11:00:23.720 --> 11:00:30.920
Indeed, when you are far away, Janet, I'll try to forget it. I shall notice only its wisdom,

11:00:30.920 --> 11:00:38.480
which is such that I have made it my law of action. Adèle must go to school,

11:00:38.860 --> 11:00:46.900
and you, Miss Eyre, must get a new situation. Yes, sir, I will advertise immediately,

11:00:47.400 --> 11:00:55.540
and meantime, I suppose, I was going to say, I suppose I may stay here till I find another

11:00:55.540 --> 11:01:03.640
to betake myself to. But I stopped, feeling what not do to risk a long sentence,

11:01:04.140 --> 11:01:07.440
for my voice was not quite under command.

11:01:08.400 --> 11:01:15.440
In about a month I hope to be a bridegroom, continued Mr. Rochester, and in the interim

11:01:15.440 --> 11:01:25.240
I shall myself look out for employment and an asylum for you. Thank you, sir. I am sorry to give.

11:01:26.240 --> 11:01:33.640
No need to apologize. I consider that when a dependent does her duty as well as you have done

11:01:33.640 --> 11:01:40.780
yours, she has a sort of claim upon her employer for any little assistance he can

11:01:40.780 --> 11:01:48.120
conveniently render her. Indeed, I have already, through my future mother-in-law, heard of a place

11:01:48.120 --> 11:01:55.460
that I think will suit. It is to undertake the education of the five daughters of Mr.

11:01:56.820 --> 11:02:05.160
Mrs. Dionysius O'Gaul of Bitternut Lodge, Connaught, Ireland. You'll like Ireland, I think.

11:02:05.540 --> 11:02:14.140
They're such warm-hearted people there, they say. It is a long way off, sir. No matter. A girl of

11:02:14.140 --> 11:02:21.700
sense will not object to the voyage or the distance. Not the voyage, but the distance,

11:02:21.740 --> 11:02:31.520
and then the sea is a barrier. From what, Jane? From England and from Thornfield and, well,

11:02:32.080 --> 11:02:40.560
from you, sir. I said this almost involuntarily, and with as little sanction of free will,

11:02:40.560 --> 11:02:49.440
my tears gushed out. I did not cry so as to be heard. However, I avoided sobbing.

11:02:50.420 --> 11:02:59.220
The thought of Mrs. O'Gaul and Bitternut Lodge struck cold to my heart, and colder the thought

11:02:59.220 --> 11:03:09.480
of all the brine and foam, destined as it seemed to rush between me and the master at whose side

11:03:09.480 --> 11:03:22.060
I now walked, and coldest the remembrance of the wider ocean, wealth, caste, custom intervened

11:03:22.060 --> 11:03:33.620
between me and what I naturally and inevitably loved. It is a long way, I again said. It is,

11:03:33.620 --> 11:03:41.440
to be sure, and when you get to Bitternut Lodge, Conalt. Ireland. I shall never see you again,

11:03:41.740 --> 11:03:49.420
Jane. That's morally certain. I never go over to Ireland, not having myself much of a fancy for

11:03:49.420 --> 11:03:56.400
the country. We have been good friends, Jane, have we not? Yes, sir. And when friends are on

11:03:56.400 --> 11:04:02.680
the eve of separation, they like to spend the little time that remains to them close to each

11:04:02.680 --> 11:04:10.920
other. Come, we'll talk over the voyage, and the parting quietly half an hour or so,

11:04:11.060 --> 11:04:20.060
while the stars enter into their shining life up in heaven yonder. Here is the chestnut tree,

11:04:20.440 --> 11:04:27.500
here is the bench at its old roots. Come, we will sit there in peace tonight,

11:04:27.500 --> 11:04:36.720
though we should never more be destined to sit there together. He seated me and himself.

11:04:38.220 --> 11:04:46.540
It is a long way to Ireland, Janet, and I am sorry to send my little friend on such weary travels,

11:04:46.920 --> 11:04:54.640
but if I can't do better, how is it to be helped? Are you anything akin to me,

11:04:54.640 --> 11:05:02.200
you think, Jane? I could risk no sort of answer by this time. My heart was still.

11:05:02.960 --> 11:05:12.940
Because, he said, I sometimes have a queer feeling with regard to you, especially when you are near

11:05:12.940 --> 11:05:22.720
me, as now. It is as if I had a string somewhere under my left ribs, tightly and inextricably

11:05:22.720 --> 11:05:30.720
knotted, to a similar string situated in the corresponding quarter of your little frame.

11:05:31.040 --> 11:05:39.820
And if that boisterous channel and two hundred miles or so of land come broad between us,

11:05:40.140 --> 11:05:48.580
I am afraid that chord of communion will be snapped. And then, I have a nervous notion

11:05:48.580 --> 11:05:55.160
I should take to bleeding inwardly. As for you, you would forget me.

11:05:55.520 --> 11:06:04.420
That I never should, sir. You know, impossible to proceed. Jane, do you hear that nightingale

11:06:04.420 --> 11:06:12.280
singing in the wood? Listen. In listening, I sobbed convulsively, for I could repress

11:06:12.280 --> 11:06:20.120
what I endured no longer. I was obliged to yield, and I was shaken from head to foot

11:06:20.120 --> 11:06:27.880
with acute distress. When I did speak, it was only to express an impetuous wish

11:06:27.880 --> 11:06:37.340
that I had never been born or never come to Thornfield. Because you are sorry to leave it?

11:06:37.960 --> 11:06:45.020
The vehemence of emotion stirred by grief and love within me was claiming mastery,

11:06:45.680 --> 11:06:52.400
and struggling for full sway, and asserting a right to predominate, to overcome,

11:06:53.140 --> 11:06:59.680
to live, rise, and reign at last. Yes, and to speak.

11:07:00.640 --> 11:07:09.440
I grieve to leave Thornfield. I love Thornfield. I love it. Because I have lived in it a full

11:07:09.440 --> 11:07:18.500
and delightful life. Momentarily, at least. I have not been trampled on. I have not been petrified.

11:07:18.900 --> 11:07:25.360
I have not been buried with inferior minds, and excluded from every glimpse of communion

11:07:25.360 --> 11:07:33.520
with what is bright and energetic and high. I have talked face to face with what I reference,

11:07:34.120 --> 11:07:41.400
with what I delight in, with an original, vigorous, and expanded mind. I have known you,

11:07:41.420 --> 11:07:50.120
Mr. Rochester, and it strikes me with terror and anguish to feel I absolutely must be torn from you

11:07:50.120 --> 11:07:59.120
forever. I see the necessity of departure, and it is like looking on the necessity of death.

11:07:59.960 --> 11:08:09.260
Where do you see the necessity? he asked suddenly. Where? You, sir, have placed it before me.

11:08:10.140 --> 11:08:17.040
In what shape? In the shape of Miss Ingram, a noble and beautiful woman, your bride.

11:08:17.840 --> 11:08:24.660
My bride? What bride? I have no bride. But you will have.

11:08:26.020 --> 11:08:35.920
Yes, I will. I will. He set his teeth. Then I must go. You have said it yourself.

11:08:37.100 --> 11:08:43.860
No, you must stay. I swear it. And the oath shall be kept.

11:08:44.720 --> 11:08:51.780
I tell you I must go, I retorted, roused, to something like passion. Do you think I can stay

11:08:51.780 --> 11:08:59.100
to become nothing to you? Do you think I am an automaton, a machine without feelings,

11:08:59.540 --> 11:09:06.980
and can bear to have my morsel of bread snatched from my lips, and my drop of living water dashed

11:09:06.980 --> 11:09:17.260
from my cup? Do you think because I am poor, obscure, plain, and little, I am soulless and

11:09:17.260 --> 11:09:25.960
heartless? You think wrong. I have as much soul as you, and full as much heart, and if God had

11:09:25.960 --> 11:09:32.140
gifted me with some beauty and much wealth, I should have made it as hard for you to leave me

11:09:32.140 --> 11:09:40.200
as it is now for me to leave you. I am not talking to you now through the medium of custom,

11:09:41.620 --> 11:09:48.740
conventionalities, nor even of mortal flesh. It is my spirit that addresses your spirit,

11:09:49.180 --> 11:09:56.500
just as if both had passed through the grave and we stood at God's feet equal, as we are.

11:09:56.500 --> 11:10:06.420
As we are, repeated Mr. Rochester. So, he added, enclosing me in his arms, gathering me to his

11:10:06.420 --> 11:10:18.040
breast, pressing his lips on my lips. So, Jane. Yes, so, sir, I rejoined. And yet not so, for you

11:10:18.040 --> 11:10:27.020
are a married man, or as good as a married man, and wed to one inferior to you, to one with whom

11:10:27.020 --> 11:10:35.380
you have no sympathy, whom I do not believe you truly love, for I have seen and heard you sneer at

11:10:35.380 --> 11:10:45.180
her. I would scorn such a union. Therefore, I am better than you. Let me go. Where, Jane? To Ireland?

11:10:45.980 --> 11:10:55.660
Yes, to Ireland. I have spoken my mind and can go anywhere now. Jane, be still. Don't struggle so,

11:10:55.660 --> 11:11:04.240
like a wild, frantic bird that is rending its own plumage in its desperation. I am no bird.

11:11:05.160 --> 11:11:11.940
And no net ensnares me. I am a free, human being, with an independent will,

11:11:11.940 --> 11:11:21.600
which I now exert to leave you. Another effort set me at liberty, and I stood erect before him.

11:11:22.600 --> 11:11:32.720
And your will shall decide your destiny, he said. I offer you my hand, my heart, and a share of all

11:11:32.720 --> 11:11:43.760
possessions. You play a farce, which I merely laugh at. I ask you to pass through life at my side,

11:11:44.540 --> 11:11:52.340
and to be my second self, and best earthly companion. For that fate, you have already

11:11:52.340 --> 11:12:00.640
made your choice, and must abide by it. Jane, be still a few moments. You are overexcited.

11:12:00.640 --> 11:12:07.880
I will be still, too. A waft of wind came sweeping down the laurel walk,

11:12:08.180 --> 11:12:16.460
and trembled through the boughs of the chestnut. It wandered away, away, to an indefinite distance.

11:12:16.680 --> 11:12:24.640
It died. The nightingale's song was then the only voice of the hour. In listening to it,

11:12:24.640 --> 11:12:32.260
I again wept. Mr. Rochester sat quiet, looking at me gently and seriously.

11:12:33.040 --> 11:12:37.600
Some time passed before he spoke. He at last said,

11:12:38.480 --> 11:12:46.600
Come to my side, Jane, and let us explain and understand one another. I will never again come

11:12:46.600 --> 11:12:55.500
to your side. I am torn away now, and cannot return. But Jane, I summon you as my wife.

11:12:56.080 --> 11:13:03.320
It is you only I intend to marry. I was silent. I thought he mocked me.

11:13:03.940 --> 11:13:13.300
Come, Jane, come hither. Your bride stands between us. He rose, and with a stride reached me.

11:13:14.010 --> 11:13:22.420
My bride is here, he said again, drawing me to him, because my equal is here, and my likeness.

11:13:23.700 --> 11:13:33.440
Jane, will you marry me? Still I did not answer, and still I writhed myself from his grasp.

11:13:34.040 --> 11:13:44.220
For I was still incredulous. Do you doubt me, Jane? Entirely. You have no faith in me,

11:13:44.720 --> 11:13:51.720
not a wit. Am I a liar in your eyes? he asked passionately.

11:13:52.680 --> 11:14:00.120
Little skeptic, you shall be convinced. What love have I for Miss Ingram?

11:14:00.120 --> 11:14:09.240
None, and that you know. What love has she for me? None, as I have taken pains to prove.

11:14:09.920 --> 11:14:18.040
I caused a rumour to reach her that my fortune was not third of what was supposed, and after that,

11:14:18.380 --> 11:14:25.280
I presented myself to see the result. It was coldness both from her and her mother.

11:14:25.600 --> 11:14:35.900
I would not. I could not marry Miss Ingram. You, you strange, you almost unearthly thing,

11:14:36.680 --> 11:14:48.360
I love as my own flesh. You, poor and obscure and small and plain as you are.

11:14:48.960 --> 11:14:59.920
I entreat to accept me as a husband. What, me? I ejaculated. Being in this earnestness,

11:15:00.080 --> 11:15:09.400
and especially in this incivility, to credit his sincerity. Me, who have not a friend in the world,

11:15:09.400 --> 11:15:17.200
but you, if you are my friend. Not a shilling, but what you have given me.

11:15:18.120 --> 11:15:30.940
You, Jane, I must have you for my own, entirely my own. Will you be mine? Say yes, quickly.

11:15:32.040 --> 11:15:41.060
Mr. Rochester, let me look at your face. Turn to the moonlight. Why? Because I want to read your

11:15:41.060 --> 11:15:50.080
countenance. Turn. There, you will find it scarcely more legible than a crumpled, scratched page.

11:15:50.560 --> 11:15:59.780
Read on. Only make haste, for I suffer. His face was very much agitated and very much flushed,

11:15:59.780 --> 11:16:05.880
and there were strong workings in the features and strange gleams in the eyes.

11:16:06.580 --> 11:16:15.080
Oh, Jane, you torture me, he exclaimed, with that searching and yet faithful and generous look.

11:16:15.520 --> 11:16:24.720
You torture me. How can I do that? If you are true and your offer real, my only feelings to you must

11:16:24.720 --> 11:16:33.520
be gratitude and devotion. They cannot torture. Gratitude, he ejaculated and added wildly.

11:16:34.340 --> 11:16:43.700
Jane, accept me quickly. Say, Edward, give me my name. Edward, I will marry you. Are you in

11:16:43.700 --> 11:16:52.420
earnest? Do you truly love me? Do you sincerely wish me to be your wife? I do, and if an oath is

11:16:52.420 --> 11:17:02.100
necessary to satisfy you, I swear it. Then, sir, I will marry you, Edward, my little wife.

11:17:03.040 --> 11:17:11.640
Dear Edward, come to me. Come to me entirely now, said he, and added in his deepest tone,

11:17:11.700 --> 11:17:19.740
speaking in my ear as his cheek was laid on mine. Make my happiness. I will make yours.

11:17:19.740 --> 11:17:27.280
God pardon me, he subjoined ere long, and man-meddle not with me. I have her,

11:17:27.760 --> 11:17:34.220
and will hold her. There is no one to meddle, sir. I have no kindred to interfere.

11:17:35.280 --> 11:17:42.300
No, that is the best of it, he said, and if I had loved him less, I should have thought his

11:17:42.300 --> 11:17:50.640
accent and look of exultation savage. But, sitting by him, roused from the nightmare of parting,

11:17:51.340 --> 11:17:59.300
called the Paradise of Union, I thought only of the bliss given me to drink in so abundant a flow.

11:17:59.840 --> 11:18:08.740
Again and again he said, Are you happy, Jane? And again and again I answered, Yes.

11:18:10.080 --> 11:18:20.740
After which he murmured, It will atone. It will atone. Have I not found her friendless and cold

11:18:20.740 --> 11:18:29.600
and comfortless? Will I not guard and cherish and solace her? Is there not love in my heart

11:18:29.600 --> 11:18:38.720
and constancy in my resolves? It will expiate at God's tribunal. I know my Maker sanctioned

11:18:38.720 --> 11:18:48.640
what I do. For the world's judgment I wash my hands thereof. For man's opinion I defy it.

11:18:49.100 --> 11:18:56.980
But what had befallen the night? The moon was not yet set, and we were all in shadow.

11:18:57.520 --> 11:19:05.740
I could scarcely see my Master's face, near as I was, and what ailed the chestnut tree?

11:19:06.360 --> 11:19:14.440
It writhed and groaned, while wind roared in the laurel walk and came sweeping over us.

11:19:15.540 --> 11:19:23.540
We must go in, said Mr. Rochester. The weather changes. I could have sat with thee till morning,

11:19:24.120 --> 11:19:34.020
Jane. And so, thought I, could I with you? I have said so, perhaps. But a livid, vivid

11:19:34.020 --> 11:19:41.240
spark leapt out of a cloud at which I was looking, and there was a crack, a crash,

11:19:41.660 --> 11:19:49.680
and a close rattling peel, and I thought only of hiding my dazzled eyes against Mr. Rochester's

11:19:49.680 --> 11:19:59.200
shoulder. The rain rushed down. He hurried me to the walk, through the grounds and into the house.

11:19:59.200 --> 11:20:06.980
But we were quite wet before we could pass the threshold. He was taking off my shawl

11:20:06.980 --> 11:20:14.940
in the hall, and shaking the water out of my loosened hair, when Mrs. Fairfax emerged from

11:20:14.940 --> 11:20:24.500
her room. I did not observe her at first, nor did Mr. Rochester. The lamp was lit. The clock

11:20:24.500 --> 11:20:26.860
was on the stroke of twelve.

11:20:28.180 --> 11:20:36.800
Hasten to take off your wet things, said he, and before you go, good night, good night, my darling.

11:20:38.340 --> 11:20:48.100
He kissed me repeatedly. When I looked up, on leaving his arms, there stood the widow, pale,

11:20:48.100 --> 11:20:55.140
grave and amazed. I only smiled at her and ran upstairs.

11:20:57.640 --> 11:21:05.480
Explanation will do for another time, thought I. Still, when I reached my chamber, I felt a

11:21:05.480 --> 11:21:13.260
pang at the idea she should even temporarily misconstrue what she had seen. But joy soon

11:21:13.260 --> 11:21:21.420
faced every other feeling, and loud as the wind blew, near and deep as the thunder crashed,

11:21:22.080 --> 11:21:30.340
fierce and frequent as the lightning gleamed, cataract-like as the rain fell during a storm

11:21:30.340 --> 11:21:40.660
of two hours' duration, I experienced no fear and little awe. Mr. Rochester came thrice to my door,

11:21:40.660 --> 11:21:48.740
in the course of it, to ask if I was safe and tranquil. And that was comfort. That was strength

11:21:48.740 --> 11:21:57.860
for anything. Before I left my bed in the morning, little Adele came running in to tell me that the

11:21:57.860 --> 11:22:03.900
great horse Chestnut at the bottom of the orchard had been struck by lightning in the night,

11:22:04.240 --> 11:22:06.440
and half of it split away.

11:22:30.160 --> 11:22:34.800
As I rose and dressed, I thought over what had happened, and wondered if it were a dream.

11:22:34.800 --> 11:22:42.260
I could not be certain of the reality till I had seen Mr. Rochester again, and heard him renew his words of love and promise.

11:22:43.320 --> 11:22:47.900
While arranging my hair, I looked at my face in the glass, and felt that it was no longer plain.

11:22:48.720 --> 11:22:57.400
There was hope in its aspect, and life in its colour, and my eyes seemed as if they had beheld the fount of fruition, and burrowed beams from the lustrous ribble.

11:22:57.400 --> 11:23:07.660
I had often been unwilling to look at my master because I feared he would not be pleased at my look, but I was sure I might lift my face to his now, and not cool his affection by its expression.

11:23:08.700 --> 11:23:12.700
I took a plain but clean and light summer dress from my drawer, and put it on.

11:23:13.340 --> 11:23:19.040
It seemed no attire had ever so well become me, because none I had ever worn in so blissful a mood.

11:23:19.860 --> 11:23:31.660
I was not surprised when I ran down the hall to see that a brilliant June morning had succeeded to the tempest of the night, and to feel, through the open glass door, the breathing of a fresh and fragrant breeze.

11:23:32.340 --> 11:23:34.280
Nature must be gladsome when I was so happy.

11:23:34.760 --> 11:23:45.700
A beggar woman and her little boy, paled, ragged objects both, were coming up the walk, and I ran down and gave them all the money I happened to have in my purse, some three or four shillings.

11:23:45.700 --> 11:23:48.620
Good or bad, they must partake of my jubilee.

11:23:49.440 --> 11:23:55.600
The rocks called, and blitherbirds sang, but nothing was so merry or so musical as my own rejoicing art.

11:23:56.440 --> 11:24:00.880
Mrs. Fairfax surprised me by looking out the window with a sad countenance and saying gravely,

11:24:01.500 --> 11:24:03.640
Miss Eyre, will you come to breakfast?

11:24:04.620 --> 11:24:08.740
During the meal she was quiet and cool, but I could not undeceive her then.

11:24:09.260 --> 11:24:12.800
I must wait for my master to give explanations, and so must she.

11:24:12.800 --> 11:24:15.900
I ate what I could, and then I hastened upstairs.

11:24:16.720 --> 11:24:18.560
I met a deal leaving the schoolroom.

11:24:19.420 --> 11:24:21.360
Where are you going? It is time for lessons.

11:24:22.420 --> 11:24:24.400
Mr. Rochester has sent me away to the nursery.

11:24:25.860 --> 11:24:26.480
Where is he?

11:24:27.060 --> 11:24:31.780
In there, pointing to the apartment she had left, and I went in, and there he stood.

11:24:32.980 --> 11:24:35.000
Come and bid me good morning, said he.

11:24:35.220 --> 11:24:42.260
I gladly advanced, and it was not merely a cold word now, or even a shake of the hand that I received, but an embrace and a kiss.

11:24:42.260 --> 11:24:47.380
It seemed natural. It seemed genial to be so well-loved, so caressed by him.

11:24:48.380 --> 11:24:51.580
Jane, you look blooming and smiling and pretty, said he.

11:24:51.780 --> 11:24:56.680
Truly pretty this morning. Is this my pale little elf? Is this my mustard seed?

11:24:57.180 --> 11:25:04.100
This little sunny-fade girl, with the dimpled cheek and rosy lips, the satin-smooth hazel hair, and the radiant hazel eyes?

11:25:04.480 --> 11:25:10.200
I had green eyes, Rita, but you must excuse the mistake. For him they were new-dyed, I suppose.

11:25:10.760 --> 11:25:12.320
It is Jane Erso.

11:25:13.160 --> 11:25:18.100
Soon to be Jane Rochester, he added. In four weeks, Janet, not a day more. Do you hear that?

11:25:18.700 --> 11:25:22.560
I did, and I could not quite comprehend it. It made me giddy.

11:25:22.780 --> 11:25:29.620
The feeling the announcement sent through me was something stronger than it was consistent with joy, something that smoked and stunned.

11:25:30.400 --> 11:25:32.300
It was, I think, almost fear.

11:25:33.260 --> 11:25:36.220
You blushed, and now you're white, Jane. What is that for?

11:25:37.140 --> 11:25:38.800
Because you gave me a new name.

11:25:38.800 --> 11:25:41.600
Jane Rochester, and it seemed so strange.

11:25:43.320 --> 11:25:49.720
Yes, Mrs. Rochester, said he. Young Mrs. Rochester. Fairfax Rochester's girl-bride.

11:25:50.320 --> 11:25:56.200
It can never be, sir. It does not sound likely. Human beings never enjoy complete happiness in this world.

11:25:56.620 --> 11:25:59.620
I was not born for a different destiny to the rest of my species.

11:26:00.380 --> 11:26:07.600
To imagine such a lot befalling me is a fairy tale, a daydream, which I can and will realize. I shall begin today.

11:26:07.600 --> 11:26:14.820
This morning I wrote to my banker in London to send me certain jewels he has in his keeping, heirlooms for the ladies of Thornfield.

11:26:15.460 --> 11:26:23.820
In a day or two I hope to pour them into your lap, for every privilege, every attention shall be yours, that I would accord a peer's daughter if about to marry her.

11:26:24.540 --> 11:26:29.080
Oh, sir, never rain jewels. I don't like to hear them spoken of.

11:26:29.800 --> 11:26:33.860
Jewels for Jane Eyre sound unnatural and strange. I would rather not have them.

11:26:33.860 --> 11:26:40.260
I will myself put the diamond chain around your neck and encircle it on your forehead, which it will become.

11:26:40.960 --> 11:26:51.160
For nature, at least, has stemmed her patent of nobility under this brow, Jane, and I will clasp the bracelets on these fine wrists and load these fairy-like fingers with rings.

11:26:51.820 --> 11:27:01.880
No, no, sir. Think of other subjects and speak of other things, and in another strain. Don't address me as if I were a beauty. I'm your plain quakerish governess.

11:27:02.580 --> 11:27:08.700
You are a beauty in my eyes, and a beauty just after the desire of my heart. Delicate and aerial.

11:27:09.940 --> 11:27:15.900
Punen insignificant, you mean? You're dreaming, sir, or you're sneering. For God's sake, don't be ironical.

11:27:16.740 --> 11:27:26.840
I will make the world acknowledge your beauty too, he went on, while I really became uneasy at the strain he had adopted, because I felt he was either deluding himself or trying to delude me.

11:27:26.840 --> 11:27:35.200
I will attire my Jane in satin and lace, and she shall have roses in her hair, and I will cover the head I love best with a priceless veil.

11:27:36.380 --> 11:27:43.840
And then you wouldn't know me, sir, and I shall not be a Jane Eyre any longer, but an ape in a harlequin's jacket, a Jane Barrett plumes.

11:27:43.840 --> 11:27:57.540
I would as soon see you, Mr. Rochester, tricked out on stage trappings as myself clad in a court lady's robe, and I don't call you handsome, sir, though I love you most dearly, far too dearly to flatter you. Don't flatter me.

11:27:58.400 --> 11:28:01.940
He pursued this theme, however, without noticing my deprecation.

11:28:01.940 --> 11:28:07.640
This very day I shall take you in the carriage to Millcote, and you must choose some dresses for yourself.

11:28:07.880 --> 11:28:16.560
I told you we shall be married in four weeks. The wedding is to take place quietly in the church down below Yonder, and then I shall waft you away at once to town.

11:28:16.900 --> 11:28:27.460
After a brief stay there, I shall bear my treasure to regions nearer the sun, to French vineyards and Italian plains, and she shall see whatever is famous in old story and in modern record.

11:28:27.460 --> 11:28:34.640
She shall taste, too, of the life of cities, and she shall learn to value herself by just comparison with others.

11:28:35.660 --> 11:28:47.560
Shall I travel? And with you, sir? You shall so join at Paris, Rome, and Naples, at Florence, Venice, and Vienna. All the ground I have wandered over shall be retrodden by you.

11:28:47.560 --> 11:28:57.480
Wherever I stand my hoof, your sift foot shall step also. Ten years since I flew through Europe half mad with disgust, hate, and rage as my companions.

11:28:58.260 --> 11:29:02.540
Now I shall revisit it healed and cleansed, with a very angel as my comforter.

11:29:02.900 --> 11:29:10.880
I laughed at him as he said this. I am not an angel, I asserted, and I will not be one till I die. I shall be myself, Mr. Rochester.

11:29:10.880 --> 11:29:19.500
Well, you must neither expect nor exact anything celestial of me, for you will not get it any more than I shall get it of you, which I do not at all anticipate.

11:29:20.260 --> 11:29:21.920
What do you anticipate of me?

11:29:23.060 --> 11:29:34.840
For a little while you will perhaps be as you are now, a very little while, but then you will turn cool, and then you will be capricotious, and then you will be stern, and I shall have much ado to please you.

11:29:34.840 --> 11:29:44.700
But when you get well used to me, you will perhaps like me again. Like me, I say, not love me. I suppose your love will ever risk in six months or less.

11:29:45.160 --> 11:29:57.180
I have observed in books written by men, that period assigned as the farthest to which a husband's ardour extends. Yet, after all, as a friend and companion, I hope never to become quite distasteful to my dear master.

11:29:58.980 --> 11:30:10.280
Distasteful? And like you again? I think I shall like you again, and yet again, and I will make you confess I do not only like, but love you with truth, feather, and constancy.

11:30:12.140 --> 11:30:13.960
Yet you are not capricotious, sir?

11:30:13.960 --> 11:30:26.640
To women who please me only by their faces, I am the very devil when I find out they have neither souls nor hearts, when they open to me a perspective of flatness, triviality, and perhaps imbecility, coarseness, and ill temper.

11:30:27.080 --> 11:30:38.840
But to the clear-eyed and eloquent tongue, to the soul made of fire, and the character in the bends but does not break, at once supple and stable, tractable and consistent, I am ever tender and true.

11:30:39.760 --> 11:30:44.040
Had you ever experienced such a character, sir? Did you ever love such a one?

11:30:44.960 --> 11:30:51.440
I love it now. But before me, if I indeed, in any respect, come up to your difficult standard?

11:30:52.400 --> 11:30:59.920
I never met your likeness, Jane. You pleased me, and you master me. You seem to submit, and I like the sense of fliancy you impart.

11:30:59.920 --> 11:31:15.720
And while I am twining the soft silken skein around my finger, it sends a thrill up my arm to my heart. I am influenced, conquered, and the influence is sweeter than I can express, and the conquest I undergo has a victory beyond any triumph I can win.

11:31:16.400 --> 11:31:21.460
Why do you smile, Jane? What does that inexplicable, that uncanny turn of the countenance mean?

11:31:22.160 --> 11:31:29.860
I was thinking, sir—you will excuse the idea, it was involuntary—I was thinking of Hercules and Samson with their charmers.

11:31:30.380 --> 11:31:37.480
You were, you little elfish! Hush, sir! You don't talk very wisely just now, any more than those gentlemen acted very wisely.

11:31:38.100 --> 11:31:46.600
However, had they been married, they would no doubt by their severity as husbands have made up for their softness as suitors. And so will you, I fear.

11:31:47.080 --> 11:31:53.220
I wonder how you will answer me a year hence, should I ask a favour that does not suit your convenience or pleasure to grant.

11:31:54.000 --> 11:32:01.020
Ask me something now, Jane, the least thing, I desire to be entreated. Indeed I will, sir, I have my petition already.

11:32:01.700 --> 11:32:09.400
Speak, but if you look up and smile with that countenance, I shall swear concession before I know to what, and that will make a fool of me.

11:32:09.400 --> 11:32:19.720
Not at all, sir. I ask only this. Don't send for the jewels, and don't crown me with roses. You might as well put a board of gold lace around that plain pocket handkerchief you have there.

11:32:20.540 --> 11:32:29.560
I might as well guilt-refined gold. I know it. Your request is granted, then, for the time. I will remand the order I dispatched to my banker.

11:32:30.320 --> 11:32:34.800
But you have not yet asked for anything. You have prayed a gift to be withdrawn. Try again.

11:32:34.800 --> 11:32:41.140
Well then, sir, have the goodness to gratify my curiosity, which is much piqued on one point.

11:32:41.900 --> 11:32:42.820
He looked disturbed.

11:32:43.500 --> 11:32:50.880
What, what? he said hastily. Curiosity is a dangerous petition. It is well I have not taken a vow to accord every request.

11:32:51.820 --> 11:32:54.260
But there can be no danger in complying with this, sir.

11:32:54.820 --> 11:33:01.680
Utter it, Jane, but I wish that instead of a mere enquiry into perhaps a secret, it was a wish for half my estate.

11:33:02.520 --> 11:33:09.860
Now, King Ahasuerus, what do I want with half your estate? Do you think I am a Jew, Yuzuru, seeking good investment in land?

11:33:10.280 --> 11:33:15.820
I would much rather have all your confidence. You will not exclude me from your confidence if you admit me to your heart.

11:33:16.540 --> 11:33:27.500
You are welcome to all my confidence that it is worth having, Jane. But for God's sake, don't desire a useless burden. Don't long for poison. Don't turn out a downright eave on my hands.

11:33:28.340 --> 11:33:34.940
Why not, sir? You have just been telling me how much you would like to be conquered and how pleasant over persuasion is to you.

11:33:35.360 --> 11:33:44.520
Don't you think I had better take advantage of the confession and begin in coax and entreat, even cry and be salty if necessary, for the sake of a mere essay of my power?

11:33:45.340 --> 11:33:50.080
I dare you to any such experiment. Encroach, presume, and the game is up.

11:33:50.860 --> 11:34:04.700
Is it, sir? You soon gave in. How stern you look now. Your eyebrows have become as thick as my finger, and your forehead resembles what in some astonishing poetry I once saw styled a blue-piled thunderloft.

11:34:05.200 --> 11:34:14.440
That will be your married look, sir, I suppose. If that be your married look, I, as a Christian, will soon give up the notion of consulting with the mere spirit of Salamander.

11:34:15.400 --> 11:34:17.920
But what had you to ask, thing? Out with it.

11:34:18.940 --> 11:34:25.100
There, you are less than civil now, and I like rudeness a great deal better than flattery. I'd rather be a thing than an angel.

11:34:25.900 --> 11:34:31.300
This is what I have to ask. Why did you take such pains to make me believe you wished to marry Miss Ingram?

11:34:32.820 --> 11:34:42.460
Is that all? Thank God it is no worse. And now he unlit his black brows, looked down, smiling at me, and stroked my hair, as if well pleased at seeing a danger averted.

11:34:42.980 --> 11:34:52.380
I think I may confess, he continued, even although I should make you a little indignant, Jane, and I've seen what a fire spirit you can be when you're indignant.

11:34:52.980 --> 11:35:01.540
You glowed in the cool moonlight last night when you mutinied against fate and claimed your rank as my equal. Janet, by the by, it was you who made me the offer.

11:35:01.800 --> 11:35:05.380
Of course I did. But the point of you, please, sir. Miss Ingram?

11:35:06.080 --> 11:35:16.980
Well, I feigned courtship of Miss Ingram, because I wished to render you as madly in love with me as I was with you, and I knew jealousy would be the best ally I could call for in the furtherance of that end.

11:35:18.260 --> 11:35:29.380
Excellent. Now you're small. Not one whit bigger than the end of my little finger. It was a burning shame and a scandalous disgrace to act in that way. Did you think nothing of Miss Ingram's feelings, sir?

11:35:30.140 --> 11:35:40.780
Her feelings are concentrated in one, pride, and that needs humbling. Were you jealous, Jane? Never mind, Mr. Rochester. It is in no way interesting to you to know that.

11:35:41.620 --> 11:35:48.940
Answer me truly once more. Do you think Miss Ingram will not suffer from your dishonest coquetry? Won't she feel forsaken and deserted?

11:35:50.180 --> 11:35:59.260
Impossible. When you told me how she, on the contrary, deserted me, the idea of my insolvency cooled, or rather extinguished, her flame in a moment.

11:36:00.320 --> 11:36:06.280
You have a curious designing mind, Mr. Rochester. I'm afraid your principles at some points are eccentric.

11:36:07.360 --> 11:36:12.220
My principles were never trained, Jane. They may have grown a little awry for lack of attention.

11:36:12.880 --> 11:36:22.760
Once again, seriously, may I enjoy that great good that has been vouchsafed to me without fearing that anyone else is suffering the bitter pain I myself felt a little while ago?

11:36:23.660 --> 11:36:34.160
That you may, my good little girl. There is not another being in the world that has the same pure love for me as yourself. I lay that pleasant mention to my soul, Jane. I believe in your affection.

11:36:35.060 --> 11:36:44.180
I turned my lips to the hand that lay on my shoulder. I loved him very much. More than I could trust myself to say. More than words had power to express.

11:36:45.120 --> 11:36:52.660
Ask something more, he said presently. It is my delight to be entreated and to yield. I was again ready with my request.

11:36:54.100 --> 11:37:05.560
Communicate your intentions to Mrs. Fairfax, sir. She saw me with you last night in the hall, and she was shocked. Give her some explanation before I see her again. It pains me to be misjudged by so good a woman.

11:37:06.480 --> 11:37:15.980
Go to your room and put on your bonnet, he replied. I mean you to accompany me to Millcote this morning, and while you prepare for the drive, I will enlighten the old lady's understanding.

11:37:16.800 --> 11:37:21.000
Did she think, Janet, you had given the world for love and considered it well lost?

11:37:21.780 --> 11:37:25.000
I believe she thought I had forgotten my station. Ain't you, sir?

11:37:26.360 --> 11:37:33.420
Station! Station! Your station is in my heart, and on the necks of those who would insult you, now and hereafter. Go.

11:37:34.400 --> 11:37:40.600
I was soon dressed, and when I heard Mr. Rochester quit Mrs. Fairfax's parlour, I hurried down to it.

11:37:41.320 --> 11:37:49.280
The old lady had been reading her morning portion of scripture, the lesson for the day. Her Bible lay open before her, and her spectacles were upon it.

11:37:49.280 --> 11:38:01.600
Her occupation, suspended by Mr. Rochester's announcement, seemed now forgotten. Her eyes, fixed on the blank wall opposite, expressed the surprise of a quiet mind stirred by unwanted tidings.

11:38:02.560 --> 11:38:12.420
Seeing me, she roused herself. She made a sort of effort to smile, and framed a few words of congratulation, but the smile expired, and the sentence was abandoned and finished.

11:38:13.300 --> 11:38:17.440
She put up her spectacles, shut the Bible, and pushed her chair back from the table.

11:38:18.220 --> 11:38:24.800
I feel so astonished, she began. I hardly know what to say to you, Miss Eyre. I've surely not been dreaming, have I?

11:38:25.320 --> 11:38:29.440
Sometimes I half fall asleep when I'm sitting alone, and fancy things that have never happened.

11:38:30.180 --> 11:38:41.820
It has seemed to me, more than once when I've been in a doze, that my dear husband, who died fifteen years since, has come in and sat down beside me, and that I have even heard him call me by my name, Alice, as he used to do.

11:38:42.340 --> 11:38:47.440
Now, can you tell me whether it's actually true that Mr. Rochester has asked you to marry him?

11:38:47.640 --> 11:38:53.700
Don't laugh at me, but I really thought he came in here five minutes ago, and said that in a month you would be his wife.

11:38:54.260 --> 11:38:56.480
He has said the same thing to me, I replied.

11:38:56.980 --> 11:39:00.280
He has? Do you believe him? Have you accepted him?

11:39:00.940 --> 11:39:01.380
Yes.

11:39:02.480 --> 11:39:04.180
She looked at me bewildered.

11:39:04.520 --> 11:39:06.000
I could never have thought it.

11:39:06.000 --> 11:39:14.040
He is a proud man. All the Rochester's were proud, and his father at least liked money. He, too, has always been called careful.

11:39:14.660 --> 11:39:17.340
He means to marry you? He tells me so.

11:39:18.340 --> 11:39:24.500
She surveyed my whole person. In her eyes, I read that they had there found no charm powerful enough to solve the enigma.

11:39:25.540 --> 11:39:33.060
It passes me, she continued, but no doubt it is true since you say so. How it will answer I cannot tell. I really don't know.

11:39:33.620 --> 11:39:40.300
The quality of position and fortune is often advisable in such cases, and there are twenty years of differences in your ages.

11:39:40.800 --> 11:39:42.240
He might almost be your father.

11:39:42.940 --> 11:39:47.300
No, indeed, Mrs. Fairfax, exclaimed I, needled. He is nothing like my father.

11:39:47.740 --> 11:39:55.700
No one who saw us together would suppose it for an instant. Mr. Rochester looks as young, and is as young, as some men of five and twenty.

11:39:57.100 --> 11:40:00.320
Is it really for love who is going to marry you? she asked.

11:40:00.320 --> 11:40:05.760
I was so hurt by the coldness in her scepticism that the tears rose to my eyes.

11:40:06.840 --> 11:40:13.600
I am sorry to grieve you, pursued the widow, but you are so young and so little acquainted with men. I wish to put you on your guard.

11:40:14.460 --> 11:40:22.400
It is an old saying that all is not gold with the glitters, and in this case I do fear there will be something found to be different to what either you or I expect.

11:40:23.420 --> 11:40:30.120
Why, am I a monster? I said. Is it impossible that Mr. Rochester should have a sincere affection for me?

11:40:30.900 --> 11:40:36.860
No, you are very well, and much improved of late, and Mr. Rochester, I dare say, is fond of you.

11:40:37.120 --> 11:40:39.620
I have always noticed that you were a sort of pet of his.

11:40:40.360 --> 11:40:46.260
There are times when, for your sake, I have been a little uneasy at his much preference, and have wished to put you on your guard.

11:40:46.260 --> 11:40:49.680
But I did not like to suggest even the possibility of wrong.

11:40:50.180 --> 11:40:56.480
I knew such an idea would shock, perhaps offend you, and you were so discreet, and so thoroughly modest and sensible.

11:40:56.880 --> 11:40:59.060
I hope you might be trusted to protect yourself.

11:40:59.940 --> 11:41:09.620
Last night I cannot tell you what I suffered when I saw it all over the house, and could find you nowhere, nor the master either, and then at twelve o'clock, so you come in with him.

11:41:10.400 --> 11:41:15.080
Well, never mind that now, I interrupted impatiently. It is enough that all was right.

11:41:15.920 --> 11:41:20.740
I hope all will be right in the end, she said, but believe me, you cannot be too careful.

11:41:21.320 --> 11:41:25.300
Try and keep Mr. Rochester at a distance. Distrust yourself as well as him.

11:41:25.800 --> 11:41:29.100
Gentlemen in his station are not accustomed to marry their governesses.

11:41:30.100 --> 11:41:33.880
I was growing truly irritated. Happily Adele ran in.

11:41:34.400 --> 11:41:42.940
Let me go! Let me go to Melkote too, she cried. Mr. Rochester won't, though there is so much room in the new carriage. Beg him to let me go, Mademoiselle.

11:41:42.940 --> 11:41:48.360
That I will, Adele, and I hastened away with her, glad to quit my gloomy monitress.

11:41:49.040 --> 11:41:56.120
The carriage was ready, they were bringing it round to the front, and my master was on the pavement, pilot following him backwards and forwards.

11:41:57.000 --> 11:41:59.480
Adele may accompany us, may she not, sir?

11:41:59.920 --> 11:42:03.420
I told her no, I'll have no brats, I'll have only you.

11:42:04.100 --> 11:42:07.120
Do let her go, Mr. Rochester, if you please, it would be better.

11:42:07.880 --> 11:42:09.700
Not it, she will be a restraint.

11:42:09.700 --> 11:42:13.580
He was quite peremptory, both in look and voice.

11:42:14.040 --> 11:42:18.260
The chill of Mrs. Fairfax's warnings and the damp of her doubts were upon me.

11:42:19.360 --> 11:42:25.680
Something of unsubstantiality and uncertainty beset my hopes. I have lost a sense of power over him.

11:42:26.200 --> 11:42:30.180
I was about, mechanically, to obey him without further remonstrance.

11:42:30.680 --> 11:42:33.200
But as he helped me into the carriage he looked at my face.

11:42:33.700 --> 11:42:36.580
What is the matter? he asked. All the sunshine is gone.

11:42:36.580 --> 11:42:41.160
Do you really wish the band to go? Will it annoy you if she is left behind?

11:42:41.860 --> 11:42:43.480
I would rather she went, sir.

11:42:44.020 --> 11:42:47.720
Then off with your bonnet and back like a flash of lightning, cried he to Adele.

11:42:48.280 --> 11:42:49.960
She obeyed him with what speed she might.

11:42:50.600 --> 11:43:00.680
After all, a single morning's interruption will not matter much, said he, when I mean shortly to claim you, your thoughts, conversation and company for life.

11:43:01.400 --> 11:43:06.660
Adele, when lifted in, commenced kissing me by way of expressing her gratitude for my intercession.

11:43:07.420 --> 11:43:10.680
She was instantly stirred away into a corner of the other side of him.

11:43:11.140 --> 11:43:17.460
She then peered around to where I sat, so Stone, a neighbour, was too restrictive to him in his present fractious mood.

11:43:17.840 --> 11:43:21.160
She dared whisper no observations, nor ask of him any information.

11:43:22.100 --> 11:43:27.200
Let her come to me, I entreated. She will perhaps trouble you, sir. There's plenty of room on this side.

11:43:27.720 --> 11:43:30.400
He handed her over as if she had been a lap-dog.

11:43:31.140 --> 11:43:34.220
I'll send her to school yet, he said, but now he was smiling.

11:43:35.240 --> 11:43:39.240
Adele heard him and asked if she was to go to school, San Mademoiselle.

11:43:39.940 --> 11:43:51.980
Yes, he replied, absolutely, San Mademoiselle, for I am to take Mademoiselle to the moon, and there I shall seek a cave in one of the white valleys among the volcano tops, and Mademoiselles shall live with me there and only me.

11:43:52.580 --> 11:43:55.980
She'll have nothing to eat. You will starve her, observed Adele.

11:43:55.980 --> 11:44:02.380
I shall gather manna for her morning and night. The plains and hillsides in the moon are bleached with manna, Adele.

11:44:02.800 --> 11:44:05.480
She'll want to warm herself. What will she do for her fire?

11:44:06.460 --> 11:44:13.140
Fire rises out of the lunar mountains. When she's cold, I'll carry her up to a peak and lay her down on the edge of a crater.

11:44:14.200 --> 11:44:20.300
Qu'elle sera mal, pour comfortable, and her clothes they will wear out. How can she get new ones?

11:44:21.160 --> 11:44:23.700
Mr. Rochester professed to be puzzled.

11:44:24.000 --> 11:44:26.500
Hmm, said he. What would you do, Adele?

11:44:27.920 --> 11:44:36.260
Could all your brains for an expedient? How would a white or pink cloud answer for a gown, do you think? And could one cut a pretty enough scarf out of a rainbow?

11:44:37.320 --> 11:44:41.660
She's far better than she is, concluded Adele, after musing some time.

11:44:42.180 --> 11:44:48.900
Besides, if you would get tired of living with only you in the moon, if I were Mademoiselle, I would never consent to go with you.

11:44:49.440 --> 11:44:52.180
She has consented. She has pledged her word.

11:44:53.080 --> 11:44:58.400
But you can't get her there. There's no road to the moon. It is all air, and neither you nor she can fly.

11:44:59.540 --> 11:45:06.400
Adele, look at that field. We were now outside Thornfield Gate, and barrelling lightly along the smooth road to Millcote,

11:45:06.900 --> 11:45:13.900
where the dust was well laid by the thunderstorm, and where the low hedges and lofty timber trees on each side glistened green and rain-refreshed.

11:45:14.840 --> 11:45:23.520
In that field, Adele, I was walking late one evening about a fortnight since, the evening of the day you helped me to make hay in the orchard meadows.

11:45:24.240 --> 11:45:31.860
And as I was tired with raking swaths, I sat down to rest me on a stire, and there I took out a little book and a pencil,

11:45:32.320 --> 11:45:37.520
and began to write about a misfortune that befell me long ago, and a wish I had for happy days to come.

11:45:38.000 --> 11:45:45.740
I was writing away very fast, though daylight was fading from the leaf, when something came up the path and stopped two yards off me.

11:45:46.100 --> 11:45:52.440
I looked at it. It was a little thing with a veil of gossam on its head. I beckoned it to come near me.

11:45:53.040 --> 11:45:57.840
It stood soon at my knee. I never spoke to it, and it never spoke to me in words.

11:45:58.420 --> 11:46:02.820
But I read its eyes, and it read mine, and our speechless colloquy was to this effect.

11:46:03.580 --> 11:46:08.260
It was a fairy, and come from Elfland, it said, and its errand was to make me happy.

11:46:08.920 --> 11:46:13.560
I must go with it out of the common world to a lonely place, such as the moon, for instance.

11:46:14.280 --> 11:46:17.980
And it nodded its head towards her horn, rising over Hayhill.

11:46:18.520 --> 11:46:22.000
It told me of the alabaster cave and silver vale where we might live.

11:46:22.420 --> 11:46:27.260
I said I should like to go, but reminded it, as you did me, that I had no wings to fly.

11:46:27.260 --> 11:46:30.600
Oh, returned the fairy, that does not signify.

11:46:31.000 --> 11:46:33.700
Here is a talisman that will remove all the difficulties.

11:46:34.520 --> 11:46:36.080
And she held out a pretty gold ring.

11:46:37.200 --> 11:46:41.880
Put it, she said, of the fourth finger of my left hand, and I am yours and your mine,

11:46:42.360 --> 11:46:44.880
and we shall leave earth and make our heaven yonder.

11:46:45.380 --> 11:46:46.840
She nodded again at the moon.

11:46:47.500 --> 11:46:51.540
The ring ideal is in my breecher's pocket, under the disguise of a sovereign.

11:46:52.420 --> 11:46:54.400
But I mean soon to change it to a ring again.

11:46:55.060 --> 11:46:57.420
But what has Mademoiselle to do with that?

11:46:57.540 --> 11:46:58.540
I don't care for the fairy.

11:46:59.100 --> 11:47:01.120
You said it was Mademoiselle you would take to the moon.

11:47:01.940 --> 11:47:04.400
Mademoiselle is a fairy, he said, whispering mysteriously.

11:47:05.680 --> 11:47:09.020
Whereupon I told her not to mind his pain, and she, on her part,

11:47:09.480 --> 11:47:13.580
invents the fund of genuine French skepticism, denominating Mr. Rochester,

11:47:14.300 --> 11:47:19.600
un rare mentor, and assuring him that she made no account whatever of his con de fille,

11:47:19.600 --> 11:47:25.360
and that de reste il y en avait partie fille et quand même il y en avait.

11:47:25.820 --> 11:47:29.460
She was sure they would never appear to him, nor ever give him rings,

11:47:29.820 --> 11:47:31.520
or offer to live with him in the moon.

11:47:33.080 --> 11:47:36.660
The hour spent at Millcote was a somewhat harassing one to me.

11:47:37.200 --> 11:47:40.100
Mr. Rochester obliged me to go to a certain silk warehouse.

11:47:40.940 --> 11:47:43.260
There I was ordered to choose half a dozen dresses.

11:47:43.720 --> 11:47:44.920
I hated the business.

11:47:45.360 --> 11:47:47.340
I begged Lee to defer it.

11:47:47.340 --> 11:47:49.800
No, it should be gone through with now.

11:47:50.540 --> 11:47:53.800
By dint of entreaties expressed in energetic whispers,

11:47:54.340 --> 11:47:56.120
I reduced the half-dozen to two.

11:47:57.000 --> 11:47:59.420
These, however, he vowed he would select himself.

11:48:00.380 --> 11:48:03.680
With anxiety I watched as I rove over the gay stores.

11:48:04.200 --> 11:48:07.860
He would fixed on a rich silk with the most brilliant amethyst dye,

11:48:08.340 --> 11:48:09.820
and a superb pink satin.

11:48:10.160 --> 11:48:12.580
I told him, in a new series of whispers,

11:48:13.000 --> 11:48:16.680
that he might as well buy me a gold gown and a silver bonnet at once.

11:48:16.680 --> 11:48:20.140
I should certainly never venture to wear his choice.

11:48:20.740 --> 11:48:23.780
With infinite difficulty, for he was stubborn as a stone,

11:48:24.280 --> 11:48:27.960
I persuaded him to make an exchange in favour of a silver-black satin

11:48:27.960 --> 11:48:29.000
and pearl-grey silk.

11:48:29.740 --> 11:48:32.120
It might pass for the present, he said,

11:48:32.620 --> 11:48:36.180
but he would yet see me glittering like a parterre.

11:48:36.560 --> 11:48:38.720
Glad was I to get him out of the silk warehouse,

11:48:39.080 --> 11:48:40.640
and then out of a jeweller's shop.

11:48:41.200 --> 11:48:43.560
The more he bought me, the more my cheek burned

11:48:43.560 --> 11:48:45.440
with a sense of annoyance and degradation.

11:48:45.440 --> 11:48:49.340
As we re-entered the carriage, and I sat back feverish, in fact,

11:48:49.700 --> 11:48:52.800
I remembered what, in the hurry of events, dark and bright,

11:48:52.860 --> 11:48:53.760
I had wholly forgotten.

11:48:54.580 --> 11:48:57.260
The letter of my uncle, John Eyre, to Mrs. Reed.

11:48:57.960 --> 11:49:00.520
His intention to adopt me make me his legatee.

11:49:01.320 --> 11:49:03.620
It would indeed be a relief, I thought,

11:49:04.140 --> 11:49:06.460
if I had ever so small an independency.

11:49:06.960 --> 11:49:09.840
I never came bare being dressed like a doll by Mr. Rochester

11:49:09.840 --> 11:49:11.780
or sitting like a second Darnay

11:49:11.780 --> 11:49:14.220
with a golden shower falling daily round me.

11:49:14.220 --> 11:49:16.880
I write to Madeira the moment I get home,

11:49:17.040 --> 11:49:20.120
and tell my uncle John I am going to be married and to whom.

11:49:20.980 --> 11:49:23.780
If I had but a prospect of one day bringing Mr. Rochester

11:49:23.780 --> 11:49:25.120
an accession of fortune,

11:49:25.620 --> 11:49:27.800
I could better endure to be kept by him now.

11:49:28.700 --> 11:49:30.440
And somewhat relieved by this idea,

11:49:30.620 --> 11:49:32.680
which I failed not to execute that day,

11:49:34.060 --> 11:49:36.900
I ventured once more to meet my master's and lover's eye,

11:49:37.400 --> 11:49:39.980
which most pertinently sought mine,

11:49:40.280 --> 11:49:42.280
though I averted both face and gaze.

11:49:42.280 --> 11:49:46.380
He smiled, and I thought his smile was such as a salt and mite

11:49:46.380 --> 11:49:48.620
in a blissful and fond moment,

11:49:48.980 --> 11:49:51.440
bestow on a slave his golden gems had enriched.

11:49:52.480 --> 11:49:56.040
I crushed his hand, which was ever hunting mine, vigorously,

11:49:56.540 --> 11:49:59.100
and thrust it back to him red with a passionate pressure.

11:50:00.040 --> 11:50:02.060
You need not look in that way, I said.

11:50:02.320 --> 11:50:05.120
If you do, I'll wear nothing but my own low-wood frocks

11:50:05.120 --> 11:50:06.180
to the end of the chapter.

11:50:06.960 --> 11:50:08.900
I'll be married in this lilac gingham.

11:50:09.240 --> 11:50:12.200
You may make a dressing-gown for yourself out of pearly grey silk

11:50:12.200 --> 11:50:15.840
and an infinite series of waistcoats out of the black satin.

11:50:16.580 --> 11:50:18.660
He chuckled. He rubbed his hands.

11:50:19.100 --> 11:50:21.200
Oh, is it rich to see and hear her?

11:50:21.280 --> 11:50:24.280
He exclaimed. Is she original? Is she pecaned?

11:50:24.500 --> 11:50:26.860
I would not exchange this one little English girl

11:50:26.860 --> 11:50:29.200
for the Grand Turk's whole seracchio,

11:50:29.480 --> 11:50:31.880
gazellide, hoary forms, and all.

11:50:34.280 --> 11:50:35.940
The eastern illusion put me again.

11:50:36.660 --> 11:50:40.980
I'll not stand you an inch of this dead in a seracchio, I said,

11:50:40.980 --> 11:50:43.740
so don't consider me an equivalent for one.

11:50:44.220 --> 11:50:46.060
If you ever fancy for anything in that line,

11:50:46.280 --> 11:50:49.260
away with you, sir, to the bazaars of Stamboul without delay,

11:50:49.940 --> 11:50:52.140
and lay out in extensive slave purchases

11:50:52.560 --> 11:50:56.340
some of that spare cash you seem at a loss to spend satisfactory here.

11:50:57.120 --> 11:50:58.480
And what will you do, Janet,

11:50:58.800 --> 11:51:01.200
while I am bargaining for so many tons of flesh

11:51:01.200 --> 11:51:02.940
and such an assortment of black eyes?

11:51:03.780 --> 11:51:06.380
I'll be preparing myself to go out as a missionary

11:51:06.380 --> 11:51:08.740
to preach liberty to them that I enslaved,

11:51:08.740 --> 11:51:11.100
your harem inmates among the rest.

11:51:11.560 --> 11:51:14.140
I'll get admitted there, and I'll stir up mutiny,

11:51:14.640 --> 11:51:17.300
and you, three-tailed beshaw, as you are, sir,

11:51:17.920 --> 11:51:20.980
shall in a thrice find yourself fettered amongst our hands.

11:51:21.660 --> 11:51:24.220
Nor will I, for one, consent to cut your bonds

11:51:24.220 --> 11:51:25.440
till you have signed a charter,

11:51:25.800 --> 11:51:28.860
the most liberal that this pot has ever yet conferred.

11:51:30.640 --> 11:51:32.840
I would consent to be at your mercy, Jane.

11:51:33.280 --> 11:51:35.140
I would have no mercy, Mr. Rochester,

11:51:35.620 --> 11:51:38.160
if you supplicated for it with an eye like that,

11:51:38.160 --> 11:51:40.060
but while you looked so, I should be certain

11:51:40.060 --> 11:51:42.720
that whatever charter you might grant under curshion,

11:51:43.060 --> 11:51:46.100
your first act, when released, would be to violate its conditions.

11:51:47.280 --> 11:51:48.800
Why, Jane, what would you have?

11:51:49.520 --> 11:51:52.660
I fear you will compel me to go through a private marriage ceremony

11:51:53.300 --> 11:51:55.240
besides that performed at the altar.

11:51:56.020 --> 11:51:58.560
You will stipulate, I see, for peculiar terms.

11:51:59.060 --> 11:52:00.040
What will they be?

11:52:00.920 --> 11:52:02.700
I only want an easy mind, sir,

11:52:03.100 --> 11:52:05.300
not crushed by crowded obligations.

11:52:05.800 --> 11:52:08.260
Do you remember what you said of Céline Varence?

11:52:08.900 --> 11:52:11.060
Of the diamonds the cashmere you gave her?

11:52:11.380 --> 11:52:13.760
I will not be your English, Céline Varence.

11:52:14.360 --> 11:52:16.700
I shall continue to act as a deals governess.

11:52:17.320 --> 11:52:19.540
By that I shall earn my board and lodgings,

11:52:19.860 --> 11:52:21.260
and thirty pounds a year besides.

11:52:21.740 --> 11:52:23.900
I'll furnish my own wardrobe out of that money,

11:52:24.380 --> 11:52:26.420
and you shall give me nothing but...

11:52:26.420 --> 11:52:27.240
Well, but what?

11:52:28.000 --> 11:52:30.680
Your regard, and if I give you mine in return,

11:52:30.960 --> 11:52:31.920
that debt will be quit.

11:52:32.820 --> 11:52:35.700
Well, for cool native impotence,

11:52:35.940 --> 11:52:38.800
and pure innate pride you haven't your equal, said he.

11:52:39.140 --> 11:52:40.520
We were now approaching Thornfield.

11:52:41.320 --> 11:52:43.140
Will it please you to dine with me today?

11:52:43.440 --> 11:52:45.360
he asked as we re-entered the gates.

11:52:46.060 --> 11:52:46.920
No, thank you, sir.

11:52:47.800 --> 11:52:50.940
And what for? No thank you, if one may inquire.

11:52:51.500 --> 11:52:53.160
I never have dined with you, sir,

11:52:53.300 --> 11:52:56.040
and I see no reason why I should now, till...

11:52:56.040 --> 11:52:58.880
Till what? You delight in half-phrases.

11:52:59.500 --> 11:53:00.520
So I can't help it.

11:53:01.100 --> 11:53:03.880
Do you suppose I eat like an ogre or a gowl,

11:53:03.980 --> 11:53:06.260
that you dread being the companion of my repast?

11:53:07.080 --> 11:53:09.700
I have formed no superstition of the subject, sir,

11:53:09.920 --> 11:53:12.260
but I want to go on as usual for another month.

11:53:13.580 --> 11:53:15.920
You will give up your governessing slavery at once.

11:53:16.960 --> 11:53:19.200
Indeed, begging your pardon, sir, I shall not.

11:53:19.740 --> 11:53:21.460
I shall just go on with it as usual.

11:53:21.820 --> 11:53:23.620
I shall keep out of your way all day,

11:53:23.920 --> 11:53:25.380
as I have been accustomed to do.

11:53:25.900 --> 11:53:27.120
You may sing for me in the evening,

11:53:27.160 --> 11:53:28.800
when you feel disposed to see me,

11:53:28.800 --> 11:53:31.780
and I'll come then, but at no other time.

11:53:32.800 --> 11:53:33.880
I want a smoke, Janet,

11:53:34.100 --> 11:53:36.520
or a pinch of snuff to comfort me and all this.

11:53:37.720 --> 11:53:40.900
Poor me donna own continence, as a deal would say.

11:53:41.560 --> 11:53:44.760
And unfortunately I have neither my cigar-case nor my snuff-box.

11:53:45.540 --> 11:53:46.880
But listen, whisper,

11:53:47.980 --> 11:53:49.740
it is your time now, little tyrant,

11:53:49.840 --> 11:53:51.540
but it will be mine presently,

11:53:51.980 --> 11:53:54.460
and when I have fairly seized you to heaven to hold,

11:53:54.840 --> 11:53:56.800
I'll just, figuratively speaking,

11:53:56.800 --> 11:53:59.280
attach you to a chain like this,

11:53:59.520 --> 11:54:00.820
touching his watch-guard.

11:54:01.500 --> 11:54:02.680
Yes, bunny-wee thing,

11:54:02.840 --> 11:54:05.420
I'll wear you in my bosom lest a jewelish time.

11:54:06.880 --> 11:54:09.500
He said this as he helped me to alight from the carriage,

11:54:09.940 --> 11:54:11.620
and while he afterwards lifted out a deal,

11:54:11.960 --> 11:54:14.320
I entered the house and made good my retreat upstairs.

11:54:15.920 --> 11:54:18.220
He duly summoned me to his presence in the evening.

11:54:18.800 --> 11:54:20.580
I'd prepared an occupation for him,

11:54:20.620 --> 11:54:22.660
for I was determined not to spend the whole time

11:54:22.660 --> 11:54:24.220
in that city at stake conversation.

11:54:24.820 --> 11:54:26.240
I remembered his fine voice,

11:54:26.240 --> 11:54:27.560
and knew he liked to sing.

11:54:28.180 --> 11:54:29.520
Good singers generally do.

11:54:30.100 --> 11:54:31.580
I was no vocalist myself,

11:54:31.600 --> 11:54:33.660
and in his fastidious judgment,

11:54:34.060 --> 11:54:35.100
no musician either.

11:54:35.640 --> 11:54:38.400
But I delighted in listening when the performance was good.

11:54:39.000 --> 11:54:41.280
No sooner had twilight that our romance

11:54:41.280 --> 11:54:44.300
began to lower her blue and starry banner over the letters,

11:54:45.000 --> 11:54:45.760
that I rose,

11:54:46.220 --> 11:54:46.960
opened the piano,

11:54:47.380 --> 11:54:49.940
and entreated him for the love of heaven to give me a song.

11:54:50.700 --> 11:54:52.760
He said I was a capricious witch,

11:54:53.100 --> 11:54:54.840
and that he would rather sing another time,

11:54:54.840 --> 11:54:57.380
but I averred that no time was like the present.

11:54:59.180 --> 11:55:00.620
Did I like his voice?

11:55:01.320 --> 11:55:01.900
He asked.

11:55:02.920 --> 11:55:03.520
Very much.

11:55:04.060 --> 11:55:07.160
I was not fond of pampering that susceptible vanity of his,

11:55:07.600 --> 11:55:10.720
but for once, and for motives of expediency,

11:55:11.440 --> 11:55:13.640
I would ensueth and stimulate it.

11:55:14.440 --> 11:55:16.360
Vain Janet, you must play the accompaniment.

11:55:17.200 --> 11:55:18.800
Very well, sir. I will try.

11:55:19.680 --> 11:55:20.660
I did try,

11:55:20.700 --> 11:55:22.640
but was presently swept off the stool

11:55:22.640 --> 11:55:25.020
and denominated a little bungler,

11:55:25.700 --> 11:55:28.040
being pushed unceremoniously to one side,

11:55:28.320 --> 11:55:30.180
which was precisely what I wanted.

11:55:31.080 --> 11:55:32.300
He usurped my place,

11:55:32.440 --> 11:55:34.100
and proceeded to accompany himself,

11:55:34.460 --> 11:55:35.880
for he could play as well as sing.

11:55:36.600 --> 11:55:38.140
I heed me to the winter recess,

11:55:38.420 --> 11:55:39.300
and while I sat then,

11:55:39.340 --> 11:55:41.420
looked out at the misty trees and dim lawn.

11:55:41.740 --> 11:55:43.740
Two sweet airs were sung in mellow tones

11:55:43.740 --> 11:55:45.080
the following strain.

11:55:46.480 --> 11:55:48.340
The truest love the devil heart

11:55:48.340 --> 11:55:50.380
felt at its kindlet's core

11:55:50.380 --> 11:55:52.940
did throw each vein in quickened start

11:55:52.940 --> 11:55:54.880
the tide of being poor.

11:55:55.920 --> 11:55:57.520
Her coming was my hope each day,

11:55:57.700 --> 11:55:59.000
her parting was my pain.

11:55:59.680 --> 11:56:01.460
The chance that did her steps delay

11:56:01.460 --> 11:56:03.000
was ice in every vein.

11:56:04.260 --> 11:56:06.200
I dreamed it would be nameless bliss,

11:56:06.680 --> 11:56:08.320
as I loved left to be,

11:56:08.920 --> 11:56:10.500
and to this object did I press

11:56:10.500 --> 11:56:12.460
as blind as eagerly.

11:56:13.340 --> 11:56:15.560
But wide as pathless was the space

11:56:15.560 --> 11:56:17.260
that lay our lives between,

11:56:18.060 --> 11:56:19.900
and dangerous as the foamy race

11:56:19.900 --> 11:56:21.800
of ocean surges green,

11:56:22.720 --> 11:56:24.460
and haunted as a rubber path

11:56:24.460 --> 11:56:26.520
through wilderness or wood,

11:56:26.860 --> 11:56:27.800
for might and right,

11:56:28.120 --> 11:56:29.180
and woe and wrath,

11:56:29.520 --> 11:56:30.800
between our spirits stood.

11:56:32.240 --> 11:56:33.160
I dangerous dared,

11:56:33.440 --> 11:56:34.700
I hindered and scorned,

11:56:34.820 --> 11:56:36.360
I omens did defy.

11:56:36.820 --> 11:56:39.120
Whatever menaced, harassed, warned,

11:56:39.640 --> 11:56:41.340
I passed impetuous by.

11:56:42.980 --> 11:56:44.020
On sped my rainbow

11:56:44.020 --> 11:56:44.860
fast as light,

11:56:45.360 --> 11:56:46.640
I flew as in a dream,

11:56:46.640 --> 11:56:49.220
for glorious rose upon my sight

11:56:49.220 --> 11:56:52.180
the child of shower and gleam.

11:56:52.460 --> 11:56:54.580
Still bright the clouds of suffering dim,

11:56:55.020 --> 11:56:56.860
shines that soft, solemn joy,

11:56:57.660 --> 11:56:59.780
nor care I now how dense and grim

11:56:59.780 --> 11:57:01.260
disaster's gathered eye.

11:57:02.440 --> 11:57:04.160
I care not in this moment sweet,

11:57:04.820 --> 11:57:06.940
though all I have rushed o'er,

11:57:07.240 --> 11:57:09.120
should come in pinion strong and fleet,

11:57:09.460 --> 11:57:10.880
proclaiming vengeance sore.

11:57:12.100 --> 11:57:14.480
Though haughty hate should strike me down,

11:57:14.480 --> 11:57:16.520
bright bar approached to me,

11:57:16.880 --> 11:57:19.460
and grinding might with furious frown,

11:57:19.760 --> 11:57:21.080
swear endless enmity.

11:57:22.280 --> 11:57:24.120
My love has placed a little hand,

11:57:24.380 --> 11:57:25.580
with noble faith in mine,

11:57:26.460 --> 11:57:28.420
and vowed that wedlock's sacred band

11:57:28.420 --> 11:57:30.440
our nature shall entwine.

11:57:31.120 --> 11:57:33.380
My love has sworn with seal and kiss,

11:57:33.700 --> 11:57:35.280
with me to live, to die.

11:57:36.060 --> 11:57:37.900
I have at last my nameless bliss,

11:57:38.640 --> 11:57:40.880
as I love, loved am I.

11:57:41.920 --> 11:57:43.760
He rose and came towards me,

11:57:43.760 --> 11:57:45.620
and I saw his face all kindled,

11:57:45.760 --> 11:57:47.220
with his full falcon eye flashing,

11:57:47.800 --> 11:57:50.140
and tenderness and passion in every alignment.

11:57:51.400 --> 11:57:52.800
I qualled momentarily.

11:57:53.400 --> 11:57:54.580
Then I rallied.

11:57:55.100 --> 11:57:58.220
Soft scene, daring demonstration I would not have,

11:57:58.600 --> 11:58:00.080
and I stood in peril of both.

11:58:00.800 --> 11:58:02.520
A weapon of defence must be prepared.

11:58:03.020 --> 11:58:04.160
I wetted my tongue.

11:58:04.520 --> 11:58:06.860
As he reached me, I asked with asperity,

11:58:07.860 --> 11:58:09.440
Whom he was going to marry now?

11:58:10.460 --> 11:58:12.020
That was a strange question

11:58:12.020 --> 11:58:13.560
to be put by his darling Jane.

11:58:14.220 --> 11:58:15.840
Indeed, I considered it

11:58:15.840 --> 11:58:17.580
a very natural and necessary one.

11:58:18.040 --> 11:58:20.400
He had talked of his future wife dying with him.

11:58:20.840 --> 11:58:22.840
What did he mean by such a pagan idea?

11:58:23.200 --> 11:58:24.880
I had no intention of dying with him.

11:58:24.920 --> 11:58:26.120
He might depend on that.

11:58:27.640 --> 11:58:29.400
Oh, all he longed, all he prayed for,

11:58:29.520 --> 11:58:30.740
was that I might live with him.

11:58:30.980 --> 11:58:32.780
Death was not for such as I.

11:58:34.000 --> 11:58:34.940
Indeed it was.

11:58:35.260 --> 11:58:36.720
I had as good a right to die

11:58:36.720 --> 11:58:38.120
when my time came as he had,

11:58:38.120 --> 11:58:39.720
but I should bide that time

11:58:39.720 --> 11:58:41.220
and not be hurried away in a city.

11:58:42.920 --> 11:58:44.820
Would I forgive him for the selfish idea

11:58:44.820 --> 11:58:46.940
and prove my pardon by a reconciling kiss?

11:58:47.480 --> 11:58:49.540
No, I would rather be excused.

11:58:50.140 --> 11:58:51.100
Here I heard myself

11:58:51.100 --> 11:58:53.120
apostrophised as a hard little thing,

11:58:53.300 --> 11:58:54.200
and it was added.

11:58:55.000 --> 11:58:57.220
Any other woman would have been melted to marrow

11:58:57.220 --> 11:58:59.400
at hearing such stances crooned in her praise.

11:59:00.260 --> 11:59:02.220
I assured him I was naturally hard,

11:59:02.560 --> 11:59:03.780
very flinty,

11:59:03.880 --> 11:59:05.660
and that he would often find me so,

11:59:05.660 --> 11:59:07.380
and that, moreover,

11:59:07.640 --> 11:59:10.260
I was determined to show him diverse record points

11:59:10.260 --> 11:59:12.320
in my character before the ensuring

11:59:12.320 --> 11:59:13.680
four weeks elapsed.

11:59:13.900 --> 11:59:15.620
He should know full of what sort of bargain

11:59:15.620 --> 11:59:17.680
he had made while there was yet time

11:59:17.680 --> 11:59:18.720
to rescind it.

11:59:19.400 --> 11:59:21.340
Would I be quiet and talk rationally?

11:59:22.060 --> 11:59:23.340
I would be quiet if he liked,

11:59:23.520 --> 11:59:25.000
and as to talking rationally,

11:59:25.280 --> 11:59:27.280
I flattered myself I was doing that now.

11:59:28.100 --> 11:59:29.580
He fretted, pitched, and shored.

11:59:30.680 --> 11:59:31.700
Very good, I thought.

11:59:31.880 --> 11:59:33.760
You may fume and fidget as you please,

11:59:33.760 --> 11:59:36.140
but this is the best plan to pursue with you,

11:59:36.200 --> 11:59:36.800
I'm certain.

11:59:37.480 --> 11:59:38.940
I like you more than I can say,

11:59:39.260 --> 11:59:42.100
but I will not sink into baths of sentiment,

11:59:42.600 --> 11:59:43.940
and with this needle of riparty

11:59:44.360 --> 11:59:46.700
I'll keep you from the edge of a gulf too,

11:59:47.240 --> 11:59:47.900
and, moreover,

11:59:48.540 --> 11:59:50.020
maintained by its pungent aid,

11:59:50.360 --> 11:59:51.960
let distance between you and myself

11:59:51.960 --> 11:59:54.700
be most conductive to a real mutual advantage.

11:59:56.120 --> 11:59:57.160
From less to more,

11:59:57.240 --> 11:59:59.540
I woked him up to considerable irritation.

12:00:00.080 --> 12:00:02.160
Then, after he had retired in Dajian,

12:00:02.160 --> 12:00:03.800
quite to the other end of the room,

12:00:04.200 --> 12:00:05.120
I got up and saying,

12:00:05.640 --> 12:00:06.720
I wish you good night, sir,

12:00:06.900 --> 12:00:08.940
in my natural and wanted respectful manner.

12:00:09.660 --> 12:00:12.120
I stepped out by the side door and got away.

12:00:13.280 --> 12:00:14.760
This system thus entered on,

12:00:15.160 --> 12:00:16.560
I pursued during the whole season

12:00:16.560 --> 12:00:17.280
of probation,

12:00:17.720 --> 12:00:18.940
and with the best success.

12:00:20.660 --> 12:00:21.940
He was kept, to be sure,

12:00:22.120 --> 12:00:23.600
rather crass and crusty,

12:00:23.980 --> 12:00:25.440
but on the whole I could see he was

12:00:25.440 --> 12:00:26.540
accidentally entertained,

12:00:27.300 --> 12:00:28.560
and that a lameplike submission

12:00:28.560 --> 12:00:30.520
and turtledove sensibility,

12:00:31.520 --> 12:00:33.140
while thus during his despotism

12:00:33.140 --> 12:00:35.000
more would have pleased his judgment,

12:00:35.500 --> 12:00:36.860
satisfied his common sense,

12:00:37.320 --> 12:00:39.060
and even suited his tasteless.

12:00:40.180 --> 12:00:41.360
In other people's presence

12:00:41.360 --> 12:00:42.660
I was, as formerly,

12:00:43.420 --> 12:00:44.540
differential and quiet,

12:00:45.060 --> 12:00:47.260
any other line of conduct being uncalled for.

12:00:47.540 --> 12:00:48.920
It was only in the evening

12:00:48.920 --> 12:00:50.800
conferences I thus

12:00:50.800 --> 12:00:52.360
thwarted and afflicted him.

12:00:52.720 --> 12:00:54.780
He continued to send for me punctually

12:00:54.780 --> 12:00:56.380
the moment the clock struck seven,

12:00:56.380 --> 12:00:58.580
though when I appeared before him now

12:00:58.580 --> 12:01:00.620
he had no such honeying terms as

12:01:01.140 --> 12:01:03.160
love and darling on his lips.

12:01:03.800 --> 12:01:05.500
The best words at my service were

12:01:05.500 --> 12:01:06.620
provoking puppet,

12:01:07.120 --> 12:01:07.920
malicious elf,

12:01:08.560 --> 12:01:10.600
sprite, changeling, etc.

12:01:11.440 --> 12:01:12.440
For caresses, too,

12:01:12.520 --> 12:01:13.500
I now got grimaces,

12:01:14.320 --> 12:01:16.600
for a pressure of the hand, a pinch in the arm,

12:01:17.440 --> 12:01:18.480
for a kiss on the cheek

12:01:18.480 --> 12:01:19.960
as the weird tweak of the ear.

12:01:20.660 --> 12:01:21.600
It was all right.

12:01:21.900 --> 12:01:24.300
At present I decidedly preferred these fierce

12:01:24.300 --> 12:01:25.860
favors to anything more tender.

12:01:26.680 --> 12:01:27.980
Mrs. Fairfax, I saw,

12:01:28.420 --> 12:01:30.380
approved me. Her anxiety on my

12:01:30.380 --> 12:01:32.320
account vanished. Therefore I was

12:01:32.320 --> 12:01:33.260
certain I did well.

12:01:34.120 --> 12:01:36.180
Meantime Mr. Rochester affirmed that I was

12:01:36.180 --> 12:01:38.300
wearing him to skin and bone and threatened

12:01:38.300 --> 12:01:40.100
awful vengeance for my present

12:01:40.100 --> 12:01:42.520
conduct at some period fast coming.

12:01:43.100 --> 12:01:44.520
I laughed in my sleeve at his

12:01:44.520 --> 12:01:44.940
menaces.

12:01:45.440 --> 12:01:47.680
I can keep you in a reasonable check now,

12:01:47.820 --> 12:01:50.240
I reflected, and I don't doubt to be able to

12:01:50.240 --> 12:01:52.340
do it hereafter. If one expedient

12:01:52.340 --> 12:01:54.360
loses its virtue, another must be

12:01:54.360 --> 12:01:55.080
devised.

12:01:56.340 --> 12:01:58.320
Yet, after all, my task was not an easy

12:01:58.320 --> 12:02:00.280
one. Often I would rather

12:02:00.280 --> 12:02:01.860
have pleased than tease him.

12:02:02.480 --> 12:02:04.300
My future husband was becoming to me

12:02:04.300 --> 12:02:06.320
my whole world, and more than the

12:02:06.320 --> 12:02:08.340
world, almost my hope of heaven.

12:02:09.100 --> 12:02:10.320
He stood between me and

12:02:10.320 --> 12:02:12.300
every thought of religion as

12:02:12.300 --> 12:02:14.280
an eclipse intervenes between man and the

12:02:14.280 --> 12:02:16.260
broad sun. I could not in

12:02:16.260 --> 12:02:18.200
those days seek God for His

12:02:18.200 --> 12:02:20.300
creature, of whom I had made an

12:02:20.300 --> 12:02:20.780
idol.

12:02:44.780 --> 12:02:46.140
CHAPTER XXV

12:02:46.580 --> 12:02:48.400
The month of courtship had wasted.

12:02:48.800 --> 12:02:50.600
Its very last hours were being numbered.

12:02:50.600 --> 12:02:57.540
There was no putting off the day that advanced, the bridal day, and all preparations for its

12:02:57.540 --> 12:02:58.660
arrival were complete.

12:03:00.100 --> 12:03:02.300
I at least had nothing more to do.

12:03:03.160 --> 12:03:08.840
There were my trunks, packed, locked, corded, ranged in a row along the wall of my little

12:03:08.840 --> 12:03:09.340
chamber.

12:03:10.260 --> 12:03:14.580
To-morrow, at this time, there would be far on the road to London.

12:03:16.100 --> 12:03:25.220
And so should I, D. V.—or rather, not I, but one Jane Rochester, a person whom as yet

12:03:25.220 --> 12:03:26.100
I knew not.

12:03:27.440 --> 12:03:30.580
The cards of the address alone remained to nail on.

12:03:31.480 --> 12:03:34.440
They lay four little squares in the drawer.

12:03:35.800 --> 12:03:41.880
Mr. Rochester had himself written the direction, Mrs. Rochester, Hotel London, on each.

12:03:42.880 --> 12:03:47.420
I could not persuade myself to affix them, or to have them affixed.

12:03:48.020 --> 12:03:50.580
Mrs. Rochester, she did not exist.

12:03:51.380 --> 12:03:55.540
She would not be born till to-morrow, some time after eight o'clock a.m.

12:03:56.460 --> 12:04:01.240
And I would wait to be assured she had come into the world alive before I assigned to

12:04:01.240 --> 12:04:02.500
her all that property.

12:04:04.100 --> 12:04:11.080
It was enough that in yonder closet, opposite my dressing-table, garments, said to be hers,

12:04:11.080 --> 12:04:15.140
had already displaced my black-stuff low-wood frock.

12:04:15.840 --> 12:04:22.400
For not to me appertained that suit of wedding remnant—the pearl-coloured robe, the vapoury

12:04:22.400 --> 12:04:25.220
veil pendant from the usurp portmanteau.

12:04:26.040 --> 12:04:32.820
I shut the closet to conceal the strange wraith-like apparel it contained, which, at this evening

12:04:32.820 --> 12:04:38.300
hour, nine o'clock, gave out certainly a most ghostly shimmer through the shadow of my apartment.

12:04:39.080 --> 12:04:41.920
I will leave you by yourself, White Dream,' I said.

12:04:42.500 --> 12:04:43.600
I am feverish.

12:04:43.720 --> 12:04:44.800
I hear the wind blowing.

12:04:45.500 --> 12:04:49.240
I will go out of doors and feel it.'

12:04:49.600 --> 12:04:55.160
It was not only the hurry of preparation that made me feverish, not only the anticipation

12:04:55.160 --> 12:04:58.940
of the great change, the new life which was to commence to-morrow.

12:04:59.520 --> 12:05:05.340
Both these circumstances had their share doubtless in producing that restless, excited mood which

12:05:05.340 --> 12:05:08.860
hurried me forth at this late hour into the darkening grounds.

12:05:10.280 --> 12:05:13.360
But a third cause influenced my mind more than they.

12:05:15.900 --> 12:05:18.920
I had at heart a strange and anxious thought.

12:05:20.220 --> 12:05:22.340
Something had happened which I could not comprehend.

12:05:23.420 --> 12:05:26.000
No one knew of, or had seen the event but myself.

12:05:27.040 --> 12:05:29.180
It had taken place the preceding night.

12:05:30.540 --> 12:05:35.560
Mr. Rochester that night was absent from home, nor was he yet returned.

12:05:36.600 --> 12:05:40.480
Business had called him to a small estate of two or three farms he possessed thirty

12:05:40.480 --> 12:05:41.360
miles off.

12:05:43.040 --> 12:05:48.340
Business it was requisite he should settle in person, previous to his meditated departure

12:05:48.340 --> 12:05:49.140
from England.

12:05:50.720 --> 12:05:56.840
I waited now his return, eager to disburden my mind, and to seek of him the solution of

12:05:56.840 --> 12:05:58.740
the enigma that perplexed me.

12:05:59.660 --> 12:06:05.640
Stay till he comes, reader, and when I disclose my secret to him you shall hear the confidence.

12:06:08.080 --> 12:06:14.020
I sought the orchard, driven to its shelter by the wind, which all day had blown strong

12:06:14.020 --> 12:06:18.380
and full from the south, without, however, bringing a speck of rain.

12:06:20.020 --> 12:06:25.040
Instead of subsiding as night drew on, it seemed to augment its rush and deepen its

12:06:25.040 --> 12:06:25.380
roar.

12:06:25.380 --> 12:06:31.900
The trees blew steadfastly one way, never writhing round, and scarcely tossing back

12:06:31.900 --> 12:06:33.520
their boughs once in an hour.

12:06:34.620 --> 12:06:38.160
So continuous was the strain bending their branchy heads northward.

12:06:39.880 --> 12:06:44.740
The clouds drifted from pole to pole, fast following, mass on mass.

12:06:45.980 --> 12:06:49.120
No glimpse of blue sky had been visible that July day.

12:06:51.640 --> 12:06:57.540
It was not without a certain wild pleasure I ran before the wind, delivering my trouble

12:06:57.540 --> 12:07:00.820
of mind to the measureless air torrent thundering through space.

12:07:02.140 --> 12:07:05.760
Descending the laurel walk, I faced the wreck of the chestnut tree.

12:07:06.880 --> 12:07:08.600
It stood up black and driven.

12:07:09.980 --> 12:07:13.280
The trunk, split down the centre, gasped ghastly.

12:07:14.560 --> 12:07:19.680
The clove and hearth were not broken from each other, for the firm base and strong roots

12:07:19.680 --> 12:07:21.160
kept them unsundered below.

12:07:22.700 --> 12:07:27.000
Though community of vitality was destroyed, the sap could flow no more.

12:07:27.660 --> 12:07:32.940
The great boughs on each side were dead, and next winter's tempests would be sure to fell

12:07:32.940 --> 12:07:34.640
one or both to earth.

12:07:35.720 --> 12:07:42.180
As yet, however, they might be said to form one tree—a ruin, but an entire ruin.

12:07:43.800 --> 12:07:49.500
You did right to hold fast to each other, I said, as if the monster splinters were living

12:07:49.500 --> 12:07:50.980
things and could hear me.

12:07:51.780 --> 12:07:57.320
I think, scathed as you look, and charred and scorched, there must be a little sense

12:07:57.320 --> 12:08:02.240
of life in you yet, rising out of that adhesion at the faithful, honest roots.

12:08:02.800 --> 12:08:08.240
You will never have green leaves more, never more see birds making nests and singing idols

12:08:08.240 --> 12:08:09.920
in your bowels.

12:08:10.300 --> 12:08:14.640
The time of pleasure and love is over with you, but you are not desolate.

12:08:15.620 --> 12:08:18.460
Each of you has a comrade to sympathise with him in his decay.

12:08:20.380 --> 12:08:26.120
As I looked up then, the moon appeared momentarily in that part of the sky which filled their

12:08:26.120 --> 12:08:26.620
fissure.

12:08:27.480 --> 12:08:30.120
Her disk was blood-red and half overcast.

12:08:31.120 --> 12:08:36.900
She seemed to throw on me one bewildered dreary glance, and buried herself again instantly

12:08:36.900 --> 12:08:38.420
in the deep drift of cloud.

12:08:39.900 --> 12:08:46.380
The wind fell for a second round Thornfield, but far away over wood and water poured a

12:08:46.380 --> 12:08:47.780
wild melancholy wail.

12:08:48.860 --> 12:08:51.480
It was sad to listen to, and I ran off again.

12:08:53.660 --> 12:08:58.400
Here and there I strayed through the orchard, gathered up the apples with which the grass

12:08:58.400 --> 12:09:00.640
and the tree roots were thickly strewn.

12:09:01.380 --> 12:09:04.980
Then I employed myself in dividing the ripe from the unripe.

12:09:05.760 --> 12:09:09.180
I carried them into the house, and put them away in the storeroom.

12:09:10.220 --> 12:09:15.760
Then I repaired to the library to ascertain whether the fire was lit, for, though summer,

12:09:16.240 --> 12:09:21.040
I knew on such a gloomy evening Mr. Rochester would like to see a cheerful hearth when he

12:09:21.040 --> 12:09:22.100
came in.

12:09:23.000 --> 12:09:26.260
Yes, the fire had been kindled some time, and burnt well.

12:09:27.040 --> 12:09:31.880
I placed his armchair by the chimney-corner, I wheeled the table near it, I let down the

12:09:31.880 --> 12:09:34.920
curtain, and had the candles brought in ready for lighting.

12:09:36.620 --> 12:09:40.800
More restless than ever when I had completed these arrangements, I could not sit still,

12:09:41.600 --> 12:09:43.160
nor even remain in the house.

12:09:44.260 --> 12:09:49.600
A little time-piece in the room, and the old clock in the hall, simultaneously struck ten.

12:09:51.420 --> 12:09:57.100
How late it grows, I said, I will run down to the gates, it is moonlight at intervals,

12:09:57.540 --> 12:09:59.200
I can see a good way on the road.

12:10:00.040 --> 12:10:04.420
He may be coming now, and to meet him will save some minutes of suspense.

12:10:07.660 --> 12:10:11.240
The wind roared high in the great trees which embowered the gates.

12:10:12.340 --> 12:10:17.940
But the road, as far as I could see, to the right hand and the left, was all still and

12:10:17.940 --> 12:10:23.500
solitary, save for the shadows of clouds crossing it at intervals as the moon looked out.

12:10:24.460 --> 12:10:29.040
It was but a long pale line, unvaried by one moving speck.

12:10:30.640 --> 12:10:36.620
A pure ill tear dimmed my eye while I looked, a tear of disappointment and impatience.

12:10:37.820 --> 12:10:39.540
Ashamed of it, I wiped it away.

12:10:40.740 --> 12:10:45.940
I lingered, the moon shut herself wholly within her chamber, and drew close her curtain of

12:10:45.940 --> 12:10:46.760
dense cloud.

12:10:47.560 --> 12:10:51.180
The night grew dark, rain came driving fast on the gale.

12:10:51.760 --> 12:10:54.440
I wish he would come, I wish he would come!

12:10:55.160 --> 12:10:58.740
I exclaimed, ceased with hypochondriac foreboding.

12:10:59.960 --> 12:11:02.380
I had expected his arrival before tea.

12:11:03.120 --> 12:11:04.320
Now it was dark.

12:11:04.780 --> 12:11:06.040
What could keep him?

12:11:06.260 --> 12:11:07.480
Had an accident happened?

12:11:08.620 --> 12:11:11.100
The event of last night again recurred to me.

12:11:11.500 --> 12:11:13.680
I interpreted as a warning of distress.

12:11:14.360 --> 12:11:20.420
I feared my hopes were too bright to be realised, and I had enjoyed so much bliss lately that

12:11:20.420 --> 12:11:24.140
I imagined my fortune had passed its meridian and must now decline.

12:11:26.120 --> 12:11:31.980
While I cannot return to the house, I thought, I cannot sit by the fireside while he is abroad

12:11:31.980 --> 12:11:33.060
in inclement weather.

12:11:34.360 --> 12:11:36.720
Better tire my limbs than strain my heart.

12:11:37.040 --> 12:11:39.060
I will go forward and meet him.

12:11:40.520 --> 12:11:41.760
I set out.

12:11:41.960 --> 12:11:43.880
I walked fast, but not far.

12:11:44.560 --> 12:11:48.000
Ere I had measured a quarter of a mile, I heard the tramp of hooves.

12:11:48.960 --> 12:11:50.840
A horseman came on, full gallop.

12:11:51.020 --> 12:11:52.600
A dog ran by his side.

12:11:55.040 --> 12:12:01.840
Away with evil presentiment, it was he, here he was, mounted on Messoror, followed by Pilate.

12:12:02.580 --> 12:12:08.600
He saw me, for the moon had opened a blue field in the sky, and rode in it watery bright.

12:12:09.940 --> 12:12:12.300
He took his hat off and waved it round his head.

12:12:13.080 --> 12:12:14.640
I now ran to meet him.

12:12:15.720 --> 12:12:20.360
There, he exclaimed, as he stretched out his hand and bent from the saddle.

12:12:21.020 --> 12:12:23.060
You cannot do without me, that is evident.

12:12:23.420 --> 12:12:24.940
Step on my boot-toe.

12:12:25.100 --> 12:12:26.100
Give me both hands.

12:12:26.320 --> 12:12:26.700
Mount.

12:12:28.000 --> 12:12:28.960
I obeyed.

12:12:29.060 --> 12:12:30.200
Joy made me agile.

12:12:30.200 --> 12:12:32.080
I sprang up before him.

12:12:32.960 --> 12:12:37.900
A hearty kissing I got for a welcome, and some boastful triumph, which I swallowed as

12:12:37.900 --> 12:12:38.720
well as I could.

12:12:40.520 --> 12:12:43.240
He checked himself in his exultation to demand,

12:12:43.520 --> 12:12:47.580
"'But is there anything the matter, Janet, that you come to meet me at such an hour?

12:12:47.920 --> 12:12:49.200
Is there anything wrong?'

12:12:50.380 --> 12:12:52.420
"'No, but I thought you would never come.

12:12:52.680 --> 12:12:56.800
I could not bear to wait in the house for you, especially with this rain and wind.'

12:12:56.800 --> 12:12:58.560
"'Rain and wind, indeed.

12:12:58.560 --> 12:13:00.640
Yes, you are dripping like a mermaid.

12:13:01.320 --> 12:13:02.640
Put my cloak round you.

12:13:03.100 --> 12:13:04.720
But I think you are feverish, Janet.

12:13:05.360 --> 12:13:07.400
Both your cheek and hand are burning hot.

12:13:08.400 --> 12:13:10.340
I ask again, is there anything the matter?

12:13:11.300 --> 12:13:12.100
Nothing now.

12:13:12.180 --> 12:13:13.920
I am neither afraid nor unhappy.'

12:13:16.000 --> 12:13:17.560
"'Then you have been both?'

12:13:18.360 --> 12:13:18.760
"'Rather.

12:13:18.940 --> 12:13:23.160
But I'll tell you all about it by and by, sir, and I dare say you will only laugh at

12:13:23.160 --> 12:13:24.120
me for my pains.'

12:13:26.300 --> 12:13:28.700
"'I'll laugh at you heartily when to-morrow is past.

12:13:29.340 --> 12:13:30.700
Till then I dare not.

12:13:30.800 --> 12:13:32.340
My prize is not certain.

12:13:33.380 --> 12:13:38.060
This is you, who have been as slippery as an eel this last month, and as thorny as a

12:13:38.060 --> 12:13:38.820
brier rose.

12:13:39.520 --> 12:13:42.260
I could not lay a finger anywhere, but I was pricked.

12:13:42.840 --> 12:13:45.600
And now I seem to have gathered up a stray lamb in my arms.

12:13:46.360 --> 12:13:50.300
You wandered out of the fold to seek your shepherd, did you, Jane?'

12:13:50.300 --> 12:13:52.520
"'I wanted you, but don't boast.

12:13:52.520 --> 12:13:54.440
Here we are at Thornfield.

12:13:54.600 --> 12:13:56.740
Now let me get down.'

12:13:57.140 --> 12:13:58.460
He landed on the pavement.

12:13:59.360 --> 12:14:04.520
As John took his horse, and he followed me into the hall, he told me to make haste and

12:14:04.520 --> 12:14:08.220
put something dry on, and then returned to him in the library.

12:14:09.240 --> 12:14:14.820
And he stopped me, as I made for the staircase, to exhort a promise that I would not be long.

12:14:15.760 --> 12:14:16.800
Nor was I long.

12:14:17.240 --> 12:14:19.180
In five minutes I rejoined him.

12:14:19.220 --> 12:14:20.360
I found him at supper.

12:14:21.260 --> 12:14:23.220
"'Take a seat and bear me company, Jane.

12:14:23.420 --> 12:14:24.160
Please God!

12:14:24.640 --> 12:14:29.280
It is the last meal but one you will eat at Thornfield Hall for a long time.'

12:14:29.280 --> 12:14:32.560
I sat down near him, but told him I could not eat.

12:14:33.320 --> 12:14:36.260
"'Is it because you have the prospect of a journey before you, Jane?

12:14:36.840 --> 12:14:40.800
Is it the thoughts of going to London that takes away your appetite?'

12:14:41.460 --> 12:14:46.260
"'I cannot see my prospects clearly to-night, sir, and I hardly know what thoughts they

12:14:46.260 --> 12:14:47.140
have in my head.

12:14:48.040 --> 12:14:52.400
Everything in life seems unreal, except me.

12:14:52.560 --> 12:14:53.880
I am substantial enough.

12:14:54.100 --> 12:14:54.980
Touch me.

12:14:56.140 --> 12:14:58.560
You, sir, are the most phantom-like of all.

12:14:59.100 --> 12:15:01.300
You are a mere dream.'

12:15:01.300 --> 12:15:03.260
He held out his hand, laughing.

12:15:03.460 --> 12:15:08.620
"'Is that a dream?' said he, placing it close to my eyes.

12:15:09.440 --> 12:15:14.360
He had a rounded muscular and vigorous hand, as well as a long strong arm.

12:15:15.600 --> 12:15:21.900
"'Yes, though I touch it, it is a dream,' said I, as I put it down from before my face.

12:15:22.980 --> 12:15:25.160
"'Sir, have you finished supper?'

12:15:25.160 --> 12:15:27.360
"'Yes, Jane.'

12:15:27.860 --> 12:15:30.440
I rang the bell, and ordered away the tray.

12:15:31.140 --> 12:15:36.500
When we were alone again, I stirred the fire, and then took a low seat at my master's knee.

12:15:38.840 --> 12:15:41.200
"'It is near midnight,' I said.

12:15:42.420 --> 12:15:47.180
"'Yes, but remember, Jane, you promised to wake with me the night before my wedding.'

12:15:47.180 --> 12:15:49.920
"'I did, and I will keep my promise.

12:15:50.320 --> 12:15:53.960
For an hour or two at least, I have no wish to go to bed.'

12:15:53.960 --> 12:15:56.760
"'Are all your arrangements complete?'

12:15:56.760 --> 12:15:58.520
"'All, sir.'

12:15:58.520 --> 12:16:01.460
"'And on my part likewise,' he returned.

12:16:01.900 --> 12:16:06.460
"'I have settled everything, and we shall leave Thornfield to-morrow, within half an

12:16:06.460 --> 12:16:08.340
hour after our return from church.'

12:16:09.060 --> 12:16:10.880
"'Very well, sir.'

12:16:10.880 --> 12:16:13.600
"'With what an extraordinary smile you uttered that word.

12:16:13.820 --> 12:16:14.940
Very well, Jane.

12:16:15.960 --> 12:16:18.440
What a bright spot of colour you have on each cheek!

12:16:19.260 --> 12:16:21.140
And how strangely your eyes glitter.

12:16:21.560 --> 12:16:23.200
Are you well?'

12:16:23.200 --> 12:16:25.200
"'I believe I am.'

12:16:25.200 --> 12:16:25.880
"'Believe?

12:16:25.960 --> 12:16:27.140
What is the matter?

12:16:27.380 --> 12:16:28.540
Tell me what you feel.'

12:16:30.480 --> 12:16:31.960
"'I could not, sir.

12:16:32.260 --> 12:16:34.160
No words could tell you what I feel.

12:16:34.860 --> 12:16:37.420
I wish this present hour would never end.

12:16:37.420 --> 12:16:40.260
Who knows with what fate the next may come charged.'

12:16:41.860 --> 12:16:43.340
"'This is hypochondria, Jane.

12:16:43.560 --> 12:16:46.060
You have been over-excited, or over-fatigued.'

12:16:47.380 --> 12:16:50.060
"'Do you, sir, feel calm and happy?'

12:16:50.540 --> 12:16:51.440
"'Calm, no.

12:16:51.760 --> 12:16:54.260
But happy to the heart's core.'

12:16:55.680 --> 12:16:58.940
I looked up at him to read the signs of bliss in his face.

12:16:59.340 --> 12:17:01.640
It was ardent and flushed.

12:17:02.500 --> 12:17:05.180
"'Give me your confidence, Jane,' he said.

12:17:05.760 --> 12:17:10.220
"'Relieve your mind of any way that oppresses it, by imparting it to me.

12:17:10.600 --> 12:17:11.820
What do you fear?

12:17:12.160 --> 12:17:14.740
That I shall not prove a good husband?'

12:17:14.740 --> 12:17:17.500
"'It is the idea furthest from my thoughts.'

12:17:18.580 --> 12:17:23.120
"'Are you apprehensive of the new sphere you are about to enter, of the new life into

12:17:23.120 --> 12:17:25.060
which you are passing?'

12:17:25.860 --> 12:17:26.340
"'No.'

12:17:26.340 --> 12:17:27.880
"'You puzzle me, Jane.

12:17:28.100 --> 12:17:32.000
Your look and tone of sorrowful audacity perplex and pain me.

12:17:32.410 --> 12:17:33.840
I want an explanation.'

12:17:35.740 --> 12:17:36.920
"'Then, sir, listen.

12:17:37.340 --> 12:17:38.890
You were from home last night.'

12:17:39.840 --> 12:17:40.880
"'I was.

12:17:41.000 --> 12:17:41.960
I know that.

12:17:42.040 --> 12:17:44.980
And you hinted a while ago at something which had happened in my absence.

12:17:45.840 --> 12:17:47.880
Nothing, probably, of consequence.

12:17:48.460 --> 12:17:50.720
But in short, it has disturbed you.

12:17:51.080 --> 12:17:52.860
Let me hear it.'

12:17:52.860 --> 12:17:53.500
"'Mrs.

12:17:53.540 --> 12:17:55.180
Fairfax has said something, perhaps.

12:17:55.580 --> 12:17:57.740
Or you have overheard the servant's talk.

12:17:58.180 --> 12:18:00.660
Your sensitive self-respect has been wounded.'

12:18:01.440 --> 12:18:03.200
"'No, sir.'

12:18:03.200 --> 12:18:04.660
It struck twelve.

12:18:04.960 --> 12:18:10.080
I waited till the timepiece had concluded its silver chime, and the clock its horse

12:18:10.080 --> 12:18:12.920
vibrating stroke, and then I proceeded.

12:18:14.440 --> 12:18:20.820
All day yesterday I was very busy, and very happy in my ceaseless bustle, for I am not,

12:18:20.960 --> 12:18:26.600
as you seem to think, troubled by any haunting fears about the new sphere, and so on.

12:18:27.040 --> 12:18:31.780
I think it is a glorious thing to have the hope of living with you, because I love you.

12:18:32.140 --> 12:18:34.040
No, sir, don't caress me now.

12:18:34.180 --> 12:18:35.240
Let me talk undisturbed.'

12:18:37.760 --> 12:18:42.740
Yesterday I trusted well in Providence, and believed that events were working together

12:18:42.740 --> 12:18:44.000
for your good and mine.

12:18:44.780 --> 12:18:46.780
It was a fine day, if you recollect.

12:18:47.380 --> 12:18:52.940
The calmness of the air and sky forbade apprehensions respecting your safety or comfort on your

12:18:52.940 --> 12:18:53.360
journey.

12:18:54.160 --> 12:19:00.520
I walked a little while on the pavement after tea, thinking of you, and as I beheld you

12:19:00.520 --> 12:19:04.520
in imagination so near, I scarcely missed your actual presence.

12:19:05.800 --> 12:19:12.100
I thought of the life that lay before me—your life, sir—an existence more expansive and

12:19:12.100 --> 12:19:19.280
stirring than my own, as much more so as the depth of the sea to which the brook runs are

12:19:19.280 --> 12:19:21.320
than the shallows of its own straight channel.

12:19:22.160 --> 12:19:25.620
I wondered why moralists call this world a dreary wilderness.

12:19:26.500 --> 12:19:28.640
For me it blossomed like a rose.

12:19:30.120 --> 12:19:33.560
Just at sunset the air turned cold and the sky cloudy.

12:19:34.420 --> 12:19:35.580
I went in.

12:19:36.120 --> 12:19:40.420
Sophie called me upstairs to look at my wedding-dress, which they had just brought.

12:19:41.880 --> 12:19:47.980
And under it, in the box, I found your present—the veil which, in your princely extravagance,

12:19:47.980 --> 12:19:54.600
you sent forth from London—resolved, I suppose, since I would not have jewels, to cheat me

12:19:54.600 --> 12:19:56.260
into accepting something as costly.

12:19:57.400 --> 12:20:02.320
I smiled as I unfolded it, and devised how I would tease you about your aristocratic

12:20:02.320 --> 12:20:07.960
tastes and your efforts to mask your plebeian bride and the attributes of a pares.

12:20:09.020 --> 12:20:13.340
I thought how I would carry down to you the square of unembroidered blonde I had myself

12:20:13.340 --> 12:20:19.460
as a covering for my low-born head, and ask if that was not good enough for a woman who

12:20:19.460 --> 12:20:23.460
could bring her husband neither fortune, beauty, nor connections.

12:20:24.520 --> 12:20:30.580
I saw plainly how you would look, and heard you impertuous Republican answers, and your

12:20:30.580 --> 12:20:36.300
haughty disavow of any necessity on your part to augment your wealth or elevate your standing

12:20:36.300 --> 12:20:39.220
by marrying either a purse or a coronet.

12:20:40.060 --> 12:20:43.980
How well you read me, you witch!' interposed Mr. Rochester.

12:20:44.800 --> 12:20:47.440
But what did you find in the veil besides its embroidery?

12:20:48.100 --> 12:20:51.540
Did you find poison, or a dagger, that you look so mournful now?

12:20:54.080 --> 12:20:55.200
No, no, sir.

12:20:55.680 --> 12:21:01.120
Besides the delicacy and richness of the fabric, I found nothing save Fairfax Rochester's

12:21:01.120 --> 12:21:01.640
pride.

12:21:02.120 --> 12:21:05.780
And that did not scare me, because I am used to the sight of the demon.

12:21:06.700 --> 12:21:10.580
But, sir, as it grew dark, the wind rose.

12:21:10.840 --> 12:21:17.620
It blew yesterday evening, not as it blows now, wild and high, but with a sullen moaning

12:21:17.620 --> 12:21:19.580
sound, far more eerie.

12:21:20.240 --> 12:21:21.880
I wished you were at home.

12:21:22.480 --> 12:21:27.640
I came into this room, and the sight of the empty chair and fireless hearth chilled me.

12:21:28.560 --> 12:21:31.500
For some time after I went to bed I could not sleep.

12:21:32.260 --> 12:21:35.060
A sense of anxious excitement distressed me.

12:21:36.200 --> 12:21:40.780
The gale still rising seemed to my ear to muffle a mournful undersound.

12:21:41.840 --> 12:21:44.680
Whether in the house or abroad, I could not at first tell.

12:21:45.700 --> 12:21:49.900
But it reoccurred, doubtful yet doleful at every lull.

12:21:51.660 --> 12:21:55.240
At last I may doubt it must be some dog howling at a distance.

12:21:57.060 --> 12:21:58.700
I was glad when it ceased.

12:21:59.440 --> 12:22:04.180
On sleeping I continued in dreams the idea of a dark and gusty night.

12:22:05.200 --> 12:22:11.100
I continued also the wish to be with you, and experienced a strange regretful consciousness

12:22:11.100 --> 12:22:13.520
of some barrier dividing us.

12:22:15.100 --> 12:22:19.340
During all my first sleep I was following the windings of an unknown road.

12:22:20.460 --> 12:22:22.580
Total obscurity environed me.

12:22:22.840 --> 12:22:24.100
Rain pelted me.

12:22:24.560 --> 12:22:30.180
I was burdened with the charge of a little child, a very small creature, too young and

12:22:30.180 --> 12:22:35.340
feeble to walk, and which strived in my cold arms and wailed piteously in my ear.

12:22:36.340 --> 12:22:41.660
I thought, sir, that you were on the road a long way before me, and I strained every

12:22:41.660 --> 12:22:45.740
nerve to overtake you, and made effort and effort to utter your name and entreat you

12:22:45.740 --> 12:22:46.320
to stop.

12:22:47.560 --> 12:22:53.720
But my movements were fettered, and my voice still died away inarticulate, while you, I

12:22:53.720 --> 12:22:56.780
felt, withdrew farther and farther every moment.

12:22:58.380 --> 12:23:02.580
And these dreams were in your spirits now, Jane, when I am close to you.

12:23:03.000 --> 12:23:07.480
Little nervous subject, forget visionary woe, and think only of real happiness.

12:23:08.360 --> 12:23:09.740
You say you love me, Janet.

12:23:10.140 --> 12:23:11.900
Yes, I will not forget that.

12:23:12.320 --> 12:23:13.760
And you cannot deny it.

12:23:14.240 --> 12:23:16.980
Those words did not die inarticulate on your lips.

12:23:17.420 --> 12:23:19.120
I heard them clear and soft.

12:23:19.780 --> 12:23:23.300
A thought too solemn, perhaps, but sweet as music.

12:23:24.320 --> 12:23:28.100
I think it is a glorious thing to have the hope of living with you, Edward, because I

12:23:28.100 --> 12:23:28.980
love you.

12:23:29.680 --> 12:23:30.660
Do you love me, Jane?

12:23:30.980 --> 12:23:32.060
Repeat it.

12:23:33.140 --> 12:23:35.720
I do, sir, I do with my whole heart.

12:23:37.800 --> 12:23:40.540
Well, he said after some minute's silence.

12:23:41.800 --> 12:23:46.360
It is strange, but that sentence has penetrated my breast painfully.

12:23:47.560 --> 12:23:48.080
Why?

12:23:48.650 --> 12:23:53.420
I think because you said it with such an earnest, religious energy, and because your upward

12:23:53.420 --> 12:23:57.300
gaze at me now is the very sublime of faith, truth, and devotion.

12:23:58.640 --> 12:24:01.500
It is too much as if some spirit were near me.

12:24:02.020 --> 12:24:05.460
Look wicked, Jane, as you know well how to look.

12:24:05.840 --> 12:24:08.640
Quain one of your wild, shy, provoking smiles.

12:24:09.640 --> 12:24:14.280
Tell me you hate me, tease me, vex me, do anything but move me.

12:24:14.280 --> 12:24:17.180
I would rather be incensed than saddened.

12:24:18.480 --> 12:24:24.340
I will tease you and vex you to your heart's content when I finish my tale, but hear me

12:24:24.340 --> 12:24:25.180
to the end.

12:24:27.480 --> 12:24:29.420
I thought, Jane, you had told me all.

12:24:29.820 --> 12:24:32.320
I thought I had found the source of your melancholy in a dream.

12:24:33.440 --> 12:24:34.740
I shook my head.

12:24:35.560 --> 12:24:36.000
What?

12:24:36.180 --> 12:24:36.980
Is there more?

12:24:37.260 --> 12:24:39.500
But I will not believe it to be anything important.

12:24:40.520 --> 12:24:42.560
I warn you of incredulity beforehand.

12:24:42.560 --> 12:24:43.760
Go on.'

12:24:45.400 --> 12:24:51.100
The disquietude of his air, the somewhat apprehensive impatience of his manner, surprised me.

12:24:51.860 --> 12:24:52.940
But I proceeded.

12:24:54.580 --> 12:25:00.980
I dreamt another dream, sir, that Thornfield Hall was a dreary ruin, the retreat of bats

12:25:00.980 --> 12:25:01.840
and owls.

12:25:02.540 --> 12:25:08.500
I thought that of all the stately front nothing remained but a shell-like wall, very high

12:25:08.500 --> 12:25:09.840
and very fragile looking.

12:25:10.800 --> 12:25:15.420
I wandered, on a moonlit night, through the grass-grown enclosure within.

12:25:16.680 --> 12:25:22.160
Here I stumbled over a marble hearth, and there over a fallen fragment of cornice.

12:25:23.740 --> 12:25:27.280
Wrapped up in a shawl, I still carried the unknown little child.

12:25:28.100 --> 12:25:31.700
I might not lay it down anywhere, however tired were my arms.

12:25:32.960 --> 12:25:36.680
However much its weight impeded my progress, I must retain it.

12:25:37.300 --> 12:25:40.560
I heard the gallop of a horse at a distance on the road.

12:25:40.700 --> 12:25:46.300
I was sure it was you, and you were departing for many years and for a distant country.

12:25:46.920 --> 12:25:52.780
I climbed the thin wall with frantic perilous haste, eager to catch one glimpse of you from

12:25:52.780 --> 12:25:53.340
the top.

12:25:53.920 --> 12:25:58.640
The stones rolled from under my feet, the ivy branches I grasped gave way.

12:25:59.460 --> 12:26:03.100
The child clung round my neck in terror and almost strangled me.

12:26:03.680 --> 12:26:05.360
At last I gained the summit.

12:26:06.180 --> 12:26:11.420
I saw you, like a speck on a white track, lessening every moment.

12:26:12.740 --> 12:26:15.100
The blast blew so strong I could not stand.

12:26:15.920 --> 12:26:17.440
I sat down on the narrow ledge.

12:26:17.980 --> 12:26:20.080
I hushed the scared infant in my lap.

12:26:21.180 --> 12:26:22.980
You turned an angle off the road.

12:26:23.840 --> 12:26:25.720
I bent forward to take a last look.

12:26:26.500 --> 12:26:29.880
The wall crumbled, I was shaken, the child rolled from my knee.

12:26:30.480 --> 12:26:32.940
I lost my balance, fell and woke.

12:26:34.360 --> 12:26:36.100
Now, Jane, that is all.

12:26:36.860 --> 12:26:40.760
All the preface, sir, the tale is yet to come.'

12:26:40.760 --> 12:26:43.040
On waking a gleam dazzled my eyes.

12:26:43.400 --> 12:26:45.600
I thought, oh, it is daylight.

12:26:46.800 --> 12:26:49.660
But I was mistaken, it was only candlelight.

12:26:51.020 --> 12:26:53.140
Sophie, I supposed, had come in.

12:26:53.960 --> 12:26:59.440
There was a light in the dressing-table, and the door of the closet, where, before going

12:26:59.440 --> 12:27:02.960
to bed, I had hung my wedding-dress and veil, stood open.

12:27:04.040 --> 12:27:05.700
I heard a rustling there.

12:27:05.900 --> 12:27:08.340
I asked, Sophie, what are you doing?

12:27:09.200 --> 12:27:12.400
No one answered, but a form emerged from the closet.

12:27:13.420 --> 12:27:19.660
It took the light, held it aloft, and surveyed the garments pendant from the portmanteau.

12:27:20.340 --> 12:27:24.280
Sophie, Sophie, I again cried, and still it was silent.

12:27:25.540 --> 12:27:27.000
I had risen up in bed.

12:27:27.260 --> 12:27:28.240
I bent forward.

12:27:28.960 --> 12:27:34.640
First surprised, then bewilderment came over me, and then my blood crept cold from my veins.

12:27:36.040 --> 12:27:37.940
Mr. Rochester, this was not Sophie.

12:27:38.560 --> 12:27:39.460
It was not Leah.

12:27:40.240 --> 12:27:41.880
It was not Mrs. Fairfax.

12:27:42.180 --> 12:27:45.840
It was not—no, I was sure of it, and I am still.

12:27:46.240 --> 12:27:49.560
It was not even that strange woman, Grace Poole.'

12:27:50.660 --> 12:27:54.800
"'It must have been one of them,' interrupted my master.

12:27:55.840 --> 12:27:59.040
"'No, sir, I solemnly assure you to the contrary.

12:27:59.600 --> 12:28:03.700
The shape standing before me had never crossed my eyes within the precincts of Thornfield

12:28:03.700 --> 12:28:04.520
Hall before.

12:28:05.140 --> 12:28:07.880
The height, the contour, were new to me.

12:28:08.260 --> 12:28:09.860
Describe it, Jane.'

12:28:10.620 --> 12:28:15.820
"'It seems, sir, a woman tall and large, with thick and dark hair hanging long down

12:28:15.820 --> 12:28:16.600
her back.

12:28:17.120 --> 12:28:19.200
I know not what dress she had on.

12:28:19.200 --> 12:28:25.600
It was white and straight, but with a gown, sheet, or shroud, I cannot tell.'

12:28:25.600 --> 12:28:27.600
"'Did you see her face?'

12:28:27.600 --> 12:28:32.060
"'Not at first, but presently she took my veil from its place.

12:28:32.420 --> 12:28:37.960
She held it up, gazed at it long, and then she threw it over her own head and turned

12:28:37.960 --> 12:28:38.500
the mirror.

12:28:39.660 --> 12:28:44.360
At that moment I saw the reflection of the visage and features quite distinctly in the

12:28:44.360 --> 12:28:45.200
oblong glass.'

12:28:45.860 --> 12:28:47.340
"'And how were they?'

12:28:48.240 --> 12:28:50.100
"'Fearful and ghastly to me.

12:28:50.220 --> 12:28:52.620
Oh, sir, I never saw a face like it.

12:28:53.040 --> 12:28:54.620
It was a discoloured face.

12:28:54.700 --> 12:28:56.140
It was a savage face.

12:28:56.860 --> 12:29:02.020
I wished I could forget the roll of the red eyes, and the fearful blackened inflation

12:29:02.020 --> 12:29:02.980
of the liniments.'

12:29:04.320 --> 12:29:06.280
"'Ghosts are usually pale, Jane.'

12:29:06.830 --> 12:29:08.160
This, sir, was purple.

12:29:08.660 --> 12:29:14.340
The lips were swelled and dark, the brow furrowed, the black eyebrows widely raised over the

12:29:14.340 --> 12:29:15.400
bloodshot eyes.

12:29:16.180 --> 12:29:19.000
Shall I tell you of what it reminded me?'

12:29:19.000 --> 12:29:19.960
"'You may.'

12:29:20.760 --> 12:29:24.440
"'Of the foul German spectre, the vampire.'

12:29:25.300 --> 12:29:25.860
"'Ah!

12:29:25.880 --> 12:29:28.040
What did it do?'

12:29:28.040 --> 12:29:34.600
"'Sir, it removed my veil from its gaunt head, rent it into two parts, and flinging

12:29:34.600 --> 12:29:36.620
both on the floor, trampled on them.

12:29:38.420 --> 12:29:41.880
Afterwards it drew aside the winded curtain and looked out.

12:29:42.500 --> 12:29:47.380
Perhaps it saw dawn approaching, for taking the candle it retreated to the door.

12:29:48.920 --> 12:29:53.800
Just at my bedside the figure stopped, the fiery eyes glared upon me.

12:29:54.600 --> 12:29:58.700
She thrust up her candle close to my face, and extinguished it under my eyes.

12:30:00.380 --> 12:30:06.860
I was aware her lurid visage flamed over mine, and I lost consciousness for the second time

12:30:06.860 --> 12:30:09.620
in my life—only the second time.

12:30:10.320 --> 12:30:12.100
I became insensible from terror.'

12:30:12.940 --> 12:30:15.660
"'Who was with you when you revived?'

12:30:15.660 --> 12:30:18.860
"'No one, sir, but the broad day.

12:30:19.460 --> 12:30:26.540
I rose, bathed my head and face in water, drank a long draught, felt that though enfeebled

12:30:26.540 --> 12:30:31.560
I was not ill, and determined that to numb at you would I impart this vision.

12:30:32.480 --> 12:30:36.860
Now sir, tell me who and what that woman was?'

12:30:36.860 --> 12:30:40.580
"'The creature of an overstimulated brain, that is certain.

12:30:41.180 --> 12:30:43.260
I must be careful of you, my treasure.

12:30:44.160 --> 12:30:46.220
Nerves like yours were not made for rough handling.'

12:30:47.480 --> 12:30:48.880
"'Sir, depend on it.

12:30:48.980 --> 12:30:50.400
My nerves were not in fault.

12:30:50.980 --> 12:30:52.080
The thing was real.

12:30:52.420 --> 12:30:54.380
The transaction actually took place.'

12:30:55.500 --> 12:30:57.000
"'And your previous dreams?

12:30:57.120 --> 12:30:58.160
Were they real, too?

12:30:58.500 --> 12:30:59.900
Is Thornfield Hall a ruin?

12:31:00.520 --> 12:31:03.120
Am I severed from you by insuperable obstacles?

12:31:04.220 --> 12:31:08.520
Am I leaving you without a tear, without a kiss, without a word?

12:31:09.620 --> 12:31:10.600
Not yet.

12:31:11.560 --> 12:31:13.320
Am I about to do it?

12:31:13.760 --> 12:31:17.200
Why, the day is already commenced which is to bind us indissolubly.

12:31:17.820 --> 12:31:22.180
And when we are once united there shall be no reoccurrence of these mental terrors.

12:31:22.660 --> 12:31:23.720
I guarantee that.'

12:31:24.920 --> 12:31:26.200
"'Mental terrors, sir.

12:31:26.680 --> 12:31:29.000
I wish I could believe them to be only such.

12:31:29.540 --> 12:31:34.540
I wish it more now than ever, since even you cannot explain to me the mystery of that awful

12:31:34.540 --> 12:31:35.340
visitant.

12:31:36.420 --> 12:31:39.560
And since I cannot do it, Jane, it must have been unreal.'

12:31:41.980 --> 12:31:47.540
"'But, sir, when I said so to myself on rising this morning, and when I looked round the

12:31:47.540 --> 12:31:52.380
room to gather courage and comfort from the cheerful aspect of each familiar object in

12:31:52.940 --> 12:31:58.700
There, on the carpet, I saw what gave the distinct lie to my hypothesis.

12:31:59.820 --> 12:32:02.960
The veil torn from top to bottom in two halves.

12:32:04.800 --> 12:32:07.620
I felt Mr. Rochester start and shudder.

12:32:08.180 --> 12:32:10.520
He hastily flung his arms round me.

12:32:11.060 --> 12:32:16.780
"'Thank God,' he exclaimed, that if anything malignant did come near you last night, it

12:32:16.780 --> 12:32:18.200
was only the veil that was harmed.

12:32:18.760 --> 12:32:22.740
Oh, to think what might have happened!'

12:32:22.740 --> 12:32:27.840
He drew his breath short, and strained me so close to him I could scarcely pant.

12:32:29.520 --> 12:32:32.140
After some minute's silence he continued cheerily.

12:32:33.180 --> 12:32:36.380
"'Now, Janet, I'll explain to you all about it.

12:32:36.580 --> 12:32:38.620
It was half a dream, half reality.

12:32:39.680 --> 12:32:42.820
A woman did, I doubt not, enter your room.

12:32:43.160 --> 12:32:47.400
And that woman was—must have been—Grace Poole.

12:32:47.720 --> 12:32:49.920
You call her a strange being yourself.

12:32:50.580 --> 12:32:53.280
From all you know you have reasoned so to call her.

12:32:54.000 --> 12:32:55.460
What did she do to me?

12:32:55.660 --> 12:32:56.800
What to Mason?'

12:32:57.660 --> 12:33:01.900
In a state between sleeping and waking you noticed her entrance and her actions.

12:33:02.600 --> 12:33:08.080
But feverish, almost delirious as you were, you ascribed to her a goblin appearance different

12:33:08.080 --> 12:33:08.880
from her own.

12:33:09.600 --> 12:33:16.020
The long dishevelled hair, the swelled black face, the exaggerated stature, were figments

12:33:16.020 --> 12:33:19.360
of imagination, results of nightmare.

12:33:20.460 --> 12:33:24.740
The spiteful tearing of the veil was real, and it is like her.

12:33:25.540 --> 12:33:28.720
I see you would ask why I keep such a woman in my house.

12:33:29.380 --> 12:33:33.300
When we be married a year and a day I will tell you, but not now.

12:33:33.940 --> 12:33:35.160
Are you satisfied, Jane?

12:33:35.800 --> 12:33:38.900
Do you accept my solution of the mystery?'

12:33:39.420 --> 12:33:43.360
I reflected, and in truth it appeared to me the only possible one.

12:33:44.700 --> 12:33:48.980
Satisfied I was not, but to please him I endeavoured to appear so.

12:33:50.200 --> 12:33:55.140
Relieved I certainly did feel, so I answered him with a contented smile.

12:33:55.900 --> 12:34:00.260
And now, as it was long past one, I prepared to leave him.

12:34:02.340 --> 12:34:07.300
Does not Sophie sleep with Adèle in the nursery?' he asked, as I lit my candle.

12:34:08.060 --> 12:34:12.400
Yes, sir, and there is room enough in Adèle's little bed for you.

12:34:12.620 --> 12:34:15.000
You must share it with her to-night, Jane.

12:34:15.520 --> 12:34:20.200
It is no wonder that the incidents you have related should make you nervous, and I would

12:34:20.200 --> 12:34:21.740
rather you did not sleep alone.

12:34:22.840 --> 12:34:24.220
Promise me to go to the nursery.'

12:34:25.180 --> 12:34:27.400
I shall be very glad to do so, sir.

12:34:29.600 --> 12:34:31.780
And fasten the door securely on the inside.

12:34:32.320 --> 12:34:36.920
Wake Sophie when you go upstairs, and her pretence of requesting her to rouse you in

12:34:36.920 --> 12:34:41.420
good time to-morrow, for you must be dressed and have finished breakfast before eight.

12:34:42.440 --> 12:34:44.560
And now, no more sombre thoughts.

12:34:45.080 --> 12:34:46.480
Chase dull care away, Janet.

12:34:47.260 --> 12:34:49.860
Don't you hear to what soft whispers the wind has fallen?

12:34:50.720 --> 12:34:53.720
And there is no more beating of rain against the window panes.

12:34:54.160 --> 12:34:55.860
Look here.'

12:34:55.860 --> 12:34:57.180
He lifted up the curtain.

12:34:57.180 --> 12:35:00.620
It is a lovely night.'

12:35:00.620 --> 12:35:01.660
It was.

12:35:02.180 --> 12:35:04.120
Half heaven was pure and stainless.

12:35:04.860 --> 12:35:10.640
The clouds, now trooping before the winds, which had shifted to the west, were now filing

12:35:10.640 --> 12:35:12.920
off eastward in long, silvered columns.

12:35:13.880 --> 12:35:15.140
The moon shone peacefully.

12:35:17.600 --> 12:35:22.020
Well,' said Mr. Rochester, gazing inquiringly into my eyes,

12:35:22.720 --> 12:35:24.160
How is my Janet now?

12:35:25.120 --> 12:35:28.380
The night is most serene, sir, and so am I.

12:35:29.220 --> 12:35:35.360
And you will not dream of separation and sorrow to-night, but of happy love and blissful union.'

12:35:35.360 --> 12:35:37.680
This prediction was but half fulfilled.

12:35:38.660 --> 12:35:45.120
I did not indeed dream of sorrow, but as little did I dream of joy, for I never slept at all.

12:35:46.260 --> 12:35:52.540
With little Adèle in my arms I watched the slumber of childhood, so tranquil, so passionless,

12:35:52.720 --> 12:35:56.400
so innocent, and waited for the coming day.

12:35:57.300 --> 12:36:03.320
All my life was awake and a stir in my frame, and as soon as the sun rose I rose too.

12:36:05.000 --> 12:36:10.420
I remember Adèle clung to me as I left her, I remember I kissed her as I loosened my little

12:36:10.420 --> 12:36:16.360
hands from her neck, and I cried over her with strange emotion, and quitted her because

12:36:16.360 --> 12:36:19.420
I feared my sobs would break her still sound repose.

12:36:20.480 --> 12:36:27.600
She seemed the emblem of my past life, and he I was now to array myself to meet, the

12:36:27.600 --> 12:36:31.080
dread, but adored, type of my unknown future day.

12:36:52.880 --> 12:36:54.000
CHAPTER XXVI.

12:36:54.180 --> 12:36:56.180
Sophie came at seven to dress me.

12:36:56.500 --> 12:37:01.560
She was very long indeed in accomplishing her task, so long that Mr. Rochester, grown

12:37:01.560 --> 12:37:05.960
and I suppose impatient of my delay, sent up to ask why I did not come.

12:37:06.620 --> 12:37:12.160
She was just fastening my veil, the plain square of blonde, after all, to my hair with

12:37:12.160 --> 12:37:12.700
a brooch.

12:37:13.300 --> 12:37:15.940
I hurried from under her hands as soon as I could.

12:37:16.840 --> 12:37:22.620
Stop, she cried in French, look at yourself in the mirror, you have not taken one peep.

12:37:23.620 --> 12:37:25.160
So I turned at the door.

12:37:25.560 --> 12:37:31.180
I saw a robed and veiled figure, so unlike my usual self, that it seemed almost like

12:37:31.180 --> 12:37:32.320
the image of a stranger.

12:37:33.620 --> 12:37:36.800
Jane called the voice, and I hastened down.

12:37:37.700 --> 12:37:40.600
I was received at the foot of the stairs by Mr. Rochester.

12:37:41.860 --> 12:37:47.100
Lingera, he said, my brain is on fire with impatience, and you, Terry, so long.

12:37:47.800 --> 12:37:53.360
He took me into the dining-room, surveyed me keenly all over, pronounced me fair as

12:37:53.360 --> 12:37:58.900
a lily at not only the pride of his life, but the desire of his eyes, and then telling

12:37:58.900 --> 12:38:03.280
me he would give me but ten minutes to eat some breakfast, he rang the bell.

12:38:04.540 --> 12:38:08.580
One of his lately hired servants, a footman, answered it.

12:38:09.680 --> 12:38:11.180
Is John getting the carriage ready?

12:38:11.920 --> 12:38:12.560
Yes, sir.

12:38:13.320 --> 12:38:14.840
Is the luggage brought down?

12:38:15.720 --> 12:38:17.300
They are bringing it down, sir.

12:38:18.740 --> 12:38:24.060
Go you to the church, see if Mr. Wood, the clergyman, and the clerk are there.

12:38:24.480 --> 12:38:25.920
Return and tell me.

12:38:26.760 --> 12:38:30.920
The church, as the reader knows, was but just beyond the gates.

12:38:31.260 --> 12:38:32.700
The footman soon returned.

12:38:34.220 --> 12:38:37.820
Mr. Wood is in the vestry, sir, putting on his surplice.

12:38:38.400 --> 12:38:39.240
And the carriage?

12:38:40.440 --> 12:38:42.020
The horses are harnessing.

12:38:43.380 --> 12:38:48.020
We shall not want it to go to church, but it must be ready the moment we return, all

12:38:48.020 --> 12:38:52.020
the boxes and luggage arranged and strapped on, and the coachman in his seat.

12:38:53.160 --> 12:38:53.800
Yes, sir.

12:38:54.360 --> 12:38:55.500
Jane, are you ready?

12:38:56.500 --> 12:38:57.420
I rose.

12:38:58.140 --> 12:39:03.980
There were no groomsmen, no bridesmaids, no relatives to wait for, or marshal.

12:39:04.340 --> 12:39:06.340
None but Mr. Rochester and I.

12:39:08.100 --> 12:39:10.680
Mrs. Fairfax stood in the hall as we passed.

12:39:11.200 --> 12:39:15.420
I would faint have spoken to her, but my hand was held by a grasp of iron.

12:39:15.880 --> 12:39:20.260
I was hurried along by a stride I could hardly follow, and to look at Mr.

12:39:20.260 --> 12:39:25.500
Rochester's face was to feel that not a second of delay would be tolerated for any purpose.

12:39:26.920 --> 12:39:32.920
I wonder what other bridegroom ever looked as he did, so bent up to a purpose, so grimly

12:39:32.920 --> 12:39:39.500
resolute, or who, under such steadfast brows, ever revealed such flaming and flashing eyes.

12:39:41.900 --> 12:39:44.900
I know not whether the day was fair or foul.

12:39:45.300 --> 12:39:48.940
In descending the drive, I gazed neither on sky nor earth.

12:39:49.760 --> 12:39:55.120
My heart was with my eyes, and both seemed migrated into Mr. Rochester's frame.

12:39:56.120 --> 12:40:01.420
I wanted to see the invisible thing on which, as we went along, he appeared to fasten a

12:40:01.420 --> 12:40:02.960
glance fierce and fell.

12:40:03.760 --> 12:40:08.020
I wanted to feel the thoughts whose force he seemed breasting and resisting.

12:40:09.820 --> 12:40:11.860
At the churchyard wicked, he stopped.

12:40:13.220 --> 12:40:15.160
He discovered I was quite out of breath.

12:40:15.900 --> 12:40:17.580
Am I crawled in my love?

12:40:17.900 --> 12:40:18.480
He said.

12:40:19.120 --> 12:40:21.300
Delay an instant, lean on me, Jane.

12:40:23.360 --> 12:40:29.400
And now I can recall the picture of the grey old house of God rising calm before me, of

12:40:29.400 --> 12:40:33.440
a rook wheeling round the steeple, of a ruddy morning sky beyond.

12:40:34.380 --> 12:40:40.440
I remember something, too, of the green grave-mounds, and have not forgotten, either, two figures

12:40:40.440 --> 12:40:46.740
of strangers, straying amongst the low hillocks and reading the mementos graven on the few

12:40:46.740 --> 12:40:47.780
mossy headstones.

12:40:48.540 --> 12:40:54.120
I noticed them because, as they saw us, they passed round to the back of the church, and

12:40:54.120 --> 12:40:58.880
I doubt not they were going to enter by the side aisle door and witness the ceremony.

12:41:00.100 --> 12:41:02.100
By Mr. Rochester they were not observed.

12:41:02.400 --> 12:41:07.640
He was earnestly looking at my face, from which the blood hand, I dare say, momentarily

12:41:07.640 --> 12:41:12.740
fled, for I felt my forehead dewy and my cheeks and lips cold.

12:41:14.500 --> 12:41:19.880
When I rallied, which I soon did, he walked gently with me up the path to the porch.

12:41:21.820 --> 12:41:24.320
We entered the quiet and humble temple.

12:41:24.880 --> 12:41:30.660
The priest waited in his white surplice at the lowly altar, the clerk beside him.

12:41:31.320 --> 12:41:35.580
All was still, two shadows only moved in a remote corner.

12:41:36.420 --> 12:41:38.180
My conjecture had been correct.

12:41:38.720 --> 12:41:44.220
The strangers had slipped in before us, and they now stood by the vault of the Rochester's,

12:41:44.340 --> 12:41:51.480
their backs towards us, viewing through the rails the old time-stained marble tomb, where

12:41:51.480 --> 12:41:57.480
a kneeling angel guarded the remains of Damer de Rochester, slain at Marston Moor at the

12:41:57.480 --> 12:42:01.240
time of the civil wars, and of Elizabeth, his wife.

12:42:02.340 --> 12:42:05.080
Our place was taken at the communion rails.

12:42:05.920 --> 12:42:09.900
Hearing a cautious step behind me, I glanced over my shoulder.

12:42:10.520 --> 12:42:15.940
One of the strangers, a gentleman evidently, was advancing up the chancel.

12:42:17.060 --> 12:42:18.160
The service began.

12:42:18.960 --> 12:42:24.340
The explanation of the intent of matrimony was gone through, and then the clergyman came

12:42:24.340 --> 12:42:29.740
a step further forward, and bending slightly towards Mr. Rochester, went on.

12:42:31.560 --> 12:42:37.320
I require and charge you both, as you will answer at the dreadful day of judgment, when

12:42:37.320 --> 12:42:43.780
the secrets of all hearts shall be disclosed, that if either of you know any impediment

12:42:43.780 --> 12:42:50.840
why you may not lawfully be joined together in matrimony, you do now confess it, for be

12:42:50.840 --> 12:42:57.740
well assured that so many as are coupled together otherwise than God's word doth allow are not

12:42:57.740 --> 12:43:01.720
joined together by God, neither is their matrimony lawful.

12:43:02.720 --> 12:43:05.200
He paused, as the custom is.

12:43:05.780 --> 12:43:09.060
When is the pause after that sentence ever broken by reply?

12:43:09.720 --> 12:43:12.260
Not perhaps once in a hundred years.

12:43:13.120 --> 12:43:18.160
Who had not lifted his eyes from his book, and had held his breath but for a moment,

12:43:18.160 --> 12:43:19.460
was proceeding.

12:43:19.980 --> 12:43:26.120
His hand was already stretched towards Mr. Rochester, as his lips unclosed to ask, Wilt

12:43:26.120 --> 12:43:28.520
thou have this woman for thy wedded wife?

12:43:29.320 --> 12:43:34.540
When a distinct and near voice said, The marriage cannot go on.

12:43:35.000 --> 12:43:37.440
I declare the existence of an impediment.

12:43:39.040 --> 12:43:41.640
The clergyman looked up at the speaker, and stood mute.

12:43:42.060 --> 12:43:43.380
The clerk did the same.

12:43:43.380 --> 12:43:48.200
Mr. Rochester moved slightly, as if an earthquake had rolled under his feet.

12:43:48.600 --> 12:43:53.820
Taking a firmer footing, and not turning his head or eyes, he said, Proceed.

12:43:55.600 --> 12:44:01.380
Profound silence fell when he had uttered that word, with deep but low intonation.

12:44:02.600 --> 12:44:08.220
Presently Mr. Wood said, I cannot proceed without some investigation into what has been

12:44:08.220 --> 12:44:11.720
and evidence of its truth or falsehood.

12:44:13.420 --> 12:44:18.580
The ceremony is quite broken off, subjoined the voice behind us.

12:44:18.940 --> 12:44:21.320
I am in a condition to prove my allegation.

12:44:22.100 --> 12:44:25.240
An insuperable impediment to this marriage exists.

12:44:28.220 --> 12:44:30.500
Mr. Rochester heard, but he did not.

12:44:30.980 --> 12:44:36.580
He stood stubborn and rigid, making no movement but to possess himself of my hand.

12:44:36.990 --> 12:44:42.240
What a hot and strong grasp he had, and how like quarried marble was his pale,

12:44:42.500 --> 12:44:44.600
firm, massive front at this moment.

12:44:45.340 --> 12:44:49.020
How his eyes shone, still watchful, and yet wild beneath.

12:44:51.140 --> 12:44:52.620
Mr. Wood seemed at a loss.

12:44:54.040 --> 12:44:57.140
What is the nature of the impediment, he asked.

12:44:57.900 --> 12:45:01.100
Perhaps it maybe got over, explained away?

12:45:02.920 --> 12:45:04.580
Hardly was the answer.

12:45:05.320 --> 12:45:09.220
I have called it insuperable, and I speak advisedly.

12:45:11.140 --> 12:45:13.900
The speaker came forward and leaned on the rails.

12:45:14.340 --> 12:45:19.440
He continued, uttering each word distinctly, calmly, steadily, but not loudly.

12:45:21.580 --> 12:45:25.280
It simply consists in the existence of a previous marriage.

12:45:26.180 --> 12:45:28.300
Mr. Rochester has a wife now living.

12:45:30.200 --> 12:45:36.520
My nerves vibrated to those low-spoken words as they had never vibrated to thunder.

12:45:37.120 --> 12:45:41.720
My blood felt their subtle violence as it had never felt frost or fire.

12:45:42.200 --> 12:45:45.880
But I was collected, and in no dangerous wounding.

12:45:47.300 --> 12:45:48.560
I looked at Mr. Rochester.

12:45:48.980 --> 12:45:50.440
I made him look at me.

12:45:51.180 --> 12:45:53.280
His whole face was colorless rock.

12:45:53.780 --> 12:45:56.680
His eye was both spark and flint.

12:45:57.320 --> 12:45:58.700
He disavowed nothing.

12:45:59.400 --> 12:46:01.760
It seemed as if he would defy all things.

12:46:03.360 --> 12:46:08.060
Without speaking, without smiling, without seeming to recognize in me a human being,

12:46:08.500 --> 12:46:12.940
he only twined my waist with his arm and riveted me to his side.

12:46:14.160 --> 12:46:15.560
Who are you?

12:46:15.840 --> 12:46:17.260
He asked of the intruder.

12:46:19.340 --> 12:46:24.000
My name is Briggs, a solicitor of Street London.

12:46:24.000 --> 12:46:28.040
And you would thrust on me a wife?

12:46:29.200 --> 12:46:35.360
I would remind you of your lady's existence, sir, which the law recognizes if you do not.

12:46:37.840 --> 12:46:43.040
Favor me with an account of her, with her name, her parentage, her place of abode.

12:46:44.840 --> 12:46:51.840
Certainly, Mr. Briggs calmly took a paper from his pocket and read out in a sort of official nasal voice.

12:46:52.840 --> 12:46:59.500
I affirm and can prove that on the 20th of October A.D., a date of 15 years back,

12:47:00.100 --> 12:47:09.440
Edward Fairfax Rochester of Thornfield Hall in the county of and of Ferndean Manor in Shea, England,

12:47:10.440 --> 12:47:17.480
was married to my sister, Bertha Antoinetta Mason, daughter of Jonas Mason, merchant,

12:47:17.480 --> 12:47:24.180
and of Antoinetta, his wife, a Creole, at church, Spanish town, Jamaica.

12:47:25.200 --> 12:47:28.720
The record of the marriage will be found in the register of that church.

12:47:28.920 --> 12:47:32.960
A copy of it is now in my possession, signed Richard Mason.

12:47:35.280 --> 12:47:39.740
That, if a genuine document, may prove I have been married,

12:47:40.120 --> 12:47:45.800
but it does not prove that the woman mentioned therein as my wife is still living.

12:47:46.900 --> 12:47:51.040
She was living three months ago, returned the lawyer.

12:47:52.440 --> 12:47:53.500
How do you know?

12:47:54.700 --> 12:48:00.120
I have a witness to the fact, whose testimony even you, sir, will scarcely controvert.

12:48:01.480 --> 12:48:02.980
Produce him, or go to hell.

12:48:04.520 --> 12:48:06.280
I will produce him first.

12:48:06.460 --> 12:48:07.600
He is on the spot.

12:48:08.700 --> 12:48:11.100
Mr. Mason, have the goodness to step forward.

12:48:12.560 --> 12:48:15.820
Mr. Rochester, on hearing the name, set his teeth.

12:48:16.600 --> 12:48:20.520
He experienced, too, a sort of strong convulsive quiver.

12:48:20.980 --> 12:48:27.400
Near to him as I was, I felt a spasmodic movement of fury or despair run through his frame.

12:48:28.560 --> 12:48:32.860
The second stranger, who had hitherto lingered in the background, now drew near.

12:48:33.260 --> 12:48:36.520
A pale face looked over the solicitor's shoulder.

12:48:37.140 --> 12:48:38.720
Yes, it was Mason himself.

12:48:39.420 --> 12:48:42.180
Mr. Rochester turned and glared at him.

12:48:43.140 --> 12:48:46.540
His eye, as I have often said, was a black eye.

12:48:47.300 --> 12:48:52.680
It had now a tawny, nay, a bloody light in its gloom, and his face flushed.

12:48:53.040 --> 12:48:58.600
Olive-cheek and hue-less forehead received a glow as from spreading, ascending heart-fire.

12:48:59.280 --> 12:49:01.900
And he stirred, lifted his strong arm.

12:49:02.420 --> 12:49:05.300
He could have struck Mason, dashed him on the church floor,

12:49:05.300 --> 12:49:08.640
shocked by ruthless blow, the breath from his body.

12:49:09.360 --> 12:49:13.620
But Mason shrank away and cried faintly, Good God!

12:49:15.740 --> 12:49:17.680
Contempt fell cool on Mr. Rochester.

12:49:18.180 --> 12:49:21.480
His passion died as if a blight had shriveled it up.

12:49:21.720 --> 12:49:24.200
He only asked, What have you to say?

12:49:26.640 --> 12:49:29.980
An inaudible reply escaped Mason's white lips.

12:49:31.100 --> 12:49:33.880
The devil is in it, if you cannot answer distinctly.

12:49:33.880 --> 12:49:36.480
I again demand, What have you to say?

12:49:38.220 --> 12:49:43.940
Sir, sir, interrupted the clergyman, do not forget you're in a sacred place.

12:49:45.400 --> 12:49:48.200
Then addressing Mason, he inquired gently,

12:49:49.500 --> 12:49:54.000
Are you aware, sir, whether or not this gentleman's wife is still living?

12:49:55.800 --> 12:49:58.760
Courage, urged the lawyer, speak out.

12:50:00.380 --> 12:50:05.520
She is now living at Thornfield Hall, said Mason in more articulate tones.

12:50:06.140 --> 12:50:07.640
I saw her there last April.

12:50:08.140 --> 12:50:09.880
I am her brother.

12:50:11.700 --> 12:50:16.280
At Thornfield Hall, ejaculated the clergyman, impossible.

12:50:17.140 --> 12:50:20.100
I am an old resident in this neighborhood, sir, and

12:50:20.100 --> 12:50:23.580
I never heard of a Mrs. Rochester at Thornfield Hall.

12:50:24.980 --> 12:50:29.740
I saw a grim smile contort Mr. Rochester's lips, and he muttered,

12:50:30.460 --> 12:50:36.820
No, by God, I took care that none should hear of it, or of her under that name.

12:50:38.020 --> 12:50:41.260
He mused, for ten minutes he held counsel with himself.

12:50:41.800 --> 12:50:44.580
He formed his resolve and enhanced it.

12:50:45.380 --> 12:50:50.660
Enough, all shouts bowed out at once, like the bullet from the barrel.

12:50:51.560 --> 12:50:54.500
Wood, close your book and take off your surplus.

12:50:55.200 --> 12:50:58.680
John Green, to the clerk, leave the church.

12:50:58.960 --> 12:51:00.540
There will be no wedding today.

12:51:02.140 --> 12:51:03.220
The man obeyed.

12:51:06.200 --> 12:51:08.980
Mr. Rochester continued, hardily and recklessly.

12:51:10.000 --> 12:51:11.480
Bigamy is an ugly word.

12:51:12.160 --> 12:51:17.060
I meant, however, to be a bigamist, but fate has outmaneuvered me, or

12:51:17.060 --> 12:51:19.900
providence has checked me, perhaps the last.

12:51:20.660 --> 12:51:25.500
I am little better than a devil at this moment, and as my pastor there would

12:51:25.500 --> 12:51:29.300
tell me, deserve no doubt the sternest judgments of God,

12:51:29.740 --> 12:51:32.380
even to the quenchless fire and deathless worm.

12:51:33.120 --> 12:51:35.160
Gentlemen, my plan is broken up.

12:51:35.520 --> 12:51:38.100
What this lawyer and his client say is true.

12:51:38.600 --> 12:51:42.280
I have been married, and the woman to whom I was married lives.

12:51:43.900 --> 12:51:48.280
You say you never heard of a Mrs. Rochester at the house up yonder, Wood.

12:51:48.900 --> 12:51:53.440
But I dare say you have many a time inclined your ear to gossip about the

12:51:53.440 --> 12:51:56.940
mysterious lunatic kept there under watch and ward.

12:51:57.860 --> 12:52:01.240
Some have whispered to you that she is my bastard half-sister.

12:52:01.680 --> 12:52:03.640
Some my cast-off mistress.

12:52:04.640 --> 12:52:09.220
I now inform you that she is my wife, whom I married fifteen years ago,

12:52:09.700 --> 12:52:15.620
Bertha Mason by name, sister of this resolute personage, who is now with

12:52:15.620 --> 12:52:21.280
quivering limbs and white cheeks, showing you what a stout heart men can bear.

12:52:22.940 --> 12:52:25.000
Cheer up, Dick, never fear me.

12:52:25.580 --> 12:52:28.160
I'd almost as soon strike a woman as you.

12:52:29.360 --> 12:52:35.060
Bertha Mason is mad, and she came of a mad family, idiots and maniacs,

12:52:35.120 --> 12:52:36.460
through its three generations.

12:52:37.820 --> 12:52:43.120
Her mother, a Creole, was both a mad woman and a drunkard, as I found out

12:52:43.120 --> 12:52:47.700
after I had wed the daughter, for they were silent on family secrets before.

12:52:49.260 --> 12:52:53.780
Bertha, like a dutiful child, copied her parent in both points.

12:52:54.660 --> 12:52:58.060
I had a charming partner, pure, wise, modest.

12:52:58.480 --> 12:53:00.240
You can fancy I was a happy man.

12:53:00.700 --> 12:53:02.300
I went through rich scenes.

12:53:03.160 --> 12:53:06.720
Oh, my experience has been heavenly, if you only knew it.

12:53:07.660 --> 12:53:09.740
But I owe you no further explanation.

12:53:10.360 --> 12:53:14.320
Briggs, Wood, Mason, I invite you all to come up to the house

12:53:14.320 --> 12:53:18.140
and visit Mrs. Poole's patient and my wife.

12:53:18.700 --> 12:53:21.960
You shall see what sort of a being I was cheated into espousing,

12:53:22.580 --> 12:53:25.740
and judge whether or not I had a right to break the compact,

12:53:26.280 --> 12:53:28.880
and seek sympathy with something at least human.

12:53:29.980 --> 12:53:36.500
This girl, looking at me, knew no more than you, Wood, of the disgusting secret.

12:53:36.500 --> 12:53:40.860
She thought all was fair and legal, and never dreamt she was going to be entrapped

12:53:40.860 --> 12:53:44.140
into a feigned union with a defrauded wretch,

12:53:44.540 --> 12:53:47.860
already bound to a bad, mad, and embruted partner.

12:53:48.620 --> 12:53:49.940
Come, all of you, follow.

12:53:52.100 --> 12:53:54.860
Still holding me fast, he left the church.

12:53:55.380 --> 12:53:56.940
The three gentlemen came after.

12:53:57.620 --> 12:54:00.480
At the front door of the hall, we found the carriage.

12:54:01.360 --> 12:54:05.920
Take it back to the coach house, John, said Mr. Rochester Cooley.

12:54:06.500 --> 12:54:08.320
It will not be wanted today.

12:54:09.100 --> 12:54:15.860
At our entrance, Mrs. Fairfax, Adelle Sophie Lee advanced to meet and greet us.

12:54:17.600 --> 12:54:21.520
To the right about, every soul, cried the master.

12:54:21.840 --> 12:54:23.280
Away with your congratulations.

12:54:23.600 --> 12:54:24.600
Who wants them?

12:54:24.720 --> 12:54:27.780
Not I. They are fifteen years too late.

12:54:28.740 --> 12:54:32.700
He passed on and ascended the stairs, still holding my hand,

12:54:32.980 --> 12:54:36.260
and still beckoning the gentlemen to follow him, which they did.

12:54:36.500 --> 12:54:40.320
We mounted the first staircase, passed up the gallery,

12:54:40.600 --> 12:54:42.260
proceeded to the third story.

12:54:42.800 --> 12:54:46.620
The low black door, opened by Mr. Rochester's master key,

12:54:47.200 --> 12:54:52.420
admitted us to the tapestryed room, with its great bed and its pictorial cabinet.

12:54:53.800 --> 12:54:56.720
You know this place, Mason, said our guide.

12:54:57.180 --> 12:54:58.880
She bit and stabbed you here.

12:55:00.760 --> 12:55:04.720
He lifted the hangings from the wall, uncovering the second door.

12:55:04.720 --> 12:55:06.320
This too he opened.

12:55:07.140 --> 12:55:12.800
In a room without a window, there burnt a fire guarded by a high and strong fender,

12:55:13.340 --> 12:55:16.780
and a lamp suspended from the ceiling by a chain.

12:55:17.700 --> 12:55:21.940
Grace Poole bent over the fire, apparently cooking something in a saucepan.

12:55:23.140 --> 12:55:28.580
In the deep shade, at the farther end of the room, a figure ran backwards and forwards.

12:55:29.460 --> 12:55:34.300
What it was, were the beast or human being one could not at first sight tell.

12:55:34.720 --> 12:55:37.540
It grovelled seemingly on all fours.

12:55:37.540 --> 12:55:41.380
It snatched and growled like some strange wild animal,

12:55:41.760 --> 12:55:45.960
but it was covered with clothing, and a quantity of dark grizzled hair,

12:55:46.260 --> 12:55:48.980
wild as a mane, hid its head and face.

12:55:50.020 --> 12:55:53.080
Good morrow, Mrs. Poole, said Mr. Rochester.

12:55:53.580 --> 12:55:56.040
How are you, and how is your charge today?

12:55:57.600 --> 12:56:01.040
We're tolerable, sir, thank you, replied Grace,

12:56:01.660 --> 12:56:04.120
lifting the boiling mess carefully onto the hob.

12:56:04.720 --> 12:56:06.660
Rather snappish, but not rages.

12:56:08.420 --> 12:56:12.080
A fierce cry seemed to give the lie to her favourable report.

12:56:12.560 --> 12:56:16.800
The clothed hyena rose up and stood tall on its hind feet.

12:56:18.060 --> 12:56:21.040
Ah, sir, she sees you, exclaimed Grace.

12:56:21.440 --> 12:56:22.600
You'd better not stay.

12:56:24.180 --> 12:56:27.580
Only a few moments, Grace, you must allow me a few moments.

12:56:28.760 --> 12:56:31.500
Take care, then, sir, for God's sake, take care.

12:56:32.860 --> 12:56:34.980
The maniac bellowed.

12:56:35.080 --> 12:56:37.760
She parted her shaggy locks from her visage,

12:56:38.200 --> 12:56:40.080
and gazed wildly at her visitors.

12:56:41.080 --> 12:56:44.780
I recognised well that purple face, those bloated features.

12:56:46.020 --> 12:56:47.300
Mrs. Poole advanced.

12:56:48.540 --> 12:56:52.140
Keep out of the way, said Mr. Rochester, thrusting her aside.

12:56:52.520 --> 12:56:55.980
She has no knife now, I suppose, and I am on my guard.

12:56:57.600 --> 12:57:00.060
One never knows what she has, sir, she is so cunning.

12:57:00.060 --> 12:57:03.520
It is not in mortal discretion to fathom her craft.

12:57:05.580 --> 12:57:08.940
We had better leave her, whispered Mason.

12:57:09.580 --> 12:57:12.940
Go to the devil, was his brother-in-law's recommendation.

12:57:14.280 --> 12:57:16.500
Where? cried Grace.

12:57:17.180 --> 12:57:19.460
The three gentlemen retreated simultaneously.

12:57:20.160 --> 12:57:21.980
Mr. Rochester flung me behind him.

12:57:22.300 --> 12:57:25.260
The lunatic sprang and grappled his throat viciously,

12:57:25.540 --> 12:57:27.080
and laid her teeth to his cheek.

12:57:27.580 --> 12:57:28.340
They struggled.

12:57:28.340 --> 12:57:32.340
She was a big woman, in stature almost equaling her husband,

12:57:32.900 --> 12:57:37.320
and corpulent besides, she showed virile force in the contest.

12:57:38.200 --> 12:57:41.860
More than once she almost throttled him, athletic as he was.

12:57:42.700 --> 12:57:45.160
He could have settled her with a well-planted blow,

12:57:45.560 --> 12:57:48.360
but he would not strike, he would only wrestle.

12:57:49.660 --> 12:57:51.360
At last he mastered her arms.

12:57:51.780 --> 12:57:55.980
Grace Poole gave him a cord, and he pinioned them behind her,

12:57:55.980 --> 12:57:59.980
with more rope, which was at hand, he bound her to a chair.

12:58:01.080 --> 12:58:04.140
The operation was performed amidst the fiercest yells,

12:58:04.580 --> 12:58:06.520
and the most convulsive plunges.

12:58:07.340 --> 12:58:09.700
Mr. Rochester then turned to the spectators.

12:58:10.760 --> 12:58:13.960
He looked at them with a smile both acrid and desolate.

12:58:16.240 --> 12:58:18.910
That is my wife, said he.

12:58:19.900 --> 12:58:23.140
Such is the sole conjugal embrace I am ever to know.

12:58:23.140 --> 12:58:26.780
Such are the endearments which are to solace my leisure hours,

12:58:27.300 --> 12:58:31.120
and this is what I wished to have, laying his hand on my shoulder,

12:58:31.480 --> 12:58:35.680
this young girl who stands so grave and quiet at the mouth of hell,

12:58:36.340 --> 12:58:39.300
looking collectively at the gambles of a demon.

12:58:40.180 --> 12:58:44.200
I wanted her, just as a change after that fierce ragu.

12:58:45.080 --> 12:58:47.260
Wooden Briggs, look at the difference.

12:58:47.960 --> 12:58:51.540
Compare these clear eyes with a red bald yonder,

12:58:51.540 --> 12:58:56.120
this face with that mask, this form with that bulk.

12:58:56.700 --> 12:58:59.560
Then judge me, priest of the gospel and man of the law,

12:58:59.800 --> 12:59:04.140
and remember with what judgment ye judge, ye shall be judged.

12:59:05.520 --> 12:59:06.420
Off with you now.

12:59:06.540 --> 12:59:08.140
I must shut up my prize.

12:59:10.840 --> 12:59:12.020
We all withdrew.

12:59:13.020 --> 12:59:18.060
Mr. Rochester stayed a moment behind us to give some further order to Grace Poole.

12:59:18.850 --> 12:59:21.620
The solicitor addressed me as he descended the stair.

12:59:22.540 --> 12:59:26.200
You, madam, said he, are cleared from all blame.

12:59:26.800 --> 12:59:30.540
Your uncle will be glad to hear it, if indeed he should be still living,

12:59:31.140 --> 12:59:33.240
when Mr. Mason returns to Madeira.

12:59:34.880 --> 12:59:38.220
My uncle? What of him? Do you know him?

12:59:39.720 --> 12:59:41.020
Mr. Mason does.

12:59:41.880 --> 12:59:46.120
Mr. Eyre has been the Funchal correspondent of his house for some years.

12:59:47.320 --> 12:59:52.360
When your uncle received your letter intimating the contemplated union between yourself and Mr.

12:59:52.540 --> 12:59:58.440
Rochester, Mr. Mason, who was staying at Madeira to recruit his health, on his way back to Jamaica,

12:59:58.960 --> 13:00:00.220
happened to be with him.

13:00:00.800 --> 13:00:05.900
Mr. Eyre mentioned the intelligence, for he knew that my client here was acquainted with the

13:00:05.900 --> 13:00:07.520
gentleman of the name of Rochester.

13:00:08.640 --> 13:00:14.060
Mr. Mason, astonished and distressed, as you may suppose, revealed the real state of matters.

13:00:14.980 --> 13:00:20.600
Your uncle, I am sorry to say, is now on a sick bed, from which, considering the nature of his

13:00:20.600 --> 13:00:26.640
disease, decline, and the stage it has reached, it is unlikely he will ever rise.

13:00:27.280 --> 13:00:33.200
He could not then hasten to England himself, to extricate you from the snare into which you had

13:00:33.200 --> 13:00:39.220
fallen, but he implored Mr. Mason to lose no time in taking steps to prevent the false marriage.

13:00:40.420 --> 13:00:42.640
He referred him to me for assistance.

13:00:43.320 --> 13:00:49.620
I used all dispatch, and am thankful I was not too late, as you doubtless must be also.

13:00:51.180 --> 13:00:57.140
Were I not morally certain that your uncle will be dead, ere you reach Madeira, I would advise you to

13:00:57.140 --> 13:01:02.660
accompany Mr. Mason back, but as it is, I think you had better remain in England till you can hear

13:01:02.660 --> 13:01:05.680
further, either from or of Mr. Eyre.

13:01:07.400 --> 13:01:09.340
Have we anything else to stay for?

13:01:09.720 --> 13:01:11.440
He inquired of Mr. Mason.

13:01:12.100 --> 13:01:18.720
No, no, let us be gone, was the anxious reply, and without waiting to take leave of Mr. Rochester,

13:01:19.220 --> 13:01:21.500
they made their exit at the hall door.

13:01:22.500 --> 13:01:28.980
The clergyman stayed to exchange a few sentences, either of admonition or reproof, with his haughty

13:01:28.980 --> 13:01:32.740
parishioner. This duty done, he too departed.

13:01:34.420 --> 13:01:40.860
I heard him go, as I stood at the half-open door of my own room, to which I had now withdrawn.

13:01:41.440 --> 13:01:48.300
The house cleared, I shut myself in, fastened the belt that none might intrude, and proceeded,

13:01:48.840 --> 13:01:56.880
not to weep, not to mourn, I was yet too calm for that, but mechanically to take off the wedding dress

13:01:56.880 --> 13:02:03.240
and replace it by the stuff gown I had worn yesterday, as I thought for the last time.

13:02:04.000 --> 13:02:11.960
I then sat down, I felt weak and tired, I leaned my arms on a table, and my head dropped on them,

13:02:12.980 --> 13:02:18.620
and now I thought, till now I had only heard, seen, moved, followed up and down where I was

13:02:18.620 --> 13:02:27.320
led or dragged, watched event rush on event, disclosure open beyond disclosure, but now I thought.

13:02:30.060 --> 13:02:35.900
The morning had been a quiet morning enough. All except the brief scene with the lunatic.

13:02:36.620 --> 13:02:41.260
The transaction in the church had not been noisy. There was no explosion of passion,

13:02:41.640 --> 13:02:48.520
no loud altercation, no dispute, no defiance or challenge, no tears, no sobs. A few words

13:02:48.520 --> 13:02:55.040
had been spoken, a calmly pronounced objection to the marriage made, some stern short questions

13:02:55.040 --> 13:03:02.520
put by Mr. Rochester, answers, explanations given, evidence adduced, an open admission of

13:03:02.520 --> 13:03:07.960
the truth had been uttered by my master. Then the living proof had been seen,

13:03:08.240 --> 13:03:16.040
the intruders were gone, and all was over. I was in my own room as usual, just myself,

13:03:16.460 --> 13:03:22.400
without obvious change. Nothing had smitten me or scathed me or maimed me.

13:03:23.040 --> 13:03:29.880
And yet, where was the Jane Eyre of yesterday? Where was her life? Where were her prospects?

13:03:31.980 --> 13:03:39.380
Jane Eyre, who had been an ardent, expectant woman, almost a bride, was a cold, solitary girl

13:03:39.380 --> 13:03:48.900
again. Her life was pale, her prospects were desolate. A Christmas frost had come at mid-summer,

13:03:48.900 --> 13:03:56.240
a white December storm had whirled over June. Ice glazed the ripe apples. Drifts crushed the

13:03:56.240 --> 13:04:03.040
blowing roses. On Hayfield and Cornfield lay a frozen shroud. Lanes, which last night blushed

13:04:03.040 --> 13:04:10.460
full of flowers, today were pathless with untrodden snow. And the woods, which twelve hours since,

13:04:11.080 --> 13:04:18.200
waved leafy and flagrant as groves between the tropics, now spread waist wild and white as

13:04:18.200 --> 13:04:25.780
pine forests in wintry Norway. My hopes were all dead, struck with a subtle doom such as,

13:04:25.840 --> 13:04:29.640
in one night, fell on all the first born in the land of Egypt.

13:04:32.420 --> 13:04:36.760
I looked on my cherished wishes, yesterday so blooming and glowing,

13:04:37.380 --> 13:04:44.420
they lay stark, chill, livid corpses that could never revive. I looked at my love,

13:04:44.420 --> 13:04:50.580
that feeling which was my master's, which he had created. It shivered in my heart,

13:04:50.940 --> 13:04:56.200
like a suffering child in a cold cradle. Sickness and anguish had seized it.

13:04:56.580 --> 13:05:02.020
It could not seek Mr. Rochester's arms. It could not derive warmth from his breast.

13:05:03.300 --> 13:05:09.380
Oh, never more could it turn to him, for faith was blighted, confidence destroyed.

13:05:11.200 --> 13:05:16.560
Mr. Rochester was not to me what he had been, for he was not what I had sought him.

13:05:17.420 --> 13:05:23.160
I would not ascribe vice to him, I would not say he had betrayed me, but the attribute of

13:05:23.160 --> 13:05:29.940
stainless truth was gone from his idea, and from his presence I must go, that I perceived well.

13:05:31.040 --> 13:05:37.300
When, how, whither, I could not yet discern, but he himself, I doubt not, would hurry me from

13:05:37.300 --> 13:05:46.400
Thornfield. Real affection, it seemed, he could not have for me. It had been only fitful passion,

13:05:47.300 --> 13:05:53.760
that was borked, he would want me no more. I should fear even to cross his path now,

13:05:54.480 --> 13:06:00.400
my view must be hateful to him. Oh, how blind had been my eyes, how weak my conduct.

13:06:02.140 --> 13:06:10.340
My eyes were covered and closed. Eddying darkness seemed to swim round me, and reflection came in

13:06:10.340 --> 13:06:17.700
as black and confused a flow. Self-abandoned, relaxed, and effortless, I seemed to have laid

13:06:17.700 --> 13:06:24.120
me down in the dried-up bed of a great river. I heard a flood loosened in remote mountains,

13:06:24.700 --> 13:06:30.000
and felt the torrent come. To rise I had no will, to flee I had no strength.

13:06:30.560 --> 13:06:37.960
I lay faint, longing to be dead. One idea only, still throbbed, lifelike within me.

13:06:39.620 --> 13:06:45.700
A remembrance of God. It begot an unuttered prayer, those words went wandering up and down

13:06:45.700 --> 13:06:52.540
in my rayless mind, as something that should be whispered, but no energy was found to express them.

13:06:53.900 --> 13:06:58.000
Be not far from me, for trouble is near, there is none to help.

13:06:59.420 --> 13:07:04.700
It was near, and as I had lifted no petition to heaven to avert it,

13:07:05.160 --> 13:07:12.340
as I had neither joined my hands, nor bent my knees, nor moved my lips, it came. In full heavy

13:07:12.340 --> 13:07:19.140
swing the torrent poured over me. The whole consciousness of my life-lawn, my love lost,

13:07:19.220 --> 13:07:26.560
my hope quenched, my faith death-struck, swayed full and mighty above me in one sullen mass.

13:07:27.560 --> 13:07:33.500
That bitter hour cannot be described. In truth, the waters came into my soul,

13:07:33.960 --> 13:07:42.060
I sank in deep mire, I felt no standing, I came into deep waters. The floods overflowed me.

13:08:15.400 --> 13:08:20.800
Jane Eyre by Charlotte Bronte, chapter 27.

13:08:25.620 --> 13:08:36.840
Sometime in the afternoon, I raised my head, and looking round, and seeing the western sun gelding the sign of its decline on the wall, I asked,

13:08:37.520 --> 13:08:49.680
What am I to do? But the answer my mind gave, leave thorn-filled at once, was so prompt, so dread, that I stopped my ears.

13:08:51.260 --> 13:08:54.160
I said I could not bear such words now.

13:08:55.440 --> 13:09:22.980
That I am not Edward Rochester's wife is the least part of my will, I alleged. That I have wakened out of most glorious dreams, and found them all void and vain, is a horror I could bear and master. But that I must leave him decidedly, instantly, entirely, is intolerable. I cannot do it.

13:09:24.880 --> 13:09:45.080
But then, a voice within me averred that I could do it, and foretold that I should do it. I wrestled with my own resolution. I wanted to be weak, that I might avoid the awful passage of further suffering I so laid out for me.

13:09:45.080 --> 13:10:04.180
And conscience, turned tyrant, held passion by the throat, told her tauntingly, she had yet but dipped her dainty feet in the slaw, and swore that with that arm of iron he would thrust her down to unsounded depth of agony.

13:10:05.660 --> 13:10:11.480
Let me be torn away then, I cried. Let another help me.

13:10:12.440 --> 13:10:31.280
No, you shall tear yourself away. None shall help you. You shall yourself pluck out your right eye. Yourself cut off your right hand. Your heart shall be the victim, and you the priest to transfix it.

13:10:32.780 --> 13:10:47.060
I rose up suddenly, terror-struck at the solitude which so ruthless a judge haunted, at the silence which so awful a voice filled. My head swam as I stood erect.

13:10:48.260 --> 13:10:59.560
I perceived that I was sickening from excitement and indignation. Neither meat nor drink had passed my lips that day, for I had taken no breakfast.

13:11:01.020 --> 13:11:13.140
And with a strange bang, I now reflected that, long as I had been shut up here, no message had been sent to ask how I was, or to invite me to come down.

13:11:13.140 --> 13:11:20.080
Not even little Adele had tapped at the door. Not even Mrs Fairfax had sought me.

13:11:22.080 --> 13:11:28.960
Friends always forget those whom fortune forsakes, I murmured, as I untrew the bolt and passed out.

13:11:29.780 --> 13:11:40.560
I stumbled over an obstacle. My head was still dizzy, my sight was dim, and my limbs were feeble. I could not soon recover myself.

13:11:41.660 --> 13:11:54.520
I fell, but not on the ground. An outstretched arm caught me. I looked up. I was supported by Mr Rochester, who sat in a chair across my chamber threshold.

13:11:56.580 --> 13:12:08.140
You come out at last, he said. Well, I have been waiting for you long, and listening. Yet not one movement have I heard, nor one sob.

13:12:09.240 --> 13:12:14.720
Five minutes more of that deathlike hush, and I should have forced the lock like a burglar.

13:12:16.240 --> 13:12:20.920
So you shun me? You shut yourself up and grieve alone?

13:12:21.920 --> 13:12:30.980
I would rather you had come and abraded me with vehemence. You are passionate. I expected a scene of some kind.

13:12:32.080 --> 13:12:38.060
I was prepared for the hot rain of tears. Only I wanted them to be shed on my breast.

13:12:39.220 --> 13:12:44.360
Now a senseless floor has received them, or your drenched anchor-chief.

13:12:45.540 --> 13:12:55.660
But I err. You have not wept at all. I see a white cheek and a faded eye, but no trace of tears.

13:12:58.100 --> 13:13:02.020
I suppose, then, your heart has been weeping blood?

13:13:05.420 --> 13:13:15.800
Well, Jane, not a word of reproach? Nothing bitter? Nothing poignant? Nothing to cut a feeling or sting passion?

13:13:17.360 --> 13:13:22.740
You sit quietly where I have placed you, and regard me with a weary passive look.

13:13:24.600 --> 13:13:34.200
Jane, I never meant to wound you thus. If the man who had but one little yule lamp that was dear to him as a daughter,

13:13:34.880 --> 13:13:43.180
that ate of his bread and drank of his cup, and lay in his bosom, had by some mistake slaughtered it at the shambles,

13:13:44.040 --> 13:13:48.200
he would not have fruit his bloody blunder more than I now rue mine.

13:13:49.480 --> 13:13:51.340
Will you ever forgive me?

13:13:53.120 --> 13:14:04.500
Rita, I forgave him at the moment and on the spot. There was such deep remorse in his eye, such true pity in his tone,

13:14:05.620 --> 13:14:13.660
such manly energy in his manner, and besides, there was such unchanged love in his whole look and mean.

13:14:14.780 --> 13:14:24.160
I forgave him all. Yet, not in words, not outwardly, only at my heart's core.

13:14:25.640 --> 13:14:27.880
You know I am a scoundrel, Jane.

13:14:29.080 --> 13:14:38.080
Here long he inquired wistfully, wondering, I suppose, at my continued silence and tameness, the result rather of weakness than of will.

13:14:38.900 --> 13:14:45.100
Yes, sir. Then tell me so, roundly and sharply. Don't spare me.

13:14:46.120 --> 13:14:51.080
I cannot. I am tired and sick. I want some water.

13:14:53.020 --> 13:14:59.080
He heaved a sort of shuddering sigh, and taking me in his arms, carried me downstairs.

13:15:00.360 --> 13:15:07.820
At first, I did not know to what room he had borne me. All was cloudy to my glazed sight.

13:15:08.900 --> 13:15:16.880
Presently I felt the revival warmth of a fire. For summer as it was, I had become icy cold in my chamber.

13:15:18.140 --> 13:15:27.320
He put wine to my lips. I tasted it and revived. Then I ate something he offered me, and was soon myself.

13:15:28.120 --> 13:15:33.980
I was in the library, sitting in his chair. He was quite near.

13:15:35.600 --> 13:15:42.760
If I could go out of life now, without too sharp a bang, it would be well for me, I thought.

13:15:43.700 --> 13:15:50.560
Then I should not have to make the effort of cracking my heartstrings in rending them from among Mr. Rochester's.

13:15:51.640 --> 13:15:56.600
I must leave him, it appears. I do not want to leave him.

13:15:57.320 --> 13:15:59.200
I cannot leave him.

13:16:01.560 --> 13:16:03.100
How are you now, Jane?

13:16:04.300 --> 13:16:07.060
Much better, sir. I shall be well soon.

13:16:08.540 --> 13:16:10.080
Taste the wine again, Jane.

13:16:10.880 --> 13:16:19.120
I obeyed him. Then he put the glass on the table, stood before me, and looked at me attentively.

13:16:20.440 --> 13:16:27.260
Suddenly he turned away, with an inarticulate exclamation, full of passionate emotion of some kind.

13:16:28.280 --> 13:16:34.440
He walked fast through the room and came back. He stooped towards me as if to kiss me.

13:16:35.160 --> 13:16:41.380
But I remembered caresses were now forbidden. I turned my face away and put his aside.

13:16:42.360 --> 13:16:46.590
What? How is this? He exclaimed heartily.

13:16:47.940 --> 13:16:51.640
Oh, I know. You won't kiss the husband of Bertha Mason.

13:16:52.680 --> 13:16:56.600
You consider my arms filled and my embraces appropriated?

13:16:58.480 --> 13:17:01.980
At any rate, there is neither room nor claim for me, sir.

13:17:03.280 --> 13:17:09.440
Why, Jane? I will spare you the trouble of much talking. I will answer for you.

13:17:09.440 --> 13:17:14.940
Because I have a wife already, you would reply? I guess rightly?

13:17:16.300 --> 13:17:16.860
Yes.

13:17:17.960 --> 13:17:21.760
If you think so, you must have a strange opinion of me.

13:17:22.360 --> 13:17:29.760
You must regard me as a plotting profligate, a base and low rake who has been simulating disinterested love,

13:17:30.360 --> 13:17:36.540
in order to draw you into a snare deliberately laid, and strip you of honour, and rob you of self-respect.

13:17:37.340 --> 13:17:38.780
What do you say to that?

13:17:40.460 --> 13:17:47.640
I see you can say nothing. In the first place, you are feigned still and have enough to do to draw your breath.

13:17:48.380 --> 13:17:53.320
In the second place, you cannot yet accustom yourself to accuse and revile me.

13:17:53.900 --> 13:18:00.160
And besides, the floodgates of tears are opened, and they would rush out if you spoke much.

13:18:00.860 --> 13:18:06.420
And you have no desire to expostulate, to upbraid, to make a scene.

13:18:07.260 --> 13:18:12.460
You are thinking how to act. Talking, you consider, is of no use.

13:18:13.680 --> 13:18:16.840
I know you. I am on my guard.

13:18:19.020 --> 13:18:27.840
Sir, I do not wish to act against you, I said, and my unsteady voice warned me to curtail my sentence.

13:18:29.160 --> 13:18:35.080
Not in your sense of the word, but in mine, you are scheming to destroy me.

13:18:36.260 --> 13:18:39.640
You have as good as said that I am a married man.

13:18:40.400 --> 13:18:44.100
As a married man, you will shun me, keep out of my way.

13:18:45.060 --> 13:18:47.420
Just now, you have refused to kiss me.

13:18:48.700 --> 13:18:55.000
You intend to make yourself a complete stranger to me, to live under this roof only as an adult governess.

13:18:55.000 --> 13:19:02.480
If ever I say a friendly word to you, if ever a friendly feeling inclines you again to me, you will say,

13:19:03.340 --> 13:19:08.640
That man had nearly made me his mistress. I must be ice and rock to him.

13:19:09.660 --> 13:19:12.420
And ice and rock you will accordingly become.

13:19:14.640 --> 13:19:17.240
I cleared and steadied my voice to reply.

13:19:18.700 --> 13:19:20.460
All is changed about me, sir.

13:19:21.520 --> 13:19:23.120
I must change too.

13:19:23.820 --> 13:19:25.860
There is no doubt of that.

13:19:26.720 --> 13:19:35.340
And to avoid fluctuations of feeling and continual combats with recollections and associations, there is only one way.

13:19:36.500 --> 13:19:38.440
Adele must have a new governess, sir.

13:19:39.480 --> 13:19:41.880
Oh, Adele will go to school.

13:19:42.440 --> 13:19:44.300
I have settled that already.

13:19:45.120 --> 13:19:50.320
Nor do I mean to torment you with the hideous associations and recollections of Thornfield Hall.

13:19:50.320 --> 13:20:00.900
This accursed place, this tent of Aiken, this insolent vault, offering the ghastliness of living death to the light of the open sky.

13:20:01.880 --> 13:20:08.480
This narrow stone hell, with its one real fiend, worse than a legion of such as we imagine.

13:20:09.860 --> 13:20:13.360
Jane, you shall not stay here.

13:20:13.840 --> 13:20:14.960
Nor will I.

13:20:15.700 --> 13:20:21.420
I was wrong ever to bring you to Thornfield Hall, knowing as I did how it was haunted.

13:20:22.600 --> 13:20:29.280
I charged them to conceal from you, before I ever saw you, all knowledge of the curse of the place.

13:20:30.220 --> 13:20:36.620
Merely because I feared Adele never would have a governess to stay if she knew with what inmate she was housed.

13:20:36.620 --> 13:20:59.040
And my plans would not permit me to remove the minyak elsewhere, though I possessed an old house, ferned in manner, even more retired and hidden than this, where I could have lodged her safely enough, had not a scruple about the unhealthiness of the situation in the heart of a wood, made my conscience recalled from the arrangement.

13:21:00.420 --> 13:21:04.560
Probably those damp walls would soon have eased me of her charge.

13:21:05.640 --> 13:21:13.520
But to each villain his own vice, and mine is not a tendency to indirect assassination, even of what I most hate.

13:21:16.060 --> 13:21:25.360
Concealing the madwoman's neighbourhood from you, however, was something like covering a child with a cloak and laying it down near a yubus tree.

13:21:26.300 --> 13:21:30.480
That demon's vicinage is poisoned, and always was.

13:21:32.060 --> 13:21:45.220
But I'll shut up Thornfield Hall, I'll nail up the front door and bolt the lower windows, I'll give Mrs. Poole two hundred a year to live here with my wife, as you term that fearful hag.

13:21:45.900 --> 13:21:57.180
Grace will do much for money, and she shall have her son, the keeper at Grimsby Retreat, to bear her company and be at hand to give her aid in the paroxysms.

13:21:57.720 --> 13:22:12.280
When my wife is prompted by her familiar to burn people in their beds at night, to stab them, to bite their flesh from their bones and so on, sir, I interrupted him, you are inexorable for that unfortunate lady.

13:22:12.280 --> 13:22:21.900
You speak of her with hate, with vindictive antipathy. It is cruel. She cannot help being mad.

13:22:23.160 --> 13:22:37.920
Jane, my little darling, so I will call you, for so you are. You don't know what you are talking about. You misjudge me again. It is not because she is mad I hate her.

13:22:37.920 --> 13:22:41.980
If you were mad, do you think I should hate you?

13:22:42.880 --> 13:22:44.320
I do indeed, sir.

13:22:45.180 --> 13:22:51.820
Then you are mistaken, and you know nothing about me, and nothing about the sort of love of which I am capable.

13:22:52.960 --> 13:23:00.380
Every atom of your flesh is as dear to me as my own. In pain and sickness it would still be dear.

13:23:01.120 --> 13:23:12.880
Your mind is my treasure, and if it were broken, it would be my treasure still. If you raved, my arms should confine you, and not a straight waistcoat.

13:23:13.940 --> 13:23:27.880
Your grasp, even in fury, would have a charm for me. If you flew at me as wildly as that woman did this morning, I should receive you in an embrace, at least as fond as it would be restrictive.

13:23:28.860 --> 13:23:53.420
I should not shrink from you with disgust as I did from her. In your quiet moments, you should have no watcher and no nurse but me, and I could hang over you with untiring tenderness, though you gave me no smile in return, and never weary of gazing into your eyes, though they had no longer a ray of recognition for me.

13:23:54.520 --> 13:24:07.760
But why do I follow that train of ideas? I was talking of removing you from Thornfield. All you know is prepared for prom departure. Tomorrow you shall go.

13:24:07.760 --> 13:24:28.620
I only ask you to endure one more night under this roof, Jane, and then farewell to its miseries and terrors for ever. I have a place to repair to, which will be a secure sanctuary from hateful reminiscences, from unwelcome intrusion, even from falsehood and slander.

13:24:29.460 --> 13:24:35.060
And take Adele with you, sir, I interrupted. She will be a companion for you.

13:24:36.040 --> 13:24:55.260
What do you mean, Jane? I told you I would send Adele to school. And what do I want with a child for a companion, and not my own child, a French dancer's bastard? Why do you importune me about her? I say, why do you assign Adele to me for a companion?

13:24:56.240 --> 13:25:03.060
You spoke of retirement, sir. And retirement and solitude are dull. Too dull for you.

13:25:03.980 --> 13:25:07.920
Solitude? Solitude? He reiterated with irritation.

13:25:09.440 --> 13:25:21.740
I see I must come to an explanation. I don't know what Sphinx-like expression is forming in your countenance. You are to share my solitude. Do you understand?

13:25:23.020 --> 13:25:39.680
I shook my head. It required a degree of courage, excited as he was becoming, even to risk that mute sign of descent. He had been walking fast about the room, and he stopped, as if suddenly rooted to one spot.

13:25:40.440 --> 13:25:52.320
He looked at me long and hard. I turned my eyes from him, fixed them on the fire, and tried to assume and maintain a quiet, collected respect.

13:25:53.320 --> 13:26:11.980
Now for the hitch in Jane's character, he said at last, speaking more calmly than from his look I had expected him to speak. The reel of silk has run smoothly enough so far, but I always knew there would come a knot and a puzzle. Here it is.

13:26:12.860 --> 13:26:25.600
Now for vexation and exasperation and endless trouble. By God, I long to exert a fraction of Samson's strength and break the entangled moods like Toe.

13:26:26.280 --> 13:26:32.080
He recommands his walk, but soon again stopped, and this time just before me.

13:26:32.920 --> 13:26:39.500
Jane, will you hear reason? He stooped and approached his lips to my ear.

13:26:40.780 --> 13:26:45.240
Because, if you won't, I'll try violence.

13:26:46.200 --> 13:26:56.400
His voice was hoarse. His look, that of a man who is just about to burst an insufferable bond and plunge headlong into white license.

13:26:57.740 --> 13:27:05.060
I saw that in another moment, and with one impetus of frenzy more, I should be able to do nothing with him.

13:27:05.060 --> 13:27:19.840
The present, the passing second of time, was all I had in which to control and restrain him. A movement of repulsion, flight, fear, would have sealed my doom and haze.

13:27:19.840 --> 13:27:30.640
But I was not afraid, not in the least. I felt an inward power, a sense of influence which supported me.

13:27:31.640 --> 13:27:41.180
The crisis was perilous, but not without its charm, such as the Indian perhaps feels when he slips over the rapid in his canoe.

13:27:42.200 --> 13:27:50.680
I took hold of his clenched hand, loosened the contorted fingers, and said to him, soothingly,

13:27:51.780 --> 13:28:01.180
Sit down, I'll talk to you as long as you like, and hear all you have to say, whether reasonable or unreasonable.

13:28:02.940 --> 13:28:06.940
He sat down, but he did not get leave to speak directly.

13:28:07.740 --> 13:28:17.260
I had been struggling with tears for some time. I had taken great pains to repress them, because I knew he would not like to see me weep.

13:28:17.740 --> 13:28:30.560
Now, however, I considered it well to let them flow as freely and as long as they liked. If the flood annoyed him, so much the better. So I gave way and cried heartily.

13:28:32.420 --> 13:28:39.840
Soon I heard him earnestly entreating me to become post. I said I could not, while he was in such a passion.

13:28:40.940 --> 13:28:54.840
But I am not angry, Jane. I only love you too well. And you had steeled your little pale face with such a resolute, frozen look. I could not endure it.

13:28:56.080 --> 13:28:58.960
Hush now, and wipe your eyes.

13:29:01.160 --> 13:29:07.520
His softened voice announced that he was subdued, so I, in my turn, became calm.

13:29:08.840 --> 13:29:17.820
Now he made an effort to rest his head on my shoulder, but I would not permit it. Then he would draw me to him. No.

13:29:19.000 --> 13:29:27.420
Jane! Jane! he said, in such an accent of bitter sadness, it thrilled along every nerve I had.

13:29:28.580 --> 13:29:35.300
You don't love me then? It was only my station and the rank of my wife that you valued?

13:29:36.720 --> 13:29:44.020
Now that you think me disqualified to become your husband, you recoil from my touch as if I were some toad or ape.

13:29:45.480 --> 13:29:54.480
These words cut me. Yet what could I do or say? I ought probably to have done or said nothing.

13:29:55.580 --> 13:30:04.040
But I was so tortured by a sense of remorse at thus hurting his feelings, I could not control the wish to drop balm where I had wounded.

13:30:05.560 --> 13:30:16.720
I do love you, I said, more than ever, but I must not show or indulge the feeling, and this is the last time I must express it.

13:30:17.320 --> 13:30:28.060
The last time, Jane? What? Do you think you can live with me and see me daily, and yet, if you still love me, be always cold and distant?

13:30:29.360 --> 13:30:41.640
No, sir. That I am certain I could not. And therefore, I see there is but one way. But you will be furious if I mention it.

13:30:42.480 --> 13:30:47.080
Oh, mention it! If I storm, you have the art of weeping.

13:30:48.600 --> 13:30:51.800
Mr. Rochester, I must leave you.

13:30:51.800 --> 13:31:02.140
For how long, Jane? For a few minutes, while you smooth your hair, which is somewhat disheveled, and bathe your face, which looks feverish?

13:31:03.280 --> 13:31:14.800
I must leave Adele and Thornfield. I must part with you for my whole life. I must begin a new existence, among strange faces and strange scenes.

13:31:15.460 --> 13:31:25.260
Of course, I told you you should. I pass over the madness about parting from me. You mean you must become a part of me.

13:31:25.980 --> 13:31:35.860
As to the new existence, it is all right. You shall yet be my wife. I am not married. You shall be Mrs. Rochester.

13:31:36.520 --> 13:31:42.640
Both virtually and nominally, I shall keep only to you, so long as you and I live.

13:31:43.580 --> 13:31:50.480
You shall go to a place I have in the south of France, a whitewashed villa on the shores of the Mediterranean.

13:31:51.620 --> 13:32:01.220
There you shall live a happy and guarded and most innocent life. Never fear that I wish to lure you into error, to make you my mistress.

13:32:01.220 --> 13:32:10.600
Why did you shake your head? Jane, you must be reasonable. Or in truth, I shall again become frantic.

13:32:11.620 --> 13:32:20.560
His voice and hand quivered, his large nostrils dilated, his eye blazed. Still, I dare to speak.

13:32:21.620 --> 13:32:34.560
Sir, your wife is living. That is a fact acknowledged this morning by yourself. If I lived with you as you desire, I should then be your mistress.

13:32:35.580 --> 13:32:45.400
To say otherwise is sophistical, is false. Jane, I am not a gentle tempered man. You forget that.

13:32:45.400 --> 13:32:59.860
I am not long enduring. I am not cool and dispassionate. Out of pity to me and yourself, put your finger on my pulse, feel how it throbs, and beware.

13:33:00.940 --> 13:33:09.660
He bared his wrist and offered it to me. The blood was forsaking his cheek and lips. They were growing livid.

13:33:09.660 --> 13:33:21.320
I was distressed on all hands. To agitate him thus deeply by a resistance he saw aboard was cruel. To yield was out of the question.

13:33:22.540 --> 13:33:36.980
I did what human beings do instinctively when they are driven to utter extremity. Looked for aid to one higher than man. The words, God help me, burst involuntarily from my lips.

13:33:37.700 --> 13:33:55.780
I am a fool, cried Mr. Rochester suddenly. I keep telling her I am not married and do not explain to her why. I forget she knows nothing of the character of that woman or of the circumstances attending my infernal union with her.

13:33:56.640 --> 13:34:16.260
Oh, I am certain Jane will agree with me in opinion when she knows all that I know. Just put your hand in mine, Janet, that I may have the evidence of touch as well as sight to prove your namey, and I will in a few words show you the real state of the case.

13:34:17.080 --> 13:34:34.580
Can you listen to me? Yes, sir. For hours, if you will. I only ask minutes. Jane, did you ever hear or know that I was not the eldest son of my house? That I had once a brother older than I?

13:34:34.580 --> 13:34:47.440
I remember Mrs. Fairfax told me so once. And did you ever hear that my father was an avaricious, grasping man? I have understood something to that effect.

13:34:48.380 --> 13:35:05.460
Well, Jane, being so, it was his resolution to keep the property together. He could not bear the idea of dividing his estate and leaving me a fair portion. All, he resolved, should go to my brother, Rowland.

13:35:06.300 --> 13:35:31.100
Yet as little could he endure that a son of his should be a poor man. I must be provided for by a wealthy marriage. He sought me a partner betimes. Mr. Mason, a West India planter and merchant, was his old acquaintance. He was certain his possessions were real and vast. He made inquiries.

13:35:32.140 --> 13:35:44.940
Mr. Mason, he found, had a son and daughter. And he learned from him that he could and would give the latter a fortune of thirty thousand pounds. That sufficed.

13:35:44.940 --> 13:36:02.760
When I left college, I was sent out to Jamaica to espouse a bride already courted for me. My father said nothing about her money. But he told me Miss Mason was the boast of Spanish town for her beauty. And this was no lie.

13:36:03.620 --> 13:36:28.100
I found her a fine woman in the style of Blanche Ingram, tall, dark and majestic. Her family wished to secure me because I was of a good race. And so did she. They showed her to me in parties splendidly dressed. I seldom saw her alone and had very little private conversation with her.

13:36:28.100 --> 13:36:52.320
She flattered me and lavishly displayed for my pleasure her charms and accomplishments. All the men in her circle seemed to admire her and envy me. I was dazzled, stimulated. My senses were excited. And being ignorant, raw and inexperienced, I thought I loved her.

13:36:53.300 --> 13:37:15.100
There is no folly so besotted that the idiotic rivalries of society, the prurience, the rashness, the blindness of youth, will not hurry a man to its commission. Her relatives encouraged me. Competitors picked me. She alerted me. A marriage was achieved almost before I knew where I was.

13:37:15.100 --> 13:37:35.280
Oh, I have no respect for myself when I think of that act. An agony of inward contempt masters me. I never loved, I never esteemed, I did not even know her. I was not sure of the existence of one virtue in her nature.

13:37:35.280 --> 13:37:56.380
I had marked neither modesty, nor benevolence, nor candour, nor refinement in her mind or manners. And I married her, gross grovelling more like blockhead than I was. With less sin I might have, but let me remember to whom I am speaking.

13:37:57.740 --> 13:38:15.280
My bride's mother I had never seen. I understood she was dead. The honeymoon over, I learned my mistake. She was only mad and shut up in a lunatic asylum. There was a younger brother too, a complete dumb idiot.

13:38:16.120 --> 13:38:39.040
The elder one, whom you have seen, and whom I cannot hate whilst I abhor all his kindred, because he has some grains of affection in his feeble mind, shown in the continued interest he takes in his wretched sister, and also in a dog-like attachment he once bore me, will probably be in the same state one day.

13:38:39.860 --> 13:39:00.720
My father and my brother Roland knew all this, but they thought only of the thirty thousand pounds and joined in the plot against me. These were vile discoveries, but except from the treachery of concealment, I should have made them no subject of reproach to my wife.

13:39:00.720 --> 13:39:24.380
Even when I found her nature wholly alien to mine, her taste obnoxious to me, her cast of mind common, low, narrow, and singularly incapable of being led to anything higher, expended to anything larger, when I found that I could not pass a single evening, nor even a single hour of the day with her in comfort.

13:39:24.380 --> 13:39:37.360
That kindly conversation could not be sustained between us, because whatever topic I started, immediately received from her a turn at once coarse and trite, perverse and imbecile.

13:39:38.140 --> 13:39:56.560
When I perceived that I should never have a quiet or settled household, because no servant would bear the continued outbreaks of her violent and unreasonable temper, or the vexations of her absurd, contradictory, exacting orders, even then I restrained myself.

13:39:56.560 --> 13:40:17.520
I issued a breeding, I curtailed remonstrance. I tried to devour my repentance and disgust in secret. I repressed the deep antipathy I felt. Jane, I will not trouble you with abominable details. Some strong words shall express what I have to say.

13:40:18.480 --> 13:40:40.240
I lived with that woman upstairs four years, and before that time she had tried me indeed. Her character ripened and developed with frightful rapidity. Her vices sprang up fast and rank. They were so strong, only cruelty could check them, and I would not use cruelty.

13:40:40.960 --> 13:41:03.700
What a pygmy intellect she had, and what giant propensities! How fearful were the curses those propensities entailed on me! Bertha Mason, the true daughter of an infamous mother, dragged me through all the hideous and degrading agonies which must attend a man bound to a wife at once intemperate and unchaste.

13:41:05.180 --> 13:41:29.360
My brother in the interval was dead, and at the end of the four years my father died too. I was rich enough now, yet poor to hideous indigence. A nature the most gross, impure, deprave I ever saw was associated with mine, and called by the law and by society a part of me.

13:41:29.360 --> 13:41:42.340
And I could not read myself of it by any legal proceedings, for the doctors now discovered that my wife was mad. Her excesses had prematurely developed the germs of insanity.

13:41:44.080 --> 13:41:51.780
Jane, you don't like my narrative? You look almost sick. Shall I defer the rest to another day?

13:41:52.880 --> 13:42:00.420
No, sir. Finish it now. I pity you. I do pity you.

13:42:01.480 --> 13:42:24.940
Pity, Jane, from some people, is a noxious and insulting sort of tribute, which one is justified in hurling back in the teeth of those who offer it. But that is the sort of pity native to callous, selfish hearts. It is a hybrid egotistical pain at hearing of woes, crossed with ignorant contempt for those who have endured them.

13:42:25.700 --> 13:42:42.780
But that is not your pity, Jane. It is not the feeling of which your whole face is full at this moment, with which your eyes are now almost overflowing, with which your heart is heaving, with which your hand is trembling in mine.

13:42:43.920 --> 13:43:01.560
Your pity, my darling, is the suffering mother of love. Its anguish is the very natal pang of the divine passion. I accept it, Jane. Let the daughter have free advance. My arms wait to receive her.

13:43:03.180 --> 13:43:07.880
Now, sir, proceed. What did you do when you found she was mad?

13:43:09.580 --> 13:43:25.240
Jane, I approached the verge of despair. A remnant of self-respect was all that intervened between me and the girls. In the eyes of the world, I was doubtless covered with grimy dishonour.

13:43:25.240 --> 13:43:36.860
But I resolved to be clean in my own sight, and to the last I repudiated the contamination of her crimes and wrenched myself from connection with her mental defects.

13:43:38.240 --> 13:43:55.740
Still, society associated my name and person with hers. I yet saw her and heard her daily, something of her breath, for mixed with the air I breathed. And besides, I remembered I had once been her husband.

13:43:56.500 --> 13:44:08.860
That recollection was then, and is now, inexpressibly odious to me. Moreover, I knew that while she lived I could never be the husband of another and better wife.

13:44:09.620 --> 13:44:23.500
And though five years my senior, her family and her father had lied to me, even in the particular of her age, she was likely to live as long as I, being as robust in frame as she was in firm in mind.

13:44:23.500 --> 13:44:28.780
Thus, at the age of twenty-six, I was hopeless.

13:44:31.280 --> 13:44:49.080
One night I had been awakened by her yells, since the medical man had pronounced her mad, she had of course been shut up. It was a fiery West Indian night, one of the description that frequently preceded the hurricanes of those climates.

13:44:49.080 --> 13:45:04.780
Being unable to sleep in bed, I got up and opened the window. The air was like sulfur streams. I could find no refreshment anywhere. Mosquitoes came buzzing in and hummed sullenly round the room.

13:45:05.460 --> 13:45:20.760
The sea, which I could hear from thence, rumbled dull like an earthquake. Black clouds were casting up over it. The moon was setting in the waves, broad and red, like a hot cannonball.

13:45:20.760 --> 13:45:36.000
She threw her last bloody glance over a world quivering with a ferment of tempest. I was physically influenced by the atmosphere unseen, and my ears were filled with the curse of a maniac still shrieked out.

13:45:36.000 --> 13:45:59.960
Weren't she momentarily mingled my name with such a tone of demon hate, with such language, no Professor Harlot ever had a foul of vocabulary than she. Though two rooms off, I heard every word, the thin partitions of the West Indian house, opposing but slight obstruction to her wolfish cries.

13:46:01.380 --> 13:46:14.440
This life, said I at last, is hell. This is the air. Those are the sounds of the bottomless pit. I have a right to deliver myself from it if I can.

13:46:15.240 --> 13:46:32.080
The sufferings of this mortal state will leave me with the heavy flesh that now cumbers my soul. Of the fanatic's burning eternity, I have no fear. There is not a future state worse than this present one. Let me break away and go home to God.

13:46:32.880 --> 13:47:00.200
I said this whilst I knelt down it, and unlocked a trunk which contained a brace of loaded pistols. I meant to shoot myself. I only entertain the intention for a moment, for not being insane. The crisis of exquisite and unalloyed despair, which had originated the wish and design of self-destruction, was passed in a second.

13:47:02.080 --> 13:47:17.580
A wind fresh from Europe blew over the ocean and rushed through the open casement. The storm broke, streamed, thundered, blazed, and the air grew pure. I then framed and fixed a resolution.

13:47:18.440 --> 13:47:41.980
While I walked under the dripping orange trees of my wet garden, and amongst its drenched pomegranates and pineapples, and while the refogging dawn of the tropics kindled round me, I reasoned thus Jane. And now listen, for it was true wisdom that consoled me in that hour, and showed me the right path to follow.

13:47:43.160 --> 13:48:05.440
The sweet wind from Europe was still whispering in the refreshed leaves, and the Atlantic was thundering in glorious liberty. My heart, dried up and scorched for a long time, swelled to the tone, and filled with living blood, my being longed for renewal, my soul thirst for a pure draught.

13:48:05.440 --> 13:48:24.040
I saw hope revive, and felt regeneration possible. From a flowery arch at the bottom of my garden, I gazed over the sea, bluer than the sky. The old world was beyond. Clear prospects opened thus.

13:48:25.420 --> 13:48:50.780
Go, said hope, and live again in Europe. There is not known what a solid name you bear, nor that a filthy burden is bound to you. You may take the maniac with you to England, confine her with due attendance and precautions at Thornfield, then travel yourself to what clime you will, and form what new tie you like.

13:48:51.620 --> 13:49:13.960
That woman who has so abused your longsuffering, so sullied your name, so outraged your honour, so blighted your youth, is not your wife, nor are you her husband. See that she is scared for as her condition demands, and you have done all that God and humanity requires of you.

13:49:13.960 --> 13:49:31.940
Let her identity, her connection with yourself, be buried in oblivion. You are bound to impart them to no living being. Place her in safety and comfort. Shelter her degradation with secrecy, and leave her.

13:49:33.100 --> 13:49:56.720
I acted precisely on this suggestion. My father and brother had not made my marriage known to their acquaintance, because in the very first letter I wrote to apprise them of the Union, having already begun to experience extreme disgust of its consequences, and from the family character and constitution seeing a hideous future opening to me,

13:49:56.720 --> 13:50:16.160
I added an urgent charge to keep it secret, and very soon the infamous conduct of the wife my father had selected for me was such as to make him blush to own her as his daughter-in-law. Far from desiring to publish the connection, he became as anxious to conceal it as myself.

13:50:17.560 --> 13:50:41.200
To England, then, I conveyed her. A fearful voyage I had, with such a monster in the vessel. Glad was I, when I at last got her to Thornfield, and saw her safely lodged in that third-story room, of whose secret in a cabinet she has now for ten years made a wild beast stand, a goblin's cell.

13:50:42.000 --> 13:51:04.100
I had some trouble in finding an attendant for her, as it was necessary to select one on whose fidelity dependence could be placed, for her ravings would inevitably betray my secret. Besides, she had lucid intervals of days, sometimes weeks, which she filled up with abuse of me.

13:51:04.880 --> 13:51:28.080
At last I hired Grace Poole from the Grimsby retreat. She and the surgeon, Carter, who dressed Mason's wounds that night he was stabbed and worried, are the only two I have ever admitted to my confidence. Mrs Fairfax may indeed have suspected something, but she could have gained no precise knowledge as to facts.

13:51:30.340 --> 13:51:48.320
Grace has, on the whole, proved a good keeper, though owing partly to a fault of her own, of which it appears nothing can cure her, and which is incident to her harassing profession. Her vigilance has been more than once lulled and baffled.

13:51:49.180 --> 13:52:08.300
The lunatic is both cunning and malignant. She has never failed to take advantage of her guardian's temporary lapses, once to secret the knife with which she stabbed her brother, and twice to possess herself of the key of her cell, an issue therefrom in the night-time.

13:52:09.020 --> 13:52:31.300
On the first of these occasions, she perpetrated the attempt to burn me in my bed. On the second, she paid that ghastly visit to you. I thank Providence, who watched over you, that she then spent her fury on your wedding apparel, which perhaps brought back vague reminiscences of her own bridal days.

13:52:32.220 --> 13:52:48.100
But on what might have happened, I cannot endure to reflect. When I think of the thing which flew at my throat this morning, hanging its black and scarlet visage over the nest of my dove, my blood curdles.

13:52:49.960 --> 13:52:58.020
And what, sir, I asked while he paused, did you do when you had settled her here? Where did you go?

13:52:59.140 --> 13:53:16.440
What did I do, Jane? I transformed myself into a willow-the-wisp. Where did I go? I pursued wanderings as wild as those of the March Spirit. I saw the continent, and went devious through all its lands.

13:53:17.160 --> 13:53:27.760
My fixed desire was to seek and find a good and intelligent woman whom I could love, a contrast to the fury I left at Thornfield.

13:53:29.000 --> 13:53:30.760
But you could not marry, sir.

13:53:30.760 --> 13:53:41.220
I had determined and was convinced that I could and ought. It was not my original intention to deceive, as I have deceived you.

13:53:41.220 --> 13:54:02.460
I meant to tell my tale plainly and make my proposals openly, and it appeared to me so absolutely rational that I should be considered free to love and be loved. I never doubted some woman might be found willing and able to understand my case and accept it, in spite of the curse with which I was burdened.

13:54:03.280 --> 13:54:04.120
Well, sir?

13:54:05.100 --> 13:54:21.860
When you are inquisitive, Jane, you always make me smile. You open your eyes like an eager bird and make every now and then a restless movement, as if answers in speech did not flow fast enough for you and you wanted to read the tablet of one's heart.

13:54:21.860 --> 13:54:39.140
But before I go on, tell me what you mean by your, well, sir? It is a small phrase, very frequent with you, and which many a time has drawn me on and on through interminable talk. I don't very well know why.

13:54:40.100 --> 13:54:57.040
I mean, what next? How did you proceed? What came of such an event? Precisely. And what do you wish to know now? Whether you found anyone you liked? Whether you asked her to marry you? And what she said?

13:54:58.520 --> 13:55:09.180
I can tell you whether I found anyone I liked and whether I asked her to marry me, but what she said is yet to be recorded in the Book of Fate.

13:55:10.520 --> 13:55:32.880
For ten long years I roved about, living first in one capital, then another. Sometimes in St. Petersburg, oftener in Paris, occasionally in Rome, Naples and Florence. Provided with plenty of money and the passport of an old name, I could choose my own society.

13:55:32.880 --> 13:56:01.640
No circles were closed against me. I sought my ideal of a woman amongst English ladies, French countesses, Italian signoras and German graffiton. I could not find her. Sometimes, for a fleeting moment, I thought I caught a glance, heard a tone, beheld a form which announced the realization of my dream. But I was presently undeceived.

13:56:02.300 --> 13:56:30.460
You are not to suppose that I desired perfection, either of mind or person. I longed only for what suited me, for the antipodes of the Creole, and I longed vainly. Amongst them all, I found not one whom, had I been ever so free, I warned as I was of the risks, the horrors, the loathings of incongruous unions, would have asked to marry me.

13:56:31.520 --> 13:56:55.920
Disappointment made me reckless. I tried dissipation, never debauchery, that I hated and hate. That was my Indian miscellaneous attribute. Rooted disgust at it and her restrained me much, even in pleasure. An enjoyment that bordered on riots seemed to approach me to her and her vices, and I eschewed it.

13:56:56.620 --> 13:57:15.620
Yet I could not live alone, so I tried the companionship of mistresses. The first I chose was Céline Varan, another of those steps which made a man spurn himself when he recalls them. You already know what she was, and how my liaison with her terminated.

13:57:15.620 --> 13:57:35.040
She had two successors, an Italian, Jacinta, and a German, Clara, both considered singularly handsome. What was their beauty to me in a few weeks? Jacinta was unprincipled and violent. I tired of her in three months.

13:57:35.820 --> 13:58:00.380
Clara was honest and quiet, but heavy, mindless, and unimpressible. Not one whit to my taste. I was glad to give her a sufficient sum to set her up in a good line of business, and so get decently rid of her. But Jane, I see by your face you are not forming a very favorable opinion of me just now.

13:58:01.700 --> 13:58:21.340
You think me an unfeeling loose principal, Rick, don't you? I don't like you so well as I have done sometimes, indeed, sir. Did it not seem to you in the least wrong to live in that way, first with one mistress, then another? You talk of it as a mere matter of cause.

13:58:22.020 --> 13:58:46.280
It was with me, and I did not like it. It was a grovelling fashion of existence. I should never like to return to it. Hiring a mistress is the next worth thing to buying a slave. Both are often by nature and always by position inferior, and to live familiarly with inferiors is degrading.

13:58:46.280 --> 13:58:51.700
I now hate the recollection of the time I passed with Celine, Jacinta, and Clara.

13:58:53.160 --> 13:59:21.260
I felt the truth of these words, and I drew from them the certain inference that if I were so far to forget myself and all the teachings that had ever been instilled into me, as under any pretext, with any justification, through any temptation, to become the successor of these poor girls, he would one day regard me with the same feeling which now in his mind desecrated their memory.

13:59:21.920 --> 13:59:34.720
I did not give utterance to this conviction. It was enough to feel it. I impressed it on my heart that it might remain there to serve me as aid in the time of trial.

13:59:36.080 --> 13:59:41.180
Now, Jane, why don't you say, well, sir, I have not done?

13:59:42.820 --> 13:59:49.740
You are looking grave. You disapprove of me still, I see. But let me come to the point.

13:59:51.020 --> 14:00:14.380
Last January, rid of all mistresses, in a harsh bitter frame of mind, the result of a useless, roving, lonely life, corroded with disappointment, sourly disposed against all men, and especially against all womankind, for I began to regard the notion of an intellectual, faithful, loving woman as a mere dream.

14:00:14.380 --> 14:00:30.300
Recalled by business, I came back to England. On a frosty winter afternoon, I rode inside of Thornfield Hall, a bored spot. I expected no peace, no pleasure there.

14:00:31.160 --> 14:00:55.060
On a stile in Hay Lane, I saw a quiet little figure sitting by itself. I passed it, as negligently as I did the polluted willow opposite to it. I had no presentiment of what it would be to me, no inward warning that the arbitrest of my life, my genius for good or evil, waited there in humble guise.

14:00:55.060 --> 14:01:14.000
I did not know it, even when, on the occasion of Mithril's accident, it came up and gravely offered me help. Childish and slander creature. It seemed as if a lynet had hopped to my foot and proposed to bear me on its tiny wing. I was surly.

14:01:14.000 --> 14:01:27.480
But the thing would not go. It stood by me with strange perseverance, and looked and spoke with a sort of authority. I must be aided, and by that hand, and aided I was.

14:01:28.380 --> 14:01:53.400
When once I had pressed the frail shoulder, something new, a fresh sap and scents, stole into my frame. It was well I had learned that this elf must return to me, that it belonged to my house down below. Or I could not have felt it pass away from under my hand, and seen it vanish behind the dim hedge, without singular regret.

14:01:54.180 --> 14:02:10.900
I heard you come home that night, Jane, though probably you were not aware that I thought of you, or watched for you. The next day, I observed you, myself unseen, for half an hour, while you played with Adele in the gallery.

14:02:11.500 --> 14:02:23.200
It was a snowy day, I recollect, and you could not go out of doors. I was in my room. The door was ajar. I could both listen and watch.

14:02:24.340 --> 14:02:45.840
Adele claimed your outward attention for a while, yet I fancied your thoughts were elsewhere. But you were very patient with our my little Jane. You talked to her and amused her a long time. When at last she left you, you lapsed at once into deep reverie. You betook yourself slowly to pace the gallery.

14:02:46.600 --> 14:03:13.780
Now and then, in passing a casement, you glanced out at the thick falling snow. You listened to the subbing wind, and again you paced gently on and dreamt. I think those day visions were not dark. There was a pleasurable illumination in your eye occasionally, a soft excitement in your aspect, which told of no bitter, bilious, hypochondriac pruding.

14:03:14.660 --> 14:03:30.560
Your look revealed rather the sweet musings of youth, when its spirit follows on willing wings the flight of hope up and on to an ideal heaven. The voice of Mrs Fairfax, speaking to a servant in the hall, wakened you.

14:03:30.560 --> 14:03:51.220
And how curiously you smiled to and at yourself, Janet. There was much sense in your smile. It was very shrewd, and seemed to make light of your own abstraction. It seemed to say, My fine visions are all very well. But I must not forget they are absolutely unreal.

14:03:51.220 --> 14:04:06.520
I have a rosy sky and a green flowery Eden in my brain, but without, I am perfectly aware, lies at my feet a rough track to travel, and around me gather black tempests to encounter.

14:04:07.440 --> 14:04:27.580
You ran downstairs and demanded of Mrs Fairfax some occupation. The weekly house accounts to make up, or something of that sort, I think it was. I was vexed with you for getting out of my sight. Impatiently I waited for evening, when I might summon you to my presence.

14:04:27.580 --> 14:04:48.760
An unusual, to me, a perfectly new character I suspected was yours. I desired to search deeper and know it better. You entered the room with a look and air at once shy and independent. You were quaintly dressed, much as you are now.

14:04:48.760 --> 14:05:15.220
I made you talk. Here long I found you full of strange contrasts. Your garb and manner were restricted by rule. Your air was often diffident, and altogether that of one refined by nature, but absolutely unused to society, and a good deal afraid of making herself disadvantageously conspicuous by some solicism or blunder.

14:05:16.140 --> 14:05:33.840
Yet, when addressed, you lifted a keen, a daring, and a glowing eye to your interlocutus face. There was penetration and power in each glance you gave. When plied by close questions, you found ready and round answers.

14:05:34.620 --> 14:05:49.060
Very soon you seemed to get used to me. I believe you felt the existence of sympathy between you and your dream and crossmaster, Jane, for it was astonishing to see how quickly a certain pleasant ease tranquilized your manner.

14:05:49.820 --> 14:06:14.380
Snarl as I would, you showed no surprise, fear, annoyance, or displeasure at my morose-ness. You watched me, and now and then smiled at me with a simple, yet sagacious grace I cannot describe. I was at once content and stimulated with what I saw. I liked what I had seen and wished to see more.

14:06:15.440 --> 14:06:30.640
Yet, for a long time, I treated you distantly and sought your company rarely. I was an intellectual epicure, and wished to prolong the gratification of making this novel and picket acquaintance.

14:06:31.620 --> 14:06:43.980
Besides, I was for a while troubled with the haunting fear that, if I handled the flower freely, its bloom would fade. The sweet charm of freshness would leave it.

14:06:43.980 --> 14:06:55.300
I did not then know that it was no transitory blossom, but rather the radiant resemblance of one, cut in an indestructible gem.

14:06:56.420 --> 14:07:17.900
Moreover, I wished to see whether you would seek me if I shunned you, but you did not. You kept in the schoolroom as still as your own desk and easel. If by chance I met you, you passed me as soon and with as little token of recognition as was consistent with respect.

14:07:17.900 --> 14:07:33.460
Your habitual expression in those days, Jane, was a thoughtful look. Not despondent, for you were not sickly, but not buoyant, for you had little hope and no actual pleasure.

14:07:34.720 --> 14:07:57.720
I wondered what you thought of me, or if you ever thought of me. To find this out, I resumed my notice of you. There was something glad in your glance and genial in your manner when you conversed. I saw you had a social heart. It was the silent schoolroom. It was the tedium of your life that made you mournful.

14:07:58.620 --> 14:08:15.400
I permitted myself the delight of being kind to you. Kindness stirred emotion soon. Your face became soft in expression. Your tones gentle. I liked my name pronounced by your lips in a grateful, happy accent.

14:08:16.320 --> 14:08:37.180
I used to enjoy a chance meeting with you, Jane, at this time. There was a curious hesitation in your manner. You glanced at me with a slight trouble, a hovering doubt. You did not know what my caprice might be, whether I was going to play the master and be stern, or the friend and be benignant.

14:08:37.180 --> 14:08:54.740
I was now too fond of you often to stimulate the first whim, and, when I stretched my hand out cordially, such bloom and light and bliss rose to your young, wistful features. I had much adore often, to avoid straining you then and there to my heart.

14:08:55.840 --> 14:09:16.320
Don't talk any more of those days, sir," I interrupted, furtively dashing away some tears from my eyes. His language was torture to me. For I knew what I must do, and do soon, and all these reminiscences and these revelations of his feelings only made my work more difficult.

14:09:17.220 --> 14:09:31.760
No, Jane, he returned. What necessity is there to dwell on the past, when the present is so much surer, the future so much brighter? I shuddered to hear the infatuated assertion.

14:09:32.880 --> 14:09:52.160
You see now how the case stands, do you not? he continued. After a youth and manhood passed half in unutterable misery and half in dreary solitude, I have, for the first time, found what I can truly love. I have found you.

14:09:53.080 --> 14:10:09.560
You are my sympathy, my better self, my good angel. I am bound to you with a strong attachment. I think you good, gifted, lovely. A fervent, a solemn passion is conceived in my heart.

14:10:09.560 --> 14:10:22.960
It leans to you, draws you to my center and spring of life, wraps my existence about you, and kindling in pure, powerful flame, fuses you and me in one.

14:10:24.000 --> 14:10:44.460
It was because I felt and knew this that I resolved to marry you. To tell me that I had already a wife is empty mockery. You know now that I had but a hideous demon. I was wrong to attempt to deceive you, but I feared a stubbornness that exists in your character.

14:10:44.460 --> 14:11:02.980
I feared early instilled prejudice. I wanted to have you safe before hazarding conferences. This was cowardly. I should have appealed to your nobleness and magnanimity at first, as I do now, opened to you plainly my life of agony,

14:11:02.980 --> 14:11:20.220
described to you my hunger and thirst after a higher and worthier existence, shown to you not my resolution, that word is weak, but my resistless bent to love faithfully and well, where I am faithfully and well loved in return.

14:11:21.300 --> 14:11:29.160
Then I should have asked you to accept my pledge of fidelity and to give me yours. Jane, give it me now.

14:11:30.240 --> 14:11:31.360
A pause.

14:11:32.740 --> 14:11:34.520
Why are you silent, Jane?

14:11:35.500 --> 14:11:58.800
I was experiencing an ordeal. A hand of fiery iron crossed my vitals. A terrible moment, full of struggle, blackness, burning. Not a human being that ever lived could wish to be loved better than I was loved, and him who thus loved me I absolutely worshipped, and I must renounce love and idol.

14:11:58.800 --> 14:12:04.640
One gray word comprised my intolerable duty. Depart.

14:12:06.160 --> 14:12:09.540
Jane, you understand what I want of you?

14:12:10.580 --> 14:12:14.280
Just this promise. I will be yours, Mr. Rochester.

14:12:16.700 --> 14:12:20.400
Mr. Rochester, I will not be yours.

14:12:22.160 --> 14:12:23.480
Another long silence.

14:12:25.080 --> 14:12:36.560
Jane, recommends he, with a gentleness that broke me down with grief and turned me stone cold with ominous terror for this still voice with the pant of a lion rising.

14:12:37.400 --> 14:12:42.580
Jane, do you mean to go one way in the world and to let me go another?

14:12:43.860 --> 14:12:44.640
I do.

14:12:45.600 --> 14:12:50.320
Jane, bending towards me and embracing me, do you mean it now?

14:12:51.320 --> 14:12:52.240
I do.

14:12:52.240 --> 14:12:54.220
And now?

14:12:54.960 --> 14:13:02.000
Softly kissing my forehead and cheek. I do, extricating myself from restraint rapidly and completely.

14:13:03.020 --> 14:13:10.640
Oh, Jane, this is bitter. This is wicked. It would not be wicked to love me.

14:13:12.000 --> 14:13:13.420
It would to obey you.

14:13:14.300 --> 14:13:21.120
A wide look raised his brows, crossed his features. He rose, but he forbore yet.

14:13:21.980 --> 14:13:29.160
I laid my hand on the back of a chair for support. I shook. I feared. But I resolved.

14:13:30.400 --> 14:13:39.740
One instant, Jane. Give one glance to my horrible life when you are gone. All happiness will be torn away with you. What then is left?

14:13:40.340 --> 14:13:47.380
For a wife I have but the maniac upstairs. As well might you refer me to some corpse in yonder churchyard.

14:13:48.500 --> 14:13:53.240
What shall I do, Jane? Where turn for a companion and for some hope?

14:13:54.840 --> 14:14:02.720
Do as I do. Trust in God and yourself. Believe in heaven. Hope to meet again there.

14:14:03.700 --> 14:14:05.340
Then you shall not yield?

14:14:06.600 --> 14:14:07.000
No.

14:14:07.820 --> 14:14:12.600
Then you condemn me to live wretched and to die accursed? His voice rose.

14:14:13.800 --> 14:14:17.720
I advise you to live sinless, and I wish you to die tranquil.

14:14:18.820 --> 14:14:26.000
Then you snatch love and innocence from me? You fling me back on lust for a passion? Vice for an occupation?

14:14:27.580 --> 14:14:33.480
Mr. Rochester, I no more assign this fate to you than I grasp at it for myself.

14:14:34.140 --> 14:14:43.800
We were born to strive and endure. You as well as I. Do so. You will forget me before I forget you.

14:14:44.980 --> 14:14:54.680
You make me a liar by such language. You sully my honor. I declared I could not change. You tell me to my face I shall change soon.

14:14:54.680 --> 14:15:01.400
And what a distortion in your judgment! What a perversity in your ideas is proved by your conduct!

14:15:02.400 --> 14:15:10.280
Is it better to drive a fellow creature to despair than to transgress a mere human law, no man being injured by the breach?

14:15:11.560 --> 14:15:17.280
For you have neither relatives nor acquaintances whom you need fear to offend by living with me.

14:15:17.940 --> 14:15:28.400
This was true. And while he spoke, my very conscience and reason turned traitors against me, and charged me with crime in resisting him.

14:15:29.420 --> 14:15:33.740
They spoke almost as loud as feeling, and that claimed widely.

14:15:34.880 --> 14:15:44.160
O comply, it said! Think of his misery! Think of his danger! Look at his state when left alone!

14:15:44.940 --> 14:15:58.420
Remember his headlong nature! Consider the recklessness following on despair! Soothe him! Save him! Love him! Tell him you love him and will be his!

14:15:59.460 --> 14:16:04.280
Who in the world cares for you? Or who will be injured by what you do?

14:16:05.280 --> 14:16:08.460
Still, indomitable was the reply.

14:16:09.360 --> 14:16:19.200
I care for myself. The more solitary, the more friendless, the more unsustained I am, the more I will respect myself.

14:16:20.220 --> 14:16:30.580
I will keep the law given by God, sanctioned by man. I will hold to the principles received by me when I was sane and not mad, as I am now.

14:16:31.320 --> 14:16:42.340
Laws and principles are not for times when there is no temptation. They are for such moments as this, when body and soul rise in mutiny against their rigor.

14:16:43.280 --> 14:16:52.220
Stringent are they, inviolate they shall be. If at my individual convenience I might break them, what would be their worth?

14:16:52.920 --> 14:17:08.220
They have a worth, so I have always believed, and if I cannot believe it now, it is because I am insane, quite insane, with my veins running fire and my heart beating faster than I can count its throbs.

14:17:09.940 --> 14:17:18.680
Preconceived opinions, foregone determinations are all I have at this hour to stand by. There I plant my foot.

14:17:20.240 --> 14:17:21.440
I did.

14:17:22.680 --> 14:17:34.160
Mr. Rochester, reading my countenance, saw I had done so. His fury was wrought to the highest. He must yield to it for a moment, whatever followed.

14:17:34.160 --> 14:17:42.420
He crossed the floor and seized my arm and grasped my waist. He seemed to devour me with his flaming glance.

14:17:43.780 --> 14:17:50.200
Physically, I felt at the moment, powerless as stubble exposed to the draught and glow of a furnace.

14:17:51.460 --> 14:17:57.900
Mentally, I still possessed my soul, and with it the certainty of ultimate safety.

14:17:58.760 --> 14:18:07.660
The soul, fortunately, has an interpreter, often an unconscious but still a faithful interpreter, in the eye.

14:18:08.760 --> 14:18:21.140
My eye rose to his, and while I looked in his fierce face, I gave an involuntary sigh. His grip was painful, and my overtaxed strength almost exhausted.

14:18:22.540 --> 14:18:33.260
Never, said he, as he ground his teeth, never was anything at once so frail and so indomitable, a mere reed she feels in my hand.

14:18:34.000 --> 14:18:45.220
And he shook me with the force of his hold. I could bend her with my finger and thumb, and what good would it do if I bent, if I upstore, if I crushed her?

14:18:45.220 --> 14:18:56.820
Consider that eye. Consider the resolute, wild, frithing, looking out of it. Define me with more than courage, with a stern triumph.

14:18:58.200 --> 14:19:12.160
Whatever I do with its cage, I cannot get at it, the savage, beautiful creature. If I tear, if I rend the slight prison, my outrage will only let the captive lose.

14:19:13.040 --> 14:19:21.900
Conqueror I might be of the house, but the inmate would escape to heaven before I could call myself possessor of its clay-dwelling place.

14:19:22.960 --> 14:19:32.760
And it is you, spirit, with will and energy and virtue and purity that I want, not alone your brittle frame.

14:19:33.740 --> 14:19:47.480
Of yourself, you could come with soft flight and nestle against my heart if you would. Seized against your will, you will elude the grasp like an essence. You will vanish ere I inhale your fragrance.

14:19:48.660 --> 14:19:51.380
Oh, come, Jane, come!

14:19:52.620 --> 14:20:06.620
As he said this, he released me from his clutch and only looked at me. The look was far worse to resist than the frantic strain. Only an idiot, however, would have succumbed to now.

14:20:07.580 --> 14:20:14.320
I had dared and baffled his fury. I must elude his sorrow. I retired to the door.

14:20:15.580 --> 14:20:17.140
You are going, Jane?

14:20:18.560 --> 14:20:19.700
I am going, sir.

14:20:20.880 --> 14:20:22.160
You are leaving me?

14:20:23.460 --> 14:20:23.960
Yes.

14:20:25.160 --> 14:20:36.420
You will not come? You will not be my comforter, my rescuer? My deep love, my wild woe, my frantic prayer are all nothing to you?

14:20:37.520 --> 14:20:44.980
What an unutterable pathos was in his voice! How hard it was to reiterate firmly, I am going.

14:20:45.920 --> 14:20:48.360
Jane! Mr. Rochester!

14:20:49.960 --> 14:21:05.440
Withdraw then, I consent. But remember, you leave me here in anguish. Go up to your own room. Think over all I have said. And, Jane, cast a glance on my sufferings. Think of me.

14:21:06.700 --> 14:21:10.780
He turned away. He threw himself on his face on the sofa.

14:21:10.780 --> 14:21:17.200
Oh, Jane! My hope! My love! My life!

14:21:17.200 --> 14:21:32.540
Broken anguish from his lips. Then came a deep, strong sob. I had already gained the door. But, reader, I walked back. Walked back as determinedly as I had retreated.

14:21:33.380 --> 14:21:42.980
I knelt down by him. I turned his face from the cushion to me. I kissed his cheek. I smoothed his hair with my hand.

14:21:44.320 --> 14:21:56.420
God bless you, my dear master, I said. God keep you from harm and wrong. Direct you, soulless you. Reward you well for your past kindness to me.

14:21:58.140 --> 14:22:05.240
Little Jane's love would have been my best reward, he answered. Without it, my heart is broken.

14:22:05.960 --> 14:22:12.000
But Jane will give me her love. Yes, nobly, generously.

14:22:14.000 --> 14:22:27.820
Up the blood rushed to his face. Fourth flashed the fire from his eyes. Erect his prank. He held his arms out. But I evaded the embrace and at once quitted the room.

14:22:29.420 --> 14:22:36.140
Farewell was the cry of my heart as I left him. Despair added. Farewell forever.

14:22:40.360 --> 14:22:50.380
That night I never thought to sleep. But a slumber fell on me as soon as I lay down in bed. I was transported in thought to the scenes of childhood.

14:22:51.420 --> 14:22:59.220
I dreamt I lay in the red room at Gatehead. That the night was dark and my mind impressed with strange fears.

14:22:59.980 --> 14:23:11.640
The light that long ago had struck me into syncope, recalled in this vision, seemed glidingly to mount the wall and tremingly to pause in the centre of the obscured ceiling.

14:23:12.700 --> 14:23:23.220
I lifted up my head to look. The roof resolved to clouds, high and dim. The gleam was such as the moon imparts to vapours she is about to sever.

14:23:23.940 --> 14:23:33.640
I watched her come. Watched with the strangest anticipation, as though some word of doom were to be written on her disk.

14:23:34.980 --> 14:23:43.940
She broke forth as never moon yet burst from cloud. A hand first penetrated the sable folds and waved them away.

14:23:43.940 --> 14:23:52.040
Then, not a moon, but a white human form shone in the azure, inclining a glorious brow earthward.

14:23:53.080 --> 14:24:03.960
It gazed and gazed on me. It spoke to my spirit. Immeasurably distant was the tone, yet so near. It whispered in my heart.

14:24:03.960 --> 14:24:08.180
My daughter, flea-demptation.

14:24:09.320 --> 14:24:10.640
Mother, I will.

14:24:11.740 --> 14:24:15.440
So I answered after I had waked from the trance-like dream.

14:24:16.500 --> 14:24:23.600
It was yet night, but July nights are short. Soon after midnight, dawn comes.

14:24:25.520 --> 14:24:30.020
It cannot be too early to commence the task I have to fulfil, thought I.

14:24:30.020 --> 14:24:36.040
I rose. I was dressed, for I had taken off nothing but my shoes.

14:24:37.140 --> 14:24:41.480
I knew where to find in my drawers some linen, a locket, a ring.

14:24:42.520 --> 14:24:50.740
In seeking these articles, I encountered the beads of a pearl necklace Mr. Rochester had forced me to accept a few days ago.

14:24:51.700 --> 14:24:58.120
I left that. It was not mine. It was the visionary bride who had melted in air.

14:24:58.880 --> 14:25:07.780
The other articles I made up in a parcel. My purse, containing twenty shillings, it was all I had, I put in my pocket.

14:25:08.640 --> 14:25:18.020
I tied on my straw bonnet, pinned my shawl, took the parcel and my slippers, which I would not put on yet, and stole from my room.

14:25:19.960 --> 14:25:24.380
Farewell, kind Mrs Fairfax, I whispered, as I glided past her door.

14:25:25.320 --> 14:25:29.940
Farewell, my darling Adele, I said, as I glanced towards the nursery.

14:25:31.040 --> 14:25:34.240
No thought could be admitted of entering to embrace her.

14:25:35.160 --> 14:25:41.100
I had to deceive a fine ear, for, ought I knew, it might now be listening.

14:25:42.060 --> 14:25:53.420
I would have got past Mr. Rochester's chamber without a pause, but my heart, momentarily stopping its speed at that threshold, my foot was forced to stop also.

14:25:54.440 --> 14:26:03.840
No sleep was there. The inmate was walking restlessly from wall to wall, and again and again he sighed while I listened.

14:26:05.020 --> 14:26:09.900
There was a heaven, a temporary heaven in this room for me if I chose.

14:26:10.820 --> 14:26:17.840
I had but to go in and to say, Mr. Rochester, I will love you and live with you through life till death.

14:26:18.620 --> 14:26:23.580
And a fount of rapture would spring to my lips. I thought of this.

14:26:25.060 --> 14:26:30.460
That kind master, who could not sleep now, was waiting with impatience for day.

14:26:31.380 --> 14:26:38.240
He would send for me in the morning. I should be gone. He would have me sought for, vainly.

14:26:38.880 --> 14:26:46.080
He would feel himself forsaken, his love rejected, he would suffer, perhaps cruel desperate.

14:26:46.780 --> 14:26:55.220
I thought of this, too. My hand moved towards the lock. I caught it back and glided on.

14:26:56.960 --> 14:27:03.580
Drarily I wound my way downstairs. I knew what I had to do, and I did it mechanically.

14:27:04.720 --> 14:27:11.520
I sought the key of the side door in the kitchen. I sought, too, a file of oil and a feather.

14:27:12.260 --> 14:27:21.040
I hold the key and the lock. I got some water. I got some bread, for perhaps I should have to walk far.

14:27:21.780 --> 14:27:29.220
And my strength, sorely shaken of late, must not break down. All this I did without one sound.

14:27:30.320 --> 14:27:37.060
I opened the door, passed out, shut it softly. Dim dawn glimmered in the yard.

14:27:37.780 --> 14:27:43.260
The great gates were closed and locked, but a wicket in one of them was only latched.

14:27:44.420 --> 14:27:51.300
Through that I departed. It, too, I shut, and now I was out of Thornfield.

14:27:53.920 --> 14:28:00.640
A mile off, beyond the field, lay a road which stretched in the contrary direction to Millcote.

14:28:01.380 --> 14:28:07.740
A road I had never travelled, but often noticed and wanted where it led.

14:28:08.640 --> 14:28:13.380
The other I bent my steps. No reflection was to be allowed now.

14:28:14.060 --> 14:28:18.120
Not one glance was to be cast back, not even one forward.

14:28:19.360 --> 14:28:23.000
Not one thought was to be given either to the past or the future.

14:28:23.000 --> 14:28:33.000
The first was a page so heavenly sweet, so deadly sad, that to read one line of it would dissolve my courage and break down my energy.

14:28:34.180 --> 14:28:40.360
The last was an awful blank, something like the world when the deluge was gone by.

14:28:41.980 --> 14:28:48.780
I skirted fields and hedges and lanes till after sunrise. I believe it was a lovely summer morning.

14:28:49.340 --> 14:28:54.520
I knew my shoes, which I had put on when I left the house, were soon wet with the dew.

14:28:55.660 --> 14:29:01.080
But I looked neither to rising sun, nor smiling sky, nor wakening nature.

14:29:02.380 --> 14:29:11.720
He who is taken out to pass through a fair scene to the scaffold, thinks not of the flowers that smile on his road, but of the block and axe edge,

14:29:11.720 --> 14:29:21.260
of the deserviment of bone and vein, of the grave gaping at the end, and I thought of queer flight and homeless wandering.

14:29:22.340 --> 14:29:25.920
And oh, with agony I thought of what I left.

14:29:27.680 --> 14:29:38.300
I could not help it. I thought of him now, in his room, watching the sunrise, hoping I should soon come to say I would stay with him and be his.

14:29:38.300 --> 14:29:48.340
I longed to be his. I pant to return. It was not too late. I could yet spare him the bitter pang of bereavement.

14:29:49.800 --> 14:30:00.540
As yet my flight, I was sure, was undiscovered. I could go back and be his comforter, his pride, his redeemer from misery, perhaps from ruin.

14:30:01.180 --> 14:30:08.540
Oh, that fear of his self-abandonment, far worse than my abandonment, how it goaded me.

14:30:09.760 --> 14:30:19.660
It was a barbed arrowhead in my breast. It tore me when I tried to extract it. It sickened me when remembrance thrust it farther in.

14:30:20.980 --> 14:30:28.800
Birds began singing in break and cobs. Birds were faithful to their mates. Birds were emblems of love.

14:30:28.800 --> 14:30:37.120
What was I? In the midst of my pain of heart and frantic effort of principle, I abhorred myself.

14:30:38.100 --> 14:30:51.400
I had no solace from self-approbation, none even from self-respect. I had injured, wounded, left my master. I was hateful in my own eyes.

14:30:52.200 --> 14:30:58.300
Still I could not turn, nor retrace one step. God must have led me on.

14:30:59.620 --> 14:31:06.140
As to my own will or conscience, impassioned grief had trampled one and stifled the other.

14:31:07.220 --> 14:31:14.200
I was weeping widely as I walked along my solitary way. Fast, fast I went like one delirious.

14:31:15.200 --> 14:31:21.640
A weakness, beginning inwardly, extending to my limbs, seized me and I fell.

14:31:22.540 --> 14:31:31.860
I lay on the ground some minutes, pressing my face to the wet turf. I had some fear, or hope, that here I should die.

14:31:32.620 --> 14:31:42.260
But I was soon up, crawling forwards on my hands and knees, and then again raised to my feet, as eager and as determined as ever to reach the road.

14:31:43.440 --> 14:31:52.780
When I got there, I was forced to sit to rest me under the hedge. And while I sat, I heard wheels and saw a coach come on.

14:31:53.660 --> 14:31:56.780
I stood up and lifted my hand. It stopped.

14:31:58.200 --> 14:32:06.280
I asked where it was going. The driver named the place along way off, and where I was sure Mr. Rochester had no connections.

14:32:06.900 --> 14:32:14.640
I asked for what sum he would take me there. He said thirty shillings. I answered I had but twenty.

14:32:15.660 --> 14:32:23.620
Well, he would try to make it due. He further gave me leave to get into the inside, as the vehicle was empty.

14:32:24.460 --> 14:32:28.300
I entered, was shut in, and it rolled on its way.

14:32:30.280 --> 14:32:40.980
Gentle reader, may you never feel what I then felt. May your eyes never shed such stormy, scolding, heart-wrenching tears as poured from mine.

14:32:42.300 --> 14:32:56.120
May you never appeal to heaven in prayers so hopeless and so agonized as in that hour left my lips. For never may you, like me, dread to be the instrument of evil to what you wholly love.

14:33:00.520 --> 14:33:17.200
CHAPTER XXVIII JANE AYRE

14:33:27.560 --> 14:33:46.940
Two days have passed. It is a summer evening. The coachman has set me down at a place called White Cross. He could take me no farther for the sum I had given, and I was not possessed of another shilling in the world. The coach is a mile off by this time. I am alone.

14:33:46.940 --> 14:34:03.160
At this moment I discover that I forgot to take my parcel out of the pocket of the coach, where I had placed it for safety. There it remains. There it must remain. And now I am absolutely destitute.

14:34:03.800 --> 14:34:30.020
White Cross is no town, nor even a hamlet. It is but a stone pillar set up where four roads meet, whitewashed, I suppose, to be more obvious at a distance and in darkness. Four arms spring from its summit, the nearest town to which these point is, according to the inscription, distant ten miles, the farthest above twenty.

14:34:30.660 --> 14:34:52.400
From the well-known names of these towns I learn in what county I have lighted. A North Midland Shire, dusk with moorland, rigid with mountain. This I see. There are great moors behind and on each hand of me. There are waves of mountains far beyond that deep valley at my feet.

14:34:53.200 --> 14:35:12.500
The population here must be thin, and I see no passengers on these roads. They stretch out east, west, north and south-wide. Broad and lonely, they are all cut in the moor, and the heather grows deep and wild to their very verge.

14:35:13.340 --> 14:35:34.500
Yet a chance traveller might pass by, and I wish no eye to see me now. Strangers would wonder what I am doing, lingering here at the signpost, evidently objectless and lost. I might be questioned, I could give no answer, but what would sound incredible and excite suspicion?

14:35:35.460 --> 14:35:57.680
Not a tie holds me to human society at this moment. Not a charm or hope calls me where my fellow creatures are. None that saw me would have a kind thought or a good wish for me. I have no relative but the Universal Mother. Noture, I will seek her breast and ask repose.

14:35:58.640 --> 14:36:25.200
I struck straight into the heath. I held onto a hollow I saw deeply, furrowing the brown moor side. I waded knee-deep in its dark growth. I turned with its turnings, and finding a moss-blackened granite crag in a hidden angle, I sat down under it. High banks of moor were about me. The crag protected my head. The sky was over that.

14:36:25.960 --> 14:36:44.880
Some time passed before I felt tranquil even here. I had a vague dread that wild cattle might be near, or that some sportsman or poacher might discover me. If a gust of wind swept the waste, I looked up, fearing it was the rush of a bull.

14:36:44.880 --> 14:36:58.480
If a plover whistled, I imagined it a man, finding my apprehensions unfounded, however, and calmed by the deep silence that rained as evening declined at nightfall.

14:36:58.480 --> 14:37:26.420
I took confidence, as yet I had not thought. I had only listened, watched, dreaded. Now I regained the faculty of reflection. What was I to do? Where to go? Oh, intolerable questions, when I could do nothing and go nowhere, when a long way must yet be measured by my weary, trembling limbs before I could reach human habitation.

14:37:28.480 --> 14:37:42.380
I had to be entreated before I could get a lodging, reluctant sympathy importuned. Almost certain repulse incurred before my tale could be listened to, or one of my wants relieved.

14:37:42.380 --> 14:37:55.320
I touched the heath, it was dry, and yet warm with the beat of the summer day. I looked at the sky, it was pure, a kindly star twinkled just above the Chasm Ridge.

14:37:55.940 --> 14:38:19.340
The dew fell, but with perpetuous softness. No breeze whispered. Nature seemed to me benign and good. I thought she loved me, outcast as I was, and I, who from man could anticipate only mistrust, rejection, insult, clung to her with filial fondness.

14:38:20.160 --> 14:38:28.620
Tonight, at least, I would be her guest. As I was her child, my mother would lodge me without money and without price.

14:38:29.440 --> 14:38:39.320
I had one morsel of bread yet, the remnant of a roll I had bought in a town we passed through at noon with a stray penny, my last coin.

14:38:39.320 --> 14:38:49.320
I saw ripe bilberries gleaming here and there, like jet-beads in the heath. I gathered a handful and ate them with the bread.

14:38:50.620 --> 14:38:57.140
My hunger, sharp before, was, if not satisfied, appeased by this hermit's meal.

14:38:57.760 --> 14:39:03.340
I said my evening prayers at its conclusion, and then chose my couch.

14:39:04.060 --> 14:39:16.640
Beside the crag, the heath was very deep. When I lay down, my feet were buried in it. Rising high on each side, it left only a narrow space for the night air to invade.

14:39:17.700 --> 14:39:25.600
I folded my shawl double and spread it over me for a couplet. A low, mossy swell was my pillow.

14:39:26.280 --> 14:39:31.620
Thus lodged, I was not, at least, at the commencement of the night cold.

14:39:32.380 --> 14:39:37.360
My rest might have been blissful enough, only a sad heart broke it.

14:39:37.820 --> 14:39:43.520
It plained of its gaping wounds, its inward bleeding, its writhing cords.

14:39:44.400 --> 14:39:50.480
It trembled for Mr. Rochester and his doom. It bemoaned him with a bitter pity.

14:39:50.480 --> 14:39:57.380
It demanded him with ceaseless longing, an impudent as a bird with both wings broken.

14:39:58.220 --> 14:40:02.820
It still quivered at shattered pinions in vain attempts to seek him.

14:40:03.820 --> 14:40:07.460
Worn out with this torture of thought, I rose to my knees.

14:40:07.880 --> 14:40:15.960
Night was come, and her planets were risen, a safe, still night, too serene for the companionship of fear.

14:40:15.960 --> 14:40:26.280
We know that God is everywhere, but certainly we feel his presence most when his works are on the grander scale spread before us.

14:40:26.340 --> 14:40:35.080
And it is in the unclouded night sky, where his worlds wield their silent course, that we read clearest his infatude.

14:40:36.160 --> 14:40:42.700
His omnipotence, his omnipresence, I had risen to my knees to pray for Mr. Rochester.

14:40:42.700 --> 14:40:55.920
Looking up, I, with tear-dimmed eyes, saw the mighty Milky Way, remembering what it was, what countless systems there swept space like a soft trace of light.

14:40:56.560 --> 14:40:59.120
I felt the might and strength of God.

14:40:59.780 --> 14:41:10.760
Sure was I of his efficiency to save what he had made, convinced I grew that neither earth should perish, nor one of the souls it treasured.

14:41:10.760 --> 14:41:17.400
I turned my prayer to thanksgiving, the source of life was also the saviour of spirits.

14:41:18.260 --> 14:41:24.100
Mr. Rochester was safe, he was God's, and my God would he be guarded.

14:41:25.000 --> 14:41:30.940
I again nestled to the breast of the hill, and erlong in sleep forgot sorrow.

14:41:31.620 --> 14:41:39.600
But next day, want came to me pale and bare, long after the little birds had left their nests.

14:41:39.600 --> 14:41:46.700
Long after bees had come in the sweet prime of day to gather the heath honey before the dew was dried.

14:41:47.140 --> 14:41:55.720
When the long morning shadows were curtailed, and the sun filled earth and sky, I got up and I looked round me.

14:41:56.440 --> 14:42:01.480
What a still, hot, perfect day, what a golden desert to spreading more.

14:42:02.300 --> 14:42:06.340
Everywhere sunshine, I wished I could live in it and on it.

14:42:06.340 --> 14:42:13.060
I saw a lizard run over the crag, I saw a bee busy among the sweet bilberries.

14:42:13.720 --> 14:42:22.480
I would fain at the moment had become bee or lizard, and I might have found fitting nutriment, permanent shelter here.

14:42:23.340 --> 14:42:27.340
But I was a human being, and had a human being's wants.

14:42:28.220 --> 14:42:31.700
I must not linger where there was nothing to supply them.

14:42:31.700 --> 14:42:37.620
I rose, I looked back at the bed I had left, hopeless of the future.

14:42:38.160 --> 14:42:45.600
I wished but this, that my Maker had that night thought good to require my soul of me while I slept,

14:42:45.900 --> 14:42:51.600
and that this weary frame, absolved by death from further conflict with fate,

14:42:52.360 --> 14:42:58.540
had now but to decay quietly, and mingle in peace with the soil of this wilderness.

14:42:59.490 --> 14:43:07.380
Life, however, was yet in my possession, with all its requirements, and pains, and responsibilities.

14:43:08.420 --> 14:43:17.500
The burden must be carried, the want provided for, the suffering endured, the responsibility fulfilled, I set out.

14:43:18.380 --> 14:43:24.420
White cross regained, I followed a road which led from the sun, now fervent and high.

14:43:24.420 --> 14:43:29.360
By no other circumstance had I willed to decide my choice.

14:43:29.920 --> 14:43:34.080
I walked a long time, and when I thought I had nearly done enough,

14:43:34.560 --> 14:43:40.260
and might consciously yield to the fatigue that almost overpowered me,

14:43:40.640 --> 14:43:46.240
might relax this forced action, and, sitting down on a stone I saw near,

14:43:46.880 --> 14:43:52.100
submit resistlessly to the apathy that clogged heart and limb.

14:43:52.100 --> 14:43:55.300
I heard a bell chime, a church bell.

14:43:55.940 --> 14:44:01.420
I turned in the direction of the sound, and there, amongst the romantic hills,

14:44:02.020 --> 14:44:08.820
whose changes and aspect I had ceased to note an hour ago, I saw a hamlet and a spire.

14:44:09.660 --> 14:44:15.660
All the valley at my right hand was full of pasture fields, and cornfields, and wood,

14:44:15.660 --> 14:44:20.840
and a glittering stream ran zigzag through the varied shades of green,

14:44:21.300 --> 14:44:26.860
the mellowing grain, the sombre woodland, the clear and sunny leaf.

14:44:27.800 --> 14:44:31.240
Recalled by the rumbling of wheels to the road before me,

14:44:31.680 --> 14:44:34.940
I saw a heavily laden wagon laboring up the hill,

14:44:35.460 --> 14:44:39.260
and not far beyond were two cows and their drover.

14:44:39.900 --> 14:44:42.400
Human life and human labour were near.

14:44:42.400 --> 14:44:47.660
I must struggle on, strive to live, and bend to toil like the rest.

14:44:48.420 --> 14:44:51.820
About two o'clock p.m. I entered the village.

14:44:52.300 --> 14:44:57.720
At the bottom of its one street there was a little shop with some cakes of bread in the window.

14:44:58.440 --> 14:45:00.400
I covered it a cake of bread.

14:45:00.720 --> 14:45:05.220
With that refreshment I could perhaps regain a degree of energy.

14:45:05.540 --> 14:45:08.440
Without it, it would be difficult to proceed.

14:45:09.380 --> 14:45:16.420
The wish to have some strength and some vigour returned to me as soon as I was amongst my fellow beings.

14:45:17.460 --> 14:45:22.360
I felt it would be degrading to faint with hunger on the causeway of a hamlet.

14:45:23.240 --> 14:45:27.780
Had I nothing about me I could offer in exchange for one of these rolls.

14:45:28.620 --> 14:45:33.520
I considered I had a small silk handkerchief tied round my throat.

14:45:34.000 --> 14:45:35.220
I had my gloves.

14:45:35.220 --> 14:45:41.500
I could hardly tell how men and women in extremities of destitution proceeded.

14:45:42.500 --> 14:45:46.520
I did not know whether either of these articles would be accepted.

14:45:46.880 --> 14:45:49.940
Probably they would not, but I must try.

14:45:50.780 --> 14:45:51.900
I entered the shop.

14:45:52.220 --> 14:45:58.280
A woman was there, seeing a respectably dressed person, a lady as she supposed.

14:45:58.600 --> 14:46:00.700
She came forward with civility.

14:46:01.240 --> 14:46:02.820
How could she serve me?

14:46:02.820 --> 14:46:04.980
I was seized with shame.

14:46:05.160 --> 14:46:08.500
My tongue would not utter the request I had prepared.

14:46:09.060 --> 14:46:13.860
I did not offer her the half-worn gloves, the creased handkerchief.

14:46:14.260 --> 14:46:16.660
Besides, I felt it would be absurd.

14:46:17.540 --> 14:46:21.820
I only begged permission to sit down a moment, as I was tired.

14:46:22.920 --> 14:46:28.960
Disappointed in the expectation of a customer, she coolly acceded to my request.

14:46:28.960 --> 14:46:31.240
She pointed to a seat.

14:46:31.740 --> 14:46:32.920
I sunk into it.

14:46:33.800 --> 14:46:40.840
I felt sorely urged to weep, but conscience how unreasonably such a manifestation would be.

14:46:41.560 --> 14:46:43.380
I restrained it.

14:46:43.700 --> 14:46:49.960
Soon I asked her if there were any dressmaker or plain workwoman in the village.

14:46:50.800 --> 14:46:55.500
Yes, two or three, quite as many as there was employment for.

14:46:56.140 --> 14:46:57.260
I reflected.

14:46:57.600 --> 14:46:59.500
I was driven to the point now.

14:46:59.840 --> 14:47:02.600
I was brought face to face with necessity.

14:47:03.500 --> 14:47:09.620
I stood in the position of one without a resource, without a friend, without a coin.

14:47:09.980 --> 14:47:11.400
I must do something.

14:47:11.760 --> 14:47:12.300
What?

14:47:12.900 --> 14:47:14.620
I must apply somewhere.

14:47:14.960 --> 14:47:15.420
Where?

14:47:16.320 --> 14:47:20.780
Did she know of any place in the neighbourhood where a servant was wanted?

14:47:21.660 --> 14:47:23.360
Nah, she couldn't say.

14:47:23.360 --> 14:47:26.580
What was the cheap trade in this place?

14:47:27.100 --> 14:47:29.100
What did most of the people do?

14:47:29.960 --> 14:47:31.640
Some were farm labourers.

14:47:31.720 --> 14:47:36.840
A good deal worked at Mr Oliver's needle factory and at the foundry.

14:47:37.480 --> 14:47:39.640
Did Mr Oliver employ women?

14:47:40.280 --> 14:47:42.240
Nah, it was men's work.

14:47:43.000 --> 14:47:44.560
And what did the women do?

14:47:45.240 --> 14:47:46.960
I know it was the answer.

14:47:47.440 --> 14:47:49.860
Some does one thing and some another.

14:47:50.620 --> 14:47:53.020
Poor folk mungered on as they can.

14:47:54.020 --> 14:48:01.120
She seemed to be tired of my questions and, indeed, what claim had I to importune her?

14:48:01.620 --> 14:48:03.480
A neighbour or two came in.

14:48:03.880 --> 14:48:05.980
My chair was evidently wanted.

14:48:06.340 --> 14:48:07.400
I took leave.

14:48:08.160 --> 14:48:13.980
I passed up the street, looking as I went at all the houses to the right hand and to

14:48:13.980 --> 14:48:20.360
But I could discover no pretext, nor see an inducement to enter any.

14:48:20.860 --> 14:48:26.640
I rambled round the hamlet, going sometimes to a little distance and returning again,

14:48:27.020 --> 14:48:28.700
for an hour or more.

14:48:28.980 --> 14:48:35.760
Much exhausted and suffering greatly now for want of food, I turned aside into a lane and

14:48:35.760 --> 14:48:37.540
sat down under the hedge.

14:48:38.540 --> 14:48:40.920
Er, many minutes had elapsed.

14:48:40.920 --> 14:48:48.060
I was again on my feet, however, and again searching something, a resource, or at least

14:48:48.060 --> 14:48:49.080
an informant.

14:48:49.560 --> 14:48:55.680
A pretty little house stood at the top of the lane, with a garden before it, exquisitely

14:48:55.680 --> 14:48:57.580
neat and brilliantly blooming.

14:48:58.460 --> 14:48:59.660
I stopped at it.

14:48:59.940 --> 14:49:05.160
What business had I to approach the white door or touch the glittering knocker?

14:49:05.160 --> 14:49:11.540
In what way could it possibly be the interest of the inhabitants of that dwelling to serve

14:49:11.540 --> 14:49:12.060
me?

14:49:12.800 --> 14:49:15.080
Yet I drew near and knocked.

14:49:15.700 --> 14:49:20.280
A mould-looking, cleanly attired young woman opened the door.

14:49:20.920 --> 14:49:27.600
In such a voice as might be expected from a hopeless heart and fainting frame, a voice

14:49:27.800 --> 14:49:32.600
wretchedly low and faltering, I asked if a servant was wanted here.

14:49:33.480 --> 14:49:36.920
No, said she, we do not keep a servant.

14:49:37.620 --> 14:49:41.180
Can you tell me where I could get employment of any kind?

14:49:41.800 --> 14:49:42.800
I continued.

14:49:43.620 --> 14:49:46.980
I am a stranger without acquaintance in this place.

14:49:47.320 --> 14:49:49.740
I want some work, no matter what.

14:49:50.500 --> 14:49:57.260
But it was not her business to think for me or to seek a place for me, besides, in her

14:49:57.260 --> 14:50:00.720
eyes, how doubtful must have appeared my character.

14:50:01.620 --> 14:50:01.920
Position.

14:50:02.300 --> 14:50:02.880
Tale.

14:50:03.840 --> 14:50:05.040
She shook her head.

14:50:05.220 --> 14:50:08.480
She was sorry she could give me no information.

14:50:09.380 --> 14:50:15.200
And the white door closed, quite gently and civilly, but it shut me out.

14:50:15.720 --> 14:50:21.120
If she had held it open a little longer, I believe I should have begged a piece of bread,

14:50:21.660 --> 14:50:23.340
for I was now brought low.

14:50:23.340 --> 14:50:31.620
I could not bear to return to the sordid village, where, besides, no prospect of aid was visible.

14:50:32.420 --> 14:50:38.780
I should have longed rather to deviate to a wood, I saw not far off, which appeared

14:50:38.780 --> 14:50:41.960
in its thick shade to offer inviting shelter.

14:50:42.540 --> 14:50:49.700
But I was so sick, so weak, so gnawed with nature's cravings, instinct kept me roaming

14:50:49.700 --> 14:50:52.960
round abodes, where there was a chance of food.

14:50:53.560 --> 14:50:56.100
Solitude would be no solitude.

14:50:56.500 --> 14:51:03.940
Rest, no rest, while the vulture, hunger, thus sunk beak and talons in my side.

14:51:04.780 --> 14:51:12.600
I drew new houses, I left them and came back again, and again I wandered away, always repelled

14:51:12.600 --> 14:51:16.020
by the consciousness of having no claim to ask.

14:51:16.020 --> 14:51:20.360
No right to expect interest in my isolated lot.

14:51:21.740 --> 14:51:28.480
Meantime the afternoon advanced, while I thus wandered about like a lost and starving dog.

14:51:29.000 --> 14:51:32.740
In crossing a field I saw the church spire before me.

14:51:33.080 --> 14:51:35.000
I hastened towards it.

14:51:35.520 --> 14:51:41.200
Near the churchyard and in the middle of a garden stood a well-built, though small house,

14:51:41.480 --> 14:51:44.100
which I had no doubt was the parsonage.

14:51:44.100 --> 14:51:50.260
I remembered that strangers who arrive at a place where they have no friends and who

14:51:50.260 --> 14:51:56.260
want employment sometimes apply to the clergyman for introduction and aid.

14:51:57.020 --> 14:52:03.500
It is the clergyman's function to help, at least with advice, those who wish to help

14:52:03.950 --> 14:52:04.320
themselves.

14:52:05.120 --> 14:52:11.740
I seemed to have something like a right to seek counsel here, renewing then my courage

14:52:11.740 --> 14:52:16.320
and gathering my feeble remains of strength I pushed on.

14:52:16.980 --> 14:52:19.960
I reached the house and knocked at the kitchen door.

14:52:20.440 --> 14:52:21.940
An old woman opened.

14:52:22.360 --> 14:52:24.940
I asked, was this the parsonage?

14:52:25.700 --> 14:52:26.440
Yes.

14:52:27.020 --> 14:52:28.560
Was the clergyman in?

14:52:29.000 --> 14:52:29.560
No.

14:52:30.240 --> 14:52:31.600
Would he be in soon?

14:52:32.100 --> 14:52:34.300
No, he was gone from home.

14:52:34.780 --> 14:52:35.980
To a distance?

14:52:36.620 --> 14:52:37.780
Not so far.

14:52:38.800 --> 14:52:43.000
He had been called away by the sudden death of his father.

14:52:43.380 --> 14:52:48.440
He was at Marsh End now, and would very likely stay there a fortnight longer.

14:52:49.020 --> 14:52:51.360
Was there any lady of the house?

14:52:52.120 --> 14:52:58.660
No, there was naught but here, and she was housekeeper, and of her reader I could not

14:52:58.660 --> 14:53:02.660
bear to ask the relief for want of which I was thinking.

14:53:03.120 --> 14:53:06.540
I could not yet beg, and again I crawled away.

14:53:07.280 --> 14:53:09.760
Once more I took off my handkerchief.

14:53:10.040 --> 14:53:13.780
Once more I thought of the cakes of bread in the little shop.

14:53:14.540 --> 14:53:20.220
Oh, for butter crust, for but one mouthful to allay the pang of famine.

14:53:21.220 --> 14:53:24.300
Instinctively I turned my face again to the village.

14:53:24.900 --> 14:53:27.720
I found the shop again, and I went in.

14:53:28.040 --> 14:53:32.420
And though others were there besides the woman, I ventured the request.

14:53:32.980 --> 14:53:35.500
Would she give me a roll for this handkerchief?

14:53:35.500 --> 14:53:38.600
She looked at me with evident suspicion.

14:53:39.500 --> 14:53:42.260
No, she never sold stuff either way.

14:53:42.960 --> 14:53:45.720
Almost desperate I asked for half a cake.

14:53:46.000 --> 14:53:47.440
She again refused.

14:53:47.760 --> 14:53:50.540
How could she tell where I had got the handkerchief?

14:53:50.780 --> 14:53:51.460
She said.

14:53:52.080 --> 14:53:53.560
Would she take my gloves?

14:53:54.220 --> 14:53:54.760
No.

14:53:55.100 --> 14:53:56.660
What could she do with them?

14:53:57.660 --> 14:54:01.440
Reader, it is not pleasant to dwell on these details.

14:54:01.440 --> 14:54:06.840
Some say there is enjoyment in looking back to painful experience past.

14:54:07.320 --> 14:54:12.300
But at this day I can scarcely bear to review the times to which I allude.

14:54:12.720 --> 14:54:16.640
The moral degradation blent with the physical suffering,

14:54:17.280 --> 14:54:21.660
form too distressing a recollection ever to be willingly dwelt on.

14:54:22.280 --> 14:54:25.020
I blame none of these who repulse me.

14:54:25.340 --> 14:54:30.260
I felt it was what was to be expected, and what could not be helped,

14:54:30.260 --> 14:54:34.620
an ordinary beggar is frequently an object of suspicion,

14:54:35.220 --> 14:54:38.220
a well-dressed beggar, inevitably so.

14:54:38.680 --> 14:54:42.000
To be sure, what I begged was employment,

14:54:42.460 --> 14:54:45.880
but whose business was it to provide me with employment?

14:54:46.580 --> 14:54:51.490
Not certainly that of persons who saw me then for the first time,

14:54:51.920 --> 14:54:54.480
and who knew nothing about my character,

14:54:55.080 --> 14:54:58.500
and as to the woman who would not take my handkerchief

14:54:58.500 --> 14:55:00.420
in exchange for her bread.

14:55:00.920 --> 14:55:05.240
Why, she was right, if the offer appeared to her sinister

14:55:05.240 --> 14:55:08.040
or the exchange unprofitable.

14:55:08.520 --> 14:55:10.320
Let me condense now.

14:55:10.740 --> 14:55:12.640
I am sick of the subject.

14:55:13.460 --> 14:55:16.480
A little before dark I passed the farmhouse,

14:55:16.840 --> 14:55:19.740
at the open door of which the farmer was sitting,

14:55:20.120 --> 14:55:22.420
eating his supper of bread and cheese.

14:55:22.860 --> 14:55:24.620
I stopped and said,

14:55:24.620 --> 14:55:28.900
Will you give me a piece of bread, for I am very hungry.

14:55:29.480 --> 14:55:32.420
He cast on me a glance of surprise,

14:55:32.940 --> 14:55:36.760
but without answering he cut a thick slice from his loaf

14:55:36.760 --> 14:55:38.320
and gave it to me.

14:55:38.980 --> 14:55:42.300
I imagined he did not think I was a beggar,

14:55:42.420 --> 14:55:45.300
but only an eccentric sort of lady,

14:55:45.680 --> 14:55:48.360
who had taken a fancy to his brown loaf.

14:55:48.960 --> 14:55:51.840
As soon as I was out of sight of his house,

14:55:52.180 --> 14:55:54.100
I sat down and ate it.

14:55:54.100 --> 14:55:57.680
I could not hope to get a lodging under a roof

14:55:57.680 --> 14:56:02.060
and sort it in the wood I had been before alluded to.

14:56:02.500 --> 14:56:05.520
But by night was wretched, my rest broken,

14:56:05.920 --> 14:56:08.600
the ground was damp, the air cold.

14:56:09.100 --> 14:56:12.860
Besides, intruders passed near me more than once,

14:56:13.360 --> 14:56:16.660
and I had again and again to change my quarters.

14:56:17.280 --> 14:56:21.600
No sense of safety or tranquillity befriended me.

14:56:22.380 --> 14:56:24.200
Towards morning it rained,

14:56:24.620 --> 14:56:27.060
the whole of the following day was wet.

14:56:27.760 --> 14:56:29.380
Do not ask me, reader,

14:56:29.720 --> 14:56:32.000
to give a minute account of that day.

14:56:32.240 --> 14:56:34.600
As before I sought work,

14:56:35.080 --> 14:56:37.580
as before I was repulsed,

14:56:37.800 --> 14:56:39.920
as before I starved,

14:56:40.060 --> 14:56:42.700
but once did food pass my lips.

14:56:43.260 --> 14:56:44.820
At the door of a cottage

14:56:44.820 --> 14:56:48.720
I saw a little girl about to throw a mess of cold porridge

14:56:48.720 --> 14:56:50.140
into a pig trough.

14:56:50.140 --> 14:56:52.900
Will you give me that? I asked.

14:56:53.560 --> 14:56:54.960
She stared at me.

14:56:55.080 --> 14:56:57.120
Mother, she exclaimed,

14:56:57.400 --> 14:57:00.640
there is a woman wants me to give her these porridge.

14:57:01.500 --> 14:57:04.000
Well, alas, replied a voice within,

14:57:04.460 --> 14:57:06.260
give it her if she's a beggar.

14:57:06.440 --> 14:57:07.900
The pig doesn't want it.

14:57:08.540 --> 14:57:11.960
The girl emptied the stiffened mould into my hand

14:57:11.960 --> 14:57:14.420
and I devoured it ravenously.

14:57:15.060 --> 14:57:17.100
As the wet twilight deepened

14:57:17.100 --> 14:57:20.220
I stopped in a solitary bridle path

14:57:20.220 --> 14:57:23.600
which I had been pursuing an hour or more.

14:57:24.220 --> 14:57:26.580
My strength is quite failing me,

14:57:27.000 --> 14:57:29.300
I said in a solid look way.

14:57:30.060 --> 14:57:32.500
I feel I cannot go much farther.

14:57:33.220 --> 14:57:35.900
Shall I be an outcast again this night?

14:57:36.380 --> 14:57:38.100
While the rain descends so,

14:57:38.460 --> 14:57:41.840
must I lay my head on the cold drenched ground?

14:57:42.500 --> 14:57:45.140
I fear I cannot do otherwise,

14:57:45.140 --> 14:57:47.300
for who will receive me?

14:57:47.760 --> 14:57:49.430
But it will be very dreadful

14:57:49.680 --> 14:57:51.420
with this feeling of hunger,

14:57:51.780 --> 14:57:53.080
faintness, chill

14:57:53.080 --> 14:57:55.540
and this sense of desolation,

14:57:55.980 --> 14:57:58.120
this total prostration of hope,

14:57:58.720 --> 14:58:02.760
in all likelihood though I should die before morning.

14:58:03.220 --> 14:58:08.040
And why cannot I reconcile myself to the prospect of death?

14:58:08.840 --> 14:58:12.560
Why do I struggle to retain a valueless life?

14:58:12.560 --> 14:58:18.180
Because I know or believe Mr Rochester is living

14:58:18.180 --> 14:58:22.380
and then to die of want and cold is a fate

14:58:22.380 --> 14:58:24.680
to which nature cannot submit passively.

14:58:25.820 --> 14:58:29.020
O Providence, sustain me a little longer.

14:58:29.560 --> 14:58:31.160
Aid, direct me.

14:58:31.760 --> 14:58:36.020
My glazed eye wandered over the dim and misty landscape.

14:58:36.600 --> 14:58:39.560
I saw I had strayed far from the village.

14:58:39.940 --> 14:58:41.760
It was quite out of sight.

14:58:41.760 --> 14:58:46.020
The very cultivation surrounding it had disappeared.

14:58:46.920 --> 14:58:49.940
I had by crossways and by paths

14:58:49.940 --> 14:58:53.140
once more drawn near the tract of Moorland

14:58:53.140 --> 14:58:55.820
and now only a few fields,

14:58:56.080 --> 14:59:00.220
almost as wild and unproductive as the heath

14:59:00.220 --> 14:59:02.880
from which they were scarcely reclaimed,

14:59:03.440 --> 14:59:05.860
lay between me and the dusky hill.

14:59:06.460 --> 14:59:09.740
Well, I would rather die yonder than in a street

14:59:09.740 --> 14:59:11.500
or on a frequented road.

14:59:12.060 --> 14:59:12.900
I reflected.

14:59:13.700 --> 14:59:16.200
And far better that crows and ravens,

14:59:16.380 --> 14:59:18.940
if any ravens there be in these regions,

14:59:19.380 --> 14:59:21.660
should pick my flesh from my bones

14:59:21.660 --> 14:59:25.720
than that they should be prisoned in a workhouse coffin

14:59:25.720 --> 14:59:28.220
and moulded in a pauper's grave.

14:59:28.880 --> 14:59:31.340
To the hill then I turned.

14:59:31.700 --> 14:59:32.800
I reached it.

14:59:32.800 --> 14:59:36.760
It remained now only to find a hollow where I could lie down

14:59:36.760 --> 14:59:40.400
and feel at least hidden, if not secure.

14:59:40.920 --> 14:59:43.920
But all the surface of the waste looked level.

14:59:44.400 --> 14:59:47.320
It showed no variation but a tint green,

14:59:48.180 --> 14:59:51.140
where rush and moss overgrew the marshes,

14:59:51.300 --> 14:59:54.960
black where the dry soil bore only heath,

14:59:55.480 --> 14:59:56.980
dark as it was getting.

14:59:57.380 --> 14:59:59.780
I could still see these changes,

15:00:00.200 --> 15:00:04.260
though but as mere alternations of light and shade,

15:00:04.260 --> 15:00:07.100
for colour had faded with the daylight.

15:00:07.960 --> 15:00:10.880
My eyes still roved over the sullen swell

15:00:10.880 --> 15:00:12.760
and along the moor edge.

15:00:13.160 --> 15:00:15.740
Vanishing amidst the wildest scenery,

15:00:16.180 --> 15:00:17.980
when on one dim point,

15:00:18.280 --> 15:00:20.760
far in among the marshes and the ridges,

15:00:21.100 --> 15:00:22.540
a light sprung up.

15:00:23.000 --> 15:00:25.260
That is, an igneous aphatus,

15:00:25.760 --> 15:00:27.220
was my first thought,

15:00:27.420 --> 15:00:29.800
and I expected it would soon vanish.

15:00:30.300 --> 15:00:33.480
It burnt on, however, quite steadily,

15:00:33.480 --> 15:00:36.000
neither receding nor advancing.

15:00:36.880 --> 15:00:40.500
Is it, then, a bonfire just kindled?

15:00:40.760 --> 15:00:41.900
I questioned.

15:00:42.280 --> 15:00:44.460
I watched to see whether it would spread,

15:00:44.840 --> 15:00:47.860
but no, as it did not diminish,

15:00:48.400 --> 15:00:50.900
so it did not enlarge.

15:00:51.060 --> 15:00:53.320
It may be a candle in a house.

15:00:53.580 --> 15:00:54.480
I then conjectured,

15:00:55.380 --> 15:00:57.920
but if so, I can never reach it.

15:00:58.240 --> 15:01:00.200
It is much too far away,

15:01:00.580 --> 15:01:02.840
and were it within a yard of me,

15:01:02.840 --> 15:01:04.240
what would it avail?

15:01:04.920 --> 15:01:06.700
I should but knock at the door

15:01:06.700 --> 15:01:08.840
to have it shut in my face.

15:01:09.540 --> 15:01:11.820
And I sunk down where I stood

15:01:11.820 --> 15:01:14.540
and hid my face against the ground.

15:01:15.240 --> 15:01:16.800
I lay still awhile.

15:01:17.500 --> 15:01:20.880
The night wind swept over the hill and over me

15:01:20.880 --> 15:01:23.340
and died moaning in the distance.

15:01:23.880 --> 15:01:25.420
The rain fell fast,

15:01:25.860 --> 15:01:27.980
wetting me afresh to the skin.

15:01:28.640 --> 15:01:31.400
Could I but had stiffened to the still frost,

15:01:31.400 --> 15:01:33.780
the friendly numbness of death?

15:01:34.260 --> 15:01:35.820
It might have pelted on.

15:01:35.940 --> 15:01:37.580
I should not have felt it,

15:01:37.680 --> 15:01:39.520
but my yet living flesh

15:01:39.520 --> 15:01:41.800
shuddered at its chilling influence.

15:01:42.340 --> 15:01:43.660
I rose ere long.

15:01:44.380 --> 15:01:45.920
The light was yet there,

15:01:46.220 --> 15:01:48.760
shining dim but constant through the rain.

15:01:49.280 --> 15:01:50.720
I tried to walk again.

15:01:51.340 --> 15:01:55.240
I dragged my exhausted limbs slowly towards it.

15:01:55.660 --> 15:01:58.440
It led me a slant over the hill,

15:01:58.740 --> 15:02:00.000
through a wide bog,

15:02:00.000 --> 15:02:03.100
which would have been impassable in winter,

15:02:03.440 --> 15:02:06.160
and was splashy and shaking even now,

15:02:06.480 --> 15:02:07.740
in the height of summer.

15:02:08.460 --> 15:02:09.900
Here I fell twice,

15:02:10.020 --> 15:02:13.300
but as often as I rose and rallied my faculties,

15:02:14.180 --> 15:02:16.440
this light was my forlorn hope.

15:02:16.900 --> 15:02:18.100
I must gain it.

15:02:18.540 --> 15:02:19.940
Having crossed the marsh,

15:02:20.240 --> 15:02:22.780
I saw a trace of white over the moor.

15:02:23.040 --> 15:02:24.360
I approached it.

15:02:24.620 --> 15:02:26.400
It was a road or a track.

15:02:26.780 --> 15:02:28.660
It led straight up to the light,

15:02:28.660 --> 15:02:31.720
which now beamed from a sort of knoll,

15:02:32.140 --> 15:02:33.760
amidst a clump of trees,

15:02:34.100 --> 15:02:35.320
furs apparently,

15:02:35.500 --> 15:02:37.240
from what I could distinguish

15:02:37.240 --> 15:02:39.260
at the character of their forms

15:02:39.260 --> 15:02:41.620
and foliage through the gloom.

15:02:41.960 --> 15:02:44.280
My star vanished as I drew near.

15:02:45.000 --> 15:02:46.840
Some obstacle had intervened

15:02:46.840 --> 15:02:48.360
between me and it.

15:02:49.140 --> 15:02:50.460
I put out my hand

15:02:50.460 --> 15:02:52.780
to feel the dark mass before me.

15:02:53.240 --> 15:02:55.160
I discriminated the rough stones

15:02:55.160 --> 15:02:56.260
of a low wall.

15:02:56.260 --> 15:02:59.260
Above it, something like palisades,

15:03:00.060 --> 15:03:02.640
and within a high and prickly hedge.

15:03:03.580 --> 15:03:04.520
I groped on.

15:03:05.060 --> 15:03:07.060
Again a whitish object

15:03:07.060 --> 15:03:08.400
gleamed before me.

15:03:08.560 --> 15:03:10.460
It was a gate, a wicket.

15:03:10.860 --> 15:03:12.480
It moved on its hinges

15:03:12.480 --> 15:03:13.900
as I touched it.

15:03:14.160 --> 15:03:16.960
On each side stood a sable bush holly,

15:03:17.220 --> 15:03:18.080
or yew.

15:03:18.780 --> 15:03:21.220
Entering the gate and passing the shrubs,

15:03:21.640 --> 15:03:23.220
the silhouette of a house

15:03:23.220 --> 15:03:25.480
rose to view, black, low,

15:03:25.480 --> 15:03:26.740
and rather long.

15:03:27.080 --> 15:03:29.180
But the guiding light shone nowhere.

15:03:29.720 --> 15:03:31.100
Always obscurity.

15:03:31.800 --> 15:03:34.300
Were the inmates retired to rest?

15:03:34.780 --> 15:03:36.580
I fear it must be so.

15:03:37.020 --> 15:03:38.220
In seeking the door,

15:03:38.440 --> 15:03:39.620
I turned an angle.

15:03:40.260 --> 15:03:42.780
There shot out the friendly gleam again,

15:03:43.000 --> 15:03:44.820
from the lozenge panes

15:03:44.820 --> 15:03:46.740
of a very small lattice window,

15:03:47.520 --> 15:03:49.220
within a foot off the ground,

15:03:49.940 --> 15:03:51.100
made still smaller

15:03:51.100 --> 15:03:52.900
by the grove of ivy

15:03:52.900 --> 15:03:54.840
or some other creeping plant,

15:03:54.840 --> 15:03:56.960
whose leaves clustered thick

15:03:56.960 --> 15:03:59.400
over the portion of the house wall

15:03:59.400 --> 15:04:00.680
in which it was set.

15:04:01.260 --> 15:04:04.100
The aperture was so screened and narrow

15:04:04.100 --> 15:04:06.140
that curtain or shutter

15:04:06.140 --> 15:04:08.160
had been deemed unnecessary.

15:04:08.160 --> 15:04:10.160
And when I stooped down

15:04:10.160 --> 15:04:12.220
and put aside the spray of foliage

15:04:12.220 --> 15:04:13.600
shooting over it,

15:04:13.900 --> 15:04:15.560
I could see all within.

15:04:16.040 --> 15:04:18.040
I could see clearly a room

15:04:18.040 --> 15:04:19.340
with a sanded floor,

15:04:20.020 --> 15:04:20.820
clean scoured,

15:04:21.380 --> 15:04:22.700
a dresser of walnut,

15:04:22.700 --> 15:04:25.620
with pewter plates ranged in rows,

15:04:26.140 --> 15:04:28.260
reflecting the redness and radiance

15:04:28.260 --> 15:04:29.860
of a glowing peat fire.

15:04:30.400 --> 15:04:31.600
I could see a clock,

15:04:31.900 --> 15:04:33.240
a white deal table,

15:04:33.480 --> 15:04:34.380
some chairs.

15:04:35.140 --> 15:04:37.980
The candle, whose ray had been my beacon,

15:04:38.620 --> 15:04:39.840
burnt on the table,

15:04:40.180 --> 15:04:41.560
and by its light

15:04:41.560 --> 15:04:43.020
an elderly woman,

15:04:43.560 --> 15:04:44.760
somewhat rough looking,

15:04:45.240 --> 15:04:47.040
but scrupulously clean,

15:04:47.400 --> 15:04:48.780
like all about her,

15:04:49.020 --> 15:04:50.240
was knitting a stocking.

15:04:50.240 --> 15:04:52.620
I noticed these objects

15:04:52.620 --> 15:04:53.900
coarsely only.

15:04:54.360 --> 15:04:56.280
In them there was nothing extraordinary.

15:04:57.540 --> 15:04:58.640
A group of more

15:04:58.640 --> 15:05:00.660
interest appeared near the half.

15:05:01.120 --> 15:05:02.020
Sitting still

15:05:02.020 --> 15:05:04.060
amidst the rosy piece

15:05:04.060 --> 15:05:05.940
and warmth suffusing it,

15:05:06.320 --> 15:05:08.340
two young, graceful women,

15:05:08.780 --> 15:05:10.480
ladies in every point,

15:05:11.160 --> 15:05:13.520
sat, one in a low rocking chair,

15:05:13.900 --> 15:05:15.640
the other on a lower stool,

15:05:16.140 --> 15:05:17.980
both wore deep mourning

15:05:17.980 --> 15:05:19.860
of crepe and bombazing.

15:05:19.860 --> 15:05:21.840
Which sombre garb

15:05:21.840 --> 15:05:24.340
singularly set off very fair necks

15:05:24.340 --> 15:05:25.220
and faces.

15:05:25.960 --> 15:05:27.680
A large old pointer dog

15:05:27.680 --> 15:05:29.540
rested its massive head

15:05:29.540 --> 15:05:31.300
on the knee of one girl.

15:05:31.660 --> 15:05:33.980
In the lap of the other was cushioned

15:05:33.980 --> 15:05:34.820
a black cat.

15:05:35.640 --> 15:05:37.860
A strange place was this humble

15:05:37.860 --> 15:05:39.940
kitchen for such occupants.

15:05:40.520 --> 15:05:41.600
Who were they?

15:05:42.000 --> 15:05:43.580
They could not be the daughters

15:05:43.580 --> 15:05:45.900
of the elderly person at the table,

15:05:46.320 --> 15:05:48.120
for she looked like a rustic,

15:05:48.120 --> 15:05:50.060
and they were all delicacy

15:05:50.060 --> 15:05:51.280
and cultivation.

15:05:51.980 --> 15:05:54.360
I had nowhere seen such faces

15:05:54.360 --> 15:05:55.280
as theirs.

15:05:55.800 --> 15:05:58.000
And yet, as I gazed on them,

15:05:58.360 --> 15:06:00.120
I seemed intimate with

15:06:00.120 --> 15:06:01.220
every liniment.

15:06:01.840 --> 15:06:03.780
I cannot call them handsome.

15:06:04.300 --> 15:06:06.080
They were too pale and grey

15:06:06.080 --> 15:06:08.060
for the word, as they each

15:06:08.060 --> 15:06:09.420
bent over a book.

15:06:09.960 --> 15:06:11.960
They looked thoughtful, almost

15:06:11.960 --> 15:06:12.880
to severity.

15:06:13.800 --> 15:06:15.780
A stand between them supported

15:06:15.780 --> 15:06:17.900
a second candle and two great

15:06:17.900 --> 15:06:19.880
volumes, to which they

15:06:19.880 --> 15:06:21.200
frequently referred,

15:06:21.800 --> 15:06:23.540
comparing them, seemingly

15:06:23.540 --> 15:06:25.720
with the smaller books they held

15:06:25.720 --> 15:06:26.820
in their hands.

15:06:27.300 --> 15:06:29.580
Like people consulting a dictionary

15:06:29.580 --> 15:06:31.660
to aid them in the task of

15:06:31.660 --> 15:06:32.400
translation.

15:06:33.180 --> 15:06:35.580
This scene was as silent as if

15:06:35.580 --> 15:06:37.560
all the figures had been shadows

15:06:37.560 --> 15:06:40.080
and the firelit apartment a picture.

15:06:40.420 --> 15:06:42.060
So hushed was it.

15:06:42.220 --> 15:06:43.780
I could hear the cinders

15:06:43.780 --> 15:06:46.280
fall from the grate, the clock tick

15:06:46.280 --> 15:06:48.040
in its obscure corner,

15:06:48.220 --> 15:06:49.900
and I even fancied

15:06:49.900 --> 15:06:52.120
I could distinguish the click-click

15:06:52.120 --> 15:06:54.140
of the woman's knitting needles.

15:06:54.680 --> 15:06:55.960
When, therefore,

15:06:56.180 --> 15:06:57.800
a voice broke the strange

15:06:57.800 --> 15:06:59.240
stillness at last,

15:06:59.540 --> 15:07:01.760
it was audible enough to me.

15:07:02.300 --> 15:07:03.600
Listen, Diana,

15:07:03.920 --> 15:07:06.080
said one of the absorbed students.

15:07:06.760 --> 15:07:08.140
France and old Daniel

15:07:08.140 --> 15:07:09.880
are together in the night-time,

15:07:10.100 --> 15:07:12.120
and France is telling a dream

15:07:12.120 --> 15:07:14.140
from which he has awakened in terror.

15:07:14.380 --> 15:07:14.920
Listen.

15:07:15.900 --> 15:07:17.960
And in a low voice she read

15:07:17.960 --> 15:07:20.360
something of which not one word

15:07:20.360 --> 15:07:22.580
was intelligible to me.

15:07:22.920 --> 15:07:24.180
For it was in an

15:07:24.180 --> 15:07:26.020
unknown tongue, neither

15:07:26.020 --> 15:07:27.500
French nor Latin.

15:07:28.000 --> 15:07:29.800
Whether it was Greek or German,

15:07:29.920 --> 15:07:31.060
I could not tell.

15:07:31.740 --> 15:07:33.660
That is strong, she said,

15:07:33.800 --> 15:07:36.160
when she had finished. I relish it.

15:07:36.820 --> 15:07:38.080
The other girl, who

15:07:38.080 --> 15:07:40.180
had lifted her head to listen to her

15:07:40.180 --> 15:07:42.360
sister, repeated, while

15:07:42.360 --> 15:07:43.820
she gazed at the fire,

15:07:44.340 --> 15:07:46.200
a line of what had been read.

15:07:46.920 --> 15:07:48.020
At a later day

15:07:48.020 --> 15:07:50.020
I knew the language and the book.

15:07:50.400 --> 15:07:52.380
Therefore, I will herequote

15:07:52.380 --> 15:07:53.900
the line, though

15:07:53.900 --> 15:07:56.220
when I first heard it, it was

15:07:56.220 --> 15:07:58.340
only like a stroke on sounding

15:07:58.340 --> 15:08:00.620
brass to me, conveying

15:08:00.620 --> 15:08:01.440
no meaning.

15:08:02.700 --> 15:08:03.880
The foot came forward

15:08:03.880 --> 15:08:06.420
to tell how the star knocked.

15:08:06.660 --> 15:08:07.680
Good, good,

15:08:07.680 --> 15:08:09.580
she exclaimed,

15:08:09.740 --> 15:08:11.600
while her dark and deep eyes

15:08:11.600 --> 15:08:13.760
sparkled. There you have

15:08:13.760 --> 15:08:15.800
a dim and mighty archangel

15:08:15.800 --> 15:08:17.560
fitly set before you.

15:08:18.360 --> 15:08:19.980
The line is worth a hundred

15:08:19.980 --> 15:08:21.660
pages of Faustian.

15:08:25.540 --> 15:08:27.240
I like it.

15:08:27.480 --> 15:08:29.140
Both were again silent.

15:08:29.820 --> 15:08:31.760
Is there only country where they

15:08:31.760 --> 15:08:33.240
talk, eye that way,

15:08:33.760 --> 15:08:35.740
us the old woman, looking up

15:08:35.740 --> 15:08:37.980
from her knitting? Yes, Hannah,

15:08:38.460 --> 15:08:39.960
a far larger country

15:08:39.960 --> 15:08:41.840
than England, where they

15:08:41.840 --> 15:08:43.520
talk in no other way.

15:08:44.100 --> 15:08:45.860
Well, for sure case,

15:08:46.140 --> 15:08:47.900
I know how they can understand

15:08:48.340 --> 15:08:49.300
to one another.

15:08:49.520 --> 15:08:51.820
And if either of you went there,

15:08:51.980 --> 15:08:54.220
you could tell what they said, I guess.

15:08:54.660 --> 15:08:55.960
We probably tell

15:08:55.960 --> 15:08:57.560
something of what they said,

15:08:57.680 --> 15:08:59.940
but not all, for we are not

15:08:59.940 --> 15:09:02.040
as clever as you think us, Hannah.

15:09:02.500 --> 15:09:03.940
We don't speak German,

15:09:03.940 --> 15:09:06.360
and we cannot read it without a dictionary

15:09:06.360 --> 15:09:07.340
to help us.

15:09:07.900 --> 15:09:09.980
And what good does it do you?

15:09:10.760 --> 15:09:12.060
We mean to teach it

15:09:12.060 --> 15:09:13.760
sometime, or at least

15:09:13.760 --> 15:09:16.000
their elements, as they say,

15:09:16.340 --> 15:09:18.100
and then we shall get more money

15:09:18.100 --> 15:09:19.300
than we do now.

15:09:20.240 --> 15:09:22.060
Very like, but give over

15:09:22.060 --> 15:09:24.200
studying, you've done enough for tonight.

15:09:24.880 --> 15:09:25.980
I think we have,

15:09:26.100 --> 15:09:27.500
at least I'm tired.

15:09:27.980 --> 15:09:29.020
Mary, are you?

15:09:29.760 --> 15:09:31.940
Mortally, after all, it's

15:09:31.940 --> 15:09:34.420
tough work fagging away at a language

15:09:34.420 --> 15:09:35.660
with no master

15:09:35.660 --> 15:09:36.820
but a lexicon.

15:09:37.520 --> 15:09:40.140
It is, especially such a language

15:09:40.140 --> 15:09:42.060
as this crabbed but glorious

15:09:42.060 --> 15:09:43.780
douche. I wonder

15:09:43.780 --> 15:09:45.600
when St John will come home.

15:09:46.360 --> 15:09:47.920
Surely he will not be

15:09:47.920 --> 15:09:49.840
long now. It is just

15:09:49.840 --> 15:09:51.740
ten. Looking at a little

15:09:51.740 --> 15:09:53.900
gold watch, she drew from her

15:09:53.900 --> 15:09:55.680
girdle. It rains

15:09:55.680 --> 15:09:58.100
fast, Hannah. Will you have

15:09:58.100 --> 15:09:59.680
the goodness to look at the fire

15:09:59.680 --> 15:10:00.800
in the parlour?

15:10:01.340 --> 15:10:03.920
The woman rose. She opened a door

15:10:03.920 --> 15:10:06.040
through which I dimly saw

15:10:06.040 --> 15:10:07.860
a passage. Soon

15:10:07.860 --> 15:10:10.080
I heard her stir a fire

15:10:10.080 --> 15:10:11.200
in an inner room.

15:10:11.640 --> 15:10:13.500
She presently came back.

15:10:14.220 --> 15:10:15.900
Ah, children, she

15:10:15.900 --> 15:10:17.800
said. It fair troubles

15:10:17.800 --> 15:10:19.880
me to go into yon room now.

15:10:20.340 --> 15:10:21.840
It looks so lonesome

15:10:21.840 --> 15:10:23.700
with the chair empty and set

15:10:23.700 --> 15:10:25.800
back in a corner. She wiped

15:10:25.800 --> 15:10:27.620
her eyes with her apron. The

15:10:27.620 --> 15:10:29.520
two girls, grave before,

15:10:29.860 --> 15:10:30.980
look sad now.

15:10:31.680 --> 15:10:33.360
But he is in a better place,

15:10:33.500 --> 15:10:35.480
continued Hannah. We shouldn't

15:10:35.480 --> 15:10:37.540
wish him here again, and

15:10:37.540 --> 15:10:39.500
then nobody need to have a quieter

15:10:39.500 --> 15:10:41.080
death, nor he had.

15:10:41.780 --> 15:10:43.520
You say he never mentioned

15:10:43.520 --> 15:10:45.720
us, inquired one of the ladies.

15:10:46.300 --> 15:10:47.600
He hadn't time,

15:10:47.940 --> 15:10:49.640
Ben. He was gone in a minute.

15:10:49.820 --> 15:10:50.780
Was your father?

15:10:51.560 --> 15:10:53.560
He had been a bit ailing like

15:10:53.560 --> 15:10:55.480
the day before, but not

15:10:55.480 --> 15:10:57.600
to signify, and when Mr.

15:10:57.640 --> 15:10:59.640
St. John asked if he would like

15:10:59.640 --> 15:11:01.600
either of you to be sent for,

15:11:02.120 --> 15:11:03.700
he fair laughed at him.

15:11:04.140 --> 15:11:05.440
He began again

15:11:05.440 --> 15:11:07.640
with a bit of heaviness in his head

15:11:07.640 --> 15:11:09.620
the next day. That

15:11:09.620 --> 15:11:11.300
is a fortnight sin,

15:11:11.580 --> 15:11:13.640
and he went to sleep and never

15:11:13.640 --> 15:11:15.660
wakened. He wore a moustache

15:11:16.040 --> 15:11:17.760
when your brother went into

15:11:17.760 --> 15:11:19.500
the chamber and fanned him.

15:11:20.020 --> 15:11:21.620
Ah, children, that's

15:11:21.620 --> 15:11:23.320
the last of the old stock.

15:11:23.320 --> 15:11:25.820
For ye and Mr. St. John

15:11:25.820 --> 15:11:27.360
is like of different sort.

15:11:27.660 --> 15:11:28.800
To them is gone.

15:11:29.440 --> 15:11:31.300
For all your mother wore Mitch

15:11:31.300 --> 15:11:33.420
your way, and a most

15:11:33.420 --> 15:11:35.500
a book learned. She willed

15:11:35.500 --> 15:11:37.620
a picture, oh yea, Mary.

15:11:38.540 --> 15:11:39.520
Diana is like

15:11:39.520 --> 15:11:41.440
your father. I thought

15:11:41.440 --> 15:11:43.380
them so similar I could not

15:11:43.380 --> 15:11:44.980
tell where the old servant,

15:11:45.200 --> 15:11:47.280
for such I now concluded her

15:11:47.280 --> 15:11:49.240
to be, saw the difference.

15:11:50.200 --> 15:11:51.400
Both were fair

15:11:51.400 --> 15:11:53.860
complexioned and slenderly made,

15:11:54.280 --> 15:11:55.260
both possessed

15:11:55.260 --> 15:11:57.140
faces full of distinction

15:11:57.140 --> 15:11:58.380
and intelligence.

15:11:59.180 --> 15:12:01.460
One, to be sure, had hair

15:12:01.460 --> 15:12:03.120
a shade darker than the other,

15:12:03.500 --> 15:12:05.260
and there was a difference in their

15:12:05.260 --> 15:12:07.460
style of wearing it. Mary's

15:12:07.460 --> 15:12:09.440
pale brown locks were parted

15:12:09.440 --> 15:12:10.640
and braided smooth.

15:12:11.260 --> 15:12:13.320
Diana's duskier tresses

15:12:13.320 --> 15:12:15.220
covered her neck with thick

15:12:15.220 --> 15:12:17.300
curls. The clock struck

15:12:17.300 --> 15:12:19.620
ten. You want your supper,

15:12:19.620 --> 15:12:22.040
I am sure, observed Hannah,

15:12:22.480 --> 15:12:24.100
and so will Mr. St. John

15:12:24.100 --> 15:12:25.180
when he comes in.

15:12:25.600 --> 15:12:27.780
And she proceeded to prepare

15:12:27.780 --> 15:12:29.980
the meal. The ladies rose.

15:12:30.240 --> 15:12:32.000
They seemed about to withdraw

15:12:32.000 --> 15:12:33.440
to the parlour.

15:12:33.780 --> 15:12:35.760
Till this moment I had been

15:12:35.760 --> 15:12:37.720
so intent on watching them.

15:12:38.080 --> 15:12:40.040
Their appearance and conversation

15:12:40.040 --> 15:12:41.740
had excited in me so

15:12:41.740 --> 15:12:43.840
keen an interest. I had

15:12:43.840 --> 15:12:45.720
half forgotten my own

15:12:45.720 --> 15:12:47.840
wretched position. Now it

15:12:47.840 --> 15:12:49.040
occurred to me.

15:12:49.660 --> 15:12:51.640
More desolate, more desperate

15:12:51.640 --> 15:12:53.540
than ever, it seemed from

15:12:53.540 --> 15:12:55.940
contrast. And how impossible

15:12:55.940 --> 15:12:57.680
did it appear to touch the

15:12:57.680 --> 15:12:59.480
inmates of this house with

15:12:59.480 --> 15:13:01.440
concern on my behalf

15:13:01.440 --> 15:13:03.660
to make them believe in the truth

15:13:03.660 --> 15:13:05.560
of my wants and woes,

15:13:05.980 --> 15:13:07.520
to induce them to vouch

15:13:07.520 --> 15:13:09.980
safe a rest for my wanderings.

15:13:10.180 --> 15:13:11.700
As I groped out the

15:13:11.700 --> 15:13:13.740
door and knocked at it

15:13:13.740 --> 15:13:16.000
hesitantly, I felt

15:13:16.000 --> 15:13:17.980
that last idea to be a

15:13:17.980 --> 15:13:19.980
mere chimera. Hannah

15:13:19.980 --> 15:13:21.860
opened. What do you

15:13:21.860 --> 15:13:23.700
want? She inquired,

15:13:23.860 --> 15:13:26.100
in a voice of surprise, as she

15:13:26.100 --> 15:13:27.980
surveyed me by the light of the

15:13:27.980 --> 15:13:29.040
candle she held.

15:13:29.600 --> 15:13:31.740
May I speak to your mistresses?

15:13:31.920 --> 15:13:33.940
I said. You had

15:13:33.940 --> 15:13:35.920
better tell me what you have to

15:13:35.920 --> 15:13:37.960
say to them. Where do you come

15:13:37.960 --> 15:13:40.100
from? I am a stranger.

15:13:40.800 --> 15:13:41.900
What is your business

15:13:41.900 --> 15:13:43.060
here at this hour?

15:13:43.060 --> 15:13:45.420
I want a night's shelter

15:13:45.420 --> 15:13:47.600
in an outhouse or anywhere

15:13:47.600 --> 15:13:49.720
and a morsel of bread to

15:13:49.720 --> 15:13:51.440
eat. Distrust,

15:13:51.720 --> 15:13:53.320
the very feeling I dreaded,

15:13:53.680 --> 15:13:55.240
appeared in Hannah's face.

15:13:55.440 --> 15:13:57.420
I'll give you a piece of bread,

15:13:57.740 --> 15:13:59.360
she said after a pause.

15:13:59.940 --> 15:14:01.400
But we can't take in a

15:14:01.400 --> 15:14:03.220
vagrant to lodge. It isn't

15:14:03.220 --> 15:14:05.220
likely. Do let

15:14:05.220 --> 15:14:06.800
me speak to your mistresses?

15:14:07.720 --> 15:14:09.080
No, not I.

15:14:09.420 --> 15:14:11.140
What can they do for you?

15:14:11.140 --> 15:14:13.060
You should not be roving about

15:14:13.060 --> 15:14:14.760
now. It looks very ill.

15:14:15.540 --> 15:14:17.220
But where shall I go if you

15:14:17.220 --> 15:14:19.440
drive me away? What shall I do?

15:14:20.600 --> 15:14:21.440
Oh, I'll

15:14:21.440 --> 15:14:23.260
warrant you know where to go

15:14:23.260 --> 15:14:25.160
and what to do. Mind you

15:14:25.160 --> 15:14:26.900
don't do wrong. That's all.

15:14:27.100 --> 15:14:28.820
Here is a penny. Now go.

15:14:29.660 --> 15:14:31.300
A penny cannot feed me

15:14:31.300 --> 15:14:33.400
and I have no strength to go farther.

15:14:33.880 --> 15:14:34.940
Don't shut the door.

15:14:35.160 --> 15:14:37.100
Oh, don't. For God's sake.

15:14:37.760 --> 15:14:39.300
I must. The rain is

15:14:39.300 --> 15:14:41.320
driving in. Tell the young

15:14:41.320 --> 15:14:43.140
ladies. Let me see them.

15:14:43.840 --> 15:14:45.340
Indeed, I will not.

15:14:45.680 --> 15:14:47.520
You are not what you ought to be

15:14:47.520 --> 15:14:49.260
or you wouldn't make such a

15:14:49.260 --> 15:14:50.480
noise. Move off.

15:14:51.040 --> 15:14:53.540
But I must die if I am turned away.

15:14:54.360 --> 15:14:55.220
Not you,

15:14:55.220 --> 15:14:57.380
I'm feared. You have some ill planes

15:14:57.380 --> 15:14:59.420
agate that bring you about

15:14:59.420 --> 15:15:01.660
folks' houses at this time of night.

15:15:02.000 --> 15:15:03.440
If you've any followers,

15:15:04.260 --> 15:15:05.460
housebreakers or such

15:15:05.460 --> 15:15:07.240
like, anywhere near,

15:15:07.240 --> 15:15:09.240
you may tell them we are not

15:15:09.240 --> 15:15:10.940
by ourselves in the house.

15:15:11.160 --> 15:15:13.160
We have a gentleman and dogs

15:15:13.160 --> 15:15:15.260
and guns. Here the

15:15:15.260 --> 15:15:17.380
honest but inflexible servant

15:15:17.380 --> 15:15:19.200
clapped the door to and

15:15:19.200 --> 15:15:20.240
bolted it within.

15:15:20.900 --> 15:15:23.280
This was the climax, a pang

15:15:23.280 --> 15:15:24.680
of exquisite suffering,

15:15:25.120 --> 15:15:26.840
a throw of true despair.

15:15:27.480 --> 15:15:29.300
Rent and heave my heart.

15:15:29.680 --> 15:15:30.960
Worn out indeed

15:15:30.960 --> 15:15:33.260
I was. Not another step

15:15:33.260 --> 15:15:34.160
could I stir.

15:15:34.160 --> 15:15:36.400
I sunk on the wet

15:15:36.400 --> 15:15:38.220
doorstep. I groaned.

15:15:38.220 --> 15:15:40.180
I wrung my hands. I wept

15:15:40.180 --> 15:15:41.520
in utter anguish.

15:15:42.540 --> 15:15:44.080
Oh, this spectre of death.

15:15:44.520 --> 15:15:45.900
Oh, this last hour

15:15:45.900 --> 15:15:47.760
approaching in such horror.

15:15:48.680 --> 15:15:50.520
Alas, this isolation,

15:15:50.940 --> 15:15:52.320
this vanishment from my

15:15:52.320 --> 15:15:54.400
kind. Not only the anchor

15:15:54.400 --> 15:15:56.320
of hope but the footing of

15:15:56.320 --> 15:15:57.700
fortitude was gone.

15:15:58.220 --> 15:15:59.820
At least for a moment

15:15:59.820 --> 15:16:02.220
but the last I soon endeavoured

15:16:02.220 --> 15:16:02.960
to regain.

15:16:03.580 --> 15:16:05.800
I can't but die, I said,

15:16:06.020 --> 15:16:07.400
and I believe in God.

15:16:07.880 --> 15:16:09.820
Let me try to wait his will

15:16:09.820 --> 15:16:10.860
in silence.

15:16:11.580 --> 15:16:13.940
These words I not only thought

15:16:13.940 --> 15:16:15.760
but uttered, and

15:16:15.760 --> 15:16:17.740
thrusting back all my misery

15:16:17.740 --> 15:16:20.100
into my heart, I made an effort

15:16:20.100 --> 15:16:22.020
to compel it to remain there,

15:16:22.380 --> 15:16:23.580
dumb and still.

15:16:24.140 --> 15:16:26.000
All men must die,

15:16:26.380 --> 15:16:27.980
said a voice quite close at

15:16:27.980 --> 15:16:29.840
hand, but all are not

15:16:29.840 --> 15:16:31.420
condemned to meet lingering

15:16:31.420 --> 15:16:32.960
and premature doom.

15:16:33.540 --> 15:16:35.360
Such as yours would be

15:16:35.360 --> 15:16:37.440
if you perished here of want.

15:16:38.180 --> 15:16:39.740
Who or what speaks?

15:16:40.300 --> 15:16:41.480
I asked, terrified,

15:16:41.620 --> 15:16:43.380
at the unexpected sound

15:16:43.380 --> 15:16:45.540
and, incapable now

15:16:45.540 --> 15:16:47.440
of deriving from any

15:16:47.440 --> 15:16:49.480
occurrence, a hope evade.

15:16:50.360 --> 15:16:51.700
A form was near.

15:16:52.020 --> 15:16:52.840
What form?

15:16:53.300 --> 15:16:55.520
The pitch-dark night and my

15:16:55.520 --> 15:16:57.500
enfeebled vision prevented me

15:16:57.500 --> 15:16:58.560
from distinguishing.

15:16:59.220 --> 15:17:00.920
With a loud, long knock,

15:17:01.320 --> 15:17:03.740
the newcomer appealed to the door.

15:17:04.520 --> 15:17:06.660
Is it you, Mr St John?

15:17:06.800 --> 15:17:07.600
cried Hannah.

15:17:08.520 --> 15:17:09.700
Yes, yes,

15:17:09.860 --> 15:17:10.800
open, quickly.

15:17:11.500 --> 15:17:13.260
Well, how wet and cold

15:17:13.260 --> 15:17:15.500
you must be. Such a wild night

15:17:15.500 --> 15:17:17.180
as it is. Come in,

15:17:17.300 --> 15:17:19.480
your sisters are quite uneasy about

15:17:19.480 --> 15:17:21.360
you, and I believe there are

15:17:21.360 --> 15:17:23.360
bad folks about. There has

15:17:23.360 --> 15:17:25.220
been a beggar-woman, I declare

15:17:25.220 --> 15:17:26.560
she has not gone yet.

15:17:26.920 --> 15:17:29.420
Lay down there, get up, for shame,

15:17:29.700 --> 15:17:30.860
move up, I say.

15:17:31.560 --> 15:17:32.500
Hush, Hannah,

15:17:32.940 --> 15:17:35.120
I have a word to say to the woman.

15:17:35.540 --> 15:17:37.000
You have done your duty

15:17:37.000 --> 15:17:39.360
in excluding. Now let me do

15:17:39.360 --> 15:17:40.780
mine in admitting her.

15:17:41.160 --> 15:17:43.200
I was near and listened to both

15:17:43.200 --> 15:17:45.120
you and her. I think

15:17:45.120 --> 15:17:46.780
this is a peculiar case.

15:17:47.220 --> 15:17:49.020
I must at least examine

15:17:49.020 --> 15:17:50.680
into it. Young woman,

15:17:50.960 --> 15:17:52.720
rise and pass before me

15:17:52.720 --> 15:17:54.100
into the house.

15:17:54.680 --> 15:17:56.600
With difficulty I obeyed

15:17:56.600 --> 15:17:58.560
him. Presently I stood

15:17:58.560 --> 15:18:00.380
within that clean, bright

15:18:00.380 --> 15:18:02.560
kitchen, on the very half,

15:18:03.080 --> 15:18:04.580
trembling, sickening,

15:18:04.780 --> 15:18:06.460
conscience of an aspect

15:18:06.460 --> 15:18:08.600
in the last degree ghastly,

15:18:09.000 --> 15:18:10.640
wild and weather-beaten.

15:18:11.060 --> 15:18:12.620
The two ladies, their

15:18:12.620 --> 15:18:14.340
brother, Mr St John,

15:18:14.740 --> 15:18:16.840
the old servant, were all gazing

15:18:16.840 --> 15:18:18.640
at me. St John,

15:18:18.960 --> 15:18:20.640
who is it? I heard

15:18:20.640 --> 15:18:22.680
someone ask. I cannot

15:18:22.680 --> 15:18:24.620
tell. I found her at the door

15:18:24.620 --> 15:18:25.740
was the reply.

15:18:26.300 --> 15:18:28.360
She does look white, said Hannah.

15:18:29.260 --> 15:18:31.000
As white as clay or death

15:18:31.000 --> 15:18:31.940
was responded.

15:18:32.360 --> 15:18:34.280
She will fall, let her sit.

15:18:34.820 --> 15:18:36.900
And indeed my head swum.

15:18:37.260 --> 15:18:38.840
I dropped, but a chair

15:18:38.840 --> 15:18:40.460
received me. I still

15:18:40.460 --> 15:18:42.840
possessed my senses, though

15:18:42.840 --> 15:18:44.740
just now I could not speak.

15:18:45.480 --> 15:18:46.780
Perhaps a little water

15:18:46.780 --> 15:18:48.740
would restore her, Hannah,

15:18:48.740 --> 15:18:50.820
fetch some, but she is worn

15:18:50.820 --> 15:18:52.820
to nothing, how very thin

15:18:52.820 --> 15:18:54.660
and how very bloodless.

15:18:55.180 --> 15:18:56.420
A mere spectre.

15:18:57.160 --> 15:18:58.840
Is she ill or only

15:18:58.840 --> 15:19:00.660
famished? Famished,

15:19:00.720 --> 15:19:02.720
I think. Hannah, is that

15:19:02.720 --> 15:19:04.700
milk? Give it to me and

15:19:04.700 --> 15:19:06.860
a piece of bread. Diana,

15:19:07.060 --> 15:19:08.720
I knew her by the long

15:19:08.720 --> 15:19:10.620
curls, which I saw dripping

15:19:10.620 --> 15:19:12.720
between me and the fire as

15:19:12.720 --> 15:19:14.000
she bent over me,

15:19:14.620 --> 15:19:16.780
broke some bread, dipped it in

15:19:16.780 --> 15:19:19.140
the milk and put it to my lips.

15:19:19.480 --> 15:19:20.820
Her face was near

15:19:20.820 --> 15:19:22.940
mine. I saw there was pity

15:19:22.940 --> 15:19:25.020
in it, and I felt sympathy

15:19:25.020 --> 15:19:26.500
in her hurried breathing.

15:19:27.060 --> 15:19:28.900
In her simple words, too,

15:19:29.140 --> 15:19:31.220
the same balm like emotion

15:19:31.220 --> 15:19:33.040
spoke. Try to eat?

15:19:33.540 --> 15:19:34.840
Yes, try,

15:19:35.140 --> 15:19:36.540
repeated Mary gently.

15:19:37.260 --> 15:19:39.000
And Mary's hand removed

15:19:39.000 --> 15:19:40.940
my sodden bonnet and lifted

15:19:40.940 --> 15:19:43.040
my head. I tasted

15:19:43.040 --> 15:19:44.920
what they offered me, feebly

15:19:44.920 --> 15:19:46.980
at first, eagerly soon.

15:19:47.740 --> 15:19:49.100
Not too much at

15:19:49.100 --> 15:19:50.900
first. Restrain her, said the

15:19:50.900 --> 15:19:53.140
brother. She has had enough

15:19:53.140 --> 15:19:55.020
and he withdrew the cup of

15:19:55.020 --> 15:19:56.760
milk and the plate of bread.

15:19:57.240 --> 15:19:58.960
A little more, St. John.

15:19:59.460 --> 15:20:00.980
Look at the avidity in

15:20:00.980 --> 15:20:02.900
her eyes. No more

15:20:02.900 --> 15:20:04.920
at present, sister. Try if

15:20:04.920 --> 15:20:07.040
she can speak now. Ask her

15:20:07.040 --> 15:20:09.020
her name. I felt

15:20:09.020 --> 15:20:11.160
I could speak and I answered.

15:20:12.120 --> 15:20:12.900
My name

15:20:12.900 --> 15:20:14.080
is Joan Elliott.

15:20:14.740 --> 15:20:16.660
Anxious as ever to avoid

15:20:16.660 --> 15:20:18.860
discovery, I had before

15:20:18.860 --> 15:20:21.360
resolved to assume an alias.

15:20:21.720 --> 15:20:23.080
And where do you live?

15:20:23.300 --> 15:20:24.440
Where are your friends?

15:20:24.860 --> 15:20:26.060
I was silent.

15:20:26.600 --> 15:20:28.840
Can we sing for anyone you know?

15:20:29.520 --> 15:20:30.960
I shook my head.

15:20:31.340 --> 15:20:32.760
What account can you give

15:20:32.760 --> 15:20:33.640
of yourself?

15:20:34.440 --> 15:20:36.560
Somehow, now that I had

15:20:36.560 --> 15:20:38.500
once crossed the threshold of this

15:20:38.500 --> 15:20:40.540
house, and once was brought

15:20:40.540 --> 15:20:42.420
face to face with its owners,

15:20:42.940 --> 15:20:45.040
I felt no longer outcast,

15:20:45.580 --> 15:20:46.760
vagrant, and

15:20:46.760 --> 15:20:48.580
disowned by the wide world.

15:20:49.120 --> 15:20:50.720
I dared to put off the

15:20:50.720 --> 15:20:52.660
mendicant, to resume

15:20:52.660 --> 15:20:54.760
my natural manner and character.

15:20:55.320 --> 15:20:56.720
I began once more

15:20:56.720 --> 15:20:58.560
to know myself, and

15:20:58.560 --> 15:21:00.500
when Mr. St. John demanded

15:21:00.500 --> 15:21:02.640
an account, which at

15:21:02.640 --> 15:21:04.640
present I was far too weak to

15:21:04.640 --> 15:21:06.560
render, I said after

15:21:06.560 --> 15:21:07.780
a brief pause,

15:21:07.780 --> 15:21:10.300
Sir, I can give you

15:21:10.300 --> 15:21:11.920
no details tonight.

15:21:12.480 --> 15:21:13.860
But what then, said

15:21:13.860 --> 15:21:15.860
he, do you expect me

15:21:15.860 --> 15:21:16.920
to do for you?

15:21:17.380 --> 15:21:19.780
Nothing, I replied. My

15:21:19.780 --> 15:21:21.800
strength suffice for but short

15:21:21.800 --> 15:21:23.900
answers. Diana took the

15:21:23.900 --> 15:21:25.820
word. Do you mean,

15:21:25.820 --> 15:21:27.820
she asked, that we have

15:21:27.820 --> 15:21:29.840
now given you what age you

15:21:29.840 --> 15:21:31.860
require, and that we may

15:21:31.860 --> 15:21:33.660
dismiss you to the moor

15:21:33.660 --> 15:21:34.880
and the rainy night?

15:21:34.880 --> 15:21:37.440
I looked at her. She had,

15:21:37.760 --> 15:21:39.380
I thought, a remarkable

15:21:39.380 --> 15:21:41.220
countenance, instinct

15:21:41.220 --> 15:21:43.220
both with power and goodness.

15:21:44.180 --> 15:21:45.060
I took sudden

15:21:45.060 --> 15:21:47.060
courage. Answering

15:21:47.060 --> 15:21:49.100
her compassionate gaze with a

15:21:49.100 --> 15:21:50.440
smile, I said,

15:21:51.020 --> 15:21:52.540
I will trust you,

15:21:52.880 --> 15:21:55.120
if I were a masterless and

15:21:55.120 --> 15:21:57.080
stray dog. I know

15:21:57.080 --> 15:21:58.900
that you would not turn me from

15:21:58.900 --> 15:22:00.380
your hearth tonight,

15:22:00.760 --> 15:22:02.740
as it is I really have no

15:22:02.740 --> 15:22:05.080
fear. Do with me

15:22:05.080 --> 15:22:06.800
and for me as you like,

15:22:07.100 --> 15:22:08.820
but excuse me from much

15:22:08.820 --> 15:22:10.640
discourse. My breath

15:22:10.640 --> 15:22:12.600
is short. I feel a spasm

15:22:12.600 --> 15:22:14.840
when I speak. All three

15:22:14.840 --> 15:22:16.820
surveyed me, and all three

15:22:16.820 --> 15:22:17.700
were silent.

15:22:18.280 --> 15:22:20.620
Hannah, said Mr. St. John

15:22:20.620 --> 15:22:22.700
at last, let her sit

15:22:22.700 --> 15:22:24.660
there at present and ask her

15:22:24.660 --> 15:22:26.800
no questions. In ten minutes

15:22:26.800 --> 15:22:28.660
more, give her the remainder of

15:22:28.660 --> 15:22:30.020
that milk and bread.

15:22:30.020 --> 15:22:32.540
Mary and Diana let us

15:22:32.540 --> 15:22:34.260
go into the parlour and talk

15:22:34.260 --> 15:22:35.320
the matter over.

15:22:36.240 --> 15:22:38.440
They withdrew. Very soon

15:22:38.440 --> 15:22:40.060
one of the ladies returned.

15:22:40.420 --> 15:22:41.820
I could not tell which.

15:22:42.200 --> 15:22:44.260
A kind of pleasant stupor was

15:22:44.260 --> 15:22:46.100
stealing over me as I sat

15:22:46.100 --> 15:22:48.220
by the denial fire.

15:22:49.260 --> 15:22:50.380
In an undertone

15:22:50.380 --> 15:22:52.280
she gave some directions to

15:22:52.280 --> 15:22:54.120
Hannah. Erlong,

15:22:54.420 --> 15:22:55.700
with the servant's aid,

15:22:56.260 --> 15:22:58.620
I contrived to mount a staircase,

15:22:58.620 --> 15:23:01.100
my dripping clothes were removed.

15:23:01.720 --> 15:23:03.200
Soon a warm,

15:23:03.400 --> 15:23:05.100
dry bed received me.

15:23:05.400 --> 15:23:06.320
I, thank God,

15:23:06.840 --> 15:23:09.000
experienced amidst unutterable

15:23:09.540 --> 15:23:10.400
exhaustion

15:23:10.400 --> 15:23:12.600
a glow of grateful joy

15:23:12.600 --> 15:23:13.840
and slept.

15:23:16.720 --> 15:23:17.540
28

15:23:42.080 --> 15:23:43.480
XXIX.

15:23:44.400 --> 15:23:49.760
The recollection of about three days and nights succeeding this is very dim in my mind.

15:23:50.280 --> 15:23:56.140
I can recall some sensations felt in that interval, but few thoughts framed and no actions

15:23:56.140 --> 15:24:02.780
performed. I knew I was in a small room and in a narrow bed. To that bed I seemed to have grown.

15:24:03.440 --> 15:24:09.320
I lay on it motionless as a stone, and to have torn me from it would have been almost to kill me.

15:24:09.320 --> 15:24:17.060
I took no note of the lapse of time, of the change from morning to noon, from noon to evening.

15:24:17.600 --> 15:24:22.760
I observed when anyone entered or left the apartment. I could even tell who they were.

15:24:23.240 --> 15:24:29.000
I could understand what was said when the speaker stood near to me, but I could not answer. To open

15:24:29.000 --> 15:24:36.080
my lips or move my limbs was equally impossible. Hannah, the servant, was my most frequent visitor.

15:24:36.080 --> 15:24:42.280
Her coming disturbed me. I had a feeling that she wished me away, that she did not understand

15:24:42.280 --> 15:24:49.600
me or my circumstances, that she was prejudiced against me. Diana and Mary appeared in the chamber

15:24:49.600 --> 15:24:54.700
once or twice a day. They would whisper sentences of this sort at my bedside.

15:24:55.560 --> 15:25:06.040
It is very well we took her in. Yes, she would certainly have been found dead at the door in

15:25:06.040 --> 15:25:11.320
strange hardships, I imagine. Poor, emaciated, pallid wanderer.

15:25:12.480 --> 15:25:19.000
She is not an uneducated person, I should think, by her manner of speaking. Her accent was quite

15:25:19.000 --> 15:25:24.480
pure, and the clothes she took off, though splashed and wet, were little worn and fine.

15:25:25.600 --> 15:25:33.220
She has a peculiar face, fleshlish and haggard as it is, I rather like it. And when in good health

15:25:33.220 --> 15:25:40.000
and animated I can fancy her physiognomy would be agreeable. Never once in their dialogues did I

15:25:40.000 --> 15:25:46.100
hear a syllable of regret at the hospitality they had extended to me, or of suspicion of,

15:25:46.200 --> 15:25:54.240
or aversion to, myself. I was comforted. Mr. St. John came but once. He looked at me and said

15:25:54.240 --> 15:26:03.200
my state of lethargy was the result of reaction from excessive and protracted fatigue. He

15:26:03.200 --> 15:26:08.680
nature he was sure would manage best left to herself. He said every nerve had been

15:26:08.680 --> 15:26:15.380
overstrained in some way, and the whole system must sleep torpid a while. There was no disease.

15:26:15.780 --> 15:26:21.540
He imagined my recovery would be rapid enough when once commenced. These opinions he delivered

15:26:21.540 --> 15:26:28.500
in a few words in a quiet low voice, and added after a pause in the tone of a man little accustomed

15:26:28.500 --> 15:26:37.780
to expansive comment, rather an unusual physiognomy, certainly not indicative of vulgarity

15:26:37.780 --> 15:26:45.400
or degradation. Far otherwise, responded Diana, to speak truth, St. John, my heart rather warms to

15:26:45.400 --> 15:26:51.680
the poor little soul. I wish we may be able to benefit her permanently. That is hardly likely,

15:26:51.700 --> 15:26:57.340
was the reply. You will find she is some young lady who has had a misunderstanding with her friends,

15:26:57.340 --> 15:27:03.500
and has probably injudiciously left them. We may perhaps succeed in restoring her to them

15:27:03.500 --> 15:27:08.960
if she is not obstinate, but I trace lines of force in her face which make me skeptical

15:27:08.960 --> 15:27:15.720
of her tractability. He stood considering me some minutes, then added. She looks sensible,

15:27:16.180 --> 15:27:23.740
but not at all handsome. She is so ill, St. John. Ill or well, she would always be plain.

15:27:23.740 --> 15:27:27.440
The grace and harmony of beauty are quite wanting in those features.

15:27:27.920 --> 15:27:34.720
On the third day I was better. On the fourth I could speak, move, rise, in bed, and turn.

15:27:35.860 --> 15:27:40.460
Hannah had brought me some gruel and dry toast, about, as I suppose, the dinner hour.

15:27:41.020 --> 15:27:47.160
I had eaten with relish. The food was good, void of the feverish flavor which had hitherto poisoned

15:27:47.160 --> 15:27:52.600
what I had swallowed. When she left me I felt comparatively strong and revived.

15:27:53.560 --> 15:28:00.200
Ere long satiety of repose and desire for action stirred me. I wished to rise, but what could I put

15:28:00.200 --> 15:28:06.600
on? Only my damp and bemired apparel, in which I had slept on the ground and fallen in the marsh.

15:28:07.180 --> 15:28:14.640
I felt ashamed to appear before my benefactor so clad. I was spared the humiliation. On the

15:28:14.640 --> 15:28:20.700
bedside were all my own things, clean and dry. My black silk frock hung against the wall.

15:28:21.140 --> 15:28:26.060
The traces of the bog were removed from it. The creases left by the wet smoothed out.

15:28:26.360 --> 15:28:31.940
It was quite decent. My very shoes and stockings were purified and rendered presentable.

15:28:32.600 --> 15:28:36.860
There were the means of washing in the room, and a comb and brush to smooth my hair.

15:28:37.540 --> 15:28:43.300
After a weary process, and resting every five minutes, I succeeded in dressing myself.

15:28:43.960 --> 15:28:50.060
My clothes hung loose on me, for I was much wasted, but I covered deficiencies with a shawl,

15:28:50.500 --> 15:28:56.240
and once more clean and respectable looking. No speck of the dirt, no trace of the disorder

15:28:56.240 --> 15:29:03.180
I so hated, and which seemed so to degrade me, left. I crept down a stone staircase with the

15:29:03.180 --> 15:29:08.920
aid of the banisters, to a narrow low passage, and found my way presently to the kitchen.

15:29:09.820 --> 15:29:14.660
It was full of the fragrance of new bread, and the warmth of a generous fire.

15:29:15.320 --> 15:29:21.700
Hannah was baking. Prejudices, it is well known, are most difficult to eradicate from the heart

15:29:21.700 --> 15:29:28.060
whose soil has never been loosened or fertilized by education. They grow there firm as weeds among

15:29:28.060 --> 15:29:35.060
stones. Hannah had been cold and stiff indeed at the first. Latterly she had begun to relent a

15:29:35.060 --> 15:29:39.140
and when she saw me come in tidy and well dressed, she even smiled.

15:29:39.900 --> 15:29:45.440
What, you have got up, she said. You are better then. You may sit you down in my chair,

15:29:45.500 --> 15:29:52.280
on the hearthstone, if you will. She pointed to the rocking chair. I took it. She bustled about,

15:29:52.480 --> 15:29:57.760
examining me every now and then from the corner of her eye. Turning to me as she took some loaves

15:29:57.760 --> 15:30:02.680
from the oven, she asked bluntly, Did you ever go a-begging afore you came here?

15:30:03.160 --> 15:30:08.680
I was indignant for a moment, but remembering that anger was out of the question, and that I

15:30:08.680 --> 15:30:14.380
had indeed appeared as a beggar to her, I answered quietly, but still not without a certain marked

15:30:14.380 --> 15:30:21.640
firmness. You are mistaken in supposing me a beggar. I am no beggar, any more than yourself

15:30:21.640 --> 15:30:28.940
or your young ladies. After a pause she said, I done it understand that. You've like no house,

15:30:28.940 --> 15:30:35.480
nor no brass, I guess. The want of house or brass, by which I suppose you mean money,

15:30:35.900 --> 15:30:41.520
does not make a beggar in your sense of the word. Are you book-learned? she inquired presently.

15:30:42.040 --> 15:30:48.640
Yes, very. But you've never been to a boarding school? I was at a boarding school eight years.

15:30:49.160 --> 15:30:56.440
She opened her eyes wide. Whatever cannot you keep yourself for then? I have kept myself,

15:30:56.440 --> 15:31:02.280
and I trust shall keep myself again. What are you going to do with these gooseberries? I inquired,

15:31:02.360 --> 15:31:08.900
as she brought out a basket of the fruit. Make them into pies. Give them to me, and I'll pick them.

15:31:09.360 --> 15:31:16.880
Nay, I don't want you to do not. But I must do something. Let me have them. She consented,

15:31:16.900 --> 15:31:23.040
and she even brought me a clean towel to spread over my dress, lest, she said, I should mucky it.

15:31:24.380 --> 15:31:30.300
You've not been used to a servant's work, I see by your hands, she remarked. Happen you've been a dressmaker?

15:31:31.260 --> 15:31:37.480
No, you are wrong. And now never mind what I have been. Don't trouble your head further about me.

15:31:37.840 --> 15:31:43.300
But tell me the name of the house where we are. Some calls it Marsh End, and some calls it Moore

15:31:43.300 --> 15:31:50.580
House. And the gentleman who lives here is called Mr. St. John? Nay, he doesn't live here. He is only

15:31:50.580 --> 15:31:57.020
staying awhile. When he is at home, he is in his own parish at Morton. That village a few miles off?

15:31:57.180 --> 15:32:05.160
Aye. And what is he? He is a parson. I remembered the answer of the old housekeeper at the parsonage

15:32:05.160 --> 15:32:12.240
when I had asked to see the clergyman. This, then, was his father's residence? Aye. Old Mr.

15:32:12.240 --> 15:32:18.880
John Rivers lived here, and his father and grandfather and great-grandfather afore him.

15:32:20.260 --> 15:32:26.640
The name, then, of that gentleman is Mr. St. John Rivers? Aye, St. John is like his cursand name.

15:32:27.640 --> 15:32:33.940
And his sisters are called Diana and Mary Rivers? Yes. Their father is dead?

15:32:34.860 --> 15:32:41.540
Dead three weeks' sin of a stroke. They have no mother? The mistress has been dead this money a

15:32:41.540 --> 15:32:48.220
year. Have you lived with the family long? I have lived here thirty years. I nursed them all

15:32:48.220 --> 15:32:54.880
three. That proves you must have been an honest and faithful servant. I will say so much for you,

15:32:54.960 --> 15:33:00.740
though you have had the incivility to call me a beggar. She again regarded me with a surprised

15:33:00.740 --> 15:33:07.480
stare. I believe, she said, I was quite mistaken in my thoughts of you. But there are so many

15:33:07.480 --> 15:33:12.400
cheats goes about. You must forgive me. And though I continued rather severely,

15:33:12.620 --> 15:33:16.920
you wished to turn me from the door on a night when you should not have shut out a dog.

15:33:17.820 --> 15:33:24.120
Well, it was hard. But what can a body do? I thought more of the children nor of myself.

15:33:24.360 --> 15:33:30.180
Poor things! They have liked nobody to take care of them but me. I like to look sharpish.

15:33:30.580 --> 15:33:33.320
I maintained a grave silence for some minutes.

15:33:34.100 --> 15:33:37.880
You might not think too hardly of me, she again remarked.

15:33:38.900 --> 15:33:44.300
But I do think hardly of you, I said, and I'll tell you why. Not so much because you refused to

15:33:44.300 --> 15:33:50.020
give me shelter or regarded me as an impostor, as because you just now made it a species of

15:33:50.020 --> 15:33:55.980
reproach that I had no brass and no house. Some of the best people that ever lived have been as

15:33:55.980 --> 15:34:00.940
destitute as I am, and if you are a Christian you ought not to consider poverty a crime.

15:34:01.860 --> 15:34:08.240
No more I ought, said she. Mr. St. John tells me so, too. And I see I wore wrong.

15:34:08.860 --> 15:34:15.140
But I've clear, different notion on you now to what I had. You look a right down decent little

15:34:15.140 --> 15:34:23.740
crater. That will do. I forgive you now. Shake hands. She put her flowery and horny hand into

15:34:23.740 --> 15:34:29.580
mine. Another and heartier smile illumined her rough face, and from that moment we were friends.

15:34:31.000 --> 15:34:36.380
Hannah was evidently fond of talking. While I picked the fruit and she made the paste for the

15:34:36.380 --> 15:34:41.200
pies, she proceeded to give me sundry details about her deceased master and mistress,

15:34:41.620 --> 15:34:48.020
and the children, as she called the young people. Old Mr. Rivers, she said, was a plain man enough,

15:34:48.100 --> 15:34:54.320
but a gentleman, and of as ancient a family as could be found. Marsh End had belonged to

15:34:54.320 --> 15:34:59.720
Rivers ever since it was a house, and it was, she affirmed, a bound two hundred year old,

15:34:59.760 --> 15:35:04.560
for all it looked but a small humble place, not to compare with Mr. Oliver's grand hall

15:35:04.560 --> 15:35:09.540
down in Morton Vale, but she could remember Bill Oliver's father a journeyman needle-maker,

15:35:10.000 --> 15:35:15.480
and the Rivers were gentry in the old days of the Henrys, as anybody might see by looking

15:35:15.480 --> 15:35:22.800
into the registers, in Morton Church vestry. Still, she allowed, the old master was like other folk,

15:35:22.800 --> 15:35:29.400
not much out of the common way, stark mad a shooting and farming and suchlike. The mistress

15:35:29.400 --> 15:35:35.800
was different. She was a great reader, and studied a deal, and the barons had taken after her.

15:35:36.460 --> 15:35:41.580
There was nothing like them in these parts, nor ever had been. They had liked learning,

15:35:41.640 --> 15:35:47.120
all three almost from the time they could speak, and they had always been of a meck of their own.

15:35:47.860 --> 15:35:52.620
Mr. St. John, when he grew up, would go to college and be a parson, and the girls,

15:35:52.640 --> 15:35:57.980
as soon as they left school, would seek places as governesses, for they had told their father

15:35:57.980 --> 15:36:04.940
that some years ago lost a great deal of money by a man he had trusted turning bankrupt, and as he

15:36:04.940 --> 15:36:10.900
was now not rich enough to give them fortunes, they must provide for themselves. They had lived

15:36:10.900 --> 15:36:16.180
very little at home for a long while, and were only now come to stay a few weeks on account of

15:36:16.180 --> 15:36:22.200
their father's death. But they did so like Marsh End and Morton, and all these moors and hills about.

15:36:22.740 --> 15:36:27.180
They had been in London and many other grand towns, but they always said there was no place

15:36:27.180 --> 15:36:32.980
like home. And then they were so agreeable with each other, never fell out nor threeped.

15:36:33.280 --> 15:36:36.480
She did not know where there was such a family for being united.

15:36:37.520 --> 15:36:42.260
Having finished my task of gooseberry picking, I asked where the two ladies and their brother were

15:36:42.260 --> 15:36:48.460
now. Gone over to Morton for a walk, but they would be back in half an hour to tea.

15:36:49.660 --> 15:36:56.100
They returned within the time Hannah had allotted them. They entered by the kitchen door. Mr. St.

15:36:56.140 --> 15:37:02.200
John, when he saw me, merely bowed and passed through. The two ladies stopped. Mary, in a few

15:37:02.200 --> 15:37:07.620
words, kindly and calmly expressing the pleasure she felt in seeing me well enough to be able to

15:37:07.620 --> 15:37:11.980
come down. Diana took my hand. She shook her head at me.

15:37:12.460 --> 15:37:18.280
You should have waited for my leave to descend, she said. You still look very pale, and so thin.

15:37:18.540 --> 15:37:20.600
Poor child! Poor girl!

15:37:21.800 --> 15:37:28.020
Diana had a voice toned to my ear like the cooing of a dove. She possessed eyes whose gaze I

15:37:28.020 --> 15:37:33.920
delighted to encounter. Her whole face seemed to me full of charm. Mary's countenance was

15:37:33.920 --> 15:37:39.500
equally intelligent, her features equally pretty, but her expression was more reserved,

15:37:39.860 --> 15:37:45.340
and her manners, though gentle, more distant. Diana looked and spoke with a certain authority.

15:37:45.840 --> 15:37:51.100
She had a will, evidently. It was my nature to feel pleasure in yielding to an authority

15:37:51.100 --> 15:37:57.260
supported like hers, and to bend, where my conscience and self-respect permitted,

15:37:57.880 --> 15:37:59.780
to an active will.

15:37:59.780 --> 15:38:04.740
And what business have you here? she continued. It is not your place.

15:38:05.260 --> 15:38:10.160
Mary and I sit in the kitchen sometimes, because at home we like to be free, even to license,

15:38:10.600 --> 15:38:13.520
but you are a visitor and must go into the parlour.

15:38:14.340 --> 15:38:16.020
I am very well here.

15:38:16.560 --> 15:38:19.940
Not at all, with Hannah bustling about and covering you with flour.

15:38:21.060 --> 15:38:24.220
Besides, the fire is too hot for you, interposed Mary.

15:38:24.220 --> 15:38:30.340
To be sure, added her sister, come, you must be obedient. And still holding my hand,

15:38:30.400 --> 15:38:33.300
she made me rise and led me into the inner room.

15:38:33.980 --> 15:38:38.680
Sit there, she said, placing me on the sofa, while we take our things off and get the tea ready.

15:38:39.180 --> 15:38:44.560
It is another privilege we exercise in our little moorland home, to prepare our own meals when we

15:38:44.560 --> 15:38:50.440
are so inclined, or when Hannah is baking, brewing, washing, or ironing. She closed the

15:38:50.440 --> 15:38:56.680
door, leaving me soulless with Mr. St. John, who sat opposite, a book or newspaper in his hand.

15:38:57.120 --> 15:39:00.560
I examined first the parlour, and then its occupant.

15:39:01.140 --> 15:39:07.060
The parlour was rather a small room, very plainly furnished, yet comfortable, because clean and

15:39:07.060 --> 15:39:12.940
neat. The old-fashioned chairs were very bright, and the walnut wood table was like a looking glass.

15:39:13.500 --> 15:39:19.140
A few strange antique portraits of the men and women of other days decorated the stained walls.

15:39:19.140 --> 15:39:24.080
A cupboard with glass doors contained some books and an ancient set of china.

15:39:24.760 --> 15:39:30.480
There was no superfluous ornament in the room, not one modern piece of furniture save a brace

15:39:30.480 --> 15:39:36.880
of work-boxes and a lady's desk in rosewood which stood on a side table. Everything,

15:39:37.040 --> 15:39:41.960
including the carpet and curtains, looked at once well worn and well saved.

15:39:43.160 --> 15:39:47.180
Mr. St. John, sitting as still as one of the dusty pictures on the walls,

15:39:47.180 --> 15:39:53.580
keeping his eyes fixed on the page he perused, and his lips mutely sealed, was easy enough to

15:39:53.580 --> 15:40:00.400
examine. Had he been a statue instead of a man, he could not have been easier. He was young,

15:40:00.560 --> 15:40:07.860
perhaps from twenty-eight to thirty, tall, slender. His face riveted the eye. It was like a

15:40:07.860 --> 15:40:15.980
Greek face, very pure in outline, quite a straight, classic nose, quite an Athenian mouth and chin.

15:40:16.500 --> 15:40:22.700
It is seldom, indeed, an English face come so near the antique models as did his. He might

15:40:22.700 --> 15:40:28.400
well be a little shocked at the irregularity of my liniments, his own being so harmonious.

15:40:28.940 --> 15:40:35.200
His eyes were large and blue, with brown lashes. His high forehead, colorless as ivory,

15:40:35.580 --> 15:40:39.120
was partially streaked over by careless locks of fair hair.

15:40:40.300 --> 15:40:46.920
This is a gentle delineation, is it not, reader? Yet he whom it describes scarcely impressed one

15:40:46.920 --> 15:40:52.540
with the idea of a gentle, a yielding, an impressible, or even of a placid nature.

15:40:53.400 --> 15:40:58.500
Quiescent as he now sat, there was something about his nostril, his mouth, his brow,

15:40:58.920 --> 15:41:04.720
which to my perceptions indicated elements within either restless, or hard, or eager.

15:41:05.420 --> 15:41:11.940
He did not speak to me one word, nor even direct to me one glance, till his sisters returned.

15:41:12.980 --> 15:41:18.120
Diana, as she passed in and out, in the course of preparing tea, brought me a little cake,

15:41:18.300 --> 15:41:19.680
baked on the top of the oven.

15:41:20.420 --> 15:41:25.420
Eat that now, she said, you must be hungry. Hannah says you have had nothing but some

15:41:25.420 --> 15:41:31.320
gruel since breakfast. I did not refuse it, for my appetite was awakened and keen.

15:41:31.320 --> 15:41:36.900
Mr. Rivers now closed his book, approached the table, and as he took a seat fixed his

15:41:36.900 --> 15:41:42.500
blue pictorial-looking eyes full on me. There was an unceremonious directness,

15:41:42.960 --> 15:41:48.400
a searching, decided steadfastness in his gaze now, which told that intention,

15:41:48.860 --> 15:41:52.520
and not diffidence, had hitherto kept it averted from the stranger.

15:41:53.280 --> 15:41:55.140
You are very hungry, he said.

15:41:55.140 --> 15:42:03.340
I am, sir. It is my way, it always was my way, by instinct, ever to meet the brief with brevity,

15:42:03.840 --> 15:42:10.040
the direct with plainness. It is well for you that a low fever has forced you to abstain for

15:42:10.040 --> 15:42:14.260
the last three days. There would have been danger in yielding to the cravings of your

15:42:14.260 --> 15:42:18.820
appetite at first. Now you may eat, though still not immoderately.

15:42:19.520 --> 15:42:26.680
I trust I shall not eat long at your expense, sir, was my very clumsily contrived, unpolished

15:42:26.680 --> 15:42:32.540
answer. No, he said coolly, when you have indicated to us the residence of your friends,

15:42:32.620 --> 15:42:39.200
we can write to them, and you may be restored to home. That, I must plainly tell you, is out of my

15:42:39.200 --> 15:42:46.340
power to do, being absolutely without home and friends. The three looked at me, but not

15:42:46.340 --> 15:42:51.540
trustfully. I felt there was no suspicion in their glances, there was more of curiosity.

15:42:52.400 --> 15:42:57.720
I speak particularly of the young ladies. St. John's eyes, though clear enough in a literal

15:42:57.720 --> 15:43:04.180
sense, in a figurative one were difficult to fathom. He seemed to use them rather as instruments to

15:43:04.180 --> 15:43:10.980
search other people's thoughts, than as agents to reveal his own. The which combination of keenness

15:43:10.980 --> 15:43:16.180
and reserve was considerably more calculated to embarrass than to encourage.

15:43:18.040 --> 15:43:22.840
Do you mean to say, he asked, that you are completely isolated from every connection?

15:43:23.800 --> 15:43:30.180
I do. Not a tie links me to any living thing. Not a claim do I possess to admittance under

15:43:30.180 --> 15:43:37.660
any roof in England. A most singular position at your age. Here I saw his glance directed to my

15:43:37.660 --> 15:43:43.700
hands, which were folded on the table before me. I wondered what he sought there. His words

15:43:43.700 --> 15:43:50.820
soon explained the quest. You have never been married? You are a spinster? Diana laughed.

15:43:50.880 --> 15:43:57.720
Why, she can't be above seventeen or eighteen years old, St. John, said she. I am near nineteen,

15:43:58.080 --> 15:44:05.660
but I am not married. No. I felt a burning glow mount to my face, for bitter and agitating

15:44:05.660 --> 15:44:12.040
recollections were awakened by the allusion to marriage. They all saw the embarrassment

15:44:12.040 --> 15:44:18.440
and the emotion. Diana and Mary relieved me by turning their eyes elsewhere than to my crimsoned

15:44:18.440 --> 15:44:24.260
visage. But the colder and sterner brother continued to gaze till the trouble he had

15:44:24.260 --> 15:44:30.220
excited forced out tears as well as colour. Where did you last reside, he now asked?

15:44:30.220 --> 15:44:36.260
You are too inquisitive, St. John, murmured Mary in a low voice, but he leaned over the

15:44:36.260 --> 15:44:43.140
table and required an answer by a second firm and piercing look. The name of the place where

15:44:43.140 --> 15:44:52.400
and of the person with whom I lived is my secret, I replied concisely. Which, if you like, you have,

15:44:52.400 --> 15:44:57.520
in my opinion, a right to keep, both from St. John and every other questioner, remarked Diana.

15:44:58.600 --> 15:45:03.900
Yet if I know nothing about you or your history, I cannot help you, he said. And you need help,

15:45:04.100 --> 15:45:11.020
do you not? I need it, and I seek it so far, sir, that some true philanthropist will put me in the

15:45:11.020 --> 15:45:17.360
way of getting work which I can do, and the remuneration for which will keep me, but if in

15:45:17.360 --> 15:45:24.460
the barest necessities of life. I know not whether I am a true philanthropist, yet I am willing to

15:45:24.980 --> 15:45:31.180
utmost of my power in a purpose so honest. First, then, tell me what you have been accustomed to do

15:45:31.180 --> 15:45:38.540
and what you can do. I had now swallowed my tea. I was mightily refreshed by the beverage, as much

15:45:38.540 --> 15:45:46.880
so as a giant with wine, it gave me new tone to my unstrung nerves, and it enabled me to address this

15:45:46.880 --> 15:45:54.040
penetrating young judge steadily. Mr. Rivers, I said, turning to him, and looking at him as he

15:45:54.040 --> 15:46:00.420
looked at me, openly and without diffidence, you and your sisters have done me a great service,

15:46:00.860 --> 15:46:06.560
the greatest man can do to his fellow being. You have rescued me by your noble hospitality from

15:46:06.560 --> 15:46:14.480
death. This benefit conferred gives you an unlimited claim on my gratitude, and a claim to a certain

15:46:14.480 --> 15:46:20.740
extent on my confidence. I will tell you as much of the history of the wanderer you have harbored,

15:46:20.740 --> 15:46:26.220
as I can tell, without compromising my own peace of mind, my own security,

15:46:26.440 --> 15:46:33.900
moral and physical, and that of others. I am an orphan, the daughter of a clergyman.

15:46:34.520 --> 15:46:40.480
My parents died before I could know them. I was brought up a dependent, educated in a charitable

15:46:40.480 --> 15:46:46.580
institution. I will even tell you the name of the establishment, where I passed six years as a pupil

15:46:46.580 --> 15:46:52.880
and two as a teacher, Lowood Orphan Asylum. You will have heard of it, Mr. Rivers.

15:46:53.400 --> 15:46:59.120
The Reverend Robert Brocklehurst is the treasurer. I have heard of Mr. Brocklehurst,

15:46:59.600 --> 15:47:06.660
and I have seen the school. I left Lowood nearly a year since to become a private governess.

15:47:06.900 --> 15:47:13.040
I obtained a good situation and was happy. This place I was obliged to leave four days before I

15:47:13.040 --> 15:47:19.500
came here. The reason of my departure I cannot and ought not to explain. It would be useless,

15:47:19.980 --> 15:47:26.580
dangerous, and would sound incredible. No blame attached to me. I am as free from culpability

15:47:26.580 --> 15:47:33.700
as any one of you three. Miserable I am and must be for a time, for the catastrophe which drove me

15:47:33.700 --> 15:47:41.620
from a house I had found a paradise was of a strange and direful nature. I observed but two

15:47:41.620 --> 15:47:48.840
points in planning my departure—speed, secrecy. To secure these I had to leave behind me everything

15:47:48.840 --> 15:47:54.540
I possessed except a small parcel, which in my hurry and trouble of mind I forgot to take out of

15:47:54.540 --> 15:48:01.460
the coach that brought me to Whitcross. To this neighbourhood then I came quite destitute. I slept

15:48:01.460 --> 15:48:07.700
two nights in the open air and wandered about two days without crossing a threshold. But twice in

15:48:07.700 --> 15:48:14.240
space of time did I taste food, and it was when brought by hunger, exhaustion, and despair almost

15:48:14.240 --> 15:48:20.860
to the last gasp that you, Mr. Rivers, forbade me to perish of want at your door and took me under

15:48:20.860 --> 15:48:28.620
the shelter of your roof. I know all your sisters have done for me, for I have not been insensible

15:48:28.620 --> 15:48:36.680
during my seeming torpor, and I owe to their spontaneous, genuine, genial compassion as large

15:48:36.680 --> 15:48:39.720
as your evangelical charity."

15:48:40.660 --> 15:48:44.960
"'Don't make her talk any more now, St. John,' said Diana, as I paused.

15:48:45.020 --> 15:48:50.000
"'She is evidently not yet fit for excitement. Come to the sofa and sit down, Miss Elliot.'

15:48:50.800 --> 15:48:57.840
I gave an involuntary half-start at hearing the alias. I had forgotten my new name. Mr. Rivers,

15:48:57.960 --> 15:49:00.720
whom nothing seemed to escape, noticed it at once.

15:49:01.240 --> 15:49:04.120
"'You said your name was Jane Elliot,' he observed.

15:49:04.780 --> 15:49:10.340
I did say so, and it is the name by which I think it expedient to be called at present,

15:49:10.860 --> 15:49:15.380
but it is not my real name, and when I hear it, it sounds strange to me.

15:49:16.260 --> 15:49:18.090
"'Your real name you will not give?'

15:49:18.900 --> 15:49:24.040
No, I fear discovery above all things, and whatever disclosure would lead to it I avoid.'

15:49:25.020 --> 15:49:27.660
"'You are quite right, I am sure,' said Diana.

15:49:28.000 --> 15:49:30.660
"'Now do, brother, let her be at peace a while.'

15:49:31.220 --> 15:49:35.900
But when St. John had mused a few moments, he recommended as imperturbably,

15:49:35.900 --> 15:49:38.100
and with as much acumen as ever,

15:49:38.320 --> 15:49:41.860
"'You would not like to be long dependent on our hospitality.

15:49:42.060 --> 15:49:46.780
You would wish, I see, to dispense as soon as may be with my sister's compassion,

15:49:47.220 --> 15:49:52.100
and above all with my charity. I am quite sensible of the distinction drawn,

15:49:52.220 --> 15:49:57.140
nor do I resent it. It is just. You desire to be independent of us.'

15:49:57.940 --> 15:50:05.700
I do. I have already said so. Show me how to work, or how to seek work. That is all I now ask.

15:50:05.860 --> 15:50:11.300
Then let me go, if it be but to the meanest cottage. But till then, allow me to stay here.'

15:50:12.180 --> 15:50:15.760
I dread another essay of the horrors of homeless destitution.

15:50:17.180 --> 15:50:21.360
"'Indeed you shall stay here,' said Diana, putting her white hand on my head.

15:50:21.360 --> 15:50:27.620
"'You shall,' repeated Mary, in the tone of undemonstrative sincerity which seemed natural to

15:50:27.620 --> 15:50:31.960
her. "'My sisters, you see, have a pleasure in keeping you,' said Mr. St. John,

15:50:32.060 --> 15:50:36.280
as they would have a pleasure in keeping and cherishing a half-frozen bird some wintry wind

15:50:36.280 --> 15:50:41.180
might have driven through their casement. I feel more inclined to put you in the way of keeping

15:50:41.180 --> 15:50:51.340
yourself, and shall endeavour to do so. But observe, my sphere is narrow. I am but the

15:50:51.340 --> 15:50:57.880
homeless sort, and if you are inclined to despise the day of small things, seek some more efficient

15:50:57.880 --> 15:51:03.740
sucker than such as I can offer.' "'She has already said that she is willing to do anything honest

15:51:03.740 --> 15:51:09.040
she can do,' answered Diana for me. "'And you know, St. John, she has no choice of helpers.

15:51:09.400 --> 15:51:12.250
She is forced to put up with such crusty people as you.'

15:51:13.840 --> 15:51:18.680
"'I will be a dressmaker. I will be a plain workwoman. I will be a servant,

15:51:18.680 --> 15:51:21.640
a nurse-girl, if I can be no better,' I answered.

15:51:22.740 --> 15:51:25.580
"'Right,' said Mr. St. John quite coolly.

15:51:25.740 --> 15:51:30.140
"'If such is your spirit, I promise to aid you in my own time and way.'

15:51:30.900 --> 15:51:34.960
He now resumed the book with which he had been occupied before tea.

15:51:35.500 --> 15:51:41.880
I soon withdrew, for I had talked as much and sat up as long as my present strength would permit.

15:52:01.740 --> 15:52:02.700
CHAPTER XXX.

15:52:03.120 --> 15:52:07.000
The more I knew of the inmates of Morehouse, the better I liked them.

15:52:07.400 --> 15:52:13.780
In a few days I had so far recovered my health that I could sit up all day and walk out sometimes.

15:52:13.780 --> 15:52:20.560
I could join with Diana and Mary in all their occupations, converse with them as much as they wished,

15:52:21.020 --> 15:52:23.620
and aid them when and where they would allow me.

15:52:24.040 --> 15:52:30.140
There was a reviving pleasure in this intercourse, of a kind now tasted by me for the first time,

15:52:30.580 --> 15:52:36.180
the pleasure arising from perfect congeniality of tastes, sentiments, and principles.

15:52:37.240 --> 15:52:41.720
I liked to read what they liked to read. What they enjoyed delighted me.

15:52:41.720 --> 15:52:46.140
What they approved I reverenced. They loved their sequestered home.

15:52:46.700 --> 15:52:52.500
I, too, in the gray, small, antique structure, with its low roof, its lattice casements,

15:52:52.760 --> 15:52:59.940
its moldering walls, its avenue of aged furs, all grown a slant under the stress of mountain winds,

15:53:00.520 --> 15:53:06.400
its garden dark with yew and holly, and where no flowers but of the hardiest species would bloom,

15:53:06.860 --> 15:53:09.140
found a charm both potent and permanent.

15:53:09.940 --> 15:53:13.260
They clung to the purple moors behind and around their dwelling,

15:53:13.880 --> 15:53:18.480
to the hollow vale into which the pebbly bridle path leading from their gate descended,

15:53:18.940 --> 15:53:24.880
and which wound between fernbanks first and then amongst a few of the wildest little pasture fields

15:53:24.880 --> 15:53:30.860
that ever bordered a wilderness of heath, or gave sustenance to a flock of gray moorland sheep,

15:53:31.160 --> 15:53:37.020
with their little mossy-faced lambs. They clung to this scene, I say, with a perfect

15:53:37.020 --> 15:53:43.240
enthusiasm of attachment. I could comprehend the feeling and share both its strength and truth.

15:53:43.840 --> 15:53:49.100
I saw the fascination of the locality. I felt the consecration of its loneliness.

15:53:49.940 --> 15:53:56.360
My eye feasted on the outline of swell and sweep, on the wild coloring communicated to ridge and

15:53:56.360 --> 15:54:03.640
dell, by moss, by heathbell, by flower-sprinkled turf, by brilliant bracken and mellow granite

15:54:04.500 --> 15:54:11.460
These details were just to me what they were to them, so many pure and sweet sources of pleasure.

15:54:12.240 --> 15:54:18.240
The strong blast and the soft breeze, the rough and the halcyon day, the hours of sunrise and

15:54:18.240 --> 15:54:23.860
sunset, the moonlight and the clouded night, developed for me in these regions the same

15:54:23.860 --> 15:54:29.840
attraction as for them, wound round my faculties the same spell that entranced theirs.

15:54:31.540 --> 15:54:37.620
Indoors we agreed equally well. They were both more accomplished and better read than I was,

15:54:38.060 --> 15:54:42.420
but with eagerness I followed in the path of knowledge they had trodden before me.

15:54:42.860 --> 15:54:48.180
I devoured the books they lent me. Then it was full satisfaction to discuss with them in the

15:54:48.180 --> 15:54:54.080
evening what I had perused during the day. Thought fitted thought, opinion met opinion,

15:54:54.080 --> 15:54:56.900
we coincided, in short, perfectly.

15:54:58.120 --> 15:55:04.800
If in our trio there was a superior and a leader it was Diana. Physically she far excelled me,

15:55:04.860 --> 15:55:10.680
she was handsome, she was vigorous. In her animal spirits there was an affluence of life

15:55:10.680 --> 15:55:16.420
and certainty of flow, such as excited my wonder, while it baffled my comprehension.

15:55:16.960 --> 15:55:23.060
I could talk a while when the evening commenced, but the first gush of vivacity and fluency gone,

15:55:23.060 --> 15:55:30.040
I was feigned to sit on a stool at Diana's feet, to rest my head on her knee, and listen alternately

15:55:30.040 --> 15:55:36.780
to her and Mary, while they sounded thoroughly the topic on which I had but touched. Diana offered

15:55:36.780 --> 15:55:43.720
to teach me German. I liked to learn of her. I saw the part of instructress pleased and suited her,

15:55:44.180 --> 15:55:50.420
that of scholar pleased and suited me no less. Our natures dovetailed mutual affection of the

15:55:50.420 --> 15:55:56.480
strongest kind was the result. They discovered I could draw. Their pencils and color boxes were

15:55:56.480 --> 15:56:03.160
immediately at my service. My skill, greater in this one point than theirs, surprised and charmed

15:56:03.160 --> 15:56:09.440
them. Mary would sit and watch me by the hour together. Then she would take lessons, and a

15:56:09.440 --> 15:56:16.840
docile, intelligent, assiduous pupil she made. Thus occupied and mutually entertained, days passed

15:56:16.840 --> 15:56:24.980
like hours, and weeks like days. As to Mr. St. John, the intimacy which had arisen so naturally

15:56:24.980 --> 15:56:31.380
and rapidly between me and his sisters did not extend to him. One reason of the distance yet

15:56:31.380 --> 15:56:37.720
observed between us was that he was comparatively seldom at home. A large proportion of his time

15:56:37.720 --> 15:56:42.600
appeared devoted to visiting the sick and poor among the scattered population of his parish.

15:56:43.320 --> 15:56:48.980
No weather seemed to hinder him in these pastoral excursions. Rain or fair he would,

15:56:49.320 --> 15:56:55.080
when his hours of morning study were over, take his hat and, followed by his father's old pointer,

15:56:55.320 --> 15:57:01.780
Carlo, go out on his mission of love or duty. I scarcely know in which light he regarded it.

15:57:02.400 --> 15:57:08.280
Sometimes, when the day was very unfavorable, his sisters would expostulate. He would then

15:57:08.280 --> 15:57:14.580
with a peculiar smile, more solemn than cheerful. And if I let a gust of wind or a sprinkling of

15:57:14.580 --> 15:57:20.280
rain turn me aside from these easy tasks, what preparation would such sloth be for the future,

15:57:20.420 --> 15:57:26.640
I proposed to myself? Diana and Mary's general answer to this question was a sigh,

15:57:27.020 --> 15:57:33.260
and some minutes of apparently mournful meditation. But besides his frequent absences,

15:57:33.260 --> 15:57:38.560
there was another barrier to friendship with him. He seemed of a reserved and abstracted

15:57:38.560 --> 15:57:44.620
and even of a brooding nature. Zealous in his ministerial labors, blameless in his life and

15:57:44.620 --> 15:57:51.420
habits, he yet did not appear to enjoy that mental serenity, that inward content, which should be the

15:57:51.420 --> 15:57:57.440
reward of every sincere Christian and practical philanthropist. Often of an evening, when he sat

15:57:57.440 --> 15:58:03.720
the window, his desk and papers before him, he would cease reading or writing, rest his chin on

15:58:03.720 --> 15:58:10.040
his hand, and deliver himself up to I know not what course of thought, but that it was perturbed,

15:58:10.160 --> 15:58:14.840
and exciting might be seen in the frequent flash and changeful dilation of his eye.

15:58:15.800 --> 15:58:21.760
I think, moreover, that nature was not to him that treasury of delight that it was to his sisters.

15:58:21.760 --> 15:58:27.940
He expressed once, and but once in my hearing, a strong sense of the rugged charm of the hills,

15:58:28.360 --> 15:58:34.300
and an inborn affection for the dark roof and hoary walls he called his home. But there was more

15:58:34.300 --> 15:58:39.900
of gloom than pleasure in the tone and words in which the sentiment was manifested, and never did

15:58:39.900 --> 15:58:45.840
he seem to roam the moors for the sake of their soothing silence, never seek out or dwell upon the

15:58:45.840 --> 15:58:52.680
thousand peaceful delights they could yield. Incommunicative as he was, some time elapsed

15:58:52.680 --> 15:58:58.760
before I had an opportunity of gauging his mind. I first got an idea of its caliber when I heard

15:58:58.760 --> 15:59:05.240
him preach in his own church, at Morton. I wish I could describe that sermon, but it is past my

15:59:05.240 --> 15:59:12.780
power. I cannot even render faithfully the effect it produced on me. It began calm, and indeed,

15:59:12.780 --> 15:59:18.940
as far as delivery and pitch of voice went, it was calm to the end. An earnestly felt,

15:59:19.160 --> 15:59:24.380
yet strictly restrained zeal, breathed soon in the distant accents, and prompted the nervous

15:59:24.380 --> 15:59:30.740
language. This grew to force, compressed, condensed, controlled. The heart was thrilled,

15:59:30.780 --> 15:59:42.760
the mind astonished by the power of the preacher, neither was softened. Throughout there was a

15:59:42.760 --> 15:59:50.660
doctrine, election, predestination, reprobation were frequent, and each reference to these points

15:59:50.660 --> 15:59:56.860
sounded like a sentence pronounced for doom. When he had done, instead of feeling better, calmer,

15:59:57.000 --> 16:00:03.640
more enlightened by his discourse, I experienced an inexpressible sadness, for it seemed to me,

16:00:03.960 --> 16:00:09.120
I know not whether equally so to others, that the eloquence to which I had been listening

16:00:09.120 --> 16:00:15.640
had sprung from a depth where lay turbid dregs of disappointment, where move troubling impulses

16:00:15.640 --> 16:00:22.480
of insatiate yearnings and disquieting aspirations. I was sure St. John Rivers, pure-lived,

16:00:23.220 --> 16:00:30.040
conscientious, zealous as he was, had not yet found that peace of God which passeth all understanding.

16:00:30.460 --> 16:00:36.300
He had no more found it, I thought, than had I. With my concealed and wrecking regrets for my

16:00:36.300 --> 16:00:41.640
broken idol and lost Elysium, regrets to which I have latterly avoided referring,

16:00:42.040 --> 16:00:48.280
but which possessed me and tyrannized over me ruthlessly. Meantime a month was gone,

16:00:48.740 --> 16:00:53.800
Diana and Mary were soon to leave Morehouse, and return to the far different life and scene

16:00:53.800 --> 16:00:59.100
which awaited them, as governesses in a large fashionable south of England city,

16:00:59.560 --> 16:01:05.120
where each held a situation in families by whose wealthy and haughty members they were regarded

16:01:05.120 --> 16:01:11.080
only as humble dependents, and who neither knew nor sought one of their innate excellences,

16:01:11.500 --> 16:01:17.040
and appreciated only their acquired accomplishments, as they appreciated the skill of their cook,

16:01:17.460 --> 16:01:23.700
or the taste of their waiting-woman. Mr. St. John had said nothing to me yet about the employment

16:01:23.700 --> 16:01:29.420
he had promised to obtain for me, yet it became urgent that I should have a vocation of some kind.

16:01:30.200 --> 16:01:34.680
One morning, being left alone with him a few minutes in the parlour, I ventured to

16:01:34.680 --> 16:01:40.360
approach the window recess, which his table, chair, and desk consecrated as a kind of study,

16:01:40.800 --> 16:01:45.860
and I was going to speak, though not very well knowing in what words to frame my inquiry,

16:01:46.380 --> 16:01:52.140
for it is at all times difficult to break the ice of reserve glassing over such natures as his,

16:01:52.660 --> 16:01:56.340
when he saved me the trouble by being the first to commence a dialogue.

16:01:57.420 --> 16:02:01.880
Looking at me as I drew near, you have a question to ask of me, he said?

16:02:02.520 --> 16:02:07.620
Yes, I wish to know whether you have heard of any service I can offer myself to undertake.

16:02:08.800 --> 16:02:14.640
I found or devised something for you three weeks ago, but as you seemed both useful and happy here,

16:02:14.980 --> 16:02:20.540
as my sisters had evidently become attached to you, and your society gave them unusual pleasure,

16:02:21.040 --> 16:02:26.400
I deemed it inexpedient to break in on your mutual comfort, till their approaching departure

16:02:26.960 --> 16:02:29.060
should render yours necessary.

16:02:29.920 --> 16:02:32.600
And they will go in three days now, I said.

16:02:33.500 --> 16:02:37.100
Yes, and when they go, I shall return to the parsonage at Morton.

16:02:37.460 --> 16:02:40.860
Hannah will accompany me, and this old house will be shut up.

16:02:41.840 --> 16:02:46.420
I waited a few moments, expecting he would go on with the subject first broached,

16:02:46.600 --> 16:02:49.640
but he seemed to have entered another train of reflection.

16:02:50.140 --> 16:02:53.120
His look denoted abstraction from me and my business.

16:02:53.120 --> 16:02:57.020
I was obliged to recall him to a theme which was of necessity,

16:02:57.480 --> 16:03:00.040
one of close and anxious interest to me.

16:03:01.000 --> 16:03:03.620
What is the employment you had in view, Mr. Rivers?

16:03:04.140 --> 16:03:08.160
I hope this delay will not have increased the difficulty of securing it.

16:03:08.960 --> 16:03:14.280
Oh no, since it is an employment which depends only on me to give and you to accept.

16:03:15.520 --> 16:03:19.440
He again paused. There seemed a reluctance to continue.

16:03:19.440 --> 16:03:26.220
I grew impatient. A restless movement or two and an eager and exacting glance fastened on his face

16:03:26.220 --> 16:03:31.280
conveyed the feeling to him as effectually as words could have done, and with less trouble.

16:03:32.220 --> 16:03:36.500
You need be in no hurry to hear, he said. Let me frankly tell you,

16:03:36.740 --> 16:03:42.660
I have nothing eligible or profitable to suggest. Before I explain, recall, if you please,

16:03:43.120 --> 16:03:48.480
my notice clearly given that if I helped you it must be as the blind man would help the lame.

16:03:49.120 --> 16:03:52.680
I am poor, for I find that when I have paid my father's debts,

16:03:53.340 --> 16:03:58.960
all the patrimony remaining to me will be this crumbling grange, the row of scathed firs behind,

16:03:59.320 --> 16:04:05.180
and the patch of moorish soil with the yew trees and holly bushes in front. I am obscure.

16:04:05.900 --> 16:04:09.960
Rivers is an old name, but of the three sole descendants of the race,

16:04:10.080 --> 16:04:15.480
two earn the dependence crust among strangers, and the third considers himself an alien from

16:04:15.480 --> 16:04:22.500
his native country, not only for life but in death. Yes, and deems and is bound to deem himself

16:04:22.500 --> 16:04:28.820
honoured by the lot, and aspires but after the day when the cross of separation from fleshly ties

16:04:28.820 --> 16:04:34.340
shall be laid on his shoulders, and when the head of that church militant, of whose humblest

16:04:34.340 --> 16:04:42.140
members he is one, shall give the word, rise, follow me. Syngin said these words as he pronounced

16:04:42.140 --> 16:04:48.680
his sermons, with a quiet deep voice, with an unflushed cheek, and a coruscating radiance of

16:04:48.680 --> 16:04:57.580
glance. He resumed. And since I am myself poor and obscure, I can offer you but a service of poverty

16:04:57.580 --> 16:05:03.740
and obscurity. You may even think it degrading, for I see now your habits have been what the

16:05:03.740 --> 16:05:10.360
world calls refined, your tastes lean to the ideal, and your society has at least been amongst the

16:05:10.360 --> 16:05:17.320
educated. But I consider that no service degrades which can better our race. I hold that the more

16:05:17.320 --> 16:05:22.080
arid and unreclaimed the soil where the Christian labourer's task of tillage is appointed him,

16:05:22.400 --> 16:05:27.880
the scantier the mead his toil brings, the higher the honour. His, under such circumstances,

16:05:28.020 --> 16:05:33.140
is the destiny of the pioneer, and the first pioneers of the gospel were the apostles,

16:05:33.140 --> 16:05:36.240
their captain was Jesus, the Redeemer himself.

16:05:37.040 --> 16:05:45.060
Well, I said, as he again paused, proceed. He looked at me before he proceeded. Indeed,

16:05:45.200 --> 16:05:50.940
he seemed leisurely to read my face, as if its features and lines were characters on a page,

16:05:51.400 --> 16:05:56.740
the conclusions drawn from the scrutiny he partially expressed in his succeeding observations.

16:05:57.460 --> 16:06:03.240
I believe you will accept the post I offer you, said he, and hold it for a while, not permanently,

16:06:03.600 --> 16:06:09.640
though, any more than I could permanently keep the narrow and narrowing, the tranquil hidden office

16:06:09.640 --> 16:06:16.920
of English country incumbent, for in your nature is an alloy as detrimental to repose as that in mine,

16:06:17.100 --> 16:06:23.260
though of a different kind. Do explain, I urged, while he halted once again.

16:06:24.200 --> 16:06:30.760
I will, and you shall hear how poor the proposal is, how trivial, how cramping. I shall not stay

16:06:30.760 --> 16:06:37.040
long at Morton, now that my father is dead, and that I am my own master. I shall leave the place,

16:06:37.080 --> 16:06:42.800
probably in the course of a twelve month, but while I do stay, I will exert myself to the utmost for

16:06:42.800 --> 16:06:53.240
its improvement. Morton, when I came to it two years ago, had no school. The children of the

16:06:53.240 --> 16:06:59.720
one for boys, I mean now to open a second school for girls. I have hired a building for the purpose

16:06:59.720 --> 16:07:05.220
with a cottage of two rooms attached to it for the mistress's house. Her salary will be thirty

16:07:05.220 --> 16:07:11.180
pounds a year. Her house is already furnished, very simply, but sufficiently, by the kindness

16:07:11.180 --> 16:07:17.500
of a lady, Miss Oliver, the only daughter of the sole rich man in my parish, Mr. Oliver,

16:07:17.500 --> 16:07:23.740
the proprietor of a needle factory and iron foundry in the valley. The same lady pays for

16:07:23.740 --> 16:07:29.120
the education and clothing of an orphan from the workhouse, on condition that she shall aid the

16:07:29.120 --> 16:07:34.860
mistress in such menial offices connected with her own house and the school, as her occupation

16:07:34.860 --> 16:07:40.120
of teaching will prevent her having time to discharge in person. Will you be this mistress?

16:07:41.560 --> 16:07:47.140
He put the question rather hurriedly. He seemed half to expect an indignant, or at least a

16:07:47.140 --> 16:07:53.340
disdainful rejection of the offer, not knowing all my thoughts and feelings, though guessing some,

16:07:53.720 --> 16:07:59.420
he could not tell in what light the lot would appear to me. In truth it was humble, but then

16:07:59.420 --> 16:08:05.140
it was sheltered and I wanted a safe asylum. It was plodding, but then, compared with that of

16:08:05.140 --> 16:08:11.440
a governess in a rich house, it was independent. And the fear of servitude with strangers entered

16:08:11.440 --> 16:08:18.920
my soul like iron. It was not ignoble, not unworthy, not mentally degrading. I made my

16:08:18.920 --> 16:08:24.860
decision. I thank you for the proposal, Mr. Rivers, and I accept it with all my heart.

16:08:25.520 --> 16:08:31.840
But you comprehend me, he said. It is a village school. Your scholars will be only poor girls,

16:08:32.360 --> 16:08:37.960
cottagers' children at the best, farmers' daughters. Knitting, sewing, reading, writing,

16:08:37.960 --> 16:08:43.060
ciphering will be all you will have to teach. What will you do with your accomplishments?

16:08:43.760 --> 16:08:47.440
What with the largest portion of your mind, sentiments, tastes?

16:08:48.720 --> 16:08:54.920
Save them till they are wanted. They will keep. You know what you undertake, then? I do.

16:08:55.720 --> 16:09:02.180
He now smiled, not a bitter or a sad smile, but one well pleased and deeply gratified.

16:09:02.800 --> 16:09:05.620
And when will you commence the exercise of your function?

16:09:06.700 --> 16:09:11.420
I will go to my house tomorrow, and open the school, if you like, next week.

16:09:12.140 --> 16:09:19.080
Very well, so be it. He rose and walked through the room. Standing still, he again looked at me.

16:09:19.400 --> 16:09:26.180
He shook his head. What do you disapprove of, Mr. Rivers, I asked. You will not stay at Morton

16:09:26.180 --> 16:09:34.820
No, no. Why? What is your reason for saying so? I read it in your eye. It is not of that description

16:09:34.820 --> 16:09:40.520
which promises the maintenance of an even tenor in life. I am not ambitious.

16:09:41.840 --> 16:09:48.540
He started at the word ambitious. He repeated. No. What made you think of ambition? Who is

16:09:49.180 --> 16:09:54.880
I know I am. But how did you find it out? I was speaking of myself.

16:09:55.780 --> 16:10:03.960
Well, if you are not ambitious, you are. He paused. What? I was going to say impassioned,

16:10:04.240 --> 16:10:09.620
but perhaps you would have misunderstood the word and been displeased. I mean that human

16:10:09.620 --> 16:10:15.800
affections and sympathies have a most powerful hold on you. I am sure you cannot long be content

16:10:15.800 --> 16:10:20.760
to pass your leisure and solitude, and to devote your working hours to a monotonous labor

16:10:20.760 --> 16:10:26.180
wholly void of stimulus. Any more than I can be content, he added with emphasis.

16:10:26.940 --> 16:10:33.580
To live here buried in morass, pent in with mountain, my nature that God gave me contravened,

16:10:33.900 --> 16:10:40.280
my faculties heaven-bestowed, paralyzed, made useless. You hear now how I contradict myself,

16:10:40.440 --> 16:10:45.360
I who preached contentment with a humble lot, and justified the vocations even of

16:10:45.360 --> 16:10:52.500
wood and drawers of water in God's service. I, his ordained minister, almost rave in my restlessness.

16:10:53.260 --> 16:10:57.260
Well, propensities and principles must be reconciled by some means.

16:10:58.620 --> 16:11:04.240
He left the room. In this brief hour I had learned more of him than in the whole previous month,

16:11:04.600 --> 16:11:12.000
yet still he puzzled me. Diana and Mary Rivers became more sad and silent as the day approached

16:11:12.000 --> 16:11:17.760
leaving their brother in their home. They both tried to appear as usual, but the sorrow they

16:11:17.760 --> 16:11:23.880
had to struggle against was one that could not be entirely conquered or concealed. Diana intimated

16:11:23.880 --> 16:11:28.840
that this would be a different parting from any they had ever yet known. It would probably,

16:11:29.060 --> 16:11:34.700
as far as St. John was concerned, be a parting for years. It might be a parting for life.

16:11:35.460 --> 16:11:41.940
He will sacrifice all to his long-framed resolves, she said. Natural affection and feelings more

16:11:41.940 --> 16:11:48.640
potent still. St. John looks quiet, Jane, but he hides a fever in his vitals. You would think him

16:11:48.640 --> 16:11:54.680
gentle. Yet in some things he is inexorable as death, and the worst of it is my conscience will

16:11:54.680 --> 16:12:00.400
hardly permit me to dissuade him from his severe decision. Certainly I cannot for a moment blame

16:12:00.400 --> 16:12:07.300
him for it. It is right, noble, Christian, yet it breaks my heart. And the tears gushed to her

16:12:07.300 --> 16:12:14.520
fine eyes. Mary bent her head low over her work. We are now without father, we shall soon be without

16:12:14.520 --> 16:12:21.100
home and brother, she murmured. At that moment a little accident supervened which seemed decreed

16:12:21.100 --> 16:12:27.020
by fate, purposely to prove the truth of the adage that misfortunes never come singly,

16:12:27.020 --> 16:12:31.860
and to add to their distresses the vexing one of the slip between the cup and the lip.

16:12:32.740 --> 16:12:36.080
St. John passed the window reading a letter. He entered.

16:12:37.240 --> 16:12:43.480
Our uncle John is dead, said he. Both the sisters seemed struck, not shocked or appalled.

16:12:43.900 --> 16:12:47.260
The tidings appeared in their eyes rather momentous than afflicting.

16:12:48.140 --> 16:12:54.340
Dead, repeated Diana. Yes. She riveted a searching gaze on her brother's face,

16:12:54.340 --> 16:13:02.200
and what then, she demanded in a low voice. What then die, he replied, maintaining a marble

16:13:02.200 --> 16:13:10.500
immobility of feature. What then? Why, nothing. Read. He threw the letter into her lap. She

16:13:10.500 --> 16:13:16.040
glanced over it and handed it to Mary. Mary perused it in silence and returned it to her brother.

16:13:16.600 --> 16:13:22.020
All three looked at each other and all three smiled, a dreary pensive smile enough.

16:13:23.140 --> 16:13:26.480
Amen. We can yet live, said Diana at last.

16:13:27.320 --> 16:13:31.200
At any rate, it makes us no worse off than we were before, remarked Mary.

16:13:32.040 --> 16:13:37.400
Only it forces rather strongly on the mind the picture of what might have been, said Mr. Rivers,

16:13:37.820 --> 16:13:40.780
and contrasts it somewhat too vividly with what is.

16:13:41.680 --> 16:13:45.380
He folded the letter and locked it in his desk, and again went out.

16:13:46.120 --> 16:13:50.060
For some minutes no one spoke. Diana then turned to me.

16:13:50.620 --> 16:13:56.060
Jane, you will wonder at us and our mysteries, she said, and think us hard-hearted beings not

16:13:56.060 --> 16:14:01.100
to be more moved at the death of so near a relation as an uncle, but we have never seen

16:14:01.100 --> 16:14:07.520
him or known him. He was my mother's brother. My father and he quarrelled long ago. It was

16:14:07.520 --> 16:14:13.200
by his advice that my father risked most of his property in the speculation that ruined him.

16:14:13.780 --> 16:14:19.660
Mutual recrimination passed between them. They parted in anger and were never reconciled.

16:14:20.060 --> 16:14:26.420
My uncle engaged afterwards in more prosperous undertakings. It appears he realized a fortune of

16:14:26.420 --> 16:14:32.680
twenty thousand pounds. He was never married and had no near kindred but ourselves, and one other

16:14:32.680 --> 16:14:38.840
person, not more closely related than we. My father always cherished the idea that he would

16:14:38.840 --> 16:14:45.100
atone for his error by leaving his possessions to us. That letter informs us that he has bequeathed

16:14:45.100 --> 16:14:50.500
every penny to the other relation, with the exception of thirty guineas, to be divided

16:14:50.500 --> 16:14:57.480
between St. John, Diana, and Mary Rivers, for the purchase of three mourning rings. He had a right,

16:14:57.480 --> 16:15:03.780
of course, to do as he pleased, and yet a momentary damp is cast on the spirits by the receipt of such

16:15:03.780 --> 16:15:10.180
news. Mary and I would have esteemed ourself rich with a thousand pounds each, and to St. John such

16:15:10.180 --> 16:15:14.280
sum would have been valuable, for the good it would have enabled him to do.

16:15:15.520 --> 16:15:21.420
This explanation given the subject was dropped, and no further reference made to it, by either

16:15:21.420 --> 16:15:28.900
Mr. Rivers or his sisters. The next day I left Marsh End for Morton. The day after, Diana and

16:15:28.900 --> 16:15:34.640
Mary quitted it for distant be. In a week Mr. Rivers and Hannah repaired to the parsonage,

16:15:34.640 --> 16:15:37.440
and so the old grange was abandoned.

16:16:02.1000 --> 16:16:05.140
CHAPTER XXXI.

16:16:05.940 --> 16:16:12.960
My home, then, when I at last find a home, is a cottage, a little room with white-washed

16:16:12.960 --> 16:16:19.140
walls and a sanded floor, containing four painted chairs and a table, a clock, a cupboard,

16:16:19.540 --> 16:16:25.320
with two or three plates and dishes, and a set of teethings in delft. Above, a chamber

16:16:25.320 --> 16:16:31.280
of the same dimensions as the kitchen, with a deal bedstead, and chest of drawers, small,

16:16:31.280 --> 16:16:36.580
yet too large to be filled with my scanty wardrobe, though the kindness of my gentle

16:16:36.580 --> 16:16:41.960
and generous friends has increased that by a modest stock of such things as are necessary.

16:16:42.880 --> 16:16:48.360
It is evening. I have dismissed, with the fee of an orange, the little orphan who serves

16:16:48.360 --> 16:16:55.620
as a handmaid. I am sitting alone on the hearth. This morning the village school opened. I

16:16:55.620 --> 16:17:02.820
had twenty scholars, but three of the number can read, none write or cipher, several knit,

16:17:02.980 --> 16:17:09.220
and a few sew a little. They speak with the broadest accent of the district. At present

16:17:09.220 --> 16:17:15.240
they and I have a difficulty in understanding each other's language. Some of them are unmannered,

16:17:15.420 --> 16:17:21.720
rough, intractable, as well as ignorant, but others are docile, have a wish to learn, and

16:17:21.720 --> 16:17:27.480
a disposition that pleases me. I must not forget that these coarsely clad little peasants

16:17:27.480 --> 16:17:33.560
are of flesh and blood as good as the scions of gentlest genealogy, and that the germs

16:17:33.560 --> 16:17:40.080
of native excellence, refinement, intelligence, kind feeling, are as likely to exist in their

16:17:40.080 --> 16:17:46.320
hearts as in those of the best born. My duty will be to develop these germs. Surely I shall

16:17:46.320 --> 16:17:52.480
some happiness in discharging that office. Much enjoyment I do not expect in the life

16:17:52.480 --> 16:17:58.640
opening before me, yet it will, doubtless, if I regulate my mind, and exert my powers

16:17:58.640 --> 16:18:05.400
as I ought, yield me enough to live on from day to day. Was I very gleeful, settled, content,

16:18:05.740 --> 16:18:10.180
during the hours I passed in yonder bare, humble classroom this morning and afternoon?

16:18:10.900 --> 16:18:20.040
Not to deceive myself, I must reply, no. I felt desolate to a degree. I felt, yes, idiot

16:18:20.040 --> 16:18:26.240
that I am. I felt degraded. I doubted I had taken a step which sank instead of rising

16:18:26.240 --> 16:18:32.040
me in the scale of social existence. I was weakly dismayed at the ignorance, the poverty,

16:18:32.220 --> 16:18:37.200
the coarseness of all I heard and saw round me. But let me not hate and despise myself

16:18:37.200 --> 16:18:43.780
too much for these feelings. I know them to be wrong. That is a great step gained. I shall

16:18:43.780 --> 16:18:48.880
strive to overcome them. To-morrow, I trust, I shall get the better of them partially,

16:18:49.200 --> 16:18:54.320
and in a few weeks, perhaps, they will be quite subdued. In a few months, it is possible

16:18:54.320 --> 16:18:59.720
the happiness of seeing progress, and a change for the better in my scholars, may substitute

16:18:59.720 --> 16:19:01.520
gratification for disgust.

16:19:02.820 --> 16:19:09.700
Meantime, let me ask myself one question. Which is better? To have surrendered to temptation,

16:19:10.280 --> 16:19:16.180
listened to passion, made no painful effort, no struggle, but to have sunk down in the

16:19:16.180 --> 16:19:21.300
silken snare, fallen asleep on the flowers covering it, wakening in a southern clime

16:19:21.300 --> 16:19:27.200
amongst the luxuries of a pleasure villa, to have been now living in France, Mr. Rochester's

16:19:27.200 --> 16:19:33.160
mistress, delirious with his love half my time, for he would, oh yes, he would have

16:19:33.160 --> 16:19:40.180
loved me well for a while. He did love me. No one will ever love me so again. I shall

16:19:40.180 --> 16:19:45.820
never more know the sweet homage given to beauty, youth, and grace, for never to anyone

16:19:45.820 --> 16:19:52.480
else shall I seem to possess these charms. He was fond and proud of me. It is what no

16:19:52.480 --> 16:19:54.460
man besides will ever be.

16:19:55.020 --> 16:20:00.800
But where am I wandering, and what am I saying, and above all feeling? Whether is it better,

16:20:00.840 --> 16:20:06.500
I ask, to be a slave to a fool's paradise at Marseilles, fevered with delusive bliss

16:20:06.500 --> 16:20:12.460
one hour, suffocating with the bitterest tears of remorse and shame the next? Or to be a

16:20:12.460 --> 16:20:18.080
village a school mistress, free and honest, in a breezy mountain nook in the healthy heart

16:20:18.080 --> 16:20:24.800
of England? Yes, I feel now that I was right when I adhered to principle and law, and scorned

16:20:24.800 --> 16:20:30.520
and crushed the insane promptings of a frenzied moment. God directed me to a correct choice.

16:20:30.980 --> 16:20:36.800
I thank his providence for the guidance. Having brought my eventide musings to this point,

16:20:37.160 --> 16:20:43.280
I rose, went to my door, and looked at the sunset of the harvest day, and at the quiet

16:20:43.280 --> 16:20:48.720
fields before my cottage, which, with the school, was distant half a mile from the village.

16:20:49.480 --> 16:20:56.740
The birds were singing their last strains. The air was mild and dew was balm. While I

16:20:56.740 --> 16:21:02.500
looked, I thought myself happy, and was surprised to find myself air-long weeping. And why?

16:21:02.820 --> 16:21:09.080
For the doom which had roughed me from adhesion to my master, for him I was no more to see.

16:21:09.350 --> 16:21:15.920
For the desperate grief and fatal fury, consequences of my departure, which might now, perhaps,

16:21:16.020 --> 16:21:21.240
be dragging him from the path of right, too far to leave hope of ultimate restoration

16:21:21.240 --> 16:21:27.660
thither. At this thought, I turned my face aside from the lovely sky of Eve and lonely

16:21:27.660 --> 16:21:33.960
vale of Morton. I say lonely, for in that bend of it, visible to me, there was no building

16:21:33.960 --> 16:21:39.760
apparent, save the church and the parsonage, half hidden trees, and, quite at the extremity,

16:21:40.100 --> 16:21:46.240
the roof of Vale Hall, where the rich Mr. Oliver and his daughter lived. I hid my eyes,

16:21:46.480 --> 16:21:51.920
and linked my head against the stone frame of my door. But soon a slight noise near the

16:21:51.920 --> 16:21:58.040
wicket which, shut in my tiny garden from the meadow beyond, it made me look up. A dog,

16:21:58.420 --> 16:22:05.040
old Carlo, Mr. Rivers's pointer, as I saw in a moment, was pushing the gate with his

16:22:05.040 --> 16:22:12.540
nose, and St. John himself leaned upon it with folded arms. His brow knit, his gaze

16:22:12.540 --> 16:22:17.640
grave almost to displeasure fixed on me. I asked him to come in.

16:22:17.960 --> 16:22:23.620
No, I cannot stay. I have only brought you a little parcel my sister's left for you.

16:22:23.620 --> 16:22:30.440
I think it contains a color box, pencils, and paper. I approached to take it. A welcome

16:22:30.440 --> 16:22:36.260
gift it was. He examined my face, I thought, with austerity as I came near. The traces

16:22:36.260 --> 16:22:39.160
of tears were doubtless very visible upon it.

16:22:39.880 --> 16:22:43.900
Have you found your first day's work harder than you expected? he asked.

16:22:45.060 --> 16:22:51.100
Oh, no, on the contrary. I think in time I shall get on with my scholars very well. But

16:22:51.100 --> 16:22:56.360
perhaps your accommodations, your cottage, your furniture, have disappointed your expectations.

16:22:56.860 --> 16:23:00.260
They are, in truth, scanty enough, but—

16:23:00.260 --> 16:23:07.440
I interrupted. My cottage is clean and weatherproof, my furniture sufficient and commodious. All

16:23:07.440 --> 16:23:12.1000
I see has made me thankful, not despondent. I am not absolutely such a fool and sensualist

16:23:12.1000 --> 16:23:19.520
as to regret the absence of a carpet, a sofa, and silver plate. Besides, five weeks ago

16:23:19.520 --> 16:23:25.360
I had nothing. I was an outcast, a beggar, a vagrant. Now I have acquaintance, a home,

16:23:25.420 --> 16:23:31.300
a business. I wonder at the goodness of God, the generosity of my friends, the bounty of

16:23:31.300 --> 16:23:37.460
my lot. I do not repine. But you feel solitude and oppression? The little house there behind

16:23:37.460 --> 16:23:43.300
you is dark and empty. I have hardly had time yet to enjoy a sense of tranquillity, much

16:23:43.300 --> 16:23:45.520
less to grow impatient under one of loneliness.

16:23:46.160 --> 16:23:51.660
Very well. I hope you feel the content you express. At any rate, your good sense will

16:23:51.660 --> 16:23:57.160
tell you that it is too soon yet to yield to the vacillating fears of Lot's wife. What

16:23:57.160 --> 16:24:02.200
you had left before I saw you, of course, I do not know. But I counsel you to resist

16:24:02.200 --> 16:24:07.900
firmly every temptation which would incline you to look back. Pursue your present career

16:24:08.620 --> 16:24:10.340
steadily—for some months, at least.

16:24:10.900 --> 16:24:17.740
It is what I mean to do, I answered. St. John continued. It is hard work to control the

16:24:17.740 --> 16:24:22.080
workings of inclination and turn the bent of nature, but that it may be done I know

16:24:22.080 --> 16:24:28.340
from experience. God has given us, in a measure, the power to make our own fate, and when our

16:24:28.340 --> 16:24:33.540
energies seem to demand a sustenance they cannot get, when our will strains after a

16:24:33.540 --> 16:24:39.240
path we may not follow, we need neither starve from inanation nor stand still in despair.

16:24:39.240 --> 16:24:44.460
We have but to seek another nourishment for the mind, as strong as the forbidden food

16:24:44.460 --> 16:24:51.380
it longed to taste, and perhaps purer, and to hew out for the adventurous foot a road

16:24:51.380 --> 16:24:56.600
as direct and broad as the one fortune has blocked up against us, if rougher than it.

16:24:57.540 --> 16:25:02.460
A year ago I was myself intensely miserable, because I thought I had made a mistake in

16:25:02.460 --> 16:25:07.780
entering the ministry. Its uniform duties wearied me to death. I burnt for the more

16:25:07.780 --> 16:25:13.300
active life of the world, for the more exciting toils of a literary career, for the destiny

16:25:13.300 --> 16:25:18.960
of an artist, author, orator, something rather than that of a priest, yes, the heart of a

16:25:18.960 --> 16:25:26.260
politician, of a soldier, of a votary of glory, a lover of renown, a luster after power beat

16:25:26.260 --> 16:25:33.320
under my curate surplus. I considered. My life was so wretched it must be changed or

16:25:33.320 --> 16:25:41.320
die. After a season of darkness and struggling, light broke and relief fell. My cramped existence

16:25:41.320 --> 16:25:47.640
all at once spread out to a plain without bounds. My powers heard a call from heaven to rise,

16:25:48.340 --> 16:25:55.540
gather their full strength, spread their wings, and mount beyond ken. God has an errand for me,

16:25:55.640 --> 16:26:02.060
to bear which afar, to deliver it well, skill and strength, courage and eloquence, the best

16:26:02.060 --> 16:26:07.980
qualifications of soldier, statesman and orator were all needed. For these all center in the good

16:26:07.980 --> 16:26:13.540
missionary. A missionary I resolved to be. From that moment my state of mind changed,

16:26:13.680 --> 16:26:18.360
the fetters dissolved and dropped from every faculty, leaving nothing of bondage but its

16:26:18.360 --> 16:26:24.500
galling soreness, which time can only heal. My father, indeed, imposed the determination,

16:26:24.820 --> 16:26:30.840
but since his death I have not a legitimate obstacle to contend with. Some affairs settled,

16:26:30.840 --> 16:26:36.460
a successor for Morton provided, an entanglement or two of the feelings broken through or cut

16:26:36.460 --> 16:26:42.780
asunder, a last conflict with human weakness, in which I know I shall overcome, because I have

16:26:42.780 --> 16:26:50.320
vowed that I will overcome. And I leave Europe for the East. He said this in his peculiar subdued,

16:26:50.360 --> 16:26:56.180
yet emphatic voice, looking when he had ceased speaking not at me, but at the setting sun,

16:26:56.180 --> 16:27:01.860
at which I looked, too. Both he and I had our backs towards the path, leading up the

16:27:01.860 --> 16:27:07.300
field to the wicket. We had heard no step on that grass-grown track. The water running in

16:27:07.300 --> 16:27:12.760
the vale was the one lulling sound of the hour and scene. We might well then start when a gay

16:27:12.760 --> 16:27:18.960
voice, sweet as a silver bell, exclaimed, Good evening, Mr. Rivers. And good evening, old Carlo.

16:27:19.300 --> 16:27:24.060
Your dog is quicker to recognize his friends than you are, sir. He pricked his ears and

16:27:24.060 --> 16:27:28.700
wagged his tail when I was at the bottom of the field. And you have your back towards me now.

16:27:29.180 --> 16:27:34.380
It was true. Though Mr. Rivers had started at the first of those musical accents,

16:27:34.740 --> 16:27:40.300
as if a thunderbolt had split a cloud over his head, he stood yet, at the close of the sentence,

16:27:40.600 --> 16:27:45.760
in the same attitude in which the speaker had surprised him. His arm resting on the gate,

16:27:46.100 --> 16:27:52.740
his face directed towards the West. He turned at last with measured deliberation. A vision,

16:27:52.740 --> 16:27:58.060
as it seemed to me, had risen at his side. There appeared, within three feet of him,

16:27:58.300 --> 16:28:05.820
a form clad in pure white, a youthful graceful form, full yet fine in contour, and when,

16:28:05.840 --> 16:28:10.820
after bending to caress Carlo, it lifted up its head and threw back a long veil,

16:28:11.380 --> 16:28:17.880
there bloomed under his glance a face of perfect beauty. Perfect beauty is a strong expression,

16:28:17.880 --> 16:28:23.820
but I do not retrace or qualify it. As sweet features as ever the temperate clime of Albion

16:28:23.820 --> 16:28:31.340
moulded, as pure hues of rose and lily as ever her humid gales and vapoury skies generated and

16:28:31.340 --> 16:28:38.360
screened justified in this instance the term, no charm was wanting, no defect was perceptible.

16:28:38.620 --> 16:28:44.500
The young girl had regular and delicate lineaments, eyes shaped and coloured as we see them in lovely

16:28:44.500 --> 16:28:50.340
pictures, large and dark and full, the long and shadowy eyelash which encircles a fine eye

16:28:50.340 --> 16:28:57.600
with so soft a fascination, the penciled brow which gives such clearness, the white smooth forehead

16:28:57.600 --> 16:29:04.640
which adds such repose to the livelier beauties of tint and ray, the cheek oval fresh and smooth,

16:29:04.1000 --> 16:29:12.040
the lips fresh too, ruddy, healthy, sweetly formed, the even and gleaming teeth without flaw,

16:29:12.040 --> 16:29:19.400
the small dimpled chin, the ornament of rich plenteous tresses, all advantages, in short,

16:29:19.700 --> 16:29:26.580
which, combined, realised the ideal of beauty were fully hers. I wondered as I looked at this

16:29:26.580 --> 16:29:33.260
fair creature, I admired her with my whole heart. Nature had surely formed her in a partial mood,

16:29:33.600 --> 16:29:39.600
and forgetting her usual stinted stepmother, Dole of Gifts, had endowed this, her darling,

16:29:39.600 --> 16:29:45.400
with a grand dame's bounty. What did St. John Rivers think of this earthly angel?

16:29:46.020 --> 16:29:50.1000
I naturally asked myself that question as I saw him turn to her and look at her,

16:29:51.140 --> 16:29:56.980
and as naturally I sought the answer to the inquiry in his countenance. He had already

16:29:56.980 --> 16:30:02.260
withdrawn his eye from the parry, and was looking at a humble tuft of daisies which grew by the

16:30:02.260 --> 16:30:08.540
wicket. A lovely evening, but late for you to be out alone, he said, as he crushed the snowy heads

16:30:08.540 --> 16:30:15.300
of the closed flowers with his foot. Oh, I only come home from S. She mentioned the name of a large

16:30:15.300 --> 16:30:21.100
town, some twenty miles distant, this afternoon. Papa told me you had opened your school, and that

16:30:21.100 --> 16:30:26.900
the new mistress was come, and so I put on my bonnet after tea, and ran up the valley to see her.

16:30:27.140 --> 16:30:34.900
This is she, pointing to me. It is, said St. John. Do you think you shall like Morton?

16:30:34.900 --> 16:30:38.620
She asked of me, with a direct and naïve simplicity of tone and manner,

16:30:38.1000 --> 16:30:44.100
pleasing, if childlike. I hope I shall. I have many inducements to do so.

16:30:44.700 --> 16:30:47.380
Did you find your scholars as attentive as you expected?

16:30:48.200 --> 16:30:50.760
Quite. Do you like your house?

16:30:51.560 --> 16:30:54.540
Very much. Have I furnished it nicely?

16:30:55.360 --> 16:31:00.460
Very nicely, indeed. And made a good choice of an attendant for you in Alice Wood?

16:31:01.120 --> 16:31:03.1000
You have, indeed. She is teachable and handy.

16:31:04.960 --> 16:31:09.940
This, then, I thought, is Miss Oliver, the heiress, favoured, it seems, in the gifts of fortune,

16:31:10.260 --> 16:31:15.220
as well as in those of nature. What happy combination of the planets presided over her

16:31:15.220 --> 16:31:21.280
birth, I wonder? I shall come up and help you to teach sometimes, she added. It will be a change

16:31:21.280 --> 16:31:27.800
for me to visit you now and then. And I like a change. Mr. Rivers, I have been so gay during

16:31:27.800 --> 16:31:34.280
my visit to S. Last night, or rather this morning, I was dancing till two o'clock. The Nth Regiment

16:31:34.280 --> 16:31:39.680
are stationed there since the riots. And the officers are the most agreeable men in the world.

16:31:40.020 --> 16:31:43.520
They put all our young knife-grinders and scissor-merchants to shame.

16:31:44.060 --> 16:31:50.020
It seemed to me that Mr. St. John's underlip protruded, and his upper lip curled a moment.

16:31:50.500 --> 16:31:56.640
His mouth certainly looked a good deal compressed, and the lower part of his face unusually stern and

16:31:56.640 --> 16:32:02.280
square, as the laughing girl gave him this information. He lifted his gaze, too, from the

16:32:02.280 --> 16:32:09.320
daisies and turned it on her. An unsmiling, a searching, a meaning gaze it was. She answered it

16:32:09.320 --> 16:32:15.140
with a second laugh, and laughter well became her youth, her roses, her dimples, her bright eyes.

16:32:15.540 --> 16:32:19.240
As he stood mute and grave, she again felt caressing Carlo.

16:32:19.940 --> 16:32:27.700
Poor Carlo loves me, said she. He is not stern and distant to his friends, and if he could speak,

16:32:27.980 --> 16:32:34.560
he would not be silent. As she patted the dog's head, bending with native grace before his young

16:32:34.560 --> 16:32:41.500
and austere master, I saw a glow rise to that master's face. I saw his solemn eye melt with

16:32:41.500 --> 16:32:48.580
sudden fire, and flicker with resistless emotion. Flushed and kindled thus, he looked nearly as

16:32:48.580 --> 16:32:56.260
beautiful for a man as she for a woman. His chest heaved once, as if his large heart, weary of

16:32:56.260 --> 16:33:03.040
despotic constriction, had expanded, despite the will, and made a vigorous bound for the attainment

16:33:03.040 --> 16:33:10.560
of liberty. But he curbed it, I think, as a resolute rider would curb a rearing steed. He

16:33:10.560 --> 16:33:14.960
responded neither by word nor movement to the gentle advances made him.

16:33:15.880 --> 16:33:20.720
"'Papa says you never come to see us now,' continued Miss Oliver, looking up.

16:33:20.900 --> 16:33:26.400
"'You are quite a stranger at Vale Hall. He is alone this evening, and not very well.

16:33:26.760 --> 16:33:28.580
Will you return with me and visit him?'

16:33:29.380 --> 16:33:34.740
"'It is not a seasonable hour to intrude on Mr. Oliver,' answered St. John.

16:33:35.180 --> 16:33:41.820
"'Not a seasonable hour, but I declare it is. It is just the hour when Papa most wants company,

16:33:41.820 --> 16:33:49.380
when the works are closed, and he has no business to occupy him. Now, Mr. Rivers, do come. Why are

16:33:49.380 --> 16:33:56.020
you so very shy, and so very somber?' She filled up the hiatus, his silence left by a reply of her

16:33:56.020 --> 16:34:02.720
own. "'I forgot,' she exclaimed, shaking her beautiful curled head, as if shocked at herself.

16:34:03.100 --> 16:34:09.520
"'I am so giddy and thoughtless. Do excuse me. It had slipped my memory that you have good reasons

16:34:09.520 --> 16:34:16.940
to be indisposed for joining in my chatter. Diana and Mary have left you, and Morehouse is shut up,

16:34:17.040 --> 16:34:22.480
and you are so lonely. I am sure I pity you. Do come and see Papa.'

16:34:23.940 --> 16:34:27.020
"'Not to-night, Miss Rosamond, not to-night.'

16:34:28.020 --> 16:34:34.860
Mr. St. John spoke almost like an automaton. Himself only knew the effort it cost him thus to

16:34:34.860 --> 16:34:41.660
refuse. "'Well, if you are so obstinate, I will leave you, for I dare not stay any longer. The

16:34:41.660 --> 16:34:48.200
dew begins to fall. Good evening.' She held out her hand. He just touched it.

16:34:48.620 --> 16:34:55.400
"'Good evening,' he repeated in a voice low and hollow as an echo. She turned, but in a moment

16:34:55.400 --> 16:35:02.880
returned. "'Are you well?' she asked. Well might she put the question. His face was blanched as her

16:35:02.880 --> 16:35:10.340
head fell down. "'Quite well,' he enunciated, and with a bow he left the gate. She went one way, he

16:35:10.340 --> 16:35:17.120
another. She turned twice to gaze after him, as she tripped fairy-like down the field. He, as he

16:35:17.120 --> 16:35:23.300
strode firmly across, never turned at all. This spectacle of another's suffering and sacrifice

16:35:23.300 --> 16:35:29.440
wrapped my thoughts from exclusive meditation on my own. Diana Rivers had designated her brother

16:35:29.440 --> 16:35:33.120
inexorable as death. She had not exaggerated."

16:36:00.280 --> 16:36:02.420
CHAPTER XXXII.

16:36:03.680 --> 16:36:08.1000
I continued the labors of the village school as actively and faithfully as I could.

16:36:09.600 --> 16:36:17.180
It was truly hard work at first. Some time elapsed before, with all my efforts, I could comprehend my scholars and their nature.

16:36:17.740 --> 16:36:25.920
Wholly untaught, with faculties quite torpid, they seemed to me hopelessly dull, and, at first sight, all dull alike.

16:36:25.920 --> 16:36:36.680
But I soon found I was mistaken. There was a difference amongst them as amongst the educated, and when I got to know them and they me, this difference rapidly developed itself.

16:36:37.100 --> 16:36:46.880
Their amazement at me, my language, my rules and ways, once subsided. I found some of these heavy-looking, gaping rustics wake up into a sharp-witted girls enough.

16:36:46.880 --> 16:36:57.740
Many showed themselves obliging and amiable, too, and I discovered amongst them not a few examples of capacity that won both my good-will and my admiration.

16:36:58.400 --> 16:37:07.900
These soon took a pleasure in doing their work well, in keeping their persons neat, in learning their tasks regularly, in acquiring quiet and orderly manners.

16:37:07.900 --> 16:37:20.820
The rapidity of their progress, in some instances, was even surprising, and an honest and happy pride I took in it. Besides, I began personally to like some of the best girls, and they liked me.

16:37:21.520 --> 16:37:29.060
I had amongst my scholars several farmers' daughters, young women grown almost. These could already read, write and sew.

16:37:29.060 --> 16:37:44.860
And to them I taught the elements of grammar, geography, history, and the finer kinds of needlework. I found estimable characters amongst them, characters desirous of information and disposed for improvement, with whom I passed many a pleasant evening hour in their own houses.

16:37:44.860 --> 16:38:10.280
Their parents then, the farmer and his wife, loaded me with attentions. There was an enjoyment in accepting their simple kindness, and in repaying it by a consideration, a scrupulous regard to their feelings, to which they were not, perhaps, at all times customed, and which both charmed and benefited them, because while it elevated them in their own eyes, it made them amulets to merit the deferential treatment they received.

16:38:10.280 --> 16:38:30.600
I felt I became a favorite in the neighborhood. Whenever I went out, I heard on all sides cordial salutations, and was welcomed with friendly smiles. To live amidst general regard, though it be but the regard of working people, is like sitting in sunshine calm and sweet. Serene inward feelings bud and bloom under the ray.

16:38:30.600 --> 16:38:37.020
At this period of my life, my heart far oftener swelled with thankfulness than sank with dejection.

16:38:37.020 --> 16:38:53.480
And yet, reader, to tell you all, in the midst of this calm, this useful existence, after a day passed in honorable exertion amongst my scholars, an evening spent in drawing or reading contentedly alone, I used to rush into strange dreams at night.

16:38:53.480 --> 16:39:12.760
Dreams many-colored, agitated, full of the ideal, the stirring, the stormy. Dreams where, amidst unusual scenes, charged with adventure, with agitating risk and romantic chance, I still again and again meet Mr. Rochester, always at some exciting crisis.

16:39:12.760 --> 16:39:30.600
And then the sense of being in his arms, hearing his voice, meeting his eye, touching his hand and cheek, loving him, being loved by him, the hope of passing a lifetime at his side, would be renewed with all its first force and fire.

16:39:30.600 --> 16:39:46.980
Then I woke. Then I recalled where I was and how situated. Then I rose up on my curtainless bed, trembling and quivering. And then the still dark night witnessed the convulsion of despair and heard the burst of passion.

16:39:47.740 --> 16:39:55.800
By nine o'clock the next morning I was punctually opening the school, tranquil, settled, prepared for the steady duties of the day.

16:39:56.780 --> 16:40:08.740
Rosamund Oliver kept her word in coming to visit me. Her call at the school was generally made in the course of her morning ride. She would cantor up to the door on her pony, followed by a mounted livery servant.

16:40:08.740 --> 16:40:21.260
Anything more exquisite than her appearance, in her purple habit, with her Amazon's cap of black velvet placed gracefully above the long curls that kissed her cheek and floated to her shoulders, can scarcely be imagined.

16:40:21.860 --> 16:40:27.560
And it was thus she would enter the rustic building and glide through the dazzled ranks of the village children.

16:40:28.260 --> 16:40:38.200
She generally came at the hour when Mr. Rivers was engaged in giving his daily catechizing lesson. Keenly, I fear, did the eye of the visitress pierce the young pastor's heart.

16:40:38.200 --> 16:41:03.140
A sort of instinct seemed to warn him of her entrance, even when he did not see it. And when he was looking quite away from the door, if she appeared at it, her cheek would glow, and his marble-seeming features, though they refused to relax, changed indescribably, and in their very quinescence became expressive of a repressed fervor, stronger than working muscle or darting glance could indicate.

16:41:03.140 --> 16:41:21.700
Of course, she knew her power. Indeed, he did not, because he could not conceal it from her. In spite of his Christian stoicism, when she went up and dressed him and smiled gaily, encouragingly, even fondly, in his face, his hand would tremble and his eye burn.

16:41:21.700 --> 16:41:27.480
He seemed to say, with his sad and resolute look, if he did not say it with his lips,

16:41:27.480 --> 16:41:45.520
I love you, and I know you prefer me. It is not despair of success that keeps me dumb. If I offered my heart, I believe you would accept it. But that heart is already laid on a sacred altar. The fire is arranged round it. It will soon be no more than a sacrifice consumed.

16:41:45.520 --> 16:42:01.260
And then she would pout like a disappointed child. A pensive cloud would soften her radiant vivacity. She would withdraw her hand hastily from his, and turn in transient petulance from his aspect, at once so heroic and so martyr-like.

16:42:01.260 --> 16:42:16.560
Saint John, no doubt, would have given the world to follow, recall, retain her, when she thus left him. But he would not give one chance of heaven, nor relinquish, for the Elysium of her love, one hope of the true eternal paradise.

16:42:17.300 --> 16:42:33.920
Besides, he could not bind all that he had in his nature, the rover, the aspirant, the poet, the priest, in the limits of a single passion. He could not, he would not, renounce his wild field of mission warfare for the parlours and the peace of Vale Hall.

16:42:33.920 --> 16:42:50.600
I learned so much from himself, in an inroad I once, despite his reserve, had the daring to make on his confidence. Miss Oliver already honoured me with frequent visits to my cottage. I had learned her whole character, which was without mystery or disguise.

16:42:50.600 --> 16:43:10.080
She was coquettish, but not heartless, exacting, but not worthlessly selfish. She had been indulged from her birth, but was not absolutely spoiled. She was hasty, but good-humoured, vain—she could not help it, when every glance in the glass showed her such a flush of loveliness—but not affected.

16:43:10.080 --> 16:43:28.900
Liberal-handed, innocent of the pride of wealth, ingenious, sufficiently intelligent, gay, lively, and unthinking, she was very charming, in short, even to a cool observer of her own sex like me. But she was not profoundly interesting or thoroughly impressive.

16:43:28.900 --> 16:43:47.120
A very different sort of mind was hers from that, for instance, of the sisters of St. John. Still, I liked her almost as I liked my pupil Adele, except that, for a child whom we have watched over and taught, a closer affection is engendered than we can give an equally attractive adult acquaintance.

16:43:47.120 --> 16:44:14.540
She had taken an amiable caprice to me, and said I was like Mr. Rivers, only certainly, she allowed, not one-tenth so handsome, though I was a nice neat little soul enough, but he was an angel. I was, however, good, clever, composed, and firm, like him. I was a Lucis Natre, she affirmed, as a village school mistress. She was sure my previous history, if known, would make a delightful romance.

16:44:15.360 --> 16:44:44.520
One evening, while with her usual childlike activity, and thoughtless yet not offensive inquisitiveness, she was rummaging the cupboard and the table-drawer of my little kitchen. She discovered first two French books, a volume of Schuyler, a German grammar and dictionary, and then my drawing materials and some sketches, including a pencil head of a pretty little cherub-like girl, one of my scholars, and sundry views from nature, taken in the Vale of Morton and on the surrounding moors.

16:44:44.540 --> 16:44:49.540
She was first transfixed with surprise, and then electrified with delight.

16:44:50.580 --> 16:45:03.320
Had I done these pictures? Did I know French and German? What a love, what a miracle I was! I drew better than her master in the first school in S. Would I sketch a portrait of her to show to Papa?

16:45:04.240 --> 16:45:24.340
With pleasure, I replied, and I felt a thrill of artist delight at the idea of copying so perfect and radiant a model. She had then a dark blue silk dress, her arms and her neck were bare. Her only ornament was her chest-notched tresses, which waved over her shoulders with all the wild grace of natural curls.

16:45:24.340 --> 16:45:36.560
I took a sheet of fine cardboard and drew a careful outline. I promised myself the pleasure of coloring it, and, as it was getting late then, I told her she must come and sit another day.

16:45:37.480 --> 16:45:50.560
She made such a report of me to her father that Mr. Oliver himself accompanied her next evening, a tall, massive-featured, middle-aged and gray-headed man, at whose side his lovely daughter looked like a bright flower near a hoary turret.

16:45:51.160 --> 16:46:06.260
He appeared a taciturn and perhaps a proud personage, but he was very kind to me. The sketch of Rosamond's portrait pleased him highly. He said I must make a finished picture of it. He insisted, too, on my coming the next day to spend the evening at Vale Hall.

16:46:06.260 --> 16:46:35.020
I went. I founded a large, handsome residence, showing abundant evidences of wealth in the proprietor. Rosamond was full of glee and pleasure all the time I stayed. Her father was affable, and when he entered into conversation with me after tea, he expressed in strong terms his approbation of what I had done in Morton School, and said he only feared, from what he saw and heard, I was too good for the place, and would soon quit it for one more suitable.

16:46:36.200 --> 16:46:42.340
"'Indeed,' cried Rosamond, "'she is clever enough to be a governess in a high family, papa.'

16:46:42.340 --> 16:47:06.560
I thought I would far rather be where I am than in any high family in the land. Mr. Oliver spoke of Mr. Rivers, of the Rivers family, with great respect. He said it was a very old name in that neighborhood, that the ancestors of the house were wealthy, that all Morton had once belonged to them, that even now he considered the representative of that house might, if he liked, make an alliance with the best.

16:47:06.560 --> 16:47:22.540
He accounted it a pity that so fine and talented a young man should have formed the design of going out as a missionary. It was quite throwing a valuable life away. It appeared, then, that her father would throw no obstacle in the way of Rosamond's union with St. John.

16:47:23.120 --> 16:47:31.320
Mr. Oliver evidently regarded the young clergyman's good birth, old name, and sacred profession as sufficient compensation for the want of fortune.

16:47:31.980 --> 16:47:53.140
It was the fifth of November and a holiday. My little servant, after helping me to clean my house, was gone, well satisfied with the fee of a penny for her aid. All about me was spotless and bright, scoured floor, polished grate, and well rubbed chairs. I had also made myself neat, and had now the afternoon before me to spend as I would.

16:47:53.140 --> 16:48:19.900
The translation of a few pages of German occupied an hour. Then I got my palette and pencils and fell to the more soothing, because easier, occupation of completing Rosamond Oliver's miniature. The head was finished already. There was but the background to tint and the drapery to shade off. A touch of carmine, too, to add to the ripe lips. A soft curl here and there to the tresses. A deeper tinge to the shadow of the lash under the azured eyelid.

16:48:19.900 --> 16:48:28.460
I was absorbed in the execution of these nice details, when after one rapid tap my door unclosed, admitting St. John Rivers.

16:48:29.140 --> 16:48:46.800
I am come to see how you are spending your holiday, he said. Not, I hope, in thought. Know that as well. While you draw, you will not feel lonely. You see, I mistrust you still. Though you have borne up wonderfully so far, I have brought you a book for evening solace.

16:48:46.800 --> 16:49:06.820
And he laid on the table a new publication, a poem, one of those genuine productions so often vouchsafe to the fortunate public of those days, the golden age of modern literature. Alas, the readers of my era are less favored. But, courage, I will not pause either to accuse or repine.

16:49:06.820 --> 16:49:21.120
I know poetry is not dead, nor genius lost, nor has Maimon gained power over either, to bind or slay. They will both assert their existence, their presence, their liberty and strength again one day.

16:49:21.120 --> 16:49:50.340
Powerful angels safe in heaven, they smile when sordid souls triumph, and feeble ones weep over their destruction. Poetry destroyed? Genius banished? No, mediocrity, no! Do not let envy prompt you to the thought. No, they not only live, but reign and redeem. And without their divine influence spread everywhere, you would be in hell, the hell of your own meanness.

16:49:51.120 --> 16:50:14.760
While I was eagerly glancing at the bright pages of Marmion—for Marmion it was—St. John stooped to examine my drawing. His tall figure sprang erect again with a start. He said nothing. I looked up at him. He shunned my eye. I knew his thoughts well, and could read his heart plainly, at the moment I felt calmer and cooler than he.

16:50:14.760 --> 16:50:40.600
I had then temporarily the advantage of him, and I conceived an inclination to do him some good, if I could. With all his firmness and self-control, thought I, he tasks himself too far, locks every feeling and pain within, expresses confesses imparts nothing. I am sure it would benefit him to talk a little about his sweet Rosamond, whom he thinks he ought not to marry. I will make him talk.

16:50:40.600 --> 16:50:42.040
I said first,

16:50:42.340 --> 16:50:43.800
Take a chair, Mr. Rivers.

16:50:44.160 --> 16:50:47.460
But he answered, as he always did, that he could not stay.

16:50:47.460 --> 16:51:08.400
Very well, I responded mentally. Stand if you like. But you shall not go just yet. I am determined. Solitude is at least as bad for you as it is for me. I'll try if I cannot discover the secret spring of your confidence, and find an aperture in that marble breast through which I can shed one drop of the balm of sympathy.

16:51:09.060 --> 16:51:12.160
Is this portrait like? I asked bluntly.

16:51:12.700 --> 16:51:15.880
Like? Like whom? I did not observe it closely.

16:51:15.880 --> 16:51:18.160
You did, Mr. Rivers.

16:51:18.780 --> 16:51:23.860
He almost started at my sudden and strange abruptness. He looked at me astonished.

16:51:24.600 --> 16:51:33.340
Oh, that is nothing yet, I muttered within. I don't mean to be baffled by a little stiffness on your part. I am prepared to go considerable lengths.

16:51:33.780 --> 16:51:34.520
I continued,

16:51:34.820 --> 16:51:39.920
You observed it closely and distinctly. But I have no objection to your looking at it again.

16:51:40.380 --> 16:51:42.760
And I rose and placed it in his hand.

16:51:42.760 --> 16:51:50.300
A well-executed picture, he said. Very soft, clear coloring, very graceful, and correct drawing.

16:51:51.280 --> 16:51:55.760
Yes, yes, I know all that. But what of the resemblance? Who is it like?

16:51:56.700 --> 16:51:58.820
Mastering some hesitation, he answered.

16:51:59.560 --> 16:52:00.960
Miss Oliver, I presume.

16:52:00.960 --> 16:52:12.960
Of course. And now, sir, to reward you for that accurate guess, I promised to paint you a careful and faithful duplicate of this very picture, provided you admit that the gift would be acceptable to you.

16:52:13.280 --> 16:52:17.700
I don't wish to throw away my time and trouble on an offering you would deem worthless.

16:52:18.420 --> 16:52:25.680
He continued to gaze at the picture. The longer he looked, the firmer he held it, the more he seemed to covet it.

16:52:25.680 --> 16:52:33.840
It is like, he murmured. The eye is well managed. The color, light expression, are perfect. It smiles.

16:52:34.740 --> 16:52:45.720
Would it comfort, or would it wound you to have a similar painting? Tell me that. When you are in Madagascar, or in the Cape, or in India, would it be a consolation to have that momento in your possession?

16:52:45.1000 --> 16:52:50.520
Or would the sight of it bring recollections calculated to enervate and distress?

16:52:51.380 --> 16:52:58.760
He now furtively raised his eyes. He glanced at me, irresolute, disturbed. He again surveyed the picture.

16:52:59.380 --> 16:53:05.120
That I should like to have it is certain. Whether it would be judicious or wise is another question.

16:53:05.1000 --> 16:53:20.760
Since I have ascertained that Rosamond really preferred him, and that her father was not likely to oppose the match, I, less exalted in my views than St. John, had been strongly disposed in my own heart to advocate their union.

16:53:20.760 --> 16:53:33.520
It seemed to me that, should he become the possessor of Mr. Oliver's large fortune, he might do as much good with it as if he went and laid his genius out to wither, and his strength to waste under a tropical sun.

16:53:33.980 --> 16:53:43.280
With that persuasion I now answered, As far as I can see, it would be wiser and more judicious if you were to take to yourself the original at once.

16:53:43.280 --> 16:53:52.900
By this time he had sat down. He had laid the picture on the table before him, and with his brow supported on both hands, hung fondly over it.

16:53:53.560 --> 16:54:10.020
I discerned he was now neither angry nor shocked at my audacity. I saw even that, to be thus frankly addressed on a subject he had deemed unapproachable, to hear it thus freely handled, was beginning to be felt by him as a new pleasure, an unhoped for relief.

16:54:10.020 --> 16:54:29.100
Reserved people often really need the frank discussion of their sentiments and griefs, more than the expansive. The sternest-seeming stoic is human after all, and a burst with boldness and good-will into the silent sea of their soul is often to confer on them the first of obligations.

16:54:29.940 --> 16:54:46.100
She likes you, I am sure, said I, as I stood behind his chair, and her father respects you. Moreover, she is a sweet girl, rather thoughtless, but you would have sufficient thought for both yourself and her. You ought to marry her.

16:54:46.900 --> 16:54:49.360
Does she like me? he asked.

16:54:50.220 --> 16:54:59.140
Certainly. Better than she likes any one else. She talks of you continually. There is no subject she enjoys so much or touches upon so often.

16:54:59.920 --> 16:55:02.500
It is very pleasant to hear this, he said.

16:55:03.060 --> 16:55:03.560
Very.

16:55:04.420 --> 16:55:06.580
Go on for another quarter of an hour.

16:55:07.020 --> 16:55:10.740
And he actually took out his watch and laid it upon the table to measure the time.

16:55:10.740 --> 16:55:20.060
But where is the use of going on, I asked, when you are probably preparing some iron blow of contradiction or forging a fresh chain to fetter your heart?

16:55:20.720 --> 16:55:44.520
Don't imagine such hard things. Fancy me yielding and melting as I am doing. Human love rising like a freshly opened fountain in my mind and overflowing, with sweet inundation all the field I have so carefully and with such labor prepared, so assiduously sown with the seeds of good intentions, of self-denying plans, and how it is deluged with a nectarous flood.

16:55:44.520 --> 16:55:56.020
The young germs swamped, delicious poison cankering them. Now I see myself stretched on an ottoman in the drawing room, at Vale Hall, at my bride Rosamund Oliver's feet.

16:55:56.680 --> 16:56:12.160
She is talking to me with her sweet voice, gazing down on me with those eyes your skillful hand has copied so well, smiling at me with these coral lips. She is mine. I am hers. This present life and passing world suffice to me.

16:56:12.160 --> 16:56:21.080
Hush. Say nothing. My heart is full of delight. My senses are entranced. Let the time I marked pass in peace.

16:56:22.160 --> 16:56:35.940
I humoured him. The watch ticked on. He breathed fast and low. I stood silent. Amidst this hush, the quartet sped. He replaced the watch, laid the picture down, rose, and stood on the hearth.

16:56:35.940 --> 16:56:46.580
Now, said he, that little space was given to delirium and delusion. I rested my temples on the breast of temptation and put my neck voluntarily under her yoke of flowers.

16:56:47.100 --> 16:56:59.500
I tasted her cup. The pillow was burning. There is an asp in the garland. The wine has a bitter taste. Her promises are hollow. Her offer's false. I see and know all this.

16:56:59.500 --> 16:57:21.400
I gazed at him in wonder. It is strange, pursued him, that while I love Rosamund Oliver so wildly, with all the intensity indeed of a first passion, the object of which is exquisitely beautiful, graceful, fascinating, I experience at the same time a calm, unwrapped consciousness that she would not make me a good wife.

16:57:21.400 --> 16:57:32.900
That she is not the partner suited to me, and I would discover this within a year after marriage, and that twelve months' rapture would succeed a lifetime of regret. This I know.

16:57:34.160 --> 16:57:51.920
Strange indeed! I could not help ejaculating. While something in me, he went on, is acutely sensible to her charms, something else is so deeply impressed with her defects. They are such that she would sympathize in nothing I aspired to, cooperate in nothing I undertook.

16:57:51.920 --> 16:58:03.1000
Rosamund, a sufferer, a laborer, a female apostle? Rosamund, a missionary's wife? No. But you need not be a missionary. You might relinquish that scheme.

16:58:05.500 --> 16:58:28.980
Relinquish? What, my vocation, my great work, my foundation laid on earth for a mansion in heaven, my hopes of being numbered in the band who have merged all ambitions in the glorious one of bettering their race, of carrying knowledge into the realms of ignorance, of substituting peace for war, freedom for bondage, religion for superstition, the hope of heaven for the fear of hell?

16:58:28.980 --> 16:58:37.480
Must I relinquish that? It is dearer than the blood in my veins. It is what I have to look forward to and to live for.

16:58:37.480 --> 16:58:40.360
After a considerable pause, I said,

16:58:40.360 --> 16:58:45.160
And Miss Oliver, are her disappointment and sorrow of no interest to you?

16:58:45.960 --> 16:58:58.980
Miss Oliver is ever surrounded by suitors and flatterers. In less than a month my image will be effaced from her heart. She will forget me, and will marry probably someone who will make her far happier than I should do.

16:58:59.820 --> 16:59:04.880
You speak coolly enough, but you suffer in the conflict. You are wasting away.

16:59:05.680 --> 16:59:26.400
No, if I get a little thin it is with anxiety about my prospects. Yet unsettled, my departure continually procrastinated. Only this morning I received intelligence that the successor, whose arrival I have been so long expecting, cannot be ready to replace me for three months to come yet, and perhaps the three months may extend to six.

16:59:26.780 --> 16:59:31.220
You tremble and become flushed whenever Miss Oliver enters the schoolroom.

16:59:31.840 --> 16:59:55.100
Again the surprised expression crossed his face. He had not imagined that a woman would dare to speak so to a man. For me, I felt at home in this sort of discourse. I could never rest in communication with strong, discreet, and refined minds, whether male or female, till I had passed the outwards of conventional reserve, and crossed the threshold of confidence, and won a place by their heart's very hearthstone.

16:59:55.100 --> 17:00:15.020
You are original, said he, and not timid. There is something brave in your spirit, as well as penetrating in your eye. But allow me to assure you that you partially misinterpret my emotions. You think them more profound and potent than they are. You give me a larger allowance of sympathy than I have a just claim to.

17:00:15.020 --> 17:00:35.800
When I color and when I shade before Miss Oliver, I do not pity myself. I scorn the weakness. I know it is ignoble, a mere fever of the flesh. Not, I declare, the convulsion of the soul. That is just as fixed as a rock, firm, set in the depths of a restless sea. Know me to be what I am, a cold, hard man.

17:00:35.800 --> 17:00:38.100
I smiled incredulously.

17:00:38.100 --> 17:00:58.380
You have taken my confidence by storm, he continued, and now it is much at your service. I am simply in my original state, stripped of that blood-bleached robe with which Christianity covers human deformity, a cold, hard, ambitious man. Natural affection only of all the sentiments has permanent power over me.

17:00:58.380 --> 17:01:27.840
Reason and not feeling is my guide. My ambition is unlimited. My desire to rise higher, to do more than others insatiable. I honor endurance, perseverance, industry, talent, because these are the means by which men achieve great ends and mount to lofty eminence. I watch your career with interest, because I consider you a specimen of a diligent, orderly, energetic woman, not because I deeply compassionate what you have gone through or what you still suffer.

17:01:28.640 --> 17:01:32.780
You would describe yourself as a mere pagan philosopher, I said.

17:01:33.440 --> 17:01:39.840
No, there is this difference between me and diastic philosophers. I believe, and I believe the gospel.

17:01:40.480 --> 17:01:55.080
You missed your epithet. I am not a pagan, but a Christian philosopher, a follower of the sect of Jesus. As his disciple, I adopt his pure, his merciful, his benignant doctrines. I advocate them. I am sworn to spread them.

17:01:55.080 --> 17:02:22.700
One in youth to religion, she has cultivated my original qualities thus. From the minute germ, natural affection, she has developed the overshadowing tree philanthropy. From the wild stringy root of human uprightness, she has reared a due sense of the divine justice, of the ambition to win power and renown for her wretched self. She has formed the ambition to spread my master's kingdom to achieve victories for the standard of the cross.

17:02:22.700 --> 17:02:37.380
So much has religion done for me, turning the original materials to the best account, pruning and training nature. But she could not eradicate nature, nor will it be eradicated, till this mortal shall put on immortality.

17:02:38.300 --> 17:02:44.200
Having said this, he took his hat, which lay on the table beside my pallet. Once more he looked at the portrait.

17:02:44.660 --> 17:02:50.660
She is lovely, he murmured. She is well named, the rose of the world, indeed.

17:02:51.580 --> 17:02:54.300
And may I not paint one like it for you?

17:02:56.180 --> 17:02:57.880
Cibono, no.

17:02:58.540 --> 17:03:06.440
He drew over the picture the sheet of thin paper on which I was accustomed to rest my hand in painting, to prevent the cardboard from being sullied.

17:03:07.040 --> 17:03:17.540
What he suddenly saw on this blank paper it was impossible for me to tell, but something had caught his eye. He took it up with a snatch, he looked at the edge, then shot a glance at me.

17:03:17.920 --> 17:03:29.220
An expressively peculiar and quite incomprehensible, a glance that seemed to take and make note of every point in my shape, face and dress, for it traversed all, quick, keen as lightning.

17:03:29.840 --> 17:03:34.400
His lips parted as if to speak, but he checked the coming sentence, whatever it was.

17:03:34.400 --> 17:03:36.960
What is the matter? I asked.

17:03:37.740 --> 17:03:49.720
Nothing in the world, was the reply, and, replacing the paper, I saw him dexterously tear a narrow strip from the margin. It disappeared in his glove, and with one hasty nod and good afternoon he vanished.

17:03:50.440 --> 17:03:56.280
Well, I exclaimed, using an expression of the district, that caps the globe, however.

17:03:56.900 --> 17:04:04.460
I, in my turn, scrutinized the paper, but saw nothing on it save a few dingy stains of paint, where I had tried the tint in my pencil.

17:04:04.820 --> 17:04:14.220
I pondered the mystery a minute or two, but finding it insolvable, and being certain it could not be of much moment, I dismissed and soon forgot it.

17:04:19.720 --> 17:04:21.340
The End

17:04:54.720 --> 17:04:58.320
When Mr. St. John went, it was beginning to snow.

17:04:58.940 --> 17:05:01.660
The whirling storm continued all night.

17:05:02.340 --> 17:05:06.540
The next day a keen wind brought fresh and blinding falls.

17:05:07.020 --> 17:05:11.260
By twilight the valley was drifted up and almost impassable.

17:05:11.980 --> 17:05:17.720
I had closed my shutter, laid a mat to the door to prevent the snow from blowing in under

17:05:17.720 --> 17:05:24.020
it, trimmed my fire, and after sitting nearly an hour on the hearth listening to the muffled

17:05:24.020 --> 17:05:29.260
fury of the tempest, I lit a candle, took down Marmion, and beginning.

17:05:30.080 --> 17:05:38.400
Day set on Norham's castled steep, and Tweed's fair river broad and deep, and Cheviot's mountain's

17:05:38.400 --> 17:05:45.700
lone, the massive towers, the donjon keep, the flanking walls that round them sweep in

17:05:45.700 --> 17:05:47.260
the yellow luster shone.

17:05:48.200 --> 17:05:50.880
I soon forgot storm in music.

17:05:52.120 --> 17:05:53.420
I heard a noise.

17:05:53.720 --> 17:05:55.560
The wind, I thought, shook the door.

17:05:56.240 --> 17:06:02.520
No, it was St. John Rivers, who, lifting the latch, came in out of the frozen hurricane,

17:06:02.880 --> 17:06:09.520
the howling darkness, and stood before me, the cloak that covered his tall figure all

17:06:09.520 --> 17:06:10.620
white as a glacier.

17:06:10.620 --> 17:06:17.200
I was almost in consternation, so little had I expected any guest from the blocked-up vale

17:06:17.200 --> 17:06:17.940
that night.

17:06:18.820 --> 17:06:20.760
Any ill news, I demanded.

17:06:21.180 --> 17:06:22.420
Has anything happened?

17:06:23.520 --> 17:06:31.220
No, how very easily alarmed you are, he answered, removing his cloak and hanging it up against

17:06:31.220 --> 17:06:36.380
the door, towards which he again coolly pushed the mat which his entrance had deranged.

17:06:36.880 --> 17:06:38.820
He stamped the snow from his boots.

17:06:39.760 --> 17:06:46.800
I shall sully the purity of your floor, said he, but you must excuse me for once.

17:06:48.000 --> 17:06:49.720
Then he approached the fire.

17:06:50.680 --> 17:06:57.580
I have had hard work to get here, I assure you, he observed, as he warmed his hands over

17:06:57.580 --> 17:06:58.100
the flame.

17:06:59.040 --> 17:07:01.180
One drift took me up to the waste.

17:07:01.620 --> 17:07:04.000
Happily, the snow is quite soft yet.

17:07:05.080 --> 17:07:07.060
But why are you come?

17:07:07.540 --> 17:07:09.340
I could not forbear saying.

17:07:10.660 --> 17:07:17.340
Rather an inhospitable question to put to a visitor, but, since you ask it, I answer

17:07:17.340 --> 17:07:19.820
simply to have a little talk with you.

17:07:20.180 --> 17:07:23.660
I got tired of my mute books and empty rooms.

17:07:24.320 --> 17:07:30.560
Besides, since yesterday, I have experienced the excitement of a person to whom a tale

17:07:30.560 --> 17:07:34.580
has been half told, and who is impatient to hear the sequel.

17:07:35.500 --> 17:07:37.060
He sat down.

17:07:37.560 --> 17:07:44.740
I recalled his singular conduct of yesterday, and really I began to fear his wits were touched.

17:07:45.480 --> 17:07:50.660
If he were insane, however, his was a very cool and collected insanity.

17:07:51.280 --> 17:07:57.260
I had never seen that handsome featured face of his look more like chiseled marble than

17:07:57.260 --> 17:08:04.400
it did just now, as he put aside his snow-wet hair from his forehead and let the firelight

17:08:04.400 --> 17:08:10.360
shine free on his pale brow and cheek as pale, where it grieved me to discover the

17:08:10.360 --> 17:08:14.560
hollow trace of care or sorrow now so plainly graved.

17:08:15.260 --> 17:08:19.900
I waited, expecting he would say something I could at least comprehend.

17:08:20.580 --> 17:08:25.780
But his hand was now at his chin, his finger on his lip, he was thinking.

17:08:26.480 --> 17:08:30.160
It struck me that his hand looked wasted like his face.

17:08:30.680 --> 17:08:34.740
A perhaps uncalled-for gush of pity came over my heart.

17:08:35.200 --> 17:08:36.460
I was moved to say,

17:08:37.220 --> 17:08:40.320
I wish Diana or Mary would come and live with you.

17:08:40.560 --> 17:08:46.500
It is too bad that you should be quite alone, and you are recklessly rash about your own health.

17:08:47.560 --> 17:08:49.760
Not at all, said he.

17:08:50.140 --> 17:08:52.240
I care for myself when necessary.

17:08:52.680 --> 17:08:53.680
I am well now.

17:08:54.000 --> 17:08:55.800
What do you see amiss in me?

17:08:56.620 --> 17:09:00.200
This was said with a careless, abstracted indifference,

17:09:00.600 --> 17:09:06.120
which showed that my solicitude was, at least in his opinion, wholly superfluous.

17:09:06.500 --> 17:09:07.720
I was silenced.

17:09:08.660 --> 17:09:12.180
He still slowly moved his finger over his upper lip,

17:09:12.640 --> 17:09:16.180
and still his eye dwelt dreamily on the glowing grate.

17:09:16.860 --> 17:09:18.740
Thinking it urgent to say something,

17:09:19.260 --> 17:09:24.200
I asked him presently if he felt any cold draft from the door which was behind him.

17:09:25.080 --> 17:09:29.260
No, no, he responded shortly and somewhat testily.

17:09:30.600 --> 17:09:35.020
Well, I reflected, if you won't talk, you may be still.

17:09:35.280 --> 17:09:37.800
I'll let you alone now and return to my book.

17:09:38.720 --> 17:09:43.000
So I snuffed the candle and resumed the perusal of Marmion.

17:09:43.720 --> 17:09:44.700
He soon stirred.

17:09:45.040 --> 17:09:47.720
My eye was instantly drawn to his movements.

17:09:48.380 --> 17:09:51.260
He only took out a Morocco pocketbook,

17:09:51.260 --> 17:09:56.820
thence produced a letter which he read in silence, folded it, put it back,

17:09:57.220 --> 17:09:58.780
relapsed into meditation.

17:09:59.680 --> 17:10:04.280
It was vain to try to read with such an inscrutable fixture before me,

17:10:04.600 --> 17:10:07.500
nor could I, in impatience, consent to be dumb.

17:10:07.920 --> 17:10:11.320
He might rebuff me if he liked, but talk I would.

17:10:12.120 --> 17:10:14.780
Have you heard from Diana and Mary lately?

17:10:15.500 --> 17:10:18.140
Not since the letter I showed you a week ago.

17:10:18.940 --> 17:10:22.980
There has not been any change made about your own arrangements.

17:10:23.560 --> 17:10:26.740
You will not be summoned to leave England sooner than you expected.

17:10:27.880 --> 17:10:29.520
I fear not, indeed.

17:10:29.960 --> 17:10:32.440
Such chance is too good to befall me.

17:10:33.500 --> 17:10:35.860
Baffled so far, I changed my ground.

17:10:36.460 --> 17:10:40.080
I bethought myself to talk about the school and my scholars.

17:10:41.240 --> 17:10:45.440
Mary Garrett's mother is better, and Mary came back to school this morning,

17:10:45.440 --> 17:10:49.680
and I shall have four new girls next week from the foundry clothes.

17:10:50.000 --> 17:10:52.280
They would have come today but for the snow.

17:10:53.540 --> 17:10:54.180
Indeed.

17:10:55.440 --> 17:10:57.260
Mr. Oliver pays for two.

17:10:58.160 --> 17:10:58.900
Does he?

17:10:59.420 --> 17:11:02.740
He means to give the whole school a treat at Christmas.

17:11:03.720 --> 17:11:04.340
I know.

17:11:05.260 --> 17:11:06.340
Was it your suggestion?

17:11:07.060 --> 17:11:07.560
No.

17:11:08.240 --> 17:11:09.000
Whose, then?

17:11:09.580 --> 17:11:10.960
His daughter's, I think.

17:11:11.940 --> 17:11:12.980
It is like her.

17:11:13.040 --> 17:11:14.840
She is so good-natured.

17:11:14.840 --> 17:11:15.920
Yes.

17:11:17.280 --> 17:11:19.680
Again came the blank of a pause.

17:11:20.120 --> 17:11:21.760
The clock struck eight strokes.

17:11:22.560 --> 17:11:23.600
It aroused him.

17:11:23.960 --> 17:11:27.600
He uncrossed his legs, sat erect, turned to me.

17:11:28.480 --> 17:11:33.280
Leave your book a moment, and come a little nearer the fire, he said.

17:11:34.540 --> 17:11:38.820
Wondering, and of my wonder finding no end, I complied.

17:11:39.820 --> 17:11:42.100
Half an hour ago, he pursued,

17:11:42.100 --> 17:11:46.760
I spoke of my impatience to hear the sequel of a tale.

17:11:47.420 --> 17:11:51.040
On reflection, I find the matter will be better managed

17:11:51.040 --> 17:11:56.260
by my assuming the narrator's part, and converting you into a listener.

17:11:56.980 --> 17:12:00.660
Before commencing, it is but fair to warn you

17:12:00.660 --> 17:12:04.360
that the story will sound somewhat hackneyed in your ears,

17:12:04.840 --> 17:12:11.040
but stale details often regain a degree of freshness when they pass through new lips.

17:12:11.540 --> 17:12:15.500
For the rest, whether trite or novel, it is short.

17:12:16.780 --> 17:12:21.680
Twenty years ago, a poor curate, never mind his name at this moment,

17:12:22.340 --> 17:12:24.840
fell in love with a rich man's daughter.

17:12:25.340 --> 17:12:30.960
She fell in love with him and married him against the advice of all her friends,

17:12:31.140 --> 17:12:35.120
who consequently disowned her immediately after the wedding.

17:12:35.940 --> 17:12:39.840
Before two years passed, the rash pair were both dead

17:12:39.840 --> 17:12:43.740
and laid quietly side by side under one slab.

17:12:44.540 --> 17:12:45.940
I have seen their grave.

17:12:46.300 --> 17:12:49.820
It formed part of the pavement of a huge churchyard

17:12:49.820 --> 17:12:57.420
surrounding the grim, soot-black old cathedral of an overgrown manufacturing town in Blankshire.

17:12:58.780 --> 17:13:04.160
They left a daughter, which, at its very birth, charity received in her lap.

17:13:04.640 --> 17:13:08.920
Cold as that of the snowdrift I almost stuck fast in tonight.

17:13:09.920 --> 17:13:15.200
Charity carried the friendless thing to the house of its rich maternal relations.

17:13:15.820 --> 17:13:22.220
It was reared by an aunt-in-law called, I come to names now, Mrs. Reed of Gateshead.

17:13:22.840 --> 17:13:25.180
You start, and did you hear a noise?

17:13:25.780 --> 17:13:31.640
I dare say it is only a rat scrambling along the rafters of the adjoining schoolroom.

17:13:32.060 --> 17:13:38.540
It was a barn before I had it repaired and altered, and barns are generally haunted by rats.

17:13:38.920 --> 17:13:40.280
To proceed.

17:13:40.920 --> 17:13:43.980
Mrs. Reed kept the orphan ten years.

17:13:44.620 --> 17:13:49.360
Whether it was happy or not with her, I cannot say, never having been told.

17:13:49.960 --> 17:13:54.120
But at the end of that time she transferred it to a place you know,

17:13:54.400 --> 17:13:59.660
being no other than Lowood School, where you so long resided yourself.

17:14:00.760 --> 17:14:04.140
It seems her career there was very honourable.

17:14:04.640 --> 17:14:08.320
From a pupil, she became a teacher like yourself.

17:14:08.320 --> 17:14:13.720
Really, it strikes me there are parallel points in her history and yours.

17:14:14.420 --> 17:14:16.600
She left it to be a governess.

17:14:17.120 --> 17:14:20.080
There again your fates were analogous.

17:14:20.500 --> 17:14:25.080
She undertook the education of the ward of a certain Mr. Rochester.

17:14:26.420 --> 17:14:28.960
Mr. Rivers, I interrupted.

17:14:30.260 --> 17:14:35.260
I can guess your feelings, he said, but restrain them for a while.

17:14:35.260 --> 17:14:38.540
I have nearly finished, hear me to the end.

17:14:39.560 --> 17:14:45.740
Of Mr. Rochester's character I know nothing, but the one fact that he professed to offer

17:14:45.740 --> 17:14:50.640
honourable marriage to this young girl, and that at the very altar

17:14:50.640 --> 17:14:54.920
she discovered he had a wife yet alive, though a lunatic.

17:14:55.520 --> 17:15:00.900
What his subsequent conduct and proposals were is a matter of pure conjecture.

17:15:00.900 --> 17:15:06.920
But when an event transpired which rendered inquiry after the governess necessary,

17:15:07.540 --> 17:15:09.660
it was discovered she was gone.

17:15:09.980 --> 17:15:12.940
No one could tell when, where, or how.

17:15:13.520 --> 17:15:16.300
She had left Thornfield Hall in the night.

17:15:16.800 --> 17:15:19.680
Every research after her course had been vain.

17:15:20.140 --> 17:15:23.100
The country had been scoured far and wide.

17:15:23.620 --> 17:15:27.380
No vestige of information could be gathered respecting her.

17:15:27.940 --> 17:15:32.660
Yet that she should be found is become a matter of serious urgency.

17:15:33.380 --> 17:15:35.640
Advertisements have been put in all the papers.

17:15:36.160 --> 17:15:40.480
I myself have received a letter from one Mr. Briggs, a solicitor,

17:15:40.880 --> 17:15:43.500
communicating the details I have just imparted.

17:15:44.060 --> 17:15:45.820
Is it not an odd tale?

17:15:47.200 --> 17:15:53.980
Just tell me this, said I, and since you know so much you surely can tell it me.

17:15:54.680 --> 17:15:56.060
What of Mr. Rochester?

17:15:56.620 --> 17:15:58.440
How and where is he?

17:15:58.640 --> 17:15:59.700
What is he doing?

17:16:00.080 --> 17:16:00.800
Is he well?

17:16:01.920 --> 17:16:05.240
I am ignorant of all concerning Mr. Rochester.

17:16:05.720 --> 17:16:09.100
The letter never mentions him but to narrate the fraudulent

17:16:09.100 --> 17:16:11.600
and illegal attempt I have adverted to.

17:16:12.320 --> 17:16:14.880
You should rather ask the name of the governess,

17:16:15.200 --> 17:16:18.180
the nature of the event which requires her appearance.

17:16:19.300 --> 17:16:21.540
Did no one go to Thornfield Hall then?

17:16:21.840 --> 17:16:23.840
Did no one see Mr. Rochester?

17:16:24.720 --> 17:16:25.920
I suppose not.

17:16:26.060 --> 17:16:28.080
But they wrote to him.

17:16:28.480 --> 17:16:29.280
Of course.

17:16:30.440 --> 17:16:31.820
And what did he say?

17:16:32.240 --> 17:16:33.460
Who has his letters?

17:16:35.020 --> 17:16:38.520
Mr. Briggs intimates that the answer to his application

17:16:38.520 --> 17:16:42.460
was not from Mr. Rochester but from a lady.

17:16:42.760 --> 17:16:45.140
It is signed Alice Fairfax.

17:16:46.660 --> 17:16:49.200
I felt cold and dismayed.

17:16:49.660 --> 17:16:52.360
My worst fears then were probably true.

17:16:52.360 --> 17:16:56.140
He had in all probability left England

17:16:56.140 --> 17:17:01.660
and rushed in reckless desperation to some former haunt on the continent.

17:17:02.460 --> 17:17:05.100
And what opiate for his severe sufferings,

17:17:05.560 --> 17:17:08.980
what object for his strong passions had he sought there?

17:17:09.780 --> 17:17:11.680
I dared not answer the question.

17:17:12.200 --> 17:17:15.860
Oh, my poor master, once almost my husband,

17:17:16.380 --> 17:17:19.000
whom I had often called my dear Edward.

17:17:20.420 --> 17:17:25.020
He must have been a bad man, observed Mr. Rivers.

17:17:26.120 --> 17:17:31.560
You don't know him, don't pronounce an opinion upon him, I said with warmth.

17:17:32.900 --> 17:17:35.420
Very well, he answered quietly.

17:17:36.020 --> 17:17:40.140
And indeed, my head is otherwise occupied than with him.

17:17:40.360 --> 17:17:42.360
I have my tale to finish.

17:17:43.160 --> 17:17:45.640
Since you won't ask the governess's name,

17:17:45.860 --> 17:17:48.060
I must tell it of my own accord.

17:17:48.700 --> 17:17:50.580
Stay, I have it here.

17:17:50.880 --> 17:17:55.300
It is always more satisfactory to see important points written down

17:17:55.300 --> 17:17:57.540
fairly committed to black and white.

17:17:59.080 --> 17:18:04.300
And the pocketbook was again deliberately produced, opened, sought through.

17:18:04.820 --> 17:18:10.680
From one of its compartments was extracted a shabby slip of paper hastily torn off.

17:18:11.320 --> 17:18:16.520
I recognized in its texture and its stains of ultramarine and lake and vermilion

17:18:16.520 --> 17:18:19.260
the ravished margin of the portrait cover.

17:18:20.100 --> 17:18:22.840
He got up, held it close to my eyes,

17:18:23.140 --> 17:18:26.940
and I read, traced in Indian ink in my own handwriting,

17:18:27.540 --> 17:18:32.840
the words Jane Eyre, the work doubtless of some moment of abstraction.

17:18:34.520 --> 17:18:37.980
Briggs wrote to me of a Jane Eyre, he said.

17:18:38.580 --> 17:18:41.700
The advertisements demanded a Jane Eyre.

17:18:42.060 --> 17:18:44.280
I knew a Jane Elliot.

17:18:45.100 --> 17:18:47.780
I confess I had my suspicions,

17:18:48.200 --> 17:18:53.560
but it was only yesterday afternoon they were at once resolved into certainty.

17:18:54.600 --> 17:18:57.820
You own the name and renounce the alias?

17:18:58.560 --> 17:19:02.660
Yes, yes, but where is Mr. Briggs?

17:19:03.060 --> 17:19:06.360
He perhaps knows more of Mr. Rochester than you do.

17:19:07.560 --> 17:19:08.900
Briggs is in London.

17:19:09.300 --> 17:19:13.220
I should doubt his knowing anything at all about Mr. Rochester.

17:19:13.220 --> 17:19:16.800
It is not in Mr. Rochester he is interested.

17:19:17.780 --> 17:19:21.500
Meantime you forget essential points in pursuing trifles.

17:19:21.840 --> 17:19:26.780
You do not inquire why Mr. Briggs sought after you what he wanted with you.

17:19:28.060 --> 17:19:30.220
Well, what did he want?

17:19:31.720 --> 17:19:36.940
Merely to tell you that your uncle, Mr. Eyre of Madeira, is dead,

17:19:37.580 --> 17:19:40.620
that he has left you all his property,

17:19:40.620 --> 17:19:46.360
and that you are now rich, merely that, nothing more.

17:19:47.280 --> 17:19:49.720
I, rich?

17:19:51.140 --> 17:19:55.040
Yes, you, rich, quite an heiress.

17:19:57.100 --> 17:19:58.380
Silence succeeded.

17:20:00.080 --> 17:20:03.140
You must prove your identity, of course,

17:20:03.880 --> 17:20:05.780
resumed St. John presently.

17:20:06.220 --> 17:20:08.940
A step which will offer no difficulties.

17:20:08.940 --> 17:20:12.200
You can then enter on immediate possession.

17:20:12.920 --> 17:20:15.880
Your fortune is vested in the English funds.

17:20:16.320 --> 17:20:19.080
Briggs has the will and the necessary documents.

17:20:20.720 --> 17:20:23.000
Here was a new card turned up.

17:20:23.460 --> 17:20:29.160
It is a fine thing, reader, to be lifted in a moment from indigence to wealth,

17:20:29.580 --> 17:20:37.120
a very fine thing, but not a matter one can comprehend or consequently enjoy all at once.

17:20:37.640 --> 17:20:42.700
And then there are other chances in life far more thrilling and rapture-giving.

17:20:43.440 --> 17:20:50.060
This is solid, an affair of the actual world, nothing ideal about it.

17:20:50.480 --> 17:20:56.400
All its associations are solid and sober, and its manifestations are the same.

17:20:57.220 --> 17:21:03.180
One does not jump and spring and shout hurrah at hearing one has got a fortune.

17:21:03.660 --> 17:21:08.360
One begins to consider responsibilities and to ponder business.

17:21:08.980 --> 17:21:13.360
On a base of steady satisfaction rise certain grave cares,

17:21:13.960 --> 17:21:19.240
and we contain ourselves and brood over our bliss with a solemn brow.

17:21:20.880 --> 17:21:28.540
Besides, the words legacy, bequest, go side by side with the words death, funeral.

17:21:29.360 --> 17:21:34.300
My uncle, I had heard, was dead, my only relative.

17:21:35.140 --> 17:21:41.640
Ever since being made aware of his existence, I had cherished the hope of one day seeing him.

17:21:42.200 --> 17:21:43.600
Now I never should.

17:21:44.480 --> 17:21:53.500
And then this money came only to me, not to me and a rejoicing family, but to my isolated self.

17:21:54.460 --> 17:21:59.300
It was a grand boon, doubtless, and independence would be glorious.

17:21:59.700 --> 17:22:03.260
Yes, I felt that. That thought swelled my heart.

17:22:04.480 --> 17:22:08.980
You unbend your forehead at last, said Mr. Rivers.

17:22:09.600 --> 17:22:13.860
I thought Medusa had looked at you and that you were turning to stone.

17:22:15.020 --> 17:22:18.480
Perhaps now you will ask how much you are worth.

17:22:19.860 --> 17:22:21.500
How much am I worth?

17:22:22.420 --> 17:22:26.800
Oh, a trifle. Nothing, of course, to speak of.

17:22:27.320 --> 17:22:32.320
Twenty thousand pounds, I think they say. But what is that?

17:22:33.440 --> 17:22:35.800
Twenty thousand pounds!

17:22:37.220 --> 17:22:43.360
Here was a new stunner. I had been calculating on four or five thousand.

17:22:44.140 --> 17:22:46.780
This news actually took my breath for a moment.

17:22:46.780 --> 17:22:52.280
Mr. St. John, whom I had never heard laugh before, laughed now.

17:22:53.140 --> 17:23:00.480
Well, said he, if you had committed a murder and I had told you your crime was discovered,

17:23:00.960 --> 17:23:03.920
you could scarcely look more aghast.

17:23:05.540 --> 17:23:12.840
It is a large sum. Don't you think there is a mistake?

17:23:14.020 --> 17:23:15.460
No mistake at all.

17:23:16.780 --> 17:23:22.180
Perhaps you have read the figures wrong. It may be two thousand.

17:23:23.320 --> 17:23:28.700
It is written in letters, not figures. Twenty thousand.

17:23:30.640 --> 17:23:37.520
I again felt rather like an individual of but average gastronomical powers,

17:23:38.000 --> 17:23:43.680
sitting down to feast alone at a table spread with provisions for a hundred.

17:23:44.480 --> 17:23:47.860
Mr. Rivers rose now and put his cloak on.

17:23:49.040 --> 17:23:56.060
If it were not such a very wild night, he said, I would send Hannah down to keep you company.

17:23:56.540 --> 17:24:00.920
You look too desperately miserable to be left alone.

17:24:01.660 --> 17:24:06.360
But Hannah, poor woman, could not stride the drifts so well as I.

17:24:06.620 --> 17:24:13.100
Her legs are not quite so long. So I must in-leave you to your sorrows.

17:24:13.680 --> 17:24:14.600
Good night.

17:24:15.500 --> 17:24:19.360
He was lifting the latch. A sudden thought occurred to me.

17:24:20.000 --> 17:24:22.040
Stop one minute, I cried.

17:24:23.140 --> 17:24:23.660
Well?

17:24:24.480 --> 17:24:32.400
It puzzles me to know why Mr. Briggs wrote to you about me, or how he knew you or could fancy

17:24:32.400 --> 17:24:38.680
that you, living in such an out-of-the-way place, had the power to aid in my discovery.

17:24:39.630 --> 17:24:47.040
Well, I am a clergyman, he said, and the clergy are often appealed to about odd matters.

17:24:47.960 --> 17:24:49.520
Again the latch rattled.

17:24:50.600 --> 17:24:57.780
No, that does not satisfy me, I exclaimed, and indeed there was something in the hasty

17:24:57.780 --> 17:25:04.100
and unexplanatory reply which, instead of allaying, piqued my curiosity more than ever.

17:25:04.740 --> 17:25:10.820
It is a very strange piece of business, I added. I must know more about it.

17:25:11.420 --> 17:25:12.680
Another time.

17:25:13.560 --> 17:25:15.680
No, tonight, tonight.

17:25:16.440 --> 17:25:23.220
And as he turned from the door, I placed myself between it and him. He looked rather embarrassed.

17:25:24.720 --> 17:25:29.720
You certainly shall not go till you have told me all, I said.

17:25:30.740 --> 17:25:33.280
I would rather not just now.

17:25:34.100 --> 17:25:36.400
You shall, you must.

17:25:37.140 --> 17:25:40.620
I would rather Diana or Mary informed you.

17:25:41.940 --> 17:25:46.080
Of course these objections wrought my eagerness to a climax,

17:25:46.840 --> 17:25:52.020
gratified it must be, and that without delay, and I told him so.

17:25:53.140 --> 17:25:59.420
But I apprised you that I was a hard man, said he, difficult to persuade.

17:26:00.280 --> 17:26:04.040
And I am a hard woman, impossible to put off.

17:26:05.060 --> 17:26:10.600
And then, he pursued, I am cold, no fervour infects me.

17:26:11.740 --> 17:26:20.420
Whereas I am hot and fire dissolves ice, the blaze there has thawed all the snow from your cloak.

17:26:21.000 --> 17:26:26.440
By the same token it has streamed onto my floor and made it like a trampled street.

17:26:26.960 --> 17:26:30.120
As you hope ever to be forgiven, Mr. Rivers,

17:26:30.120 --> 17:26:36.880
the high crime and misdemeanour of spoiling a santed kitchen. Tell me what I wish to know.

17:26:38.240 --> 17:26:45.360
Well then, he said, I yield, if not to your earnestness, to your perseverance,

17:26:45.780 --> 17:26:53.480
as stone is worn by continual dropping. Besides, you must know some day, as well now as later.

17:26:54.260 --> 17:26:56.500
Your name is Jane Eyre.

17:26:57.360 --> 17:26:59.820
Of course that was all settled before.

17:27:00.780 --> 17:27:09.280
You are not, perhaps, aware that I am your namesake, that I was christened St. John Eyre Rivers?

17:27:10.560 --> 17:27:17.860
No, indeed. I remember now seeing the letter E comprised in your initials written in books

17:27:17.860 --> 17:27:22.780
you have at different times lent me. But I never asked for what name it stood.

17:27:23.800 --> 17:27:25.820
But what then, surely?

17:27:26.920 --> 17:27:34.560
I stopped. I could not trust myself to entertain, much less to express, the thought that rushed upon

17:27:34.560 --> 17:27:43.740
me, that embodied itself, that in a second stood out a strong, solid probability. Circumstances

17:27:43.740 --> 17:27:51.580
knit themselves, fitted themselves, shot into order. The chain that had been lying hitherto

17:27:51.580 --> 17:27:59.300
a formless lump of links was drawn out straight. Every ring was perfect, the connection complete.

17:28:00.080 --> 17:28:05.940
I knew by instinct how the matter stood before St. John had said another word.

17:28:06.400 --> 17:28:12.200
But I cannot expect the reader to have the same intuitive perception, so I must repeat his

17:28:12.200 --> 17:28:21.380
explanation. My mother's name was Eyre. She had two brothers, one a clergyman, who married

17:28:21.380 --> 17:28:29.080
Miss Jane Reid of Gateshead, the other John Eyre Esquire Merchant, late of Funkle, Madeira.

17:28:30.040 --> 17:28:37.220
Mr. Briggs, being Mr. Eyre's solicitor, wrote to us last August to inform us of our uncle's death,

17:28:37.600 --> 17:28:43.660
and to say that he had left his property to his brother the clergyman's orphan daughter,

17:28:44.260 --> 17:28:50.060
overlooking us in consequence of a quarrel never forgiven between him and my father.

17:28:50.600 --> 17:28:55.880
He wrote again a few weeks since, to intimate that the heiress was lost,

17:28:56.160 --> 17:29:02.360
and asking if we knew anything of her. A name, casually written on a slip of paper,

17:29:02.780 --> 17:29:06.400
has enabled me to find her out. You know the rest.

17:29:07.680 --> 17:29:11.760
Again he was going, but I set my back against the door.

17:29:12.560 --> 17:29:18.800
Do let me speak, I said. Let me have one moment to draw breath and reflect.

17:29:20.260 --> 17:29:26.940
I paused. He stood before me, hat in hand, looking composed enough. I resumed.

17:29:27.780 --> 17:29:31.680
Your mother was my father's sister. Yes.

17:29:32.520 --> 17:29:36.000
My aunt, consequently. He bowed.

17:29:36.940 --> 17:29:44.060
My Uncle John was your Uncle John? You, Diana, and Mary are his sister's children,

17:29:44.260 --> 17:29:47.880
as I am his brother's child? Undeniably.

17:29:49.180 --> 17:29:55.640
You three, then, are my cousins. Half our blood on each side flows from the same source.

17:29:56.560 --> 17:30:00.160
We are cousins, yes. I surveyed him.

17:30:00.660 --> 17:30:05.140
It seemed I had found a brother, one I could be proud of,

17:30:05.140 --> 17:30:12.020
one I could love, and two sisters whose qualities were such that when I knew them

17:30:12.020 --> 17:30:18.020
but as mere strangers they had inspired me with genuine affection and admiration.

17:30:18.700 --> 17:30:24.860
The two girls on whom, kneeling down on the wet ground and looking through the low,

17:30:25.040 --> 17:30:31.420
latticed window of Moore House kitchen, I had gazed, with so bitter a mixture of interest

17:30:31.420 --> 17:30:38.360
and despair, were my near kinswomen, and the young and stately gentleman who had found me

17:30:38.360 --> 17:30:46.080
almost dying at his threshold was my blood relation, glorious discovery to a lonely wretch.

17:30:46.700 --> 17:30:54.520
This was wealth indeed, wealth to the heart, a mine of pure genial affections.

17:30:55.020 --> 17:31:01.580
This was a blessing, bright, vivid, and exhilarating, not like the ponderous gift of

17:31:01.580 --> 17:31:09.000
gold, rich and welcome enough in its way, but sobering from its weight. I now clapped my hands

17:31:09.000 --> 17:31:13.100
in sudden joy. My pulse bounded, my veins thrilled.

17:31:13.840 --> 17:31:21.380
Oh, I am glad, I am glad, I exclaimed. St. John smiled.

17:31:22.480 --> 17:31:28.460
Did I not say you neglected essential points to pursue trifles? He asked.

17:31:28.860 --> 17:31:34.780
You were serious when I told you you had got a fortune, and now, for a matter of no moment,

17:31:34.860 --> 17:31:41.080
you are excited. What can you mean? It may be of no moment to you.

17:31:41.080 --> 17:31:48.700
You have sisters and don't care for a cousin. But I had nobody, and now three relations,

17:31:49.020 --> 17:31:55.900
or two, if you don't choose to be counted, are born into my world full-grown. I say again,

17:31:55.980 --> 17:32:05.320
I am glad. I walked fast through the room. I stopped, half-suffocated, with the thoughts that

17:32:05.320 --> 17:32:11.800
faster than I could receive, comprehend, settle them, thoughts of what might, could,

17:32:12.080 --> 17:32:19.920
would, and should be, and that ere long. I looked at the blank wall. It seemed a sky

17:32:19.920 --> 17:32:28.140
thick with ascending stars. Everyone lit me to a purpose or delight. Those who had saved my life,

17:32:28.140 --> 17:32:35.100
whom, till this hour, I had loved barrenly, I could now benefit. They were under a yoke.

17:32:35.200 --> 17:32:42.700
I could free them. They were scattered. I could reunite them. The independence, the affluence,

17:32:42.820 --> 17:32:50.100
which was mine, might be theirs too. Were we not four? Twenty thousand pounds shared equally

17:32:50.100 --> 17:32:58.500
be five thousand each. Justice enough and to spare. Justice would be done. Mutual happiness

17:32:58.500 --> 17:33:05.280
secured. Now the wealth did not weigh on me. Now it was not a mere bequest of coin.

17:33:05.820 --> 17:33:14.400
It was a legacy of life, hope, enjoyment. How I looked while these ideas were taking my spirit

17:33:14.400 --> 17:33:22.200
by storm, I cannot tell. But I perceived soon that Mr. Rivers had placed a chair behind me

17:33:22.200 --> 17:33:30.420
and was gently attempting to make me sit down on it. He also advised me to be composed. I scorned

17:33:30.420 --> 17:33:37.200
the insinuation of helplessness and distraction, shook off his hand, and began to walk about again.

17:33:37.920 --> 17:33:44.420
Write to Diana and Mary tomorrow, I said, and tell them to come home directly.

17:33:45.120 --> 17:33:49.100
Diana said they would both consider themselves rich with a thousand pounds,

17:33:49.540 --> 17:33:56.240
so with five thousand they will do very well. Tell me where I can get you a glass of water,

17:33:56.740 --> 17:34:01.360
said St. John. You must really make an effort to tranquilize your feelings.

17:34:02.560 --> 17:34:10.300
Nonsense! And what sort of an effect will the bequest have on you? Will it keep you in England,

17:34:10.800 --> 17:34:15.440
induce you to marry Miss Oliver, and settle down like an ordinary mortal?

17:34:16.360 --> 17:34:23.080
You wander. Your head becomes confused. I have been too abrupt in communicating the news.

17:34:23.480 --> 17:34:25.980
It has excited you beyond your strength.

17:34:26.740 --> 17:34:35.200
Mr. Rivers, you quite put me out of patience. I am rational enough. It is you who misunderstand,

17:34:35.700 --> 17:34:43.160
or rather who affect to misunderstand. Perhaps if you explained yourself a little more fully,

17:34:43.460 --> 17:34:52.300
I should comprehend better. Explain? What is there to explain? You cannot fail to see

17:34:52.300 --> 17:34:59.100
that twenty thousand pounds, the sum in question, divided equally between the nephew and three

17:34:59.100 --> 17:35:06.180
nieces of our uncle, will give five thousand to each. What I want is that you should write

17:35:06.180 --> 17:35:13.140
to your sisters and tell them of the fortune that has accrued to them. To you, you mean?

17:35:13.940 --> 17:35:23.120
I have intimated my view of the case. I am incapable of taking any other. I am not brutally

17:35:23.120 --> 17:35:32.320
selfish, blindly unjust, or fiendishly ungrateful. Besides, I am resolved I will have a home and

17:35:32.320 --> 17:35:40.720
connections. I like Morehouse, and I will live at Morehouse. I like Diana and Mary, and I will

17:35:40.720 --> 17:35:48.900
attach myself for life to Diana and Mary. It would please and benefit me to have five thousand

17:35:48.900 --> 17:35:57.300
pounds. It would torment and oppress me to have twenty thousand, which, moreover, could never be

17:35:57.300 --> 17:36:05.980
mine injustice, though it might in law. I abandon to you, then, what is absolutely superfluous to me.

17:36:05.980 --> 17:36:13.320
Let there be no opposition and no discussion about it. Let us agree amongst each other

17:36:13.320 --> 17:36:21.720
and decide the point at once. This is acting on first impulses. You must take days to consider

17:36:21.720 --> 17:36:29.100
such a matter, ere your word can be regarded as valid. Oh, if all you doubt is my sincerity,

17:36:29.100 --> 17:36:38.920
I am easy. You see the justice of the case? I do see a certain justice, but it is contrary

17:36:38.920 --> 17:36:47.500
to all custom. Besides, the entire fortune is your right. My uncle gained it by his own efforts.

17:36:47.900 --> 17:36:55.200
He was free to leave it to whom he would. He left it to you. After all, justice permits you

17:36:55.200 --> 17:37:00.680
to keep it. You may, with a clear conscience, consider it absolutely your own.

17:37:01.500 --> 17:37:09.640
With me, said I, it is fully as much a matter of feeling as of conscience. I must indulge my

17:37:09.640 --> 17:37:17.860
feelings. I so seldom have had an opportunity of doing so. Were you to argue, object, and annoy me

17:37:17.860 --> 17:37:24.440
for a year, I could not forgo the delicious pleasure of which I have caught a glimpse,

17:37:24.900 --> 17:37:31.860
that of repaying, in part, a mighty obligation, and winning to myself lifelong friends.

17:37:32.740 --> 17:37:40.260
You think so now, rejoined St. John, because you do not know what it is to possess,

17:37:40.260 --> 17:37:47.220
nor consequently to enjoy, wealth. You cannot form a notion of the importance

17:37:47.220 --> 17:37:53.980
twenty thousand pounds would give you, of the place it would enable you to take in society,

17:37:54.520 --> 17:38:03.120
of the prospects it would open to you. You cannot. And you, I interrupted, cannot at all

17:38:03.120 --> 17:38:11.360
imagine the craving I have for fraternal and sisterly love. I never had a home. I never had

17:38:11.360 --> 17:38:19.420
brothers or sisters. I must and will have them now. You are not reluctant to admit me and own me,

17:38:19.420 --> 17:38:28.040
are you? Jane, I will be your brother. My sisters will be your sisters, without stipulating for this

17:38:28.040 --> 17:38:37.920
sacrifice of your just rights. Brother, yes, at the distance of a thousand leagues. Sisters, yes,

17:38:37.920 --> 17:38:45.940
slaving amongst strangers. I, wealthy, gorged with gold I never earned, and do not merit. You,

17:38:46.120 --> 17:38:54.920
penniless, famous equality in fraternization, close union, intimate attachment. But, Jane,

17:38:54.920 --> 17:39:01.120
your aspirations after family ties and domestic happiness may be realized otherwise

17:39:01.120 --> 17:39:10.580
than by the means you contemplate. You may marry. Nonsense again. Marry. I don't want to marry,

17:39:10.920 --> 17:39:18.100
and never shall marry. That is saying too much. Such hazardous affirmations are a proof

17:39:18.100 --> 17:39:25.560
of the excitement under which you labor. It is not saying too much. I know what I feel,

17:39:25.940 --> 17:39:33.040
and how averse are my inclinations to the bare thought of marriage. No one would take me for

17:39:33.040 --> 17:39:41.220
love, and I will not be regarded in the light of a mere money speculation. And I do not want a

17:39:41.220 --> 17:39:50.000
stranger, unsympathizing, alien, different from me. I want my kindred, those with whom I have full

17:39:50.000 --> 17:39:56.700
fellow feeling. Say again you will be my brother. When you uttered the words, I was satisfied,

17:39:56.940 --> 17:40:05.500
happy. Repeat them, if you can. Repeat them sincerely. I think I can. I know I have always

17:40:05.500 --> 17:40:12.000
loved my own sisters, and I know on what my affection for them is grounded respect for their

17:40:12.000 --> 17:40:19.700
worth and admiration of their talents. You too have principle and mind. Your tastes and habits

17:40:19.700 --> 17:40:26.840
resemble Diana's and Mary's. Your presence is always agreeable to me. In your conversation,

17:40:27.200 --> 17:40:35.180
I have already for some time found a salutary solace. I feel I can easily and naturally make

17:40:35.180 --> 17:40:44.000
in my heart for you as my third and youngest sister. Thank you. That contents me for tonight.

17:40:44.740 --> 17:40:50.600
Now you had better go, for if you stay longer you will perhaps irritate me afresh by some

17:40:50.600 --> 17:40:57.440
mistrustful scruple. And the school, Miss Eyre. It must now be shut up, I suppose.

17:40:58.220 --> 17:41:02.640
No, I will retain my post of mistress till you get a substitute.

17:41:03.520 --> 17:41:07.560
He smiled at probation, we shook hands, and he took leave.

17:41:08.740 --> 17:41:15.840
I need not narrate in detail the further struggles I had and arguments I used to get

17:41:15.840 --> 17:41:24.380
matters regarding the legacy settled as I wished. My task was a very hard one, but as I was absolutely

17:41:24.380 --> 17:41:31.340
resolved, as my cousins saw at length that my mind was really and immutably fixed on making a

17:41:31.340 --> 17:41:37.620
just division of the property, as they must in their own hearts have felt the equity of the

17:41:37.620 --> 17:41:43.900
intention, and must besides have been innately conscious that in my place they would have done

17:41:43.900 --> 17:41:50.680
precisely what I wished to do, they yielded at length so far as to consent to put the affair

17:41:50.680 --> 17:41:57.860
to arbitration. The judges chosen were Mr. Oliver and an able lawyer. Both coincided,

17:41:57.900 --> 17:42:05.480
in my opinion, I carried my point. The instruments of transfer were drawn out. St. John, Diana,

17:42:05.480 --> 17:42:09.580
Mary, and I, each became possessed of a competency.

17:42:33.920 --> 17:42:35.120
CHAPTER XXXIV.

17:42:35.680 --> 17:42:37.940
It was near Christmas, by the time all was settled.

17:42:38.420 --> 17:42:40.540
The season of general holiday approached.

17:42:40.540 --> 17:42:45.740
I now closed Morton's school, taking care that the parting should not be barren on my

17:42:45.740 --> 17:42:46.080
side.

17:42:47.040 --> 17:42:51.760
Good fortune opens the hand as well as the heart wonderfully, and to give some what when

17:42:51.760 --> 17:42:57.200
we have largely received is but to afford a vent to the unusual ebullition of the sensations.

17:42:58.060 --> 17:43:03.640
I had long felt with pleasure that many of my rustic scholars liked me, and when we parted,

17:43:03.780 --> 17:43:05.460
that consciousness was confirmed.

17:43:06.020 --> 17:43:09.380
They manifested their affection plainly and strongly.

17:43:10.140 --> 17:43:15.220
Deep was my gratification to find I had really a place in their unsophisticated hearts.

17:43:16.060 --> 17:43:20.820
I promised them that never a week should pass in future that I did not visit them and give

17:43:20.820 --> 17:43:22.640
them an hour's teaching in their school.

17:43:24.100 --> 17:43:29.840
Mr. Rivers came up as, having seen the classes now numbering sixty girls file out before

17:43:29.840 --> 17:43:35.500
me and lock the door, I stood with the key in my hand, exchanging a few words of special

17:43:35.500 --> 17:43:41.520
farewell with some half-dozen of my best scholars, as decent, respectable, modest, and well-informed

17:43:41.520 --> 17:43:45.620
young women as could be found in the ranks of the British peasantry.

17:43:46.400 --> 17:43:51.360
And that is saying a great deal, for, after all, the British peasantry are the best-taught,

17:43:51.480 --> 17:43:54.420
best-mannered, most self-respecting of any in Europe.

17:43:54.880 --> 17:44:01.120
Since those days I have seen paisans and bayrungen, and the best of them seem to me ignorant,

17:44:01.120 --> 17:44:04.160
of course, and besotted compared with my Morton girls.

17:44:05.340 --> 17:44:10.700
Do you consider you have got your reward for a season of exertion, asked Mr. Rivers when

17:44:10.700 --> 17:44:11.540
they were gone?

17:44:12.100 --> 17:44:16.340
Does not the consciousness of having done some real good in your day and generation

17:44:16.340 --> 17:44:17.320
give pleasure?

17:44:18.800 --> 17:44:19.320
Doubtless.

17:44:20.440 --> 17:44:22.600
And you have only toiled a few months.

17:44:23.200 --> 17:44:27.260
Would not a life devoted to the task of regenerating your race be well spent?

17:44:27.940 --> 17:44:29.460
Yes, I said.

17:44:30.120 --> 17:44:32.040
But I could not go on for ever so.

17:44:32.400 --> 17:44:36.620
I want to enjoy my own faculties as well as to cultivate those of other people.

17:44:37.260 --> 17:44:38.680
I must enjoy them now.

17:44:39.040 --> 17:44:41.640
Don't recall either my mind or body to the school.

17:44:42.020 --> 17:44:44.680
I am out of it and disposed for full holiday.

17:44:45.580 --> 17:44:46.940
He looked grave.

17:44:47.860 --> 17:44:48.880
What now?

17:44:49.220 --> 17:44:51.400
What sudden eagerness is this, you events?

17:44:51.820 --> 17:44:53.280
What are you going to do?

17:44:54.060 --> 17:44:56.640
To be active, as active as I can.

17:44:57.200 --> 17:45:01.760
And first I must beg you to set Hannah at liberty and get somebody else to wait on you.

17:45:02.660 --> 17:45:03.640
Do you want her?

17:45:04.500 --> 17:45:06.840
Yes, to go with me to Morehouse.

17:45:07.360 --> 17:45:11.320
Diana and Mary will be at home in a week, and I want to have everything in order against

17:45:11.320 --> 17:45:11.940
their arrival.

17:45:13.080 --> 17:45:14.040
I understand.

17:45:14.480 --> 17:45:16.800
I thought you were flying off on some excursion.

17:45:17.260 --> 17:45:18.420
It is better so.

17:45:18.760 --> 17:45:20.060
Hannah shall go with you.

17:45:20.820 --> 17:45:24.580
Tell her to be ready by to-morrow then, and here is the school-room key.

17:45:25.060 --> 17:45:27.360
I will give you the key of my cottage in the morning.

17:45:27.1000 --> 17:45:28.840
He took it.

17:45:29.980 --> 17:45:32.680
You give it up very gleefully, said he.

17:45:32.980 --> 17:45:37.520
I don't quite understand your light-heartedness, because I cannot tell what employment you

17:45:37.520 --> 17:45:40.920
propose to yourself as a substitute for the one you are relinquishing.

17:45:41.680 --> 17:45:45.700
What aim, what purpose, what ambition in life have you now?

17:45:46.880 --> 17:45:49.820
My first aim will be to clean down.

17:45:50.020 --> 17:45:52.320
Do you comprehend the full force of the expression?

17:45:52.880 --> 17:45:55.900
To clean down Morehouse from chamber to cellar.

17:45:56.380 --> 17:46:02.020
My next to rub it up with beeswax, oil, and an indefinite number of cloths till it glitters again.

17:46:02.580 --> 17:46:07.500
My third to arrange every chair, table, bed, carpet with mathematical precision.

17:46:08.320 --> 17:46:14.060
Afterwards I shall go near to ruin you in coals and peat to keep up good fires in every room.

17:46:14.060 --> 17:46:19.560
And lastly, the two days preceding that on which your sisters are expected will be devoted

17:46:19.560 --> 17:46:24.500
by Hannah and me to such a beating of eggs, sorting of currants, grating of spices,

17:46:25.220 --> 17:46:30.200
compounding of Christmas cakes, chopping up of materials for mince pies, and solemnizing

17:46:30.200 --> 17:46:36.680
of other culinary rites, as words can convey but an inadequate notion of to the uninitiated like you.

17:46:37.220 --> 17:46:41.900
My purpose, in short, is to have all things in an absolutely perfect state of readiness

17:46:41.900 --> 17:46:49.220
for Diana and Mary before next Thursday, and my ambition is to give them a bow ideal of a welcome when they come.

17:46:50.200 --> 17:46:54.020
St. John smiled slight. Still he was dissatisfied.

17:46:54.840 --> 17:46:57.780
It is all very well for the present, said he.

17:46:58.160 --> 17:47:02.280
But seriously, I trust that when the first flush of vivacity is over,

17:47:02.720 --> 17:47:06.960
you will look a little higher than domestic endearments and household joys.

17:47:07.780 --> 17:47:10.640
The best things the world has, I interrupted.

17:47:11.320 --> 17:47:15.080
No, Jane, no. This world is not the scene of fruition.

17:47:15.680 --> 17:47:21.080
Do not attempt to make it so, nor of rest. Do not turn slothful.

17:47:21.600 --> 17:47:23.880
I mean, on the contrary, to be busy.

17:47:24.740 --> 17:47:30.860
Jane, I excuse you for the present. Two months' grace I allow you for the full enjoyment of your new position,

17:47:31.120 --> 17:47:34.840
and for pleasing yourself with this late-found charm of relationship.

17:47:34.840 --> 17:47:41.280
But then I hope you will begin to look beyond Morehouse and Morton, and sisterly society,

17:47:41.680 --> 17:47:45.920
and the selfish calm and sensual comfort of civilized affluence.

17:47:46.300 --> 17:47:50.380
I hope your energies will then once more trouble you with their strength.

17:47:51.340 --> 17:47:52.860
I looked at him with surprise.

17:47:53.760 --> 17:47:58.200
St. John, I said, I think you are almost wicked to talk so.

17:47:58.480 --> 17:48:03.040
I am disposed to be as content as a queen, and you try to stir me up to restlessness.

17:48:03.040 --> 17:48:04.600
To what end?

17:48:06.300 --> 17:48:10.620
To the end of turning to profit the talents which God has committed to your keeping,

17:48:11.100 --> 17:48:14.260
and of which he will surely one day demand a strict account.

17:48:15.040 --> 17:48:19.140
Jane, I shall watch you closely and anxiously, I warn you of that,

17:48:19.580 --> 17:48:26.460
and try to restrain the disproportionate fervour with which you throw yourself into commonplace home pleasures.

17:48:27.100 --> 17:48:30.220
Don't cling so tenaciously to ties of the flesh.

17:48:30.220 --> 17:48:34.680
Save your constancy and ardour for an adequate cause.

17:48:35.320 --> 17:48:38.640
Forbear to waste them on trite, transient objects.

17:48:39.040 --> 17:48:40.180
Do you hear, Jane?

17:48:41.340 --> 17:48:43.580
Yes, just as if you were speaking Greek.

17:48:43.860 --> 17:48:47.600
I feel I have adequate cause to be happy, and I will be happy.

17:48:48.040 --> 17:48:48.660
Good-bye.

17:48:50.020 --> 17:48:54.620
Happy at Morehouse I was, and hard I worked, and so did Hannah.

17:48:54.880 --> 17:48:59.820
She was charmed to see how jovial I could be amidst the bustle of a house turned topsy-turvy.

17:48:59.820 --> 17:49:03.060
How I could dust, and brush, and clean, and cook.

17:49:03.500 --> 17:49:06.720
And really, after a day or two of confusion, worse confounded,

17:49:06.980 --> 17:49:11.1000
it was delightful, by degrees, to invoke order from the chaos ourselves had made.

17:49:12.700 --> 17:49:17.640
I had previously taken a journey to S., to purchase some new furniture,

17:49:18.140 --> 17:49:22.560
my cousins having given me carte blanche to effect what alterations I pleased,

17:49:23.400 --> 17:49:25.980
and of some having been set aside for that purpose.

17:49:25.980 --> 17:49:30.040
The ordinary sitting-room and bedrooms I left much as they were,

17:49:30.380 --> 17:49:33.1000
for I knew Diana and Mary would derive more pleasure from seeing again

17:49:33.1000 --> 17:49:37.120
the old homely tables and chairs and beds

17:49:37.120 --> 17:49:39.940
than from the spectacle of the smartest innovations.

17:49:40.820 --> 17:49:45.280
Still, some novelty was necessary to give their return the piquancy

17:49:45.280 --> 17:49:48.080
with which I wished it to be invested.

17:49:49.060 --> 17:49:51.140
Dark, handsome new carpets and curtains,

17:49:51.140 --> 17:49:56.400
an arrangement of some carefully selected antique ornaments in porcelain and bronze,

17:49:56.920 --> 17:50:00.320
new coverings in mirrors and dressing cases for the toilet tables,

17:50:00.860 --> 17:50:04.180
answered the end. They looked fresh without being glaring.

17:50:05.420 --> 17:50:11.040
A spare parlor and bedroom I refurnished entirely with old mahogany and crimson upholstery.

17:50:11.240 --> 17:50:15.060
I laid canvas on the passage and carpets on the stairs.

17:50:15.680 --> 17:50:18.900
When all was finished, I thought more houses complete a model

17:50:18.900 --> 17:50:23.180
of bright, modest snugness within, as it was at this season,

17:50:23.620 --> 17:50:26.920
a specimen of wintry waste and desert-drewiness without.

17:50:27.900 --> 17:50:32.220
The eventful Thursday at length came. They were expected about dark,

17:50:32.760 --> 17:50:35.440
and at our desk fires were lit upstairs and below.

17:50:35.620 --> 17:50:40.540
The kitchen was in perfect trim. Hannah and I were dressed and all was in readiness.

17:50:41.280 --> 17:50:45.620
St. John arrived first. I had entreated him to keep quite clear of the house

17:50:45.620 --> 17:50:47.020
till everything was arranged.

17:50:47.020 --> 17:50:51.1000
And, indeed, the bare idea of the commotion, at once sorted and trivial,

17:50:52.180 --> 17:50:56.200
going on within its walls, sufficed to scare him to estrangement.

17:50:57.020 --> 17:51:01.220
He found me in the kitchen, watching the progress of certain cakes for tea, then baking.

17:51:02.440 --> 17:51:06.840
Approaching the hearth, he asked if I was at last satisfied with housemaids' work.

17:51:07.460 --> 17:51:12.800
I answered by inviting him to accompany me on a general inspection of the result of my labors.

17:51:12.800 --> 17:51:16.940
With some difficulty I got him to make the tour of the house.

17:51:17.780 --> 17:51:23.060
He just looked in at the doors I opened, and when he had wandered upstairs and downstairs

17:51:23.060 --> 17:51:26.880
he said I must have gone through a great deal of fatigue and trouble

17:51:26.880 --> 17:51:30.940
to have affected such considerable changes in so short a time.

17:51:31.780 --> 17:51:36.480
But not a syllable did he utter indicating pleasure in the improved aspect of his abode.

17:51:37.260 --> 17:51:41.920
This silence damped me. I thought perhaps the alterations had disturbed

17:51:41.920 --> 17:51:46.960
some old associations he valued. I inquired whether this was the case,

17:51:47.480 --> 17:51:49.820
no doubt in a somewhat crestfallen tone.

17:51:50.400 --> 17:51:56.720
Not at all. He had, on the contrary, remarked that I had scrupulously respected every association.

17:51:57.240 --> 17:52:01.780
He feared, indeed, I must have bestowed more thought on the matter than it was worth.

17:52:02.320 --> 17:52:07.340
How many minutes, for instance, had I devoted to studying the arrangement of this very room?

17:52:07.860 --> 17:52:10.560
By the by, could I tell him where such a book was?

17:52:11.560 --> 17:52:13.620
I showed him the volume on the shelf.

17:52:14.120 --> 17:52:19.020
He took it down, and with drawing to his accustomed window recess, he began to read it.

17:52:19.460 --> 17:52:23.440
Now, I did not like this reader. St. John was a good man,

17:52:23.720 --> 17:52:28.520
but I began to feel he had spoken truth of himself when he said he was hard and cold.

17:52:29.260 --> 17:52:32.1000
The humanities and amenities of life had no attraction for him.

17:52:33.600 --> 17:52:35.440
Its peaceful enjoyments no charm.

17:52:36.520 --> 17:52:41.300
Literally, he lived only to aspire, after what was good and great, certainly,

17:52:41.560 --> 17:52:45.700
but still he would never rest, nor approve of others resting around him.

17:52:46.280 --> 17:52:50.700
As I looked at his lofty forehead, still and pale as a white stone,

17:52:51.100 --> 17:52:57.440
at his fine liniments fixed in study, I comprehended all at once that he would hardly make a good husband,

17:52:57.900 --> 17:53:00.320
that it would be a trying thing to be his wife.

17:53:00.320 --> 17:53:05.360
I understood, as by inspiration, the nature of his love for Miss Oliver.

17:53:05.900 --> 17:53:08.760
I agreed with him that it was but a love of the senses.

17:53:09.380 --> 17:53:15.740
I comprehended how he should despise himself for the feverish influence it exercised over him,

17:53:16.660 --> 17:53:19.380
how he should wish to stifle and destroy it,

17:53:19.420 --> 17:53:24.800
and how he should mistrust its ever-conducing permanently to his happiness, or hers.

17:53:24.800 --> 17:53:29.760
I saw he was of the material from which nature hues her heroes,

17:53:30.220 --> 17:53:34.600
Christian and Pagan, her lawgivers, her statesmen, her conquerors,

17:53:34.980 --> 17:53:39.020
a steadfast bulwark for great interests to rest upon,

17:53:39.620 --> 17:53:46.280
but at the fireside too often a cold, cumbrous column, gloomy and out of place.

17:53:46.680 --> 17:53:52.420
This parlour is not his sphere, I reflected, the Himalayan rich or caffer bush,

17:53:52.420 --> 17:53:56.840
even the plague-cursed Guinea Coast swamp would suit him better.

17:53:57.480 --> 17:54:01.460
Well may he eschew the calm of domestic life, it is not his element.

17:54:02.060 --> 17:54:05.940
There his faculties stagnate, they cannot develop or appear to advantage.

17:54:06.680 --> 17:54:10.160
It is in scenes of strife and danger, where courage is proved,

17:54:10.400 --> 17:54:16.760
and energy exercised, and fortitude tasked, that he will speak and move, the leader and superior.

17:54:17.480 --> 17:54:20.600
A merry child would have the advantage of him on this hearth.

17:54:20.600 --> 17:54:24.260
He is right to choose a missionary's career. I see it now.

17:54:25.240 --> 17:54:29.440
They are coming, they are coming! cried Hannah, throwing open the parlour door.

17:54:30.020 --> 17:54:33.900
At the same moment old Carlo barked joyfully. Out I ran.

17:54:34.380 --> 17:54:37.240
It was now dark, but a rumbling of wheels was audible.

17:54:37.960 --> 17:54:42.280
Hannah soon had a lantern lit. The vehicle had stopped at the wicket.

17:54:42.580 --> 17:54:47.180
The driver opened the door. First one well-known form, then another, stepped out.

17:54:47.180 --> 17:54:52.080
In a minute I had my face under their bonnets in contact first with Mary's soft cheek,

17:54:52.420 --> 17:54:56.940
then with Diana's flowing curls. They laughed, kissed me, then Hannah,

17:54:57.280 --> 17:55:01.620
patted Carlo, who was half-wild with delight, asked eagerly if all was well,

17:55:01.740 --> 17:55:04.800
and being assured in the affirmative, hastened into the house.

17:55:05.800 --> 17:55:08.820
They were stiff from their long and jolting drive from Whitcross,

17:55:09.280 --> 17:55:14.960
and chilled with the frosty night air, but their pleasant countenances expanded to the cheerful firelight.

17:55:14.960 --> 17:55:19.500
While the driver and Hannah brought in the boxes, they demanded St. John.

17:55:20.040 --> 17:55:25.080
At this moment he advanced from the parlour. They both threw their arms round his neck at once.

17:55:25.760 --> 17:55:29.880
He gave each one a quiet kiss, said in a low tone a few words of welcome,

17:55:30.500 --> 17:55:35.980
stood awhile to be talked to, and then, intimating that he supposed they would soon rejoin him in the parlour,

17:55:36.560 --> 17:55:38.600
withdrew there as to a place of refuge.

17:55:39.140 --> 17:55:44.940
I had lit their candles to go upstairs, but Diana had first to give hospitable orders respecting the driver.

17:55:45.900 --> 17:55:51.340
This done, both followed me. They were delighted with the renovation and decoration of their rooms,

17:55:51.760 --> 17:55:55.620
with the new drapery and fresh carpets, and rich tinted china vases.

17:55:56.260 --> 17:55:58.600
They expressed their gratification ungrudgingly.

17:55:59.520 --> 17:56:02.760
I had the pleasure of feeling that my arrangements met their wishes exactly,

17:56:02.760 --> 17:56:07.660
and that what I had done added a vivid charm to their joyous return home.

17:56:08.700 --> 17:56:14.680
Sweet was that evening. My cousins, full of exhilaration, were so eloquent in narrative and comment

17:56:14.680 --> 17:56:17.900
that their fluency covered St. John's taciturnity.

17:56:18.340 --> 17:56:25.220
He was sincerely glad to see his sisters, but in their glow of fervour and flow of joy he could not sympathize.

17:56:25.680 --> 17:56:30.420
The event of the day, that is, the return of Diana and Mary, pleased him.

17:56:30.420 --> 17:56:36.340
But the accompaniments of that event, the glad tumult, the garrulous glee of reception, irked him.

17:56:36.720 --> 17:56:38.980
I saw he wished the quieter morrow was come.

17:56:39.520 --> 17:56:45.400
In the very meridian of the night's enjoyment, about an hour after tea, a rap was heard at the door.

17:56:46.160 --> 17:56:48.120
Hannah entered with the intimation that

17:56:48.120 --> 17:56:54.580
a poor lad was come at that unlikely time to fetch Mr. Rivers to see his mother, who was drawing away.

17:56:55.560 --> 17:56:57.080
Where does she live, Hannah?

17:56:57.680 --> 17:57:03.120
Clear up at Whitcross Brow, almost four miles off, and more and moss all the way.

17:57:04.080 --> 17:57:05.420
Tell them I will go.

17:57:06.300 --> 17:57:11.160
I'm sure, sir, you had better not. It's the worst road to travel after dark that can be.

17:57:11.440 --> 17:57:17.660
There's no track at all over the bog, and then it is such a bitter night, the keenest win you ever felt.

17:57:17.940 --> 17:57:20.900
You had better send word, sir, that you will be there in the morning.

17:57:21.940 --> 17:57:25.020
But he was already in the passage, putting on his cloak,

17:57:25.020 --> 17:57:28.700
and without one objection, one murmur, he departed.

17:57:29.720 --> 17:57:32.860
It was then nine o'clock. He did not return till midnight.

17:57:33.860 --> 17:57:38.040
Starved and tired enough he was, but he looked happier than when he set out.

17:57:38.400 --> 17:57:41.620
He had performed an act of duty, made an exertion,

17:57:42.180 --> 17:57:46.340
felt his own strength to do and deny, and was on better terms with himself.

17:57:47.220 --> 17:57:50.420
I am afraid the whole of the ensuing week tried his patience.

17:57:50.420 --> 17:57:54.040
It was Christmas week. We took no settled employment,

17:57:54.440 --> 17:57:58.340
but spent it in a sort of married domestic dissipation.

17:57:59.240 --> 17:58:02.720
The air of the Moors, the freedom of home, the dawn of prosperity,

17:58:02.980 --> 17:58:07.260
acted on Diana and Mary's spirits like some life-giving elixir.

17:58:07.580 --> 17:58:10.640
They were gay from morning till noon, from noon till night.

17:58:11.040 --> 17:58:15.100
They could always talk, and their discourse, witty, pithy, original,

17:58:15.100 --> 17:58:19.600
had such charms for me that I preferred listening to and sharing in it

17:58:19.600 --> 17:58:23.800
to doing anything else. St. John did not rebuke our vivacity,

17:58:23.940 --> 17:58:27.200
but he escaped from it. He was seldom in the house.

17:58:27.400 --> 17:58:30.420
His parish was large, the population scattered,

17:58:30.720 --> 17:58:35.020
and he found daily business in visiting the sick and poor in its different districts.

17:58:35.540 --> 17:58:39.820
One morning, at breakfast, Diana, after looking a little pensive for some minutes,

17:58:40.040 --> 17:58:42.880
asked him if his plans were yet unchanged.

17:58:44.060 --> 17:58:46.880
Unchanged and unchangeable was the reply,

17:58:47.180 --> 17:58:50.900
and he proceeded to inform us that his departure from England

17:58:50.900 --> 17:58:53.720
was now definitely fixed for the ensuing year.

17:58:54.880 --> 17:58:59.080
And Rosamond Oliver suggested Mary, the words seeming to

17:58:59.080 --> 17:59:03.160
escape her lips involuntarily, for no sooner had she uttered them

17:59:03.160 --> 17:59:07.140
than she made a gesture as if wishing to recall them. St. John

17:59:07.140 --> 17:59:11.140
had a book in his hand. It was his unsocial custom to read at meals.

17:59:11.140 --> 17:59:13.300
He closed it and looked up.

17:59:14.900 --> 17:59:19.100
Rosamond Oliver, said he, is about to be married to Mr. Granby,

17:59:19.440 --> 17:59:23.320
one of the best connected and most estimable residents in S.,

17:59:24.260 --> 17:59:26.460
grandson and heir to Sir Frederick Granby.

17:59:27.040 --> 17:59:29.400
I had the intelligence from her father yesterday.

17:59:30.700 --> 17:59:35.060
His sisters looked at each other, and at me. We all three looked at him.

17:59:35.480 --> 17:59:37.240
He was serene as glass.

17:59:38.020 --> 17:59:41.520
The match must have been got up hastily, said Diana.

17:59:41.980 --> 17:59:43.780
They cannot have known each other long.

17:59:44.680 --> 17:59:48.280
But two months they met in October at the county ball at S.

17:59:48.840 --> 17:59:52.700
But where there are no obstacles to a union, as in the present case,

17:59:52.800 --> 17:59:57.100
where the connection is in every point desirable, delays are unnecessary.

17:59:57.680 --> 18:00:01.340
They will be married as soon as S. Palace, which Sir Frederick

18:00:01.340 --> 18:00:04.340
gives up to them, can be refitted for their reception.

18:00:05.220 --> 18:00:08.840
The first time I found St. John alone after this communication,

18:00:09.340 --> 18:00:12.320
I felt tempted to inquire if the event distressed him.

18:00:12.540 --> 18:00:16.580
But he seemed so little to need sympathy, that so far from

18:00:16.580 --> 18:00:20.200
venturing to offer him more, I experienced some shame at the

18:00:20.200 --> 18:00:24.500
recollection of what I had already hazarded. Besides, I was out of practice

18:00:24.500 --> 18:00:27.1000
in talking to him. His reserve was again frozen over,

18:00:28.320 --> 18:00:32.540
and my frankness was congealed beneath it. He had not kept his

18:00:32.540 --> 18:00:36.400
promise of treating me like his sisters. He continually made little

18:00:36.400 --> 18:00:40.360
chilling differences between us, which did not at all tend to the

18:00:40.360 --> 18:00:44.340
development of cordiality. In short, now that I was acknowledged

18:00:44.340 --> 18:00:48.340
his kinswoman, and lived under the same roof with him, I felt the

18:00:48.340 --> 18:00:52.360
distance between us to be far greater than when he had known me only as the village

18:00:52.360 --> 18:00:56.380
school mistress. When I remembered how far I had once been admitted

18:00:56.380 --> 18:01:00.060
to his confidence, I could hardly comprehend his present frigidity.

18:01:01.080 --> 18:01:04.620
Such being the case, I felt not a little surprised

18:01:04.620 --> 18:01:08.420
when he raised his head suddenly from the desk, over which he was stooping,

18:01:08.620 --> 18:01:12.180
and said, You see, Jane, the battle is fought,

18:01:12.260 --> 18:01:16.160
and the victory won. Startled at being thus addressed,

18:01:16.380 --> 18:01:20.620
I did not immediately reply. After a moment's hesitation I answered,

18:01:21.640 --> 18:01:24.340
But are you sure you are not in the position

18:01:24.340 --> 18:01:27.460
of those conquerors whose triumphs have cost them too dear?

18:01:27.460 --> 18:01:31.880
Would not such another ruin you? I think not,

18:01:32.300 --> 18:01:35.680
and if I were, it does not much signify. I shall never

18:01:35.680 --> 18:01:39.640
be called upon to contend for such another. The event of the

18:01:39.640 --> 18:01:43.860
conflict is decisive. My way is now clear. I thank God for it.

18:01:44.580 --> 18:01:47.620
So saying, he returned to his papers in his silence.

18:01:48.520 --> 18:01:52.660
As our mutual happiness, i.e. Diana's, Mary's, and mine,

18:01:53.180 --> 18:01:56.260
settled into a quiet character, and we resumed our usual habits

18:01:56.260 --> 18:01:59.780
and regular studies, St. John stayed more at home.

18:02:00.260 --> 18:02:03.580
He sat with us in the same room, sometimes for hours together.

18:02:04.500 --> 18:02:08.200
While Mary drew, Diana pursued a course of encyclopedic reading

18:02:08.200 --> 18:02:11.540
she had, to my awe and amazement, undertaken,

18:02:11.960 --> 18:02:15.920
and I fagged away at German. He pondered a mystic lore of his own,

18:02:16.300 --> 18:02:20.460
that of some Eastern tongue, the acquisition of which he thought necessary to his

18:02:20.460 --> 18:02:24.280
plans. Thus engaged, he appeared, sitting

18:02:24.280 --> 18:02:28.440
in his own recess, quiet and absorbed enough. But that blue eye

18:02:28.440 --> 18:02:32.460
of his had a habit of leaving the outlandish-looking grammar, and wandering

18:02:32.460 --> 18:02:36.200
over, and sometimes fixing upon us, his fellow students,

18:02:36.720 --> 18:02:40.440
with a curious intensity of observation. If caught,

18:02:40.480 --> 18:02:44.680
it would be instantly withdrawn, yet ever and anon, it returned searchingly

18:02:44.680 --> 18:02:48.580
to our table. I wondered what it meant. I wondered, too,

18:02:48.580 --> 18:02:52.640
at the punctual satisfaction. He never failed to exhibit on an

18:02:52.640 --> 18:02:57.260
occasion that seemed to me of small moment, namely, my weekly visit

18:02:57.260 --> 18:03:00.660
to Morton School. And still more was I puzzled when,

18:03:00.780 --> 18:03:04.1000
if the day was unfavorable, if there was snow or rain or high wind,

18:03:05.340 --> 18:03:09.140
and his sisters urged me not to go, he would invariably

18:03:09.140 --> 18:03:13.260
make light of their solicitude, and encourage me to accomplish the task

18:03:13.260 --> 18:03:17.320
without regard to the elements. Jane is not such a weakling

18:03:17.320 --> 18:03:21.420
as you would make her, he would say. She can bear a mountain blast,

18:03:21.420 --> 18:03:25.800
or a shower, or a few flakes of snow, as well as any of us.

18:03:26.120 --> 18:03:29.540
Her constitution is both sound and elastic, better

18:03:29.540 --> 18:03:33.360
calculated to endure variations of climate than many more robust.

18:03:34.300 --> 18:03:37.640
And when I returned, sometimes a good deal tired, and

18:03:37.640 --> 18:03:41.540
not a little weather-beaten, I never dared to complain, because

18:03:41.540 --> 18:03:45.420
I saw that to murmur would be to vex him. On all occasions

18:03:45.420 --> 18:03:49.520
fortitude pleased him. The reverse was a special annoyance.

18:03:49.520 --> 18:03:53.780
One afternoon, however, I got leave to stay at home, because I really

18:03:53.780 --> 18:03:57.340
had a cold. His sisters were gone to Morton in my stead.

18:03:57.840 --> 18:04:01.900
I sat reading Schiller, he deciphering his crabbed oriental

18:04:01.900 --> 18:04:05.820
scrolls. As I exchanged a translation for an exercise,

18:04:06.240 --> 18:04:10.040
I happened to look his way. There I found myself under the influence

18:04:10.040 --> 18:04:13.680
of the ever watchful blue eye. How long it had been searching

18:04:13.680 --> 18:04:17.360
me through and through, and over and over, I cannot tell.

18:04:17.360 --> 18:04:21.660
So keen was it, and yet so cold, I felt for the moment

18:04:21.660 --> 18:04:25.760
superstitious, as if I were sitting in the room with something uncanny.

18:04:26.720 --> 18:04:28.060
Jane, what are you doing?

18:04:29.180 --> 18:04:30.040
Learning German.

18:04:31.020 --> 18:04:33.920
I want you to give up German and learn Hindostani.

18:04:34.720 --> 18:04:36.260
You are not in earnest.

18:04:37.240 --> 18:04:40.760
In such earnest that I must have it so, and I will tell you why.

18:04:41.520 --> 18:04:45.480
He then went on to explain that Hindostani was the language he himself

18:04:45.480 --> 18:04:49.640
was at present studying, that, as he advanced, he was apt to forget

18:04:49.640 --> 18:04:53.540
the commencement, that it would assist him greatly to have a pupil

18:04:53.540 --> 18:04:57.440
with whom he might again and again go over the elements, and so fix them

18:04:57.440 --> 18:05:01.720
thoroughly in his mind, that his choice had hovered for some time between

18:05:01.720 --> 18:05:06.340
me and his sisters, but that he had fixed on me because he saw I could

18:05:06.340 --> 18:05:10.540
sit at a task the longest of the three. Would I do him this favor?

18:05:11.080 --> 18:05:14.520
I should not, perhaps, have to make the sacrifice long,

18:05:14.520 --> 18:05:17.660
as it wanted now barely three months to his departure.

18:05:18.840 --> 18:05:22.860
St. John was not a man to be lightly refused. You felt that

18:05:22.860 --> 18:05:26.080
every impression made on him, either for pain or pleasure,

18:05:26.500 --> 18:05:29.680
was deep-graved and permanent. I consented.

18:05:30.440 --> 18:05:34.140
When Diana and Mary returned, the former found her scholar

18:05:34.140 --> 18:05:38.380
transferred from her to her brother. She laughed, and both she and Mary

18:05:38.380 --> 18:05:42.640
agreed that St. John should never have persuaded them to such a step.

18:05:42.640 --> 18:05:45.700
He answered quietly, I know it.

18:05:46.760 --> 18:05:50.840
I found him a very patient, very forbearing, and yet an

18:05:50.840 --> 18:05:54.700
exacting master. He expected me to do a great deal,

18:05:55.180 --> 18:05:58.920
and when I fulfilled his expectations, he, in his own way,

18:05:59.060 --> 18:06:02.440
fully testified his approbation. By degrees,

18:06:02.680 --> 18:06:06.380
he acquired a certain influence over me that took away my liberty of mind.

18:06:07.040 --> 18:06:10.180
His praise and notice were more restraining than his indifference.

18:06:10.180 --> 18:06:13.880
I could no longer talk or laugh freely when he was by,

18:06:14.380 --> 18:06:18.560
because a tiresomely importunate instinct reminded me that vivacity,

18:06:18.860 --> 18:06:21.640
at least in me, was distasteful to him.

18:06:22.140 --> 18:06:26.600
I was so fully aware that only serious moods and occupations were acceptable

18:06:26.600 --> 18:06:30.320
that in his presence every effort to sustain or follow

18:06:30.320 --> 18:06:34.800
any other became vain. I fell under a freezing spell.

18:06:35.500 --> 18:06:38.200
When he said go, I went. Come,

18:06:38.200 --> 18:06:42.280
I came. Do this. I did it. But I did not

18:06:42.280 --> 18:06:46.180
love my servitude. I wished many a time he had continued

18:06:46.180 --> 18:06:50.320
to neglect me. One evening, when at bedtime, his

18:06:50.320 --> 18:06:54.500
sisters and I stood round him, bidding him good night, he kissed each of them,

18:06:54.500 --> 18:06:58.620
as was his custom, and, as was equally his custom, he gave me

18:06:58.620 --> 18:07:02.540
his hand. Diana, who chanced to be in a frolicsome humor,

18:07:03.180 --> 18:07:06.400
she was not painfully controlled by his will, for hers

18:07:06.400 --> 18:07:09.200
in another way was as strong, exclaimed,

18:07:09.940 --> 18:07:14.380
St. John, you used to call Jane your third sister, but you don't treat her as such.

18:07:14.720 --> 18:07:18.640
You should kiss her, too. She pushed me towards him.

18:07:19.120 --> 18:07:22.540
I thought Diana very provoking and felt uncomfortably confused,

18:07:23.460 --> 18:07:26.500
and while I was thus thinking and feeling, St. John

18:07:26.500 --> 18:07:30.360
bent his head. His Greek face was brought to a level

18:07:30.360 --> 18:07:34.040
with mine. His eyes questioned my eyes piercingly.

18:07:34.040 --> 18:07:38.500
He kissed me. There are no such things as marble kisses,

18:07:38.660 --> 18:07:42.040
or ice kisses, or I should say, my ecclesiastical

18:07:42.860 --> 18:07:45.320
cousin's salute belonged to one of these classes.

18:07:46.040 --> 18:07:50.160
But there may be experiment kisses, and his was an experiment

18:07:50.160 --> 18:07:53.900
kiss. When given, he viewed me to learn the result.

18:07:54.500 --> 18:07:57.780
It was not striking. I am sure I did not blush.

18:07:58.440 --> 18:08:02.220
Perhaps I might have turned a little pale, for I felt as if

18:08:02.220 --> 18:08:06.460
the kiss were a seal affixed to my fetters. He never omitted

18:08:06.460 --> 18:08:10.200
the ceremony afterwards, and the gravity and quiescence

18:08:10.200 --> 18:08:14.560
with which I underwent it seemed to invest it for him with a certain charm.

18:08:15.160 --> 18:08:17.1000
As for me, I daily wished more to please him.

18:08:18.340 --> 18:08:22.560
But to do so, I felt daily more and more that I must disown

18:08:22.560 --> 18:08:25.820
half my nature, stifle half my faculties,

18:08:26.400 --> 18:08:30.620
wrest my tastes from their original bent, force myself to the adoption

18:08:30.620 --> 18:08:34.640
of pursuits for which I had no natural vocation. He wanted

18:08:34.640 --> 18:08:38.840
to train me to an elevation I could never reach. It racked

18:08:38.840 --> 18:08:42.840
me hourly to aspire to the standard he uplifted. The thing was

18:08:42.840 --> 18:08:46.740
as impossible as to mold my irregular features to his correct and classic

18:08:46.740 --> 18:08:50.620
pattern, to give my changeable green eyes the sea-blue

18:08:50.620 --> 18:08:54.860
tint and solemn lester of his own. Not his ascendancy

18:08:54.860 --> 18:08:58.940
alone, however, held me enthralled at present. Of late, it had been

18:08:58.940 --> 18:09:03.380
easy enough for me to look sad. A cankering evil sat at my heart

18:09:03.380 --> 18:09:07.180
and drained my happiness at its source, the evil of suspense.

18:09:08.500 --> 18:09:11.480
Perhaps you think I had forgotten Mr. Rochester, reader,

18:09:12.040 --> 18:09:14.140
amidst these changes of place and fortune.

18:09:14.900 --> 18:09:19.120
Not for a moment. His idea was still with me,

18:09:19.160 --> 18:09:22.980
because it was not a vapor sunshine could disperse, nor a

18:09:22.980 --> 18:09:27.160
sand-traced effigy storms could wash away. It was a name

18:09:27.160 --> 18:09:31.160
engraven on a tablet, fated to last as long as the marble

18:09:31.160 --> 18:09:35.040
it inscribed. The craving to know what had become of him

18:09:35.040 --> 18:09:39.260
followed me everywhere. When I was at Morton, I re-entered

18:09:39.260 --> 18:09:43.340
my cottage every evening to think of that, and now at Morehouse

18:09:43.340 --> 18:09:46.380
I sought my bedroom each night to brood over it.

18:09:46.920 --> 18:09:50.960
In the course of my necessary correspondence with Mr. Briggs about the will,

18:09:51.480 --> 18:09:55.260
I had inquired if he knew anything of Mr. Rochester's present residence

18:09:55.260 --> 18:09:59.660
and state of health, but, as St. John had conjectured, he was quite

18:09:59.660 --> 18:10:03.660
ignorant of all concerning him. I then wrote to Mrs. Fairfax

18:10:03.660 --> 18:10:07.280
entreating information on the subject. I had calculated

18:10:07.280 --> 18:10:11.200
with certainty on this step answering my end. I felt sure

18:10:11.200 --> 18:10:15.320
it would elicit an early answer. I was astonished when a fortnight

18:10:15.320 --> 18:10:19.520
passed without reply, but when two months wore away, and day after

18:10:19.520 --> 18:10:23.340
day the post arrived and brought nothing for me, I fell prey to

18:10:23.340 --> 18:10:27.260
the keenest anxiety. I wrote again.

18:10:27.480 --> 18:10:31.500
There was a chance of my first letter having missed. Renewed hope

18:10:31.500 --> 18:10:35.320
followed renewed effort. It shone like the former for some weeks,

18:10:35.560 --> 18:10:39.540
then, like it, faded, flickered. Not a line,

18:10:39.880 --> 18:10:43.340
not a word reached me. When half a year wasted

18:10:43.340 --> 18:10:47.260
in vain expectancy, my hope died out, and then I felt

18:10:47.260 --> 18:10:51.460
dark indeed. A fine spring shone round me, which

18:10:51.460 --> 18:10:55.460
I could not enjoy. Summer approached. Diana tried to cheer

18:10:55.460 --> 18:10:59.380
me. She said I looked ill, and wished to accompany me to the seaside.

18:11:00.020 --> 18:11:03.740
This St. John opposed. He said I did not want dissipation,

18:11:03.760 --> 18:11:07.300
I wanted employment. My present life was too purposeless.

18:11:07.480 --> 18:11:11.900
I required a name, and, I suppose, by way of supplying deficiencies,

18:11:12.520 --> 18:11:15.340
he prolonged still further my lessons in Hindostani,

18:11:15.980 --> 18:11:18.760
and grew more urgent in requiring their accomplishment.

18:11:18.760 --> 18:11:23.180
And I, like a fool, never thought of resisting him. I could not

18:11:23.180 --> 18:11:26.820
resist him. One day I had come to my studies

18:11:26.820 --> 18:11:31.140
in lower spirits than usual. The ebb was occasioned by a poignantly

18:11:31.140 --> 18:11:34.980
felt disappointment. Hannah had told me in the morning there was a letter

18:11:34.980 --> 18:11:38.940
for me, and when I went down to take it, almost certain that the long

18:11:38.940 --> 18:11:43.080
looked-for tidings were vouchsafed me at last, I found only

18:11:43.080 --> 18:11:46.120
an unimportant note from Mr. Briggs on business.

18:11:46.120 --> 18:11:49.900
The bitter check had wrung for me some tears,

18:11:50.040 --> 18:11:54.420
and now, as I sat poring over the crabbed characters of flourishing tropes

18:11:54.420 --> 18:11:57.680
of an Indian scribe, my eyes felled again.

18:11:58.760 --> 18:12:02.300
St. John called me to his side to read. In attempting to

18:12:02.300 --> 18:12:06.040
do this, my voice failed me. Words were lost and sobs.

18:12:06.560 --> 18:12:10.220
He and I were the only occupants of the parlour. Diana was practicing

18:12:10.220 --> 18:12:13.220
her music in the drawing-room. Mary was gardening.

18:12:13.220 --> 18:12:17.500
It was a very fine May day, clear, sunny, and breezy.

18:12:18.040 --> 18:12:20.860
My companion expressed no surprise at this emotion,

18:12:21.380 --> 18:12:24.600
nor did he question me as to its cause. He only said,

18:12:25.120 --> 18:12:28.460
We will wait a few minutes, Jane, till you are more composed.

18:12:29.400 --> 18:12:33.460
And while I smothered the paroxysm with all haste, he sat calm

18:12:33.460 --> 18:12:37.300
and patient, leaning on his desk and looking like a physician watching with the eye

18:12:37.300 --> 18:12:41.300
of science an expected and fully understood crisis in a patient's

18:12:41.300 --> 18:12:45.300
malady. Having stifled my sobs, wiped my eyes,

18:12:45.400 --> 18:12:49.280
and muttered something about not being very well that morning, I resumed

18:12:49.280 --> 18:12:53.540
my task, and succeeded in completing it. St. John

18:12:53.540 --> 18:12:57.580
put away my books, and his, locked his desk, and said,

18:12:58.380 --> 18:13:01.400
Now, Jane, you shall take a walk, and with me.

18:13:02.020 --> 18:13:05.220
I will call Diana and Mary. No.

18:13:05.700 --> 18:13:09.600
I want only one companion this morning, and that must be you.

18:13:09.600 --> 18:13:13.720
Put on your things, go out by the kitchen door. Take the road

18:13:13.720 --> 18:13:16.900
towards the head of Marsh Glen. I will join you in a moment.

18:13:17.540 --> 18:13:21.820
I know no medium. I never in my life have known any medium

18:13:21.820 --> 18:13:25.900
in my dealings with positive hard characters, antagonistic to my own,

18:13:26.380 --> 18:13:29.480
between absolute submission and determined revolt.

18:13:30.080 --> 18:13:33.780
I have always faithfully observed the one up to the very moment

18:13:33.780 --> 18:13:37.260
of bursting, sometimes with volcanic vehemence, into the other,

18:13:37.260 --> 18:13:41.600
and as neither present circumstances warranted, nor my present

18:13:41.600 --> 18:13:45.340
mood inclined me to mutiny, I observed careful obedience to

18:13:45.340 --> 18:13:49.100
St. John's directions, and in ten minutes I was treading the wild

18:13:49.100 --> 18:13:53.460
track of the Glen, side by side with him. The breeze was from the

18:13:53.460 --> 18:13:57.540
west. It came over the hills, sweet with scents of heath and rush.

18:13:58.240 --> 18:14:01.480
The sky was of stainless blue. The stream descending

18:14:01.480 --> 18:14:05.740
the ravine, swelled with past spring rains, poured along plentiful

18:14:05.740 --> 18:14:10.040
and clear, catching golden gleams from the sun and sapphire tints

18:14:10.040 --> 18:14:13.800
from the firmament. As we advanced and left the track,

18:14:13.960 --> 18:14:17.400
we trod a soft turf, mossy fine and emerald green,

18:14:17.960 --> 18:14:21.880
minutely enameled with a tiny white flower, and spangled with a star-like

18:14:21.880 --> 18:14:25.680
yellow blossom. The hills meantime shut us quite in,

18:14:25.980 --> 18:14:29.040
for the Glen, towards its head, wound to their very core.

18:14:29.940 --> 18:14:34.320
Let us rest here, said St. John, as we reached the first stragglers

18:14:34.320 --> 18:14:38.460
of a battalion of rocks, guarding a sort of pass beyond which

18:14:38.460 --> 18:14:42.520
the beck rushed down a waterfall, and where, still a little further,

18:14:42.720 --> 18:14:46.460
the mountain shook off turf and flower, had only heath for

18:14:46.460 --> 18:14:50.500
raiment, and crag for gem, where it exaggerated the wild

18:14:50.500 --> 18:14:54.460
to the savage, and exchanged the fresh for the frowning,

18:14:54.860 --> 18:14:58.620
where it guarded the forlorn hope of solitude and a last refuge

18:14:58.620 --> 18:15:02.180
for silence. I took a seat.

18:15:02.180 --> 18:15:06.220
St. John stood near me. He looked up the pass and down

18:15:06.220 --> 18:15:10.200
the hollow. His glance wandered away with the stream, and turned

18:15:10.200 --> 18:15:14.280
to traverse the unclouded heaven which colored it. He removed his

18:15:14.280 --> 18:15:18.300
hat, let the breeze stir his hair and kiss his brow. He seemed

18:15:18.300 --> 18:15:22.480
in communion with the genius of the haunt. With his eye he bade farewell

18:15:22.480 --> 18:15:23.100
to something.

18:15:24.120 --> 18:15:28.360
And I shall see it again, he said aloud, in dreams when I

18:15:28.360 --> 18:15:32.080
sleep by the gangies, and again in a more remote hour,

18:15:32.380 --> 18:15:36.560
when another slumber overcomes me on the shore of a darker stream.

18:15:37.900 --> 18:15:40.000
Strange words of a strange love!

18:15:40.560 --> 18:15:43.480
An austere patriot's passion for his fatherland!

18:15:44.260 --> 18:15:48.540
He sat down. For half an hour we never spoke. Neither he to me

18:15:48.540 --> 18:15:52.540
nor I to him. That interval passed. He recommends

18:15:52.540 --> 18:15:56.520
Jane, I go in six weeks. I have taken my birth

18:15:56.520 --> 18:15:59.980
in an East Indian inn which sails on the 20th of June.

18:16:00.840 --> 18:16:04.780
God will protect you, for you have undertaken his work, I answered.

18:16:05.800 --> 18:16:09.160
Yes, said he, there is my glory

18:16:09.160 --> 18:16:12.780
and joy. I am the servant of an infallible master.

18:16:13.360 --> 18:16:16.680
I am not going out under human guidance, subject to

18:16:16.680 --> 18:16:20.720
the defective laws and erring control of my feeble fellow worms.

18:16:21.460 --> 18:16:25.020
My king, my law-giver, my captain, is the all-perfect.

18:16:25.020 --> 18:16:29.320
It seems strange to me that all round me do not burn

18:16:29.320 --> 18:16:33.260
to enlist under the same banner, to join in the same enterprise.

18:16:34.560 --> 18:16:37.120
All have not your powers, and it would be folly

18:16:37.120 --> 18:16:39.600
for the feeble to wish to march with the strong.

18:16:40.820 --> 18:16:44.940
I do not speak to the feeble, or think of them. I address

18:16:44.940 --> 18:16:49.220
only such as are worthy of the work, and competent to accomplish it.

18:16:50.240 --> 18:16:53.060
Those are few in number, and difficult to discover.

18:16:54.280 --> 18:16:57.120
You say truly, but when found,

18:16:57.400 --> 18:17:00.860
it is right to stir them up, to urge and exhort them to effort,

18:17:01.020 --> 18:17:05.100
to show them what their gifts are, and why they were given, to speak

18:17:05.100 --> 18:17:08.880
heaven's message in their ear, to offer them direct from God

18:17:08.880 --> 18:17:13.220
a place in the ranks of his chosen. If they are really

18:17:13.220 --> 18:17:17.140
qualified for the task, will not their own hearts be the first

18:17:17.140 --> 18:17:21.140
to inform them of it? I felt as if an awful charm was

18:17:21.140 --> 18:17:25.220
framing round and gathering over me. I trembled to hear some fatal

18:17:25.220 --> 18:17:28.260
words spoken which would at once declare and rivet the spell.

18:17:29.900 --> 18:17:33.500
And what does your heart say? demanded St. John.

18:17:34.600 --> 18:17:36.900
My heart is mute, my heart is mute,

18:17:37.240 --> 18:17:41.660
I answered, struck and thrilled. Then I must speak for it,

18:17:41.880 --> 18:17:44.980
continued the deep, relentless voice. Jane,

18:17:45.220 --> 18:17:49.460
come with me to India. Come as my help-meet and fellow-labourer.

18:17:50.280 --> 18:17:53.620
The glen and sky spun round, the hills heaved.

18:17:53.980 --> 18:17:57.640
It was as if I had heard a summons from heaven, as if a visionary messenger,

18:17:58.440 --> 18:18:00.580
like him of Macedonia, had announced,

18:18:01.180 --> 18:18:04.880
Come over and help us. But I was no apostle.

18:18:05.300 --> 18:18:08.500
I could not behold the herald, I could not receive his call.

18:18:09.600 --> 18:18:12.360
Oh, St. John, I cried, have some mercy.

18:18:13.220 --> 18:18:17.240
I appealed to one who, in the discharge of what he believed his duty,

18:18:17.240 --> 18:18:20.600
knew neither mercy nor remorse. He continued,

18:18:21.680 --> 18:18:24.800
God and nature intended you for a missionary's wife.

18:18:25.080 --> 18:18:28.440
It is not personal, but mental endowments they have given you.

18:18:28.860 --> 18:18:33.540
You are formed for labour, not for love. A missionary's wife you must,

18:18:33.840 --> 18:18:37.540
shall be. You shall be mine. I claim you, not for my

18:18:37.540 --> 18:18:41.340
pleasure, but for my sovereign service. I am not fit

18:18:41.340 --> 18:18:45.480
for it, I have no vocation, I said. He had calculated

18:18:45.480 --> 18:18:49.160
on these first objections. He was not irritated by them.

18:18:49.660 --> 18:18:53.600
Indeed, as he leaned back against the crag behind him, folded his

18:18:53.600 --> 18:18:57.620
arms on his chest, and fixed his countenance, I saw he was prepared

18:18:57.620 --> 18:19:01.520
for a long and trying opposition, and had taken in a stock of patience

18:19:01.520 --> 18:19:05.620
to last him to its close. Resolved, however, that the clothes

18:19:05.620 --> 18:19:09.160
should be conquest for him. Humility, Jane,

18:19:09.540 --> 18:19:13.800
said he, is the groundwork of Christian virtues. You say

18:19:13.800 --> 18:19:17.560
right that you are not fit for the work. Who is fit for it?

18:19:17.720 --> 18:19:21.900
Or, who, that ever truly called, believes himself worthy

18:19:21.900 --> 18:19:25.520
of the summons? I, for instance, am but dust and ashes.

18:19:26.080 --> 18:19:29.960
With St. Paul, I acknowledge myself the chiefest of sinners,

18:19:30.480 --> 18:19:33.960
but I do not suffer this sense of my personal vileness to daunt

18:19:33.960 --> 18:19:38.160
me. I know, my leader, that he is just

18:19:38.160 --> 18:19:41.940
as well as mighty, and while he has chosen a feeble instrument to

18:19:41.940 --> 18:19:45.660
perform a great task, he will, from the boundless stores of his

18:19:45.660 --> 18:19:49.480
providence, supply the inadequacy of the means to the end.

18:19:50.000 --> 18:19:53.980
Think like me, Jane. Trust like me. It is the rock of

18:19:53.980 --> 18:19:57.800
ages I ask you to lean on. Do not doubt, but it will bear the weight

18:19:57.800 --> 18:20:01.800
of your human weakness. I do not understand

18:20:01.800 --> 18:20:05.580
a missionary life. I have never studied missionary labors.

18:20:06.880 --> 18:20:10.580
There, I, humble as I am, can give you the aid you want.

18:20:10.580 --> 18:20:15.000
I can set your task from hour to hour, stand by you always,

18:20:15.600 --> 18:20:18.920
help you from moment to moment. This I could do in the beginning.

18:20:19.660 --> 18:20:22.860
Soon, for I know your powers, you would be as strong and apt

18:20:22.860 --> 18:20:25.560
as myself, and would not require my help.

18:20:26.700 --> 18:20:30.980
But my powers, where are they for this undertaking? I do not feel

18:20:30.980 --> 18:20:34.300
them. Nothing speaks or stirs in me while you talk.

18:20:34.800 --> 18:20:38.100
I am sensible of no light kindling, no life quickening,

18:20:38.100 --> 18:20:42.300
no voice cancelling or cheering. Oh, I wish I could

18:20:42.300 --> 18:20:46.000
make you see how much my mind is at this moment like a rayless dungeon,

18:20:46.460 --> 18:20:50.160
with one shrinking fear fettered in its steps, the fear of

18:20:50.160 --> 18:20:53.460
being persuaded by you to attempt what I cannot accomplish.

18:20:54.520 --> 18:20:58.400
I have an answer for you. Hear it. I have watched

18:20:58.400 --> 18:21:02.160
you ever since we first met. I have made you my study for

18:21:02.160 --> 18:21:06.240
ten months. I have proved you in that time by sundry tests,

18:21:06.240 --> 18:21:10.540
and what have I seen and elicited? In the village school I found

18:21:10.540 --> 18:21:14.260
you could perform well, punctually, uprightly, labor,

18:21:14.400 --> 18:21:18.560
uncongenial to your habits and inclinations. I saw you could perform

18:21:18.560 --> 18:21:22.460
it with capacity and tact. You could win while you controlled.

18:21:23.180 --> 18:21:26.420
In the calm with which you learnt you had become suddenly rich,

18:21:26.880 --> 18:21:29.720
I read a mind clear of the vice of Dimah.

18:21:29.940 --> 18:21:34.420
Lucre had no undue power over you. In the resolute readiness with

18:21:34.420 --> 18:21:38.400
which you cut your wealth into four shares, keeping but one to yourself

18:21:38.400 --> 18:21:41.900
and relinquishing the three others to the claim of abstract justice,

18:21:42.480 --> 18:21:46.680
I recognized a soul that reveled in the flame and excitement of sacrifice.

18:21:47.260 --> 18:21:50.200
In the tractability with which, at my wish,

18:21:50.420 --> 18:21:54.420
you first took a study in which you were interested, and adopted

18:21:54.420 --> 18:21:58.720
another because it interested me. In the untiring assiduity

18:21:58.720 --> 18:22:02.700
with which you have since persevered in it. In the unflagging

18:22:02.700 --> 18:22:06.580
energy and unshaken temper with which you have met its difficulties,

18:22:07.280 --> 18:22:10.640
I acknowledge the compliment of the qualities I seek.

18:22:11.520 --> 18:22:15.120
Jane, you are docile, diligent, disinterested,

18:22:15.640 --> 18:22:18.140
faithful, constant, and courageous,

18:22:18.920 --> 18:22:23.140
very gentle, and very heroic. Cease to mistrust

18:22:23.140 --> 18:22:26.500
yourself. I can trust you unreservedly.

18:22:26.840 --> 18:22:30.920
As a conductress of Indian schools and a helper amongst Indian women,

18:22:30.920 --> 18:22:35.000
your assistance will be, to me, invaluable.

18:22:36.480 --> 18:22:39.060
My iron shroud contracted round me.

18:22:39.440 --> 18:22:42.180
Persuasion advanced with slow, sure step.

18:22:43.120 --> 18:22:47.140
Shut my eyes as I would. These last words of his succeeded in making

18:22:47.140 --> 18:22:50.800
the way, which had seemed blocked up, comparatively clear.

18:22:51.680 --> 18:22:55.120
My work, which had appeared so vague, so hopelessly diffuse,

18:22:55.980 --> 18:22:58.960
condensed itself as he proceeded, and assumed a definite form

18:22:58.960 --> 18:23:02.100
under his shaping hand. He waited for an answer.

18:23:02.680 --> 18:23:06.600
I demanded a quarter of an hour to think before I again hazarded a reply.

18:23:08.000 --> 18:23:10.700
Very willingly, he rejoined, and rising,

18:23:11.320 --> 18:23:14.900
he strode a little distance up the pass, threw himself down

18:23:14.900 --> 18:23:17.100
on a swell of heath, and there lay still.

18:23:18.600 --> 18:23:22.780
I can do what he wants me to do. I am forced to see and acknowledge that,

18:23:22.780 --> 18:23:27.240
I meditated. That is, if life be spared me,

18:23:27.240 --> 18:23:31.400
but I feel mine is not the existence to be long protracted under an

18:23:31.400 --> 18:23:34.880
Indian son. What then? He does not care for that.

18:23:35.460 --> 18:23:39.640
When my time came to die, he would resign me in all serenity and sanctity

18:23:39.640 --> 18:23:43.460
to the God who gave me. The case is very

18:23:43.460 --> 18:23:47.280
plain before me. In leaving England, I should leave a loved

18:23:47.280 --> 18:23:51.040
but empty land. Mr. Rochester is not there.

18:23:52.160 --> 18:23:55.820
And if he were, what is, what can that ever be

18:23:55.820 --> 18:23:59.220
to me? My business is to live without him now,

18:23:59.500 --> 18:24:03.840
nothing so absurd, so weak as to drag on from day to day as if

18:24:03.840 --> 18:24:07.160
I were waiting some impossible change in circumstances,

18:24:07.620 --> 18:24:11.860
which might reunite me to him. Of course, as St. John once

18:24:11.860 --> 18:24:16.060
said, I must seek another interest in life to replace the one lost.

18:24:16.620 --> 18:24:19.840
Is not the occupation he now offers me truly the most

18:24:19.840 --> 18:24:23.740
glorious man can adopt or God assign? Is it not

18:24:23.740 --> 18:24:28.060
by its noble cares and sublime results, the one best calculated

18:24:28.060 --> 18:24:31.400
to fill the void left by up-torn affections and demolished hopes?

18:24:32.300 --> 18:24:35.440
I believe I must say yes, and yet I shudder.

18:24:36.420 --> 18:24:39.880
Alas, if I join St. John, I abandon half myself.

18:24:40.420 --> 18:24:43.320
If I go to India, I go to premature death.

18:24:44.000 --> 18:24:48.000
And how will the interval between leaving England for India and India for the

18:24:48.000 --> 18:24:51.900
grave be filled? Oh, I know well. That too

18:24:51.900 --> 18:24:55.960
is very clear to my vision. By straining to satisfy St. John till

18:24:55.960 --> 18:25:00.760
my sinews ache, I shall satisfy him, to the finest central point

18:25:00.760 --> 18:25:03.400
and farthest outward circle of his expectations.

18:25:04.080 --> 18:25:08.260
If I do go with him, if I do make the sacrifice he urges,

18:25:08.580 --> 18:25:12.400
I will make it absolutely. I will throw all on the altar,

18:25:12.720 --> 18:25:17.360
heart, vitals, the entire victim. He will never love me,

18:25:17.500 --> 18:25:20.700
but he shall approve me. I will show him energies

18:25:20.700 --> 18:25:24.560
he has not seen, resources he has never suspected.

18:25:25.580 --> 18:25:28.840
Yes, I can work as hard as he can, and with his

18:25:28.840 --> 18:25:32.840
little grudging. Consent, then, to his demand is possible.

18:25:33.700 --> 18:25:36.700
But for one item, one dreadful item,

18:25:37.480 --> 18:25:40.760
it is that he asks me to be his wife, and has no more

18:25:40.760 --> 18:25:44.400
of a husband's heart for me than that frowning giant of a rock,

18:25:44.940 --> 18:25:48.760
down which the stream is foaming in yonder gorge. He prizes

18:25:48.760 --> 18:25:52.940
me as a soldier with a good weapon, and that is all. Unmarried to

18:25:52.940 --> 18:25:56.940
him, this would never grieve me. But can I let him complete

18:25:56.940 --> 18:26:00.780
his calculations, coolly put into practice his plans,

18:26:01.360 --> 18:26:05.060
go through the wedding ceremony? Can I receive from him

18:26:05.060 --> 18:26:08.800
the bridal ring, endure all the forms of love, which

18:26:08.800 --> 18:26:13.080
I doubt not he would scrupulously observe, and know that the

18:26:13.080 --> 18:26:16.840
spirit was quite absent? Can I bear the consciousness

18:26:16.840 --> 18:26:20.460
that every endearment he bestows is a sacrifice made on principle?

18:26:21.460 --> 18:26:25.300
No, such a martyrdom would be monstrous. I will

18:26:25.300 --> 18:26:29.260
never undergo it. As his sister I might accompany him,

18:26:29.640 --> 18:26:32.400
not as his wife. I will tell him so.

18:26:33.480 --> 18:26:37.260
I looked towards the knoll, there he lay, still as a prostrate

18:26:37.260 --> 18:26:41.220
column. His face turned to me, his eye beaming

18:26:41.220 --> 18:26:45.660
watchful and keen. He started to his feet and approached me.

18:26:45.660 --> 18:26:49.220
I am ready to go to India, if I may go free.

18:26:50.740 --> 18:26:53.640
Your answer requires a commentary, he said.

18:26:54.060 --> 18:26:57.800
It is not clear. You have hitherto been

18:26:57.800 --> 18:27:01.660
my adopted brother, I your adopted sister. Let us

18:27:01.660 --> 18:27:05.720
continue as such. You and I had better not marry. He shook

18:27:05.720 --> 18:27:09.780
his head. Adopted fraternity will not do in this case.

18:27:10.200 --> 18:27:13.740
If you were my real sister it would be different. I should take

18:27:13.740 --> 18:27:17.980
you and seek no wife. But, as it is, either our union

18:27:17.980 --> 18:27:21.500
must be consecrated and sealed by marriage, or it cannot exist.

18:27:22.300 --> 18:27:25.460
Practical obstacles oppose themselves to any other plan.

18:27:26.080 --> 18:27:29.700
Do you not see it, Jane? Consider a moment. Your strong

18:27:29.700 --> 18:27:33.700
sense will guide you. I did consider, and

18:27:33.700 --> 18:27:37.860
still my sense, such as it was, directed me only to the fact that we did

18:27:37.860 --> 18:27:41.580
not love each other as man and wife should, and therefore

18:27:41.580 --> 18:27:44.620
it inferred we ought not to marry. I said so.

18:27:45.640 --> 18:27:49.880
St. John, I returned, I regard you as a brother, you me as a sister.

18:27:50.260 --> 18:27:53.820
So let us continue. We cannot, we cannot,

18:27:54.300 --> 18:27:57.880
he answered with short, sharp determination. It would not

18:27:57.880 --> 18:28:01.880
do. You have said you will go with me to India. Remember, you have said

18:28:01.880 --> 18:28:05.960
that. Conditionally. Well, well,

18:28:06.180 --> 18:28:09.640
to the main point, the departure with me from England,

18:28:09.640 --> 18:28:13.860
the cooperation with me and my future labors. You do not object.

18:28:14.300 --> 18:28:17.760
You have already as good as put your hand to the plow. You are

18:28:17.760 --> 18:28:22.060
too consistent to withdraw it. You have but one end to keep in view,

18:28:22.240 --> 18:28:25.000
how the work you have undertaken can best be done.

18:28:25.920 --> 18:28:29.800
Simplify your complicated interests, feelings, thoughts, wishes, aims.

18:28:30.500 --> 18:28:33.880
Merge all considerations in one purpose, that

18:28:33.880 --> 18:28:37.780
of fulfilling with effect, with power, the mission of your great

18:28:37.780 --> 18:28:41.200
master. To do so you must have a coadjutor,

18:28:41.700 --> 18:28:45.660
not a brother, that is a loose tie, but a husband.

18:28:46.320 --> 18:28:50.200
I too do not want a sister. A sister might any day be taken

18:28:50.200 --> 18:28:54.020
from me. I want a wife, the sole help-meat

18:28:54.020 --> 18:28:57.920
I can influence efficiently in life and retain absolutely

18:28:57.920 --> 18:29:01.900
till death. I shuddered as he spoke, I felt

18:29:01.900 --> 18:29:05.200
his influence in my marrow, his hold on my limbs.

18:29:06.280 --> 18:29:09.860
Seek one elsewhere than in me, St. John, seek one fitted

18:29:09.860 --> 18:29:13.800
to you. One fitted to my purpose you mean,

18:29:14.220 --> 18:29:17.800
fitted to my vocation. Again I tell you, it is not

18:29:17.800 --> 18:29:21.420
the insignificant private individual, the mere man with the man's

18:29:21.780 --> 18:29:24.940
selfish senses I wish to mate. It is a missionary.

18:29:26.280 --> 18:29:29.680
And I will give the missionary my energies. It is all he

18:29:29.680 --> 18:29:33.480
wants, but not myself. That would be only adding the husk and shell

18:29:33.480 --> 18:29:37.280
to the kernel. For them he has no use. I retain them.

18:29:37.880 --> 18:29:41.920
You cannot, you ought not. Do you think God will be satisfied

18:29:41.920 --> 18:29:45.360
with half an oblation? Will he accept a mutilated

18:29:45.360 --> 18:29:49.580
sacrifice? It is the cause of God, I advocate. It is

18:29:49.580 --> 18:29:53.640
under his standard, I enlist you. I cannot accept on his behalf

18:29:53.640 --> 18:29:56.780
a divided allegiance. It must be entire.

18:29:57.640 --> 18:30:01.820
Oh, I will give my heart to God, I said. You do not want it.

18:30:02.400 --> 18:30:06.040
I will not swear, reader, that there was not something of repressed

18:30:06.040 --> 18:30:09.500
sarcasm both in the tone in which I uttered this sentence,

18:30:09.880 --> 18:30:13.840
and in the feeling that accompanied it. I had silently feared

18:30:13.840 --> 18:30:16.740
St. John till now, because I had not understood him.

18:30:17.780 --> 18:30:21.400
He had held me in awe, because he had held me in doubt.

18:30:21.820 --> 18:30:26.020
How much of him was saint, how much mortal, I could not hear to

18:30:26.020 --> 18:30:29.860
foretell. But revelations were being made in this conference.

18:30:29.860 --> 18:30:33.820
The analysis of his nature was proceeding before my eyes.

18:30:34.200 --> 18:30:37.880
I saw his fallibilities. I comprehended them.

18:30:38.220 --> 18:30:42.100
I understood that, sitting there, where I did, on the bank of Heath,

18:30:42.660 --> 18:30:46.040
and with that handsome form before me, I sat at

18:30:46.040 --> 18:30:49.880
the feet of a man, erring his eye. The veil fell

18:30:49.880 --> 18:30:54.080
from his hardness and despotism. Having felt in him the presence

18:30:54.080 --> 18:30:57.880
of these qualities, I felt his imperfection, and took courage.

18:30:57.880 --> 18:31:01.420
I was with an equal, one with whom I might argue,

18:31:01.980 --> 18:31:04.540
one whom, if I saw good, I might resist.

18:31:06.240 --> 18:31:09.880
He was silent after I had uttered the last sentence, and I presently

18:31:09.880 --> 18:31:14.240
risked an upward glance at his countenance. His eye bent on me,

18:31:14.460 --> 18:31:17.340
expressed at once stern surprise and keen inquiry.

18:31:18.380 --> 18:31:21.580
Is she sarcastic, and sarcastic to me,

18:31:21.880 --> 18:31:25.720
it seemed to say. What does this signify?

18:31:26.460 --> 18:31:29.500
Do not let us forget that this is a solemn matter,

18:31:29.740 --> 18:31:33.920
he said ere long, one of which we may neither think

18:31:33.920 --> 18:31:38.040
nor talk lightly without sin. I trust, Jane, you are

18:31:38.040 --> 18:31:42.060
in earnest when you say you will give your heart to God. It is all I want.

18:31:43.000 --> 18:31:45.760
Once wrench your heart from man, and fix it on your

18:31:45.760 --> 18:31:49.940
Maker. The advancement of that Maker's spiritual kingdom on earth

18:31:49.940 --> 18:31:53.920
will be your chief delight and endeavor. You will be ready to do at

18:31:53.920 --> 18:31:57.920
once whatever furthers that end. You will see what impetus

18:31:57.920 --> 18:32:01.840
would be given to your efforts and mind by our physical and mental union

18:32:01.840 --> 18:32:06.120
in marriage, the only union that gives a character of permanent conformity

18:32:06.520 --> 18:32:09.720
to the destinies and designs of human beings.

18:32:10.480 --> 18:32:14.080
And passing over all minor compresses, all trivial

18:32:14.080 --> 18:32:18.380
difficulties and delicacies of feeling, all scruple about the degree,

18:32:18.980 --> 18:32:22.380
kind, strength, or tenderness of mere personal inclination,

18:32:22.380 --> 18:32:25.380
you will hasten to enter into that union at once.

18:32:26.420 --> 18:32:30.420
Shall I, I said briefly, and I looked at his features, beautiful in their

18:32:30.420 --> 18:32:33.980
harmony, but strangely formidable in their still severity,

18:32:34.580 --> 18:32:38.380
at his brow, commanding but not open, at his eyes,

18:32:38.500 --> 18:32:42.740
bright and deep, and searching, but never soft, at his tall

18:32:42.740 --> 18:32:46.500
imposing figure, and fancied myself an idea,

18:32:46.860 --> 18:32:50.080
his wife. Oh, it would never do,

18:32:50.080 --> 18:32:54.620
as his curate, his comrade, all would be right. I would cross

18:32:54.620 --> 18:32:58.500
oceans with him in that capacity, toil under eastern suns

18:32:58.500 --> 18:33:02.140
in Asian deserts with him in that office, admire and

18:33:02.140 --> 18:33:06.380
emulate his courage and devotion and vigor, accommodate quietly

18:33:06.380 --> 18:33:10.380
to his masterhood, smile undisturbed at his ineradicable

18:33:10.380 --> 18:33:14.020
ambition, discriminate the Christian from the man,

18:33:14.680 --> 18:33:18.200
profoundly esteem the one, and freely forgive the other.

18:33:18.200 --> 18:33:22.680
I should suffer often, no doubt, attached to him only in this capacity,

18:33:23.260 --> 18:33:25.880
my body would be under rather a stringent yoke,

18:33:26.260 --> 18:33:30.300
but my heart and mind would be free. I should still have

18:33:30.300 --> 18:33:34.340
my unbladed self to turn to, my natural unenslaved

18:33:34.340 --> 18:33:37.580
feelings with which to communicate in moments of loneliness.

18:33:38.600 --> 18:33:42.460
There would be recesses in my mind which would be only mine, to which

18:33:42.460 --> 18:33:46.480
he never came, and sentiments growing there fresh and sheltered,

18:33:46.480 --> 18:33:50.560
which his austerity could never blight, nor his measured warrior march

18:33:50.560 --> 18:33:54.700
trampled down. But as his wife, at his side always,

18:33:54.800 --> 18:33:58.500
and always restrained and always checked, forced to keep the fire of

18:33:58.500 --> 18:34:02.600
my nature continually low, to compel it to burn inwardly and never

18:34:02.600 --> 18:34:06.520
utter a cry, though the imprisoned flame consumed vital after

18:34:06.520 --> 18:34:09.100
vital, this would be unendurable.

18:34:10.740 --> 18:34:14.200
St. John, I exclaimed, when I had got so far in my meditation.

18:34:15.280 --> 18:34:17.900
Well? he answered icily.

18:34:19.440 --> 18:34:23.200
I repeat, I freely consent to go with you as your fellow missionary,

18:34:23.540 --> 18:34:27.920
but not as your wife. I cannot marry you and become part of you.

18:34:28.740 --> 18:34:32.060
A part of me you must become, he answered steadily.

18:34:32.820 --> 18:34:34.640
Otherwise the whole bargain is void.

18:34:35.540 --> 18:34:39.360
How can I, a man not yet thirty, take out with me to India

18:34:39.360 --> 18:34:42.340
a girl of nineteen, unless she be married to me?

18:34:42.340 --> 18:34:46.500
How can we be forever together, sometimes in solitudes,

18:34:47.540 --> 18:34:50.380
sometimes amidst savage tribes and unwed?

18:34:50.880 --> 18:34:54.820
Very well, I said shortly, under the circumstances, quite as

18:34:54.820 --> 18:34:58.720
well as if I were either your real sister, or a man and a clergyman

18:34:58.720 --> 18:35:02.240
like yourself. It is known that you are not my sister.

18:35:02.560 --> 18:35:06.820
I cannot introduce you as such. To attempt it would be to fasten

18:35:06.820 --> 18:35:11.020
injurious suspicions on us both. And for the rest,

18:35:11.020 --> 18:35:15.520
though you have a man's vigorous brain, you have a woman's heart.

18:35:15.680 --> 18:35:17.740
And it would not do.

18:35:18.300 --> 18:35:23.300
It would do, I affirmed with some disdain, perfectly well. I have a woman's heart,

18:35:23.460 --> 18:35:27.840
but not where you are concerned. For you I have only a comrade's

18:35:27.840 --> 18:35:31.580
constancy, a fellow soldier's frankness, fidelity, fraternity,

18:35:31.720 --> 18:35:35.200
if you like, a neophyte's respect and submission to his

18:35:35.200 --> 18:35:37.840
hierophant. Nothing more. Don't fear.

18:35:39.140 --> 18:35:42.900
It is what I want, he said, speaking to himself.

18:35:43.840 --> 18:35:47.580
It is just what I want, and there are obstacles in the way.

18:35:47.860 --> 18:35:51.740
They must be hewn down. Jane, you would not repent

18:35:51.740 --> 18:35:55.200
marrying me, be certain of that. We must be married.

18:35:55.700 --> 18:35:59.240
I repeat it. There is no other way, and undoubtedly

18:35:59.240 --> 18:36:02.840
enough of love would follow upon marriage to render the union right

18:36:02.840 --> 18:36:06.960
even in your eyes. I scorn your idea of love.

18:36:06.960 --> 18:36:11.060
I could not help saying, as I rose up and stood before him,

18:36:11.360 --> 18:36:15.240
leaning my back against the rock, I scorn the counterfeit

18:36:15.240 --> 18:36:19.860
sentiment you offer. Yes, St. John, I scorn you when you offer it.

18:36:20.780 --> 18:36:23.220
He looked at me fixedly, compressing

18:36:23.480 --> 18:36:27.080
his well-cut lips while he did so. Whether he was

18:36:27.080 --> 18:36:31.240
incensed or surprised, or what, it was not easy to tell.

18:36:31.880 --> 18:36:34.120
He could command his countenance thoroughly.

18:36:35.940 --> 18:36:38.800
I scarcely expected to hear that expression

18:36:38.800 --> 18:36:42.500
from you, he said. I think I have done

18:36:42.500 --> 18:36:44.820
and uttered nothing to deserve scorn.

18:36:46.260 --> 18:36:50.300
I was touched by his gentle tone, and overawed by his high, calm

18:36:50.300 --> 18:36:54.080
mind. Forgive me the words, St. John,

18:36:54.420 --> 18:36:58.120
but it is your own fault that I have been roused to speak so unguardedly.

18:36:58.980 --> 18:37:02.440
You have introduced a topic on which our natures are at variance,

18:37:02.440 --> 18:37:06.780
a topic we should never discuss. The very name of love

18:37:06.780 --> 18:37:10.460
is an apple of discord between us. If the reality were

18:37:10.460 --> 18:37:13.360
required, what should we do? How should we feel?

18:37:13.960 --> 18:37:17.960
My dear cousin, abandon your scheme of marriage. Forget it.

18:37:19.060 --> 18:37:22.620
No, said he. It is a long, cherished

18:37:22.620 --> 18:37:26.140
scheme, and the only one which can secure my great end.

18:37:26.660 --> 18:37:30.440
But I shall urge you no further at present. Tomorrow I leave

18:37:30.440 --> 18:37:34.640
home for Cambridge. I have many friends there to whom I should wish

18:37:34.640 --> 18:37:38.140
to say farewell. I shall be absent to fortnight.

18:37:38.780 --> 18:37:42.800
Take that space of time to consider my offer, and do not forget

18:37:42.800 --> 18:37:46.520
that if you reject it, it is not me you deny, but God.

18:37:47.440 --> 18:37:50.900
Through my means, he opens to you a noble career,

18:37:51.660 --> 18:37:54.440
as my wife only can you enter upon it.

18:37:54.960 --> 18:37:58.540
Refuse to be my wife, and you limit yourself forever to

18:37:58.540 --> 18:38:01.580
a track of selfish ease and barren obscurity.

18:38:02.720 --> 18:38:06.460
Trumble, lest in that case you should be numbered with those who have denied

18:38:06.460 --> 18:38:09.280
the faith, and are worse than infidels.

18:38:11.300 --> 18:38:14.840
He had done. Turning for me, he once

18:38:14.840 --> 18:38:18.820
more looked to the river, looked to hill. But this time

18:38:18.820 --> 18:38:22.700
his feelings were all pent in his heart. I was not worthy to hear

18:38:22.700 --> 18:38:26.820
them uttered. As I walked by his side homeward, I read

18:38:26.820 --> 18:38:31.120
well in his iron silence all he felt towards me. The disappointment

18:38:31.120 --> 18:38:34.940
of an austere and despotic nature, which has met resistance where

18:38:34.940 --> 18:38:39.100
it expected submission, the disapprobation of a cool and flexible

18:38:39.100 --> 18:38:43.000
judgment, which has detected in another feelings and views in which

18:38:43.000 --> 18:38:46.880
it has no power to sympathize. In short, as a man,

18:38:47.300 --> 18:38:50.880
he would have wished to coerce me into obedience. It was only

18:38:50.880 --> 18:38:54.960
as a sincere Christian he bore so patiently with my perversity, and

18:38:54.960 --> 18:38:57.780
allowed so long a space for reflection and repentance.

18:38:58.740 --> 18:39:02.740
That night, after he had kissed his sisters, he thought proper to forget

18:39:02.740 --> 18:39:06.340
even to shake hands with me, but left the room in silence.

18:39:07.500 --> 18:39:11.360
I, who though I had no love, had much friendship for him.

18:39:12.240 --> 18:39:14.420
I was hurt by the marked omission.

18:39:15.140 --> 18:39:17.880
So much hurt that tears started to my eyes.

18:39:18.580 --> 18:39:22.940
I see you and St. John have been quarreling, Jane, said Diana, during

18:39:22.940 --> 18:39:27.160
your walk on the moor. But go after him. He is now lingering in the passage

18:39:27.160 --> 18:39:29.220
expecting you. He will make it up.

18:39:30.240 --> 18:39:34.780
I have not much pride under such circumstances. I would always

18:39:34.780 --> 18:39:38.860
rather be happy than dignified, and I ran after him. He stood

18:39:38.860 --> 18:39:40.000
at the foot of the stairs.

18:39:41.000 --> 18:39:43.300
Good night, St. John, said I.

18:39:44.020 --> 18:39:46.240
Good night, Jane, he replied calmly.

18:39:47.080 --> 18:39:51.040
Then shake hands, I added. What a cold, loose

18:39:51.040 --> 18:39:55.340
touch he impressed on my fingers. He was deeply displeased

18:39:55.340 --> 18:39:58.900
by what had occurred that day. Corgeality would not warm,

18:39:59.080 --> 18:40:03.200
nor tears move him. No happy reconciliation was to

18:40:03.200 --> 18:40:06.640
be had with him. No cheering smile or generous word.

18:40:07.180 --> 18:40:11.180
But still the Christian was patient and placid, and when I asked

18:40:11.180 --> 18:40:14.940
him if he forgave me, he answered that he was not in the habit of

18:40:14.940 --> 18:40:19.240
cherishing the remembrance of vexation, that he had nothing to

18:40:19.240 --> 18:40:23.440
give, not having been offended. And with that answer he left me.

18:40:24.140 --> 18:40:26.980
I would much rather he had knocked me down.

18:40:49.260 --> 18:40:49.740
35.

18:40:51.920 --> 18:40:55.800
He did not leave for Cambridge the next day, as he had said he would.

18:40:56.640 --> 18:41:10.080
He deferred his departure a whole week, and during that time he made me feel what severe punishment a good yet stern and conscientious, yet implacable man can inflict on one who has offended him.

18:41:10.720 --> 18:41:21.020
Without one overt act of hostility, one abrading word, he contrived to impress me momently with the conviction that I was put beyond the pale of his favor.

18:41:22.040 --> 18:41:31.060
Not that St. John harbored a spirit of unchristian vindictiveness, not that he would have injured a hair of my head if it had been fully in his power to do so.

18:41:31.760 --> 18:41:36.640
Both by nature and principle, he was superior to the mean gratification of vengeance.

18:41:37.380 --> 18:41:47.720
He had forgiven me for saying I scorned him and his love, but he had not forgotten the words, and as long as he and I lived, he never would forget them.

18:41:47.720 --> 18:42:00.880
I saw by his look when he turned to me that they were always written on the air between him and me, whenever I spoke they sounded in my voice to his ear, and their echo toned every answer he gave me.

18:42:00.880 --> 18:42:29.440
He did not abstain from conversing with me. He even called me as usual each morning to join him at his desk, and I fear the corrupt man within him had a pleasure unimparted to and unshared by the pure Christian, in evincing with what skill he could, while acting and speaking apparently just as usual, extract from every deed and every phrase the spirit of interest and approval which had formerly communicated a certain austere charm to his language and manner.

18:42:29.440 --> 18:42:40.880
To me he was in reality become no longer flesh but marble. His eye was a cold bright blue gem, his tongue a speaking instrument, nothing more.

18:42:42.060 --> 18:42:53.140
All this was torture to me, refined lingering torture. It kept up a slow fire of indignation and a trembling trouble of grief which harassed and crushed me altogether.

18:42:53.860 --> 18:43:09.220
I felt how, if I were his wife, this good man, pure as the deep sunless source, could soon kill me, without drawing from my veins a single drop of blood or receiving on his own crystal conscience the faintest stain of crime.

18:43:10.120 --> 18:43:33.400
Especially I felt this when I made any attempt to propitiate him. No Ruth met my Ruth. He experienced no suffering from estrangement, no yearning after reconciliation, and though more than once my fast falling tears blistered the page over which we both bent, they produced no more effect on him than if his heart had been really a matter of stone or metal.

18:43:34.280 --> 18:43:51.240
To his sisters meantime he was somewhat kinder than usual, as if afraid that mere coldness would not sufficiently convince me how completely I was banished and banned. He added the force of contrast. And this I am sure he did not by malice but on principle.

18:43:52.140 --> 18:44:16.420
The night before he left home, happening to see him walking in the garden about sunset, and remembering, as I looked at him, that this man, alienated as he now was, had once saved my life and that we were near relations, I was moved to make a last attempt to regain his friendship. I went out and approached him as he stood leaning over the little gate. I spoke to the point at once.

18:44:17.440 --> 18:44:22.480
St. John, I am unhappy because you are still angry with me. Let us be friends.

18:44:23.700 --> 18:44:35.580
I hope we are friends, was the unmoved reply while he still watched the rising of the moon, which he had been contemplating as I approached. No, St. John, we are not friends as we were. You know that.

18:44:36.460 --> 18:44:41.560
Are we not? That is wrong. For my part I wish you no ill and all good.

18:44:42.360 --> 18:44:56.880
I believe you, St. John, for I am sure you are incapable of wishing any one ill. But, as I am your kinswoman, I should desire somewhat more of affection than that sort of general philanthropy you extend to mere strangers.

18:44:57.580 --> 18:45:04.380
Of course, he said, your wish is reasonable, and I am far from regarding you as a stranger.

18:45:05.180 --> 18:45:20.540
This, spoken in a cool, tranquil tone, was mortifying and baffling enough. Had I attended to the suggestions of pride and ire, I should immediately have left him. But something worked within me more strongly than those feelings could.

18:45:20.540 --> 18:45:32.700
I deeply venerated my cousin's talent and principle. His friendship was of value to me. To lose it tried me severely. I would not so soon relinquish the attempt to reconquer it.

18:45:34.160 --> 18:45:41.380
Must we part in this way, St. John? And when you go to India, will you leave me so, without a kinder word than you have yet spoken?

18:45:42.160 --> 18:45:45.320
He now turned quite from the moon and faced me.

18:45:46.000 --> 18:45:50.980
When I go to India, Jane, will I leave you? What, do you not go to India?

18:45:52.100 --> 18:45:54.560
You said I could not unless I married you.

18:45:55.720 --> 18:45:58.580
And you will not marry me? You adhere to that resolution?

18:46:00.360 --> 18:46:13.920
Reader, do you know, as I do, what terror those cold people can put into the ice of their questions? How much of the fall of the avalanche is in their anger? Of the breaking up of the frozen sea and their displeasure?

18:46:14.980 --> 18:46:19.000
No, St. John, I will not marry you. I adhere to my resolution.

18:46:20.160 --> 18:46:24.880
The avalanche had shaken and slid a little forward, but it did not yet crash down.

18:46:25.820 --> 18:46:29.920
Once more, why this refusal? He asked.

18:46:31.020 --> 18:46:40.820
Formerly, I answered, because you did not love me. Now, I replied, because you almost hate me. If I were to marry you, you would kill me. You are killing me now.

18:46:42.500 --> 18:46:45.400
His lips and cheeks turned white, quite white.

18:46:46.180 --> 18:46:49.180
I should kill you? I am killing you?

18:46:49.180 --> 18:47:07.980
Your words are such as ought not to be used, violent, unfeminine, and untrue. They betray an unfortunate state of mind. They merit severe reproof. They would seem inexcusable, but that it is the duty of man to forgive his fellow, even until seventy and seven times.

18:47:08.820 --> 18:47:21.220
I had finished the business now. While earnestly wishing to erase from his mind the trace of my former offence, I had stamped on that tenacious surface another and far deeper impression. I had burnt it in.

18:47:22.380 --> 18:47:30.220
Now you will indeed hate me, I said. It is useless to attempt to conciliate you. I see I have made an eternal enemy of you.

18:47:31.140 --> 18:47:43.560
A fresh wrong did these words inflict, the worst because they touched on the truth. That bloodless lip quivered to a temporary spasm. I knew the steely ire I had whetted. I was heart-rung.

18:47:44.580 --> 18:47:52.380
You utterly misinterpret my words, I said at once, seizing his hand. I have no intention to grieve or pain you. Indeed, I have not.

18:47:53.460 --> 18:47:58.480
Most bitterly he smiled. Most decidedly, he withdrew his hand from mine.

18:47:59.400 --> 18:48:07.120
And now you recall your promise, and will not go to India at all, I presume, said he after a considerable pause.

18:48:07.740 --> 18:48:10.940
Yes, I will, as your assistant, I answered.

18:48:11.880 --> 18:48:19.380
A very long silence succeeded. What struggle there was in him between nature and grace in this interval I cannot tell.

18:48:19.960 --> 18:48:28.060
Only singular gleams scintillated in his eyes, and strange shadows passed over his face. He spoke at last.

18:48:29.220 --> 18:48:38.400
I before proved to you the absurdity of a single woman of your age proposing to accompany abroad a single man of mine.

18:48:39.100 --> 18:48:48.800
I proved it to you in such terms as I should have thought would have prevented your ever again alluding to the plan. That you have done so I regret for your sake.

18:48:49.540 --> 18:48:54.900
I interrupted him. Anything like a tangible reproach gave me courage at once.

18:48:55.700 --> 18:49:01.560
Keep to common sense, St. John, you are verging on nonsense. You pretend to be shocked by what I have said.

18:49:01.840 --> 18:49:09.720
You are not really shocked, for with your superior mind you cannot be either so dull or so conceited as to misunderstand my meaning.

18:49:10.400 --> 18:49:15.180
I say again, I will be your curate, if you like, but never your wife.

18:49:16.100 --> 18:49:24.260
Again he turned lividly pale, but as before controlled his passion perfectly. He answered emphatically but calmly.

18:49:25.540 --> 18:49:32.580
A female curate who is not my wife would never suit me. With me then it seems you cannot go.

18:49:32.980 --> 18:49:40.420
But if you are sincere in your offer, I will while in town speak to a married missionary whose wife needs a coadjutor.

18:49:40.420 --> 18:49:51.640
Your own fortune will make you independent of the society's aid, and thus you may still be spared the dishonor of breaking your promise and deserting the band you engage to join.

18:49:52.380 --> 18:50:05.480
Now, I never had, as the reader knows, either given any formal promise or entered into any engagement, and this language was all much too hard and much too despotic for the occasion.

18:50:05.480 --> 18:50:18.020
I replied, There is no dishonor, no breach of promise, no desertion in the case. I am not under the slightest obligation to go to India, especially with strangers.

18:50:18.720 --> 18:50:25.500
With you I would have ventured much, because I admire, confide in, and as a sister I love you.

18:50:25.840 --> 18:50:31.660
But I am convinced that, go when and with whom I would, I should not live long in that climate.

18:50:32.900 --> 18:50:36.860
Ah, you are afraid of yourself, he said, curling his lip.

18:50:37.940 --> 18:50:46.900
I am. God did not give me my life to throw away, and to do, as you would wish me, would, I begin to think, be almost equivalent to committing suicide.

18:50:48.240 --> 18:50:56.860
Moreover, before I definitely resolve on quitting England, I will know for certain whether I cannot be of greater use by remaining in it than by leaving it.

18:50:57.260 --> 18:50:58.580
What do you mean?

18:50:59.480 --> 18:51:09.480
It would be fruitless to attempt to explain, but there is a point on which I have long endured painful doubt, and I can go nowhere till by some means that doubt is removed.

18:51:10.680 --> 18:51:24.480
I know where your heart turns, and to what it clings. The interest you cherish is lawless and unconsecrated. Long since you ought to have crushed it. Now you should blush to allude to it. You think of Mr. Rochester?

18:51:25.220 --> 18:51:28.520
It was true. I confessed it by silence.

18:51:29.420 --> 18:51:31.900
Are you going to seek Mr. Rochester?

18:51:32.700 --> 18:51:35.340
I must find out what has become of him.

18:51:36.540 --> 18:51:47.600
It remains for me then, he said, to remember you in my prayers, and to entreat God for you, in all earnestness, that you may not indeed become a castaway.

18:51:47.600 --> 18:51:55.840
I had thought I recognized in you one of the Chosen, but God sees not as man sees. His will be done.

18:51:57.320 --> 18:52:03.240
He opened the gate, passed through it, and strayed away down the Glen. He was soon out of sight.

18:52:04.500 --> 18:52:08.880
On re-entering the parlour, I found Diana standing at the window, looking very thoughtful.

18:52:10.240 --> 18:52:16.160
Diana was a great deal taller than I. She put her hand on my shoulder, and stooping, examined my face.

18:52:17.140 --> 18:52:23.660
Jane, she said, you are always agitated and pale now. I am sure there is something the matter.

18:52:24.540 --> 18:52:27.260
Tell me what business St. John and you have on hand.

18:52:28.000 --> 18:52:39.220
I have watched you this half hour from the window. You must forgive my being such a spy, but for a long time I have fancied I hardly know what. St. John is a strange being.

18:52:40.220 --> 18:52:45.100
She paused. I did not speak. Soon she resumed.

18:52:46.320 --> 18:52:56.820
That brother of mine cherishes peculiar views of some sort respecting you, I am sure. He has long distinguished you by a notice and interest he never showed to any one else.

18:52:57.400 --> 18:53:01.040
To what end? I wish he loved you, does he, Jane?

18:53:02.360 --> 18:53:07.120
I put her cool hand to my hot forehead. No die, not one wit.

18:53:08.480 --> 18:53:15.400
Then why does he follow you so with his eyes, and get you so frequently alone with him, and keep you so continually at his side?

18:53:16.160 --> 18:53:19.360
Mary and I had both concluded he wished you to marry him.

18:53:20.340 --> 18:53:23.760
He does. He has asked me to be his wife.

18:53:24.460 --> 18:53:32.520
Diana clapped her hands. That is just what we hoped and thought. And you will marry him, Jane, won't you? And then he will stay in England.

18:53:33.880 --> 18:53:41.300
Far from that, Diana. His sole idea in proposing to me is to procure a fitting fellow-labourer in his Indian toils.

18:53:42.480 --> 18:53:45.100
What? He wishes you to go to India?

18:53:46.400 --> 18:53:46.960
Yes.

18:53:48.160 --> 18:53:56.140
Madness, she exclaimed. You would not live three months there, I am certain. You shall never go. You have not consented, have you, Jane?

18:53:57.020 --> 18:53:59.000
I have refused to marry him.

18:54:00.160 --> 18:54:03.640
And have consequently displeased him, she suggested.

18:54:05.060 --> 18:54:10.640
Deeply. He will never forgive me, I fear. Yet I offered to accompany him as his sister.

18:54:11.660 --> 18:54:21.500
It was frantic folly to do so, Jane. Think of the task you undertook, one of incessant fatigue, where fatigue kills even the strong. And you are weak.

18:54:22.140 --> 18:54:33.980
St. John, you know him, would urge you to impossibilities. With him there would be no permission to rest during the hot hours, and unfortunately I have noticed, whatever he exacts, you force yourself to perform.

18:54:34.540 --> 18:54:37.620
I am astonished you found courage to refuse his hand.

18:54:38.260 --> 18:54:40.160
You do not love him, then, Jane?

18:54:40.840 --> 18:54:42.180
Not as a husband.

18:54:43.280 --> 18:54:44.700
Yet he is a handsome fellow.

18:54:45.820 --> 18:54:49.180
And I am so plain, you see, Di. We should never suit.

18:54:50.800 --> 18:54:57.920
Plain? You? Not at all. You are much too pretty, as well as too good, to be grilled alive in Calcutta.

18:54:58.640 --> 18:55:02.900
And again she earnestly conjured me to give up all thoughts of going out with her brother.

18:55:03.800 --> 18:55:13.120
I must indeed, I said, for when just now I repeated the offer of serving him for a deacon, he expressed himself shocked at my want of decency.

18:55:13.780 --> 18:55:25.700
He seemed to think I had committed an impropriety in proposing to accompany him unmarried, as if I had not from the first hoped to find in him a brother, and habitually regarded him as such.

18:55:26.680 --> 18:55:29.240
What makes you say he does not love you, Jane?

18:55:30.080 --> 18:55:38.120
You should hear himself on the subject. He has again and again explained that it is not himself, but his office he wishes to mate.

18:55:38.920 --> 18:55:44.100
He has told me I am formed for labor, not for love, which is true, no doubt.

18:55:44.640 --> 18:55:49.820
But, in my opinion, if I am not formed for love, it follows that I am not formed for marriage.

18:55:50.940 --> 18:55:56.520
Would it not be strange, Di, to be chained for life to a man who regarded one but as a useful tool?

18:55:58.140 --> 18:56:01.300
Insupportable, unnatural, out of the question.

18:56:02.740 --> 18:56:16.620
And then, I continued, though I have only sisterly affection for him now, yet, if forced to be his wife, I can imagine the possibility of conceiving an inevitable strange, torturing kind of love for him,

18:56:16.620 --> 18:56:22.820
because he is so talented, and there is often a certain heroic grandeur in his look, manner, and conversation.

18:56:23.980 --> 18:56:27.240
In that case, my lot would become unspeakably wretched.

18:56:27.940 --> 18:56:36.380
He would not want me to love him, and if I showed the feeling, he would make me sensible that it was a superfluity unrequired by him, unbecoming in me.

18:56:36.760 --> 18:56:37.780
I know he would.

18:56:38.520 --> 18:56:42.140
And yet St. John is a good man, said Diana.

18:56:42.840 --> 18:56:52.840
He is a good and a great man, but he forgets pitilessly the feelings and claims of little people in pursuing his own large views.

18:56:53.660 --> 18:57:00.600
It is better, therefore, for the insignificant to keep out of his way, lest in his progress he should trample them down.

18:57:01.440 --> 18:57:04.100
Here he comes. I will leave you, Diana.

18:57:04.420 --> 18:57:07.360
And I hastened upstairs as I saw him entering the garden.

18:57:08.120 --> 18:57:10.360
But I was forced to meet him again at supper.

18:57:10.920 --> 18:57:14.040
During that meal he appeared just as composed as usual.

18:57:14.740 --> 18:57:20.800
I had thought he would hardly speak to me, and I was certain he had given up the pursuit of his matrimonial scheme.

18:57:21.760 --> 18:57:24.480
The sequel showed I was mistaken on both points.

18:57:25.220 --> 18:57:32.620
He addressed me precisely in his ordinary manner, or what had, of late, been his ordinary manner, one scrupulously polite.

18:57:33.220 --> 18:57:42.440
No doubt he had invoked the help of the Holy Spirit to subdue the anger I had roused in him, and now believed he had forgiven me once more.

18:57:43.140 --> 18:57:47.920
For the evening reading before prayers, he selected the twenty-first chapter of Revelation.

18:57:48.840 --> 18:57:54.160
It was at all times pleasant to listen, while from his lips fell the words of the Bible.

18:57:54.980 --> 18:57:58.280
Never did his fine voice sound at once so sweet and full.

18:57:58.280 --> 18:58:05.380
Never did his manner become so impressive in its noble simplicity as when he delivered the Oracles of God.

18:58:06.100 --> 18:58:13.540
And to-night that voice took a more solemn tone, that manner a more thrilling meaning, as he sat in the midst of his household circle,

18:58:14.400 --> 18:58:21.160
the May moon shining in through the uncurtain window, and rendering almost unnecessary the light of the candle on the table.

18:58:21.900 --> 18:58:30.180
As he sat there, bending over the great old Bible, and described from its page the vision of the new heaven and the new earth,

18:58:30.960 --> 18:58:39.680
told how God would come to dwell with men, how He would wipe away all tears from their eyes, and promised that there should be no more death,

18:58:40.280 --> 18:58:46.040
neither sorrow, nor crying, nor any more pain, because the former things were passed away.

18:58:46.820 --> 18:58:55.640
The succeeding words thrilled me strangely as he spoke them, especially as I felt by the slight indescribable alteration in sound,

18:58:56.660 --> 18:58:59.320
that in uttering them his eye had turned on me.

18:58:59.320 --> 18:59:10.720
He that overcometh shall inherit all things, and I will be his God, and he shall be my son, but, was slowly distinctly read,

18:59:11.520 --> 18:59:21.780
the fearful, the unbelieving, etc., shall have their part in the lake which burneth with fire and brimstone, which is the second death.

18:59:23.420 --> 18:59:26.380
Henceforward I knew what fate St. John feared for me.

18:59:27.540 --> 18:59:35.660
A calm, subdued triumph, blent with a longing earnestness, marked his enunciation of the last glorious verses of that chapter.

18:59:36.480 --> 18:59:44.420
The reader believed his name was already written in the Lamb's Book of Life, and he yearned after the hour which should admit him to the city

18:59:44.420 --> 18:59:50.940
to which the kings of the earth bring their glory and honor, which has no need of sun or moon to shine in it,

18:59:51.100 --> 18:59:55.340
because the glory of God lightens it, and the Lamb is the light thereof.

18:59:56.180 --> 19:00:01.680
In the prayer following the chapter, all his energy gathered, all his stern zeal awoke.

19:00:02.080 --> 19:00:06.840
He was in deep earnest, wrestling with God and resolved on a conquest.

19:00:06.840 --> 19:00:11.760
He supplicated strength for the weak-hearted, guidance for wanderers from the fold,

19:00:11.840 --> 19:00:19.900
a return, even at the eleventh hour, for those whom the temptations of the world and the flesh were luring from the narrow path.

19:00:20.520 --> 19:00:25.000
He asked, he urged, he claimed the boon of a brand snatched from the burning.

19:00:26.080 --> 19:00:28.100
Earnestness is ever deeply solemn.

19:00:29.020 --> 19:00:32.120
First, as I listened to that prayer, I wondered at his.

19:00:32.900 --> 19:00:37.980
Then, when it continued in rows, I was touched by it, and at last awed.

19:00:38.600 --> 19:00:42.300
He felt the greatness and goodness of his purpose so sincerely.

19:00:43.120 --> 19:00:46.480
Others who heard him plead for it could not but feel it too.

19:00:47.480 --> 19:00:49.720
The prayer over, we took leave of him.

19:00:50.100 --> 19:00:52.760
He was to go at a very early hour in the morning.

19:00:53.680 --> 19:00:59.640
Diana and Mary, having kissed him, left the room, in compliance, I think, with a whispered hint from him.

19:00:59.640 --> 19:01:03.220
I tendered my hand and wished him a pleasant journey.

19:01:04.520 --> 19:01:09.120
Thank you, Jane. As I said, I shall return from Cambridge in a fortnight.

19:01:09.720 --> 19:01:11.840
That space, then, is left you for reflection.

19:01:12.980 --> 19:01:17.560
If I listen to human pride, I should say no more to you of marriage with me.

19:01:17.880 --> 19:01:24.520
But I listen to my duty, and keep steadily in view my first aim, to do all things to the glory of God.

19:01:25.420 --> 19:01:28.800
My master was long-suffering, so will I be.

19:01:28.800 --> 19:01:32.420
I cannot give you up to perdition as a vessel of wrath.

19:01:33.460 --> 19:01:36.040
Repent, resolve while there is yet time.

19:01:36.780 --> 19:01:39.420
Remember, we are bid to work while it is day.

19:01:40.120 --> 19:01:43.020
Warned that the night cometh when no man shall work.

19:01:43.920 --> 19:01:47.920
Remember the fate of Dives, who had his good things in this life.

19:01:48.500 --> 19:01:52.900
God give you strength to choose that better part which shall not be taken from you.

19:01:53.640 --> 19:01:56.840
He laid his hand on my head as he uttered the last words.

19:01:56.840 --> 19:01:59.700
He had spoken earnestly, mildly.

19:02:00.140 --> 19:02:03.560
His look was not, indeed, that of a lover beholding his mistress.

19:02:04.220 --> 19:02:08.020
But it was that of a pastor recalling his wandering sheep,

19:02:08.400 --> 19:02:12.020
or better, of a guardian angel watching the soul for which he is responsible.

19:02:13.480 --> 19:02:16.720
All men of talent, whether they be men of feeling or not,

19:02:17.140 --> 19:02:20.220
whether they be zealots, or aspirants, or despots,

19:02:20.800 --> 19:02:24.560
provided only they be sincere, have their sublime moments,

19:02:24.560 --> 19:02:26.760
when they subdue and rule.

19:02:27.560 --> 19:02:31.840
I felt veneration for St. John, veneration so strong

19:02:31.840 --> 19:02:35.580
that its impetus thrust me at once to the point I had so long shunned.

19:02:36.560 --> 19:02:38.840
I was tempted to see struggling with him,

19:02:39.320 --> 19:02:43.020
to rush down the torrent of his will into the gulf of his existence,

19:02:43.680 --> 19:02:45.420
and there lose my own.

19:02:46.420 --> 19:02:49.300
I was almost as hard beset by him now

19:02:49.300 --> 19:02:52.620
as I had been once before in a different way by another.

19:02:53.280 --> 19:02:55.740
I was a fool both times.

19:02:56.420 --> 19:02:59.060
To have yielded then would have been an error of principle.

19:02:59.800 --> 19:03:02.720
To have yielded now would have been an error of judgment.

19:03:03.760 --> 19:03:06.680
So I think at this hour, when I look back to the crisis

19:03:06.680 --> 19:03:08.460
through the quiet medium of time,

19:03:09.180 --> 19:03:11.580
I was unconscious of folly at the instant.

19:03:12.880 --> 19:03:15.520
I stood motionless under my hierophant's touch.

19:03:16.120 --> 19:03:19.020
My refusals were forgotten, my fears overcome,

19:03:19.660 --> 19:03:21.260
my wrestlings paralyzed.

19:03:22.620 --> 19:03:25.260
Everything that was possible, i.e. my marriage with St. John,

19:03:25.620 --> 19:03:27.360
was fast becoming the possible.

19:03:28.360 --> 19:03:30.860
All was changing utterly with a sudden sweep.

19:03:31.580 --> 19:03:34.620
Religion called, angels beckoned, God commanded,

19:03:34.800 --> 19:03:36.900
life rolled together like a scroll,

19:03:37.740 --> 19:03:40.520
death's gates opening, showed eternity beyond.

19:03:41.420 --> 19:03:43.960
It seemed that for safety and bliss there,

19:03:44.540 --> 19:03:46.780
all here might be sacrificed in a second.

19:03:47.480 --> 19:03:49.720
The dim room was full of visions.

19:03:49.720 --> 19:03:53.260
Could you decide now? asked the missionary.

19:03:54.060 --> 19:03:56.400
The inquiry was put in gentle tones.

19:03:56.760 --> 19:03:58.520
He drew me to him gently.

19:03:59.300 --> 19:04:03.160
Oh, that gentleness, how far more potent is it than force.

19:04:04.040 --> 19:04:06.020
I could resist St. John's wrath.

19:04:06.840 --> 19:04:09.320
I grew pliant as a reed under his kindness.

19:04:10.360 --> 19:04:12.860
Yet I knew all the time, if I yielded now,

19:04:13.360 --> 19:04:17.240
I should not the less be made to repent some day of my former rebellion.

19:04:18.200 --> 19:04:19.700
His nature was not changed,

19:04:19.720 --> 19:04:21.280
by one hour of solemn prayer.

19:04:21.840 --> 19:04:23.160
It was only elevated.

19:04:24.580 --> 19:04:27.700
I could decide if I were but certain, I answered,

19:04:28.240 --> 19:04:32.040
were I but convinced that it is God's will I should marry you.

19:04:32.300 --> 19:04:35.500
I could vow to marry you here and now, come afterwards what would.

19:04:36.700 --> 19:04:39.840
My prayers are heard, ejaculated St. John.

19:04:40.280 --> 19:04:43.780
He pressed his hand firmer on my head, as if he claimed me.

19:04:44.060 --> 19:04:48.700
He surrounded me with his arm, almost as if he loved me.

19:04:48.700 --> 19:04:51.540
I say almost, I knew the difference,

19:04:52.080 --> 19:04:54.460
for I had felt what it was to be loved.

19:04:55.280 --> 19:04:58.400
But, like him, I had now put love out of the question,

19:04:58.540 --> 19:04:59.660
and thought only of duty.

19:05:00.840 --> 19:05:03.420
I contended with my inward dimness of vision,

19:05:04.080 --> 19:05:05.900
before which clouds yet rolled.

19:05:06.780 --> 19:05:12.800
I sincerely, deeply, fervently longed to do what was right, and only that.

19:05:14.160 --> 19:05:17.320
Show me, show me the path, I entreated of heaven.

19:05:17.320 --> 19:05:20.240
I was excited more than I had ever been,

19:05:20.700 --> 19:05:24.500
and whether what followed was the effect of excitement the reader shall judge.

19:05:25.500 --> 19:05:27.060
All the house was still,

19:05:27.780 --> 19:05:31.940
for I believe all, except St. John and myself, were now retired to rest.

19:05:32.780 --> 19:05:34.580
The one candle was dying out.

19:05:35.460 --> 19:05:37.380
The room was full of moonlight.

19:05:38.240 --> 19:05:40.060
My heart beat fast and thick.

19:05:40.640 --> 19:05:41.880
I heard its throb.

19:05:42.860 --> 19:05:46.920
Suddenly it stood still to an inexpressible feeling that thrilled it through,

19:05:47.320 --> 19:05:49.580
and passed at once to my head and extremities.

19:05:50.860 --> 19:05:53.160
The feeling was not like an electric shock,

19:05:53.840 --> 19:05:56.960
but it was quite as sharp, as strange, as startling.

19:05:57.620 --> 19:06:01.260
It acted on my senses, as if their utmost activity,

19:06:01.560 --> 19:06:03.400
hitherto had been but torpor,

19:06:04.300 --> 19:06:07.060
from which they were now summoned and forced to wake.

19:06:07.700 --> 19:06:09.180
They rose expectant.

19:06:09.520 --> 19:06:12.720
Eye and ear waited, while the flesh quivered on my bones.

19:06:14.340 --> 19:06:16.680
What have you heard, what do you see?

19:06:17.100 --> 19:06:17.840
asked St. John.

19:06:18.620 --> 19:06:21.960
I saw nothing, but I heard a voice somewhere cry.

19:06:24.640 --> 19:06:26.960
Jane, Jane, Jane.

19:06:27.760 --> 19:06:28.660
Nothing more.

19:06:30.040 --> 19:06:32.220
Oh God, what is it? I gasped.

19:06:33.080 --> 19:06:34.900
I might have said, where is it?

19:06:35.040 --> 19:06:36.940
For it did not seem in the room,

19:06:37.600 --> 19:06:40.000
nor in the house, nor in the garden.

19:06:40.000 --> 19:06:44.300
It did not come out of the air, nor from under the earth, nor from overhead.

19:06:45.200 --> 19:06:49.600
I had heard it, where or whence, forever impossible to know.

19:06:50.660 --> 19:06:52.720
And it was the voice of a human being,

19:06:53.020 --> 19:06:55.320
a known, loved, well-remembered voice,

19:06:55.820 --> 19:06:58.480
that of Edward Fairfax, Rochester.

19:06:59.220 --> 19:07:03.000
And it spoke in pain and woe wildly, eerily, urgently.

19:07:04.000 --> 19:07:07.860
I am coming, I cried. Wait for me. Oh, I will come.

19:07:07.860 --> 19:07:10.700
I flew to the door and looked into the passage.

19:07:10.780 --> 19:07:13.200
It was dark. I ran out into the garden.

19:07:13.560 --> 19:07:14.400
It was void.

19:07:15.180 --> 19:07:17.240
Where are you? I exclaimed.

19:07:18.100 --> 19:07:21.360
The hills beyond Marsh Glen sent the answer faintly back.

19:07:22.200 --> 19:07:23.300
Where are you?

19:07:24.000 --> 19:07:24.800
I listened.

19:07:25.760 --> 19:07:27.920
The wind sighed low in the firs.

19:07:28.340 --> 19:07:30.940
All was moorland loneliness and midnight hush.

19:07:32.320 --> 19:07:36.360
Down superstition I commented as that spectre rose up black,

19:07:36.360 --> 19:07:38.900
by the black yew at the gate.

19:07:39.560 --> 19:07:42.600
This is not thy deception, not thy witchcraft.

19:07:43.020 --> 19:07:44.340
It is the work of nature.

19:07:44.860 --> 19:07:48.780
She was aroused and did no miracle but her best.

19:07:49.720 --> 19:07:53.640
I broke from St. John, who had followed, and would have detained me.

19:07:54.160 --> 19:07:56.540
It was my time to assume ascendancy.

19:07:57.040 --> 19:07:59.220
My powers were in play and in force.

19:07:59.680 --> 19:08:02.200
I told him to forbear question or remark.

19:08:02.520 --> 19:08:04.220
I desired him to leave me.

19:08:04.220 --> 19:08:06.380
I must and would be alone.

19:08:07.040 --> 19:08:08.340
He obeyed at once.

19:08:08.960 --> 19:08:13.000
Where there is energy to command well enough, obedience never fails.

19:08:13.540 --> 19:08:19.940
I mounted to my chamber, locked myself in, fell on my knees, and prayed in my way.

19:08:20.200 --> 19:08:24.060
A different way to St. John's, but effective in its own fashion.

19:08:24.740 --> 19:08:30.920
I seemed to penetrate very near a mighty spirit, and my soul rushed out in gratitude at his feet.

19:08:30.920 --> 19:08:39.600
I rose from the thanksgiving, took a resolve, and lay down, unscared, enlightened, eager but for the daylight.

19:09:01.340 --> 19:09:03.020
CHAPTER XXXVI.

19:09:03.1000 --> 19:09:04.880
The daylight came.

19:09:05.480 --> 19:09:06.640
I rose at dawn.

19:09:07.240 --> 19:09:11.060
I busied myself for an hour or two with arranging my things in my

19:09:11.060 --> 19:09:14.660
chamber, drawers, and wardrobe, in the order wherein I should wish

19:09:14.660 --> 19:09:16.380
to leave them during a brief absence.

19:09:17.280 --> 19:09:19.580
Meantime, I heard St. John quit his room.

19:09:20.180 --> 19:09:21.460
He stopped at my door.

19:09:21.880 --> 19:09:23.180
I feared he would knock.

19:09:23.820 --> 19:09:26.500
No, but a slip of paper was passed under the door.

19:09:27.020 --> 19:09:27.860
I took it up.

19:09:28.020 --> 19:09:29.280
It bore these words.

19:09:29.860 --> 19:09:32.360
You left me too suddenly last night.

19:09:32.880 --> 19:09:36.260
Had you stayed but a little longer, you would have laid your

19:09:36.260 --> 19:09:39.500
hand on the Christian's cross and the angel's crown.

19:09:40.080 --> 19:09:43.140
I shall expect your clear decision when I return this day

19:09:43.140 --> 19:09:43.680
fortnight.

19:09:44.600 --> 19:09:48.020
Meantime, watch and pray that you enter not into temptation.

19:09:48.800 --> 19:09:52.540
The spirit I trust is willing, but the flesh I see is weak.

19:09:53.260 --> 19:09:54.900
I shall pray for you hourly.

19:09:55.520 --> 19:09:56.720
Yours, St. John.

19:09:57.780 --> 19:10:01.800
My spirit, I answered mentally, is willing to do what is right.

19:10:02.300 --> 19:10:05.260
And my flesh, I hope, is strong enough to accomplish the will

19:10:05.260 --> 19:10:08.920
of heaven, when once that will is distinctly known to me.

19:10:09.540 --> 19:10:13.160
At any rate, it shall be strong enough to search, inquire, to

19:10:13.160 --> 19:10:16.780
grope an outlet from this crowd of doubt, and find the open day

19:10:16.780 --> 19:10:17.580
of certainty.

19:10:18.720 --> 19:10:22.520
It was the first of June, yet the morning was overcast and

19:10:22.520 --> 19:10:22.740
chilly.

19:10:23.280 --> 19:10:25.080
Rain beat fast on my casement.

19:10:25.680 --> 19:10:28.520
I heard the front door open and St. John pass out.

19:10:29.220 --> 19:10:32.040
Looking through the window, I saw him traverse the garden.

19:10:32.660 --> 19:10:35.560
He took the way over the Misty Moors in the direction of

19:10:35.560 --> 19:10:36.100
Whitcross.

19:10:36.660 --> 19:10:37.880
There he would meet the coach.

19:10:38.660 --> 19:10:41.680
In a few more hours, I shall succeed you in that track,

19:10:41.880 --> 19:10:43.080
cousin, I thought.

19:10:43.560 --> 19:10:45.640
I, too, have a coach to meet at Whitcross.

19:10:46.140 --> 19:10:49.740
I, too, have some to see and ask after in England before I

19:10:49.740 --> 19:10:50.580
depart for ever.

19:10:51.740 --> 19:10:54.080
It wanted yet two hours of breakfast time.

19:10:54.580 --> 19:10:57.660
I filled the interval in walking softly about my room and

19:10:57.660 --> 19:11:00.720
pondering the visitation which had given my plans their

19:11:00.720 --> 19:11:01.400
present bent.

19:11:02.140 --> 19:11:06.360
I recalled that inward sensation I had experienced, for I

19:11:06.360 --> 19:11:09.980
could recall it with all its unspeakable strangeness.

19:11:10.440 --> 19:11:12.320
I recalled the voice I had heard.

19:11:12.700 --> 19:11:16.380
Again I questioned whence it came, as vainly as before.

19:11:16.960 --> 19:11:20.320
It seemed in me, not in the external world.

19:11:21.020 --> 19:11:24.580
I asked, was it a mere nervous impression, a delusion?

19:11:25.100 --> 19:11:27.360
I could not conceive or believe.

19:11:27.900 --> 19:11:29.980
It was more like an inspiration.

19:11:30.960 --> 19:11:33.820
The wondrous shock of feeling had come like the earthquake

19:11:33.820 --> 19:11:37.040
which shook the foundations of Paul and Silas's prison.

19:11:37.980 --> 19:11:40.400
It had opened the doors of the soul's cell

19:11:40.400 --> 19:11:42.020
and loosed its bands.

19:11:42.860 --> 19:11:45.500
It had wakened it out of its sleep, once it sprang

19:11:45.500 --> 19:11:47.860
trembling, listening, aghast.

19:11:48.460 --> 19:11:52.860
Then vibrated thrice a cry on my startled ear, and in my

19:11:52.860 --> 19:11:56.940
quaking heart, and through my spirit, which neither feared

19:11:56.940 --> 19:12:01.240
nor shook, but exalted as if in joy over the success of one

19:12:01.240 --> 19:12:04.980
effort it had been privileged to make, independent of the

19:12:04.980 --> 19:12:05.960
cumbrous body.

19:12:06.660 --> 19:12:10.700
Ere many days, I said, as I terminated my musings, I will know

19:12:10.700 --> 19:12:13.920
something of him whose voice seemed last night to summon me.

19:12:14.520 --> 19:12:16.220
Letters have proved of no avail.

19:12:16.820 --> 19:12:18.940
Personal inquiry shall replace them.

19:12:19.820 --> 19:12:23.520
At breakfast I announced to Diana and Mary that I was going a

19:12:23.520 --> 19:12:26.680
journey, and should be absent at least for days.

19:12:27.560 --> 19:12:28.500
Alone, Jane?

19:12:28.680 --> 19:12:29.280
They asked.

19:12:29.940 --> 19:12:33.700
Yes, it was to see or hear news of a friend about whom I had

19:12:33.700 --> 19:12:35.740
for some time been uneasy.

19:12:36.800 --> 19:12:40.560
They might have said, as I have no doubt they thought, that

19:12:40.560 --> 19:12:43.400
they had believed me to be without any friends save them,

19:12:43.800 --> 19:12:45.780
for indeed I had often said so.

19:12:46.100 --> 19:12:49.440
But with their true natural delicacy they abstained from

19:12:49.440 --> 19:12:52.900
comment, except that Diana asked me if I was sure I was

19:12:52.900 --> 19:12:53.880
well enough to travel.

19:12:54.280 --> 19:12:56.300
I looked very pale, she observed.

19:12:56.860 --> 19:13:00.540
I replied that nothing ailed me save anxiety of mind, which I

19:13:00.540 --> 19:13:01.680
hoped soon to alleviate.

19:13:02.680 --> 19:13:05.780
It was easy to make my further arrangements, for I was

19:13:05.780 --> 19:13:08.060
troubled with no inquiries, no surmises.

19:13:08.880 --> 19:13:11.520
Having once explained to them that I could not now be

19:13:11.520 --> 19:13:15.500
explicit about my plans, they kindly and wisely acquiesced in

19:13:15.500 --> 19:13:17.300
the silence with which I pursued them.

19:13:17.800 --> 19:13:21.060
According to me the privilege of free action I should, under

19:13:21.060 --> 19:13:23.260
similar circumstances, have accorded them.

19:13:23.540 --> 19:13:27.840
I left Morehouse at three o'clock p.m., and soon after four I

19:13:27.840 --> 19:13:31.020
stood at the foot of the signpost of Whitcross, waiting the

19:13:31.020 --> 19:13:33.480
arrival of the coach which was to take me to distant

19:13:33.480 --> 19:13:34.160
Thornfield.

19:13:35.120 --> 19:13:39.160
Amidst the silence of those solitary roads and desert hills I

19:13:39.160 --> 19:13:41.360
heard it approach from a great distance.

19:13:41.1000 --> 19:13:45.680
It was the same vehicle whence, a year ago, I had alighted one

19:13:45.680 --> 19:13:47.460
summer evening on this very spot.

19:13:47.460 --> 19:13:50.600
How desolate, how hopeless, and objectless!

19:13:51.220 --> 19:13:52.660
It stopped as I beckoned.

19:13:53.220 --> 19:13:56.900
I entered, not now obliged to part with my whole fortune as the

19:13:56.900 --> 19:13:58.200
price of its accommodation.

19:13:59.240 --> 19:14:02.360
Once more, on the road to Thornfield, I felt like the

19:14:02.360 --> 19:14:03.960
messenger pigeon flying home.

19:14:04.940 --> 19:14:07.480
It was a journey of six and thirty hours.

19:14:07.840 --> 19:14:12.040
I had set out from Whitcross on a Tuesday afternoon, and early on

19:14:12.040 --> 19:14:15.240
the succeeding Thursday morning the coach stopped to water the

19:14:15.240 --> 19:14:18.440
horses at a wayside inn, situated in the midst of scenery,

19:14:18.860 --> 19:14:22.580
whose green hedges and large fields, and low pastoral hills,

19:14:23.020 --> 19:14:26.380
how mild the feature and verdant of hue compared with the stern

19:14:26.380 --> 19:14:31.280
North Midland moors of Morton, met my eye like the liniments of a

19:14:31.280 --> 19:14:32.520
whence familiar face.

19:14:33.280 --> 19:14:35.440
Yes, I knew the character of this landscape.

19:14:35.720 --> 19:14:37.960
I was sure we were near my bourn.

19:14:38.680 --> 19:14:40.940
How far is Thornfield Hall from here?

19:14:41.140 --> 19:14:42.400
I asked of the ossler.

19:14:43.060 --> 19:14:45.400
Just two miles, ma'am, cross the fields.

19:14:46.280 --> 19:14:48.860
My journey is closed, I thought to myself.

19:14:49.300 --> 19:14:53.300
I got out of the coach, gave a box I had into the ossler's

19:14:53.300 --> 19:14:57.260
charge to be kept till I called for it, paid my fare, satisfied

19:14:57.260 --> 19:14:58.880
the coachman, and was going.

19:14:59.360 --> 19:15:03.160
The brightening day gleamed on the sign of the inn, and I read

19:15:03.160 --> 19:15:05.620
in gilt letters the Rochester Arms.

19:15:06.220 --> 19:15:07.300
My heart leapt up.

19:15:07.420 --> 19:15:09.720
I was already on my master's very lands.

19:15:10.140 --> 19:15:11.100
It fell again.

19:15:11.160 --> 19:15:12.200
The thought struck it.

19:15:12.960 --> 19:15:16.140
Your master himself may be beyond the British channel, for ought

19:15:16.140 --> 19:15:16.700
you know.

19:15:17.060 --> 19:15:21.180
And then, if he is at Thornfield Hall, towards which you hasten,

19:15:21.440 --> 19:15:23.080
who besides him is there?

19:15:23.420 --> 19:15:24.780
His lunatic wife.

19:15:24.1000 --> 19:15:26.840
And you have nothing to do with him.

19:15:27.140 --> 19:15:29.460
You dare not speak to him or seek his presence.

19:15:29.920 --> 19:15:31.300
You have lost your labor.

19:15:31.700 --> 19:15:34.120
You had better go no farther, urged the monitor.

19:15:34.620 --> 19:15:36.760
Ask information of the people at the inn.

19:15:37.060 --> 19:15:38.640
They can give you all you seek.

19:15:38.640 --> 19:15:40.760
They can solve your doubts at once.

19:15:41.140 --> 19:15:44.840
Go up to that man, and inquire if Mr. Rochester be at home.

19:15:45.720 --> 19:15:50.040
The suggestion was sensible, and yet I could not force myself to

19:15:50.040 --> 19:15:50.860
act on it.

19:15:51.260 --> 19:15:54.500
I so dreaded a reply that would crush me with despair.

19:15:55.280 --> 19:15:57.520
To prolong doubt was to prolong hope.

19:15:58.060 --> 19:16:01.440
I might yet once more see the hall under the ray of her star.

19:16:01.1000 --> 19:16:05.520
There was the stile before me, the very fields through which I

19:16:05.520 --> 19:16:10.220
hurried, blind, deaf, distracted, with a revengeful fury tracking

19:16:10.220 --> 19:16:13.440
and scourging me, on the morning I fled from Thornfield.

19:16:14.220 --> 19:16:17.680
ere I well knew what course I had resolved to take, I was in the

19:16:17.680 --> 19:16:18.380
midst of them.

19:16:18.780 --> 19:16:20.120
How fast I walked.

19:16:21.080 --> 19:16:22.580
How I ran sometimes.

19:16:23.100 --> 19:16:26.220
How I looked forward to catch the first view of the well-known

19:16:26.220 --> 19:16:26.620
woods.

19:16:27.180 --> 19:16:30.820
With what feelings I welcomed single trees I knew, and familiar

19:16:30.820 --> 19:16:33.020
glimpses of meadow and hill between them.

19:16:33.640 --> 19:16:35.580
At last the woods rose.

19:16:36.040 --> 19:16:37.720
The rookery clustered dark.

19:16:38.140 --> 19:16:40.220
A loud calling broke the morning stillness.

19:16:40.940 --> 19:16:42.720
Strange delight inspired me.

19:16:43.020 --> 19:16:44.100
On I hastened.

19:16:44.380 --> 19:16:47.600
Another field crossed, a lane threaded, and there were the

19:16:47.600 --> 19:16:52.300
courtyard walls, the back offices, the house itself.

19:16:52.800 --> 19:16:54.160
The rookery still hid.

19:16:55.020 --> 19:16:58.720
My first view of it shall be in front, I determined, where its

19:16:58.720 --> 19:17:02.540
bold battlements will strike the eye nobly at once, and where I can

19:17:02.540 --> 19:17:04.500
single out my master's very window.

19:17:05.120 --> 19:17:07.160
Perhaps he will be standing at it.

19:17:07.280 --> 19:17:08.480
He rises early.

19:17:09.020 --> 19:17:12.240
Perhaps he is now walking in the orchard, or on the pavement in

19:17:12.240 --> 19:17:12.500
front.

19:17:13.160 --> 19:17:15.220
Could I but see him but a moment?

19:17:15.840 --> 19:17:19.260
Surely in that case I should not be so mad as to rend to him?

19:17:19.760 --> 19:17:20.800
I cannot tell.

19:17:20.840 --> 19:17:21.740
I am not certain.

19:17:22.320 --> 19:17:24.380
And if I did, what then?

19:17:25.100 --> 19:17:27.360
God bless him, what then?

19:17:28.280 --> 19:17:31.1000
Who would be hurt by my once more tasting the life his glance can

19:17:31.1000 --> 19:17:32.440
give me?

19:17:32.780 --> 19:17:33.600
I rave.

19:17:33.760 --> 19:17:36.560
Perhaps at this moment he is watching the sunrise over the

19:17:36.560 --> 19:17:39.520
Pyrenees, or on the tideless sea of the south.

19:17:40.520 --> 19:17:44.240
I had coasted along the lower wall of the orchard, turned its

19:17:44.240 --> 19:17:44.700
angle.

19:17:45.100 --> 19:17:48.900
There was a gate just there, opening into the meadow, between

19:17:48.900 --> 19:17:51.580
two stone pillars crowned by stone balls.

19:17:52.540 --> 19:17:56.980
From behind one pillar, I could peep round quietly at the full

19:17:56.980 --> 19:17:57.980
front of the mansion.

19:17:58.680 --> 19:18:03.080
I advanced my head with precaution, desirous to ascertain if any

19:18:03.080 --> 19:18:05.360
bedroom window-blinds were yet drawn up.

19:18:06.120 --> 19:18:11.220
Battlements, windows, long front, all from the sheltered station

19:18:11.220 --> 19:18:12.420
were at my command.

19:18:13.560 --> 19:18:16.720
The crows sailing overhead perhaps watched me while I took

19:18:16.720 --> 19:18:17.380
this survey.

19:18:18.320 --> 19:18:19.640
I wonder what they thought.

19:18:20.360 --> 19:18:23.900
They must have considered I was very careful and timid at first,

19:18:24.320 --> 19:18:27.040
and that gradually I grew very bold and reckless.

19:18:27.680 --> 19:18:32.720
A peep, and then a long stare, and then a departure from my

19:18:32.720 --> 19:18:37.700
niche, and a straying out into the meadow, and a sudden stop full

19:18:37.700 --> 19:18:42.100
in front of the great mansion, and a protracted, hearty gaze

19:18:42.100 --> 19:18:42.840
towards it.

19:18:44.120 --> 19:18:47.220
What affectation of diffidence was this at first?

19:18:47.320 --> 19:18:48.460
They might have demanded.

19:18:48.920 --> 19:18:50.1000
What stupid regardlessness now?

19:18:51.1000 --> 19:18:53.760
Here an illustration reader.

19:18:54.680 --> 19:18:58.040
A lover finds his mistress asleep on a mossy bank.

19:18:58.700 --> 19:19:02.440
He wishes to catch a glimpse of her fair face without waking her.

19:19:03.400 --> 19:19:07.900
He stills softly over the grass, careful to make no sound.

19:19:08.480 --> 19:19:11.300
He pauses, fancying she has stirred.

19:19:11.620 --> 19:19:12.840
He withdraws.

19:19:13.040 --> 19:19:15.040
Not for worlds would he be seen.

19:19:15.760 --> 19:19:16.720
All is still.

19:19:17.040 --> 19:19:18.060
He again advances.

19:19:18.660 --> 19:19:19.760
He bends over her.

19:19:19.840 --> 19:19:21.880
A light veil rests on her features.

19:19:22.420 --> 19:19:24.540
He lifts it, bends lower.

19:19:25.180 --> 19:19:28.600
Now his eyes anticipate the vision of beauty, warm and blooming,

19:19:28.760 --> 19:19:30.160
and lovely and rest.

19:19:30.900 --> 19:19:33.1000
How hurried was their first glance, but how they fix.

19:19:34.520 --> 19:19:35.520
How he starts.

19:19:35.960 --> 19:19:39.620
How he suddenly and vehemently clasps in both arms the form he

19:19:39.620 --> 19:19:42.380
dared not a moment since touch with his finger.

19:19:42.1000 --> 19:19:46.420
How he calls aloud a name and drops his burden and gazes on it

19:19:46.420 --> 19:19:51.500
wildly, he thus grasps and cries and gazes, because he no longer

19:19:51.500 --> 19:19:56.060
fears to waken by any sound he can utter, by any movement he can

19:19:56.060 --> 19:19:56.460
make.

19:19:57.080 --> 19:19:59.160
He thought his love slept sweetly.

19:19:59.580 --> 19:20:01.980
He finds she is stone dead.

19:20:03.120 --> 19:20:05.1000
I looked with timorous joy towards a stately house.

19:20:06.500 --> 19:20:08.300
I saw a blackened ruin.

19:20:09.280 --> 19:20:12.880
No need to cower behind a gate-post, indeed, to peep up at

19:20:12.880 --> 19:20:16.040
chamber lattices, fearing life was a stir behind them.

19:20:16.400 --> 19:20:20.100
No need to listen for doors opening, to fancy steps on the

19:20:20.100 --> 19:20:21.400
pavement, or the gravel walk.

19:20:21.880 --> 19:20:25.180
The lawn, the grounds, were trodden and waste.

19:20:25.660 --> 19:20:27.620
The portal yawned, void.

19:20:28.420 --> 19:20:32.780
The front was, as I had once seen it in a dream, but a shell-like

19:20:32.780 --> 19:20:37.240
wall, very high and very fragile-looking, perforated with painless

19:20:37.240 --> 19:20:37.760
windows.

19:20:38.300 --> 19:20:42.800
No roof, no battlements, no chimneys, all had crashed in.

19:20:43.720 --> 19:20:46.460
And there was the silence of death about it.

19:20:46.740 --> 19:20:48.760
The solitude of a lonesome wild.

19:20:49.440 --> 19:20:52.660
No wonder that letters addressed to people here had never received

19:20:52.660 --> 19:20:57.320
an answer, as well despatch epistles to a vault in a church-isle.

19:20:57.760 --> 19:21:01.460
The grim blackness of the stones told by what fate the hall had

19:21:01.460 --> 19:21:03.820
fallen, by conflagration.

19:21:04.440 --> 19:21:05.420
But how kindled?

19:21:06.040 --> 19:21:08.080
What story belonged to this disaster?

19:21:08.580 --> 19:21:12.220
What loss, besides mortar and marble and woodwork, had followed

19:21:12.220 --> 19:21:14.500
upon it, had life been wrecked?

19:21:14.540 --> 19:21:15.620
As well as property?

19:21:15.900 --> 19:21:16.1000
If so, whose?

19:21:17.840 --> 19:21:18.960
Dreadful question.

19:21:19.400 --> 19:21:21.500
There was no one here to answer it.

19:21:21.780 --> 19:21:24.040
Not even dumb sign, mute token.

19:21:25.320 --> 19:21:28.340
In wandering round the shattered walls and through the devastated

19:21:28.340 --> 19:21:32.380
interior, I gathered evidence that the calamity was not of late

19:21:32.380 --> 19:21:32.940
occurrence.

19:21:33.700 --> 19:21:36.780
Winter snows, I thought, had drifted through that void arch.

19:21:37.440 --> 19:21:40.140
Winter rains had beaten in at those hollow casements.

19:21:40.760 --> 19:21:44.820
For, amidst the drenched piles of rubbish, spring had cherished

19:21:44.820 --> 19:21:45.500
vegetation.

19:21:46.260 --> 19:21:49.260
Grass and wheat grew here and there between the stones and fallen

19:21:49.260 --> 19:21:50.400
rafters.

19:21:50.840 --> 19:21:54.180
And, oh, where meantime was the hapless owner of this wreck?

19:21:54.500 --> 19:21:55.440
In what land?

19:21:55.520 --> 19:21:56.740
Under what auspices?

19:21:57.380 --> 19:22:01.240
My eye involuntarily wandered to the gray church tower near the

19:22:01.240 --> 19:22:06.480
gates, and I asked, Is he with Damer de Rochester, sharing the

19:22:06.480 --> 19:22:08.360
shelter of his narrow marble house?

19:22:09.120 --> 19:22:11.680
Some answer must be had to these questions.

19:22:12.220 --> 19:22:15.840
I could find it nowhere but at the inn, and thither ere long I

19:22:15.840 --> 19:22:16.440
returned.

19:22:17.040 --> 19:22:19.1000
The host himself brought my breakfast into the parlor.

19:22:20.540 --> 19:22:22.1000
I requested him to shut the door and sit down.

19:22:23.220 --> 19:22:25.280
I had some questions to ask him.

19:22:25.740 --> 19:22:28.980
But when he complied, I scarcely knew how to begin.

19:22:29.760 --> 19:22:32.120
Such horror had I of the possible answers.

19:22:33.160 --> 19:22:36.440
And yet the spectacle of desolation I had just left

19:22:36.440 --> 19:22:39.100
prepared me in a measure for a tale of misery.

19:22:39.660 --> 19:22:43.040
The host was a respectable-looking middle-aged man.

19:22:44.260 --> 19:22:48.080
You know Thornfield Hall, of course, I managed to say at last.

19:22:48.700 --> 19:22:50.600
Yes, ma'am, I lived there once.

19:22:51.280 --> 19:22:52.120
Did you?

19:22:52.480 --> 19:22:53.960
Not in my time, I thought.

19:22:54.020 --> 19:22:55.540
You were a stranger to me.

19:22:56.300 --> 19:22:59.340
I was the late Mr. Rochester's butler, he added.

19:23:00.100 --> 19:23:04.240
The late I seem to have received with full force the blow I had

19:23:04.240 --> 19:23:05.340
been trying to evade.

19:23:05.720 --> 19:23:06.1000
The late, I gasped.

19:23:06.1000 --> 19:23:07.820
Is he dead?

19:23:08.520 --> 19:23:12.560
I mean the present gentleman, Mr. Edward's father, he explained.

19:23:13.180 --> 19:23:14.040
I breathed again.

19:23:14.580 --> 19:23:18.760
My blood resumed its flow, fully assured by these words that Mr.

19:23:18.840 --> 19:23:24.060
Edward, my Mr. Rochester, God bless him wherever he was, was at

19:23:24.060 --> 19:23:27.260
least alive, was in short the present gentleman.

19:23:28.080 --> 19:23:31.300
Gladdening words, it seemed I could hear all that was to come,

19:23:31.400 --> 19:23:35.080
whatever the disclosures might be, with comparative tranquillity.

19:23:35.080 --> 19:23:39.340
Since he was not in the grave, I could bear, I thought, to learn

19:23:39.340 --> 19:23:40.840
that he was at the Antipodes.

19:23:41.680 --> 19:23:46.420
Is Mr. Rochester living at Thornfield now, I asked, knowing, of

19:23:46.420 --> 19:23:49.840
course, what the answer would be, but yet desirous of deferring the

19:23:49.840 --> 19:23:52.740
direct question as to where he really was.

19:23:53.200 --> 19:23:56.060
No, ma'am, oh, no, no one is living there.

19:23:56.420 --> 19:23:59.480
I suppose you are a stranger in these parts, or you would have

19:23:59.480 --> 19:24:00.900
heard what happened last autumn.

19:24:01.500 --> 19:24:03.140
Thornfield Hall is quite a ruin.

19:24:03.140 --> 19:24:05.980
It was burnt down just about harvest time.

19:24:06.300 --> 19:24:07.920
A dreadful calamity.

19:24:08.280 --> 19:24:11.240
Such an immense quantity of valuable property destroyed.

19:24:11.600 --> 19:24:13.780
Hardly any of the furniture could be saved.

19:24:14.520 --> 19:24:17.700
The fire broke out at dead of night, and, before the engines

19:24:17.700 --> 19:24:21.620
arrived from Millcote, the building was one mass of flame.

19:24:21.920 --> 19:24:23.440
It was a terrible spectacle.

19:24:23.660 --> 19:24:25.020
I witnessed it myself.

19:24:25.980 --> 19:24:27.980
At dead of night, I muttered.

19:24:28.600 --> 19:24:31.640
Yes, that was ever the hour of fatality at Thornfield.

19:24:32.420 --> 19:24:35.120
Was it known how it originated, I demanded?

19:24:35.820 --> 19:24:37.500
They guessed, ma'am, they guessed.

19:24:37.1000 --> 19:24:40.540
Indeed, I should say it was ascertained beyond a doubt.

19:24:41.040 --> 19:24:44.820
You are not perhaps aware, he continued, edging his chair a

19:24:44.820 --> 19:24:48.920
little nearer the table, and speaking low, that there was a

19:24:48.920 --> 19:24:52.840
lady, a lunatic, kept in the house.

19:24:53.380 --> 19:24:55.260
I have heard something of it.

19:24:55.820 --> 19:24:58.580
She was kept in very close confinement, ma'am.

19:24:58.580 --> 19:25:01.880
People, even for years, was not absolutely certain of her

19:25:01.880 --> 19:25:02.420
existence.

19:25:02.960 --> 19:25:04.160
No one saw her.

19:25:04.440 --> 19:25:07.560
They only knew by rumour that such a person was at the hall.

19:25:07.940 --> 19:25:11.080
And who or what she was, it was difficult to conjecture.

19:25:11.500 --> 19:25:14.820
They said Mr. Edward had brought her from abroad, and some

19:25:14.820 --> 19:25:16.520
believed she had been his mistress.

19:25:17.040 --> 19:25:20.600
But a queer thing happened a year since, a very queer thing.

19:25:21.480 --> 19:25:23.620
I feared now to hear my own story.

19:25:23.940 --> 19:25:26.440
I endeavoured to recall him to the main fact.

19:25:26.980 --> 19:25:28.320
And this lady?

19:25:29.260 --> 19:25:32.920
This lady, ma'am, he answered, turned out to be Mr.

19:25:33.140 --> 19:25:34.080
Rochester's wife.

19:25:34.520 --> 19:25:37.320
The discovery was brought about in the strangest way.

19:25:37.640 --> 19:25:40.600
There was a young lady, a governess at the hall, that Mr.

19:25:40.780 --> 19:25:44.180
Rochester fell in but the fire, I suggested.

19:25:44.820 --> 19:25:46.880
I'm coming to that, ma'am, that Mr.

19:25:46.1000 --> 19:25:48.120
Edward fell in love with.

19:25:48.580 --> 19:25:51.900
The servants say they never saw anybody so much in love as he

19:25:51.900 --> 19:25:54.160
was, he was after her continually.

19:25:54.580 --> 19:25:58.200
They used to watch him, servants will, you know, ma'am, and he

19:25:58.200 --> 19:26:01.360
set store in her past everything, for all.

19:26:01.920 --> 19:26:04.440
Nobody but him thought her so very handsome.

19:26:04.900 --> 19:26:08.300
She was a little, small thing, they say, almost like a child.

19:26:08.760 --> 19:26:12.360
I never saw her myself, but I've heard Leah the housemaid tell

19:26:12.360 --> 19:26:12.920
of her.

19:26:13.360 --> 19:26:14.540
Leah liked her well enough.

19:26:14.1000 --> 19:26:18.420
Mr. Rochester was about forty, and this governess not twenty.

19:26:18.800 --> 19:26:22.440
And you see, when gentlemen of his age fall in love with girls,

19:26:23.020 --> 19:26:25.200
they are often like as if they were bewitched.

19:26:25.380 --> 19:26:26.940
Well, he would marry her.

19:26:27.540 --> 19:26:31.520
You shall tell me this part of the story another time, I said, but

19:26:31.520 --> 19:26:34.540
now I have a particular reason for wishing to hear all about the

19:26:34.540 --> 19:26:34.900
fire.

19:26:35.500 --> 19:26:38.240
Was it suspected that this lunatic, Mrs.

19:26:38.480 --> 19:26:40.540
Rochester, had any hand in it?

19:26:40.1000 --> 19:26:42.240
You've hit it, ma'am.

19:26:42.360 --> 19:26:45.500
It's quite certain that it was her and nobody but her that set it

19:26:45.500 --> 19:26:45.780
going.

19:26:46.300 --> 19:26:48.620
She had a woman to take care of her called Mrs.

19:26:48.620 --> 19:26:53.180
Poole, an able woman in her line and very trustworthy, but for one

19:26:53.180 --> 19:26:56.820
fault, a fault common to a deal of them nurses and matrons.

19:26:57.220 --> 19:27:01.1000
She kept a private bottle of gin by her, and now and then took a

19:27:01.1000 --> 19:27:02.800
drop over much.

19:27:03.220 --> 19:27:07.100
It is excusable, for she had a hard life of it, but still it was

19:27:07.100 --> 19:27:07.720
dangerous.

19:27:08.040 --> 19:27:11.860
For when Mrs. Poole was fast asleep, after the gin and water,

19:27:12.560 --> 19:27:15.980
the mad lady, who was as cunning as a witch, would take the keys

19:27:15.980 --> 19:27:19.740
out of her pocket, let herself out of her chamber, and go roaming

19:27:19.740 --> 19:27:23.280
about the house, doing any wild mischief that came into her head.

19:27:23.740 --> 19:27:27.700
They say she had nearly burnt her husband in his bed once, but I

19:27:27.700 --> 19:27:28.780
don't know about that.

19:27:29.220 --> 19:27:33.120
However, on this night, she set fire first to the hangings of the

19:27:33.120 --> 19:27:37.160
room next to her own, and then she got down to a lower story and

19:27:37.160 --> 19:27:40.200
made her way to the chamber that had been the governess's.

19:27:40.860 --> 19:27:44.520
She was like as if she knew somehow how matters had gone on, and

19:27:44.520 --> 19:27:48.620
had a spite at her, and she kindled the bed there, but there was

19:27:48.620 --> 19:27:50.240
nobody sleeping in it, fortunately.

19:27:50.600 --> 19:27:54.280
The governess had run away two months before, and for all Mr.

19:27:54.500 --> 19:27:57.560
Rochester sought her as if she had been the most precious thing he

19:27:57.560 --> 19:28:01.080
had in the world, he never could hear a word of her, and he grew

19:28:01.080 --> 19:28:03.500
savage, quite savage on his disappointment.

19:28:03.960 --> 19:28:08.160
He never was a wild man, but he got dangerous after he lost her.

19:28:08.460 --> 19:28:10.060
He would be alone, too.

19:28:10.240 --> 19:28:14.200
He sent Mrs. Fairfax, the housekeeper, away to her friends at a

19:28:14.200 --> 19:28:18.360
distance, but he did it handsomely, for he settled an annuity on her

19:28:18.360 --> 19:28:20.480
for life, and she deserved it.

19:28:20.620 --> 19:28:22.060
She was a very good woman.

19:28:22.580 --> 19:28:25.660
Miss Adele, a ward he had, was put to school.

19:28:26.100 --> 19:28:29.560
He broke off acquaintance with all the gentry, and shut himself up,

19:28:29.560 --> 19:28:31.240
like a hermit, at the hall.

19:28:32.440 --> 19:28:32.920
What?

19:28:33.200 --> 19:28:34.540
He did not leave England?

19:28:35.200 --> 19:28:36.040
Leave England?

19:28:36.240 --> 19:28:36.820
Bless you!

19:28:36.880 --> 19:28:37.300
No!

19:28:37.680 --> 19:28:41.320
He would not cross the door-stones of the house except at night, when

19:28:41.320 --> 19:28:45.200
walked just like a ghost about the grounds, and in the orchard as if he had

19:28:45.200 --> 19:28:48.420
lost his senses, which it is my opinion he had.

19:28:48.820 --> 19:28:52.840
For a more spirited, bolder, keener gentleman than he was before that

19:28:52.840 --> 19:28:55.960
midge of a governess crossed him, you never saw, ma'am.

19:28:56.040 --> 19:29:00.880
He was not a man given to wine, or cards, or racing, as some are, and he

19:29:00.880 --> 19:29:05.520
was not so very handsome, but he had a courage and a will of his own, if

19:29:05.520 --> 19:29:06.440
ever man had.

19:29:06.1000 --> 19:29:11.160
I knew him from a boy, you see, and for my part, I have often wished

19:29:11.160 --> 19:29:14.900
that Miss Eyre had been sunk in the sea before she came to Thornfield

19:29:14.900 --> 19:29:15.320
Hall.

19:29:16.340 --> 19:29:19.740
Then Mr. Rochester was at home when the fire broke out?

19:29:20.960 --> 19:29:24.920
Yes, indeed was he, and he went up to the attics, when all was burning

19:29:24.920 --> 19:29:28.320
above and below, and got the servants out of their beds, and helped them

19:29:28.320 --> 19:29:29.200
down himself.

19:29:29.840 --> 19:29:33.960
Anne went back to get his mad wife out of her cell, and then they called

19:29:33.960 --> 19:29:37.720
out to him that she was on the roof, where she was standing, waving her

19:29:37.720 --> 19:29:41.560
arms above the battlements, and shouting out till they could hear her a

19:29:41.560 --> 19:29:42.200
mile off.

19:29:42.600 --> 19:29:45.340
I saw her and heard her with my own eyes.

19:29:45.680 --> 19:29:48.940
She was a big woman, and had long black hair.

19:29:49.260 --> 19:29:52.100
We could see it streaming against the flames as she stood.

19:29:52.700 --> 19:29:56.560
I witnessed, and several more witnessed Mr. Rochester ascend through the

19:29:56.560 --> 19:29:57.780
skylight onto the roof.

19:29:58.140 --> 19:30:00.060
We heard him call, Bertha.

19:30:00.620 --> 19:30:05.660
We saw him approach her, and then ma'am, she yelled and gave a spring, and

19:30:05.660 --> 19:30:08.140
the next minute she lay smashed on the pavement.

19:30:08.960 --> 19:30:09.480
Dead?

19:30:10.500 --> 19:30:11.020
Dead?

19:30:11.420 --> 19:30:14.460
I, dead as the stones on which her brains and blood were scattered.

19:30:15.340 --> 19:30:16.240
Good God!

19:30:17.280 --> 19:30:18.960
You may well say so, ma'am.

19:30:18.980 --> 19:30:20.320
It was frightful.

19:30:20.780 --> 19:30:21.940
He shuddered.

19:30:22.460 --> 19:30:23.400
And afterwards?

19:30:23.620 --> 19:30:24.220
I urged.

19:30:25.020 --> 19:30:27.860
Well, ma'am, afterwards the house was burnt to the ground.

19:30:28.160 --> 19:30:30.540
There are only some bits of wall standing now.

19:30:31.440 --> 19:30:33.020
Were any other lives lost?

19:30:33.720 --> 19:30:33.1000
No.

19:30:34.500 --> 19:30:36.680
Perhaps it would have been better if there had.

19:30:37.440 --> 19:30:38.560
What do you mean?

19:30:39.360 --> 19:30:41.940
Poor Mr. Edward, he ejaculated.

19:30:42.400 --> 19:30:44.300
I little thought ever to have seen it.

19:30:44.620 --> 19:30:48.040
Some say it was a just judgment on him for keeping his first marriage

19:30:48.040 --> 19:30:51.560
secret, and wanting to take another wife while he had one living.

19:30:51.880 --> 19:30:53.920
But I pity him for my part.

19:30:54.720 --> 19:30:57.260
You said he was alive, I exclaimed.

19:30:57.860 --> 19:31:01.640
Yes, yes, he is alive, but many think he had better be dead.

19:31:02.480 --> 19:31:03.640
Why, how?

19:31:03.940 --> 19:31:05.620
My blood was again running cold.

19:31:06.240 --> 19:31:07.140
Where is he?

19:31:07.160 --> 19:31:07.760
I demanded.

19:31:07.840 --> 19:31:08.740
Is he in England?

19:31:09.520 --> 19:31:11.280
Aye, aye, he's in England.

19:31:11.480 --> 19:31:13.400
He can't get out of England, I fancy.

19:31:13.580 --> 19:31:14.900
He's a fixture now.

19:31:15.860 --> 19:31:17.300
What agony was this?

19:31:17.440 --> 19:31:20.460
And the man seemed resolved to protract it.

19:31:20.900 --> 19:31:23.580
He is stone blind, he said at last.

19:31:23.700 --> 19:31:26.280
Yes, he is stone blind, is Mr. Edward.

19:31:26.780 --> 19:31:28.180
I had dreaded worse.

19:31:28.680 --> 19:31:30.280
I had dreaded he was mad.

19:31:30.820 --> 19:31:34.200
I summoned strength to ask what had caused this calamity.

19:31:35.160 --> 19:31:39.580
It was all his own courage, and a body may say his kindness in a way, ma'am.

19:31:39.700 --> 19:31:43.660
He wouldn't leave the house till everyone else was out before him.

19:31:44.040 --> 19:31:47.320
As he came down the great staircase at last, after Mrs.

19:31:47.560 --> 19:31:51.260
Rochester had flung herself from the battlements, there was a great crash.

19:31:51.520 --> 19:31:52.320
All fell.

19:31:52.680 --> 19:31:56.800
He was taken out from under the ruins, alive, but sadly hurt.

19:31:56.800 --> 19:32:01.840
A beam had fallen in such a way as to protect him partly, but one eye was

19:32:01.840 --> 19:32:06.200
knocked out, and one hand so crushed that Mr. Carter, the surgeon, had to

19:32:06.200 --> 19:32:07.300
amputate it directly.

19:32:07.840 --> 19:32:09.220
The other eye inflamed.

19:32:09.440 --> 19:32:11.220
He lost the sight of that also.

19:32:11.500 --> 19:32:14.840
He is now helpless, indeed blind and a cripple.

19:32:15.460 --> 19:32:16.600
Where is he?

19:32:16.600 --> 19:32:17.860
Where does he now live?

19:32:18.340 --> 19:32:22.700
At Ferndean, a manor house on a farm he has, about thirty miles off.

19:32:22.1000 --> 19:32:24.300
Quite a desolate spot.

19:32:24.860 --> 19:32:26.260
Who is with him?

19:32:26.800 --> 19:32:28.300
Old John and his wife.

19:32:28.460 --> 19:32:29.880
He would have none else.

19:32:30.140 --> 19:32:32.080
He is quite broken down, they say.

19:32:32.680 --> 19:32:34.620
Have you any sort of conveyance?

19:32:34.920 --> 19:32:37.960
We have a chaise, ma'am, a very handsome chaise.

19:32:38.340 --> 19:32:39.760
Let it be got ready instantly.

19:32:40.220 --> 19:32:44.100
And if your post-boy can drive me to Ferndean before dark this day, I'll

19:32:44.100 --> 19:32:47.220
pay both you and him twice the hire you usually demand.

19:33:10.180 --> 19:33:10.980
XXXVII.

19:33:12.700 --> 19:33:17.880
The manor house of Ferndean was a building of considerable antiquity, moderate size,

19:33:17.880 --> 19:33:21.940
and no architectural pretensions, deep buried in a wood.

19:33:22.440 --> 19:33:23.900
I had heard of it before.

19:33:24.560 --> 19:33:28.200
Mr. Rochester often spoke of it, and sometimes went there.

19:33:28.700 --> 19:33:32.680
His father had purchased the estate for the sake of the game-covers.

19:33:33.220 --> 19:33:38.300
He would have let the house, but could find no tenant in consequence of its ineligible

19:33:38.300 --> 19:33:40.360
and insolubrious site.

19:33:41.120 --> 19:33:47.140
Ferndean then remained uninhabited and unfurnished, with the exception of some two or three rooms

19:33:47.140 --> 19:33:51.860
fitted up for the accommodation of the squire, when he went there in the season to shoot.

19:33:52.760 --> 19:33:58.660
To this house I came, just air dark, on an evening marked by the characteristics of sad

19:33:58.660 --> 19:34:03.660
sky, cold gale, and continued small penetrating rain.

19:34:04.280 --> 19:34:09.340
The last mile I performed on foot, having dismissed the chaise and driver with the double

19:34:09.340 --> 19:34:11.060
remuneration I had promised.

19:34:11.900 --> 19:34:17.140
Even when within a very short distance of the manor house you could see nothing of it,

19:34:17.300 --> 19:34:20.640
so thick and dark grew the timber of the gloomy wood about it.

19:34:21.500 --> 19:34:26.600
Iron gates between granite pillars showed me where to enter, and passing through them

19:34:26.600 --> 19:34:30.640
I found myself at once in the twilight of close-ranked trees.

19:34:31.420 --> 19:34:37.280
There was a grass-grown track descending the forest aisle, between whore and knotty shafts

19:34:37.280 --> 19:34:38.620
and under-branched arches.

19:34:39.040 --> 19:34:45.060
I followed it, expecting soon to reach the dwelling, but it stretched on and on.

19:34:45.340 --> 19:34:47.220
It wound far and farther.

19:34:47.720 --> 19:34:50.340
No sign of habitation or grounds was visible.

19:34:51.080 --> 19:34:54.160
I thought I had taken a wrong direction and lost my way.

19:34:54.700 --> 19:34:58.920
The darkness of natural, as well as of sylvan desk, gathered over me.

19:34:59.220 --> 19:35:01.300
I looked round in search of another road.

19:35:01.760 --> 19:35:02.720
There was none.

19:35:02.720 --> 19:35:09.140
All was interwoven stem, columnar trunk, dense summer foliage, no opening anywhere.

19:35:09.980 --> 19:35:10.820
I proceeded.

19:35:11.340 --> 19:35:12.800
At last my way opened.

19:35:13.080 --> 19:35:14.360
The trees thinned a little.

19:35:14.940 --> 19:35:20.780
Presently I beheld a railing, then the house, scarce by this dim light distinguishable from

19:35:20.780 --> 19:35:24.320
the trees, so dank and green were its decaying walls.

19:35:25.420 --> 19:35:30.520
Entering a portal fastened only by a latch, I stood amidst a space of enclosed ground,

19:35:30.520 --> 19:35:33.540
from which the wood swept away in a semicircle.

19:35:33.860 --> 19:35:40.160
There were no flowers, no garden beds, only a broad gravel walk girdling a grass-plot,

19:35:40.300 --> 19:35:43.220
and this set in the heavy frame of the forest.

19:35:43.800 --> 19:35:47.020
The house presented two pointed gables in its front.

19:35:47.560 --> 19:35:49.200
The windows were lattice to narrow.

19:35:49.760 --> 19:35:51.560
The front door was narrow, too.

19:35:51.780 --> 19:35:53.440
One step led up to it.

19:35:53.740 --> 19:35:59.420
The whole looked, as the host of Rochester Arms had said, quite a desolate spot.

19:36:00.040 --> 19:36:02.480
It was as still as a church on a weekday.

19:36:02.880 --> 19:36:07.400
The pattering rain on the forest leaves was the only sound audible in its vicinage.

19:36:08.220 --> 19:36:09.780
Can there be life here?

19:36:09.900 --> 19:36:10.500
I asked.

19:36:11.680 --> 19:36:15.580
Yes, life of some kind there was, for I heard a movement.

19:36:16.180 --> 19:36:21.460
That narrow front door was unclosing, and some shape was about to issue from the grange.

19:36:22.260 --> 19:36:23.360
It opened slowly.

19:36:23.760 --> 19:36:28.960
A figure came out into the twilight and stood on the step, a man without a hat.

19:36:29.640 --> 19:36:33.040
He stretched forth his hand, as if to feel whether it rained.

19:36:33.860 --> 19:36:36.220
Dusk as it was, I had recognized him.

19:36:36.440 --> 19:36:40.740
It was my master, Edward Fairfax Rochester, and no other.

19:36:41.800 --> 19:36:48.700
I stayed my step, almost my breath, and stood to watch him, to examine him, myself unseen,

19:36:49.100 --> 19:36:50.700
and, alas, to him invisible.

19:36:51.480 --> 19:36:56.720
It was a sudden meeting, and one in which rapture was kept well in check by pain.

19:36:57.280 --> 19:37:03.160
I had no difficulty in restraining my voice from exclamation, my step from hasty advance.

19:37:04.060 --> 19:37:07.540
His form was of the same strong and stalwart contour as ever.

19:37:07.960 --> 19:37:13.520
His port was still erect, his hair was still raven-black, nor were his features altered

19:37:13.520 --> 19:37:14.060
or sunk.

19:37:14.520 --> 19:37:20.140
Not in one year's space, by any sorrow, could his athletic strength be quelled, or his vigorous

19:37:20.140 --> 19:37:21.420
prime blighted.

19:37:21.860 --> 19:37:24.620
But in his countenance I saw a change.

19:37:25.260 --> 19:37:27.240
That looked desperate and brooding.

19:37:27.660 --> 19:37:33.400
That reminded me of some wronged and fettered wild beast or bird, dangerous to approach

19:37:33.400 --> 19:37:35.140
in his sullen woe.

19:37:35.420 --> 19:37:41.280
The caged eagle, whose gold-ringed eyes cruelty has extinguished, might look as looked that

19:37:41.280 --> 19:37:42.340
sightless Samson.

19:37:43.460 --> 19:37:47.820
And Reader, you think I feared him in his blind ferocity?

19:37:47.820 --> 19:37:50.160
If you do, you little know me.

19:37:50.620 --> 19:37:55.460
A soft hope blent with my sorrow that soon I should dare to drop a kiss on that brow

19:37:55.460 --> 19:37:59.560
of rock, and on those lips so sternly sealed beneath it.

19:37:59.860 --> 19:38:00.880
But not yet.

19:38:01.400 --> 19:38:03.100
I would not accost him yet.

19:38:03.880 --> 19:38:09.660
He descended the one step, and advanced slowly and gropingly towards the grass-plat.

19:38:10.320 --> 19:38:12.340
Where was his daring stride now?

19:38:12.740 --> 19:38:16.360
Then he paused, as if he knew not which way to turn.

19:38:16.880 --> 19:38:23.880
He lifted his hand, and opened his eyelids, gazed blank, and, with a straining effort,

19:38:23.960 --> 19:38:27.580
on the sky, and towards the amphitheatre of trees.

19:38:28.340 --> 19:38:31.200
One saw that all to him was a void darkness.

19:38:31.900 --> 19:38:37.240
He stretched his right hand, the left arm, the mutilated one, he kept hidden in his bosom.

19:38:37.720 --> 19:38:41.980
He seemed to wish, by touch, to gain an idea of what lay around him.

19:38:41.980 --> 19:38:46.620
He met but vacancy still, for the trees were some yards off where he stood.

19:38:47.420 --> 19:38:52.140
He relinquished the endeavour, folded his arms, and stood quiet and mute in the rain,

19:38:52.560 --> 19:38:54.980
now falling fast on his uncovered head.

19:38:55.740 --> 19:38:58.660
At this moment John approached him from some quarter.

19:38:59.940 --> 19:39:01.800
Will you take my arm, sir?

19:39:01.1000 --> 19:39:02.600
He said.

19:39:02.960 --> 19:39:04.760
There is a heavy shower coming on.

19:39:05.220 --> 19:39:06.600
Had you not better go in?

19:39:07.380 --> 19:39:10.040
Let me alone, was the answer.

19:39:10.600 --> 19:39:13.100
John withdrew, without having observed me.

19:39:13.680 --> 19:39:18.660
Mr. Rochester now tried to walk about, vainly, all was too uncertain.

19:39:19.320 --> 19:39:23.380
He groped his way back to the house, and, re-entering it, closed the door.

19:39:24.360 --> 19:39:25.1000
I now drew near and knocked.

19:39:26.440 --> 19:39:28.260
John's wife opened the door for me.

19:39:28.620 --> 19:39:30.940
Mary, I said, how are you?

19:39:31.420 --> 19:39:33.640
She started as if she had seen a ghost.

19:39:33.700 --> 19:39:34.800
I calmed her.

19:39:35.380 --> 19:39:36.160
To her hurried.

19:39:36.160 --> 19:39:39.800
Is it really you, Miss, come at this late hour to this lonely place?

19:39:40.340 --> 19:39:44.880
I answered by taking her hand, and then I followed her into the kitchen, where John

19:39:44.880 --> 19:39:46.320
now sat by a good fire.

19:39:46.860 --> 19:39:51.280
I explained to them, in a few words, that I had heard all which had happened since I

19:39:51.280 --> 19:39:54.400
left Thornfield, and that I was come to see Mr. Rochester.

19:39:54.1000 --> 19:40:00.100
I asked John to go down to the Turnpike house, where I had dismissed the chaise, and bring

19:40:00.100 --> 19:40:05.640
my trunk which I had left there, and then, while I removed my bonnet and shawl, I questioned

19:40:05.640 --> 19:40:10.580
Mary as to whether I could be accommodated at the manor house for the night, and finding

19:40:10.580 --> 19:40:15.600
that arrangements to that effect, though difficult, would not be impossible, I informed

19:40:15.600 --> 19:40:16.600
her I should stay.

19:40:17.080 --> 19:40:19.440
Just at this moment the parlour bell rang.

19:40:20.780 --> 19:40:26.400
When you go in, said I, tell your master that a person wishes to speak to him, but do not

19:40:26.400 --> 19:40:27.160
give my name.

19:40:27.680 --> 19:40:30.500
I don't think he will see you, she answered.

19:40:30.640 --> 19:40:31.1000
He refuses everybody.

19:40:32.660 --> 19:40:35.640
When she returned, I inquired what he had said.

19:40:36.140 --> 19:40:39.620
You are to send in your name and your business, she replied.

19:40:40.060 --> 19:40:45.040
She then proceeded to fill a glass with water, and place it on a tray, together with candles.

19:40:45.700 --> 19:40:47.320
Is that what he rang for?

19:40:47.680 --> 19:40:48.320
I asked.

19:40:48.880 --> 19:40:52.700
Yes, he always has candles brought in at dark, though he is blind.

19:40:53.660 --> 19:40:56.080
Give the tray to me, I will carry it in.

19:40:56.800 --> 19:40:58.200
I took it from her hand.

19:40:58.520 --> 19:41:00.440
She pointed me out the parlour door.

19:41:00.800 --> 19:41:02.660
The tray shook as I held it.

19:41:02.980 --> 19:41:04.640
The water spilt from the glass.

19:41:05.240 --> 19:41:07.560
My heart struck my ribs loud and fast.

19:41:08.660 --> 19:41:11.480
Mary opened the door for me and shut it behind me.

19:41:11.740 --> 19:41:13.440
This parlour looked gloomy.

19:41:13.960 --> 19:41:19.700
A neglected handful of fire burnt low in the grate, and leaning over it with his head supported

19:41:19.700 --> 19:41:24.520
against the high, old-fashioned mantelpiece, appeared the blind tenant of the room.

19:41:25.140 --> 19:41:30.580
His old dog, Pilot, lay on one side, removed out of the way, and coiled up as if afraid

19:41:30.580 --> 19:41:32.560
of being inadvertently trodden upon.

19:41:33.400 --> 19:41:35.720
Pilot pricked up his ears when I came in.

19:41:35.980 --> 19:41:39.940
Then he jumped up with a yelp and a whine, and he bounded towards me.

19:41:40.200 --> 19:41:42.760
He almost knocked the tray from my hands.

19:41:43.440 --> 19:41:47.780
I set it on the table, then patted him, and said softly, Lie down.

19:41:48.520 --> 19:41:54.660
Mr. Rochester turned mechanically to see what the commotion was, but as he saw nothing,

19:41:55.280 --> 19:41:57.340
he returned and sighed.

19:41:58.180 --> 19:42:00.680
Give me the water, Mary, he said.

19:42:01.380 --> 19:42:04.320
I approached him with the now only half-filled glass.

19:42:04.960 --> 19:42:06.660
Pilot followed me, still excited.

19:42:07.520 --> 19:42:08.700
What is the matter?

19:42:08.960 --> 19:42:09.920
he inquired.

19:42:11.060 --> 19:42:13.080
Down, Pilot, I again said.

19:42:13.540 --> 19:42:16.760
He checked the water on its way to his lips and seemed to listen.

19:42:17.230 --> 19:42:19.260
He drank and put the glass down.

19:42:19.720 --> 19:42:21.780
This is you, Mary, is it not?

19:42:22.720 --> 19:42:24.620
Mary's in the kitchen, I answered.

19:42:25.640 --> 19:42:30.700
He put out his hand with a quick gesture, but not seeing where I stood, he did not touch

19:42:30.700 --> 19:42:31.260
me.

19:42:31.920 --> 19:42:32.680
Who is this?

19:42:32.740 --> 19:42:39.740
Who is this? he demanded, trying, as it seemed, to see with those sightless eyes, an availing

19:42:39.740 --> 19:42:40.960
and distressing attempt.

19:42:41.640 --> 19:42:42.420
Answer me.

19:42:42.580 --> 19:42:46.160
Speak again, he ordered, imperiously and aloud.

19:42:46.860 --> 19:42:49.160
Will you have a little more water, sir?

19:42:49.300 --> 19:42:52.480
I spilt half of what was in the glass, I said.

19:42:53.320 --> 19:42:54.360
Who is it?

19:42:54.560 --> 19:42:55.440
What is it?

19:42:55.460 --> 19:42:56.200
Who speaks?

19:42:57.100 --> 19:43:00.180
Pilot knows me, and John and Mary know I am here.

19:43:00.580 --> 19:43:02.760
I came only this evening, I answered.

19:43:03.820 --> 19:43:06.420
Great God, what delusion has come over me!

19:43:06.720 --> 19:43:09.040
What sweet madness has seized me!

19:43:09.700 --> 19:43:11.500
No delusion, no madness.

19:43:11.900 --> 19:43:16.560
Your mind, sir, is too strong for delusion, your health too sound for frenzy.

19:43:17.580 --> 19:43:18.840
And where is the speaker?

19:43:19.160 --> 19:43:20.380
Is it only a voice?

19:43:21.020 --> 19:43:25.960
Oh, I cannot see, but I must feel, or my heart will stop and my brain burst.

19:43:26.480 --> 19:43:31.260
Whatever, whoever you are, be perceptible to the touch, or I cannot live.

19:43:31.960 --> 19:43:32.860
He groped.

19:43:33.220 --> 19:43:36.720
I arrested his wandering hand and prisoned it in both mine.

19:43:37.450 --> 19:43:41.820
Her very fingers, he cried, her small, slight fingers.

19:43:42.080 --> 19:43:43.1000
If so, there must be more of her.

19:43:44.440 --> 19:43:46.720
The muscular hand broke from my custody.

19:43:47.300 --> 19:43:52.680
My arm was seized, my shoulder, neck, waist, I was entwined and gathered to him.

19:43:53.340 --> 19:43:54.200
Is it Jane?

19:43:54.580 --> 19:43:55.600
What is it?

19:43:55.860 --> 19:43:58.080
This is her shape, this is her size.

19:43:58.640 --> 19:44:00.320
And this is her voice, I added.

19:44:00.580 --> 19:44:02.660
She is all here, her heart too.

19:44:03.160 --> 19:44:04.180
God bless you, sir.

19:44:04.180 --> 19:44:06.480
I am glad to be so near you again.

19:44:07.560 --> 19:44:10.520
Jane Eyre, Jane Eyre, was all he said.

19:44:11.240 --> 19:44:14.020
My dear master, I answered, I am Jane Eyre.

19:44:14.260 --> 19:44:15.360
I have found you out.

19:44:15.660 --> 19:44:17.020
I am come back to you.

19:44:17.820 --> 19:44:21.040
In truth, in the flesh, my living Jane?

19:44:21.740 --> 19:44:24.660
You touch me, sir, you hold me, and fast enough.

19:44:24.960 --> 19:44:28.200
I am not like a corpse, nor vacant like Eyre, am I?

19:44:28.920 --> 19:44:33.320
My living darling, these are certainly her limbs, and these her features.

19:44:33.940 --> 19:44:37.100
But I cannot be so blessed, after all my misery.

19:44:37.760 --> 19:44:43.380
It is a dream, such dreams as I have had at night when I have clasped her once more to

19:44:43.380 --> 19:44:50.060
my heart as I do now, and kissed her as thus, and felt that she loved me and trusted that

19:44:50.060 --> 19:44:51.640
she would not leave me.

19:44:52.480 --> 19:44:54.780
Which I never will, sir, from this day.

19:44:55.880 --> 19:44:57.880
Never will, says the vision.

19:44:58.620 --> 19:45:05.140
But I always woke and found it an empty mockery, and I was desolate and abandoned, my life

19:45:05.140 --> 19:45:11.800
dark, lonely, hopeless, my soul a thirst and forbidden to drink, my heart famished and

19:45:11.800 --> 19:45:12.800
never to be fed.

19:45:13.580 --> 19:45:19.100
Gentle soft dream nestling in my arms now, you will fly too, as your sisters have all

19:45:19.100 --> 19:45:22.260
fled before you, but kiss me before you go.

19:45:22.800 --> 19:45:23.900
Embrace me, Jane.

19:45:24.820 --> 19:45:26.260
There, sir, and there.

19:45:26.800 --> 19:45:30.440
I pressed my lips to his once brilliant and now rayless eyes.

19:45:30.820 --> 19:45:33.600
I swept his hair from his brow and kissed that, too.

19:45:34.220 --> 19:45:36.240
He suddenly seemed to arouse himself.

19:45:37.100 --> 19:45:40.740
The conviction of the reality of all this seized him.

19:45:41.240 --> 19:45:42.500
Is it you?

19:45:42.700 --> 19:45:43.420
Is it, Jane?

19:45:43.980 --> 19:45:45.420
You are come back to me, then?

19:45:46.140 --> 19:45:46.940
I am.

19:45:47.540 --> 19:45:52.800
And you do not lie dead in some ditch under some stream, and you are not a pining outcast

19:45:52.800 --> 19:45:53.720
among strangers?

19:45:54.520 --> 19:45:57.700
No, sir, I am an independent woman now.

19:45:58.620 --> 19:45:59.300
Independent?

19:45:59.420 --> 19:46:00.580
What do you mean, Jane?

19:46:01.500 --> 19:46:05.920
My uncle in Madeira is dead, and he left me five thousand pounds.

19:46:06.940 --> 19:46:10.560
Ah, this is practical, this is real, he cried.

19:46:10.700 --> 19:46:12.480
I should never dream that.

19:46:12.820 --> 19:46:20.040
Besides, there is that peculiar voice of hers, so animating and piquant, as well as soft.

19:46:20.040 --> 19:46:23.780
It cheers my withered heart, it puts life into it.

19:46:24.120 --> 19:46:27.900
What, Janet, are you an independent woman, a rich woman?

19:46:28.720 --> 19:46:29.880
Quite rich, sir.

19:46:30.120 --> 19:46:35.020
If you won't let me live with you, I can build a house of my own, close up to your door,

19:46:35.240 --> 19:46:39.080
and you may come and sit in my parlour when you want company of an evening.

19:46:39.900 --> 19:46:45.240
But, as you are rich, Jane, you have now, no doubt, friends who will look after you,

19:46:45.240 --> 19:46:49.460
and not suffer you to devote yourself to a blind lame-der like me?

19:46:50.380 --> 19:46:53.680
I told you I am independent, sir, as well as rich.

19:46:54.060 --> 19:46:55.400
I am my own mistress.

19:46:56.380 --> 19:46:58.080
And you will stay with me?

19:46:58.680 --> 19:47:00.300
Certainly, unless you object.

19:47:00.700 --> 19:47:03.420
I will be your neighbour, your nurse, your housekeeper.

19:47:03.940 --> 19:47:05.020
I find you lonely.

19:47:05.360 --> 19:47:10.160
I will be your companion, to read to you, to walk with you, to sit with you, to wait

19:47:10.160 --> 19:47:13.020
on you, to be eyes and hands to you.

19:47:13.020 --> 19:47:16.020
Cease to look so melancholy, my dear master.

19:47:16.420 --> 19:47:19.160
You shall not be left desolate so long as I live.

19:47:20.040 --> 19:47:21.260
He replied not.

19:47:21.620 --> 19:47:24.220
He seemed serious, abstracted.

19:47:24.460 --> 19:47:25.540
He sighed.

19:47:25.1000 --> 19:47:28.200
He half opened his lips as if to speak.

19:47:28.640 --> 19:47:29.880
He closed them again.

19:47:30.480 --> 19:47:32.240
I felt a little embarrassed.

19:47:33.120 --> 19:47:40.420
Perhaps I had too rashly overlapped conventionalities, and he, like St. John, saw impropriety in

19:47:40.420 --> 19:47:41.740
my inconsiderateness.

19:47:41.740 --> 19:47:47.280
I had indeed made my proposal from the idea that he wished, and would ask me to be his

19:47:47.280 --> 19:47:47.740
wife.

19:47:48.720 --> 19:47:54.220
An expectation, not the less certain because unexpressed, had buoyed me up, that he would

19:47:54.220 --> 19:47:55.900
claim me at once as his own.

19:47:56.340 --> 19:48:02.520
But no hint to that effect escaping him, and his countenance becoming more overcast, I

19:48:02.520 --> 19:48:07.380
suddenly remembered that I might have been all wrong, and was perhaps playing the fool

19:48:08.020 --> 19:48:13.860
unwittingly, and I began gently to withdraw myself from his arms, but he eagerly snatched

19:48:13.860 --> 19:48:14.640
me closer.

19:48:15.180 --> 19:48:17.820
No, no, Jane, you must not go.

19:48:18.120 --> 19:48:23.300
No, I have touched you, heard you, felt the comfort of your presence, the sweetness of

19:48:23.300 --> 19:48:24.380
your consolation.

19:48:24.760 --> 19:48:26.520
I cannot give up these joys.

19:48:26.820 --> 19:48:28.700
I have little left in myself.

19:48:28.960 --> 19:48:30.100
I must have you.

19:48:30.540 --> 19:48:35.740
The world may laugh, may call me absurd, selfish, but it does not signify.

19:48:35.740 --> 19:48:37.940
My very soul demands you.

19:48:38.080 --> 19:48:42.020
It will be satisfied, or it will take deadly vengeance on its frame.

19:48:43.200 --> 19:48:45.020
Well, sir, I will stay with you.

19:48:45.020 --> 19:48:46.220
I have said so.

19:48:46.920 --> 19:48:52.080
Yes, but you understand one thing by staying with me, and I understand another.

19:48:52.980 --> 19:48:58.300
You perhaps could make up your mind to be about my hand and chair, to wait on me as

19:48:58.300 --> 19:49:03.540
a kind little nurse, for you have an affectionate heart and a generous spirit which prompt you

19:49:03.540 --> 19:49:08.520
to make sacrifices for those you pity, and that ought to suffice for me, no doubt.

19:49:09.020 --> 19:49:13.060
I suppose I should now entertain none but fatherly feelings for you.

19:49:13.360 --> 19:49:14.420
Do you think so?

19:49:14.860 --> 19:49:16.220
Come, tell me.

19:49:17.120 --> 19:49:18.800
I will think what you like, sir.

19:49:19.040 --> 19:49:22.440
I am content to be only your nurse, if you think it better.

19:49:23.800 --> 19:49:26.160
But you cannot always be my nurse, Janet.

19:49:26.440 --> 19:49:27.280
You are young.

19:49:27.440 --> 19:49:28.920
You must marry one day.

19:49:29.440 --> 19:49:31.260
I don't care about being married.

19:49:31.1000 --> 19:49:33.400
You should care, Janet.

19:49:33.820 --> 19:49:39.980
If I were what I once was, I would try to make you care, but a sightless block."

19:49:39.980 --> 19:49:42.360
He relapsed again into gloom.

19:49:42.840 --> 19:49:46.720
I, on the contrary, became more cheerful, and took fresh courage.

19:49:47.300 --> 19:49:52.760
These last words gave me an insight as to where the difficulty lay, and as it was no

19:49:52.760 --> 19:49:57.140
difficulty with me, I felt quite relieved from my previous embarrassment.

19:49:57.640 --> 19:50:00.340
I resumed a livelier vein of conversation.

19:50:01.500 --> 19:50:07.040
"'It is time some one undertook to rehumanize you,' said I, parting his thick and long uncut

19:50:07.040 --> 19:50:12.920
locks, for I see you are being metamorphosed into a lion, or something of that sort.

19:50:13.280 --> 19:50:17.720
You have a faux air of Nebuchadnezzar in the fields about you.

19:50:17.880 --> 19:50:18.760
That is certain.

19:50:19.200 --> 19:50:21.240
Your hair reminds me of eagle's feathers.

19:50:21.620 --> 19:50:25.260
Whether your nails are grown like bird's claws or not, I have not yet noticed.

19:50:25.1000 --> 19:50:31.740
On this arm I have neither hand nor nails,' he said, drawing the mutilated limb from his

19:50:31.740 --> 19:50:33.880
breast and showing it to me.

19:50:34.240 --> 19:50:36.960
"'It is a mere stump, a ghastly sight.

19:50:37.160 --> 19:50:39.360
Don't you think so, Jane?'

19:50:39.360 --> 19:50:45.080
"'It is a pity to see it, and a pity to see your eyes, and the scar of fire on your forehead,

19:50:45.560 --> 19:50:51.160
and the worst of it is, one is in danger of loving you too well for all this and making

19:50:51.160 --> 19:50:52.800
too much of you.'

19:50:53.320 --> 19:50:59.200
"'I thought you would be revolted, Jane, when you saw my arm and my sickitized vision.'

19:50:59.1000 --> 19:51:00.920
"'Did you?

19:51:01.260 --> 19:51:05.400
Don't tell me so, lest I should say something disparaging to your judgment.

19:51:06.380 --> 19:51:11.300
Now let me leave you an instant to make a better fire and have the hearth swept up.

19:51:11.660 --> 19:51:13.840
Can you tell when there is a good fire?'

19:51:14.960 --> 19:51:18.820
"'Yes, with the right eye I see a glow, a ruddy haze.

19:51:19.120 --> 19:51:20.520
And you see the candles?

19:51:21.260 --> 19:51:23.1000
Very dimly, each is a luminous cloud.

19:51:24.760 --> 19:51:26.120
Can you see me?'

19:51:27.060 --> 19:51:31.280
"'No, my fairy, but I am only too thankful to hear and feel you.

19:51:31.800 --> 19:51:33.640
When do you take supper?'

19:51:33.640 --> 19:51:35.120
"'I never take supper.'

19:51:36.020 --> 19:51:37.800
"'But you shall have some to-night.

19:51:38.020 --> 19:51:38.860
I am hungry.

19:51:39.220 --> 19:51:40.720
So are you, I dare say.

19:51:40.820 --> 19:51:41.1000
Only you forget.'

19:51:42.860 --> 19:51:45.920
"'Summoning Mary, I soon had the room in more cheerful order.

19:51:46.120 --> 19:51:49.240
I prepared him likewise a comfortable repast.

19:51:49.240 --> 19:51:54.540
My spirits were excited, and with pleasure and ease I talked to him during supper and

19:51:54.540 --> 19:51:55.880
for a long time after.

19:51:56.380 --> 19:52:02.480
There was no harassing restraint, no repressing of glee and vivacity with him, for with him

19:52:02.480 --> 19:52:05.820
I was at perfect ease because I knew I suited him.

19:52:06.320 --> 19:52:09.1000
All I said or did seemed either to console or revive him.

19:52:10.920 --> 19:52:12.040
Delightful consciousness!

19:52:12.600 --> 19:52:15.020
It brought to life and light my whole nature.

19:52:15.020 --> 19:52:19.440
In his presence I thoroughly lived, and he lived in mine.

19:52:20.100 --> 19:52:26.400
Blind as he was, smiles played over his face, joy dawned on his forehead, his liniments

19:52:26.400 --> 19:52:27.640
softened and warmed.

19:52:29.080 --> 19:52:35.500
After supper he began to ask me many questions of where I had been, what I had been doing,

19:52:35.880 --> 19:52:40.380
how I had found him out, but I gave him only very partial replies.

19:52:40.820 --> 19:52:43.780
It was too late to enter into particulars that night.

19:52:43.780 --> 19:52:50.300
Besides, I wished to touch no deep thrilling chord, to open no fresh well of emotion in

19:52:50.300 --> 19:52:50.880
his heart.

19:52:51.460 --> 19:52:57.1000
My sole present aim was to cheer him, cheered as I have said he was, and yet but by fits.

19:52:58.840 --> 19:53:04.320
If a moment's silence broke the conversation, he would turn restless, touch me, then say,

19:53:04.700 --> 19:53:05.040
Jane.

19:53:05.960 --> 19:53:09.800
You are altogether a human being, Jane, you are certain of that.

19:53:10.780 --> 19:53:13.340
I conscientiously believe so, Mr. Rochester.

19:53:14.420 --> 19:53:19.560
Yet how on this dark and doleful evening could you so suddenly rise on my lone hearth?

19:53:19.880 --> 19:53:25.060
I stretched my hand to take a glass of water from a hireling, and it was given me by you.

19:53:25.540 --> 19:53:30.920
I asked a question, expecting John's wife to answer me, and your voice spoke at my ear.

19:53:31.800 --> 19:53:39.780
Because I had come in in Mary's stead with the tray, and there is enchantment in the

19:53:39.780 --> 19:53:44.640
Who can tell what a dark, dreary, hopeless life I have dragged on for months past?

19:53:45.320 --> 19:53:51.540
Doing nothing, expecting nothing, merging night and day, feeling but the sensation of

19:53:51.540 --> 19:53:57.180
cold when I let the fire go out, of hunger when I forgot to eat, and then a ceaseless

19:53:57.180 --> 19:54:02.260
sorrow, and at times a very delirium of desire to hold my Jane again.

19:54:02.880 --> 19:54:08.060
Yes, for her restoration I longed, far more than for that of my lost sight.

19:54:08.620 --> 19:54:12.660
How can it be that Jane is with me, and says she loves me?

19:54:13.200 --> 19:54:15.400
Will she not depart as suddenly as she came?

19:54:15.980 --> 19:54:18.440
To-morrow I fear I shall find her no more.

19:54:19.220 --> 19:54:24.780
A commonplace practical reply, out of the train of his own disturbed ideas, was, I was sure,

19:54:25.240 --> 19:54:28.180
the best and most reassuring for him in this frame of mind.

19:54:28.560 --> 19:54:33.080
I passed my finger over his eyebrows, and remarked that they were scorched,

19:54:33.320 --> 19:54:37.580
and that I would apply something which should make them grow as broad and black as ever.

19:54:38.720 --> 19:54:43.100
Where is the use of doing me good in any way, beneficent spirit,

19:54:43.580 --> 19:54:49.260
when at some fatal moment you will again desert me, passing like a shadow, wither and how to

19:54:49.260 --> 19:54:54.100
me unknown, and for me remaining afterwards undiscoverable?

19:54:55.260 --> 19:54:57.340
Have you a pocket-comb about you, sir?

19:54:58.140 --> 19:54:59.420
What for, Jane?

19:55:00.200 --> 19:55:05.920
Just to comb out this shaggy black mane, I find you rather alarming when I examine you close at

19:55:05.920 --> 19:55:11.120
hand. You talk of my being a fairy, but I am sure you are more like a brownie.

19:55:11.720 --> 19:55:13.100
Am I hideous, Jane?

19:55:13.900 --> 19:55:16.400
Very, sir. You always were, you know.

19:55:17.540 --> 19:55:21.640
The wickedness has not yet been taken out of you wherever you have sojourned.

19:55:22.680 --> 19:55:27.900
Yet I have been with good people, far better than you, a hundred times better people,

19:55:28.380 --> 19:55:31.700
possessed of ideas and views you never entertained in your life,

19:55:32.080 --> 19:55:34.180
quite more refined and exalted.

19:55:35.140 --> 19:55:36.900
Who the deuce have you been with?

19:55:37.960 --> 19:55:41.060
If you twist in that way, you will make me pull the hair out of your head,

19:55:41.320 --> 19:55:45.020
and then I think you will cease to entertain doubts of my substantiality.

19:55:45.840 --> 19:55:47.300
Who have you been with, Jane?

19:55:48.020 --> 19:55:53.580
You shall not get it out of me to-night, sir. You must wait till to-morrow. To leave my tale

19:55:53.580 --> 19:55:58.300
half-toed, will, you know, be a sort of security that I shall appear at your breakfast table to

19:55:58.300 --> 19:56:04.040
finish it. By the by, I must mind not to rise on your hearth with only a glass of water, then,

19:56:04.040 --> 19:56:07.980
I must bring an egg at the least, to say nothing of fried ham.

19:56:08.1000 --> 19:56:15.200
You mocking changeling, fairy born in human bread, you make me feel as I have not felt these

19:56:15.200 --> 19:56:21.400
twelve months. If Saul could have had you for his David, the evil spirit would have been exercised

19:56:21.400 --> 19:56:27.720
without the aid of the harp. There, sir, you are read up and made decent. Now I'll leave you.

19:56:27.780 --> 19:56:33.160
I have been travelling these last three days, and I believe I am tired. Good night.

19:56:34.040 --> 19:56:38.540
Just one word, Jane. Were there only ladies in the house where you have been?

19:56:39.040 --> 19:56:43.020
I laughed and made my escape, still laughing as I ran upstairs.

19:56:43.540 --> 19:56:48.180
A good idea, I thought with glee. I see I have the means of fretting him out

19:56:48.180 --> 19:56:53.640
of his melancholy for some time to come. Very early the next morning, I heard him

19:56:53.640 --> 19:56:59.820
up in a stir, wandering from one room to another. As soon as Mary came down, I heard the question,

19:56:59.820 --> 19:57:06.500
Is Miss Eyre here? Then, which room did you put her into? Was it dry? Is she up? Go and ask if

19:57:06.500 --> 19:57:12.960
she wants anything, and when she will come down. I came down as soon as I thought there was a

19:57:12.960 --> 19:57:18.180
prospect of breakfast. Entering the room very softly, I had a view of him before he discovered

19:57:18.180 --> 19:57:24.020
my presence. It was mournful, indeed, to witness the subjugation of that vigorous spirit to a

19:57:24.780 --> 19:57:32.640
infirmity. He sat in his chair, still but not at rest, expectant, evidently, the lines of now

19:57:32.640 --> 19:57:38.720
habitual sadness marking his strong features. His countenance reminded one of a lamp quenched,

19:57:38.940 --> 19:57:44.080
waiting to be relit, and, alas, it was not himself that could now kindle the luster of

19:57:44.080 --> 19:57:50.420
animated expression. He was dependent on another for that office. I had meant to be gay and careless,

19:57:50.420 --> 19:57:54.360
but the powerlessness of the strong man touched my heart to the quick.

19:57:55.160 --> 19:57:58.040
Still, I accosted him with what vivacity I could.

19:57:58.780 --> 19:58:04.660
It is a bright sunny morning, sir, I said. The rain is over and gone, and there is a tender shining

19:58:04.660 --> 19:58:10.560
after it. You shall have a walk soon. I had waken the glow. His features beamed.

19:58:11.380 --> 19:58:18.300
Oh, you are indeed there, my Skylark. Come to me. You are not gone, not vanished. I heard one of

19:58:18.300 --> 19:58:24.920
your kind an hour ago, singing high over the wood, but its song had no music for me, any more than

19:58:24.920 --> 19:58:31.220
the rising sun had rays. All the melody on earth is concentrated in my Jane's tongue to my ear.

19:58:31.680 --> 19:58:37.640
I am glad it is not naturally a silent one. All the sunshine I can feel is in her presence.

19:58:38.380 --> 19:58:44.040
The water stood in my eyes to hear this avowal of his dependence, just as if a royal eagle,

19:58:44.040 --> 19:58:48.360
chained to a perch, should be forced to entreat a sparrow to become its purveyor.

19:58:49.060 --> 19:58:54.580
But I would not be lacrimose. I dashed off the salt drops and busied myself with preparing

19:58:54.580 --> 19:59:00.820
breakfast. Most of the morning was spent in the open air. I led him out of the wet and wild wood

19:59:00.820 --> 19:59:06.340
into some cheerful fields. I described to him how brilliantly green they were, how the flowers and

19:59:06.340 --> 19:59:13.040
hedges looked refreshed, how sparklingly blue was the sky. I sought a seat for him in a hidden and

19:59:13.040 --> 19:59:20.020
lovely spot, a dry stump of a tree, nor did I refuse to let him, when seated, place me on his knee.

19:59:20.520 --> 19:59:23.940
Why should I, when both he and I were happier nearer than apart?

19:59:24.820 --> 19:59:30.580
Pilot lay beside us, all was quiet. He broke out suddenly while clasping me in his arms.

19:59:31.500 --> 19:59:37.700
Cruel, cruel deserter! O Jane, what did I feel when I discovered you had fled from Thornfield,

19:59:37.700 --> 19:59:43.560
and when I could nowhere find you, and, after examining your apartment, ascertained you had

19:59:43.560 --> 19:59:49.680
taken no money, nor anything which could serve as an equivalent? A pearl necklace I had given you lay

19:59:49.680 --> 19:59:54.860
untouched in its little casket. Your trunks were left corded and locked as they had been prepared

19:59:54.860 --> 20:00:00.960
for the bridal tour. What could my darling do, I asked, left destitute and penniless?

20:00:01.440 --> 20:00:04.340
And what did she do? Let me hear now.

20:00:05.600 --> 20:00:11.040
Thus urged, I began the narrative of my experience for the last year. I softened

20:00:11.040 --> 20:00:16.080
considerably what related to the three days of wandering and starvation, because to have told

20:00:16.080 --> 20:00:22.380
him all would have been to inflict unnecessary pain. The little I did say lacerated his faithful

20:00:22.380 --> 20:00:28.940
heart deeper than I wished. I should not have left him thus, he said, without any means of making my

20:00:28.940 --> 20:00:35.280
way. I should have told him my intention. I should have confided in him he would never have forced me

20:00:35.280 --> 20:00:42.380
to be his mistress. Violent as he had seemed in his despair, he, in truth, loved me far too well

20:00:42.380 --> 20:00:47.840
and too tenderly to constitute himself my tyrant. He would have given me half his fortune without

20:00:47.840 --> 20:00:53.420
demanding so much as a kiss in return, rather than I should have flung myself friendless on the wide

20:00:53.420 --> 20:00:58.860
world. I had endured, he was certain, more than I had confessed to him.

20:01:00.080 --> 20:01:05.700
Well, whatever my sufferings had been, they were very short, I answered, and then I proceeded to

20:01:05.700 --> 20:01:10.540
tell him how I had been received at Morehouse, how I had obtained the office of schoolmistress,

20:01:10.760 --> 20:01:17.300
etc. The accession of fortune, the discovery of my relations, followed in due order. Of course,

20:01:17.500 --> 20:01:22.620
St. John River's name came in frequently in the progress of my tale. When I had done, that name

20:01:22.620 --> 20:01:30.640
was immediately taken up. This St. John, then, is your cousin? Yes. You have spoken of him often.

20:01:30.920 --> 20:01:38.360
Did you like him? He was a very good man, sir. I could not help liking him. A good man? Does that

20:01:38.360 --> 20:01:45.240
mean a respectable, well-conducted man of fifty? Or what does it mean? St. John was only twenty-nine,

20:01:45.240 --> 20:01:45.700
sir.

20:01:46.560 --> 20:01:52.480
Jean encore, as the French say. Is he a person of low stature, phlegmatic and plain,

20:01:52.960 --> 20:01:57.980
a person whose goodness consists rather in his guiltlessness of vice than in his prowess and

20:01:57.980 --> 20:02:04.860
virtue? He is untiringly active. Great and exalted deeds are what he lives to perform.

20:02:05.780 --> 20:02:11.740
But his brain, that is probably rather soft, he means well, but you shrug your shoulders to

20:02:11.740 --> 20:02:19.500
hear him talk. He talks little, sir. What he does say is ever to the point. His brain is first rate,

20:02:19.720 --> 20:02:28.320
I should think not impressible, but vigorous. Is he an able man, then? Truly able. A thoroughly

20:02:28.320 --> 20:02:36.240
educated man? St. John is an accomplished and profound scholar. His manners, I think you said,

20:02:36.240 --> 20:02:43.840
not to your taste, priggish and parsonic. I never mentioned his manners, but unless I had a very bad

20:02:43.840 --> 20:02:51.440
taste, they must suit it. They are polished, calm, and gentlemanlike. His appearance, I forget what

20:02:51.440 --> 20:02:56.760
description you gave of his appearance. A sort of raw curate, half strangled with his white neck

20:02:56.760 --> 20:03:04.580
cloth, and stilted up on his thick sole high-lows, eh? St. John dresses well. He is a handsome man,

20:03:04.580 --> 20:03:13.400
tall, fair with blue eyes, and a Grecian profile. A side, damn him, to me. Did you like him, Jane?

20:03:14.400 --> 20:03:21.900
Yes, Mr. Rochester, I liked him. But you asked me that before. I perceived, of course, the drift of

20:03:21.900 --> 20:03:29.440
my interlocutor. Jealousy had got hold of him. She stung him. But the sting was salutary. It gave him

20:03:29.440 --> 20:03:35.100
from the gnawing fang of melancholy. I would not, therefore, immediately charm the snake.

20:03:36.040 --> 20:03:40.640
Perhaps you would rather not sit any longer on my knee, Miss Eyre, was the next somewhat

20:03:40.640 --> 20:03:47.980
unexpected observation. Why not, Mr. Rochester? The picture you have just drawn is suggestive

20:03:47.980 --> 20:03:54.580
of a rather too overwhelming contrast. Your words have delineated very prettily a graceful Apollo.

20:03:54.580 --> 20:04:02.840
He is present to your imagination, tall, fair, blue-eyed, and with a Grecian profile. Your eyes

20:04:02.840 --> 20:04:08.560
dwell on a Vulcan, a real blacksmith, brown, broad-shouldered, and blind and lame into the

20:04:08.560 --> 20:04:14.660
bargain. I never thought of it before. But you certainly are rather like Vulcan, sir.

20:04:15.340 --> 20:04:21.760
Well, you can leave me, ma'am, but before you go. And he retained me by a firmer grasp than ever.

20:04:22.320 --> 20:04:27.460
You will be pleased just to answer me a question or two. He paused.

20:04:28.280 --> 20:04:32.880
What questions, Mr. Rochester? Then followed this cross-examination.

20:04:34.020 --> 20:04:37.620
St. John made you schoolmistress of Morton before he knew you were his cousin?

20:04:38.520 --> 20:04:49.980
Yes. You would often see him? He would visit the school sometimes? Daily. He would approve of your

20:04:49.980 --> 20:04:56.680
creature? He approved of them, yes. He would discover many things in you he could not have

20:04:56.680 --> 20:05:02.980
expected to find. Some of your accomplishments are not ordinary. I don't know about that.

20:05:03.980 --> 20:05:08.780
You had a little cottage near the school, you say. Did he ever come there to see you?

20:05:09.420 --> 20:05:13.640
Now and then. Of an evening? Once or twice.

20:05:14.420 --> 20:05:20.620
A pause. How long did you reside with him and his sisters after the cousinship was discovered?

20:05:21.480 --> 20:05:26.100
Five months. Did Rivers spend much time with the ladies of his family?

20:05:27.140 --> 20:05:32.740
Yes. The back parlor was both his study and ours. He sat near the window, and we by the table.

20:05:33.340 --> 20:05:37.420
Did he study much? A good deal. What?

20:05:38.960 --> 20:05:46.280
Hindostani. And what did you do mean time? I learned German at first. Did he teach you?

20:05:47.100 --> 20:05:55.240
He did not understand German. Did he teach you nothing? A little Hindostani. Rivers taught you

20:05:55.240 --> 20:06:07.100
Hindostani? Yes, sir. And his sisters also? No. Only you? Only me. Did you ask to learn?

20:06:07.680 --> 20:06:17.260
No. He wished to teach you? Yes. A second pause. Why did he wish it? Of what use could Hindostani

20:06:17.260 --> 20:06:25.180
be to you? He intended me to go with him to India. Ah, here I reached the root of the matter. He

20:06:25.180 --> 20:06:32.740
wanted you to marry him. He asked me to marry him. That is a fiction, an impudent invention to vex me.

20:06:33.300 --> 20:06:38.040
I beg your pardon. It is the literal truth. He asked me more than once,

20:06:38.260 --> 20:06:41.820
and was as stiff about urging his point as ever you could be.

20:06:43.840 --> 20:06:50.480
Miss Eyre, I repeat it. You can leave me. How often am I to say the same thing? Why do you remain

20:06:50.480 --> 20:06:56.880
pertinaciously perched on my knee when I have given you notice to quit? Because I am comfortable

20:06:56.880 --> 20:07:02.920
there. No, Jane, you are not comfortable there, because your heart is not with me. It is with

20:07:02.920 --> 20:07:09.620
this cousin, this St. John. Oh, till this moment I thought my little Jane was all mine. I had a

20:07:09.620 --> 20:07:14.700
belief she loved me even when she left me. That was an atom of sweet and much bitter.

20:07:15.300 --> 20:07:21.180
Long as we have been parted, hot tears as I have wept over our separation, I never thought that

20:07:21.180 --> 20:07:29.160
I was mourning her. She was loving another. But it is useless grieving. Jane, leave me. Go and marry

20:07:29.160 --> 20:07:36.620
Rivers. Shake me off then, sir. Push me away, for I'll not leave you of my own accord. Jane,

20:07:36.760 --> 20:07:43.480
I ever like your tone of voice. It still renews hope. It sounds so truthful. When I hear it,

20:07:43.600 --> 20:07:49.960
it carries me back a year. I forget that you have formed a new tie. But I am not a fool. Go.

20:07:50.580 --> 20:07:55.520
Where must I go, sir? Your own way with the husband you have chosen.

20:07:56.460 --> 20:08:03.560
Who is that? You know this St. John Rivers. He is not my husband, nor ever will be.

20:08:03.980 --> 20:08:11.280
He does not love me. I do not love him. He loves as he can love, and that is not as you love.

20:08:11.780 --> 20:08:17.700
A beautiful young lady called Rosamond. He wanted to marry me only because he thought I should make

20:08:17.700 --> 20:08:24.820
a suitable missionary's wife, which she would not have done. He is good and great, but severe,

20:08:25.080 --> 20:08:31.820
and for me cold as an iceberg. He is not like you, sir. I am not happy at his side, nor near him,

20:08:31.860 --> 20:08:38.540
nor with him. He has no indulgence for me, no fondness. He sees nothing attractive in me,

20:08:38.740 --> 20:08:44.940
not even youth, only a few useful mental points. Then I must leave you, sir, to go to him?

20:08:45.580 --> 20:08:49.760
I shuddered involuntarily and clung instinctively closer to my blind,

20:08:50.160 --> 20:08:52.680
but beloved master. He smiled.

20:08:53.660 --> 20:08:58.840
What, Jane? Is this true? Is such really the state of matters between you and Rivers?

20:08:59.740 --> 20:09:05.480
Absolutely, sir. Oh, you need not be jealous. I wanted to tease you a little to make you less

20:09:05.480 --> 20:09:10.420
sad. I thought anger would be better than grief. But if you wished me to love you,

20:09:10.420 --> 20:09:15.040
could you but see how much I do love you, you would be proud and content.

20:09:16.020 --> 20:09:21.060
All my heart is yours, sir. It belongs to you, and with you it would remain,

20:09:21.300 --> 20:09:24.500
were fate to exile the rest of me from your presence for ever.

20:09:25.880 --> 20:09:30.280
Again, as he kissed me, painful thoughts darkened his aspect.

20:09:31.020 --> 20:09:35.240
My seared vision, my crippled strength, he murmured regretfully.

20:09:35.880 --> 20:09:39.900
I caressed in order to soothe him. I knew of what he was thinking,

20:09:40.020 --> 20:09:44.960
and wanted to speak for him, but dared not. As he turned aside his face a minute,

20:09:45.440 --> 20:09:51.800
I saw a tear slide from under the sealed eyelid, and trickle down the manly cheek. My heart swelled.

20:09:52.740 --> 20:09:57.060
I am no better than the old lightning-struck chestnut tree in Thornfield Orchard,

20:09:57.600 --> 20:10:01.420
he remarked ere long. And what right would that ruin have

20:10:01.420 --> 20:10:05.020
to bid a budding woodbine cover its decay with freshness?

20:10:06.240 --> 20:10:12.660
You are no ruin, sir, no lightning-struck tree. You are green and vigorous. Plants will grow

20:10:12.660 --> 20:10:16.880
about your roots whether you ask them or not, because they take delight in your bountiful

20:10:16.880 --> 20:10:21.640
shadow. And as they grow, they will lean towards you, and wind round you,

20:10:21.800 --> 20:10:28.080
because your strength offers them so safe a prop. Again he smiled. I gave him comfort.

20:10:28.880 --> 20:10:32.220
You speak of friends, Jane? He asked.

20:10:32.920 --> 20:10:37.920
Yes, of friends, I answered rather hesitatingly, for I knew I meant more than friends,

20:10:38.140 --> 20:10:41.800
but could not tell what other word to employ. He helped me.

20:10:42.600 --> 20:10:44.940
Ah, Jane, but I want a wife.

20:10:45.760 --> 20:10:46.540
Do you, sir?

20:10:47.520 --> 20:10:49.340
Yes. Is it news to you?

20:10:50.100 --> 20:10:52.620
Of course. You said nothing about it before.

20:10:53.700 --> 20:10:55.220
Is it unwelcome news?

20:10:55.920 --> 20:10:59.820
That depends on circumstances, sir. On your choice.

20:11:00.860 --> 20:11:04.680
Which you shall make for me, Jane. I will abide by your decision.

20:11:06.260 --> 20:11:08.940
Choose, then, sir, her who loves you best.

20:11:10.120 --> 20:11:15.120
I will at least choose her I love best. Jane, will you marry me?

20:11:16.140 --> 20:11:16.940
Yes, sir.

20:11:17.760 --> 20:11:21.660
A poor blind man, whom you will have to lead about by the hand?

20:11:22.460 --> 20:11:23.640
Yes, sir.

20:11:24.320 --> 20:11:28.380
A crippled man, twenty years older than you, whom you will have to wait on?

20:11:29.120 --> 20:11:30.300
Yes, sir.

20:11:31.200 --> 20:11:31.940
Truly, Jane.

20:11:32.800 --> 20:11:34.100
Most truly, sir.

20:11:34.780 --> 20:11:37.740
Oh, my darling, God bless and reward you.

20:11:38.420 --> 20:11:44.080
Mr. Rochester, if ever I did a good deed in my life, if ever I thought a good thought,

20:11:44.480 --> 20:11:50.240
if ever I prayed a sincere and blameless prayer, if ever I wished a righteous wish,

20:11:50.240 --> 20:11:57.660
I am rewarded now. To be your wife is, for me, to be as happy as I can be on earth.

20:11:58.500 --> 20:12:00.520
Because you delight in sacrifice.

20:12:01.980 --> 20:12:07.580
Sacrifice? What do I sacrifice? Famine for food, expectation for content?

20:12:08.140 --> 20:12:13.440
To be privileged to put my arms round what I value, to press my lips to what I love,

20:12:13.440 --> 20:12:20.900
to repose on what I trust, is that to make a sacrifice? If so, then certainly I delight in

20:12:20.900 --> 20:12:26.880
sacrifice. And to bear with my infirmities, Jane, to overlook my deficiencies.

20:12:27.680 --> 20:12:33.400
Which are none, sir, to me. I love you better now, when I can be really useful to you,

20:12:33.420 --> 20:12:38.520
than I did in your state of proud independence, when you disdained every part but that of the

20:12:38.520 --> 20:12:46.540
giver and protector. Hitherto I have hated to be helped, to be led. Henceforth I feel I shall

20:12:46.540 --> 20:12:52.580
hate it no more. I did not like to put my hand into a hireling's, but it is pleasant to feel

20:12:52.580 --> 20:12:58.680
it circled by Jane's little fingers. I preferred utter loneliness to the constant attendance of

20:12:58.680 --> 20:13:06.160
servants. But Jane's soft ministry will be a perpetual joy. Jane suits me. Do I suit her?

20:13:06.960 --> 20:13:14.280
To the finest fiber of my nature, sir. The case being so, we have nothing in the world to wait for.

20:13:14.620 --> 20:13:21.400
We must be married instantly. He looked and spoke with eagerness. His old impetuosity was rising.

20:13:23.380 --> 20:13:28.880
We must become one flesh without any delay, Jane. There is but the license to get. Then we marry.

20:13:29.860 --> 20:13:34.200
Mr. Rochester, I have just discovered the sun has far declined from its meridian,

20:13:34.200 --> 20:13:38.840
and Pilate has actually gone home to his dinner. Let me look at your watch.

20:13:40.020 --> 20:13:44.740
Fasten it into your girdle, Janet, and keep it henceforward. I have no use for it.

20:13:45.380 --> 20:13:49.100
It is nearly four o'clock in the afternoon, sir. Don't you feel hungry?

20:13:49.1000 --> 20:13:55.100
The third day from this must be our wedding day, Jane. Never mind fine clothes and jewels now.

20:13:55.340 --> 20:14:01.320
All that is not worth a filip. The sun has dried up all the raindrops, sir. The breeze is still.

20:14:01.320 --> 20:14:06.620
It is quite hot. Do you know, Jane, I have your little pearl necklace at this moment

20:14:06.620 --> 20:14:12.860
fastened round my bronze scrag under my cravat? I have worn it since the day I lost my only treasure,

20:14:13.200 --> 20:14:18.720
as a memento of her. We will go home through the wood. That will be the shadiest way.

20:14:19.340 --> 20:14:21.820
He pursued his own thoughts without heeding me.

20:14:22.820 --> 20:14:31.300
Jane, you think me, I dare say, an irreligious dog, but my heart swells with gratitude to the

20:14:31.300 --> 20:14:38.140
man. He sees not as man sees, but far clearer. Judges not as man judges, but far more wisely.

20:14:38.840 --> 20:14:45.480
I did wrong. I would have sullied my innocent flower. Breathe guilt on its purity. The

20:14:45.480 --> 20:14:51.1000
omnipotent snatched it from me. I, in my stiff-necked rebellion, almost cursed the dispensation.

20:14:52.660 --> 20:14:58.020
Instead of bending to the decree, I defied it. Divine justice pursued its course.

20:14:58.620 --> 20:15:04.040
Disasters came thick on me. I was forced to pass through the valley of the shadow of death.

20:15:04.960 --> 20:15:11.320
His chastisements are mighty, and one smote me which has humbled me forever. You know I was proud

20:15:11.320 --> 20:15:16.400
of my strength, but what is it now when I must give it over to foreign guidance as a child does

20:15:16.400 --> 20:15:24.900
its weakness? Of late, Jane, only, only of late, I began to see and acknowledge the hand of God in

20:15:24.900 --> 20:15:32.1000
my doom. I began to experience remorse, repentance, the wish for reconcilement to my Maker. I began

20:15:32.1000 --> 20:15:41.400
sometimes to pray. Very brief prayers they were, but very sincere. Some days since—nay, I can

20:15:41.400 --> 20:15:49.100
number them—four. It was last Monday night. A singular mood came over me, one in which grief

20:15:49.100 --> 20:15:55.960
replaced frenzy, sorrow sullenness. I had long had the impression that since I could nowhere

20:15:55.960 --> 20:16:03.500
find you, you must be dead. Late that night, perhaps it might be between eleven and twelve o'clock,

20:16:03.880 --> 20:16:11.560
ere I retired to my dreary rest, I supplicated God that, if it seemed good to him, I might soon

20:16:11.560 --> 20:16:17.400
be taken from this life, and admitted to that world to come, where there was still hope of rejoining

20:16:17.400 --> 20:16:25.340
Jane. I was in my own room, and sitting by the window, which was open, it soothed me to feel the

20:16:25.340 --> 20:16:32.040
balmy night air, though I could see no stars, and only by a vague luminous haze knew the presence

20:16:32.040 --> 20:16:40.280
of a moon. I longed for thee, Janet. Oh, I longed for thee both with soul and flesh. I asked of God

20:16:40.280 --> 20:16:46.420
at once in anguish and humility if I had not been long enough desolate, afflicted, tormented.

20:16:47.200 --> 20:16:54.120
And might not soon taste bliss and peace once more. That I merited all I endured, I acknowledged.

20:16:54.860 --> 20:17:01.060
That I could scarcely endure more, I pleaded, and the alpha and omega of my heart's wishes

20:17:01.060 --> 20:17:10.100
broken voluntarily from my lips in the words, Jane, Jane, Jane. Did you speak these words aloud?

20:17:10.960 --> 20:17:17.900
I did, Jane. If any listener had heard me, he would have thought me mad. I pronounced them with such

20:17:17.900 --> 20:17:25.1000
frantic energy. And it was last Monday night? Somewhere near midnight? Yes, but the time is of

20:17:25.1000 --> 20:17:32.780
no consequence. What followed is the strange point. You will think me superstitious. Some

20:17:32.780 --> 20:17:39.320
superstition I have in my blood, and always had. Nevertheless, this is true. True, at least, it is

20:17:39.320 --> 20:17:47.740
that I heard what I now relate. As I exclaimed, Jane, Jane, Jane, a voice, I cannot tell whence

20:17:47.740 --> 20:17:56.220
the voice came, but I know whose voice it was, replied, I am coming. Wait for me. And a moment

20:17:56.220 --> 20:18:03.720
after went whispering on the wind the words, Where are you? I'll tell you, if I can, the idea,

20:18:03.720 --> 20:18:10.380
the pictures these words open to my mind, yet it is difficult to express what I want to express.

20:18:11.060 --> 20:18:16.660
Verndene is buried, as you see, in a heavy wood where sound falls dull and dies unreverberating.

20:18:17.560 --> 20:18:23.940
Where are you? seemed spoken amongst mountains, for I heard a hill-sun echo repeat the words.

20:18:24.800 --> 20:18:28.140
Cooler and fresher at the moment the gales seemed to visit my brow.

20:18:28.860 --> 20:18:35.280
I could have deemed that in some wild, lone scene I and Jane were meeting. In spirit,

20:18:35.580 --> 20:18:40.900
I believe we must have met. You no doubt were at that hour in unconscious sleep, Jane.

20:18:41.460 --> 20:18:44.460
Perhaps your soul wandered from its cell to comfort mine,

20:18:44.780 --> 20:18:48.240
for those were your accents, as certain as I lived they were yours.

20:18:49.1000 --> 20:18:56.600
Reader, it was on Monday night, near midnight, that I too had received the mysterious summons.

20:18:56.600 --> 20:19:02.920
Those were the very words by which I replied to it. I listened to Mr. Rochester's narrative,

20:19:03.520 --> 20:19:11.100
but made no disclosure in return. The coincidence struck me as too awful and inexplicable to be

20:19:11.100 --> 20:19:17.260
communicated or discussed. If I told anything, my tale would be such as must necessarily make

20:19:17.260 --> 20:19:23.960
a profound impression on the mind of my hearer. And that mind, yet from its sufferings too prone

20:19:23.960 --> 20:19:29.900
to gloom, needed not the deeper shade of the supernatural. I kept these things then,

20:19:30.120 --> 20:19:35.1000
and pondered them in my heart. You cannot now wonder, continued my master,

20:19:36.500 --> 20:19:42.640
that when you rose upon me so unexpectedly last night, I had difficulty in believing you any

20:19:42.640 --> 20:19:47.500
other than a mere voice and vision, something that would melt to silence and annihilation,

20:19:47.500 --> 20:19:52.920
as the midnight whisper and mountain echo had melted before. Now I thank God,

20:19:53.240 --> 20:20:01.640
I knew it to be otherwise. Yes, I thank God. He put me off his knee, rose, and reverently lifting

20:20:01.640 --> 20:20:06.920
his hat from his brow, and bending his sightless eyes to the earth, he stood in mute devotion.

20:20:07.740 --> 20:20:13.800
Only the last words of the worship were audible. I thank my Maker, that in the midst of judgment

20:20:14.440 --> 20:20:20.620
he has remembered mercy. I humbly entreat my Redeemer to give me strength to lead henceforth

20:20:20.620 --> 20:20:27.480
a purer life than I have done hitherto. Then he stretched his hand out to be led. I took

20:20:27.480 --> 20:20:33.500
that dear hand, held it a moment to my lips, then let it pass round my shoulder. Being so much

20:20:33.500 --> 20:20:39.700
lower of stature than he, I served both for his prop and guide. We entered the wood and wended

20:20:39.700 --> 20:20:43.540
homeward.

20:21:07.240 --> 20:21:08.840
CHAPTER XXXVIII.

20:21:09.240 --> 20:21:10.300
I married him.

20:21:10.300 --> 20:21:15.460
A quiet wedding we had, he and I, the parson and clerk, were alone present.

20:21:15.980 --> 20:21:20.240
When we got back from church, I went into the kitchen of the manor house, where Mary

20:21:20.240 --> 20:21:24.300
was cooking the dinner, and John cleaning the knives, and I said,

20:21:25.000 --> 20:21:28.000
Mary, I have been married to Mr. Rochester this morning.

20:21:28.760 --> 20:21:33.140
The housekeeper and her husband were both of that decent phlegmatic order of people,

20:21:33.520 --> 20:21:39.240
to whom one may at any time safely communicate a remarkable piece of news without incurring

20:21:39.240 --> 20:21:44.380
the danger of having one's ears pierced by some shrill ejaculation, and subsequently

20:21:44.380 --> 20:21:46.640
stunned by a torrent of wordy wonderment.

20:21:47.280 --> 20:21:50.540
Mary did look up, and she did stare at me.

20:21:50.760 --> 20:21:55.360
The ladle with which she was basting a pair of chickens roasting at the fire did for some

20:21:55.360 --> 20:22:00.940
three minutes hang suspended in the air, and for the same space of time John's knives also

20:22:00.940 --> 20:22:02.960
had a rest from the polishing process.

20:22:03.520 --> 20:22:06.580
But Mary, bending again over the roast, said only,

20:22:07.080 --> 20:22:09.420
Have you, Miss? Well, for sure.

20:22:10.260 --> 20:22:11.920
A short time after she pursued,

20:22:12.780 --> 20:22:17.800
I see to go out with the master, but I didn't know you were going to church to be wed, and

20:22:17.800 --> 20:22:18.780
she basted away.

20:22:19.680 --> 20:22:22.660
John, when I turned to him, was grinning from ear to ear.

20:22:23.360 --> 20:22:25.940
I told Mary how it would be, he said.

20:22:26.420 --> 20:22:31.680
I knew what Mr. Edward—John was an old servant, and had known his master when he was the cadet

20:22:31.680 --> 20:22:34.800
of the house, therefore he often gave him his Christian name.

20:22:35.380 --> 20:22:40.540
I knew what Mr. Edward would do, and I was certain he would not wait long neither, and

20:22:40.540 --> 20:22:42.340
he's done right, for aught I know.

20:22:42.660 --> 20:22:43.940
I wish you joy, Miss.

20:22:44.140 --> 20:22:46.040
And he politely pulled his forelock.

20:22:47.040 --> 20:22:47.960
Thank you, John.

20:22:48.260 --> 20:22:51.320
Mr. Rochester told me to give you and Mary this.

20:22:51.860 --> 20:22:53.960
I put into his hand a five-pound note.

20:22:54.680 --> 20:22:59.460
Without waiting to hear more, I left the kitchen, and passing the door of that sanctum some

20:22:59.460 --> 20:23:01.180
time after, I caught the words,

20:23:01.980 --> 20:23:05.160
She'll happen do better for him, nor any at the grand ladies.

20:23:05.700 --> 20:23:11.820
And again, if she beant one of the handsomest, she's known foul and very good-natured, and

20:23:11.820 --> 20:23:15.580
in his eye she's fair beautiful, any body may see that.

20:23:16.360 --> 20:23:22.300
I wrote to Morehouse, and to Cambridge immediately, to say what I had done, fully explaining also

20:23:22.300 --> 20:23:23.700
why I had thus acted.

20:23:24.320 --> 20:23:26.900
Diana and Mary approved this step unreservedly.

20:23:26.900 --> 20:23:31.400
Diana announced that she would just give me time to get over the honeymoon, and then she

20:23:31.400 --> 20:23:32.380
would come and see me.

20:23:32.940 --> 20:23:38.300
She had better not wait till then, Jane, said Mr. Rochester, when I read her letter to him.

20:23:38.680 --> 20:23:43.100
If she does, she will be too late, for our honeymoon will shine our life long.

20:23:43.760 --> 20:23:46.640
Its beams will only fade over your grave or mine.

20:23:47.620 --> 20:23:50.140
How St. John received the news, I don't know.

20:23:50.620 --> 20:23:56.080
He never answered the letter in which I communicated it, yet six months after he wrote to me.

20:23:56.080 --> 20:24:00.700
Without, however, mentioning Mr. Rochester's name, or alluding to my marriage.

20:24:01.440 --> 20:24:05.600
His letter was then calm, and, though very serious, kind.

20:24:06.200 --> 20:24:10.320
He has maintained a regular, though not frequent, correspondence ever since.

20:24:11.080 --> 20:24:15.640
He hopes I am happy, and trusts I am not one of those who live without God in the world,

20:24:15.960 --> 20:24:17.660
and only mind earthly things.

20:24:18.420 --> 20:24:21.300
You have not quite forgotten little Adele, have you, reader?

20:24:21.880 --> 20:24:22.840
I had not.

20:24:22.840 --> 20:24:28.660
I soon asked, and obtained leave of Mr. Rochester, to go and see her at the school where he had

20:24:28.660 --> 20:24:29.300
placed her.

20:24:29.720 --> 20:24:32.640
Her frantic joy at beholding me again moved me much.

20:24:33.120 --> 20:24:34.720
She looked pale and thin.

20:24:34.940 --> 20:24:36.360
She said she was not happy.

20:24:36.920 --> 20:24:41.480
I found the rules of the establishment were too strict, its course of study too severe

20:24:41.480 --> 20:24:42.840
for a child of her age.

20:24:43.340 --> 20:24:45.000
I took her home with me.

20:24:45.280 --> 20:24:49.740
I meant to become her governess once more, but I soon found this impracticable.

20:24:50.260 --> 20:24:53.140
My time and cares were now required by another.

20:24:53.540 --> 20:24:55.060
My husband needed them all.

20:24:55.820 --> 20:25:00.860
So I sought out a school conducted on a more indulgent system, and near enough to permit

20:25:00.860 --> 20:25:04.240
of my visiting her often, and bringing her home sometimes.

20:25:05.000 --> 20:25:08.740
I took care she should never want for anything that could contribute to her comfort.

20:25:09.280 --> 20:25:13.980
She soon settled in her new abode, became very happy there, and made fair progress in

20:25:13.980 --> 20:25:14.580
her studies.

20:25:15.120 --> 20:25:20.920
As she grew up a sound English education corrected in a great measure her French defects, and

20:25:20.920 --> 20:25:26.860
when she left school I found in her a pleasing and obliging companion, docile, good-tempered,

20:25:26.940 --> 20:25:27.920
and well principled.

20:25:28.500 --> 20:25:33.860
By her grateful attention to me and mine she has long since well repaid any little kindness

20:25:33.860 --> 20:25:36.080
I ever had it in my power to offer her.

20:25:36.940 --> 20:25:38.980
My tale draws to its close.

20:25:39.520 --> 20:25:44.140
One word respecting my experience of married life, and one brief glance at the fortunes

20:25:44.140 --> 20:25:48.780
of those whose names have most frequently recurred in this narrative, and I have done.

20:25:49.640 --> 20:25:51.560
I have now been married ten years.

20:25:52.140 --> 20:25:57.040
I know what it is to live entirely for and with what I love best on earth.

20:25:57.520 --> 20:26:03.700
I hold myself supremely blessed, blessed beyond what language can express, because I am my

20:26:03.700 --> 20:26:06.000
husband's life as fully as he is mine.

20:26:06.680 --> 20:26:12.200
No woman was ever nearer to her mate than I am, ever more absolutely bone of his bone

20:26:12.200 --> 20:26:13.660
and flesh of his flesh.

20:26:14.200 --> 20:26:17.020
I know no weariness of my Edward society.

20:26:17.560 --> 20:26:22.400
He knows none of mine, any more than we each do of the pulsation of the heart that beats

20:26:22.400 --> 20:26:23.580
in our separate bosoms.

20:26:24.340 --> 20:26:26.320
Consequently, we are ever together.

20:26:27.020 --> 20:26:32.820
To be together is for us to be at once as free as in solitude, as gay as in company.

20:26:33.480 --> 20:26:35.640
We talk, I believe, all day long.

20:26:35.960 --> 20:26:39.800
To talk to each other is but a more animated and an audible thinking.

20:26:40.460 --> 20:26:42.680
All my confidence is bestowed on him.

20:26:42.940 --> 20:26:45.060
All his confidence is devoted to me.

20:26:45.520 --> 20:26:47.700
We are precisely suited in character.

20:26:48.300 --> 20:26:50.080
Perfect concord is the result.

20:26:51.200 --> 20:26:54.820
Mr. Rochester continued blind for the first two years of our union.

20:26:55.500 --> 20:27:01.020
Perhaps it was that circumstance that drew us so very near, that knit us so very close,

20:27:01.520 --> 20:27:05.000
for I was then his vision, as I am still his right hand.

20:27:05.780 --> 20:27:09.800
Literally, I was what he often called me the apple of his eye.

20:27:10.240 --> 20:27:16.120
He saw nature, he saw books through me, and never did I weary of gazing for his behalf

20:27:16.120 --> 20:27:23.500
and of putting into words the effect of field, tree, town, river, cloud, sunbeam, of the

20:27:23.500 --> 20:27:29.100
landscape before us, of the weather around us, and impressing by sound on his ear what

20:27:29.100 --> 20:27:31.260
light could no longer stamp on his eye.

20:27:31.780 --> 20:27:33.900
Never did I weary of reading to him.

20:27:34.460 --> 20:27:38.980
Never did I weary of conducting him where he wished to go, of doing for him what he

20:27:38.980 --> 20:27:39.880
wished to be done.

20:27:40.580 --> 20:27:47.120
And there was a pleasure in my services, most full, most exquisite, even though sad, because

20:27:47.120 --> 20:27:50.720
he claimed these services without painful shame or damping humiliation.

20:27:51.440 --> 20:27:56.160
He loved me so truly that he knew no reluctance in profiting by my attendance.

20:27:56.620 --> 20:28:02.460
He felt that I loved him so fondly that to yield that attendance was to indulge my sweetest

20:28:02.460 --> 20:28:02.880
wishes.

20:28:03.680 --> 20:28:08.780
One morning at the end of the two years, as I was writing a letter to his dictation, he

20:28:08.780 --> 20:28:10.540
came and bent over me and said,

20:28:11.480 --> 20:28:14.480
Jane, have you a glittering ornament round your neck?

20:28:14.940 --> 20:28:16.680
I had a gold watch chain.

20:28:16.900 --> 20:28:18.340
I answered, yes.

20:28:19.320 --> 20:28:21.460
And have you a pale blue dress on?

20:28:22.120 --> 20:28:22.860
I had.

20:28:23.440 --> 20:28:28.240
He informed me then that for some time he had fancied the obscurity clouding one eye

20:28:28.240 --> 20:28:31.860
was becoming less dense, and that now he was sure of it.

20:28:32.740 --> 20:28:34.140
He and I went up to London.

20:28:34.800 --> 20:28:39.380
He had the advice of an eminent oculist, and he eventually recovered the sight of that

20:28:39.380 --> 20:28:39.920
one eye.

20:28:40.480 --> 20:28:42.800
He cannot now see very distinctly.

20:28:43.000 --> 20:28:48.020
He cannot read or write much, but he can find his way without being led by the hand.

20:28:48.560 --> 20:28:52.560
The sky is no longer a blank to him, the earth no longer a void.

20:28:53.360 --> 20:28:58.420
When his firstborn was put into his arms, he could see that the boy had inherited his

20:28:58.420 --> 20:29:02.340
own eyes as they once were, large, brilliant, and black.

20:29:02.900 --> 20:29:07.980
On that occasion, he again, with a full heart, acknowledged that God had tempered judgment

20:29:07.980 --> 20:29:08.760
with mercy.

20:29:10.080 --> 20:29:16.140
My Edward and I then are happy, and the more so because those we most love are happy likewise.

20:29:17.040 --> 20:29:19.080
Diana and Mary Rivers are both married.

20:29:20.020 --> 20:29:24.180
Alternately, once every year, they come to see us, and we go to see them.

20:29:24.900 --> 20:29:29.500
Diana's husband is a captain in the Navy, a gallant officer and a good man.

20:29:30.140 --> 20:29:35.060
Mary's is a clergyman, a college friend of her brother's, and from his attainments and

20:29:35.060 --> 20:29:36.820
principles worthy of the connection.

20:29:37.640 --> 20:29:42.080
Both Captain Fitzjames and Mr. Wharton love their wives and are loved by them.

20:29:43.020 --> 20:29:45.560
As to St. John Rivers, he left England.

20:29:45.840 --> 20:29:46.820
He went to India.

20:29:47.300 --> 20:29:49.980
He entered on the path he had marked for himself.

20:29:50.140 --> 20:29:51.360
He pursues it still.

20:29:52.140 --> 20:29:57.820
A more resolute, indefatigable pioneer never wrought amidst rocks and dangers.

20:29:58.620 --> 20:30:05.860
Firm, faithful, and devoted, full of energy, and zeal, and truth, he labors for his race.

20:30:06.460 --> 20:30:08.800
He clears their painful way to improvement.

20:30:09.340 --> 20:30:14.380
He hews down, like a giant, the prejudices of creed and caste that encumber it.

20:30:14.780 --> 20:30:16.000
He may be stern.

20:30:16.580 --> 20:30:18.040
He may be exacting.

20:30:18.560 --> 20:30:24.160
He may be ambitious yet, but his is the sternness of the warrior Great Heart, who guards his

20:30:24.160 --> 20:30:26.760
pilgrim convoy from the onslaught of Apollyon.

20:30:27.220 --> 20:30:33.740
His is the exaction of the apostle, who speaks but for Christ, when he says, Whosoever will

20:30:33.740 --> 20:30:37.980
come after me, let him deny himself and take up his cross and follow me.

20:30:38.780 --> 20:30:44.200
His is the ambition of the high Master Spirit, which aims to fill a place in the first rank

20:30:44.200 --> 20:30:48.780
of those who are redeemed from the earth, who stand without fault before the throne

20:30:48.780 --> 20:30:55.660
of God, who share the last mighty victories of the Lamb, who are called, and chosen, and

20:30:55.660 --> 20:30:56.080
faithful.

20:30:57.320 --> 20:30:58.780
St. John is unmarried.

20:30:59.080 --> 20:31:00.560
He never will marry now.

20:31:01.300 --> 20:31:06.000
Himself has hitherto sufficed to the toil, and the toil draws near its close.

20:31:06.660 --> 20:31:09.120
His glorious son hastens to its setting.

20:31:09.700 --> 20:31:15.420
The last letter I received from him drew from my eyes human tears, and yet filled my heart

20:31:15.420 --> 20:31:16.480
with divine joy.

20:31:17.200 --> 20:31:21.440
He anticipated his sure reward, his incorruptible crown.

20:31:22.020 --> 20:31:26.980
I know that a stranger's hand will write to me next, to say that the good and faithful

20:31:26.980 --> 20:31:30.500
servant has been called at length into the joy of his Lord.

20:31:30.960 --> 20:31:32.540
And why weep for this?

20:31:33.080 --> 20:31:36.000
No fear of death will darken St. John's last hour.

20:31:36.420 --> 20:31:38.120
His mind will be unclouded.

20:31:38.120 --> 20:31:39.860
His heart will be undaunted.

20:31:40.520 --> 20:31:41.720
His hope will be sure.

20:31:41.980 --> 20:31:43.500
His faith steadfast.

20:31:44.080 --> 20:31:46.060
His own words are a pledge of this.

20:31:46.940 --> 20:31:50.120
My master, he says, has forewarned me.

20:31:50.640 --> 20:31:52.800
Daily he announces more distinctly.

20:31:53.280 --> 20:31:57.000
Surely I come quickly, and hourly I more eagerly respond.

20:31:57.700 --> 20:31:58.140
Amen.

20:31:58.380 --> 20:32:00.360
Even so come, Lord Jesus.
